properties.content: On my walk today, I (we) see a "seagull" hovering, a little off the path, up in the air above me. I am surprised that it is quite large and has quite stiff, straight wings. Then it tilts a little, and I think the wings look a bit like solar panels, but completely white. I cannot see what is in the middle, between the "wings". It floats silently and then glides sideways calmly on towards Ørting. The flight height is slightly higher than the trees in the area. What have I (we) seen?

One summer morning in 1975 or 1976, my father and I were driving from our home. He had to go to work, and I had to be dropped off at the school bus where Vesterskovvej meets Skamlingvej. Therefore, the time must have been between 7.30 and 8.00. The sun had risen, it was windless with a few high-lying clouds. The object remained - completely without moving - in front of us for 3-5 minutes. I later talked to my father about how we had the feeling that "it" was as aware of our existence as the other way around. We didn't talk or move (unless it was their freezing rays that paralyzed us :-)) while the observation was taking place. After this period, the object flew away in a long circular arc to the southeast, towards Sdr. Bjert strand/Skamlingsbanken. It was a long and steady acceleration, and when the object disappeared from view it was perhaps 10 kilometers away. At the time, it was moving far faster than any jet plane. So there are many reasons not to review this after so many years; the ufo completely sticks to a design from a sci-fi film from the 50s, and I was, as it appears from personal data, 7 or 8 years old, when you have a considerable power of imagination. If I had seen it alone, I would surely have repressed the memory as fantasy. But now there were two of us who saw it and could confirm each other. And the weather was amazingly clear and the observation lasted a long time. And it is probably quite far out in the country, but it was a little after 8 o'clock, and there must have been many people up and on their way to work who may have seen something. The experience was fantastic, and it is actually mostly a fond memory, but it would add another dimension if others had also experienced something... So if you have time, as I said, it would be exciting. I'm sorry I can't give you the exact date, but we lived in the area until I started 3rd grade and that's the closest I can get - my mom doesn't remember either. I remember the minutes themselves vividly. I have sent you a Google Earth map pin of the place we got out of the car.

I just experienced a flyover that I cannot relate to anything man-made. I was sitting on my balcony and at minute 21.31 I see a silent object fly over Midtfyn. It only takes me a few seconds to grab the phone and get the camera ready. I have 5 photos taken with a mobile phone that I have not seen the quality of yet, as I would rather share this message with you. At the same time I notice an airplane, but from the sound it has an east-northeast direction. The object, as I experience it, does not deviate many degrees from north. The object is oval/egg-shaped, and moves at a speed I have not seen the like of, unless a private propeller plane has been 200 mtrs. up, or the defense's F-16, in a direct line max. has been 1000 mtr. away.

4 large star-shaped lights on a downward sloping line, invited distance 5-10 m, total width 15-20 m. "Lights" linearly with the top first, followed by the next ones in order. "Extinguishes" in the same order. The phenomenon is repeated immediately, but now in the opposite order in an upward oblique direction - a bit like an entry angle/exit angle. 8 minutes later the phenomenon is observed again, but approx. 6 km further south-east on Toftlundvej - again south/south-west

It has now been many years, but it is an experience I will never forget. We were 5 friends who were going to a prom in Jelling. We had agreed to meet at one of them for a beer before we left. We meet at the friend's place approx. 8 p.m. I didn't have any beer with me, so a classmate and I agreed to go down to the Statoil tank, which is located at the intersection. The house where we were is located next to the local sports field, and therefore we just wanted to slip over it to take a shortcut. When we were halfway across the football field, I spotted something strange in the sky. Directly above our heads was a silver oval shaped object. It was darkened, but there was glare from street lights or the like. I stopped and asked my companion what it was. We quickly agreed that it wasn't a plane or anything like that. The object was silent. After observing the object for approx. 5 minutes we went on. After walking a few meters we became aware that the object was moving in the same direction as we were walking. We stopped again, as did the object. We looked for a min. or two. After the object has moved, I will shoot the distance to approx. 200-800 meters. We had now become so insecure about the situation that we set off and went down and bought our beer. When we had done our shopping, we went back the same way. We looked up at the sky again, but now the object was gone. We continued back to the other comrades and told the story. It has been many years, but it has left its mark.

A light that looks like a trailing light appears on the horizon in the west - below the cloud cover - and disappears to the east - apparently up through the cloud cover at approx. 160 degrees - or burn out. I can't decide that. I saw it 3 times in the period 23.40 - 00.20. I estimate the speed of the objects at 5-600 km/h, although I have no prerequisites for this, other than observing ordinary planes and helicopters.

I saw three objects with green - yellow - orange light flying, seen with my eyes approx. 8 km. from the observation point. If it had been a plane, the sound from these would have been clear. I live high up, and at this time of the day it is completely quiet. The three objects flew at a distance seen as the crow flies of approx. 1000 meters, respectively calmly or at a moderate speed across the sky, after which it appeared as if they fell towards the ground and then rose to a level that was higher than the first observed, they were not followed in parallel, as one suddenly rose and disappeared east over. The others followed a parallel line and also disappeared to the east. I can't see them further than about 100 meters to the east, as our roof covers the further view. I have been in the Air Force, and have never in my time seen anything that could be mistaken for what I saw. They could not be mistaken for a plane/helicopter or other flying object that I know of. I emphasize once again absolutely no sound. I am not superstitious, do not believe in other beings, but with what I have observed today, I have changed my mind.

A red light that pulsated to almost white with a steady 5-10 second cycle hovered over the sea for approx. 100 m height (we stood at about 40 m height) and saw the light above the horizon). The speed was steady, but too fast to be a blowing balloon. It was almost windless. There was no sound. The light disappeared behind a mountain forest after a minute. Immediately afterwards we spotted another red-white pulsating light moving along the coast. At once I took it for a red lantern on a speeding boat, but then the light rose into the air until it was at the same height as the first and disappeared in the same direction. After a few minutes, similar pulsating lights were seen at the same height, but now in the opposite direction and many kilometers away on their way away. We lost sight of it as it got further away. Spoke the next day with the military ship observers on Røsnæs lighthouse, but they had not been on duty. There were no official flights in the logbook. My best "non-alien" guess is that it could have been some small multi-rotor electric helicopters. However, this type hardly has such a long flight time, so the owner must have lost them when we went home after an hour's wait. Not likely that anyone would sacrifice two such precious toys like that. Seems to fall into the same category as what many others have observed in recent months.

My little brother remembers nothing as he was only two or three years old at this time. We have often thought and talked about what it could be, when we first thought it was a shot, but when we looked more closely at the video, we could see that it changed direction. The speed it comes in, we can't even make it fit with an insect or other animal.

Approx. at At 2.40 I got out of the car in front of the north side of the house and noticed a bright shining light in the sky to the south. It moved eastward, coming from the west. The light was bright white and sharp and moved in a straight line. When the light disappeared behind the house roof, I ran in for binoculars and further around behind the house on the south side to continue the observation. The object's direction had then changed to southeast. I climbed a ladder by our garden shed to get an unobstructed view and observed the object through binoculars until it disappeared behind the trees on the hills on the horizon. In the binoculars I could see a clear layering in the colors that the object now emitted. Green at the top, yellow in the middle and red at the bottom. The top, or top, was rounded in shape, the underside more uneven with what looked like two bulges sticking out below. When I went back inside it was 2:46 am.

I come outside to go for a walk when I see a red light in the sky. It got my attention because it wasn't flashing like they usually do, and it was louder than usual, but it was high up, and there was no sound from it, but it wasn't something that I considered unexplainable, just a little weird. So I got into my car and drove out of the area I live in, but I didn't get more than 800m down the road when another red light appeared. This time there were two very powerful red lights. They flew very close and they were closer to the ground. I got out of my car and took a picture of my sighting. Again there was no sound. At first I thought hot air balloons, but they were too fast. They came into view in the north and flew in a straight line to the south. At first it looked like one was flying in a straight line behind the other When they had flown some distance past me it looked like the rear red light was flying up the side of the other. I have no logical explanation as to what it was I saw. I have ruled out helicopters, airliners, hot air balloons and laser lights. I'll bet they were moving at a speed of 200 km per hour. I hope there are others who can confirm my story, or there is a reasonable explanation.

Standing and smoking a cigarette in peace and quiet outside our house, when suddenly a red/yellow, big round thing came, without sound and moving slowly and like a jellyfish in the air. The color was strong in the center and blurred around. Called my wife and son, who managed to see it further north, where it eventually disappeared. A very strange experience I have never seen before.

The object caught my attention out of the corners of my eyes like a bird flying past the window. I waited for a sunny day to use the new solar filter for my telescope. Therefore, I was probably paying more attention to the sky than I usually am. My first thought was airplanes, but there were no wings and there were no rotor blades or other aerodynamic details to be seen. The object was a round silhouette against the sky. No sounds could be heard from rotor blades and a helicopter is not round. The object moves with approx. 500 km/h a gliding motion, stops without deceleration, continues in the same direction again without normal acceleration, stops abruptly again, stands still for a moment, and is suddenly no longer visible. I have thought a lot about cognitive processes that could have caused an illusion, but must conclude that it was a large, round object, which could be seen as a silhouette, which moved in a way that no aircraft known to me can move on.

We are sitting in the yard and have just finished putting in the last load of hay. It is windless and the sky is completely cloudless. It is completely quiet and peaceful. Suddenly I notice some light and look up at the sky. I see a "star" there. It cuts one in the eyes. I look at it for a few seconds, while thinking that it was suddenly that a "star" had appeared, and wasn't it a little bigger than usual. It almost shone, as in a Christmas fairy tale. Suddenly it becomes smaller and smaller, where after it had completely disappeared. It seemed to fly higher and higher.

Sat on the sofa with a full view to the west through a large glass wall towards the terrace/garden in the dark cottage area. Plus a bright red oblong light came into view, thought it might be a helicopter crash outside and saw 4 more objects of the same kind, apparently at the same distance from each other. High in the sky, and completely silent. Only now found out that you can report sightings. Reported the experience immediately per mail to my daughter. Didn't manage to take a photo.

Looking up towards the northeast, as I often do, and see a UFO closed up at the bottom with bright light. As it begins to close, it begins to move. Since it is closed, the view goes strongly to the east.

I saw something last night at approx. midnight, which at first resembled a star that shone very brightly. After some time it started to "fade away", i.e. the light disappeared. After 5-10 seconds the light came back and it looked like it was closer than the other stars and it looked like it was moving from left to right. This happened for about 5 minutes until it "turned off" and disappeared, then it stayed on for a few minutes, but the light did not come back on. Am very curious about what I may have seen, also have a movie where you can see the light disappear.

Luminous flash starting from the south and disappeared North-North-EAST. I would count on at least 20 starts - relatively fast. Photos and Video recorded on iPhone. - but far away. The phenomenon stopped after a plane (3 white lights and flashing red light) flew over the place from west to east.

I had a very funny experience last night. I was out walking last night. Everything was normal except that there was a bright light and sharp spot in the sky. It was so sharp that my eyes couldn't focus on it, including flickering. I compared it to the Moon and the stars around it, and it was significantly larger than the stars and slightly brighter in light than the Moon. I saw it to the north, where it was visible for 5 minutes, after which it disappeared. I walked a little further, but looked up again to see if it had come again. It was, but this time it had moved 10-15 degrees further west, was visible for another 5 min and then disappeared completely.

Unusually loud sound, like a rocket flying across the roof. Very sudden appearance, and very quickly gone again. When attempting visual observation, there was nothing to see. ftk.dk has responded negatively to the incident in the area. Sound also observed by an acquaintance in the area - but no visual sight obtained here either.

We saw two pulsating red-yellow lights, one much larger than the other. They moved south, gradually became smaller and then disappeared out of nowhere. Approx. 15 minutes before we had seen another ball of light moving across the sky in another place in the Northwest quarter.

It all started one evening when we were sitting and playing cards. Approx. at 01.30 we see a bright glowing ball in the sky that is moving... We run out onto the terrace, but it is completely silent.. It/it moves quite fast, the light is the same whether you see it/it from the front or from the back... There are also no flashes or anything that resembles a normal plane... Now we have observed this for 14 days, talked to Naviair, who can say with 100% certainty that it is not a plane. .. there have been times when it/it has emitted a very strong light.. We don't believe it's a satellite, it's simply too big.... A satellite is probably, seen from here, the size of the tip on a needle, whereas this one is the size of a very large star…

4 luminous white oblong things fly from west to east, in a playfully gliding but fast movement. They fly in a united flock, there is very clear light in them, nothing flashing. Silent and calm gliding movement across the night sky, but below star height, i.e. approx. 45 degrees.
White very early light with changing speed, appeared to be small light tail behind.

This afternoon at 16:49 I saw a phenomenon I have never seen before. A small green glowing ball flew across the sky above Varde from northeast to southwest. It split into 4-5 smaller green balls and it all disappeared. It was lightning fast, I managed to get up, but not to grab the camera. At first I thought it was fireworks, but it wasn't. It was very special. On reflection - it was flying straight towards the setting sun.

I go out into our hallway to lock our door before we go to bed. Then I see that our neighbor is looking out of their terrace door, and I wonder what they are looking at.. I go upstairs, into the bedroom, look out the window and immediately spot 3 figures. balls of light. They sort of appeared over from the forest, and sort of had to find a height to take off at. They flew past our house/window. We had the window fully open, but it was completely quiet. No sound at all. After that there were again 2 equals. balls of light with the same speed, etc. I tried to spot them in the binoculars, a little difficult because of the darkness and its speed. I could see from the one that the equation. a half circle, and there was light all around it. Yes, it was very strange. Had actually seen 3 equals. 14 days ago one evening we had guests. They came from the same place/direction. We actually just sat there and joked that yes, it could look like a UFO.

Large square hovered silently above me, moving down over Fredericia's inner city. At first think it's a parachute, but there's nothing under it. It is dark and windless, but the object is completely silent, size is difficult to say, 2 m wide and 6 m long.

At 23.45 east north east ufo with 6-8 white lights in a circle around the object. What I saw was a powerful star that seemed somewhat fluid. Then through binoculars (7x50) it came out looking like 4 to 8 white lights. It looked like it was rotating to the east, so there was only approx. 4 white lights, after which it turned back.

I'm standing outside in front of my house around 04:45 looking up at the stars while smoking a cigarette. I alternately look from one side of the sky to the other. When I turn my head to the right again, a yellow/orange intensely glowing orb has appeared since I last looked, which had been approx. 1 minute ago. Suddenly it's there. Highly visible and in motion. It flies across the sky for approx. 2 minutes until it disappears.

Was on my way to drop my brother off when I see 4 orange-red small balls ahead. I comment on this and we all get out of the car a little surprised. They move on the same course and then disappear into the clouds. Then there will be 2 more. Same course and same disappearance. Maybe brother got a useful picture of some of it - He tried to take pictures, but I won't know until tomorrow if there is any result. Just as I put the car into parking, a police car was dispatched. A little later another police call and a fire truck came, I think. I just want to interject that I am a SKEPTIC! - I don't believe in life in outer space etc, but I don't know what we saw? I can find the same place and photograph it and then draw the route into the picture if needed.

Object observed on 08-03-2023 at 14.10 in the afternoon in Ry by. Observation was taken from the road "Ellemosen", where the object was heading towards "Knudsø" towards the town of Tulstrup. The object flew behind the Ry halls and disappeared. I saw a metallic spherical round object "UFO" flying relatively slowly across the sky at low altitude in a northerly direction. I would assess the object to have been max. 100 meters high in the air and headed towards a small white cloud. The object disappeared from view, flying below the cloud and then out of my field of vision. I am not sure about the size of the object, but a guess would be 1 meter in diameter. The sky was blue with a few small white clouds in the background. The sun's rays reflected in the object as if it were made of polished chrome. I tried to take pictures with my phone of the object, but unfortunately the object was already out of my field of vision. I also tried to record a video, but to my great chagrin, I later found out that I had not pressed the record button correctly, but since the object cannot be seen in the 2 pictures that I had already taken, there probably wouldn't have been anything to see on the video clip anyway, if it had come to anything! This is the second time in my life that I can report a UFO sighting that I have witnessed.

properties.Remarks: Forklaring: Bryllup på Havartigården i Holte!  Balloner med hjerter!se beretning

properties.content: I was alone in my friend's apartment on the 15th floor in Rebæk Søpark and sat on the sofa and looked in the direction of the window. The door to the balcony was open. Suddenly I hear a strange sound and look out. Up in the sky you see a black "thing" moving in a circle and rising towards the sky at high speed. The sun shines directly in my eyes, so I can't see it very clearly. I rush to find my sunglasses and turn on my iPhone to record the strange thing in the sky. By the time I do that, the "thing" has already moved far away from me. But, anyway, I recorded what I could and would love to send that recording to you. Maybe I just saw a black bag in the sky, but it was very strange to look at, it was making noise and moving right up above the sun.

I was out walking the dog. Suddenly there is an orange orb shaped light across the sky, fairly quickly, but I manage to get home and get my husband out to see it (he absolutely does not believe in UFOs). He can't explain what it is. We see it disappear, the light slowly going out as the distance lengthens. We turn and want to go inside. We then see two more in the same direction turning off just above our heads, very close we thought. I see through the binoculars that one's light goes out, but I can see its silhouette, still round and larger than the light, the other continues, but the one that is off and goes down behind some trees, close by. So we take the car and drive in the direction of the place, but see nothing.. It was not a plane, there was no sound. Very strange that the first two keep the same height and direction, strange that the last one goes down.

properties.Remarks: Den internationale Rumstation ISSse SUFOI's kommentarse beretning

properties.content: A little after half past one in the morning, I had gone out into a small yard behind the main house in my home in the center of Odense to get some fresh air. Since, despite the city lights, it was completely starry in the part of the sky that can be seen from the yard, it was tempting to look back and try to recognize some of the constellations. Suddenly, from a point in the north-west direction, out of nowhere (from a point in the sky I was just watching) an oval object appears, where my immediate assumption was that it was a shooting star. Only when it disappeared behind our own roof in a south-westerly direction did I have doubts. The object had to be unusually large for a shooting star to be. Also, it hadn't disintegrated, and the thought that it might have been a larger meteor shooting down through the atmosphere struck me. I imagined that it could also be a plane or a helicopter after all, but no sound came from the object at any time. If it were a high-flying airliner, the relative speed across the sky would also be slower (just as the size of the object would be smaller). And if it was a jet plane or a helicopter, the speed would no less indicate engine noise. I remember the light intensity as being the same for the good 5 seconds the observation lasted, and the object could only be seen as star-colored white light, which was simply much larger than ordinary stars or shooting stars. I am immediately curious to hear if others have made a similar observation at the same time, if meteor impacts have actually been reported (on land or at sea), or if there are radar observations at the time of the observation that can tell us something.

We were looking at stars and then my mother poked me in the eyeball and said, look what's going on over there. And then there were 10 triangles towards the north, and then approx. 3 sec. and then they fired 3 shots, and there was no sound of an engine, but the sound of a witch's howl.
I was out taking pictures of the night sky. When I get home and upload pictures to the PC, I see this little blue saucer shaped thing almost at the top of the picture. What is it ?

At 22:55 I observe 2 orange/red flying objects in the sky, there is no sound but only the constant orange/red light from the flying objects. 5 minutes later 6 flying objects arrive, 2 in sequence followed by 2 flying next to each other and then 2 behind in sequence. As they fly south, #2 flying object emits some blue light towards the ground. While it does this, it stands still, and so do all the others, also at the same time as the second-to-last also emits some blue light. They fly further south and disappear. It takes approx. 5 minutes, then more arrive, they all fly in the same direction, and all disappear to the south. There are still some who stop to throw away the blue light. All this lasts for approx. 35 minutes.

Was out for an evening walk with the dog. Very star clear. Looking up and can see white dot in the sky moving at uneven speed from NE to S/SE. At first I think it must be a satellite - but due to the rather uneven speed and partly stopping - I take a closer look. Follows it all the way. It doesn't look like much and looks more like a star. When it suddenly turns around and flies towards the North/East (Orion's belt) it is strange. Cannot be a balloon, airplane (checked with Fligt radar) or satellite. No drone either - way too loud. My wife also comes out and looks and agrees that it looks strange. I film with a mobile phone, but impossible to see anything on the film.
Strong orange/yellow light with no sound flew irregularly a little up a little down, but all the time to the north. After approx. 3 min it disappeared.

I had just let the dog out in the garden when I observe what looks like a very bright shining star, almost like being blinded by a flashlight. I notice it moving and think it must be a plane. However, the way it moves is so weird that I look for the red flashing lights on the wings to be sure. To my great astonishment, I see it moving upwards at great speed. After approx. 15 sec. is no longer visible.

Standing and talking on the phone from 16.25 and for 8m00s and looking out the window, where I see a very strong glowing orange-yellow object that I can't see moving. It has no immediate extent. Since 248° is roughly in the direction of the setting sun from 240° to 245° in the time period - and in the same direction the incoming planes come from the west towards Kastrup Airport, it is most likely sunshine from a plane. However, I think that it was much quieter in the approx. 20 seconds, I observed, than the incoming planes usually do. If others have similar observations to mine, but from different angles, this observation will be interesting.

5-8 "stars" or satellite lights in collision with each other with different direction like a vortex between each other, but together flying in the same straight direction. Flew over the Carlsvogn and was altogether slightly larger than the "small" Carlsvogn.

A faint star/plane, flying from south to north in the western sky. It lights up strongly for 1-2 sec - dim again for a few seconds, then again strongly for a few seconds, after which it becomes dim and disappears in 3-5 sec. Guessing a plane, but there was something about a Russian rocket coming back down...

When I was awake several times during the night because of the heat, I went out on my balcony and smoked half a cigarette. There was cloud cover over the area I live in (Holsted) and as always I look at the night sky as I have observed several uaps 2 times before with great clarity, not planes, not satellites. This time was a little different, as I said there was cloud cover, and if it hadn't been because it was moving, I wouldn't have seen it. It was disc-shaped, gray (same color as the cloud) and flew quite low just below the cloud cover. It must have been relatively large, as I estimated from that distance that it was approx. 5-7 cm in diameter and enough wing approx. 2-3 kilometers from where I live. It flew at the speed of an F-16, which was quite slow and completely silent, it disappeared into a cloud and I saw no more of it.

Observation 1, at 19.40 A luminous ball moves slowly towards us from the south south-east. The light seems bigger and more powerful than on an airplane. There were no flashing lights to be seen. As the object is in front of us, it turns to the east and slowly disappears into the darkness. We hear no sound from the object, despite the windless weather. The object lights up roughly the same amount during the entire process (approx. 5 min.)

Today, 28.1.18 at 18.05, I spotted a red saucer-shaped object which flew very fast. I was out shopping and bought some things. When I got home, some of the things had to be put out on the balcony. After I hung up, I raised my head and saw the red object, which I have no idea what it could be. I kept an eye on it. And then suddenly the piece of scrap flew up towards the sky at a reasonable speed, stopped a few times and flew at the same speed again. Couldn't catch it on camera...disappeared silently.......
Pulsating orange light comes from the south at high speed and approx. 45 degrees disappears to the west in increasing altitude, but at the same speed.

Sat on the sofa in our home and suddenly saw out of the living room window 2 orange-red round lights moving independently of each other in the evening sky. Strange maneuvering, as one suddenly moves sharply downwards, then moves upwards again - disappearing towards the northeast together with the other. We want a logical explanation for this and think of two helicopters, but do they have orange-red lights? My husband said he could see a Y-shaped antenna on at least one.

I follow it across the sky from east to west and it moves very fast. I'm used to seeing planes as that's where they fly in for landing. But this is 4-5 times faster. I don't think it's a satellite. Maybe a rocket.

Was on my way home from Århus towards Galten, Saw a bright light approx. 100 meters up in the air. Turn right down a dirt road to observe. It switched the pulses between the colors as mentioned. Had a camera in the car plus a powerful laser stick.. Lighted it up and got flashes back. There it was approx. 50 meters from me. Started filming, taking pictures. Noticed it was completely silent. Just as slowly it started to float towards me.. How I got scared. Started the car and rushed home. To my surprise, I had received a lot of film + photos. Have seen UFOs before in this area, hence the camera in the car.
Is there anyone other than me who saw a luminous ball the size of a soccer ball flying across the sky from the south to the west on Thursday 21/4 -2016 at approx. 24/00?

I was waiting for the bus, looking at the night sky since there was a good chance of shooting stars, when I see a low-flying, fast and completely silent object heading east above me. I can best describe it as transparent, since it wasn't a clear light, but more of a dim round orange/bright light, with a black center that made it look transparent. Later in the evening, I see another again in the direction of the east. At first I thought it might be meteors, but they would simply have burned up and had more light, as well as disappearing faster than what I saw.

On 1 March at 18.15 I sat and looked out of my kitchen window, which faces Nørresø near Viborg, and over which I have a very wide view. I observed a very bright white luminous object moving at high speed towards the north/northeast. Suddenly 3-4 slightly smaller objects were shot out of it. They were also glowing white and shortly afterwards the light went out in both the "mother" object and in the "offshoots". I - who is a retired major in the army - am completely convinced that it was not a plane, the speed was too high for that, just as no normal plane flashes could be detected. I am unable to assess the flying height of the objects.
2 red spherical objects come silently across the sky, at relatively low altitude. After approx. 10 min another 2 come and disappear over the sea.

Around 22:15 I saw a light in the sky brighter than the rest of the stars. The direction was southeast, no pulsing, no sound. It was a bit greenish and there was a din glow around it. When it was covered in clouds you could see the glow even better.

Black object with orange light at bottom, moved silently at steady speed without sound. It was probably a China lamp from a black plastic bag. Can be compared to other sightings on big UFO day :-) 22/5(Hacker fun)

My eye catches something moving in the sky. Two luminous objects move across the sky. There is no sound. It is clear weather. There are clear stars. The altitude is what I would call below a low cloud cover. I can observe this soon after, where some low clouds drift in the same direction. Shortly after, three more objects arrive! In total, 12-15 objects come together one, two or three. For three to four of them, there is something resembling a stretch of orange light that rotates as if searching. The extent of this extent is the same size as the object.

After an outdoor concert at the subway station, quite a few people gathered. Most worked with clean-up, others were musicians and the audience. Just after dusk, some saw an orange glowing dot in the sky moving across the Frederiksberg Center. I don't know when it actually appeared. When I saw the dot, it was in a northerly direction, (I found the direction with a Kraks map and a pocket compass), for approx. 50-55 degree elevation. The dot was very clear and bright, no flashing or sound. It most resembled an emergency rocket. It moved slowly to the west as it slowly faded out, somewhat in the same way that airplanes can. Therefore, it seemed as if it was moving away from us. Eventually it faded out completely and was gone. There were many who saw the dot, and the reactions were very mixed. A few wondered, others were indifferent, and still others had an attitude in between.

New Year's Eve between 24:00 - 01:00 I stood, my adult daughter-in-law and my gl. colleague/neighbor and talking and as we looked at the gunpowder....we saw an orange-golden object flying across the sky reconnoitering...quietly and no doubt...it was not earthly of some kind... nor a Chinese lamp or emergency flare for a boat and the like.... My colleague was completely speechless... and it seems that several others have also experienced similar... the object we saw was flat oval/egg shaped. .. and the way it moved is as the link says... too fast to be a lantern and too slow to be an airplane, - helicopter, - firework or flare... and the kept the same height... completely different from what we usually see and experience... it stood out to that extent... I have searched all over the web for flg... and learn that there are at least 7 countries that have experienced the same phenomenon on the same date... furthermore, there are several who have seen it in different places in Denmark...

Every late evening from 11pm to 2.30am for the past 14 days I have observed a strange object moving in the black but clear night sky. The object has a clear white and very sharp color, which occasionally changes color to a sharp cobalt blue. The object moves clearly but slowly. Primarily on a straight route from west to east, but the object makes many and long-term stays on the route. Sometimes the object stands completely still in the sky. Likewise, it sometimes moves up and down, just as it occasionally flies back. It seems clear that it is examining something closely. The following has been observed by several people.

I came cycling and heard a sound like a helicopter, looked up and saw a black object that had facom as spades in the cards, or a stingray, hard to write exactly. It was thick round at the sides and had a dark pin or similar on the back too, it looked strange. Haven't seen one like that before, don't know what it is, can only write what I saw.

In 1972, or thereabouts, maybe a little later, we went as a couple on an evening walk to the North Sea at Agger north of the Limfjord. Unfortunately we have forgotten the date; but it was a very dark evening, and therefore certainly in the winter. The year can deceive us somewhat; but 1972, maybe 73 will be close. We stood in the dune and heard the roar of the sea, because you couldn't see the sea, it was actually pitch black. Suddenly, and it was actually quite sudden, a very strong light appeared, for me to see almost at the edge of the beach, my husband remembers the distance as approx. at the outer end of the built hips, however, we agree on the clarification to between hips 89 and 90; but closest to 90. The bright light appears in my memory as a round/oval-lying luminous ball with great radiant power - quite close to the ground or water surface. There was no movement. We don't remember the color; but to my inner eye I can recreate the image with red-yellow warm colors. My husband leans more towards the view that maybe the color was lighter to white. Whether the phenomenon was to be seen for 5 minutes is also difficult to assess today; but at least we don't think it was there anymore. AND. It is true that there was no light when we got to the sea. There were no sounds in connection with the observation. Waves only. And. There was absolutely no question of fishing boats or other natural phenomenon that simply landed. And, it wasn't about big waves either, which would be able to hide a larger ship between possible waves - in between. There was no wind at all that evening. We were greatly surprised by what we had seen, and have spoken many, many times since then about the episode, which we are still quite confused about. Even with our best approaches, we have never been able to come up with a single natural explanation for the phenomenon. As children born in -, and brought up next to the North Sea, we were both familiar with the phenomenon we call fire in the sea or fire in the sea, as it is probably also called. We have observed this several times both before and after the mentioned incident, which in no way resembles arson in the slightest. If our observations, even if they have been archived in our heads for many years, could be used in the investigation of UFOs, that would make us happy, and we would of course like to hear if you have an idea of what we could possibly do. in reality have seen. Today we are respectively 50 and 51 years old, and have talked about the episode as recently as today at afternoon coffee.
A silent white light, flat in shape and pulsing, that looked like something was being dragged behind it. 2 pictures have been taken where you can sense the light in the lower right corner.

First came 3 yellow lights - close to each other, then turned away like planes in formation. They were simply silent, perhaps more reminiscent of a large emergency flare. Pictures indicate it as V-shaped. 1 minute, two planes came closer, and remained together, which came three more and turned off to the west. southwest and northwest. 5 min came another 3 which continued directly south west. The light was unchanged whether viewed from the front, side or back. The light was constant - not flashing. 2 of the pictures show slightly elongated, probably taken from a different angle.

I was out walking our dog with my sister. On the way home we saw a man on a bicycle who kept looking at the sky. When we looked to see what he was looking at, we saw little red lights moving at the same time without sound. There was no sound of an airplane or anything like that at all. They moved without sound.

My wife and I were walking home from visiting my father-in-law along his dirt road. We often look at the stars when we walk and talk. I've seen plenty of shooting stars before, and it didn't look like one at all. Nor have I ever seen anything in the sky move slowly and then rush out of there at an unreal speed. It had no trace left. We're both sure we've never seen anything like it. in the sky before.

Very strange delta-like shape. Reminiscent a lot of a drone in its movements, but the shape was completely beside the point. We observed for approx. 1 hour and I called the tower at Sønderborg Airport and asked him to look at the radar, but he had nothing to report. As the object rotated, it appeared to have a pair of wings that bent down in a radius. Below that sat a lamp that flashed white, with a very soft light (not Xenon or LED). I used my 10x50 binoculars to observe, and it immediately looked like the object was hanging out over Nybøl Nor. But a drone that hangs mine. 1 hour pretty much the same place?? Who is performing? What secrets are there around Nybøl Nor? Some blurry and small pictures and video, unfortunately I couldn't zoom in enough, but you probably have the equipment for that. I'm not on Facebook, but if desired, I can email things.

I sat quietly and watched the night sky from our terrace. Towards the SW I saw a very large luminous object which gradually receded into nothingness. As the object was still, I don't suspect it was a shooting star - have any other people observed the same light???

Yesterday, 10/10/2012, I saw a strong white light in the north on my bicycle on the way to DagligBrugsen in Årslev, moving south with a speed significantly greater than that of a commercial airliner, just as the mandatory light guidance was not seen. Neither was there any sound other than the ordinary one in the street. Today, 11.10, I saw the same thing - also on the way to Brugsen. I got off the bike to find out what the hell this could be - again. As soon as I stopped, the stone did too. I decided that now it wasn't going to get away as easily as yesterday, when I had probably wondered what it could be, but hadn't really made the effort to look into it. After approx. 5 minutes when it had not moved out of the spot, I slowly drove on. I could now see that the object was following my movement, that it started at the same time as I started cycling again, and that it was following me in the same direction as I was cycling. Suddenly I saw something (today 11.10 on my way to the utility, and as last observed) which I had not noticed yesterday, namely that there was a tall antenna mast in the place where the object could be seen. I have to admit that my senses and my mind played tricks on me. What I saw was the anti-collision light on top of a transmission mast located just 100 meters from my cycle route. And then it is now afterwards, and you are not quite used to changing light patterns during the season. But of course: When I kept still, the light on the antenna mast naturally did too. Oh yes. When will I see a real flying saucer, one of those that just streaks across the sky like lightning?

I hope you can give an answer to what I saw yesterday between 23:00-23:30 on 16/9. I can't quite remember the time. But around there. I have found a picture on the web by searching a bit that is similar to what I saw. I was sitting out on my balcony with my girlfriend, and when we were sitting looking up at the stars, suddenly 10-15 "lights" "flying things" UFO-like things "" came flying over our heads (from behind) (east) ) and towards the road we were sitting. (West) It flew crazy fast!!

We saw a very bright light over the forest, at first we talked about maybe it was a Chinese lamp, light show from the ground (which didn't make sense because there were no clouds) helicopter or a drone, but there was no sound. The object was moving slowly to the west, but either slowed down or started moving towards us. I guess there are approx. 500 meters between us and the object. Suddenly, the object accelerates at an unrealistic speed to the east and disappears over the horizon, again without a sound and at a speed we have never seen before.

Last night, April 4, approx. at At 01:15 a good friend and I were sitting at Nivå harbor talking in his car and looking at the stars. It was windless, the sky was completely cloudless and there were no city lights, so it was very starry. The car was parked on a small pier (about 1 m. above sea level) that had the shape of a large semicircle. It was very dark, so you could only see the silhouette of the pier, and the silhouette of a trash can, which was the only object on the pier. Looking out towards the pier, I saw something utterly surreal. Right out at the edge of the pier approx. 20 meters ahead, I could see a silhouette of an indescribable shape, "blinking" and flitting back and forth in an area of approx. 3 meters. It was on for about 7 seconds. The form now turned into a small figure bent forward (about 160 cm), moving at the same speed as a human walking very fast. The figure moved approx. 7 meters to the left and disappeared with one about 1 meter before it reached the bin. Of course, I sat completely speechless and shaken, and looked like a big question mark. My friend and I agreed that we had observed the same thing. However, he had seen something bright dome-like 5 meters in front of the car, just before the second observation had taken place. It must be said that we also saw a shooting star for a few minutes. before the sighting of the dark figures. I will never forget what I saw last night.

I took pictures of the beautiful blood-red evening sky. Afterwards I counted 25 pictures. I thought I saw something that looked like a UFO in one of the pictures, and therefore kept taking pictures. As said 25 pieces. When I put the pictures on the computer, I could see that the same thing was in 4 of the pictures. I often see something inexplicable, but this is the first time I've caught it on camera.

At around 9.35pm I go out to walk our dog and cross the car park between Københavnsvej and the main road. We have just crossed the parking lot and have walked quite a few meters along the pavement on Pedersvej, when I look up and over towards Køge stadium and see what I first think is a matte plastic bag that has been blown away by the wind. A few seconds later I realize that there is not much wind, that it could be a bag and go back a little to be able to see it better, I then realize that it is something completely different, and not something I've seen before. I look at the object, which is saucer-shaped and the color is almost gray-white. It passes almost straight over my head without a sound and without any kind of light. It moves out towards Køge Bay at a steady speed that did not seem to be particularly high, approx. 150-200 km/h. However, I am not sure of this, as I did not have the opportunity to see how high up it was and therefore cannot say how big it was either. I could see it for approx. 10 seconds before it disappeared out of sight as silently as it had appeared. This is the first time I've ever seen anything so incredible, and I think my lower jaw almost hit the pavement, I was gaping so much, while also feeling a little uneasy about not knowing what was flying overhead head on me.

I sat and talked on the phone with my best friend, who lives in Højslev, close to Skive. I myself live in Hvalpsund, so there is only the Limfjord between us. I go outside and stand on my steps to see. Just above the roof of my garage I can see something red and green. I can't see it through the roof and decide to go inside and look through the window instead. Suddenly another one flies next to my house, up in the air of course, and here I can see that it is a triangle with lights on each side and one in the middle. I call my mother, but before she can get out, it has reached the point where it is only a small light in the sky. It flew extremely fast and had crazy acceleration, because it was flying quietly when I first saw it, and then it accelerated violently.

We saw a luminous object flying from SW to SEA at slow speed. Just above the last star in the constellation Orion's belt. I got binoculars and followed it until it had flown past all 3 stars in the belt. Suddenly it picked up speed and turned directly in a southerly direction, out into space and disappeared.

During a family birthday, we observe a larger object in the night sky south of Fredensborg, the object is stationary and changes between green, red, yellow, etc. somewhat like a star, but clearly larger than any known stars. We set up Leica binoculars to examine the object more closely, but it is initially difficult to focus on, however we can rule out with some certainty that it should be a star, a plane or a helicopter. The object changes after approx. 4-5 min color to completely yellow/white and grows considerably, then disappears at considerable speed towards Sweden. We also believe that the object was followed by a smaller and weaker object, and here we think it is a plane or similar. During the next hour, we observe a few more objects, which, however, glow shorter and "just" fade away. However, we can calmly rule out that it was something unique and "foreign" - this is not where we are looking for an explanation, but it would now be interesting to solve the mystery, or hear from others who may have seen the same. We've kind of settled on the fact that it might be a stationary rocket, or some meteorological measuring equipment, but we are by no means experts in the field.

At approx. at quarter to one my girlfriend and I observed a large number of luminous and faintly reddish dots moving silently across the Copenhagen night sky. The phenomenon was most reminiscent of hot air balloons or the like. and initially the number was around 7-9 red dots. They moved at exactly the same (same for everyone) and constant speed across the horizon - corresponding to a movement from left to right in the night sky as seen from our kitchen window. As the first of the observed red dots disappeared from our field of vision, new ones appeared. In total, there have been approx. between 14 and 20 red dots that moved with this pattern. It took a total of approx. 6-7 minutes for all dots to move across the sky. We took many pictures and video clips with our mobile phones and digital camera, but they subsequently turned out not to contain anything useful. The equipment is probably too bad. However, for good measure we have preserved the material, in case a digital change of contrast and colors can highlight something useful. As I said, there was not a sound to be heard, so if they were airplanes they must have had fairly quiet engines or were very far away. A more realistic suggestion could be some form of hot air balloons (borne by the wind it could explain the very constant and uniform movement of all the objects), but we have not been able to find any description of this in the media this evening, and also have no suggestion of the rational in putting so many balloons into the air at the same time. Another realistic suggestion could be that the objects were satellites (space junk or similar) in orbit around the earth - an expert in astronomy must be able to analyse/tell about the movement, which, seen from our window, fits with objects in orbit that pass over the horizon.

I have evening and night work at the Business School, Århus (HHÅ). On my way home and out of the building I see through a window a bright star I have not seen before. I admire it a bit and then move on. Apparently no movement of the star. Five minutes later, my wife and I, who also cleans at HHÅ, leave the building. My wife gets into the car while I go to stamp out. I spot a clear, non-glaring, orb of light fly across the sky, and I realize it's the star from before. The ball of light is warm yellow, approaching orange. No sound is heard, and the ball of light does not flash like on an airplane, and it is precisely not a dot of light, but a ball of light. I look at it and then stamp out. On the way back to the car, I look for the ball of light again and probably catch a few glimpses of it. Immediately inside the car, I tell my wife that I have seen a flying saucer, which was not saucer-shaped but round. We drive out through the gate, and I see a ball of light disappear behind a roof ridge and immediately afterwards a ball of light emerges from the roof ridge further on, and I immediately know that they are two different balls of light. I no longer turn right, but left and onto a large parking lot between HHÅ and the former Musikkonversatorium (now also part of HHÅ). Here I see 5 balls of light flying across the sky. My wife thinks she counted 6 orbs to start with. They all look the same, all bright, clear, warm yellow balls of light. I stop the car and get out. No sound to be heard. The balls of light move at a steady speed across the sky and maintain the relative position. As I remember it, two relatively close to each other at the front, then a little way down to ball of light No. 3 and then a little way down to the two at the back, which have a greater distance between them than the two at the front. I take out my cell phone and try to take a picture, sure it won't turn out well due to lighting conditions and distance. (I have taken night pictures from the balcony at HHÅ before, when there have been fireworks on the harbour. The pictures are not very good). We look at the orbs of light that continue as a line, no lateral movement, no change of speed - it's like watching a star sign fly away. The balls of light disappear behind the trees along the east side of the parking lot. I look at the mobile phone clock: 00:41. We drive out onto Fuglesangs Alle and down and out onto Viborgvej and towards Hasle. Before we reach the first traffic light at Brugsen and OK-Benzin at Viborgvej, we see two more balls of light. They look exactly like the others, same size (well actually same height), same color, same course and speed. At the intersection, we see a car turn up, as if the driver is following the balls of light. A little further up Viborgvej we see a man standing on the pavement talking on a mobile phone - we are of course sure that he has seen the UFOs and is calling home with the news! Soon after, a police car comes driving at normal speed towards Aarhus - we don't know if they saw anything. At home I look at the photograph. I don't know if the lone ball of light in the photo is one of the light balls or just a light pole in the parking lot. I'll look for it tonight at work. Here later it occurs to me that the first "star" I saw may not be among the 5 balls of light we saw afterwards. It took approx. 5 minutes from when I saw the "star" until we walked out the door. Possibly the "star" has flown away and the other balls of light have come to the side, just like the last two.

On 22 August at 22.45 above Horsens we were four people who saw something in the sky that we cannot explain. We've all seen shooting stars, planes, meteors and satellites before. This was something different and inexplicable to us. There were two small luminous dots that looked very much like the stars you see with the naked eye. No twinkle or colors - just like stars. The strange thing was that they lay side by side and followed each other very high in the sky in movements like a snake. They were higher than ordinary planes, were unusually fast and had no sound. The observation lasted approx. 9-12 seconds and then they were gone. Maybe physics can give us an explanation?

Standing and looking out of the window towards the center of Nyborg. From the rooftops above the yard comes a large triangle with lights in each corner flying, the lights are very bright and you can see the stars, up between the lights. The triangle swings sideways and around as it flies. Viewed from below, where I am standing on the first floor, I would think that the sides of the triangle are something like 50 m, if not more, it is a right triangle. I can't calculate the flight speed, nor the angle. The triangle is probably a few kilometers up, not at all plane height, which is approx. 10 km. The weather is clear with no moonlight.

Sees an object coming at high speed north, flies approx. 5km, stops in the sky, stays standing approx. an hour in the same place. The object appears to be round, glowing white with some kind of rays around it
We had friends visiting. The rest of us ran out, and over the sky came approx. 9 objects. Lighted guide lights, white round.
Also observed on 20022020 at the same time, however the object has moved more to the northwest and not as high in the sky.

Standing in the backyard, looking at the stars. I noticed what I thought was a star moving. Thought it was a satellite. It got bigger, flew east, slowed down. Thought it was the initial approach to KBH airport. It turned around in a circle, (maybe they are not allowed to land, I thought, I was surprised that it was very high up, and far from Kastrup (about 60 km). Circled several times, a very small circle, stood almost quiet at one point. Looked away for a moment. Only a light remained, like a star. Later, after about 10 minutes it was completely gone. What did I experience?

Hello, I am writing on behalf of some close acquaintances who in 1998 observed a very sharp cone of light from the sky down around Kr. Shelves. They could see it when they drove from Borrevejle and towards Kr. Shelves. The cone of light remained in the sky for approx. 15 min., it took to drive from Lyndby to Kr. Shelves. They lived on a road in Kirke Hyllinge and could see the cone of light clearly until they got out of the car in front of their driveway on the road in Kr. Shelves. They stopped the car so that the person in the passenger seat could quickly get out and see what it was. As soon as the person was out, the light disappeared, and the only thing visible was a green light far out on one side and a red light far out on the other side just above the car. There was no sound at all. After that, no observations. Right after their observation, they called me in Valby, from where they had just driven, to report what they had seen.

I come driving west on Vestre Landevej (route 9), through Nørreballe. After passing the roundabout at Østofte Gade/Koholtvej, I notice a strong red, flashing light crossing my direction of travel some distance in front of me, approx. 40-45 degrees above the horizon. The light is double, i.e. it looks like 2 light bulbs next to each other. My immediate assessment is that the light is 500-1,000 meters in front of me, and the light is flashing approx. 1 time per second (on ½ second, off ½ second). As I approach Højrebyvej (route 291), the light continues in a northerly direction. The view of the light is briefly blocked by vegetation along the road, but I can follow it for a few minutes until it is so low above the horizon (about 5 degrees) that I suspect buildings or vegetation are blocking the view. At this point, I would think that the light is near Keldernæs/Blans in Nordlolland. Cloudless and starry, approx. 10 degrees heat. I was in a moving car so I didn't hear any engine or rotor noise. My first thought was that it was either a drone or a small passenger plane (ULF or similar).

One evening after work I was riding a moped when I suddenly spotted a blue ball above the golf course. It slowly came closer. I stopped to look at it as it came in my direction. The ball seemed the same as glass, the color of a welding flame, blue and almost white in the middle. It had a glassy exterior. There was no noise. It was approx. 2-3 meters in diameter and approx. 30 meters up. It flew past me at an angle over the golf clubhouse and disappeared from my view. I then drove home as it was dark down the road behind the clubhouse and I was unsure of what I saw.

My boyfriend and I were out taking long exposure photos of the night sky and had just changed location when we spot a very powerful, slow moving, luminous object moving across the sky. Having the camera ready, we quickly took a picture of the object and then followed the object until it disappeared behind the trees. This took about 1-2 minutes. We stood in amazement afterwards and decided to go inside, whereupon we observed another powerful, slow-moving, white light. However, this light moved, unlike the previous one, from south to north, and gradually lost brightness until it completely disappeared from the sky. Both lights were as powerful as large shooting stars.

The object appeared to the east, moved over our heads and disappeared to the west, the passage took approx. a minute. The object was clear but not strongly whitish luminous with a brighter center. The moon was up and the diameter of the object was approx. one fifth of the moon's diameter. We heard no sound from the object, although there was no other noise, and we both have excellent hearing. Four to five minutes after the flyover, the phenomenon repeated itself (another object appeared), in exactly the same way. Although it was Saturday night, we were both sober.
For a very short moment we saw a box like. object with red lights.

properties.Colors: hvid hale, kerne rød til violet

properties.content: I just heard on the radio about unexplained events. About 3 years ago, we were also exposed to an inexplicable incident. I don't think it has anything to do with UFOs though. We were on our way home from Jyderup towards Roskilde by Skovvejen, and my wife was driving the car. Approx. 200 meters before we reach an illuminated UNO X tank, the light suddenly goes out on the car, and at the same moment the light also disappears on the UNO X tank. It gets totally dark and my wife brakes violently, but after 10-20 seconds the light comes on again on the car, at the same time as the light also comes back on at the service station. We have no natural explanation for it, but there were 2 of us who experienced the same thing.

I go outside to get some fresh air as I can't sleep. I then see a red-hot "ball" up in the sky whizzing by at a speed that shouldn't be possible... I've experienced this before, in the opposite direction. There were more witnesses than me, but it's been almost 10 years now.

We turned into Næsborvej in Hvidovre, after which we all spotted something that looked like a "flying car". It was definitely not an airplane, but maybe a helicopter? It was a little bigger than a car and a little wider. I stopped the car, got out and turned off the headlights. Quite slowly, completely silently, the "car" moved from north to south approx. 200 m from us. On each side was a flashing red light. Both front and back, a series of lights in 2 maybe 3 different colors, yellow, white light yellow? At the back of the cabin (corresponding to the rear window/hat shelf area) of the "flying car" there was a dim light. I turned into the driveway. The object continued slowly over the trees in Vigerslevparken, to the south. We didn't wait to see more as the 2 of the passengers who were children and myself were a bit puzzled and confused about the silent possible helicopter?

I am sitting and enjoying the good weather by the water on Christianshavn's Voldgade in Copenhagen. The time is approx. 16.00, and the weather is warm and a bit hazy - but no clouds, except on the horizon. I sit and watch the birds and a group of trees on the other side of the water (to the east), and suddenly see a bright flash of light just above the treetops. I look in the direction of the flash, and there is now a dimly lit spot on the spot that wasn't there before. It's quite far away, I want to shoot at 8-10 km away, and way up in the air layers. This luminous point, which has now come into view, begins to move slowly to the left, ie. in a northerly direction and I quickly find my camera from my bag to try to film it. However, the object is so far away that the zoom function is unable to capture it, so I give up and try to maintain eye contact instead. It disappears with the same steady speed behind the treetops, but appears on the other side. After approx. 20-30 sec. fades the object out and disappears. It cannot have been a "flare", as it moved in a horizontal trajectory, was too far up, and traveled quite a distance, several kilometers at least. I can also rule out a satellite as they don't appear in a flash of light and fade out; however, the light traveled at the same high speed as a satellite before disappearing. Duration of the observation: approx. 2 minutes

From my couch, I suddenly saw a yellow-orange spot of light the size of an orange emerge from behind a tree in a western direction and move in the sky. At first I thought it was some kind of firework, but the ball of light didn't go down. My wife and I went outside and watched the object move calmly in a slight arc to the south until it disappeared after a few minutes. The light gradually faded as the object moved south. There are many planes that pass Jelling, so we know what planes look like in the night sky, and to our knowledge it was not a plane. There was no sound either.

At first I thought it was a stray rocket, but there was no sound or bang. Then I thought shooting stars, but not with those colors and size. It came from the east horizontally and finally descending to the west. Had a teardrop-like shape, just horizontal. Was green and where it tapered at the end a light yellow ending in a dark yellow. Maybe a comet? My dog immediately responded by running barking in the direction of where I saw the object. There were 2 scheduled flights over the area in the north/south, south/north direction.

I had just gone into the kitchen and opened the window to get some fresh air when I became aware of a red flashing light, which I assumed was an aviator. When I looked again, I thought it was flying a bit strangely, it seemed to stop for a brief moment. Followed it until it disappeared behind the property opposite, a moment later it appeared on the other side of the property. Suddenly it stopped again and then flew due north for a short moment, then came back. I rushed into the living room and picked up my mobile phone, which has a built-in camera, and went into the kitchen again, where I filmed a small sequence. Then another red light came flying towards the first. This disappeared immediately after and the first disappeared behind a property. I didn't see them anymore even though I went out to look several times.

Picking up my daughter from the garden, as she doesn't want to sleep in a tent anyway. In the dark, the luminous dot slides from south>north parallel to Svendborgvej. The light is just over the horizon and I think at first it was a plane. However, the object's light was strong and constant. On Flightradar there were no planes on the same course. Maybe a satellite?

I came across this website after searching for sightings in Risskov/Aarhus and find a report that corresponds to our experience. On Tuesday evening, 18/4, my girlfriend and I are sitting in our apartment on the 2nd floor on Sletterhagevej in Risskov. I'm sitting with my phone and my boyfriend is watching TV (family fun anno 2023🙂 ). Suddenly, out of the corner of our eyes, we both see a green light/dot moving extremely fast (appearing southwest of our apartment). It appears out of nowhere and moves west and down, where it disappears behind the apartments opposite ours. However, it all takes place in a split second. Immediately, it was not a shooting star, as the distance does not seem quite out in the sky, as the size was much larger than that. It was, however, not immediately close either (it was immediately a short distance behind the apartment it disappeared behind). Pretty sure it wasn't a drone or fireworks. Visually, it looked like a ticking "drag" of a green tail, but this is probably more due to the speed (visually for the eyes). It was all without sound.

I went for a walk a little while ago, and on the way back I went and looked at the starry sky. I picked up some movement among the stars to the east, it looked like a star, but when I got to look properly, I could ascertain that it was definitely not a star (shooting star) and not a flyer either. It continued on a straight course and at times disappeared behind stars and reappeared until it disappeared just above the listed address. D therefore no compass direction as it was straight up (looked like it was moving away from the ground as it gradually got fainter and fainter in brightness) it traveled about a distance equal to a forearm, without the hand. I have previously observed something similar together with 2 others, it was mid-July 2013 at approx. 01.00. The position was then in Fuglebjerg, where it moved from south to north, with improbable speed (held up the forearm and from observation point "elbow" to end "fingertip", it took about 5 min). At that time it stopped and appeared to be moving towards Earth as it grew brighter and larger (comparable to "a small lamp" becoming a much larger lamp) before finally standing still for about 2 min., after which it withdrew and followed the same route as it had come for approx. 20 sec. to finally change course, from due north to due east and disappear, just like the one I just saw. I don't doubt for a moment that what I/we have seen cannot have been naturally occurring events, as the track has changed each time, but today only away.... I tried to take pictures/film with phone, but unfortunately it cannot be seen due to poor lighting conditions.
Last night at approx. At 00.20 we were out looking at the night sky -- we saw 7 yellow lights moving south.

Exactly the same observation as the observation above .. At first it looks like a faint star moving across in a straight direction .. But slowly and steadily it gets clearer and clearer .. And at its peak it shines like the brightest star and then loses its brightness again and then go completely out and am completely pissed off .. It's not a plane because it doesn't blink .. The whole thing lasts 5-6 seconds.

Sitting on the terrace to look for shooting stars, when I see small red lights, which form a large triangle, slide silently across the sky. It comes into view from the east over my roof and I can follow it until it disappears behind some large trees to the west. Will shoot at it approx. is 20 m wide and 25 m long, but hard to tell in the dark, where you can only see the lights. It is cloudless, but it was flying so low that if there had been clouds it would have been below. Would love to know if there are others who have observed the same thing as me.

I just woke up on the couch in the living room and go out to let our dog walk for the night before I go to bed myself. As we get out, I look up at the sky to look at the stars. I almost always do that when I walk the dog when it's dark. Unfortunately I haven't got my glasses on, but I can still see pretty clearly, just not sharp. I first look towards the Moon, which is quite clear and almost directly above the house, almost at the same time I see what I think is a rather bright star almost directly below the Moon. I look further and then turn my gaze to the Moon again, here I discover that what I thought was a powerful star is moving with constant speed across the sky to the east. The speed does not match an airplane, nor can I see the normal lights that flash on an airplane. I now rush in for my glasses and out again, and I now clearly see that it looks like a star in appearance and an airplane in terms of position in the sky and the speed also corresponds to an airplane, but the flashing lights are missing, and at no time have I heard a sound as if it were an airplane. I also wonder if it could be a satellite, but it is too low in the sky to be, I think. I probably follow it with my eyes for 3-5 minutes before it disappears into the horizon. My conclusion is that I have no idea what it was I saw.

Object came into view on the left side of the south-facing window. Larger than normal aircraft. "Fire" on the upper side, like a hot-air balloon with a gray gondola, but without a balloon (?). Flew very fast. The object became smaller as it flew across the sky (probably because altitude increased). Shortly after sunset.

We first saw a low-flying "thing", then 2 similar ones followed closely behind. They glided at reasonable speed silently across the sky. We could quickly establish that it was not a plane (due to sound, height and speed). They were not as high up as ordinary planes. They came from the west and then turned north and a little higher in the sky, where they disappeared. We went back inside and after a while we saw 3 more following.... and as they moved across the sky another one came. Everyone followed the same "path" and disappeared "poof" into the sky...!

Spotted a strange "star" from my bedroom last night. My husband and I observed the "star" for approx. 10 minutes It stood in the western sky, if you say the moon was at 3, then the "star" was at 8 in relation to. It was constantly changing color, as seen in some stars, and it was of similar brightness and size, - but it moved very erratically, and over a larger field - we saw through our barred door, and had to shift position to look out of the next "field" in the door, that's how much it moved. It was very irregular movements, up, down, sideways, falling and rising again over a larger area. Airspace closed due to ash cloud, so we ruled out flights. Too much movement to be a satellite. Not a fluke. So what?

Frosty morning 3 finger widths from the sun where a spherical object was hovering which appeared to be a reflection in a camouflage patch which became visible at sunrise. And when we drove to the side, the object descends very slowly. Thought it was a plane, but isn't that how a plane reacts?

I was standing on my balcony looking at the clear night sky when suddenly I see 4 lights pass in the sky in front of me. They started out as in a formation of a rhombus or square, but begin to zig zag between themselves and fly across very quickly. I'm not good at describing the night sky, but I can say that they passed right over the Chariot before flying over the house and out of sight. I could not immediately hear any engine noise. What I immediately found strange and makes me report this observation was the way they moved. That is, across each other at very high speed.
Was on my way out to the carport when I saw this huge flash of light (looked like a giant oversized shooting star).

At approx. 16.30 on 23/04/2009 my son calls. He is standing out in his garden looking at a strange phenomenon through his binoculars. I quickly grab my own binoculars and rush outside. With a cell phone in one hand and binoculars in the other, I get instructions from my son on where to find the phenomenon. I can't see it with the naked eye and search with binoculars. The sky is blue and almost cloudless. After a few misunderstandings about east and west, I get a milky white object in the binoculars. Approx. at 8 and at 5 at a short distance from the milky white object, stand two slightly smaller objects shining metallic. The small objects do not stand still, but seem "nervous". The small object, standing approx. at 8, makes a sudden movement towards the large object and back again. Almost like a jump. Back and forth in less than a second. A few seconds later, the two small objects disappear so quickly that I have no precise sense of direction. Maybe to the northwest. The large object remains standing. It is high in the sky to the north, about 70-80 degrees up. The sun is low to the left (west, southwest), and it fits with the object being illuminated by the sun. After observing the object for approx. 5 minutes without any movement or activity, we call it off, as it is a bit difficult with only one hand to hold the binoculars for that long. We agree that we will be called later. After a few more minutes, the object begins to move slowly to the south, i.e. even higher in the sky. I lay down on the lawn with the binoculars to keep it more stable. The movement is slow, and after a short pause it begins to move slightly to the south-southwest (toward the sun). Then the object turns sharply to the northwest (a turn of approx. 110-120 degrees). The speed is still slow, but it does not turn in an arc, but in a "break" without changing the speed. Suddenly the object is gone. I don't see the direction, it's just gone. After searching the area of the sky where it disappeared for approx. 5 min., I give up finding it again. Our son calls again. He has also lost sight of the object. If I were to judge the size of the object, I would compare it to when I see an airliner flying across the sky at a high altitude. I had approx. the same tremors in the binoculars due to the distance, so the sensation was that the object was the size of an airliner. I will also say that the object was quite clear in binoculars and there were no fins or anything protruding from the object. It was completely smooth. Once I knew exactly where it was in the sky, I could also see it with the naked eye. I sensed at first that it was a spherical object, but as I observed the object, it initially changed shape slightly. as if it occasionally became more elliptical in shape. I therefore began to sense that I was seeing a domed underside of an object that was not spherical. The observation took place in Horsens South and for me lasted approx. 15 minutes It gave an unusually strange sensation to see such an object in daylight. I am used to seeing many strange light phenomena at night, as I have two reflecting telescopes, one large and one small portable. I have also often seen many different planes at different heights and distances with my binoculars. It sure wasn't a plane, a balloon, a helicopter, or anything else I've seen before. The two small objects I caught a glimpse of were also highly unusual. Especially their very sudden movements and completely different way of shining. As if they themselves shone or were completely shiny and made of metal, whereas the large object was milky white and illuminated by the sun.

It happened when I was a child, so the episode dates back quite a few years, so me and my parents cannot remember the exact year, date and month. But the incident itself is very clear. I was 8 or 9 years old. The year 1978 or 1979. It was winter with snow. We think it's January or February. Our neighbor boy and I had gone sledding on a hill near his home. I had my dog with me. A dachshund that I tied to a pole where we were sledding. The landscape here is very hilly. A large hill divided by a small road. We sledded down the small hill so we wouldn't have to sled out onto the road. It is getting dark when the dog gives in to beeping and pulling on the leash in fright. Of course we become aware of it and wonder why it behaves like that. The boy next door says so. Look there - and points up the hill on the other side of the road. There is a large round luminous spot/circle, approx. 6-8 mi diameter, on the snow. It was like seeing a cone from a huge flashlight. The only difference was that the light didn't come from anywhere.
