There was no beam of light from anywhere. There was no sound either, but it surprises me that the dog reacted so strongly, maybe it could hear or feel something that we didn't pick up. How the circle of light got there we did not see, but it just disappeared on the spot. So we didn't see anything flying or gliding away. It disappeared as suddenly as when you press a light switch. It was there for 3-4 minutes at the most. Certainly less, but it felt long. I was now as scared as my dog and quickly ran home. So did the neighbor boy. When I got home, I was completely out of it, shaking and crying, didn't show what this was, and both my parents could both see and feel that I had been through something. that had scared me. I explained it to my parents as soon as they calmed me down a bit. They wanted to go there at once to see if there were any traces of anything, perhaps in the snow. I was terrified. Didn't want to be home alone, but certainly not with that again either. However, the end of it was that we went there again. Maybe half an hour to a full hour later. There was no trace of either people or anything else in the snow. The snow hadn't melted either. For the rest of my childhood I was afraid to cycle past this place when it was dark, so it made a big impression to see something inexplicable. I don't know what it was, but since the light came from nowhere, I've had a hard time figuring out what it was. It can't have been cars, as they can't possibly shine up there, and the lights have a beam of light. Here last year I met again with the boy next door and I said... do you remember then..., yes he could. And my parents also remember when I came home and was scared.

We are 4 people sitting enjoying the bright evening and night sky when we observe a bright white light coming towards us up in the sky from the west a little out over the sea. We naturally assume at first that it is a plane, but at the same time we wonder where it is going from and to. As it gets closer, the speed slows down. There is no sound and it gets weird as we can't see any other lights like on an airplane. At the same time, the light begins to fade (the object now has a position of 0 degrees N) and you can sense a dark object. The light disappears completely, and it's like the object is now falling down, and I grab a pair of binoculars and can now see a dark object of a rectangular shape, falling from the sky like a piece of cardboard would - that is, relatively slowly and in an odd trajectory. The object hits the water and I watch it for maybe a few minutes as it lies on the water, but when I look again - after maybe 5 minutes - it's gone.

I have to meet at work approx. at 4.50-4.55. I am fixated by a very bright star approx. west. Park my bike by the hall and look again and just above me, there is an object. Description: Black, approx. 50-100 m above me, silent, "holds" still for approx. 10 sec., then it flies on very slowly with no sound, only a faint hiss. The vessel was/is approx. 20-30 m from wing tip to wing tip. Has an "arrowhead" girth with a slight arch at the back. There is a red lamp on the left wingtip and a green one on the right. No white light underneath. Flying away at very low speed. I have no idea what I saw, but I saw it!

Walking the dog and suddenly I see a big round ball maybe 1/4 smaller than the Moon from where I'm standing. It flies across the sky without a sound and almost looks like there are orange flames at the end, very strange. It flies so fast that I unfortunately didn't manage to take a picture, and disappears behind the trees by the forest. Went and observed the sky for the last 15 min. on the way home, but no more.

Live in a cottage area where we don't have street lights, so it's very dark in our area. I have a spa outside and have many small garden lights around the spa. I go in at 9.30 pm and sit and enjoy the silence and the starry sky. I see a shooting star towards Kaløvig and then turn in the opposite direction, and suddenly I see two red lights. There is a great distance between the lights, which clearly shows that it is not an airplane or anything else I can usually see in the sky. The lights are coming closer and closer to me - I can't hear anything. The lights come so close that I per reflex makes fuck finger (thought at first - a drone with photo), but again the two red lights are too far apart for that and no sound at all. When I do f... finger the lights stay still and reverse the direction and continue towards the water and towards Aarhus. When the lights change direction, 3 white lights appear next to each of the 2 red lights, and I get up and follow the lights until I can no longer see them. After a minute or two after I hear a sound from the sky that sounded like a fighter plane !!!! And then everything went quiet again and I couldn't see the lights anymore.

It has been many years today since I saw the unidentifiable object. We have to go all the way back to the mid-80s (somewhere between 1984 and 86), but it's still an experience I remember very clearly and one I've never really put down. It was late in the evening and I it had become quite dark. At the time I must have been about 9-10 years old, I think, and I was that evening with my little brother and big brother and my big brother's friend down at our playground. At the time, we lived in a terraced house in Greve. The playground was relatively small and consisted of two wooden houses and a large sandpit as well as three asphalt hills of different sizes. The playground was surrounded by bushes and hedges, and around the hedges the terraced houses were close to the playground. From the hedge to the nearest terraced house was probably around 4-5 metres. I remember we were standing on the biggest hill when the incident happened, but I also think that some of us were standing below the hill, and there may have been other children present as well. In front of us, above one of the terraced houses that surrounded the playground, and it cannot have been more than 10-15 meters from us, a very large white and powerful light suddenly appeared. I remember we all looked at it for a while, how long I have a hard time remembering though. The light immediately seemed to float right above the terraced house in front of us (we were now standing on the big asphalt hill looking at it) and at some point we all choose to run around the house to, I think, see if there is anything at the back of the house or the light. Suddenly, however, the light is gone as suddenly as it came. It was such a violent experience that we all rushed home to our parents, probably shouting at each other that we had seen a UFO. Since that day, I have tried to rationally analyze the incident. After all, I wasn't that old at the time, so many things could have enhanced the experience. However, what still puzzles me to this day was that I don't remember the object/light making any kind of sound or for that matter smell, because I/we would have noticed. I also don't remember that we saw it coming, but that it just happened. It could therefore not have been a parachute rocket, because we would have both seen and heard that, and the light was simply too big to be a parachute rocket. It can't have been a cone of light either, as we were simply too close to not detect if it was, and the townhouses have completely flat roofs and there were no people or light fixtures on the roof. The light was not high in the sky either, but was only 10-15 meters in front of us and almost at eye level, since we were standing on the highest hill. I don't remember the light as having an oblong shape, but more oval and quite large, maybe more than 2 meters in width and height. We all knew what a rocket looked like and, not least, sounded like, and the funny thing was that I just don't remember the light making any sound, it seemed to suddenly just appear out of nowhere. Luckily it couldn't have been a ball lightning as it was simply too big for this and as I said was silent. I can't imagine that ball lightning is silent, and there was no storm forecast that night. The light was round, silent and very bright, but after all not so bright that we had to shield our eyes. The light disappeared silently, as suddenly as it appeared. I don't remember my eyes being on the object when it disappeared, because it disappeared while we were running around the other side of the townhouse. Nevertheless, we were quite a few witnesses (at least 4) who all saw and experienced the same thing, and I still cannot explain what it was that we saw that day many years ago. To me anyway, the incident remains mysterious and inexplicable to this day.

I woke up at 4.21 in the night by a noise that was mostly reminiscent of driving on a VERY uneven surface. It was as if I and the house were shaking violently. At the same time, I could hear the sound of something reminiscent of a jet engine. If I have to describe the sound of the jet engine, it's something like uuuuuh and not booming like they usually are. My wife, who slept in another room, experienced the same thing, I found out in the morning.

I was on my way out to my garage when I look and spot something that looks like a very bright star, and it is also completely still.. Regards. size, it looks a lot like Venus, which I also thought it was right when I saw it. But suddenly it starts to fade and become very small and then it disappears like something you only see in movies. Just as if it accelerates very violently and disappears upwards in an easterly direction into nothing. It was unlike any shooting star I've seen before. Unfortunately, I saw it on April 1st, so my family just kind of laughs at the whole thing and of course thinks it's a joke. However, I would like to emphasize that it is not. Of course, I hope that others have seen the same thing as me and may have seen it a little before I saw it. I almost just saw it disappear. But it was a very surreal experience for me and something I won't soon forget.

I just spotted a strange white light. I just lay in my bed looking out of my attic window as I couldn't sleep due to a cold. I spot a light moving slowly and think it's probably a satellite, but it suddenly picks up speed very quickly, and then I think it's probably a shooting star, as the light also gets stronger. But a shooting star doesn't last that long at all, and the light didn't burn out, it just pulsated slowly from dark to brighter...

Standing in the garden talking on the mobile, which made me not ready to film it, but I looked at the brightest starry sky, whereupon I observed several abnormal red lights from the east "floating" across the sky, being silent, to the west . The object was triangular it looked like, from the outside the location of the red lights which was triangular, the distance from me to the object is hard to tell as I have no idea how big it is. But it seemed to be a big scar.

is out of the living room window to the south beyond the dune and dune plantation. Light reminiscent of airplane in the sky, but it was bigger and much closer. The light moved unsystematically sideways and slightly up and down. I look through binoculars and then I see that it moves. >Then I go outside to listen, but no sound except for the ocean and the light was gone. In the living room I had darkness, and there was nothing that could reflect light. We live close to the sea and there is almost no light pollution. No one lives in the area, and there is a long way to build on to the south. There are only dunes and dune plantation. Another woman in Stenbjerg saw the same light, just from a different angle, and she had also wondered.

In the sky high up to the south we saw something that looked like a star, but it was moving very quickly to the north. After a while it changed direction to the west and then again to the south, where it disappeared from view to the southwest. What surprised us was the speed at which it moved and that it changed direction all the time.

Here we go again. I have written the observation from Egå on 1 July 2012. This time it is on the beach 3 km north of Blokhus. I take a dusk walk down to the water and a few km along the beach. A light, like a flash, comes at regular intervals from the horizon to the west, and in the clear night I can see a distant top of a thundercloud, which I can subsequently see on DMI's lightning radar driving approx. 100 km off the coast. While waiting for the next flash of lightning, I look up at the Chariot and a little to the left of it, almost vertically, I observe an object that flashes 2-3 times followed by a pause where it cannot be seen, and ½ minute later it flashes again and has now moved from 85 degrees to perhaps 70 degrees to the west and again after approx. Half a minute later it is seen again via the 2-3 flashes around 60 degrees to the west. Here it is as if it "stabilises". Fine. Probably just an observation plane, with some unstable blinkers. But no. In the next ten minutes, it happens that every time the object has flashed 2-3 times, 4-5 objects light up, which shine like some of the faintest stars and move lightning fast criss-crossing each other north of the flashing object. When they stop after 3 seconds, they turn off again and then turn on again after 2-3 flashes from the other object, and they again move quickly between each other. I would think this is happening many hundreds of kilometers away. I now go home to the cottage without looking up again. At the summer house, the urge and security to look up again is present, but the phenomenon is gone. On the other hand, there will now be another object at approx. 01.45 from due west at steady speed to the east, and this object cannot be seen as a satellite shining constantly. It is only seen when it flashes once at irregular intervals of between 3 and 10 seconds. The flash is very strong, like a powerful searchlight very far up (no engine sound during both observations). Hope you can explain the observation at 01.45 with something man-made, otherwise it will soon become too burdensome to look up at the night sky. On the way home from the beach after the first sighting, I philosophized about whether it is me who has watched too many UFO videos on Youtube and is going crazy, or whether there is perhaps something brewing from outer space. But why should they come right now, while I'm alive and not 500 million years ago or maybe only in 100,000 years? Well, maybe just now, because within the last few hundred years we have really made our existence known via eternal light from the cities on the dark side of the earth, which can probably be seen with "their" equipment far away. We also show that we have a form of intelligence with our wireless communication and satellites, which can probably also pick up signals from far away.

I cycle along Pebblinge Sø along Nørre Søgade in the direction of HC Andersen Boulevard. I look to the right across the lake towards the buildings along the lake on the Nørrebro side. I see a sharp flash low in the sky above the ridges of the roofs. But have to get off the bike to take a closer look, as I can quickly see that it is not an airplane. The light coming from it is in a rotating motion under the aircraft and every time the light appears in my direction I can sense a flat and elongated shape. At first it is completely still. Then it moves slowly to the east, in a very straight line. It then changes direction very rapidly to the west, where it stands still again, and then flies in a still direction still to the west. I cycle quietly towards Søpavillionen in the same direction and keep an eye on the aircraft. When I turn right onto HC Andersens Boulevard, the aircraft disappears behind the roof of the Lake Pavilion, and when I pass the Lake Pavilion, the aircraft is gone. It was difficult for me to sense the size and distance. But had the feeling that it was quite large, but flew quite low. If you guys have a good explanation for what I saw, I'm very interested in hearing it!

Tonight, at 21.48, I made an observation. At first I saw two "approach landing lights", however I was surprised that they were yellow/orange. I went to check Flightradar24.com but there was nothing to see. When I returned there were another 6 heading E (088) with two of them flying NE (055-075). My first guess as to what it could be was that it might be a bunch of students in T-17, but it didn't fit if they had their landing lights on that it should be yellow/orange. In addition, the speed did not fit, as I estimate it to be between 250-300 knots (I am comparing here with the daily approaches of B737, A320 etc. to EKBI). As for the altitude, I estimate it to be between 4500 and 3000 ft. I took a picture with my mob., but it turned out bad, but I also took some film of it, and there might be something on it. I followed the two flying NE with binoculars and managed to see the flying objects in silhouette, and it could easily resemble an aviator, but certainly not an airliner, it was too small for that. It could be an F-16, I'm thinking in that order of magnitude, but what surprised me the most was that there was no sound!? There were also no anti-collision lights, beacons, strobes or navigation lights. In closing, I just want to mention that I don't believe in little green men. I'm a big aviation geek and study astronomy, astrophysics and theoretical quantum physics. I have reasonable control over various satellites such as Envisat, Iridium and ISS. But I am now quite convinced that it was something man-made, approx. 1000 m above ground. With the hope that you can, and will, save the thread for me, I want to say a thousand thanks in advance.

Coordinates from Krak: WGS84:N 55° 39.870', E 12° 35.437'WGS 84 - decimal:55.66450, 12.59062. I have made a habit of going for an evening walk, especially on starry nights like tonight. I was looking at the Chariot (Big Bear) and Cassiopeia when I heard a "passenger plane" idling, sounds you often hear in Amager! I can't say for sure that it was a non-terrestrial object, but it looked mysterious, along with the apparent airliner noise. The objects were moving in a southerly direction and were bright orange, or amber if you will. There were three of them flying in a triangle formation, each of the objects consisting of three orange lights in a row. Above IslandsBrygge Metrostation they split, two of them took a more westerly course and the third banked east. I am a bit surprised by the sight, as I believe that aviation regulations dictate that all aircraft must carry two white flashing lights on the wings, and a red one on the back, as well as an orange one under the fuselage. It is not unusual to see planes at Amager, not even in the evening, but I cannot explain this in any way. I hope Ii can shed some light on the matter, and what it actually was I saw! Because I thought I saw :)
A luminous ball, larger than a tennis ball, came quite quickly from south to north. Its direction was descending and no sound.

A steady light drifts from east to northwest. I call my wife who is standing in the kitchen. She comes and sees the strange light which is now spinning around to the south (at that time I have opened the window to the east where I saw the light) No sound like a machine or helicopter, completely quiet. The light now becomes weaker and rises in a circle from south to east and further to the north. Now I get my photo rapport, but now it's over. The light was like a dot and fainter at the end as we saw it. We have many airplanes and occasionally helicopters during the day and evening, but they fly with flashing lights and further away, not with constant lights. We have lived on the 7th floor in Hjallese for 5 years and have never seen anything similar, I have always kept an eye on that. It wasn't cloudy. Distance is difficult, maybe 500 m from. Sound would be audible with the window open.

I'm not much of a night owl, as on weekdays I have to get up quite early, but since we had guests until quite late on Saturday evening, it wasn't until after midnight that I came out to walk the dog on the usual evening route. (So the night of Sunday). After approx. 10 minutes Sometimes I become aware of some yellow/orange lights flying across the sky at a good speed. Between 6 and 10 pieces were there, I would think, and there was not a sound to be heard. At first I think that it is some of these luminous balloons that are sent up for weddings etc., but then come to think of the wind direction, which is quite strong from south/west to north/east and these "balloons" fly approx. stick south, so I can't quite get it to fit.

I'm out for an evening walk with the dogs and choose to turn up a dark side road - away from the glare of the streetlights. Out of the corner of my eye I notice something moving. I look up at the sky and see a large white glowing ball which almost "vibrates". It stays the same height the whole time I see it. First slowly across the sky, then it stops abruptly and hangs completely still. Suddenly it takes off and disappears behind the trees! I couldn't hear any sounds and it didn't flash either. I have seen many drones in the dark and this was like nothing I have ever seen before! The entire period lasted approx. 3 minutes

Thought first. that it was a plane.. But when it sort of reached the point where the sun set an hour ago (I guess), it turned north... As it sort of changed direction, the light sort of silently slipped off of it.. I think it was the sun shining at the bottom, it was very similar both in the way the light disappeared on and on, the play of colors of the light when it was there.. When the light disappeared, you could suddenly see that it was completely black and absolutely nothing light was on... I was inside looking for my camera, but couldn't find it.. And when I came out, I could see it disappear quietly into some dark clouds... It generally flew very calmly, softly and slowly and did not immediately look oblong like a normal plane, more high and compact in that... My father, who is VERY skeptical in this field (am I myself), he says, would have a hard time saying what it was, but that he would guess a helicopter... But that at the same time he thought it was very strange that he couldn't hear it, since it didn't seem like it was that far away, and that it looked very strange, and had a very strange flight path to the north..

I come driving in my truck and film a sunrise, which is really beautiful. I snap away and all of a sudden an object comes into view, both on camera and in the sky, but it's in a split second that I send all the pictures to you. Hope I can find out what it is?

I hardly know what to write, it feels stupid. I stood out front and looked at the sky, there was something in the sky that was very beautiful and shiny, I thought, hold up a nice star, so inside my head I thought that it could move (I don't know, why I think this) then first it moves from side to side just as quietly. I think at first that it must be something with my eyes. Then thinking in my head, it can move up and down instead, to check if it was my eyes. And then fuck me if it doesn't start flying up and down. Here the hairs on my arms stand up and I think this can't be right. Then I think it will come down here to me, where it gets bigger and bigger, as if it is getting closer. I run into the house and slam the door, and I'm super scared.
I see what looks like two objects and it looks like they each have two lights. It turns bright white/yellow, but I also sense a reddish tinge. Immediately I think it was satellites, but I don't know

Observed a strong orange-yellow luminous object, in the shape of a distant Sct. Bonfire that moved across the sky at the same pace as an airplane that is far away. The object moved at a constant speed and light intensity until it approx. 40 seconds into the sighting, the speed and light intensity decreased. After approx. 60 seconds of observing the light in the glow of the city lights. Had it been dark, it would have been visible for a longer time. The given position is measured from Google Earth. The beginning and end bearings are measured via Google Earth together with bearings for trees and houses in the area. Don't think this could have been a satellite as the speed was greatly reduced as the light got weaker. Considers it likely that it was a plane with afterburners that made a course change at the end of the observation. The time indication is accurate within +/- 1 minute, as the observation was concluded with a look at the mobile phone clock.

I come driving - it goes slightly uphill and there are 2 sharp turns. Above me, outside the car's windshield, I see that there is a plane on its way. I think it was incredible how low it flies and how far it has to land. Then it's like it lifts up a bit higher as it comes around the side of the car and I can't make it fit at all with it being a plane - there are no wings, no tail, no windows or retracted wheels ... moreover, the material is completely matte and the shape is like a "cone" or a face with a long nose. ... thinking what the hell it is.... it's way too big to be a drone. (Looks like my car could be in that 10x....well but the road curves and I'm close to hitting an oncoming traffic as I reach the main road and turn south. From my side window I see “ the vessel" disappear at great speed - and without a sound. To the east. From behind it looks like it is a whole round shape, luminous from inside the center evenly distributed on the back. The whole thing took about 1 min at most.

It concerns three objects with approx. half a minute apart. First I see an object coming from the north direction, it looks like a flare, light with a reddish glow around followed by two more lights. They cannot be high up as it is cloudy and they fly at the same speed. I have recorded some video clips of the objects. It must be said that it is difficult to both keep the camera still and find proper focus. But happy to send the clips to you. They are in Mp4 format.

At approx. 22.40 I stayed in my living room, which had a clear view of open fields to the south-southwest towards Brabrand, True and Lyngby. I spotted a very bright and clear light in the sky above the horizon. At first thought it was a car's headlights, but the light was 100 times brighter and in the sky close to the horizon. Could hardly bear to be looked at at first with that general. eye, but the light was somewhat dimmed, and then shone down and spread out to both sides. The light also changed colors a few times, from dim red to strong red and was continuous for a few minutes at a time, before changing back to bright light. All of a sudden there were approx. 10 small slightly oval objects in the sky, they moved very quickly and like in jerks, the small ones were completely dark, but since it was a summer night they could be clearly seen. The big round with the light was completely silent in the sky. Suddenly the small ones were gone and only the big one remained and just as suddenly it and all the light was gone too. I had woken up my partner at the time, because this was too good and at the same time too strange to experience alone - so we were two adults who stood and watched this inexplicable thing.

Saw a shiny spot which basically didn't move at first. The size was about, like a small pea in an outstretched arm. There was no sound and it could be seen for a few hours I'll shoot on. After a while it started VERY slowly moving west. It was completely clear and lit up like a giant star. Could it be the ISS?

I laid out on the sofa on the terrace last night and know there are opportunities to see shooting stars. Not usually something I do in, but it was hot in the house, and cooler outside. It's not quite dark yet for me to think I can see shooting stars, so after some time on my back on the sofa I'm considering going inside. But to the left, out on the horizon, a white/yellow "ball" appears. It's not big and seems like it's far away. It rises from the horizon into the sky. Faster than a drone, Chinese lamp, or anything else I've thought of it could be. I follow it with my eyes, and after a while it seems as if it is as high up as the stars. Equally faint and small, yet luminous. I think I'm going crazy and look at all the other stars that twinkle but are completely still. This one moves in circles. Not a specific pattern, but just randomly around. I think it is affected by the weather so high up, but it does not disappear. I don't believe in goblins or aliens, but I have to ask my girlfriend if she can come out to look, but she's breastfeeding and has to cuddle the baby. I try to take a video but it's so far away that my mobile can't capture it. I keep looking and call my brother. He lives 10 km away and wonders if he can see it. It's just too hard for me to explain where it is in the sky, and since it doesn't move very much, and is so small, we give up. It does not move over the horizon, but just dances around now and then, and far, far away. I go in after a little while, and today I have to write about my report, as I am very interested in hearing if others have discovered something similar in the sky.

properties.Colors: hvid/gullig lidt større end en satellit
properties.content: Sat with my legs against the water, at the nursing home on Østerstrand (without a compass on) with my friend and mother for the 2nd day with shooting stars. They live in town and saw nothing yesterday, so left today. Around. 23.30 ± minutes I see another satellite, but a little yellower and wider and slower. Cassiopeia is approx. 30° to the left of the site. Well, it stops for a minute or so, turns a few 20-30 to the right. Flying straight 10 cm WTF (took a ruler in the outstretched arm, measure 10 cm holds the finger, until friend watches, it flies 5 cm closer to 2 stars They formed a triangle, at the last position. At the 1st stop, was it almost as far away. (Canis Minor was APPARENTLY a little to the right of the place). Unfortunately, we had already sat for 20 minutes on a bench with our necks back, so I was discouraged and had to go home. Do you have an explanation for me?

I see a white glowing circle coming flying at a relatively low altitude. At first I think it's a satellite, but then I realize it's flying too low. And then it is a completely white, luminous ball. Then I expect to hear engine noise from a plane, but it is completely silent. Next I notice that it is not flying slowly and lazily like an airplane approaching for landing. It looks like it's bouncing up and down a bit every now and then. But it could be an optical illusion. I realize it's a UFO and run in for my cell phone. I'm trying to take a picture, but since I'm not wearing reading glasses, I can't see if it'll come to anything. Then I set my iPhone to video and try to film the glowing circle as it flies towards Sweden. It doesn't make a sound and it flies relatively fast. Eventually it disappears into the horizon. It all takes 2-3 minutes. I have not been able to confirm whether anyone else saw the flying object - and whether it could be a drone. But drones probably also make a sound for approx. 500 meters altitude.

I observed an orange light, which I initially thought was the light of a distress signal. However, it was less sharp in intensity than an emergency flare, and the height above the horizon could not really match an emergency signal either. After a few seconds the light began to rise upwards and to the left, and soon after it was 2 lights with a fairly constant distance moving. The movement was not constant, but interrupted by small pauses, and sometimes the movement even went slightly backwards, almost in small jerks. After approx. 30 seconds later the light disappears, but is replaced almost immediately afterwards by another 2 lights, which behave exactly like the first 2, but with the difference that before the 2 disappear they are supplemented by another 1 light, which also follows the other 2 out to the left , but with a greater distance. After a few minutes, another light appears, exactly where the others started. This light remains alone and behaves like the others. In total, I thus saw 6 points of light disappear. During the process, what my experience tells me, an airplane comes over the horizon, from west to east, with flashing lights, and it may well be that the pilot or the passengers may have seen the lights that I saw. I can best describe the starting point on the horizon with the help of the Chariot. If you take the opposite end of the "handle" of the Chariot, there are 2 stars that draw an almost vertical line. If you continue this line towards the ground, it is close to the place where the lights showed their appearance, although starting a little way up in the sky.

I'm heading to bed. When I lie down and look out the window to enjoy the bright night sky and the moon, I suddenly see a big light (yellow) in the sky in the southern direction. At first it looks like a star, but it moves. I jump out of bed and go out on the terrace and see that the "star" is moving in an eastern direction. Wakes up my husband, who comes out and takes a look. It moves at a reasonably fast pace (faster than an airplane) and the height is approx. the same as small planes. It makes no sound. We agree that this is something out of the ordinary. I have never seen a UFO, but am absolutely convinced that we are regularly visited.

My brother and his two children saw yesterday 20-11-18 at 19:30 in the Koktvedvej area by the Hånbæk blocks in Frederikshavn - a black triangular unidentified plane with a light in each of the three corners. Information from my brother: It was approx. 100 meters up and seemed bigger than a normal plane. It made a humming pulsating sound, and flew in a peculiar manner, which my brother described as being slightly on edge. It flew over the Musikkvarteret, west of the Hånbæk blocks and continued towards Hjørring. My brother thought the lights on the craft looked very man made.

Friday evening I grab my binoculars to admire the unusually large "Jupiter" I saw toward the SSV. It was NOT Jupiter, and it was under a light cloud cover with almost blinding white light, like laser led lights. After looking at it a bit, I called my neighbor's wife, who didn't pick it up, but called back, and I asked her to go outside and see if she could also see the UFO hanging out there to the south. She could, and as she immediately said, we are not alone, but what is he doing up there. We probably looked at it for five to ten minutes. It floated a little higher above us, and she could see it flashing red (I couldn't, I have rather poor night vision, where the red light of the windmills often disappears for me), it also seemed to split in two. We saw a plane go high above it from approx. Hanstholm towards Aalborg, and clearly heard the aircraft engine. No sound from the UFO. Occasionally it would fade out for a second, then reappear. Then it disappeared a little behind the clouds, which lay on the horizon, but then it shone behind the clouds, just as when the Moon can light up behind the clouds. Although the small light was only one-fifth to one-tenth of the new moon's sigil, it lit up like a full moon behind the clouds. And then it came out again. A single mini dot of light stood out and disappeared towards Løgstør/Livø. We froze miserably, so Solveig went in and finished tucking the children, and I put on a flight suit and tried to photograph it with my late husband's Iphone 13 S. It took 3 seconds. , and I kept it on a birdhouse, but it just turned out to be a white blob. Then it disappeared - faded away again. It turned out that the neighbor's wife took her 12-year-old boy out, and he saw it too. Before it completely faded away I managed to call my neighbor on the other side and got her to go out and watch it, I'm not entirely sure if her boyfriend got to see it. At eleven I just had to go for the last walk with the dog, and then it hung out there again. Now, however, all the houses were switched off, and I didn't call anyone, but went a little down the road, and up a country road, and now it wasn't heading south, but heading north, it disappeared - and a mini light streaked north. Saturday morning when I got up at 6.25 it hung outside again - approx. those 30 - 45 degrees above the horizon, and in binoculars I could clearly see the red flash, it appeared as if it was turning clockwise, and the red came out, but also white all the time. I texted the neighbor's husband when I knew he was up there milking. Then I turned and made coffee and oatmeal and when I came back it was gone and my text hadn't been sent. It must be said that I have been thrown by my WIFI many times since 3-10. Well, a little talk back and forth gave that the hunter who has the hunt does not use drones to hunt marten. Training of Ukrainians takes place in England, and ends on 11-11. So there was an international militia meeting in Aalborg last week... could they have played with drones over a field in Vust, 9690 Fjerritslev? Saturday night very cloudy, and then nothing. Sunday morning (today) I got up at 6.25, looked out and up: AND the whole sky was lit up by, I said 30, but there were maybe only 20 bright UFOs, the closest ones flashing clearly (without binoculars) with red. The neighbor's husband called at five past seven and asked where she was - I asked if he had NOW seen them - no he had just seen a lot of stars. By then it had started to lighten and there were probably only two distinct ones left. I think his eyes, coming straight from inside the strong neon light in the milking shed, had a hard time seeing them? I don't know if he saw them. I had also called the hunter I spoke to the day before, but he is in Zealand and working until Tuesday. I guess that's all I can tell you now and here. But at least I get up early tomorrow!!

When I had to draw the curtain in the room to the northwest on the 1st floor, I saw a strong/sharp yellowish/white light that streaked across the sky. Soon after, another similar light appeared at some distance from the first. It repeated itself so that I saw a total of 4 such lights streak across the sky. No sound at all. Always the same distance between the lights and thus the same speed. I opened the window to register any Sound - but there was no sound. I therefore ruled out general. Airplane. The height is difficult to judge. The house's eaves prevent me from following the further progress of the lights. I chose to look at the lights while they were there, and when apparently no more came, I hurried down into the living room to possibly follow them from there, but then there was nothing to see. This is my observation - whether there have been more lights before "my" lights, I can't say anything about.

First a flash like a flash light. Then nothing for a few seconds. So a small white spot that first flies very slowly across the sky, then picks up speed and is gone in a few seconds. The first flash is to the east approx. 60 degrees up, disappears to the southwest and is gone at a height of about 30 degrees up.

For approx. 17 – 18 years ago (1983-84? - 1983 is most likely!) I experienced my first (and so far only) UFO. It was a cold and clear morning, the 13th of November, an hour before it got light. I was out driving with newspapers in Kgs. Lyngby and was on my way over the motorway bridge (Klampenborgvej!) when on the horizon, over Copenhagen, I saw a bright red light hanging completely still in the air. It was somewhat larger than a star and with a clarity like a taillight on a car. It hung approx. three finger widths above the city. There was no flicker and it just hung there, completely still, there was simply not a sound to be heard. I stopped my bike and stood there for approx. 5 minutes (I enjoyed the silence and the pause in the newspaper distribution). I wondered if it was Mars, but the position didn't match, so I was a bit confused. (I am an amateur astronomer and at the time in question was associated with KAF (Copenhagen Astronomical Association). Suddenly the light began to move very slowly, obliquely up to the left from my position, which has been east until it reached a position above Gentofte, where it , without stopping, changed direction at a sharp angle and flew in a straight line to a point above Jægersborg, where it changed direction to the east again. All the while it simultaneously moved north towards my position. The light changed direction 6 times in total and had finally reaching a position almost over my head. It had grown surprisingly little in comparison to the fact that it seemed to be coming towards me, just high up in the air. When it reached the final point over Jægersborg, it flew in a big arc back again towards Copenhagen where it disappeared on the horizon. The whole affair must have taken a maximum of 10 minutes in total. I contacted SUFOI the same evening (a local watchman I think) where I was told that I had observed a helicopter (!!!). Nothing with maybe, but a helicopter, like that! The person was, to put it mildly, very rude, as if he just wanted to get rid of me in a hurry, and I remember thinking that he might as well just rush me to a certain place and hung up. I later regretted not going further with my observation, but I will make up for that here.

As we drive on the motorway and approach Herlev, out of the window we can see 2 yellow lights in the sky to the right of Herlev hospital. They were high in the sky. One a bit higher than the other. Now we were driving, so it looked like they were standing still in the sky. There were 4 of us in the car and we saw them all. Got off the freeway at the first stop and drove back but we couldn't find the lights again

We are 3 people sitting on a south-facing balcony and earlier in the evening noticed what we assume was a planet, relatively low on the horizon (sea). Suddenly I notice 2 bright lights in the same place, and make my guests aware of it. All 3 of us manage to see the bright lights before they suddenly fade. I expect to see red and green flashes as I assumed the sight was landing lights, but they don't. My one guest thinks she can see the now much weaker light taking a new and fast direction upwards.

I was going out to smoke in the evening. I therefore took my usual route down through the city, where I enjoyed the view of the sky and the beauty of the city out towards the fjord. On the way I stop at the theater, I have to grab my lighter. I light my smoke when I spot what I assumed was the light of an airplane heading for the airport. It dawns on me shortly after that the light doesn't blink, it stays on as opposed to bright and moves quite slowly. At first I thought it was a satellite, but quickly changed my mind when I noticed the speed increased tremendously. At that time, the light is on its way behind some buildings between Budolfi Plads and Bleggårdsgangen. I therefore wandered over to Bleggårdsgangen, where the view out to the direction in which the light moved was sufficiently open for me to observe further. However, the light had disappeared when I got there. The light was strong, but not because it was shining down on me. The light was solid, i.e. not see through, seemed like a white pearl floating in the water. The light was bigger than a star, it was thick, like a ball or pearl. I didn't think the light was very high in the sky, judging by the thickness of the light that made it seem like it was close.

Did anyone else besides me see the mysterious light across the sky in Midtsjælland? The light hung behind the clouds, just as the Moon would, beyond Køge, seen from Haslev. It then moved over Haslev and out towards Ringsted with lightning speed, the distance covered in less than a second, only to return and hang over Køge ten seconds later and then disappear to the west at the same speed.....

I was out in the garden with my 3 children and husband. The children were playing with their new luminous toys. We suddenly saw a luminous ball, coming flying across the sky without sound, without flashing little lights. It flew fast, but not as fast as an airplane.

Went with a friend on the street, Birkmosevej in Rødovre, and observed an orange/red ball flying across the sky. There were no sounds, no flashes from the "dim". It was high up, faster than a normal plane. It quickly disappeared into the horizon. This repeated three times, a new ball appearing at regular intervals and flying in the same direction. After this I turned around and went the opposite way, after which the process repeated itself twice more, what I observed. This time, however, it flew in a slightly different direction ... I met three other people who at that time had stopped in the street and stood observing the sky. We talked about what it could be but had no possible solutions. After that I went home and chose not to look up at the sky any more!

Just went out to check if there was any potential to photograph the NLC, then lit a cigarette and headed north as there is a slightly better view from a nearby lake than from where I live. Halfway to the lake I look behind and see this bright orange glowing object coming flying under the cloud cover. It was quite large, and had no sound, but was (apparently) pentagonal, so don't think it was a balloon. It flew swiftly across the sky and disappeared into a cloud. It just as quickly reappeared and disappeared. The evening has been extremely quiet at ground level, and the clouds have not moved at anything like the speed the object was traveling at. I tried to film it with my iphone, but the quality is just too poor... it's just a bright dot. Why didn't I just bring my DSLR in the first place?!? There is probably a reasonable explanation for that, but I think now that it seemed strange.

I stood looking out my kitchen window and saw what I first thought was a plane. It was much higher up than usual though, and didn't seem to have any actual length? It was very bright/white and shiny. I followed the object until it disappeared over the roof. I knew it would come up again on the living room side right after, so I grabbed my Nikon D600 ff camera, with a Sigma 50mm f 1.4 lens attached. Unfortunately, I don't have any zoom, but only fixed optics. When the object appeared on the living room side, the object has split into several similar objects. I counted 7 when I was photographing, but can see from the pictures that there were up to 12 pieces. It must be said that I have observed unexplained things in the sky before, but never anything that comes close to this! The objects followed a path where I could see that they were flying higher and higher, towards space. Pure guess, must be 20-30 km up? One thing that struck me was that the objects changed shape? or rotated synchronously so that you could see the shape of these. That is, that all objects looked alike at all times. I know it sounds like pure science fiction, but as far as I'm concerned, in my world, it is conclusive proof that "UFOs" exist!! I have all the images in raw RAW, but have also converted them to jpg. for the sake of convenience. If you are interested in these, can I forward them? I can't really see where they can be attached? I managed to take 18 photos of the sighting and remembered to drive with a high aperture for the depth of field. Unfortunately, I didn't get to check the speed in the rush, so some of the pictures have motion blur. Others, however, are very fine, and you can sense shape etc. Fortunately, in some of the pictures there is a little house on one side, and a couple of clouds in the foreground, so you can sense some aspect ratio. I hope to God that there are others who have seen my observation, so I don't come across as completely crazy.. Compass direction etc. is found with the help of my IPad, where I use the program Skyview. Whether these are the correct "compass directions" I have written, I have no idea, but otherwise I can easily point out a direction, etc.

Was on my way home from sailing with a boat on a trailer, so couldn't park right away. Practice Moved lightning fast across the northern sky, faster than airplanes, suddenly stood still. Had to follow the road 90 degrees around and lost sight for 6-7 minutes before we could park and find the camera. Now it was in the south-south-east where the sky was darker, and here I caught some bill. Soon after, it disappeared, like turning down a dimmer switch. Couldn't keep the camera completely still, unfortunately. Should have just put it on video. At that speed, it can't be a hot air balloon.

I am sitting in bus 400S on the route ml H. Taastrup and Ballerup at around 18:30. I see from the window a dark gray object hanging/floating low in the sky. The object is elongated, looks almost like a beam. A moment later I spot a smaller and more indistinct round object slanting above the "beam". The view is occasionally disturbed when the bus drives past trees along the road, but when there are openings the object is seen in the same position and motionless. This takes place through approx. 10 minutes until the bus turns off from the ring road. At first I think it could be a balloon, like those that are sometimes used for advertising; but there are no colors or logos etc. on it. Haven't tried to film as the bus is moving a bit too fast.

I have been carrying this story for a long time, but it has not left my mind and is as clear as the day I experienced it. There are 3 of us standing in my yard and talking over a beer. It is dark and the sky is starry clear except for a single cloud formation consisting of 2 cigar-shaped clouds, very sharply defined. The clouds were spaced apart, one half above the other. In the upper cloud there was a round light, strongest in the middle, but transparent. As the clouds slowly move east I notice that the light follows, precisely positioned and fixed in the upper cloud. I point out the cloud to my two mates, who at first don't give it a real chance. Suddenly the light begins to move within the cloud, and you can clearly see that the light is moving on the cloud on the side of the light it is moving towards. I eagerly pointed it out for my friends to see, and just as they turn around, it takes off, leaving a black streak in a black sky. It goes so fast that you can't possibly follow it with your eyes. But out of the cloud this craft left a "puff" of cloud. We all saw this happen, and with 100% certainty it wasn't a cone of light, an airplane, a weather balloon, or anything like that. I'm absolutely certain it was intelligent life. Barely 2 weeks later on New Year's Eve around At 18 we had to demonstrate some fireworks for my two boys, and again I, my brother and my nephew see the same spot of light in the clouds. As if a transparent vessel is on top of the clouds, or rather hiding behind them. I fetch my neighbor, who I have told and my experience from the yard and get him out into the street and see the phenomenon, - he thinks it is a cone of light from something on the ground, but it is cloudy and foggy that day and no cone to see, only the round spot which in this case stands firmly fixed in the sky. When we look up again it is gone, but 20 seconds. afterwards it appears again a little further out on the horizon over the Little Belt, between the coastline at Fredericia and the Little Belt Bridge. This time I see it "lying" above the clouds and going from indistinct light to clear and distinct. It then hangs there for the next few minutes and then suddenly disappears again. These experiences were quite mind-numbing, because I am neither crazy nor schizophrenic or anything. etc., and I can say with absolute certainty that these were vessels that are somehow able to appear only as light, transparent light.

properties.Colors: sølvgrå med hvide og røde lys
properties.content: My husband was in the car and was on his way home. He saw the object in the sky and could see it for a long time, in front of him. When he stopped for a red light, the object was almost directly above the car, high up. It flew over the car, pulled up and sped up and flew away. My husband had to twist in the driver's seat to follow it with his eyes. He got a good look at it.

Saturday night at 01.45 I went for a dog walk at Husumvej in Brønshøj, with a friend and her dog. We were walking through our yard and I was walking with my head down towards the grass.... the yard is a little dark... and the sky is completely starry.... well but I looked down and in one of my glasses... I saw a very very bright almost flashing light... I looked up to the sky and saw the most amazing thing I have ever seen in my life. I believe in life in space... meen has never seen more than millions of shooting stars.... as well as satellites.... I have no doubt.... something flew over me... and it was not a shooting star... not even a satellite... a thick thick jet of almost fire flew across the sky... at an insane speed... and then ended with an almost... poof... but in the puff... was a sharp.... green light... and it was gone.... my friend didn't get to see it at all...!!! I'm in seven minds... really wish she had seen it too.... but it was really fast.... oops oops then sat the rest of the night looking up at the beautiful starry sky hoping that just a little glimpse again...

Was a nursing student at Glostrup Hospital, lived on the 8th floor in the student accommodation, with a good view. One afternoon, I sit at my desk and do homework. I look out the window and see 3 very bright "stars". I think it must be a plane, I get up and go to the window to take a closer look at the "stars". At the same time, one of the stars first moves at great speed, then changes direction at an angle of approx. 120 degrees. I was scared, well aware that this is not normal. The other 2 "stars" also suddenly flew at angles very fast. I went to my desk and wrote, date, time and drew what I had seen on a piece of paper. I ran into my neighbor in the dorm to make her see and understand what I had experienced. Unfortunately, there was nothing to see in the sky from her window. I have thought a lot about this experience in all the years, aging, neither before nor since seen anything like it.

I'm pretty sure I saw a UFO this morning. I looked out of my window approx. 07:00, and then a strange star. It looked like a star that twinkled/blinked and then "jumped" around in a circle a bit sporadically. Sometimes little stars came out of it for a split second. Unfortunately I didn't film it. I would like to know if it can be explained in another way? It was as if it "beamed" around the sky.

I first observed 1 red-orange round spot with a very diffuse outer diameter, moving in a westerly direction. Shortly after (about 15-30 seconds another appeared). Number 2 followed the first, and before they disappeared, they appeared to be moving northward, for they became smaller and smaller, and more blurred. I don't know about the weather. was hazy. The speed wasn't very fast and I thought it was a plane at first, but I couldn't see any lights flashing.

Walking the dog at 6. The dog has to pee, and I stand looking up at the sky when I see a bright light coming flying. At first think it's a satellite, but can see it flying towards what I think is a star. The light gets weaker the closer it gets to the star, and suddenly it has disappeared into what I think is a star. But then what I think is a star flies on and disappears.

We saw an elongated, luminous object approx. 3 kilometers away in the air, which was on its way at a fairly high speed, first upwards, then obliquely downwards to disappear behind trees. At first we thought it was a plane, but a lot of people come over here, and it wasn't a plane with that direction of flight.

Stood by the kitchen window and observed the night sky. I am incredibly interested in astronomy, and therefore know a lot about the phenomena of the sky. I live in an apartment, and can only look up at the sky from my backyard. While I stand looking at the Chariot, an orange round ball suddenly floats very slowly across the sky. It is so close that I can see that it really glows. It stays on for approx. 20 seconds, when it flies straight up into the atmosphere with an indescribable speed, And out of nowhere it stops and stands almost still in the air. A short second later, it sets off at high speed across the sky again. No tail, just a bright orange light like it's been showing all along. At the beginning of the year, when I was out for an evening walk with my husband and daughter, I observed something that was almost similar. Then we lived in a small village 25 km outside Aalborg. There was snow and quite a beautiful starry sky. When we reach a green area where there are chalk hills and fields, we suddenly see an orange ball hovering about 6-10 km above our heads. It had no tail, it was not a plane, a hot air balloon or a Chinese launched balloon. Only a large orange ball that flew at a very slow speed. This observation lasted for almost 6 minutes. In a split second, this object also flew up into the atmosphere at an unimaginable speed, stood still at a certain point, and disappeared at high speed in a direction to the southeast.

Standing in the garden and 3 lights appear, moving across the sky from the north and due south across me. There is not a sound from the 3 lights, which move at a calm pace and maintain the same distance from each other.

Hello.. On Sunday 12 August, my girlfriend and I were out looking at the night sky from our garden in Elsinore, as there were supposed to be many shooting stars... Approx. At 23.30 we see an object coming floating at a good speed across the sky, it was definitely not a shooting star or a satellite, there was no light on it and no tail, it was just a gray spot that flew over us from the north-east. It turned and flew in another direction to the south and then turned again and flew in a third direction to the northwest where it disappeared out of sight... We thought it was quite mysterious and talked about what it could be. We agreed that it couldn't be a bird either, as it was higher up than the clouds.. A quarter of an hour passed, then it came again from the west, and finally it flew over us, turned off to the south and disappeared behind the roof. Since it had no lights on, we could only see it because it was gray against the night sky, which was black. The way it turned, an airplane wouldn't be able to, it was quite sharp in its turns... And again, it had NO lights on... Have you heard of others who have seen the same phenomenon in the night sky in Helsingør in night? Guess we weren't the only ones out to watch the meteor shower.

Blinking, stationary, flying object hangs over the center of Skagen. Various light patterns. Blue, white, yellow and red. Possibly drifting but has been hanging for over 30 min now. Not normal for regular drone.

We are four adults sitting on a late summer evening with clear stars, and I love shooting stars and always look up and look for them. But on the other hand, we see something else. Somewhere in the sky a light starts in the southeast "out of the blue" and "flies" southwest for a certain distance and then disappears. But the funny thing is that the same light in color and strength then after a little moment reappears - exactly in the same place where it started. Then the light "flies" the same path or path across the sky as it had done before, and disappears in the same place again. This continues at least 10 times. Maybe 20. None of us could understand what was happening, what it was. Was it a drone? A satellite? It looked like a star or satellite in brightness and was probably not a searchlight from a lighthouse or something like that. We have not found out what it is, and we cannot rationally find an explanation for the phenomenon we all clearly experienced and were all puzzled about. Wondering what it was?

It was right around the August 1999 solar eclipse, either a few days before or after. I was 13 years old and alone at home that afternoon. It was partly cloudy. I stood on the balcony and looked, as I used to do once in a while, and then caught sight of it. It was completely chrome. Like a coin, I could see the sunlight reflected in it. I would estimate it to have been approx. 2-400 meters up. It "hung" slightly askew in the air, towards the left, and floated completely still. I stood and looked at it for about 10-15 minutes without anything happening. Then I went down to the laundry cellar and put a machine on, and when I came back up approx. 10 minutes later it was gone. Unfortunately, since there were no cameras in mobile phones then, I unfortunately never got to take a picture. The shape is hard to describe, but it most resembled a bowler hat. but more streamlined. And then without a hole in the bottom. I don't want to gamble too much on the size, but the size of a couple of cars is probably not an understatement.

Sunday 26 July 2015 around 22.55 I see something strange. I am standing in my kitchen on the second floor - the light is off - the window is open - and I can hear the usual traffic noise from Hovedvejen/Roskildevej. Suddenly, out of nowhere, I see a strange light coming from the south – down around Brøndby Stadium – in a northerly direction. It looks somewhat like "gaslight" in that it flickers between blue and green. It moves horizontally across the sky – it neither loses nor gains altitude – and then it is completely silent. As it passes my window I can see it has an oval shape. You have to make an effort to spot it, it is surrounded by some white dots. It is probably 50-100 meters above the ridge of the neighboring property - which is also a 2-storey dwelling. It seems to follow a route up along Vestvolden/Motorring 3. After passing my window, but before it seems to reach Jyllingevej, the light disappears abruptly - and it becomes invisible. The episode lasts 5-10 seconds. Then I look out of the window to the south and immediately spot a plane taking off from Kastrup and heading south. The wing lights of an airliner are clearly visible over a distance of more than 15 km. The "gas light" I had just witnessed was subdued - it did not sting the eyes in any way. Could the white spots I saw encircling the oval object be some sort of heat shield? It is difficult to say anything about the size – it could be anything from 6-12 meters long and 2-3 meters high.

UFO or what! Out running when I observe a powerful ball of light. I think it was strange how low that airplane flies though. Soon after, two more come with exactly the same light intensity, the distance between the three spheres is relatively equal. However, it is not low-passing, as first assumed, since there is no sound wave to register, so it must be something extremely high. I can subsequently hear a plane at an altitude of 10 km. Wonder what it was, haven't seen anything like it! Dogs in the village barked!

Walked around the garden and looked up at a glowing object that was moving at quite a high speed in a criss-cross pattern. Once in a while it stopped, after which it flashed maybe 5-10 times and then the parents crossed. This it repeated as long as it was visible. A shame it was so cloudy have published it on but mobile phone.

Have here July 4, 2012 approx. at 23.59 sat on my balcony and looked out over Øresund, where I observed what I thought was a plane heading towards me. When the light didn't get any closer, I took my binoculars and saw an almost round ball that seemed to consist of "small luminous diamonds with a larger luminous dot at the edge". Called my girlfriend as I couldn't understand what I was seeing. She could only note the same. After approx. 5 to 8 minutes it was suddenly gone.

Thursday night, at approx. 01:00, I stood out on the terrace to watch for shooting stars. It was a night full of stars in the sky. I had been looking to the north, turned to see if shooting stars would appear from the south. I am completely speechless, because in the south-eastern sky hangs a luminous yellow ball, approx. 8 mm measured with fingers. As I stand healing myself, noting that there are stars in the sky around it, another small ball comes sliding from the same direction, growing to the same size as the first. The object is positioned below the first object. There is some distance between the objects. The second ball sort of gave a little, as if adjusting its position before finding its location under the first object. Seeing these two objects standing in the sky approx. 4 seconds, after which the first disappears back into the sky. I see the sphere shrink - from a large sphere to a tiny dot, impossibly fast. The second ball disappears in the same way and just as quickly soon after. The whole session probably lasted 12-18 seconds.
Triangular object. Like a migratory bird formation.

Mathias went out into the garden to pee, it was completely dark at the time, when suddenly a flat, luminous disc appeared, emerging above the trees in a southern direction. It stood still for approximately 20-30 seconds, after which it continued in a westerly direction, out along the headland, in the direction of the lighthouse. There were no sounds associated with the sighting, but when it suddenly picked up speed, from the area a little outside the garden where it was hovering, there was a hissing sound, from the object. Of details can be mentioned, it was shaped like two joined plates, or very flat bowls, the upper part was bright red, almost like flames, the lower part was bright blue, pulsating, and in the assembly of the discs, it shone pink/white, all the way around. On top it had what looked like a blue antenna that stuck up a bit. On one side, a window could clearly be seen, with light in it. On the underside, 3-4 dome-shaped objects could be seen, which stuck out a little in relation to the rest of the vessel. Combined with the stars behind, and other various lights, from airplanes etc. was this something completely unique that the son saw in the sky.

Driving east from Karup towards Kjellerup off Årestrupvej. Have spotted a very sharp star that is roughly straight ahead of my line of sight (almost due east), which I can spot just above the treetops (15-20 degrees?). The road goes almost straight the whole time, but at one point there is a small soft bend to the left and back to the right. Then, all of a sudden, the star appears to be moving, and the light begins to resemble the landing lights of a long-distance plane. So I'm coming to believe that it must be a plane that is on its way to land in Karup instead. Coming closer and actually now expecting that I can see the plane close up, and see tail rudder etc., but am very surprised, as I think the object is very still in the air - almost floating like that. I drive past the object on my right, and I want to shoot for it to be 300-500 meters away. As I remember it, it had 4 red lights - almost in a square square, and then it also had other white lights in several places around. I just want to point out that I am color blind. My first idea for an explanation could be something with a mast I haven't seen before? Or a helicopter?

During a night shift last January, while taking a smoke break outside the hospital, I observed a large white luminous object moving slowly from north to south several kilometers up above the city. Then it stopped and a smaller red pulsating glowing object came out of the white object. It fell several hundred meters from the white object and turned to the west in a circular motion, disappearing due west at high speed. The first white object then disappeared at high speed straight up and out of sight.

I saw two rather large dancing round white light 'balls' - not cones - they looked like they were heading across our woods but stopped when I got out into the garden. They crossed each other and then disappeared in a northerly direction. The air was hazy, so it might be floodlights, but I didn't see any floodlights nearby. The lights didn't have a trail of light behind, and they had a clear demarcation forward, so it looked like the light was coming from the center of the sphere, not from somewhere outside. When they were closest, they were approx. 200 meters away. I spontaneously went out into the garden because it looked so strange, but am only reporting it now because I read in the local paper that others had seen the same thing.

The object was seen coming from the east while I was sitting in the living room. Went out on my west-facing balcony with binoculars and looked at it through binoculars. It had the color of fire, bright orange (like a filament in an old light bulb). There was no sound to be heard. At one point it disappeared into the clouds to the west. All the time one color without flashing or change in color. There was no trace of smoke or similar in the sky in the binoculars.

It was a cold afternoon, and here I pretend to look for satellites and stars, as I am very interested in it. I was standing on the north side of the house and the moon was not up when an object came over the roof ridge, approx. 20-40 m up. There were 3 red candles that sat in a three-corner with a length of approx. 6 m between each. They turned at an even speed counter-clockwise.

Friday 17-03 2017 at 22.00 I will close the blinds. I see a large object in the sky, which I first think is a satellite, but it glows with 2 red lights on each side, at first weak then strong. This is when I become aware that it is not a satellite, as there is no red light on a satellite. I rush into the living room to get a pair of binoculars, because they are standing still in the air. When I get back it's gone.

This "experience" is from 1998, just after dark, when I had to go out to walk the dog and had gone out into the garden from the back door, where I could see to the south towards Randers (Gudenådalen). I immediately spotted a horizontal row of blue lights with a red-orange orb just below. It came rapidly closer. I called the wife, who came out and watched. It was now almost directly above us. As it passed us we could see its blue lights in front and white lights behind, otherwise everything was black. We could not see the orange ball, not even from behind, as it disappeared with its horizontal row of white lights on the horizon to the north. It moved completely silently all the time. When we saw it from below, it appeared square. I should just add that we are used to seeing airplanes out here, be it small airplanes from Randers Airport, large airliners from Copenhagen to Aalborg and the military's Jets and helicopters, and they all make noise, whereas this one was completely silent. It wasn't a glider either, as the speed was like a jet fighter and the size must have been enormous. If I had taken my square wallet and held it outstretched as it flew over us, it would not have been able to cover it. It also did not look like any of the UFOs that I have seen in magazines, television and similar places. It was neither a round plate, disco nor cigar-shaped, but seemed almost square.

As a social worker, I had been on a home visit and was on my way home to Svenstrup. Between Godthåb and Svenstrup I saw two white glowing balls in the sky. I stopped the car and turned off the engine and got out. The two luminous objects/spheres stood still for a moment, then disappeared to the west at VERY high speed supersonic. There was not a sound to be heard, and in an instant they had disappeared from the sky. It went really fast. I have quite "entertained" both family and friends with my story. I am TOTALLY convinced that it had no natural explanation. No sound oh incredible speed. Now I have seen the documentary on Dr 1 about UFOs and many of the sightings shown here are similar to the ball lightning I saw.

D. 6 August 2022 between 16.00 and 19.00 I saw a UFO/UAP at the triangle here on Bornholm. It was located between Rø and Olsker and hung low in the sky. It consisted of a geometric pattern that I would think was a simple version of a Triquetra. First there was the "flower" with three "petals". The uppermost petal turned vertically, the other two vertically, on each side, but slightly lower than vertical. At the "crown flower's" vertical tip, after a while a triangle appeared which connected the tips and finally a circle appeared which also touched the tips of the "flower". The geometric pattern was invisible, and my friend and I could only see it because the light was bent, or the molecules were different, perhaps more "watered down". After a while, a small very bright teardrop-shaped light appeared at the tip of the "flower" which traveled very slowly down the left side of the "flower", further into the center, after which the bright light continued out of the left "leaf" then the light disappeared when it had reached the tip. Noticed that the drop shaped light shone with fine blue and white rays. Then the "flower" and then the triangle disappeared. In the end, only the circle remained, which became completely black, or not completely black, perhaps black as on a negative, where there is somehow light behind. Then the black circle began to fly, but not in a fast straight line, but rather unevenly! Like it was flying in our direction, and then a little to the left, and then a little in our direction again, and then again a little to the left. After a few seconds it disappeared. The entire session was silent. The experience lasted for a few minutes, as if it was in no rush at all.

At 23.03 I observed an object over Roskilde, which came from the west (approx. Svogerslev direction) over Rønnebærparken where I live. The object moved eastwards in a zigzag, where each zigzag is approx. 200-300 meters and the object changed direction at a frequency of approx. 1-1.5 seconds from side to side relative to the direction of flight. There was a plane that crossed the course of the object. The aircraft was a single engine type and was flying from southwest to northeast at a lower altitude than the object and I am sure the pilot saw the object because I noticed the object because of the light when it was directly above me for approx. 700-1000 meters altitude. In an outstretched arm, the object measured like a clasped hand. The object was brightly lit with a reddish glow and was completely silent. The object disappeared on the horizon in a western direction at 23.06. My assessment is that the object increased its speed considerably, since from a size of approx. 2 cm in outstretched arm and 45 degrees above the horizon, until it disappeared in the horizon as a small dot only went approx. 10-12 seconds. I have never experienced anything like it.

Approx. at 03:30 on the night of Saturday, August 8, 2015, I stood in my garden and looked at the sky. A triangular object (3 lights forming a triangle) with a red/orange light in the middle, moved very quickly in the sky from Brøndby towards Ishøj over the water. When the object passed the south line, one of the lights in the triangle flew with a very very fast movement towards the sky and disappeared in space. The rest of the triangle continued unchanged towards Ishøj. Observation time was approx. 5-6 seconds.

I had just come home from work and the day before had promised my wife to cut our hedges. I parked the car and went out to the hedge to look at it before I started. As I live in the country, I stood in our driveway and looked out over the neighbor's fields. I thought how golden and beautiful it all was, a true delight to the eye, and continued to look at the clouds and the beautiful blue sky. Suddenly I could see what I can only describe as a bright, shiny object with a silvery metallic surface. The object, which was oval in shape, appeared to have no wings and left no jet or contrails in its wake. It was moving very slowly from S to SSW or SW, and seemed like it might be flying slightly at an angle. From my property I can see 2 wind turbines on a neighbour's field, and the height and location of the object in relation to these turbines was about 2 turbine lengths up from the horizon, i.e. approx. 25 or 35 degrees. (checked the location today.) It all went relatively quickly, in retrospect, but I believe the whole sighting didn't take much more than maybe 1½ to 2 minutes before the object sadly disappeared. I don't know if I blinked, the object just disappeared. I was outside later in the afternoon and again several times during the evening hours because the sky was quite clear and bright, but unfortunately it didn't turn into more shiny objects. I hope you can use my information for something, and of course you are welcome to call or write to me if necessary.

Saw what I thought was a shooting star but then went over and looked like a satellite. But weaker in light. It appeared from the west to the left of Venus and disappeared in the opposite direction. It started to zag approx. 90 degrees above my head. Changed direction as it searched for something. Speeding up to the east, zig zagged a bit before disappearing into the horizon. Duration approx. 4-4 seconds. No plane or satellite could change direction and fly that fast in my own opinion.

I stand on the terrace at 21.45 when I hear a fighter plane and look up to the north. There I see a clear, red glowing and silent round object heading south with a fighter jet right at its heels. I call my mother and we stand speechless and watch. The object is very bright red, and it has a gliding motion, like when you see a satellite. The fighter is clearly trying to follow the object; the plane roars completely unnaturally, as if the pilot is giving the plane more gas than it can handle. The object disappears after 1-2 min. to the south. Quite a short time later, another fighter plane arrives in exactly the same direction, and a little later again, two more fighter planes - also in exactly the same direction. So we saw this object with 4 fighters following it at short intervals. The object had only a red color, no flashing lights and no sound. It had this very special gliding motion that a plane "of our world" cannot move. It was not a satellite, for that was the object too distinct; it was in our atmosphere. I can best describe the object size to be like if there is a tennis ball hanging in the air 10-15 meters from one. It seemed somewhat larger than the fighter that was right behind it. It may have been a flight exercise, but a feeling in me said otherwise; so there was something "unknown" in our airspace, which obviously had to be looked into more closely, why all those flights after the object.

I was smoking a goodnight smoke in my back garden and looked up at the stars as it was quite clear, out of the corner of my eye I see a strong flash and therefore look in the direction it came from. But when I just looked over there, there was nothing to see. However, only 2-5 seconds pass, then there is another strong flash and I can see a white spot (almost like a star) moving from east to west. It sometimes flashes strongly like a flash, almost but not at any specific rate, just like that every once in a while. When I have observed it for 10-15 sec., I can see that next to it there is one more object that flies at the same pace, and every time the first observed object flashes, it almost moves forward in a "notch", and number 2 object is included, but without flash/blink. Every time it flashes/blinks, it moves forward a good distance without being able to follow its path. Shortly before they disappear from my field of vision above my roof horizon, they change direction to the northwest and change position so that they are alternately in front.
