Never seen anything like it so that's why I'm reporting it here.

yeah.. looked like a really strong flash/flash and looked like it was far away.. came 2 times 30 to 60 sec apart.. never seen anything like that...? what was that any good suggestions..? it was crazy to watch.. imagine a little star that just suddenly gives off a huge twinkle and then nothing..? completely gone..? 2 times..?

Today, 3 February 2016, at 4.50 p.m., with fine clear weather, we happened to look out of the window and saw some mysterious danger very quickly across the sky; direction north to south, and much higher up than the small private planes. It looked like something from a New Year's rocket, like a single "star", but we could figure out that it wasn't, as the speed was very high. We wondered, but didn't even manage to open the window to hear if there was any sound, so quickly it was gone. Could it have been a shooting star that we actually think it might resemble?
At 00:15 I observed 30-40 flying objects flying one after the other at small intervals. It lasted about 45 minutes and they flew as fast as an airplane would.

Fireball suddenly appears above treetops, supposedly about 1-2km away. Moving at about 10 m/sec upwards, and driven in the direction of the wind, light wind. Flakes a bit, but rises evenly quickly. Gets smaller and smaller as it rises upwards, and disappears into the clouds after approx. 10 minutes Doubt it's an emergency rocket as it won't behave like one. Think it might be a physics experiment/joke. Hope more people have seen it/it.

23 November at 6.55. I'm on my bike on my way to Nykøbing F Station. On Østre Alle, in a direction almost due east, from position 54.766304, 11.893781 (a little before Nykøbing Zoo), I catch sight of 3 white glowing spots. In relation to the road (due east) they lie slightly to the left (approximately 260 degrees), at an angle of approx. 40 degrees. They correspond in size to half the diameter of the hole in a 1 crown held in an outstretched arm. They lie on a perfect line in relation to each other, also in terms of mutual distance. Total "width" corresponds to the width of the 3 middle fingers, held at arm's length. They are angularly aligned corresponding to a 20 degree downward slope to the right (calculated from a horizontal position). My first thought is that it was Orion's belt, but I remember the distance being greater. Before I can reflect further, the left light begins to move downwards while the middle one moves upwards until they form a triangle. Just at that point, I'm a little unsure which ones actually move, but believe with 90% certainty that the above is the correct version. In any case, it seems rather strange. From the time I first see the lights, 8-10 seconds pass when they are perfectly aligned. Only then do they move, and it only takes 6-7 seconds for them to form a perfect triangle. This seems to me to "stand still" for another 4-5 seconds, after which the lights continue their movements and become dimmer. After another 10 seconds, I can only see one (the right light). This can be observed for a further 10-15 seconds, after which it also disappears. The lights could be reminiscent of the lights from airplanes, but 3 lights so close together (although the depth distance could not be measured), seems unlikely. Their mutual first stationary location, and then mutual movement pattern, also does not seem likely for aircraft.

My girlfriend and I were looking for shooting stars when this mysterious "ball" caught our attention. The object was moving in an east-to-north trajectory. It was perfectly clear, the moon was almost full and very bright. When we first spotted the object, it looked like it was flying fast and far away. Within a short time it seemed to come closer to us and slow down. As the object got closer it got bigger, it shone brightly and was surrounded by a haze/fog. Both my girlfriend and I were very surprised and couldn't believe our eyes. We followed the object, which got bigger and bigger (coming closer and closer?) until it disappeared on the horizon behind some woods. I got a short video before it disappeared,
Orange "fireball" moved across the sky from east to south. The ball was round and looked like it had flames in it. The ball was far up, but it looked like it was getting "closer to the ground".

Going for my evening walk behind Korskærparken down by the golf course, when I see three red dots standing in a perfect V approximately 45 degrees above the horizon. There was no movement on the dots, but they were just brightly lit for about 10 minutes, after which the bottom dot in the V just went out, but the top two continued to shine for a minute, and slowly went out. I don't know if there was some kind of craft in the sky, but I noticed that a star had become visible where the V had been, there were some clouds in the sky, and the star may also have been hidden behind a cloud. No sounds could be heard, other than normal traffic noise (trains and cars).

It was after a city trip that I went up to pick up my bike with a few mates. It was a little after four and I was tired and wanted to go home. As we stood out in the yard where my bike was parked, we noticed the local disco's light show in the sky. It should be added that I certainly had a lot to drink, but my friend is almost a teetotaler. Unfortunately, my other mate never got to see it, as it didn't last more than 5-10 seconds. I'm not entirely sure about the given directions and angle as this is the first time I've ever seen anything like it. I have always had a logical way of explaining the inexplicable things I have seen in the sky, but this seems particularly inexplicable to me. Especially the way it swung out into "space" convinced me that it was something special. I have also checked for lightning and the like, but there was nothing to see at dmi. The fact that it could have been the disco light is also ruled out, as it had turned completely over to the opposite side.
We see a light above St. Jorgensen Park. It lasted about a minute. It was very clear and distinct and did not make any noise. The light suddenly went out and it was gone.
Saw initially 4-5 bright spots that moved smoothly across the sky. While we were looking, 2 more came, shining very brightly, before they disappeared in the same direction as the others.

An evening with a strong and prolonged thunderstorm passed by Aarhus. I photograph lightning and had the shutter open for approx. 30 seconds. I did not observe the object at the time of shooting, but only after a closer review of the images. The object is not visible in the pictures taken immediately before and after.

My UFO sighting dates back several years, but I only found you and the opportunity to report yesterday when I listened to the DR podcast "Flying saucer". I have not yet been able to come up with any explanation for what my friend and I saw then. We were 10-12 years old, and therefore it may also have been a vivid imagination, but we both saw the same thing and were also then mystified and wondering what it actually was. Description of the observation: Me and my best friend lie on a sea trampoline and look at clouds in the summer, in the middle of the day or in the early afternoon. Clear sunny weather. We look at the "cloud streaks" (condensation trails) that can occur behind aircraft. It was not unusual to see aircraft and/or contrails in the sky. We spot something airplane-like with condensation trails, which is just passing through the sky. It looks like a light gray or white equilateral triangle. We discover to our surprise that the triangle moves "backwards" along the condensation trail. In other words, it does not have the trail behind it like a tail, but in front of it in relation to the direction of movement. In addition, the condensation path "disappears" as the triangle moves along it. As if it "blurs" the path as it moves along it. The triangle did not move with one of the corners as the front point, but with one of the sides of the triangle in front. Hope it makes sense!

I went out to observe Saturn, as it can only be seen early in the morning at this time of year. However, I ended up finding Mercury. I then tried to locate Saturn without the telescope while the telescope was still pointed at Mercury. When I couldn't find Saturn in the sky, I decided to take a closer look at Mercury, since I had adjusted the telescope to the planet. But when I looked through the telescope, a flying object flew from right to left in my point of view in the telescope. It took the object about 5 seconds before I had to turn the telescope to keep up. So it didn't fly that fast, and since I was using a 10mm eyepiece, which makes my 8" telescope zoom really far in, it makes objects look faster. Appearance of the object: Properties of the object: Drawing of the object and position in the sky: http ://img99.imageshack.us/my.php?image=bildé027gb5.jpg I hope you guys can figure out what it could possibly be I saw as I don't think aliens with high enough technology to come here to earth, would fly around in such a craft. However, one can never be sure, but my guess as to what it might have been is a new version of a stealth aircraft or military aircraft, from its shape. Three yellow glowing orbs came into view from west to east - descending towards the ground. I only made eye contact when they came into view in my window. At first I thought they were shooting stars, but they absolutely were not. The 3 orbs were next to each other, but they didn't stick together - they moved individually They stopped about 50 meters up, they didn't seem very big. I took my camera outside to take pictures, but I was too shocked/enthralled by the sight to figure out how to turn off the flash, so the pictures haven't worked - one was just black, one was all white. There were no sounds/machine noise or any other kind of sound from the luminous balls at all, after approx. Half a minute in the same place, where they moved a little between each other, they flew slowly to the south. Approx. 10 minutes later they reappeared from exactly the same direction and took up the same position, approx. 50 meters above my neighbor's house. After again hanging in the same place, moving a little back and forth, they again flew south. Approx. 100 meters from my position, it looked like they dropped/threw something luminous towards the ground. After this, they again flew slowly to the south and disappeared quietly on the horizon. At no point could I sense any outline/shape on the glowing orbs - it was just 3 yellow glowing round orbs. It was a fantastic sight, I was really taken aback, as I quickly think that I could rule out that it could be something familiar (searchlight, fireball, helicopter, etc.) It really annoys me that I couldn't find out of operating my camera - hope you can shed light on it.

My boyfriend and I go outside to smoke before bed. We stand and admire the night sky and try to spot a shooting star (as so often before). Suddenly I see one and point up. The boyfriend sees it immediately and only has time to say "oh yes", as the object changes direction with the speed of lightning. It makes a few circular turns at high speed, then flies back obliquely at lightning speed, after which it just as quickly disappears in a northwesterly direction! There was only a very small, almost cautious cloud in the sky, where the object disappeared from view for a few seconds and reappeared. It was flying very high up and there was absolutely no sound to be heard, which is why I don't think it can be some remote controlled object! The speed doesn't indicate that either! It would be absolutely fantastic if there is a logical explanation for the phenomenon... And I/we would like to hear from you (if others have seen it!

There was no sound or noise. It moved towards the north coast. After that it stood still for a few minutes and shone very brightly. There was no sound at all, no one on. Then it disappeared, to the northeast again.

My family and I have just moved into a terraced house in Greve. We haven't lived in a house before, so I enjoy being able to look at the night sky before I go to bed. I look for satellites and shooting stars. Yesterday was no exception. I went out to have my "goodnight smoke" before going to bed. I always stand and look straight up into the air, and just as I was about to lower my head, something came whizzing over the ridge of my house. The 5 things flew in formation with 2 in front and 3 close behind them. The front two "rocked" slightly to the side while flying. They flew completely silently and yet incredibly fast. They seemed round and flat and their color was like a dull light that faded into a dark outline/contour of the UFO. Unfortunately, it was all over in approx. 5 seconds. I would give my right arm to be allowed to experience it again. Will you email me back about whether there are other sightings from around the Køgebugt/Greve area yesterday?

we were sitting in a garden when I catch an object in my field of vision.. and react to this... it's not quite round... almost resembled a cloud like thing.. thought it was an aurora I had seen. .It had a greenish/white glow...it "drove" like in a lane..but quite fast at times. When I write in orbit, it is because, after 2 hours of observation, it seemed rather "mechanically made". with... still hovering in some kind of orbit.. like it was following me home... eventually it was over my house. I think it seemed strange and can't really be explained.. If it was someone shining with a searchlight.. there would be some kind of cone of light under the object.. and then it would have stayed in the same place right? At least I think so, it would... there was no noise associated with the object. All 3 of us were very curious to know what it might be. could be, we had all seen. There were a lot of stars.. but it was hardly a star? who behaved like that? Have you heard of a similar phenomenon that informed the evening in question? (Friday night). I know it sounds artificial.. and if it was a ufo.. it wouldn't be there for that long.. or would it? But the fact that it kind of came with me.. seems quite strange to me.. inexplicable anyway. My thoughts also went to whether there was a company which, as it were, has an "advertising light" which operates in a certain way, but I don't think there is one in Odense. In addition, it changed direction a little.. and was fast at times.. vupti it was somewhere else.. as you had turned off the switch to the light, and the light was gone... so fast. Hope you can give an explanation.. we tried to photograph it.. but it didn't want to be in the picture.. just darkness. We therefore cannot document our observation, but hope you have heard of similar observations.

I live near Aalborg Airport in Vadum. A Nato exercise was supposed to have started the day before, but not many planes had arrived in Aalborg yet. One evening, I was sitting on the sofa, I could see a plane coming in for landing from east to west, as they always do. But this plane slowed in midair. Then it had to be a helicopter. But what was such a thing doing in the approach route and why was it standing still there. Those helicopters tend to do that. So I left the couch and went out into the garden. It was flashing red and white. But there was no sound from it. Why did it hang there? Now 5 minutes had passed. since it stopped. Then I saw another "helicopter". Completely white, like a satellite. It flew from south to north east of my house. There was no sound either. It was now reasonably close. Therefore, I should be able to hear something. But no. Then the first one began to fly south towards Aalborg. Also without sound. I have tried to film the first one. It's not a good video, but you can see that there is something flashing faintly and not a sound. I find it strange that you couldn't hear sound from both of them. I know that if the wind is from the west, you cannot hear anything when what you see is in the east. But I'm used to seeing both planes and helicopters on a daily basis. And it looks so strange. It must not stand still in the approach route. I bet those in the tower out at the airport could see it with binoculars. Hope I can get an answer to what it was.

I observed a rocket launch due east, and knowing the impending Danish rocket test, I took it for granted that the rocket had now been launched. But I am very surprised that there has been nothing about this in the news. Are you familiar with a launch?
Dot blinks and changes height and flies to the sides and blinks in different colors shortly after you could see the space station passing in the sky.

I was on my way home from my girlfriend, who lives in Brøndby Strand. I myself live in Hvidovre, and get off at Friheden st. I usually talk to my girlfriend the whole way home from her, and that's all and as it usually is. But purely by chance, I look out over the "sea". So you can't see the sea from there, but that's the way that the sea lies (south). I see a bright light on the horizon, and think that it's probably just a plane heading straight for me, but which will turn around in a little while to land at Kastrup airport. But I think the light looked a bit strange when you consider that it was an airplane, so I stand for a while on "Menelaos boulevard" in Hvidovre and look at the light. I then ask my girlfriend if she can see it from her apartment in Brøndby Strand, and she could! From both her angle and mine, it was a very bright light. You couldn't see the shape of the object hanging in the air at all. Suddenly the light started flashing all sorts of colors. Yellow, blue, green and white, and not only that, I could suddenly see it moving to one of the sides, and there I was really scared inside! My girlfriend couldn't see it move from her apartment, but she could still see it, and all the different colors. So the movement I then must have been away or towards my girlfriend as we saw the object from two different angles. And the angle she saw it from, she couldn't see it moving because it might be flying straight at her, or straight away from her. But after 2 minutes approx. then it started moving a lot! One thing I will never forget is that it picked up speed and I could see it more clearly than before. It had approx. 5 lights below it, which shone in 5 directions below it, and it leaned slightly to the side as it flew at the slightly higher speed. And the most eerie thing was that for a few seconds I could see something that looked like rotations from it. For the first time I could see the saucer-shaped shape. It's probably one of the scariest things I've ever seen in my life! Sure, I watch the History Channel with ancient aliens and ufo hunters, but I've also always been realistic and thought that it's just movie tricks. But after what I saw today, I saw no doubt that there really is something out there. My girlfriend could also see it rotating from her apartment and the 5 lights below it. I also tried to think what it could be if I didn't have to think flying saucer. But it wasn't a helicopter! We have got a medical helicopter in the capital area. But I don't see why it would fly back and forth, zig-zagging in the air. Furthermore, it does not have such a bright light that goes in all directions at once. I've also seen it before in the evening, that is the helicopter, and this didn't look like it at all! A long way off! An aviator is also completely out of the question. So I really don't see what it would be. It's the scariest thing in my life, but exciting too. Hope to see it again! I actually tried to film it, but my mobile didn't bother to film as there was almost no power left + I was talking to my girlfriend and it was just so sad that there was no power! But I really don't understand if there was no one but me and my boyfriend who saw it .. it was really crazy.

I casually look out of the slanted window on the 1st floor, and my gaze is caught by a dot of light that appears "behind" a telemast on the property. The object looks like a round sphere, illuminated white by the sun so that on the right side it is bright white, and on the left side it is more subdued in brightness. The object is moving in a northerly direction at high speed, speed across the sky is estimated to be 2-3 times the speed of passing satellites. The distance is impossible to estimate, it could have been 50 meters up or several kilometers. The object appears clearly defined spherical, without any color change or shape change. The size is approx. 3-4 mm in an outstretched arm at the start of observation. The object disappears in a northerly direction within 10-15 seconds, it "disappears" in the same way as a satellite can when the light fades. During the observation, a commercial airliner flies over the area, from east to west. My first thoughts were on a satellite/ISS, but both speed and brightness were too high for this. My next thought was a balloon or other airborne object, which might fit the wind direction that day (loose string on the mast indicated the wind direction). However, I would again assess the speed as being too high in relation to the wind strength, just as a balloon or bag would probably give the impression of shape-shifting. At the end of the observation, I tried to catch the object in binoculars standing by the window, but without success.

I was on my way out with my dog and on my way to the garden gate my eye caught a movement in the sky. The object came in from the west, thought at first that it was a meteor passing across the sky. But it didn't look quite right. As it got closer I saw that the light from it was round lights (white) along the side of it. There was no sound (windless morning), no flashing lights like on an airplane or satellite, no visible wings like on an airplane. It was large, elongated like a cigar and black. It followed approx. the coastline, probably 1-2 km inland and was quickly gone again. I managed to take a picture with my mobile before it was completely gone again. The whole thing took maybe 6 - 8 seconds.

I was sitting out in the garden with my friend looking at the stars when we suddenly spotted a very strong light to the south. The object hung very low and shone extremely brightly. It hung completely still in the air, and I then wondered about it, but we sat down and talked about other phenomena I have experienced. When we look up there again several minutes later, the object has moved a little bit, and now we discovered that it was moving forward very slowly and not in a straight line! It flew slightly to the right and then to the left. It flew faster and faster, but we managed to get in and get my mom and sister so they could see it too. As they came, the object flew over us and all of a sudden changed to 3 small lights and a large one in front. IT WASN'T A PLANE! It flashed in all sorts of colors and I think it was shaped like a square with a very bright tip. There is no way it could have been a plane, helicopter or anything else, as it made no noise. It was a completely windless evening and we could hear no sound. There was also no tail or anything after the object. It disappeared to the north, still flashing…

I came driving around 00.20 along Tarm Landevej from Sdr. Omme towards Hoven. Approx. 2 km. before Hoven I see a strong light, like an explosion behind some trees north of the road. I wondered if it could be an explosion in a factory. I mean this light was a few kilometers from me but it was very powerful. Afterwards came a less powerful light, in the same yellow/orange shade. As I drove on towards Hoven, I looked for the light and guessed it occasionally. I heard no sounds associated with the light. At the roundabout after Hoven, I drove towards Ølgod, and approx. 1 km. after the roundabout, on the west side of the road, over the fields, I spot what looks like a small airplane with fire in it. It's in the same direction as I'm driving, and seems to be about to land. I drive parallel to it for a few minutes, then my path turns and I see it disappear behind the trees. I feel I was close to the phenomenon, but the darkness of the night makes it difficult to judge distances.

I was born in 1948 in the small village of Everdrup, halfway between Næstved and Præstø. When I was in the 4th grade, I entered a private school in Næstved, which is why I had to cycle to a small village called Bøgesø and from there take the train to Næstved. On the road from Bøgesø to Everdrup, there is a long, small settlement, Flintemose, and some forest, and after the 2 localities, there is a clear section with a long, steep hill, which everyone, adults and children, pulled their bikes up. The road is called Flintemosevej. A summer day in August or September 1959, on the way home from school, approx. at 14.45 plus/minus ½ hour, I thus pulled my bike up that hill. It was a lovely summer day without a cloud in the sky. When I had reached 2/3 up the hill, I looked back and saw some of my mates who had just arrived at the foot of the hill and were getting off their bikes. Approx. 15 sec. later I absentmindedly looked up at the sky to the north and suddenly saw a giant pipe in the sky. It was completely shiny and completely smooth without any openings etc. protrusion to see. The ends were blunt, and it seems to me that the ends were a little narrower than the middle. There were no sounds to be heard from it, and there was no smoke or electricity. fire out of the object. I looked at the object for 2-3-4 seconds, then turned my head to see if my companions had seen it too, but apparently they hadn't, so I quickly turned my head back and looked up at the sky again - but now the object was gone! I looked all over the sky, but there was no sign of it in the completely cloudless sky. And there were no other things to see either. It is obviously difficult to judge the size of the object as there was nothing in the sky to compare it to, but from how clear and sharp I saw it I would guess it was 3-400m away and as big as 2 jumbo jets. But the size is obviously uncertain. However, I perceived it as very large and as a good distance away. Did it fly while I was watching it? I have often thought about that afterwards - but I don't actually know. IF it flew, it came approx. from the east in the longitudinal direction of the object. It had a slightly inclined position in the sky. The sighting probably happened many years ago, but I think I remember it as if it had happened a month ago. I can thus also remember who I follow. told about it, their names and what they answered me. I'm not aware of anyone else seeing it.

My observation is from 1980/1981, can't remember the exact year anymore, but the observation is still clear. I had just got time off from my part-time job and was on my way home by bike. The weather was relatively calm and clear, according to West Jutland conditions. Then I see to the left, to the west, blue and red round objects, if you imagine 2 pcs. WW stretched out, alternating red below and blue above from left to right and back again. It happens at high speed, impossible for aircraft to turn/turn that fast. I will then cycle east and actually dare not look back.

We look over Thisted, as it is fantastically starry. Suddenly, a large red ball comes floating over the city quite slowly. The light from the ball is really strong, and it comes in over the city, but turns to the south and slowly disappears into the horizon. I have seen several UFOs before, so I was not shaken, but my children and wife were. Had to lie to the kids and said it was just a shooting star. The object was fast and silent, and twice the size of Venus, which was behind the object.

I was walking the dogs when I looked up - saw something that looked like a star, flashing extremely clearly - in the direction of Gelsted. Would guess 60-70 degrees above the horizon. Then it disappeared again for a few seconds - then flashed again - to start moving to the right... then disappeared a bit to reappear in a perpendicular direction... disappeared again to reappear in a different direction again - between 2 stars came a long luminous streak - then it disappeared and reappeared in a new direction but less sound - This is how it jumped back and forth across the sky for 2-3 minutes. It wasn't a plane, nor a satellite - I see those every day - and I often see shooting stars, but I've never seen anything like this before. Maybe you know what this is? Very special experience and see how it "jumped" across the sky. Maybe you guys can help figure out what this was.

I am about to put my purchases (Rema1000) into the car, where in the corner of my left eye I see this object, which is why I quickly turn to see the object more clearly. The matte black triangle object hovers approx. 500 meters away from Strandvejen and in the direction of the beach and at a height of approx. 500 meters, which it does for approx. 5-10 minutes - meanwhile I think Hmmm, a little uneasy, but is quickly replaced by a fascination - what is going on here! The object emitted no light or sound, and its shape resembled an "overturned" pyramid, with the tip pointing in a northerly direction and its size at least 4 times larger than a fighter plane (in length•width•height). After the approx. 10 minutes the object disappears "out of the blue" like a blink of an eye... Sorry that I didn't report this earlier, but I didn't know that you had the option here in Denmark (the Nordics) plus thought, is it not known be "normal" with these UAPs.
I stood looking up at a cloudless sky at 07.15 on Saturday 12-02-11, and suddenly there was a huge shooting star. It was white light with a haze around it.

I am a radio amateur and sometimes stay up late at night and often into the morning. I was sitting inside my radio room listening to some distant stations. At 06:32 I went into my kitchen to get a cup of coffee. I have a view of the sea, live on the 3rd floor and can see Læsø and Sæby. Suddenly I saw that a little north of Læsø there was a strange light which descended and flew up, suddenly, when it was down, it moved sideways and in an oblique path. I studied the phenomenon for a few minutes as it appeared to be approaching Frederikshavn. Suddenly it rose at a tremendous speed and disappeared over Sæby. It was now 06:46, so all the electricity in Frederikshavn went out. I started my emergency station to see if anyone else had power. It turned out that the power had gone all the way down to Viborg, perhaps Esbjerg. I got the idea that the object had refueled and thereby extinguished the Danmark family.

I have heard an American ufologist talk about a trick where you can pick up UAP with high probability, by filming the sky in slomo. This is the first of three observations, after filming at different angles for a total of approx. 10 minutes I have filmed short sequences in slomo of 40-60 seconds and analyzed them in a video editing program. This has made it possible to observe at approx. 170 frames per SEC. After approx. 180 sec. recordings on 11.3 I have been able to observe uap 2 times.

A married couple living in 8210 Århus V. observed a light in the sky on 16 June 2008 and reported this to Flyvertaktisk Kommando, FTK, in Karup, from which SUFOI has received the observation report: "Last night on 16 June 2008, both my wife and I saw in absolutely sober condition an unusual phenomenon of light.” “I happened to look out at 0.45 and saw up in the air a spot of light the size of a sixth of the moon and of the same warm color as the flame of a candle. A moment later more followed until there were a total of five in a row. There weren't the colored and flashing lights that planes usually carry. The light was equally strong towards us, above us and away from us. The strangest thing, however, was that there was no sound at all. It's quiet here and we can usually hear airliners going so high up that they are only seen as a dot." "In terms of speed, it could be a plane. They moved from SW towards NE - with a little good will in the direction of Tirstrup. The question then is whether five silent planes / helicopters with very strong lighting arrived at Tirstrup at 0.55?' the place and time in question had planes in the air that could explain the sighting. SUFOI comment: The wind direction at the time in question appears to have been approx. from SV, which strengthens a presumption that - combined with the other report - it could probably be small vamluft balloons.

Below the clouds comes a very large round orange object - a bit like a ball - which "flies" very calmly at a steady pace and in a straight line across the sky to disappear into the lowest clouds to the west. There was no flashing or color change. After approx. 4 min, another completely similar one appears - from the same place and disappears in the same direction. I have a small video on my mobile but it's hard to see it properly.

It will soon be an old story, but eventually I have thought about it quite a few times, not least when I read UFO mails. We are driving from Benløse towards Ringsted, and as we are somewhere between Holbækvej and the motorway access towards Sorø, we see on our right hand side approx. 50 meters up an elongated rectangular object with 2 parallel rows of lamp-like objects. The object looks relatively large and moves a bit around the area, then follows the motorway towards Sorø.
Driving north on Bernstoffsvej. See it nnv at Bernstorffs Station. falls next vertically down.

We were watching TV when my husband suddenly spots an orange fireball coming south. My husband, I and our son ran out onto our patio as it flies over our roof. Since it is on the other side of the house, we run around and look for it. It continues in a straight direction at a speed of approx. 60 km per hour for about 2 minutes, all of a sudden it's gone.

The thing that my girlfriend, my mate and myself have seen is one of the known "balls of light" over what we guess are Hindevad and Morud, Funen. We have followed them 3 times flying slowly across the sky to finally disappear. The whole affair has vague curiosity, and not knowing where else to go, I thought this would be the place. Regarding height above the horizon at the time of disappearance, - I cannot say, but approx. from our point of view 10-15 cm above the horizon.

properties.Colors: stater som kraftig hvid spot ender m blåt skær omkring spot
properties.content: First report: Captured on screen shot from video of 4m 35s. This could not be immediately seen on replay, not even as slow motion on my phone. The object captured by chance via screen shot is grey, clear and oval-shaped exactly like the tic-tac. we have seen and heard so much about. Second report: Is shaped like a luminous point, which forms a triangle between two of the points, one corner point in the lower right corner is further associated with 4 bright points, of which it is very luminous, the perimeter around this powerful spot-like light changes color to bluish. This object appears unnaturally low and in 40 minutes it moves across the horizon from SE 175 degrees to S 205 degrees and out of sight. The object in the second observation is seen with the naked eye as an unnaturally strong light in the sky, and this observation could only be recorded and documented via the telescope combined with the zoom from the iPhone 12. This was video recorded for 39 min. together with the girlfriend. The object in the first observation was with a mobile phone and is probably the most startling. I have video plus photo and a witness as documentation, and I would really like help to clarify what we observed

I saw two yellow/green balls of light in a North/Northwest direction when I was outside, approx. 19:55. Shining appeared in the sky, lighting up the sky well, even though it was fairly dark. The orbs descended towards the ground, with quite slow speed, even after the orbs themselves were out of sight, they could still be seen lighting up the sky. Suddenly the light disappeared and then a big bang was heard. A bang for each ball of light, more balls of light appeared in the sky after the others had disappeared. But a light disappeared down towards the earth and came up again in the sky and disappeared in the middle of the sky.

There are three of us on an evening walk who experience what we think is a satellite coming from the SE, we can see it flying fast and think it must be a comet. The observation lasts for approximately 12-14 seconds, no sound is heard. According to Fligt rader, there were no planes in the airspace. The objects looked like satellites, but were flying far too fast, and their way of turning suggests that they were satellites.

We sat outside and suddenly spotted a huge star that flew alternately left and right. After approx. 7 minutes It retreated and "multiplied" into small entities/stars that shaped like a Christmas tree. After approx. 10 minutes later it retreated like a big star, where I managed to take a picture. It was in the same direction it retreated. It was a beautiful experience and we were completely enchanted, but also think it might be interesting to hear if others have seen the same thing.

We could not connect it with any phenomenon known to us, searchlight, fireworks, or the like. An airplane could be heard, but we did not associate it with the phenomenon. We have looked at your pages with celestial phenomena, and have also looked at other pages, and we have not been able to find anything similar.

We see a flashing object that moves slightly from right to left and back again, and slightly up and down. It is clear that it is not an airplane or a helicopter. The location is, if you see the drawbar of the Chariots - take the 2 outermost stars in it, then it is an extension of it approx. 8 times. Something similar was observed 5 years ago in the south-southeast. The duration is unknown, as it does not disappear the same evening. Was then observed over 1 hour..

The observation took place in Vanløse on Ålekistevej opposite no. 122 on the forecourt by the park located here. It was 22:19 and I had just sent my friend off in a taxi. On my way back to my apartment, something in the sky catches my attention out of the corner of my eye. What I observe is, at first glance, 8 - 10 lights in orange color, which in brightness far exceed stars and which move in formation from west to east. I observe due south. Distance to these lights and their speed I dare not yet guess. Naturally, I would send the video as a file to Ole Henningsen as well. Unfortunately, it is 27.2 MB and my mail does not allow sending files larger than 25 MB. It can possibly be packed in a way so that it can be done anyway. I have no experience with this, which is why I am waiting a little longer. You at SUFOI are of course welcome to contact me if you have any questions or think I or the witnesses can contribute further. In fact, I would appreciate an explanation on this, which is why I certainly hope to hear from you.
Looked like a satellite but was slow and after 3 sec. was it gone where a satellite will disappear slowly in the sky/horizon.

Me and a buddy are taken to the woods on a hilltop that's out here where we live to look at a meteor shower. There are lots of shooting stars, white, yellow, green, orange, purple. Beautiful night and everything is as it usually is, when suddenly, RIGHT above us, there is a BRIGHT white light that shines down on us, as if from a helicopter. The white light disappears into an orange ball that flies in smaller and smaller circles away from us, then turns into a green triangle and flies away in the sky. (100% not a shooting star). I have no idea what it was.

When I was driving north to get to the workplace, my colleague and I saw a bright and fairly large flying object coming from the south and high up and descending at high speed to the north. It was a large yellow/white ball of light which was round. Since it was much larger than a shooting star and had no tail, I was left wondering what the object was? It came at high speed, but not faster than we could see it from the car without being particularly focused on the sky. It would be fun if others have seen the same thing.

The object came flying slowly from the west, large and warm yellow, then stopped and "stood still" for approx. 15 seconds, after which it quickly disappeared to the north west. Approx. 2 minutes later an object similar to the first came, stopped in the same place and waited for approx. ten seconds, while much further away there was a small bright spot towards which the object then flew, as if to follow them away.

I saw an increasing light yellow dot which became very large. There was a slowdown. Size increase from start to finish approx. 50 times. The distance is relative, but presumably upon entry into the atmosphere. It was cloudless and about 18°C. No sound, and no marker lights red/green, nor any satellites nearby.

properties.Colors: 3 grønne lys med 1 rødt enden, rundt lys
properties.content: Driving towards Rudkøbing, when I happen to see a green light with a red at the end. It flew back and forth, and then it was still. I watched it for approx. 2 minutes, then I have to drive. Was approx. a little further down than a plane. Got a photo taken. Only the green is clearly visible. Stood still in between.
It was the size of a street lamp, seen from 50 meters away, which quickly appeared and disappeared again, followed by a white light.

Saw beyond the horizon a glowing ball that hung a little high in the sky, and checked with flight radar that there were no planes in that direction, it looked like an orange colored ball that just floated quietly.

We drove in a northerly direction for 1.5-2 km. south of exit 37 south of Hobro, when I observe a white-green very bright object, which comes flying in from the west - possibly a little south-west. Shortly before the object is perpendicular to my field of vision, it splits and becomes a total of four smaller, still brightly shining objects. After crossing the center of my field of vision, all four objects disappear completely, just as suddenly as they appeared. I would immediately estimate the height of the objects when they disappear to be 35-40° seen from the car. My roommate, who I made aware of the phenomenon, also saw it quite clearly. Therefore, I am quite sure that it was not light reflections from cars coming from behind. At the same time, it was still quite bright and clear, so I am also reasonably sure that it was not a plane that possibly disappeared in the haze. There were also no flashing lights, as you normally see on planes.

The boyfriend and I lay soaking up the sunshine in a park, and suddenly the boyfriend pointed up and said "LOOOO". I looked up and we saw a strangely shaped object flying over us at a relatively high speed. We only saw the object clearly for a few seconds before we could only see it through the treetops. I ran across the street to see the object again, but there it was gone. It is always difficult to estimate height, but my immediate guess is that it was approx. 100 meters up The object looked very strange, and is a little difficult to describe. Two balls with a spike is the closest we could agree to describe it. The object was black and there were sun reflections in it. We talked about the possibility that it was something that had been sent up from the 1 May party in Fælledparken. However, we immediately thought it was too big and flew too fast to be. But possibly that is the explanation anyway. But at least now you have the observation, in case you can connect it with other similar observations.

One day at the end of May 1993 (unfortunately, I can't remember the exact date) at approx. 22.30 I was sitting at my typewriter when I suddenly get a strange feeling that someone is looking at me. I lived quite far out in the country at the time, and went to look out of the windows (if there was anyone outside). Above the forest, which I have a clear view of across the open field, some small white stars were floating around between the trees. I can't say how big they were as distance judgment is not my forte. But the size of the biggest stars we can see here from Earth. There were approx. 1 km over to the forest, I want to shoot. I went outside to take a closer look at the stars, but couldn't go very far as I had a sleeping child inside the house. It was a VERY beautiful sight. I stood looking at it for a long time. It's completely quiet there. After a while, a larger object came into view above the treetops. It looked like a ball with a ring around it, and pulsated in red, green (blue) and white. The ball floated over the trees, making a strange pattern. Still no sound. I remember looking at the clock and seeing that a quarter of an hour had passed. My boyfriend at the time comes home from work and sees the lights too. The bullet stopped for a moment and then disappeared over the Jels lakes. It was an indescribably beautiful experience that I would not have been without. I always had a nice feeling of "calm". In addition to the observation, I would just like to add: We were very "impressed" by what we had seen and contacted a "UFO connoisseur" who lives/lived near Lunderskov. Unfortunately I can't remember his name. He came and took a report, but unfortunately I don't know where it ended up. I am also very grateful to him because he came out and talked to us (and at the same time helped us get rid of our "ghost"). And because he took us seriously when others just thought we were crazy.

We saw it from our windows on the 1st floor on May 4 at 22:45. The object calmly ascended to a great height and descended again a few times until it disappeared. Have others also seen it, and do you have a possible explanation for what we have seen?

Walked my dogs in our front yard. Always looking up for shooting stars and the stars. Saw a really big round disc fly from east to west at high speed. It had no lights at all. I only saw it by chance that I happened to be looking where I was looking. It shadowed the stars... I think I saw it again the following evening, and then it came from the south and turned sharply to the west again at high speed. If you imagine that it could make itself invisible, but that you could see the glare of the stars in the outline of the circle, that is what I saw.

At approximately 21.20 me and my parents drive in the direction of Grenaa along the A16 highway in Djursland. On a ridge near the "town" of Langkastrup, we suddenly see 2 pulsating objects in a northeasterly direction. The objects are whitish, round and appear to be pulsating. In the background and above the objects, brief flashes of light that look like lightning are observed, but we cannot see the "lightning branch" itself. We descend into a valley, and the objects, however, disappear from view. In the meantime, we are talking about the fact that a week or 2 ago my father and mother observed exactly the same phenomenon. When we then come out into an open area, we now see 3 objects. They are VERY clear against the dark sky. There are some stars and the moon lies behind the observers and is "half". It is very clear to see that the objects are not illuminated, but emit the powerful light themselves. The mysterious "background flashes" are constantly observed throughout the incident. A little later, 2 of the objects suddenly disappear. It looks like they "fade" into the background, but still quite quickly. We find this very strange, and when a roundabout appears with a road heading towards the objects, we decide to drive towards them. We are maybe 1-2 kilometers from home and we are considering whether to pick up my video camera and regular camera. However, we decide to continue towards the lights. The number of objects varies greatly, and 3 times 7-8 lights are observed at once. Several cars follow us, although I can't be sure that it's after the lights. At one point we pass a lake, and the water is clearly illuminated by the objects. 2 of the objects, (appeared to be the smallest) are very close to each other. The other 6 hover around them in an irregular cluster. The direction is directly north or slightly northeast of us now. I estimate the height from approx. 3x the tree line and 20-25 tree lines up to the top object. We are now on the Nordkystvejen northwest of Allingaabro, and another roundabout appears. My father says the lights are over the "Hevring camp", a military area. Therefore, we take a road at the roundabout that goes towards Hevring. The 7 lights have now disappeared and a single one remains. The remaining light now looks like it is falling just as quietly into an underlying forest, and we turn around and drive back. Arriving at the roundabout northwest of Allingaabro, we now observe the objects in an easterly direction, a good distance away. They are still very powerful and pulsating, and the strange "lightning flashes" are observed again. We turn left onto the Nordkystvejen, which just goes in an easterly direction. Since we can easily get back home from this, we decide to follow the lights a bit. It looks like they are quite a distance away and we decide to drive home. Unfortunately, I don't know what it was, but it was beautiful! Personal background and information: I am very interested in storms, and have therefore acquired a video camera and camera to "capture" lightning. I remember having a discussion earlier in the day with a meteorologist from Berlin. We talked about the possibility of thunderstorms the following afternoon, so I followed the lightning radar closely. However, no thunderstorms came near Denmark all day, and as I said, no lightning had occurred between 21-22. My mother works at Gl. Estrup, which is right near Auning, and we then live on Gl. Estrup. 2 observations have been made of the objects from this location at other times.

Very bright red with a blue tinge around it. Looked like scar to be ball shaped. Couldn't see any flashes or hear any sound. Fly at steady high speed. Fly in the direction from kbh/Christianshavn towards Dragør. Seen on Brigadevej until it disappeared over the rooftops... Maybe a Russian satellite remnant, but it must have been around 15-16/1 and I don't know if the direction would be suitable either. Just know it wasn't a plane I saw... Unfortunately didn't get any pictures.

I looked up at the sky because I heard a large airliner. I always look for them. That's why I spotted a bright dot right next to the plane, just higher up. My first thought was that it must be a balloon. But it was as if at times it stood still, and at other times moved. It actually looked like a star, but they don't move visibly. Besides, they don't shine so brightly, so you can see them on a sunny April day at noon. I probably watched the object for 5-10 min while it got fainter (maybe went higher) and then a big cloud drifted under it and I didn't see it again. As many as 3 large airliners passed by the object, they must have seen something in rows......or what.......

Was out walking the dog when I see a 5-krona-sized glowing "spot". It shines very brightly, and suddenly it seems to fly downwards towards the ground, and is probably 10 degrees above the horizon, standing completely still. Suddenly it lights up very strongly, and disappears at a furious speed towards the west. It's definitely not a man-made "light" at the speed it was going, it's not something that exists here among us humans!

Driving by car on country road E55 in a northerly direction between Væggerløse and Tjæreby Tang, when we see something in the night sky that resembles a shooting star. The speed was somewhat slower than a shooting star in my opinion, and the white tail was also much stronger and more distinct. Just before it disappears completely, there are two small "explosions" with a very short interval - perhaps within the same second.

White light moving at very high speed from east to west south west. At first I thought it was a meteor/shooting star, but the speed and appearance of the light do not seem consistent with a meteor. Observation time is quite precise. Maybe Skrydstrup has caught something on the radar?

We sat for a while in Holstebro and grilled at the same time as we had made a fire. As I had just returned from my home with my spectacles, and a comrade and I were about to test them, when he sighted a luminous orb in a south-westerly direction, moving quietly inland. It glowed constantly and not like something burning in the atmosphere. After a very short time it disappeared... I have seen quite a few things in the sky also rare pieces of meteors which fall through the clouds, but never anything like this. We are approx. 8 people who saw it.

I go to the window and look out and see 5 lights (yellow), the 4 of them in a square and the last one in front of the 4, in line with the top 2 lights. They were far, far too close to each other to be airplanes, and there were no flashes of wings. I am very interested in flying and can say with 100% certainty that it was not. The light in the 5 objects varied in intensity and they moved completely silently. The 5 objects held their formation across the sky until the lights disappeared behind clouds. I managed to take a very blurry picture, but due to the long exposure, it is quite difficult to see. Shortly after the 5 objects have disappeared, another appears in the southwest and behaves like the other 5 across the sky, still completely silent.

Have seen many shooting stars. But never before it comes straight down and suddenly stops in the middle of the sky, as if someone turns off the light. And approx. 4 minutes later it turns left at a very, very high speed up approx. 80 to 90 degrees. Has not had a friend or similar present. Always trying to analyze what it could be, but what I saw today...

When I was waiting for the bus here - down in Vesterbrograde, I suddenly noticed some flying objects in the sky. I saw 1 out of the corner of my eye and knocked it away again. But then 2 more came, and they flew in a straight line with approx. 2-3 meters distance between each other. The light was strong and yellowish. And my first thought was: That's not how planes fly. I don't know how high they were when they disappeared, when they disappeared behind some buildings. But high up they were. There was another person who was waiting for the bus too - I didn't get to talk to him because my bus was coming - but I could see from him that he saw the same thing. Because he looked at me wonderingly. I have never seen such lights in the sky before and I know what a plane in the night sky looks like. These two weren't planes, but what they were, I don't know. Can anyone tell what it is or have an idea?

Me and a friend stand and look up at the starry sky, where 3 white constant lights form a triangle, height ??? maybe 2 km, distance between the dots maybe 500 meters, there is no sound - the movement is constant, the distance between the white lights is the same, duration 10-15 minutes. 3 other friends come and see the same thing and none of us have seen this before. We have a couple of friends who saw the same thing over Varde 2 years ago, but it was 3 triangles. I remember similar phenomenon being shown on television 10-15 years ago from Belgium (I think it was Sat1) showing this. I have no idea what it is, I don't think it can be eg F16 as there was no sound, satellites maybe, but having worked in the weather service (military) I have never seen satellites fly like that. Weather balloons don't fly like that either, so who knows?

Hello. Saw a UFO for 1 time in my life. On a drive from Smørum over dark roads to Risby, we saw 3 times some round big light in the sky, dim because of the clouds. The light came at high speed from our left to right, stopped almost abruptly, hung for a short time, flew back in the direction from which it came, this too at high speed.

We saw what we first thought was a star, a white dot, approx. At 22.20. There was also a vertical "chemtrail" track, which is often seen after aircraft, but this dissipated fairly quickly, leaving only the "star" behind. We looked towards the sunset at dusk, there were no other stars in the sky, so we thought it was a bit strange (and even against the light of the sunset!) We looked in the opposite direction for a split second, and when we looked back again, the "star" suddenly gone. We observed this star-like light for max. 2 minutes before it disappeared, pist away.

It is star clear and walking the dogs as I have done for 25 years. Goes in an east direction and looks at the Charlemagne to the north, turns his head a little to the west and sees a boomerang-shaped figure coming very quickly from the NW to the south - it is semi-transparent and makes after approx. 2 seconds of violent manoeuvres, which surprises me as I am used to seeing defense aircraft practicing over our area. The maneuvers take place for approx. 4 sec and is a turn of 45-90 degrees and the speed is at least 10 x a fighter plane ??? Swing to the right the horizon around and disappear to the SW as if at impossible speed - I'm shocked - also used to see satellites and planes in general so no... I estimate that the object (like a boomerang). was approx. 1,500 m - 2,500 m up. What is subsequently surprising is that the object was gray-black and semi-transparent, like when a magnifying glass is passed over light very quickly - as I said, I am quite ordinary and not particularly interested in UFOs, but have a solid education and a fair amount of knowledge of science and can say for sure that gravity was out of the game.

Luminous object, flew directly north over Skanderborg city center, did not blink at any time, a plane came flying in a higher trajectory across the object's trajectory. Couldn't seem to hear any sound either.

We are on the balcony when a "ball" suddenly appears in the sky, just above the ridges of the houses approx. 300 m away. The ball is estimated to be the size of a large beach ball. At first the ball moves a little closer, but suddenly it moves at high speed vertically up to a height where it stands still for a longer time and here almost looks like a normal star (however, it shines brighter and more orange than the real stars. 2-3 times, while it "stands still" in the sky, it makes a quick movement to the same side, only to quickly move back to the same position again. We keep an eye on it and get the camera out, but unfortunately only when it is well up in the sky After about 8-10 minutes it fades away and eventually it's out of sight maybe behind clouds(?) It's been over a week now and we've run through all the logical explanations without getting any wiser.In my opinion, its trajectory, speed and its very spherical shape do not connect with a hot air balloon..

My husband and I were standing in our yard when I look up and see 2 round white/shiny "balls". I show it to my husband, who thinks it's a plane. I have my camera with me (I always have it when I'm in our garden, it's my hobby to photograph various flowers etc.) So I manage to photograph the 2 balls that are slowly moving towards the south. I saw both bullets very clearly. In the 1st photo I took, one bullet is very clearly visible and the other is very faintly delineated. 12 seconds later I took a new picture, and there it is clearly gone, and you can only make out the weak one, the other one disappeared. I have seen on your site that there is almost the same observation on 17.06.2010.

We just got home and were just inside the house with some things. We didn't turn on very many lights in the house when we returned to the car. We both get out to the car when we simultaneously spot a very large and very clearly shining object in the sky. It is very far down compared to shooting stars, airplanes etc. (approx. 80 m up in the air and approx. 800-1,000 m. away) We are looking towards Guldborg with our backs to Øster Kippinge when this happens. This luminous object (looked like an "i" which is laid down - some bright white light - little light to the right and longer/bigger light to the left) was very close, was very bright in the sky - suddenly appeared in the sky and was suddenly gone again with inhuman speed. Completely silent. Starry evening with many planes in the sky. The object was nowhere near being an airplane or shooting star.

2 clear golden points appeared in the sky to the west with the same direction and with too short a distance between them to be planes. The speed was great and there was no sound. 1 minute later 4 new lights appeared with the same direction. One of them turned left and appeared to fall down and burn up. We could see some kind of flame around it. Ilse and I believe in something man-made, but we don't know of anything that can fly so high at such great speed and without a sound. Others must have seen them. They were very evident on this beautiful summer evening.

I was standing with my wife in my apartment in the living room on the 5th floor, where we have a nice view of the harbor and the water, when my eyes suddenly caught a clear, yellowish object which was moving relatively slowly across the sky. In my field of vision from right to left. At first I was afraid that it was a plane that had caught fire, but the speed of the "fireball" and the fact that no sound was heard disproved this. The object was moving at an uneven pace - medium to slow - mainly from right to left, but also apparently vertically. A constant fire-like light in the form of a round dot. The brightness was like a smaller burning fire in the sky. When I went to get a camera, the light "went out". (This was observed exclusively by my wife). She described it as if "the fire suddenly went out high in the air". She is unsure whether she glimpsed a slight smoke development. No signs of crash, explosion or anything else. The light/fire quickly faded in just a few seconds. Not so dark yet at this time - Very clear weather. I'm a little unsure about compass direction (not my strong point). But observed the object while standing with my gaze directed straight ahead to the horizon - the object was slightly to the right in my field of vision and then moved centrally so that it was almost exactly in the center of my field of vision from the center of the window in the apartment.

I skimmed your brochure on celestial phenomena and what I saw did not match any of the examples. I live far out in the countryside in Midtlolland - there are no street lights here, so you can see a lot of the sky. This was neither a satellite in orbit, an airplane, a star, comet or meteor - nor laser light. I have seen these phenomena before and can recognize them well. I went out to the yard yesterday approx. at midnight and my attention was drawn to what I at first thought was a bright bright star or planet standing almost vertically above my head. Got to thinking it couldn't be Venus because it's not that high in the sky. It stood - like a star - in the same place without moving, but began to shine brighter and brighter until there was an "explosion of light" or a very powerful flash of light, much bigger than the "star" itself. Then it immediately began to move, at the same time as the light faded. I followed its movement approx. 5-10 degrees, and then it was gone. I have observed almost the same phenomenon once more within the last year. Then it was just lower towards the horizon and moving from a northerly direction to the east. I know that there was a strong meteor impact on Lolland approx. a year ago - I saw that too - and it was not the same phenomenon.

I'm out photographing with my husband. We each have our own camera. I take 5 pictures where my husband is on. At the 3rd photo, something suddenly comes along that surprises me, I forget to look up, only look at the photo, then I just take 2 more. When I put the pictures on my computer, I can see that there is also something on picture 5. At the same time, I see that there is a bright spot on picture 1, on the right. Perhaps you have a natural explanation.

I have here for the evening of 9/2 at 19:45 saw some strange lights in the sky north west of Langå. First came 5-6 lights moving west, then 1 and then 2 more - all in less than 5 min. I went outside but couldn't hear anything - but I think they were too far away. I guess the speed was helicopter speed, but the lights seemed constant, and I mean there should be strobe lights on a helicopter - isn't that right? Besides, we don't have that many helicopters in Denmark, do we?

On 27.12.2011, at approx. 00.35 I see above Odinsvej in Frederikshavn a rotating white light above the clouds. It looks like being sent around from an invisible center, like a vertical cone of light from a lighthouse and silently. It seems to be right above the clouds. The height is estimated at approx. 100 m, and the light is thrown around or rotates clockwise at a calm and completely stable pace. Two witnesses. Observed for approx. 15 minutes Immediately afterwards, the antenna signal disappears for the entire area for several hours.

This story I want to tell here, and which I have often thought about, happened in 1994. My daughter was 5 years old at the time. Unfortunately, I can't remember the date and time. We live in Silkeborg by Gødvad. One afternoon at approx. 1 p.m. my daughter comes in. I ask her what she has been doing out there. Then she tells me this story. I had my daughter draw a drawing of her experience. She drew a round UFO with a ladder going down. She told while she was drawing that it was a man and a lady who helped them up into the UFO and down again. I talked to the friend's parents if they had heard anything about a UFO, they hadn't. I asked the kindergarten if they had had any games with this topic, but no. I often wonder if it was a vivid imagination or if it was true. I saved the drawing, but haven't been able to find it since.

My girlfriend was lying on the couch watching Erin Brokowich on DR1 when she sees a red light high in the sky. She tells me that because it has more speed than airplanes normally do. I go to the window and see a bright red circular light - like a parachute rocket on New Year's Eve. I can see it speeding up and rush over to our patio door as I say "if it's a plane it's making noise". I unlock the door and go out onto the patio and look up, it's like it's slowing down sharply and it stops before it's passed our house. I call my girlfriend as I think it's a bit spooky, she looks up, but quickly disappears back inside. It just stays standing for approx. 30 seconds - all the time with the same light intensity, but then it increases sharply in a straight easterly direction. After 15 seconds I can't see it anymore. I've always liked watching aviators and was good at spotting the types, but this one I've never seen before, such a bright red light with a halo around it, and with that speed it disappeared - without smoke or sound .

My ten-year-old son, my six-year-old daughter and I are standing in the driveway waving goodbye to a playmate. At the same moment they are driving away, we suddenly see a glowing ball in the sky. All three look up and think at first that it is an emergency rocket. It stood still, looked a bit like the moon, only smaller and with a very white light, and suddenly it disappeared like a shooting star!! When we look at the moon, it appears to be half as high up. Hm...... Wondering what it was? Didn't look like anything we've ever seen before and have no idea what it could have been. There was and is nothing mysterious about it. It was there just as suddenly and was gone just as quickly!

I was eating when I saw two yellow/orange balls fly towards my living room window in Brønshøj... I called my sister and explained what I had seen... It probably took a total of 7 min. before, it was gone again... When I talk to my sister on the phone, I explain to her. that another bullet is coming.... And I record the incident... I was TOO freaked out to record it the first time (unfortunately).... My sister and her daughter (who is in kbh. northwest) go out on their balcony and look. if they can see anything - they SEE a single ball in the sky, the same color as I have explained... Both times they have flown very fast... However, the second time was the fastest, and it is as if object slows down, and it seems like an eternity before it comes out on the other side of my apartment's windows... And I can again see the object flying towards Brønshøj... To disappear again... I would like to know what these 3 bullets were... The whole incident probably took approx. 15 min... But didn't get to look at the clock.. Only that it was while I was eating, which was between 6-7pm... Hope others have seen these balls other than just us 3 girls...

I sat at Trekroner station v.RUC. at was about 23.45. Plus, 5 luminous chalky, almost luminescent round shapes appeared above the RUC out of nowhere. The sky was dark blue, there were no clouds and not many stars, and there were no airplanes nearby. The white balls flew in a row, but when they were nearer to me they went into formation like airplanes, i.e. 1 ball at the front and the four at the back like a v shape. When I looked closer, it looked like the orbs became elongated, as if they had wings on almost futuristic and tilted up and down, as if they were going to "hunt". When they were over the Bauhaus, it disappeared, like someone accidentally turning off a remote control. The whole series was silent and high in the sky, but very strange, especially because they were so white and luminous.

A white sunlit round object is seen from Zoo (Elephants) direction 270 degrees, elevation 45-50 degrees, moving slowly to the east, then stationary, then slowly in a NE direction, occasionally stationary. Height above the ground is estimated to be around 3000 - 6000 feet assessed in relation to scheduled aircraft during west-east approach. The object must certainly have been seen from the plane's cockpit obliquely to the left, but somewhat higher up. The immediate impression after looking at the object for about 10 minutes was that it was a larger drone, although it was at a very high altitude. In that case, it must be registered by the aviation authorities. A free floating weather balloon would have moved differently in my experience. Therefore, the object must have been controlled. Unfortunately, it was not possible to get a recording with either mine or my wife's mobile cameras.

The object moved quickly, completely silently. I took a picture with my mobile phone, but it's not very descriptive. At times it looked like a flame in the sphere. During the day, it happens that there are hot air balloons that fly over the area, but it was pitch black, and there was no sound to be heard, like when there are flames in the balloon. It also moved faster.

Bright white light zooms up. (Think it's a satellite at first), but the light zooms up strongly for a few seconds, then zooms down again. The object then moves north and disappears. It is just like the afterglow of a halogen bulb when it is switched off. I don't mean speed and course were uniform. I'm 100% sure it wasn't the solar collectors on a satellite. The object stood still while it was shining. Distance according to my best estimate is approx. 3000 m.

properties.Remarks: Forklaring: Bryllup på Havartigården i Holte!  Balloner med hjerter!se beretning

properties.content: I was lying in my bed and woke up to sudden noises outside our apartment. I immediately find it difficult to identify the sound and think that it is probably some people on their way home from the city. What I just wondered about was that there wasn't a conversation going on. It took approx. 3 minutes before a strong beam of light shone through our window. When I woke up the following morning, I checked DMI's website to see if lightning had been recorded over Funen during the night, but there wasn't. I don't know what it could have been. But I'm sure it's light from upstairs, as we live at 2nd floor height, while our bedroom window is a skylight that leans up to the sky. After the beam of light, the rumble I heard first intensified, so it sounded like there were several people working on something. It's hard to describe that sound, but it was like someone was standing and working on some different things some distance away (in a nearby green space). I have not yet heard from neighbors if they have observed anything.

My husband and I were going swimming. As I observe a larger reddish ball coming from the southwest direction. At first I think it is a plane that has caught fire, as I see embers falling from it, but there is no sound to be heard. I call my husband and he sees the same thing, we cycle off, at the same time the sphere turns west, and approx. 1 min. later it is gone.

In 1967 I lived in Vesterbro in an apartment. I had to draw the curtains, and plus I saw up in the sky 5 UFOs in a v-shaped formation, the right one vibrating with its wing. The UFOs looked like boomerangs, they were glowing orange and flew at great speed without a sound to the east. It should be said that it was the day after the Russians had launched a rocket into space, if that matters.

4 pcs. in rhombus shape followed by 3 in a straight line (clear red) looked sore. (For the wind?) They were under the clouds, later under clear skies. Kept exactly the same distance from each other. They disappeared one by one, each one suddenly disappearing without fading.

Formation of 5-7 diffusely but clearly uniform luminous objects in the colors yellow, green, red and blue moving at a steady speed across the sky from “at. 10.00“. "At 12.00“ 2 objects join the formation from a southern direction. 3 more green objects join the formation behind. The very back green object hangs still on the horizon "at 14.00“ for 30-60 seconds after the rest have disappeared from view. A total of 10-12 objects appeared. Each individual object had a size that was experienced as approx. 10 times a satellite. What did we see?

My husband, who is an aerospace engineer, and I saw last night a large fireball flying over Dragør for a long time, as if it was orbiting at a lower altitude under cloud cover. It burned from it. We saw it from when it was a glimmer on the horizon until it disappeared over the airport towards Sweden. We got really high when it was clear that it was a spherical thing with fire in it. We can't figure out what it was though! Has anyone else seen anything? I have a few photos of the bullet. After a while it occurred to us to get a camera, but it just looks like a small dot on the iphone. Cool experience. It seemed bigger.

I drove from Rudkøbing towards Bagenkop approx. at 17. For 20 min. could I see a large (larger than a planet - smaller than the moon) and very clearly shining something-or-other in the sky, in the same place and above the clouds. I lost sight of it when I had to avoid an accident - possibly it's just the clouds covering it.

I was on my way home in my car when I suddenly saw what I thought was a plane at first, but the flight pattern and how close it was made no sense. It was dark so couldn't really see what shape it was, but it had a white flashing light, which is why I thought it was a plane at first. Then another appeared, this one with a blue flashing light and a small red light that flashed a little fainter than the blue. The two crossed each other in flight pattern. At this point I had stopped the car to hear if it could be drones or a helicopter but I couldn't hear anything. They disappeared as quickly as they appeared.

Friday night at around 00:10 I was sitting in my office, and suddenly I happened to look out of the window and saw a very powerful shooting star. It came from a northern direction and flew south, approx. 20 degrees above the horizon in a westerly direction. It had a long tail behind it and shone very brightly. Lasted about 3 seconds. Could it have been a meteor? The distance was very difficult to judge and the size as large as a pea in an outstretched arm. It looked like it "squirted" from the head, like something fell off??

Saw a reasonably large red ball come from the south-west and then disappear in a north-easterly direction, 40 degrees approx. The speed was reasonably fast. It was 10:15 p.m. It was a strange experience. Never seen it before.

After gymnastics on Tuesday evening, I cycled home along Torstedallé and saw a very clear luminous UFO in the sky. It came over Bygholm forest from east to west and looked like an enlarged Haley's comet. A large glowing ball with a long red tail trailing behind it. I would like to hear if anyone else has seen it and if there is an explanation.

Observation at 19.40 DST. Whether the lights are double triangles, as can be seen on film, I have subsequently become unsure, as I can see that the triangles are only visible when the camera can't figure out how to focus. But I have not been able to reproduce this effect. I have no idea what it was we saw. There was no sound about it, so if they were planes, they must have been very high up. If it was a plane, then the light might be reflections from the sun, since it is not that long after sunset. And the sun might well be shining on planes that were a few kilometers up. However, the size of the lights was so large that I somewhat doubt this. The video camera is a Panasonic NV-GC280, which has a 3.0-30 mm Leica optic. (This corresponds to an SLR with 42-430mm optics). I would very much like to clarify what it was we saw.

Was out walking the dog in our garden, and had just observed a satellite, when 3 reddish objects with a luminous core appear in a formation like a right-angled triangle, 1 in front and 2 behind. An outstretched hand would cover the area as they spread across the sky. They were visible for approx. 2-3 seconds, there was no flashing or light trace. The speed was significantly higher than airplanes and spaceships, but approx. 50% of the speed of a shooting star. Never seen anything like it before

New Year 2013/2014 in Copenhagen was fantastic, and the rockets went off from midnight. Henad at approx. Between 00:45 and 01:15 both my son and I became aware that something was different. I was standing in the living room with my sister looking out over the meat town and up into the sky and saw many beautiful colors from the rockets and my son was in the room facing the yard with his mates. But he happened to be looking out the window at the same time I spotted the strange light in the sky. At first we thought it might be the Japanese paper gizmos that you send up with fire in them, but they burn up and don't move to the side in the same way that this strange light suddenly did. I followed it intensely with my eyes and it was flaming in a kind of oval shape and in the middle of the oval shape, it was black. Between the flaming outline and the inner part of it, it was separated by another black ring, so you actually got two oval flaming shapes in one big one. It wasn't until it suddenly changed direction exactly opposite of where it was going that I thought... this is not normal at all. The pace was ultra slow. It came closer and closer and I could now clearly see the flaming oval shapes and opened my window on the 5th floor and there was no sound. By then the rockets were dwindling in number and the oval shape was even more apparent. It was headed over the ridge of the building I lived in, and suddenly my son looked out the window and said, what the hell is that?
