He saw the change of direction once more and berated it completely like me afterwards. He observed no engine noise and stood for a long time watching it in the balcony doorway. Suddenly it disappeared in a new direction, but at high speed and gone it was. We both knew there were some smaller planes filming all the glory over Copenhagen on New Year's Eve, but... there was no sound... and no, we weren't drunk. So whatever it was we saw, it wasn't exactly ordinary.

I know it's a bit far-fetched, but saw something about a lot of dead fish on Als and got to thinking --- around the same time it was in the news that many saw comets and meteorites in Sweden/Norway, I was in the garden in the evening and got a huge shock when I saw a light in the clouds that very quickly came down vertically at great speed and disappeared behind the island of Enehøje from where I was standing on Kongestien in Sletnæs. If you draw a line in between, I think it fits with the current in the water ---- it went very quickly and was over in 6-7 seconds. It was a sharp ball of light with a fairly short tail --- it's the wildest thing I've seen in my life.

I was standing with my girlfriend on the balcony and smoking a cigarette when we saw a bright bright star/star shape move at a reasonable speed (slightly faster than an airliner) from the west steering, to the east without a sound. We saw other airliners passing its path higher up, making noise and flashing as usual. The light created gave a star shape (8-star), the slanted tips were long and bright white, the horizontal tips were short and blue, and the vertical ones were barely visible. We stood on the balcony, which faces west-southwest and followed it from west to east, and the light disappeared just as it passed the ridge of the roof. SUFOI's comment: The observation is probably due to the International Space Station ISS, which can be seen passing over the southern sky at times. The space station appears in the night sky as a powerful light that moves slowly in a path from west to east. On 4 May, the ISS could be seen from Gudme in the time period at 23:13:05 (appearance) and until 23:16:18 (disappearance). The ISS appeared to the west-southwest at an altitude of 10 degrees above the horizon and disappeared to the south-southeast at an altitude of 36 degrees.

I live just outside Horsens (15 km). As my girlfriend and I sit outside, we see a large orange ball to the west rising slowly into the air. When I hold my hand out against it, it is almost the size of my thumb nail. We follow it approx. one to two minutes. and then it changes direction and flies diagonally up to the north. We run in for a camera to film it, but then it's so small that it's hard to see anything, so we get binoculars and can see it. It has a lot of small lights in different colors. We also see something smaller to the southwest, but it's so small that it's hard to tell what was where.
Look at the night sky. Just followed a satellite south-north! Suddenly, a muffled red explosion high up high! No sound!, - I wonder what it could be, and have others also seen it? - and it was gone.

Saw what I thought was a satellite above the sky in said direction, northeast to southeast. Over the next 10 minutes, eight others came in the same lane, two in the opposite direction. Four of them flew in pairs in slanted formation. Of the last two in pairs, one overtook and the other, which slowed its speed, turned a little to the east. Due to tall trees in the garden I could not see their vanishing point. At the very end, a very bright one, like the brightest of the stars, flew with relatively fast speed from southwest to east and disappeared behind a treetop.
It looked like a star flying in circles, zig zagging up and down and flying across the sky to the right and back to the left and again in circles.... It remained in the sky when I went to sleep .

I am writing because I have just seen something VERY strange, I am an amateur astronomer myself and know all about various celestial phenomena! But I have just on March 8 at 21:19 observed something I have never seen before. An object that moved due west moving east and passed across the sky at approx. 45 sec. It shone bright yellow-orange with a brightness similar to that of Venus, the intensity varied slightly across the sky and at one point appeared to flash, i.e., the brightness decreased and then increased again. My own explanation is that it must be a car, but a big one of its kind!

Yesterday, approx. at 23:55 me and my friends made an unusual observation. We found ourselves at Smukfest Copenhagen. The Petshop Boys had just gone into full swing playing their music. My friend knows that I tend to look up in the air and see various patterns and shapes in the clouds, so she made a joke about it during the concert, which automatically made me look up at the starry sky. All of a sudden, two bright lights shine. Their circumference is considerably larger than the stars in the sky, and they also shine much brighter, so they stand out quickly. I alert my friends and also people standing around us to the strange light phenomenon that shines unusually bright in the sky. Suddenly the focus is off the concert, which is playing out there, and up into the air. The two powerful lights suddenly begin to move. They fly at an ok high speed into the air, side by side, but not in a straight line, as, for example, a plane would. They circulate almost straight out, and follow each other in their movements. Suddenly they disappear over the horizon. It was an amazing sight! Now it's the next day, and I just sat and wrote with my other friend, who also saw it, about it. I have read through some of your reports to see if there were others who had seen something similar. and your conclusions based on it. You mentioned something about satellites flying next to each other, but from what I could understand they were supposed to be moving at a slow speed. These two bright lights we saw yesterday were moving at a much faster pace, and it also doesn't look like what we saw when I search other people's satellite footage, which could be mistaken for something unidentified. Smukfest Copenhagen took place at Amager, out on 10øren. The phenomenon took place approx. at 23:55-23:58. It is the first time in my life that I have experienced something so unusual.

It was a very clear and completely windless evening. I have always cast my gaze towards the sky. It was cloudless. I had just said goodbye to my in-laws. As I stand and look up at the sky, a UFO comes over the roof of a factory, which is close to the house. It might stop to look at me. On the upper side it was black dented and shiny, on the lower side there were windows all around with light in. It was not possible to see through these windows. In a split second there is a sound like when you strike a bamboo stick through the air, and it disappears into the stars with a trail of fire in a few seconds. The UFO is approx. 15 meters in diameter and 4 meters thick and lenticular. Three more to come. The first stays still for approx. 30 seconds, the other two fly exactly the same course. My wife sees #2.

Fluttering rotating dark object. Seen in the sky in almost the same place. Moved in small jerks. Too far away and up in the sky to be a bird. Don't fly like an airplane. Disappeared 2 times suddenly and then suddenly reappeared. Looked like absolutely nothing we had seen before. The balcony overlooks a bit of Køge Bugt, and it was in the direction of view towards Stevs that we saw it.

I was at a Gnags concert in Rudkøbing when I observed a bright orange-yellow "ball" in the night sky. The object, which came from the NW, was in motion and grew very quickly, before finally standing still for approx. 1 min above the festival grounds. The music stage was extremely brightly lit and it seemed as if this attracted the object's attention. It then turned 90 degrees and disappeared with lightning speed towards the SW. At no time did the object have any trail of fire or any other form of color or light. It was difficult to focus directly on the object because of its bright light, (like a kind of small sun) but by letting the eye focus a little next to the object, I could see the outline, and it without a doubt looked like the UFO that you use in your logo, albeit always slightly tilted. My wife and another festival goer also saw the object, but could not explain the phenomenon either, as it did not look like or behave like any other commonly known flying object It must be said that all three of us were perfectly sober (we had small children with us).

Smoking a cigarette as always before I go to bed. Looking at stars and tracking satellites. So no satellites on the day. Looking straight up. And see 3 faint, orange dots, which are not planes and not satellites. There is no sound. They fly side by side. The one on the far right moves towards the one in the middle. They fly south south-east. I have never seen anything like it before. Has tracked lots of satellites. And once saw the ISS coming from west to east. But this was something I haven't seen before.

I was waiting for the harbor bus, when I saw an object that looks like fire, with a black oblong central core, due South. It moves very slowly straight down, and then starts to slope slightly to the east, before approx. 15.59 disappears. It seems as if the black central core is burning up, because it gets smaller and smaller before it disappears, and only the fire remains - then the fire dies out. I have never seen anything like this and wondered if it could be a meteor or similar, however my boyfriend claims they burn up much faster than was the case here.

I'm in my room looking out the window. I then look up over the house and spot it. A small ball of light. At first I thought it was a bird reflecting the lights of the city, but when I saw it fly, it was in zig-zags and arcs. I could watch it for 30 sec. before it disappeared into a cloud cover. I don't quite know what it could be, but I doubt a bird. Because the core of it was a lot clearer than the surrounding. Hope you have the answer.
Just seeing a vertical upward stream of air and thinking it looks so puffy and couldn't be a plane. May have been a rocket, but it flew very slowly and saw no explosion.
Crossed the sky at breakneck speed, then rising and then it was gone. Three white lights flashed next to each other in turn, then a red one below the three white...

I happen to look out the window, across the square and see a big orange light moving very slowly, call my mate and open the window. Coincidentally, my girlfriend is walking down the square with our dog and she had already seen it and was yelling at me like crazy. Me and my companion managed to record it until it just as quietly and silently disappeared to the north-northwest.

I'm out for a run (today's date, 19/02-2012) this evening. Coming running past the parking lot at Næstved Stadium, and then down a road called Meistersvej in Næstved. Looking at the sky west-southwest approx. at 20:53 a very sharp "star" or shooting star in the sky. The "star" begins to fall slowly downwards and suddenly disappears. I don't know what I may have seen, and am not entirely sure if it could be a shooting star, which I have otherwise only seen at high speed.

Then a globular white luminous object, much larger than the largest stars in the sky appear to be. Picked up my son, who filmed it with his iPhone, but the recording is very blurry. There were small short beams of light around the object, just like you see with small halogen spots, don't know if it's one's eyelashes that make it look like that. It seemed to be way up and if that is correct my son thinks it was flying faster than a normal airplane, I find it hard to judge speed myself. The object flew in a straight line, no noise was heard from it. My son is convinced it's some secret military hardware, I don't know if it was "just" a plane flying with some special light for some reason, but he says planes MUST flash green , red and perhaps white, and the object had a constant and very strong white light all the time. Is it correct that airplanes should flash?
Suddenly a very fast and low thing appeared, it was moving very fast, it made a small change of course, but the high speed must have caused many, many G's.

Here at my house we have set (auto) Video surveillance. That is that it monitors by movement. This Sunday night, the camera has picked up a very strange light. Only when I went through the footage, I thought it was someone who wanted to break in, because of the strong light. But I couldn't imagine such a powerful flashlight, our house is about 3 meters high and the light seemed to come from further up. It appeared on the camera at 03.08 and disappeared fifty seconds later, then reappeared at 03.15 for another 50 seconds. I myself cannot see a logical explanation for the phenomenon.

Drove off the motorway at Aarhus from Galten, after which I saw three orange glowing balls, which at one point separated and became three. Then they took different directions AND different speeds?? Very hard to judge the size but wondering if anyone else has seen it?

Larger yellow "fireball" as my father and mother describe it. It was observed from our living room in 9381 Ajstrup, and it looked as if it "crashed down"/disappeared in the direction of the neighboring town of Tylstrup. I thought I'd just write this instead of it just being quickly forgotten. I had just been out for a drive, and had my back to the observation point, and was about to park the car in the garage before I came in and my parents told me about the fireball, so unfortunately I didn't see it myself.
Two red glowing balls fly silently across the sky. Not flashed like an aviator and not that high in the sky at all. Not shooting stars nor emergency flares.? Never seen anything like...

We came by car from Rødkærsbro towards Levring. A few hundred meters before Levring, I (passenger) spotted a light to the west (direction of travel south). I assumed at first that it was a plane, but then became a bit doubtful when the light suddenly became a bit more "foggy"/diffuse, and lights (cones of light??) started to rotate around the foggy point. Then we stopped the car and the driver got out to observe while I stayed inside - observing. It seemed like the thing was standing still as it had become "foggy"/diffuse. However, I wanted to continue, as I was not completely pressured by the situation. So we drove on through Levring towards Kjellerup, but did not see the object. However, the assessment is not that it is a "flying saucer", but still believes that it can be a plane. Now, I'm not entirely sure what kind of lights might be on planes... but could it not have been a rotor flashing light on the bottom of the plane? That could explain it with those light cones. The plane has probably flown into a cloud, so the light becomes more diffuse/foggy - but the light cones from the rotor flashing are more clearly visible??

When my husband and I approx. 01.15 went out in the yard/garden on our farm, my husband suddenly said, there is a UFO flying (he usually doesn't believe in such things!!). And sure enough, when we looked to the west in the direction of Ringkøbing (there are 20 km. to Ringkøbing), we saw an oval luminous flying object flying around in a circular route (slightly changed position, not much, but same circular flight route ). It was 2-3 times the diameter of the moon and was surrounded by some haze/fog/cloudiness, yet very clearly oval UFO shaped (the way you imagine a flying saucer to be). The circular route was an "oblique circular route up and down", but at the same time away from us and towards us (the light was strongest when it was towards us). We kept an eye on it for a little over an hour, and when we went to bed a little past 2, it was still there (it could also be seen from the attic window and was still circling in the same area). There was no sound or anything strange. We have speculated a lot about what it could be. But we cannot find any logical explanation for that light (the nearest small village in that direction is 8 km. away and not in a direct line behind the UFO, and the nearest big city Ringkøbing is 20 km. away, there are no shops, companies or laser searchlights in that direction. There are only fields and farms and a gravel pit nearby. About 15 km away is a grass drying factory, but otherwise nothing. It flew up in the open sky about 40 degrees above the horizon (in between its orbit behind some trees by our neighbor's house), Its speed was quiet and calm, but at almost the same speed. It's hard to say how far away it was, but it was quite a distance. (We live on one of the highest points in the area and can see all the way to Nr. Lyngvig Lighthouse in clear weather. But the UFO was not in the same direction as Nr. Lyngvig Lighthouse, more north-west. the direction fits it.) Moreover, the weather was not clear, and the lighthouse could not be seen due to fog and cloudy weather. It wasn't stellar either. Whether it really was a flying saucer in the literal sense can be hard to dismiss... I wonder if anyone else has seen it?? It could be interesting to hear.

Latitude: 56.4738883972168 Longitude: 9.840555191040039. Original photo of a flock of geese blocking the road, but when reviewing the photos, 1, maybe 2 objects are clearly visible. Photo taken through windscreen with individual raindrops, but the object is clearly distinguishable from these.

I stood one starry evening in my backyard looking towards the North. In the distance I can see 3 luminous dots on the stripe. Might look like a big airplane, but not that far away. It is constantly moving across the northern sky towards the east. After I have observed the light for a few minutes, the heck takes off at the 2 outermost dots, and flies very quickly towards another luminous dot to the east. There they fly around for a while, while they seem to investigate something in the sky in a different direction. The last dot approaches, and then they fly together again towards the east. The time was about the year that President Buch was here in our longitudes. I don't think he was in Denmark, but maybe in one of the other Nordic countries. I wondered if it could be Airforce 1 with 2 fighters next to it, but it just couldn't really fit with the actual light in the sky. There was nothing that flashed or glowed red. Bright light only. As I sit here and replay the episode in my head, I vaguely remember that there was a lot of noise, like when a jet engine accelerates, but it just didn't quite match the speed of the lights.

Saw 3 orange objects - much larger than stars - pass across the sky from southwest to southeast at approx. one minute apart. There was no sound associated with the objects. They moved somewhat faster than an airplane.

5 small luminous points came floating - approx. 10 km away, No. 5 was playing with some movements - manner of flying - that no normal airplane can do, all were "moon colored" - speed must have been about 4-5 km per hour two inches above the horizon at an arm's length.

Coming walking and looking up at the sky. Sees something black, which in a slowly floating downward movement becomes clearer and clearer. Thinking it could be a skydiver or raptor as the nature of the movement would suit this. It's over Copenhagen, and there haven't been any planes. As the "falling" comes further down and more clearly in shape, I can see that it is at least not a parachutist, and I also find it difficult to imagine that it is a bird, partly because of its size, not heard of raptors of this size over Copenhagen, partly because of a verticality in what was observed, which was more reminiscent of a parachutist than a soaring raptor looking for prey. After following the observed for a while, while in a hovering downward movement it calmly descends further and further down, I run up to my wife, we live on the 4th floor, and call her to the window. Together we can observe a black spot in the sky that is now rising to eventually disappear. I am somewhat mystified by what I have seen and am interested to hear if there is an explanation for it, or other observations of it.

I was walking home from Fakta when I spotted a powerful orange/white ball of light pulsating a contraband. A little later it moved in a quick slightly soft arc slightly up and to the side and then hung back. When I saw it, I ran home as fast as I could and got my family out to see it too. After a while it moved again and then stood still for about a minute, then moved while the light almost went out, came back, almost went out, came back and then in an instant, the ball of light was gone!

properties.Colors: mørkegrå med turkis og røde lys
properties.content: Often sits and looks out the window in the dark. I see 4 or 5 lights flying close together, so I check the FlightRadar app to see which planes are flying so close, but there are no planes in the area. As they fly closer in my direction, I can see that they are horseshoe-like or U-shaped with many small turquoise and red lights on the "wings". I'm starting to think it could be oddly shaped drones, but they spin around themselves in different directions and have never seen a drone slowly spin around and fly upside down. I'm also thinking it could be balloons as that would explain the movement (switching positions with each other and spinning around) but the shape and all the bright lights on them is not normal for balloons. They fly over my building and then it's gone.

Crop circles/formations in cornfield. A large circle that is 80 m in diameter. 10 meters inside the circle comes another circle. From the center of the circle, three equal-sized leaf-shaped ones extend out. The center connects the three leaves with a small path. The ends of the leaf are connected to the large circle with again small paths. To the southeast, a wide "road" leads out towards an unmeasured circle where the grain is laid down in a spiral shape. TV2 Østjylland filmed the phenomenon and broadcast it on TV on Monday 7 August 2000. Subsequently, I was contacted by a man who has dealt with UFOs all his life, and he could tell that someone who had refueled had landed.

I see a white flash in the sky and this repeats itself. Then an object is seen that almost stands still in the sky or flies very slowly. There are lights that flash in the colors red, yellow and white. They flash at different intervals and the colored lines change position. When I get home, it's still in the sky, now flying slowly, relatively low and noiselessly past our house. The shape of the object, as seen from the lights, appears to be triangular.

Observation several years old, but I wrote down the process and after a discussion with colleagues have been persuaded to report on it: Date of observation: 1996.08.04. At about 18.20 Ermelundsstien near Lyngby (2800) immediately south of the Statoil tank on Klampenborgvej I saw a UFO (UFO for me to see, as I have never been able to find a "natural/rational" explanation for the sighting). I was tricked by the sound of a plane which made me look up. (I have always been interested in planes, have been gliding myself for many years, and it is a completely normal behavior for me to glance up when a plane passes. The one in question was a turbo-prop, probably the F50. At the same time that i saw the plane i saw something almost vertical above me which appeared spherical and metallic colored, probably lower than the turbo prop plane (but hard to judge).Both (plane & ufo) changed heading to some extent during the sighting, the plane to a more westerly direction, the UFO to a more northerly direction. Their "course crossings" occurred at an approximately 90 degree angle. The UFO turned to N/NW (estimated) and disappeared at a similar high speed, as the further it came away, looking more and more like an oval shape (may be correct, although I originally perceived a spherical shape, it was almost vertical from below).During the course, when it rapidly moves away, I perceive its flight as with alternating speed, or like dolphin flight.Without timing, I perceive the course as lasting 15-20 seconds, maybe a little more.

I could see the sun clearly through the hazy sky, and observed a rectangular object that remained completely fixed in the same place across the disk of the sun for the entire time I observed the phenomenon, a total of approx. 5 minutes. The object appeared to have sharp rectangular shapes and appeared completely black against the sun. I would like to attach a drawing of the sun and the object that shows the position of the object, as well as the size in relation to the sun, but do not know how to do it from this page. I tried to photograph it with the mobile camera at full zoom without success. I can't see it in the pictures, probably due to the camera's poor resolution when zooming, as well as too small a focal length. What can I have seen, are there stationary satellites in the form that can be seen from the earth with the naked eye?

Was out with rubbish from the school, where I look over towards the church, and see some twinkling lights in the sky, 3-4 pcs. and a constant light. At first I thought it was a helicopter, because the height would be approx. pass, but there is no sound, there usually is. Duration approx. 2-3 min. It must be said. that it is dark and there is snow.

I have this evening 1 May 2010 at 22.05 observed 4 flying objects over Roskilde. They flew rather quickly and they shone constantly, however they quickly disappeared "into thin air" towards Hedehusene (to the east). They disappeared as if they were disintegrating, so you couldn't follow them flying away. The whole thing took approx. 15-20 seconds. It was clearly not an airplane or a remote control toy. I have never seen anything like it, hence this email.

The observation was made in a SOBER state, and with that it must also be said that I am quite aware that it was not fireworks, despite the striking date. The object, about the size of a football (immediately) was seen flying in a precise, oblique line, almost exactly 45 degrees to the ground. The light was very strong, and the ball-round flying object was followed by a strongly luminous tail in the same colors. I must state that I am convinced that it is not a firework, since the object started 50-100 meters above the flight height of ordinary rockets, and since there was no sound/explosion. In addition to that, it can also be said that I subsequently observed 1 "normal" shooting star immediately after the above incident.

At 23.15 I stand at my kitchen window and am making coffee. Looking out my window and seeing an object flying approx. 250-300 m east of Jerup town, very low-lying. I run out to see if it's a plane. It is totally silent well enough with a red light on and a slowly flashing white light. It continued north towards Ålbæk and Skagen.

At It's about 00:30 and I'm with my girlfriend visiting her sister and husband in Rødøvre. When we go for a walk with our sister's dog one night, we can hear a strange rumble in the air. I notice 2 objects glowing orange light. Although the one object is only about 25 m above our heads, I cannot see its shape.. I then look over at Mathilde, and as I do so, I am flashed with a very bright light as if from a camera. I direct my gaze upwards again and can only see the one object which is closest to me, begin and almost "fade" into the night sky.

After looking at a colorful sky with rockets, a yellow light, which we first think is some kind of emergency rocket, slowly rose into the air. The light stays on for a while, after which it continues further up. The light gets stronger and changes to 2 red lights. Then it flies sideways, sometimes fast, then it stands still. Wild experience. My brother has had nothing to drink. I only until 17:00.

I was at home visiting my mother and drove from there around 22. She followed me out to the car, and we spotted a strong light, almost like a searchlight, which is directed towards the sky. We talked briefly about who and why this powerful light almost down by the fjord. Then I drove, still wondering about the light that I expected would disappear behind me when I passed the spot where the searchlight was. But soon after I discovered that the beam of light had now turned into something that looked like a luminous ball, white with a reddish tinge. For a brief moment I probably got a bit hot around the ears, but then convinced myself that if it was something unknown, supernatural, I probably couldn't do much anyway! However, I remember locking the car doors. From Vester Assels, where my mother lived and still lives, and home in Øksendal, where I live with my wife and our 3 children, who lived at home at the time, there is approx. 30 minutes drive and about 20 km. The ball of light followed me exactly the same distance on my right side, despite me turning and following the road home several times. Of course, I thought a lot on the trip, but I wasn't afraid at all, trusting then as now that my Creator would take care of me and make sure I got home to my family. When I reached home in the yard, I ran in after my wife and our children and told them to hurry up and get out. They all saw the ball of light, which for a short moment almost stood still, as if it wanted to say thank you for tonight or something like that, - then at high speed set a course for Sallingsund, and it was then out of sight. The family were naturally wide-eyed and amazed when I told them that I had been followed home all the way from Grandma's by the ball of light. We agreed that it had probably come to look after me, so I got home safely. We also agreed not to tell anyone about the episode, because of course we would be seen as clairvoyant, crazy or whatever. No one would believe us. My wife and I have been into the phenomenon and talked about it once since. What it was, I don't know and almost don't care, but we know what we've seen and that's it. What surprises me the most is that the phenomenon followed me at exactly the same distance all the way until I stopped in the yard at home. I don't remember when it was at all, but since all 3 children were at home and the eldest moved away when she turned 18 in 1978, it must have been before 1995.

Standing still above our heads, flashing green rhythmically. After approx. 4 minutes it suddenly moves off to the left. Kept still and blew to the right. Thus it zig-zagged 6-7 times down towards the horizon to the north and disappeared from view behind some trees.

I went out on my balcony a little past twelve to smoke a cigarette, during the voting for the Melodigrandprix. And when I had smoked half of my smoke I saw little lights coming from one point and then they split into 6-7 little smaller red/yellow dots. Then I went in to get my mobile camera on my Iphone 4 just to record it, to see it again, what it was. They then flew towards the N for a 3-5 min. and then disappeared into the blue as if it were nothing. Afterwards I wondered if it was an air show or something similar. But it was so late that it couldn't be. Then I thought, it can't be a plane either. I have never seen a flying object at such a high speed and like that from a high speed, stop and remain in the air visible, and then full speed again to the N, and then disappear into the blue. They also didn't have any kind of blinkers or anything that planes would normally have. They were perfectly clear red/yellow dots.

We were standing on the beach and enjoying the warm, clear summer evening, when in the W-SW direction we saw an object flying in our direction towards the N-NE. The light from the object pulsated and the colors changed from soft white to orange/yellowish. There were no navigation lights present. It was very difficult to estimate the height and thus the speed, but it flew at a good and even speed. Very suddenly all 3 of us lost sight of the object, we guess for approx. same distance as when we first saw it. We could hear absolutely no sounds from the object despite a very quiet evening.

I was out walking the dogs at 00.34 on the field road behind the farm, when I am illuminated and look up at something almost too bright, which shines directly down on me. It was completely still in the air, and then it just disappears into the air again, no sound or the like, it just disappears straight up and within a very short time, it just looks like the other stars in the sky, and there are none things that can? or? We live far out in the country, no street lighting cars or masts or the like that could have done it.

Yes, we have seen many exciting things in the sky for the past week, first there is the luminous ball at low altitude flying horizontally above us, it does not flash, it does not make noise like the planes we have seen next to it . We have seen it 5 days in a row! We have also seen two reddish balls coming towards each other, spinning around each other and continuing on their separate ways. Yes, not only that, I have seen a big beautiful light, like a big star, light up and go out! More to come, we saw two reddish lights moving past each other on opposite sides of a star. We thought it was one satellite until we saw it was two and then suddenly saw them come together and disintegrate into 4 bright flashes. Yes, we have seen many fine things, and I hear of many others than us who are seeing things in the sky at present. All this is within a week. Is it a special time at the moment, with many phenomena around us? I experience it that way and also hear it from acquaintances.

A single object moves silently over the center of Svendborg at a height that is difficult to observe - the object is a bit like transparent - blurry matte orange-white - in my opinion it flies very fast. The size is impossible to estimate. This is the third time in 2 years that I have observed these silent but milky luminous "cotton bubbles" in the night sky, and all have been observed before midnight. The first time there were 2 pcs. Second time 3 pieces, and tonight it was alone. I think they fly too fast and stable to be drones.

There were two of us who had set off to find amber at Vedersø Klit. On the way up from the beach I go with a phone to find Mars in the night sky, exactly where Mars would have been there is a light source. I mention, it must be Mars. My father comments that it is moving. When we notice it moving, we study it closely, it is a centered light source, glowing bright yellow, surrounded by a dense haze. The light source rotates around itself, at certain times it is completely turned away from us, then it is just an illuminated haze. The light source moves a few degrees around the night sky, no high speed, no sudden movements. There is not a cloud in the sky besides this haze. There was a full moon, so everything was very clear to us. The light source eventually disappears into the haze, and the haze dissolves, leaving no trace in the night sky. We have a 52 second recording of the light source. In this shot, it looks like it's a three-legged light source that is rotating around itself.

We lie in the garden at night and spot three lights in a triangle moving very steadily to the west. The distance between the lights makes us sure that it was neither a high-flying plane nor a helicopter, and you couldn't hear anything. It also appeared to be relatively high up, so at least above the lower thin clouds there.
First there are 4 yellow objects with exactly the same distance in the sky above Køge and 20-30 sec. after that there is 1 more. Very clear to see, and there must be many who have seen it too.

Seeing two bright objects to the east, as they are almost above where we are standing, one changes speed so that they come closer to each other flying at low altitude towards the horizon to the west until they can no longer be seen.

I observed a meteor strike northeast of Ribe. Green-orange thing with a long orange tail crashed to the ground. Heard the rumble like thunder as it struck. I had to put the kids to bed, and while they were brushing their teeth, I stood looking out the kitchen window and saw something that looked like a flare, but which gained speed and shone more and more up and down towards the ground. When I heard the thud, it must have gone into the ground.

My wife and I are sitting in the living room outside and notice a flash of light that immediately looks like a landing light on an airplane. I go out on the terrace and observe that there is no sound. It turns in a soft arc over Brædstrup as it rises and disappears from view. Before it is out of sight, two more lights appear, taking exactly the same path.

2 powerful white lights, as powerful as Sirius star seen moving in formation one above the other with approx. a distance of one degree slowly, but at a constant speed in a south-easterly direction from at the start of observation south-east in 37/36 degrees respectively to 23/22 degrees constant south-east where they disappeared. very mysterious ???

Hello. My dad has told me about something he just couldn't explain what it was and didn't tell anyone but us in the family as he doesn't want to sound like HR superstition all around I guess. That one afternoon in the summer of 1998 he should have seen 4 luminous objects swarming around one after the other at a fairly fast speed across the sky. He also claims that they gathered together in a lump the size of one of them, and then spread out again at high speed. He then stood and looked at it for approx. 2 minutes. He then rushed inside for his camera, but when he came back out, they were gone. He was very shocked the next few days, I remember. Just thought I'd report it here :)

I came home on Thursday 31.03.2016, at a little after 11 p.m., and after I got into the house it hit me, what was that in the sky to the west? It was completely cloudless and very starry with a very faint blue sky background between the stars, the black between the stars is not completely black. Observed a triangular object, a white light in each corner, a fainter white light between the three points, and 2 to 4 even fainter lights inside the triangle, with a broad side towards me and the tip farthest, looked up under it and the triangle was darker than the sky. Size of the object at first observation was like my thumb nail in outstretched arm, approx. 17 mm. wide and approx. 20 mm. long and 2 hand widths above the horizon without thumbs, approx. 170 mm. also at arm's length. The three brightest lights were slightly fainter than the nearest stars. The object slowly became smaller and the light dimmer, at approx. 23.12, the size was a little smaller than my little finger nail, which is approx. 9x13 mm. From approx. At 23.15 it became almost impossible to see the light directly, but could still see it in the peripheral vision, the edge of one's field of vision, and at approx. 23.20 it is almost completely gone and stopped the observation. The course itself, if extended in both directions, would be almost straight east to west with a course north of me. Hope there are others who have observed this, whatever it was, it is something I will never forget.

We are driving home from a family gathering in Ringsted approx. at 8.30 p.m. To the west in the night sky we see 3 luminous circles in the sky slightly behind a night cloud. We stop at Baremosevej, switch off the lights on the car and can see 3 luminous circles which disappear in different directions. We continue out of Sørupvejen, where we can still see several luminous circles in the sky. We reach Vetterslev, where we turn onto Næstvedvej, and at Susåen we see them again in the western sky. We turn onto Sandbyvej towards Glumsø and drive up to Sandby Kirke, where we could faintly glimpse them again. The view was too bad, and we turn and drive back to Sandbyvej. We drive a bit out there and can still see them flapping in the sky. We drive onto Timannsvej, where there is an unobstructed view of the north/west sky. We turn off the car and the lights and sit and watch these circles of light that zig zag in the sky. They stand completely still and disappear VERY quickly towards the north. We also looked with binoculars and could only see white light, but not what. If we see a star as 2 mm in diameter, then here they were 8 cm in diameter. They were moving at a speed that was absolutely extreme. And disappeared as quickly as they came. Don't know if it's an observation used, but we've never seen or experienced anything like it.

My bedroom faces directly west. I have white cotton curtains for the window. At 03.50 Sunday 22.11.2015 I wake up for an unknown reason (no sounds or bright light in my room) and see "through" my curtain something that I first assume are white balls shot up by a "Roman candle". There is no sound and the balls do not "fall". Within a few seconds, approx. 7-8 bright white glowing balls in a row-like design. Not in a straight line, but in a slightly uneven longitudinal row with a few pieces slightly to the side for this. At first I thought, as mentioned, that it was balls of light going upwards, but gradually it dawned on me that instead the row of balls was moving horizontally and very quickly from the west and over or slightly north of the block of houses I live in - still completely silent. The height is not great, perhaps within a few hundred meters. Since after approx. 5 seconds disappear "across" the house, I hesitate for a few seconds (5-6), after which I rush into my kitchen, whose window faces due east. There I see in the haze over Åbyhøj and Århus that the balls of light have continued further into the haze and after a further approx. 5 sec. I can no longer guess them. Regarding the weather there is clear to the west when the observation begins, the Moon is quite low and half free and half covered behind a small cloud. To the east, on the other hand, it was misty and cloudy - it must be the weather edge that was promised to bring snow in our area on Sunday morning (and it did).

The 4 objects slowly change position from having been in an almost square formation to almost coming into line as they are directly above our heads. Slowly the three luminous objects disappear - perhaps because of the city lights - but the last one continues to an angle of between 80 and 90 degrees due south above the horizon, where it disappears - again probably because of the city lights. There was no sound in connection with the observation, and the objects did not appear to follow any fixed route/line in their movement. I called a friend and he had also observed the phenomena.

On Monday 27/2 I discovered a flashing and stationary object in the sky. It disappeared after a few hours (though I think it was due to clouds). Today, 1/3, I can see it again. It looks like a big bright star, but it flashes rapidly alternating red and green colors (looks like). It does not move and I have observed it since 18:50 and it is still there now at 21:40. My girlfriend is in Jutland (Fredericia) and can also see it. We both have video footage of it, but of course it's hard to see properly on video. We have both considered whether it could be a plane, but since we have been able to see it for so many hours, in different places in the country - we have become quite doubtful about what it is.

4 minutes past midnight I go out on the terrace and can see a hovering object north of Farum. The object reflects blue, green and red light and holds its position. I go back in and 20 minutes later I come out and look for the object and when I see it still holding position I know it's not an airplane. I grab my camera and start filming it. I call the police and then the air force and report the sighting and go to the roof to get a better overview. Here I see a similar object just to the south of the other, and they have now both held position for 2 hours and 38 minutes, and it appears that they are still holding their position while flashing bright colors. Over the course of the night, I have been keeping an eye on the migration of the stars across the starry sky, and these 2 objects have kept their exact position for the time being. This morning, all stars are slowly disappearing, but these 2 objects shine just as brightly as before.

White ball with a wide, short "tail". Size ratio: Height 1 - length of tail 10. Silent. I didn't manage to register whether it disappeared behind the treetops in the Knudskoven, or whether it "simply switched off". I estimated it to be about 5-10 km away. Its appearance was something like the meteor that struck Russia this spring, but in a much smaller version.

I was sitting in my kitchen doing my hobby when I saw out my kitchen window. A round ball that could be seen coming down and starting to rise after it had been almost down to ground level. You could almost see it, but you could also see something very red in it. As it began to ascend again, it first began to change color to deep blue before flying left and right.

Wednesday evening at 22.26 I turn from Næssundvej onto the A26 and drive towards Skive. In the sky I see 4 low-flying orange objects of light heading in over Nykøbing Mors. I pull into the first parking space and stop the car. There is no engine noise from the light objects, and no smoke trails behind them. They are neither helicopters, airplanes, nor any other type of motorized aircraft, and this evening it is completely windless. The 4 orange light objects are exactly the same size. They fly from west to east in a straight horizontal line, and with an equal distance between them. The speed is like the speed of a tourist plane. Within a few minutes, the light objects are out of sight again. The orange light from the objects is vivid/flashing, and looks like encased fire. The experience is beautiful and unique.

Sitting slumped in my armchair and looking at the leaves of the trees outside in the sunlight, enjoying the sight. Between the leaves I spot a seagull and an object that I first assume to be a plane. I see it moving very slowly. It is oval and silver-white. It seems to be big. Calling my wife, who is sitting on the couch, so she can verify what I'm seeing. She sees the same thing as me. We follow the object until we can no longer see it behind the rooftops. Presumably it lasts 1-2 minutes. There is sunshine and blue skies, so others must have seen something related to this sighting. When I spot the object, it is coming from an eastern direction seen through the leaves on the trees. When it is freed from the leaves on the trees, it flies in a westerly direction and, as I said, disappears behind the roofs, since we live in the middle of the city. Our windows face south.

Out on the balcony to smoke. I glance to the northeast and there I see a white ball with yellow hints. I see no twinkling, so there is no sign that it could be a star or airplane. I further plausibilize that it cannot possibly be either, since the ball is too big to be a star and far too visible to be an airplane, and since it shone in the cloudless night sky, I remained where I was - on the balcony. I hastily grabbed my phone and filmed the bullet for approx. 10 minutes. Meanwhile, I saw other small dots flying towards the sphere. 2 dots, flew, slowly to the ball and disappeared when they were in the same position. After a while, the ball starts to shine in yellow colors, which I also got on film. I thought at the beginning of this that it was an optical illusion with the shiny ball, while my eyes started to get irritated. I also got the shiny steels on film. My hands started to get tired, so I went back inside. An hour later, when I had to smoke again, the bullet was gone.

We were, my mate and I, standing out in the street, on New Year's Eve, to fire gunpowder outside the house where he lived. I suddenly caught sight of something really far away, almost gliding just as slowly towards the east above the treetops up by my parents' house approx. 300 m to the south from where we were standing. I told my mate who saw it straight away. We hurried up to his room, which was on the 1st floor facing south and with an unobstructed view. We found binoculars and could clearly see what we called "windows" on something that was really long and fairly flat. The object moved slowly from west to east for approx. 10-15 minutes and almost slipped away from our field of vision. Many thoughts went through both of us, but this couldn't possibly be a Zeppelin, because purely in terms of size, there would be at least 2-3 Zeppelins that had to be put together, and why would it be flying around on a New Year's Eve over Holstebro? (Finally, I want to say that I have, of course, told about the experience to others, but never before today wrote to anyone about this New Year's Eve in 1978. The reasons why I am doing it so many years later is because I Today I am going to read the archives of the air force and to my great joy see that something inexplicable was seen precisely in Holstebro, Struer and Ans at the same time, the only thing I cannot remember for sure is the exact time of the evening, but would have said somewhere between 19:00 - 20:30.

I left my house at 18.10, and could hear what sounded like a jet plane, like an airliner high up. However, it seemed not to be at the 10 km altitude as they usually are.. at the same time there were white lights around it and no one blinking. It was precisely the fact that there were no flashing lights that made me take a closer look. Slowly it just disappeared into the darkness... but as I'm just writing this it came back and I tried to film with my phone. So I have sound and maybe a picture of what I saw. The second time it came around in a circle and seemed to bank a lot as the light around it was now almost vertical instead of horizontal as before... and again it has now disappeared in the same direction.
Weird colored dots that blink but don't move. Far down in the sky.

We stood out in our garden and looked towards the moon and the many stars. Suddenly we spotted a flying object, which flew far up, but still below the Moon. It was flying quite fast and we were sure it was not a plane as there are special characteristics of a plane. Suddenly it flew behind some trees, and after a few seconds it was back in the sky, visible to us. It shone very brightly for two seconds and with the speed of light it was gone again. It was cloudless and starry. It was also silent and left no trace (fog or smoke).

At At 01:40 at night my wife woke up due to going to the toilet. She got up and pulled the curtains (which she doesn't usually do) and saw strange flashes of light in the sky. She woke me up and we watched the strange lights together for approx. 20 minutes. The light was like a yellow/white round "sun", which lit up successively in different places in an elliptical path. The flashes of light were very regular and followed the same path all the time. Finally the flashes of light grew fainter and then disappeared. We couldn't hear any sounds or noise from there. The ellipse was large and did not move, only the flashes of light moved.

Had a really strange and actually a bit scary experience yesterday... Was going to drive my daughter to the train station as she was going on a trip with a lot of others, and while we're waiting for their bus... we see a big and actually bright light in the sky ... it comes from one direction and flies across... then comes one more and then 2 and then one and one and one and and and 2 and 2 and 2 and finally one more... We stopped to count, but at least 10-15 came and they were totally silent... you felt watched/invaded in a way... and of course none of us took pictures... we just stood and stared at it with great wonder... what was that... scary sensation/experience.

2 objects, orange (a'la bonfire/harbour street light), strong light, surpasses any planet. Was initially observed near Mars and disappeared slightly before and below the star Arcturus. So max. 15 degrees above the horizon. If you ignore the color, it looked like 2 planes, one below and behind the other. Very straight course. I figured it was a couple of military jets. but one lost speed, stopped, and died out. The other died out 10 seconds later, but did a small flare-up before disappearing completely. Observed in 7x50 binoculars without being able to see further details. Have seen ultralights same direction/height a few km below. Then later a flashing light (plane) for approx. same track. The weather was clear with a few clouds. Possibly space debris.

I am in my backyard hanging laundry. I hear a sound behind me and turn to follow the sound to the south. A black arrowhead shaped object flies horizontally to the south over the treetops and disappears with a sound like a missile. I look at it in wonder and think: Damn, things are going wrong, and wait for a bang, but nothing happens. I have subsequently told it to a few people, but no one has found a reasonable explanation. I have of course turned and twisted the event myself to get something comprehensible, but without success.

The time is approx. 22.30, just got home and gets out of the car. Looking to the NW in the direction of the Tolne transmitter (flashing). Just above where the transmitter is, there is a red stationary ball of light. I go approx. 10 meters out to the edge of a grassy field and observes for a minute or two. Suddenly the red light starts moving south at the same speed until I can't see it behind some large fir trees in the western direction. During the entire observation, no sound is heard and the red light shines with the same brightness all the time.

The object, which at first looked like a normal faint star, moved slowly across the sky and gradually grew brighter until within approx. 2 seconds became VERY strong - approx. 10 times more powerful than any other star in the sky, after which it "faded out" and disappeared completely. Could be reminiscent of a projector from e.g. a lighthouse or aircraft which turns, aiming the projector's eye directly at one, and then 'disappears', but the object did not change direction. Nor did it remind me of a normal shooting star, as these usually just get fainter and fainter, and not suddenly light up strongly like here. Also, all previous shooting stars I've seen move much faster and over a longer distance. Could perhaps be a satellite that rotates on its own axis and thereby reflects the sun in a flash. This could possibly explain that the object did not change direction. I'm not that familiar with stars, but the closest beacon was a very clear star, which was right above us, here in Vangede in Gentofte. The object did not pass far past this star.

My boyfriend and I had just left the house when we noticed an orange light coming from the night sky. It first moved a short distance to the west, then it stood still in the air for 3-6 seconds, then it flew to the north, again a short distance, where it stood still for approx. 1-3 seconds later it flew northwest, at extreme speed, behind some trees. We tried to follow it, but when we got behind the trees it had disappeared. The time between it reaching behind the trees and us reaching behind the trees was approx. 10 seconds. Behind the trees was a wide clear night sky, therefore it must have had an incredibly high speed to be able to disappear from sight so quickly. During the entire process, no machine noises or other suspicious noises were heard. In the aftermath, we went out into the city and overheard an upset little boy yelling at his mother about the fact that "They" actually exist. The connection between the boy's statement and the incident is of course pure speculation, but in that case an interesting case.

Not my own observation, but 2 guests who left the ades and made the observation at the same time. There was a LIGHTER cloud cover. Observation was made by 2 guests who left the address at the same time. The object described as round and reddish moved VERY slowly and did NOT look like an airplane. In motion disappeared in a light cloud cover.

I come driving up Lårbakken (completely as the only motorist on the road) in the windy darkness when the car radio starts screeching. Soon after, a green/bluish flashing, luminous glow comes on inside the car. I look in the rearview mirror for other cars, but there are none. There isn't. I turn off the radio to focus on the observation. There is nothing to see out of the windows. The flashing light disappears, and when I turn the radio back on, all its fixed stations have been replaced with random programs.

Went for a walk with the dog, when we turn down towards the Eegård Children's Home, and where there is an old, very tall oak tree, and up above the treetop I first see a blurry light and then stop to look closer. It is then approx. 6 round lights like 6 ceiling lamps in an outer circle and approx. four smaller ones in an inner circle. It is blurred because they are seen as if behind a cloud or in fog, but it all rotates very slowly and at the same time also moves slowly forward. I continue walking as I can't see anything more because of the tree canopy and as we go further forward there is a cloudless sky and I can't see anything of what I had just seen. What I have seen is actually typically the classic image of what people call a UFO!!!

Looked up at the sky and saw a very bright bright white light. The sky was completely clear, a few clouds, and it was like seeing a plane with a bright light as it lands. I didn't get to take a photo. It was gone after 5 seconds. As I moved on, I look up and spot a new light, though smaller than the first and weaker in light. It was gone in 2 seconds. Seemed to be higher up. Both came from Rudkøbing towards Ærø.

I came driving off Isterødvejen, where I suddenly become aware of light in the air in front of me approx. 500 meters away My first thought is that it is a plane that has to make an emergency landing on the road, but as I get closer, I see in front of me a round dark gray object with lights on the underside, which is holding still in the air without a sound. Got too hyped to try to take photos. If there is anyone who has an idea of what could be, I would very much like to know, or if there have been exercises or the like.

I can't remember the exact year, but it was at least in the mid-1980s. I myself was born in 1970. I was born and raised in Harlev J (just outside Aarhus), and it was here that I had an observation that, after all these years, I would now like to tell you about: I come walking along Grønhøjvej. I have to go over to Gammel Stillingvej, so I want to take the path that goes between the two parallel roads (between Grønhøjvej 36 and Gl. Stillingvej 409). Since the path was below road level, I go down a tiled staircase and just as I'm about to go down, I see a flying object that looks nothing like anything I've seen before. However, I have no doubt that I saw it. It looked like a helicopter and was about the same size and shape, or maybe rather the shape of a waterman or fireman when moving in the water, but with a flat bottom - kind of like an igloo. It had no propeller, and (of course) no wings either. It was transparent, ie. constructed of a glass-like material. Therefore, you could see into the object/cockpit. And here I saw two men. I know it sounds like I suffer from delusions and hallucinations, but I don't, and I never have (nor have I ever taken euphoric drugs). In the object, two men were sitting next to each other, but it was only one that I really noticed, namely the one sitting on the same side where I was. He was tall, slim and with long legs and was probably what we earthlings know as a 40-50 year old. I noticed that the one with the long legs had his hands placed on something that might be used to navigate. The object was close, maybe 50 meters up and was standing still in the air. When I saw it, I was extremely taken aback and a little scared because of the unexpectedness of the situation, and I clutched tightly at the railing connected to the stairs. I turned my head because (when I came walking) I had seen a woman called Anne Grethe. She stood and was stuffing something into the trunk of their car. I wanted to shout: "Anne Grethe!", but I couldn't. Then I looked up at the sky again, but there the object had unfortunately disappeared. I resented (and still do) that I hadn't fixed my gaze on the object, because then I probably would have seen it when it moved away/disappeared. The object made no sound, but I have no doubt that I saw this object! I have only told a few people about the episode as I think, "No one will believe it anyway." I told my first boyfriend, who I was with for 17 years. He was open to my explanation, but it has rarely been a topic of conversation between us. And then I've told it to my current husband, who shakes his head if the conversation rarely turns to unidentifiable flying objects, and I tell what vision I've had. In fact, I've never had the urge to talk about it widely, because I'm sure of what I saw, and I don't want to be in a situation where I have to convince people that it is true. That I know it myself, that is the most important thing for me. Because you probably think I'm shrill crazy, I'll just briefly tell you a little about myself: I'm 50 today, I'm married and the mother of two, a 22-year-old boy and an 11-year-old daughter. ling.merc. in Spanish and bachelor in English and am used to dealing with rather difficult translations. Since my big dream is to be able to make a living from publishing fiction, I write novels, and I have so far published two novels in the field of social realism, one of which is in the genre of autofiction (ie something that happened to me in reality added to fiction) . None of these novels contain supernatural themes or outer space mysteries. And science fiction is not me at all. I am not a superstitious person - not at all. I'm not interested in stars, astronomy, astrophysics or the like, but I think (like so many others) that the idea of life in space is exciting. Something I've always wondered though is: If life exists elsewhere in the universe, why would it be hostile life? Why does almost everyone talk about us being taken over by strangers, possessed by something that is evil? If there is life out there, it could be that they are just curious about what it is like on earth and therefore have no evil intentions. Wouldn't we also be curious ourselves if the earthlings once got all the way out there to the universe, which we still have no knowledge of, and we became aware that there was life? So we wouldn't want to start a war right away, would we? We have gained a lot of knowledge about the moon, space, planets and much more in the last 50-100 years. How much faster will it go in the next 1000 years? Where are we in 3021? Our skills to reach even further into space will be so much greater, so it may be that by then we will have some kind of answer to what it was that I saw. Something I have wondered though is whether or not the life that might be out there is likely to be similar to us humans? What I saw looked like humans, only larger and with longer limbs. I hadn't imagined malformed, slimy creatures like in Aliens - but creatures that were more different from us. The reason why I suddenly decided to write to you now, over 30 years later, is that I happened to hear an episode of the knowledge and technology podcast series "Flying saucer" hosted by host Frederik Dirks Gottlieb on P1. Here, Luis Elizondo (former head of the secret UFO unit in the Pentagon) will, among other things, the interview regarding some videos published by the US government. It is therefore some high-ranking people with reference to the Minister of Defense who are open to the fact that there is something out there that we cannot dismiss out of hand. It is the broadcast that has made me think: "Imagine now, if there is still someone who wants to believe me?" It also gives me hope that you as an association and as "ufologists" will listen to my experience. IF it should happen that you have received other similar inquiries, it would be incredibly nice if you could give me information about or a link to where I can read about it. If you want more information from me, you are welcome to contact me. I think I am able to clarify many concrete things, but precise information about year and season etc. I can't quite remember. But the sight of the object itself and how I reacted is still very clear to me and I will never forget it.

properties.Remarks: Forklaring: Bryllup på Havartigården i Holte!  Balloner med hjerter!se beretning

properties.content: 2 clear round candles hung over the water. We sat down, and as soon as we sat down, I sensed and looked up, something flying silently over my head. My husband doesn't see it, but we discover that the lights out over the water are gone. That same night, our son experiences the house as if shaking and a strange sound. We don't wake up, even if he turns on all the lights in the house. This he tells us the next day, and I could tell about our experience, about which he showed nothing.

I'm standing at the Shell gas station waiting for my sister, who is shopping inside. It is very nice and quiet weather. I look up and see a ball with two "prongs" at each end. At first I think of balloons/lamps with fire, but then thought it moves a bit too fast since there is no wind. We stand and watch it disappear at a steady pace, but agree that it's not a balloon and probably not a lamp either, but we can't see what it's supposed to look like either.

I was sitting on the bus on my way to work and saw a very large star-like object in the sky, but was surprised by the oblong size of the object. I could clearly see it moving/flying. It was oblong in shape, bright white, and the light seemed to be least intense in the center of the object. I first saw it under the Moon on the right, where it moved towards the left in a linear direction - after which it suddenly disappeared. Approx. 20 minutes later it was suddenly visible again, this time above the Moon on the right side and moving towards the left. It immediately seemed to be very high up. I would guess it to be "4 millimeters" in the sky, just seen with the naked eye. There were no blinkers on it like you normally see on an airplane and the speed I would think was slightly faster than an airplane. It also had no condensation trail behind it. I saw a plane somewhere else in the sky, and could immediately decide that they were in no way similar.

At approx. 23 my wife went to bed. Before that, she likes to look out of the slanted window to the south. She came down to the living room where I was sitting reading and told me that there were 2 UFOs. We both looked out the living room window to the south and saw 2 red lights (alternating red/orange) hanging next to each other approx. 20 degrees above the star Sirius. (About as high above Sirius as Sirius above the horizon). I immediately spotted 2 more red lights further down (below Sirius). I took my prism binoculars and ran up to the bedroom, opened the slanted window and caught the red lights in the binoculars. They apparently hung still. There was absolutely no sound and it wasn't 4 airplanes. It could be balloons in calm weather. But it is not common for balloons to have lights on them. The 2 lower lights disappeared down behind some trees. The top 2 hung apparently stationary, but gradually I could see in relation to the surrounding stars that they were slowly moving away to the south or south-southeast. I had the last one in my sights approx. 10 min., until it finally also went down behind the trees. It had (like the others) a red light without extension and slightly flickering now and then into orange. I've never seen anything like it and can't really imagine what it is.

I sit in total darkness and eat and drink (bad habit) by my kitchen castle and look out of my kitchen window. The sky is pitch black, but I can see a gray cloud in the distance and only that. As I look at the cloud, first a small hole appears in all the gray (the cloud), which shines yellow. The hole gets bigger and bigger and becomes like an oval. The hole/light if you will - splits in two and suddenly looks like an open powder can, both still oval - the phenomenon stands like this for a bit and suddenly the top (lid) disappears, and slowly the other light (bottom) disappears into nothingness again, and the cloud is still there. After all, there were no planes in the air this evening - so I wondered a lot and have been thinking all day - what the hell it could be. It struck me as something observational, not something fast-paced.

I can't remember if it was November or December, but it was a dark evening and completely windless and starry, in the period from 9-10pm. It was in 1988. I was 21 at the time and lived in Gødvad near Silkeborg. My mother picked me up in her car (I didn't have a car myself), and we were going to Resenbro, where my mother lived at the time, which is also near Silkeborg. When we come towards the bridge at Resenbro kro (which still existed then), I say to mother, it's strange, no planes usually come over the stream, and so far down. At that time it flew. My mother said that it was probably the plane to Greenland (the one she always kept an eye on because my big brother had almost just left for Greenland), but then we looked again, and now it was standing still over the stream. It was approx. 2-3 meters above the water and approx. 100 meters away from the bridge. It was spherical and the size of a table globe, it shone in a white, very bright light. We stopped on the bridge and stopped the engine and got out of the car. At the same time, a car came from the opposite direction, they also stopped and switched off the car. They stayed in the car for approx. a ½ minute. We just stood and looked at it. When the other 2 got out of their car, it disappeared so quickly it cannot be described. It flew towards Gødvad and just above the treetops. There was no sound either when it was stationary or when it was flying. The others got back into the car and drove towards Gødvad. I wanted us to turn the car around and also drive to Gødvad again, but mother didn't want to, because as she said, it's over all the mountains now. So we drove home to mom. We would have liked to have talked to the other 2 in the other car, but they hurried away. We told my stepfather and my little brother. My little brother wanted us to drive to Gødvad, but mother didn't want to. So it continued that we had seen it across the stream. We have talked about it many times since the time we saw a UFO over the river. I was very fascinated by it. I have always believed that they exist, so this was a confirmation for me that they do. Neither mother nor I have had it publicly, but that's because we didn't know where to turn. It is an experience I will never forget. Unfortunately, I haven't seen any UFOs since.

My girlfriend and I were out walking the dogs on Tordenskjoldsgade by the skating area opposite the 10th class centre. We sit on the bench and let the dogs play, so they could be tired before we went home to bed. After sitting and talking for a bit, I see a shooting star and we start looking up at the night sky to see if we could see more as it was starry. We spot planes, satellites and see a few more individual rock shots, when suddenly I see something that resembles a satellite, only much bigger, and which moves approx. 4-6 times faster. I manage to point up in the sky and my girlfriend also sees this satellite-like thing. It was very clear and without twinkling, so a plane is out of the question, and neither was a shooting star, as I have seen many shooting stars in my lifetime. My girlfriend has also seen quite a few of these, then we stood there and both had never seen anything like it in the sky. It was round, but at the same time somewhat square, and it flew completely silently with a speed reminiscent of a fighter jet, maybe a little faster, but without blinking. Satellites tend to be fairly small and don't move that fast, so you can follow them for a very long time. So what have we been seeing? It came out of nowhere and flew across the sky from east to west to almost fly away, i.e. into space and disappeared. I have never seen anything that resembled or resembled my sighting, nor has my girlfriend ever experienced anything that could resemble what we saw....

We sit in the living room and observe a strong orange light from the west. Opens the patio door and looks at it. It flies over to the other side of the house. I observe it in maritime binoculars with a compass. The object is the same from the front, bottom and back. We could only see the strong flickering light the color of an orange. It was full circle. I would think the height of the object was between 1.5 to 2.0 km. and it shot at a speed of approx. 300 km/h. It was silent. I have no explanation for what we saw, but can rule out misc. planes/helicopters, natural phenomena. The data of the observations are very precise. Hr been a commander in the defense for 10 years and used to observing.

I observed an object with 2 colors: green and red. It moved back and forth and stood still in between. Thought it was an airplane. It moved east, then faster to the west and was now only red. The sky was cloudless at the time. It stood still for a moment before disappearing from sight in a south-easterly direction at great speed. Couldn't keep it in the scope. No idea what it could be. But it made me turn to you.

I was sitting in my living room looking out the window to the NW when I saw what I first thought was a helicopter. My wife and I went out into the garden to take a closer look. It was NOT a helicopter - the flying object had no rotor, nor did it emit engine noise or lights. We were rather puzzled and I got my binoculars to take a closer look at the object. The strangest thing was that it looked like there were some kind of pennants fluttering from the object. Some might think that it was a flock of birds - but that was definitely not the case. The object flew quite silently from NW to NE - almost straight over our house. My wife and I could not identify the object with anything we have seen or experienced so far. In the 2 following days, I thoroughly studied newspapers and the Internet to see if others should have observed the same phenomenon or if there could possibly be a reasonable explanation. But I have not been successful in my efforts. It was a very strange experience - I hope others have seen the phenomenon and can explain what it is we have seen.

I have long observed a twinkling star and decided to look at it a little. I saw it change color to blue and took out a pair of theater binoculars. It looked oblong (3-4 balls of light in a vertical row with red, green and white light moving along it. I then borrowed a bit better binoculars and saw both yesterday and the day before several stars that do not look like stars or planets , as they change shape and direction from horizontal to vertical and change color. They are not airplanes or hot air balloons as I have observed the one twinkling star over a long period of time and it seems to have a fixed position as it is roughly same spot in the sky every night from 19:30-23:00 approx From my view on the balcony but one of the others I observed yesterday moved and at first I thought it was a plane but when I took my binoculars I could clearly see it wasn't. Planes fly past here regularly too so know what they look like and they don't stay in the same position for hours either. I don't know who can help me figure out what it is, but will try here first, as I have googled multi-colored flashing object and found an answer from malte olsen, who is a physicist at the niels bohr institute, but his answer was not clarifying. I've seen your observation chart but I'm not sure how to explain the positions etc. I have a program on my iphone with planets etc. It is between mars and jupiter i.a.

properties.Colors: hvid og skinnende som en stjerne
properties.content: My girlfriend called me on the way home from Orehoved on Nordfalster with the bus at 11.05 pm and asked me to go out and look for a UFO near the Moon. I don't know if he's kidding about that, so I went out and looked up, but since I live in the middle of the city 25 kilometers away from his location on the bus, I couldn't see the Moon. I then got up after my boyfriend at 11.35pm and we looked up all the way home and he explained to me that he had seen a bright object 10 times bigger than a star which flew in straight lines up and down around the Moon for 2 minutes . When we come up to a clearing between two houses, out of nowhere in the middle of the sky to the west an object appears that looks like a star, but 10 times bigger. It flies in a straight line to the south at a speed 5 times faster than a jet fighter. There is no sound, just a sharp flash as the object appears and disappears into the blue again. I screamed like a stung pig in the middle of the street in the clearing because I have never been more convinced that it was a UFO. Never seen such a large luminous object in the sky before, and never fly so fast and so straight. As I said, it came out of thin air and disappeared again into nothingness.

Came from Brabrand over True up to Viborg Landevej and turned towards Viborg. When I straightened my new vw, it was 2-3 km. advance just over the highway. It looked like shown many times, 2 deep dishes facing each other and 1 or 2 rows of windows. The size large as seen from Ebeltoft towards Mols like the Sun when it sets. So today it upsets me that I didn't dare to stand out and take off my glasses. I have astigmatism in both eyes and see if it was still there. I don't think so, because I think it's an optical phenomenon of some kind, which happens when you look through the double glazing of the windshield and even wear glasses with structural defects. It would be interesting if you could recreate it by experiment, because today I can show where I left off. The country road is unchanged. PS.: When the big thing disappeared, it happened in a split second.

I was standing on the terrace looking at the sky with my night binoculars when a big light came out from the west. I didn't even need my binoculars to see it. It lit up a little more than a star, but had it stood still it would have looked like a star. I thought it was a plane at first, but they usually flash, this one didn't at all. And then I went in and checked "live planes" in the sky via an app I have, and there were no planes above us. I doubt a satellite would shine so brightly here, I haven't seen it before. I hope there are others who also saw it. I followed it for approx. 1 minute from west to east at good speed across the sky.

During an evening walk with my dog, I observe a landing light from an airplane/object (often seen in the evening in Valby, as planes pass over the district for landing in Kastrup). The light from the aircraft/object is approaching much faster than usual, and I do not observe any motor noise from the aircraft/object. As it passes over Migr's head, Jegr notes that the plane/object is circular (the underside is illuminated with a red light in the middle), the plane/object is still silent, then it is lost from sight. All of this was observed under cloud cover at normal approach altitude to Kastrup, but the aircraft/object was not on the normal approach course.
