On 29.11.2012 at approx. 18:40 I look out of my kitchen window from the height of the 2nd floor towards northwest 312 degrees (Sædding Strand/Skallingen) and spot a large ball. Immediately think it's a helicopter coming in with the searchlight on. However, the light is very yellow and larger compared to searchlights on the helicopters. The ball of light doesn't move in any way, and all of a sudden it's gone. Soon after, I look again, and now suddenly there are two balls of light, slightly offset from each other. I manage to take a picture and then the orbs of light have disappeared again. Height above the horizon is difficult to define, but it was above the roof of an ordinary detached house.

A small object in the southern sky that, from our view, stood still for a long time. I have seen plenty of airplanes and this was not it. It had far too many features to be a plane. My wife and I looked at it for a long time through binoculars and this was very strange.

I see a twinkling spot, a la a star. It stands completely still, but flashes very quickly in different colors. I wonder, thinking it must be an airplane. I go to a grill bar approx. 8 minutes When I'm on my way home, it's still there. I stop and take a closer look. Can see it's not an airplane. It begins to rise upwards, slowly. I watch it most of the way home, rising upwards.

properties.Colors: orange i midten og hvid udenom
properties.content: I sat in my garden to cool off and look at the stars. There was quite a bit of meteor activity, but suddenly at 00:42 a mysterious slightly blurred object comes flying at a fairly high speed, right over my head, from northwest to southeast. How high it was up was difficult to estimate. It flew a bit wobbly/shaky and completely silent. I estimate the size to be, if you take a DKK 1 and hold out an outstretched arm, almost as big as the Moon. Because before that I observed several inexplicable flashes high in the sky to the west, which could remind me of a lot of lightning. My mother, who lives approx. 3 km further south, had seen the same flashes.

I stood on the terrace and looked for shooting stars. Suddenly, in the direction of the southwest, an object came flying that was illuminated - looked like an airplane, but there was a "cord" connected to it, as if it had something in tow - it just looked like a box.... Looked for a few seconds and then ran for binoculars/camera, but despite speed, the object was gone. It was totally cloudless, so it amazes me that it suddenly appeared in the night sky - as if a light was turned on. Tried to google an answer, but can't find any. Hope you guys can help as I'm thinking a lot about what it was.

properties.Colors: lilla, orange, gul, rød, blå, grøn
properties.content: I looked at the sky (to see the stars) and first saw 1 bright different color, it changed between colors (it stayed in the same position for all 3 hours). I tried to take pictures and film, but without success. Well, after 1 hour, another one of the same kind came and shone in the same way, but it suddenly rose 90° towards the sky and slowly flew away (out of my sight). They were long and shaped like a boomerang, also had a small shape of a fighter plane (- the last half of a fighter plane.

The object flew from northeast to southwest, relatively slowly, i.e. slower than a plane, I heard no sound. I noticed the object because it did not look like an airplane and the speed that cannot have been very high, maybe 100-200 km/h, the height I would estimate 1000-2000 m. The object continued in the same direction until I couldn't see it anymore.

I cycle out along the dirt road where I live. I notice a light to the northeast of me, it's clear in the sky, so my first shot is star. When the object flies towards me, I think plane/helicopter. The object comes closer, and not quite high up. I have a headset on and take it off to hear if it's a helicopter. I can't hear any sound, so it's very mysterious. As I approach the city limits and the street lights, the object disappears in the opposite direction from me.

My friend and I were walking on the sidewalk when we heard a huge loud noise that sounded like thunder. We looked up at the sky, but there was nothing, so we looked over towards the swimming pool. There stood something very large, straight up in the air. It rises very high in the air, it took almost 4-5 minutes and then it was filled with lots of colored light all over. The noise decreases with the increase. It is elongated and square. It looks most like the bottom of a car. There were square "things" like four wheels on a car, but they were out on the side of the UFO. When it started flying over us it was totally silent. It must have been very large because even though it was very high up in the air, we could clearly see the shape. It flew slowly over us and then it just flew away...... I'm a little unsure of the date, but the year should be correct.
Object moved at steady speed, started as a fireball, slowly decreasing in size to approx. ⅓ of the original, red at the periphery, orange-yellow centrally.

I went out to take a few pictures of the chemtrails being sprayed wildly into the air that day. So only some jet planes and not others. When I later looked at images that were enlarged, I saw a dark object on the right and many small bright dots and bright oblong formations in the upper far right. When I took the photos through the window, at first I thought it was dirt on it. The day after I took a photo from the same angle and time, but there are no "dots". I have noticed your bright "dots" because I saw them before on ufo-portal.

Driving towards Brenderup from the motorway. Red-white flashing object, the light changes to solid red/orange (no more flashing) plummets rapidly towards the ground at an angle of approx. 25 degrees. Approx. 300 - 400 meters above the horizon, the light suddenly goes out. I have seen many shooting stars over time, but never one with such a sharp angle to the earth or such clear or colored light.

I was woken up by my older brother that I was going to see a UFO. We were small and lived in a room together. I'm not sure how long it was before our parents came in. They saw it too, says my mother, with all due respect. I think there was only one, it was all black, with little orange lights around it. It began to rotate funnily, until before it began a kind of epileptic shaking. There I myself am completely focused on its movements, and actually only remember from when our parents entered my brother's and my room.

My boyfriend and I are smoking our evening cigarette on our French balcony when a distinct UFO-like object appears on the horizon above Netto. A golden-red triangle with small blue pillars of light pointing down (or up) briefly came into view. Behind the golden-red triangle, three faint flashes of light appeared in blue/green, red and yellow/orange, respectively. Having trouble remembering the exact colors. I took a picture with my cell phone.

Had been at a friend's in the evening and had to go back to my parents, where I was going to spend the night. Stopped to look at the starry sky which was clear this evening. In a south-easterly direction, towards Møn's cliff, I noticed what looked like a powerful star, but there was no comparison, as it was an unusually powerful light. After looking at this for a while, I saw that the object changed direction vertically as well as horizontally almost moving like a square. The movements were fast and my assessment is that the object moved within a range of 50-100 meters, however without knowing how far away the object was. I picked up my parents, who subsequently witnessed the phenomenon. After approx. 10 min from the start where I had seen it, it started to change brightness. Alternating very bright to fading white light. This process continued for approx. 5 min., after which the object disappeared out of sight.

We were sitting in our yard drinking evening coffee when a yellow-orange ball/light came that we thought was a plane at first, but there was no sound and it flew in different directions that a plane can't. It stood still in the sky and suddenly it slowly flew back along the same route it had come.

On a clear sky around midnight, my friend and I walked across a parking lot in Aalborg city on our way to the car. We went in the direction N to S towards the car. We lifted our heads as we walked. So many stars. Immediately I see 3 "stars" (because the 3 lights were no bigger than a star in the sky) moving quite quickly across the sky to the south. Much faster than airplanes, but a little slower than "shooting stars". The funny thing was that all 3 lights suddenly switched places on their route. They flew very fast, and then they had come too far on the horizon after the approx. 4 sec., we looked.

Three yellow glowing orbs appeared from west to east - descending towards the ground. I only made eye contact when they appeared in my window. At first I thought it was shooting stars, but it definitely wasn't. The 3 balls were next to each other, but they didn't stick together - they moved individually. They stopped approx. 50 meters up, they didn't seem very big. I took my camera outside to take pictures, but I was too shocked/enthralled by the sight to figure out how to turn off the flash, so the pictures haven't worked - one was just black, one was all white. There were no sounds/machine noise or any other kind of sound from the luminous balls at all, after approx. Half a minute in the same place, where they moved a little between each other, they flew slowly to the south. Approx. 10 minutes later they reappeared from exactly the same direction and took up the same position, approx. 50 meters above my neighbor's house. After again hanging in the same place, moving a little back and forth, they again flew south. Approx. 100 meters from my position, it looked like they dropped/threw something luminous towards the ground. After this, they again flew slowly to the south and disappeared quietly on the horizon. At no point could I sense any outline/shape on the glowing orbs - it was just 3 yellow glowing round orbs. It was a fantastic sight, I was really taken aback, as I quickly think that I could rule out that it could be something familiar (searchlight, fireball, helicopter, etc.) It really annoys me that I couldn't find out of operating my camera - hope you can shed light on it.

2 objects seen above SLAGELSE d 26 March 2016. Last night at 21.30 I saw 2 objects flying across the sky at very high speed (8-10,000 km/h) at an altitude of 20-30 km. They flew in formation. There were no streaks of condensation. They came from 230 degrees south/west and flew 60 degrees north/east. There were 3 white lights on each of them.

A little after midnight between 8 and 9 November 2017, was sleeping, but the dog wanted out. Looking out through the entrance door window, and sees a fantastically beautiful red-orange glossy shiny ball on the horizon to the north in Nivå on Zealand. The same place from which the planes enter the sky. I was completely petrified and went inside to get the camera, but it was already gone when I got back to the front door. Beautiful sight, but still think it seemed ominous and wonder if it was a cry for help, or a new form of fireworks. There was no sound. Maybe others have seen this last night also in the area? Haven't seen or heard anything about this mentioned in the media.

I have the night of 31.01.2023 at approx. 10.50 p.m. through a window, from my residence, saw a glittering, luminous object in the sky, slightly irregular and slightly larger than a star or planet, in shape. Can't say how many degrees above the horizon, but high up, like a star. I saw the object move occasionally so it was NOT a star or planet. And it was definitely NOT a plane or a helicopter. The object stood still for some time occasionally, then moved again, not far, but enough to be seen. A couple of times it kind of dipped a little, but came back to the starting position. I went to bed but got up again at 23.15 to see if the item was still there. It was, but it had moved a very long way - compared to how far it had moved previously. It was exciting and incredible to watch. It cannot be ruled out that it could have been a UFO.
It looked like a large disk with orange light on the side that waved or rotated. It was a wildly strange experience!

Sitting on the terrace and having fun. The clouds hang low and suddenly we observe a round yellow object. It is visible for approx. 20 sec., and disappears a few times in the clouds. Therefore reasonably sure of the height of the object. Sure it wasn't a plane, meteor, satellite. The wind was probably southerly, but the object was not wind-borne at the speed. The object moves from south to north, along the Roskilde fjord. Have been a soldier, and have experienced attacks from fighter planes during exercises, and based on these experiences, I would think that the speed of the object is approx. 800 km per hour. Have previously experienced planes with yellow lights, but only seen oncoming ones. Never from the side. Distance from observation point to the object, I would guess between 2 to 3 km.

I was about 5 el. 6 years old. I was out on the balcony with my sister (7-8 years old) and we just looked around at the sky. Then the UFO appeared. we stared at it for a few seconds and then I ran out to find a camera, but neither me nor my sister could figure out how to use it, and there was no roll of film in it either. When I came out again to the balcony, it was a few meters further away, to the right. And after a few seconds again, it disappeared.

Lying looking out the window looking at a star, thought there was something strange about it as it moved from one side of the treetop to the other, plus double in less than 10 min. Thought it was an airplane, so looked up to the window and studied it more closely, but couldn't see the flashes that usually happen with airplanes. Then went outside to see if I could see anything there, but it seemed to just stand still again, then went down to myself and looked out the window one more time, when suddenly something very strange comes with lots of light in the middle and red glow above and below. I rush outside again and go up the stairs and can follow it disappearing to the south at low altitude. The red light was all I could see before it sort of faded away. The way I saw it, it was not that far away, no more than 1 km, and there was no engine noise coming from it. Now you have lived here in Vandel for 13 years, and you can easily hear planes further away.
Absolutely insane and has video! Electrical impulses and activity between dark clouds with thunder lightning in the middle.

Over the summer I flew the drone over a number of fields on Lolland. After landing the drone one afternoon, I saw something that I can't explain. But there were no serrations on the tail or flat wingtips. Just a window shape, flatter at the back. No visible details, gray color. I saw it as if it was flying at an altitude of 300 meters at a little over 100km/h. Size approx. 5 meters long. Based on the drone I flew with, I had a good idea of the correlation between speed and size, but the height may well be completely wrong. One thing that amazes me is that it was completely silent. Right above me in a quiet place. The propeller from my own drone could be clearly heard and other propeller or jet aircraft could be heard many kilometers away. I thought it was a military drone of some kind, but I'm still wondering.

I took a walk around the stadium in the northern part of Randers. The time was approx. 10.30pm to look at the stars, which I usually do when the sky is clear. In this place it is very dark so my view of the sky is very clear. When I was standing there, I suddenly saw from the NE side of the sky 2 objects which looked like two bright stars moving at a very high speed. And as it seemed to me, they flew very low, approx. between 300 and a maximum of 1 km up. There was no sound from the two objects which flew west. I can tell the difference between meteorites, satellites and almost all kinds of lights on airplanes and the way they move or maneuver at night. I am SURE that what I saw last night was a UFO.
Saw a white disk flying around in the sky. The disk flew at a high speed and made a 90 degree turn.

I'm a little unsure of the date, but it was late September. Due to low-lying fog banks, it was like walking in a pot. The sky was almost starry above the horizon. I walked the dog and we chose the marketplace. At one point approx. in the middle of the square I notice a bright white light as from a plane in a north-westerly direction, moving south at a moderate speed. The dog and I take a break. And probably because of the bank of fog, I've been keeping an eye on the "plane" when it suddenly stops and stands still for a minute or two and then the hell with it and takes off in the opposite direction - stops again. Stands still for several minutes and then takes a turn again at the same speed. This happens 2 maybe 3 more times. It actually moves around with the horizon, so when I lose visual contact with the object, it is in the opposite direction to when I discovered it. I have no idea what it was that I saw, but the speed was way too high for an airplane and the way it stopped, up, shouldn't be attributed to an airplane either.

properties.Colors: metallic med rødt lys i vinduerne

properties.content: The year is 1999, and I am hunting with my father on Samsø. It is broad daylight at is about five, it's nice and warm and almost cloudless. We were on my father's boss's field a little outside Nordby. We were supposed to shoot birds - crows I think, and I was therefore told that we went our separate ways around a small forest so that if one of them chased something up, the other could shoot on the other side of the small forest. After I have started walking one way and he the other, and have walked approx. 100 to 150 meters I get the feeling that there is something above me. When I look up, there hangs in the air "I know" a white light. It hangs completely over me. It was really hard to tell how far it was up, but it was the size of a car light at a little over 50 meters away. Confused, I stood and stared, probably mostly out of wonder, at this object for approx. 7 maybe 10 seconds. Enough to see it clearly and distinctly, my best description is a ball of light or rather a ball of chromed silver that threw all the light of the sun right at my head. As I said, it was almost cloudless, but after approx. 10 sec. a small cloud comes, almost the only one in the sky, and hovers right between me and the object and blocks my view, until it approx. 3 sec. after disappearing, is the object I had just been looking at for a few seconds. before, gone. It's really unbelievable, since I could look all around the little cloud, and believe me, I did. It really was as if it disappeared with the speed of light, and I think maybe I know it too, I looked at it... When we got home I said nothing, I didn't even know what I was thinking. Over time, however, it has become crystal clear to me, although I can only guess what the hell was inside it. Or what could hold it up. Since then, I have told a few people what I saw. Now, several years later, I have almost become addicted, I haven't seen the same since, but I follow all the media in newspapers, online and TV about the strange incidents people tell about . I am personally 100% sure we are not alone….

One summer morning, the weather was really good, I stood out on our east-facing terrace and looked in the north/east direction, the sky was completely clear and there was no wind at all. Suddenly I see something slowly flying from west to east. It is a relatively small object which corresponds very well to the description given in the article, it most resembled a flying refrigerator lying down, and it actually had some things sticking out at both ends. At first I think it's a balloon, but since there's no wind, it's moving too fast and far, far too steady to be anything like a balloon. It flew almost as if it were on rails, which a balloon doesn't do. Could it be a remote-controlled plane of some kind? No! Because there was no sound at all from it, and the hum that a remote-controlled engine makes can be heard far away. I think it was moving at 30-40 kilometers an hour and it flew right over some blocks of flats which are about 60 meters from our house so it was quite close to where I was standing and therefore I'm quite sure what i saw matches my description. It has been up to a height equivalent to 10-20 meters above the roof ridge of the blocks, and the blocks are 4-storey standard blocks from the 60s. I follow the object and see that it is flying in the direction of the center of Køge, and here it is that I think that if it has continued on that course, approximately north/east, then it will end up in Copenhagen at some point. I have never forgotten what I saw, but I have also never seen the object again, however I do know that there have been people over in the blocks of flats that it flew over who have experienced a strong light beamed into their windows late in the evening, and those reports are about 10-12 years back in time, and I remember that there was a lot of talk about that/that light in the neighborhood that summer. About 10-12 years ago, I also saw some lights over Køge bay, for which I also have no explanation. I stand one evening at 9-10pm outside our front door, which faces south. It is completely starry, and it has also been during the summer period. I look at the stars and see one of them start to move slowly to the north/east, it could easily be a satellite, I think, but a few seconds later, another star starts to follow the first, and then my serious attention. And believe it or not, a few seconds after the first 2 start moving, they were completely still to start with, then first a 3 and then a 4 start moving after the first in the same direction, and there are now 4 stars flying in a straight line one after the other to the north/east. It should be said that our house is right under an approach route to the airport, so I see a lot of different planes every day and night all year round, but these 4 objects simply could not have been planes or helicopters and certainly not those Chinese hot air bags, it has become so popular to send up. I have not seen anything like it since then, and therefore I remember it as clearly as if it were yesterday.
I see 3 white/luminous points on a line flying very fast. There are no twinkles and it's not shooting stars as I know it.

I would like to report, on behalf of my grandparents, two flying objects that were seen on the evening of April 18, 2015. My grandfather is addressing my grandmother as he sits on the couch looking out the window, two brightly lit cigar shaped objects. At first my grandfather thinks it's a plane engulfed in fire and both my grandparents rush out onto their balcony. Here, however, they see the two objects, not crashing down, but disappearing with tremendous speed up behind the cloud cover. Both objects were silent.

properties.Colors: skifter fra hvid til rød, grøn
properties.content: The light phenomenon. 2 lights that sort of rotate around quite high up, sometimes we could only see 1 light that was in the sky. It moves very slowly (too slow to be a plane or helicopter, but moves faster than a star, knowing it's the Earth rotating). The light changes color from white to faint reddish and greenish. Think it's a UFO.

We were on our way from the train at Hvalsø station, and going up Hyllebjerg, when I look out over a grass field on the right side, there are 6 yellow/orange lights, and I tell my friend that they have turned on the lights on the crane. She doesn't think there is a crane. 1 min. later, more lights have come up from the horizon, and there are approx. 20 lights. They come up as an oval shape and turn off when they come up for approx. 45 degrees... and disappears. We go out into the grassy field and look at them, as we are not bothered by lamps from the street. There we can see white, round balls flying at very high speed and a faint hum across the sky. They flew from 45 degrees NW to 45 degrees SE in about 30-40 seconds...

At nine o'clock in the evening, my good friend Rasmus and I were on our way down to town, to see if there would be a small fun fair that had come to town. We saw that it was closed and then heard some voices inside a garden approx. 10 meters from us. We heard them talking about how you couldn't fly a parachute when it was dark, so it was just a pure reflex that we both looked up into the air and saw the reasonably bright light standing completely still in the air. We heard no sound or wind, only the large object, which was shaped like a bus, it was about the same size. It didn't take more than a few seconds before it started drifting south west, it looked like it was rocking back and forth, but it drifted far away until we couldn't see it anymore. My companion and I were very sure that such a plane does not exist in Denmark. I also knew that if it was a plane or a helicopter, which I'm 100% sure it wasn't, my dad is an aircraft mechanic and knows a lot about planes. We went and wondered what it was. Half an hour later we were on our way home and were talking about what it was, especially the strange red and white light that looked like a big searchlight. After we had reached a road called Amalievej, I turned to see if it should have come again. High up in the sky we then spot the very bright light and then decide to sit down and keep an eye on it. It took approx. 2-3 minutes, and it disappeared into the sky. It became so small that we could no longer see it. I have talked to my father a lot about what it could have been, and he then thought that it could have been a small hot air balloon that had just drifted far away and came back with another air stream. But it can't be, because we saw it, it was black, and we saw nothing but a black bus thing.

I am driving along main road 445 from Skanderborg towards Ry, when in an eastern direction (i.e. on my right) I see a vessel up in the air, at first glance it appears to be moving in a south-easterly direction, but this is a bit difficult to assess, since it wasn't moving very fast and I was in a hurry myself. In any case, I lose sight of it behind me, and only after approx. 5 minutes is it possible for me to stick to the side. I am now just outside Ry. I get out of the car and scan the entire horizon to spot it again, but despite it being bright sunshine and completely cloudless, I can't spot it. I then proceed to my destination in Ry, where I arrive a few minutes later. Here I catch sight of it again, and now, as I myself stand still, I can ascertain that it is moving in a north-westerly direction, where I follow it until it is out of sight. The vessel was in approx. 1 km. altitude, I will shoot at (it was clearly lower than some of the other planes I saw that day anyway). The shape of the vessel itself was oval, and without visible wings or anything. In terms of color I would think it has been glossy as you could see the sun reflecting in it. No sounds could be heard, nor was there any white streak left behind, as is usually the case after ordinary planes. It all happens between 13.45-14.00.

I walk through the yard (Ringertoften in the northwest) on my way to my laundry. I look up and see a bright star, I think at first. But then I see that it is 3-4 bigger than the biggest bright star I have seen. It moves and pulses a bright orange light. But it does not move in a straight line like a satellite or plane, but a little "wobbly". Then I stop and follow it approx. 1 minute. It is up above the cloud cover, which has large clear holes through which you can see the dark sky and a few stars. And I hear no noise from the vessel/object even though the evening is completely quiet. Finally, it pulsates wildly. The light gets smaller and disappears completely. Then it has only moved a short distance across the sky.

My observation took place when I was 12 or 13 years old around summer time. My observation was 2 very bright red orbs moving in a non-uniform trajectory up and down just above the horizon. Since it was daytime, I was amazed at the brightness they had. The 2 luminous objects have been at a distance of approx. 10 km from my observation point. The movement patterns of the objects, which were incredibly erratic as they both went up and down and around each other, ruled out most types of aircraft and emergency rockets!!. The magnification of the binoculars I used to start with was 7X. But it was not enough to see what was behind the luminous objects. Therefore, I quickly picked up my telescope with a magnification of 150X. With this I could see a metal like figure behind the red glow. When I briefly (3 sec) changed an eyepiece to be able to better distinguish details, the objects completely disappeared from the otherwise wide horizon I had apart from the Slagelse area. I know that the day after this experience UFO sightings were reported in West Zealand. Unfortunately I don't know more. To this day, I am still very much amazed, because over the last many years, as a keen amateur astronomer and not since, I have experienced nothing like it.

At 21.30 I, my better half and a friend are standing on our balcony. From the right, very low and totally silent, an object comes flying across the roofs. We may be talking about 300 meters up. The shape of the object itself cannot be fully seen due to the time in the evening. However, one could clearly see five-six vertical rows of about 15-20 constant white lights with a slight bluish tinge. Four flashing red. What we noticed was that the whole trip from right to left, i.e. from NW to SE, it was low-flying, slowly flying, and without a sound at any time. I said to the other two "see a very low-flying plane", to which our friend bluntly replied "that's not a plane at all". I contacted Copenhagen Airport to find out if they had anything in the air in the area, which was denied.
I see between 10 and 15 flames which disappear into the clouds. The whole thing lasted approx. a min.

Again I saw from my garden a very bright, white light like a star, which flew dangerously round then to the high and to the left round and straight out at high speed. Then to get smaller and fade away, like a light that went out. About the same height as airplanes. What was it. Second time in a few days.

I just read in the news about a drop on a lens that was sent in as a UFO and that you have many explanations for natural phenomena. I saw something when I was a kid approx. 6-7 years old. for which I always wanted an explanation, if you can give it, I would very much like to hear about it. In approx. In 1992, my father built a summer house in Fjellerup. We lived every weekend in a caravan on the plot while my father built. One morning approx. at 8 we eat breakfast, my mother, me and my sister. My father had started work early. He calls us all out to see something strange. We have a sea view. Out at sea, there is quite clearly a powerful orange ball. Approx. same color as red-hot metal. It is quite large because we can see a fishing boat further out and it looks very small. The ball stands still for approx. 1 min and hovers just above the water. Suddenly it starts slowly going from side to side, the distance is huge every time it goes from side to side. The speed increases and the distance it moves with becomes greater and greater, the speed clearly becomes faster and faster You probably think of some light that reflects, but it wasn't, you could see the ball a bit like 3D. There were very few people there in 92. It was there physically, like a bullet. Don't know what it was, have thought about it a lot since, have you guys heard of anything like this before and is there any explanation as to what it could be?

My wife and I see two bright flashing lights, as if they were two planes reflecting the sun, but systematically with approx. 1 blink per SEC. - and planes can't move like that, they reflect like that. There were two flashes, not normal. light from planes, we see it as 2 UFOs. At the start, they stand almost still, and we manage to get a pair of binoculars, without it being possible to identify them further. No. 1 moves south, straight away from us and slowly disappears under ridges in the distance (south of Mossø). No. 2 moves slowly to the west and gradually disappears under the same long ridge.

I lay and looked at the stars on a bench in the yard. It was no more than 50 m above me, and looked like a v. And the speed was no more than 60-80 km/h. Discovered it because I could hear something bigger sliding through the air. Very quiet.

I'm driving due west on the freeway when my daughters and I spot this short, oblong, white and slightly shiny object in the sky. The sky is cloudless and the object is conspicuous, as it neither looks like a cloud nor a streak. I drive 110 km per hour and the object is seen in a southerly direction. The object is on our left while driving for the next 10-15 min. It almost looks like it is "stuck" in the sky. Sometimes it disappears, after which it reappears. I can't figure out if it's because the direction of travel changes slightly. At some point it's gone. Our observation probably has a reasonable explanation. However, we were very excited as it was an unusual sight for us. My daughter took pictures and video.

I was standing in my garden smoking a cigarette when suddenly I saw a large ball come flying. It flew faster than an airplane and was completely silent. When I couldn't see it anymore, I looked back from where the first one came and saw 2 more, and it went on like that for approx. 20 minutes Maybe 50 of them came. We filmed it on the mobile phone and took pictures with a digital camera. They all flew the same route and the same altitude. They were all the same size except for one who was maybe twice as big. It seemed to fly closer, and not quite on the same trajectory as the others, but ended up flying the same course as the first ones, and then disappeared into the horizon. I ended up not being able to see them anymore because they were blocked from my view by trees and roofs.

I was standing outside the house when I spotted something that I thought was a plane that was going to land in Aalborg. But the light wasn't clear enough for it to be a plane. Followed object which moved slowly closer for approx. 2 minutes, after which it picked up speed and rose steeply upwards at great speed. Could follow it far up in the sky until it disappeared among the stars.

My son sees a bright orange light. We are standing outside and straight up in the air there is a bright orange light, no sound and no flashing lights. I've never seen anything like it and was totally dumbfounded and couldn't think of taking photos. The weather was almost starry and completely windless. It flew in the same trajectory until it disappeared.

New Year's Eve it's just after midnight approx. 00.15 1/1-2010. The weather is clear and cold with a full moon. The stars are very visible due to the good visibility. It's New Year's Eve and we're out to see the fireworks. We stand and look around, and spot something that is NOT fireworks, a bright orange spot of light without flashing like an airplane, approx. 4 times larger than a powerful star, seen in the east with a steady course to the west. After approx. 20-30 sec. heading west, the ball of light turns off, heading south slightly rising. It gets smaller and disappears in the sky after some time. Sound?? not known due to background noise. I think that the ball of light had a height of 2,000-3,000 meters at first OBS. Speed 200-400 km/h, distance approx. 5,000-10,000 m.

I had set up my Gopro Hero 4 camera in the garden to photograph the Lyrid meteor shower. The camera was set to Nightlapse with a shutter speed of 30 seconds, and continuous recording. Shooting stars, of which I only got 3 shots, only appear in one image, as they don't last more than the 30 sec. shutter speed. Airplanes like to appear in multiple images, as long streaks that start in one image exactly where it ended in the previous one. I have been photographing the rotation of the stars in this way for the past six months and have never observed anything that could not be immediately explained. But in these pictures there is an object that moves across the sky and flashes approx. every 15 sec. In the pictures, it appears as two short lines of light on a line. It also looks like the flash is not momentary, but flashes up and down again, as the line of light is thin at the ends and thick in the middle. I have emailed the photos to Ole Henningsen, and can also email photos of shooting stars and planes from the same series, if there is an interest in comparing. I don't think it's a real UFO sighting myself, but since I myself can't figure out what behaves like that in the sky, you are the only ones I can think of to ask.

On Sunday, June 27, I'm out enjoying the good weather, and with 2 friends I went down to Kolding Marina. I look at the really nice so-called "good weather clouds" when I spot what I first think is a seabird at a very high altitude, and tell my companions to look up. They do, and it is at the height of the clouds, because it passes through one right at that moment. But soon we discover that it is not a bird, as it does not "flutter its wings". Its shape is almost like a small, elongated "stump", bright white. It continues noisily at good speed to pass over our heads, still at a great height. Since it is directly above us, the sunlight is reflected in it, or else it lights up from within; then write it back to the first luminosity and we discuss what it might be and can both rule out airplanes, gliders, balloons, satellites and kites. The object continues its course to the southwest and, just as it came into view, disappears into a distant cloud. During the incident we were sorry that we did not have binoculars with us, as we might then have been able to write off the sighting as an Unidentified Flying Object. But until we find out what it was, well, it was a UFO.

Saw some bright light, thought it was landing lights on a plane. But could see that it wasn't. It was silent, and seemed like controlled speed. After a moment, I could hear a sound like a fuser rocket. A few stars came from the bottom.

I wake up somewhere between 3 and 4 in the morning to give my son the pacifier. I lie down in bed again, and approx. 10 minutes later I can sense through my eyelids that there is a bright white light flashing in the middle of the bedroom. I don't make a sound because I'm afraid of waking our son. But I can't really see much because of the bright white light that flashes and lights up the room. It does it for maybe 5-10 seconds in the bedroom and then moves out into the kitchen, then slowly gets weaker and then disappears completely. Approx. somewhere between 5 and 10 min later, I hear some kind of driving/aircraft above the house for a while. I really wanted to get up and see what it was, but as soon as I lift my head from the pillow the sound disappears very suddenly. When my boyfriend wakes up to go to work, I ask him if he saw the light too, and he very definitely replied YES, and that he had no idea what it was, but that it was very strange. Which I can only give him credit for. A little afraid that there might have been "someone/something" in our home.

Two flying objects come in from the south at low altitude (under a thin cloud cover) over Jægerspris. Since they are closest, they fly past for approx. 60 degrees height and turns over to the north, where first one disappears and 20 sec. after the second disappears before the eye at a height of about 10 degrees. The observation is filmed on an Ipad. Since they are the closest, they are estimated at 300-600 m. altitude. Bright orange-red, completely silent. Brightness 50x Venus. I've looked at the stars and the sky a lot, but never seen anything like this. Uniform brightness. No blinking. Round orange ball of light.

3 flying objects, 2 flew quite close, one further back and further down towards the ground, lit up brightly, rose rapidly and continued to fly. Observed from the car and it is not known how long they flew, but they were observed from the car for approx. 10 minutes. Didn't look like airplanes but were 3 fairly round objects in the sky. Was constantly in motion.
Then a big round white light. It was constant. It suddenly became very small and disappeared in a flash.

I was out to walk my dog at 10.30pm. I see a ball of light for approx. 200 meters high. At first I think it must be a plane, but it dawns on me that it's cloudy. The clouds must be at a height of 300 meters, and planes don't go down that far. The ball of light comes floating slowly from west to east. Guess it must be an emergency rocket. But it stops for a moment to disappear at a slightly higher speed towards the north. I follow it with my eyes, but it quickly fades in and is gone.

I was sitting on 25/7-2012 in Nørresundby (Aalborg) and talking to my family out in the garden. Suddenly, while I'm talking to my stepfather, some light above his head catches my vision, and I see something very strange for a split second. 2 streaks of light that approach each other in an identical arc from each side, and where they meet, shoot vertically into the air. The arches both had 2 colors, red and green in separate formation as seen in a rainbow, which this was not, however, since the brightness was intense enough to catch my eye, and since the sun was not out, at 23:30 approx. Next I thought of laser light, but that didn't seem to explain what I was seeing either. I have spent the last day waiting anxiously to see if there might be a similar observation on your website, but without success, after which I will now ask for your immediate offer. I was the only one who saw it as it only lasted a second and I was the only one sitting facing north/northwest where this happened. Neither did fireworks, which the colors reminded me of most of all, match what I saw, both because it seemed too symmetrical, almost like a triangle with soft long sides and no top, and it also shouldn't be able to change its path so drastically and vertically up into the night sky . Will greatly appreciate receiving your offer for an explanation, and contact you finally if you want the details elaborated.
Saw an orange-red flying thing in the sky --- high speed -- with human eyes the size of a handball --- silent ---

Was out with dogs when I see something that looks like a star shining bright white light. As I follow it I can see it moving fast and the light dimming and gone it was. No clouds very few far away. The sky was perfectly clear. Took approx. 7 to 13 sec.

We suddenly spotted a black/very dark thing in the sky. We stood looking at it for a long time. And couldn't figure out what it was. It can't be a helicopter, (there was no sound). And it didn't move at all. We agreed that what we saw couldn't be done as it just stood still in the air... We couldn't see an explanation for it. We took a picture, but it only shows a "spot", I'll send it to Ole Henningsen. Hope to hear more as what we saw seems completely impossible.
Filmed object that came hovering across the sky from the southwest and disappeared to the east.

From my bedroom window at At 4.48 I saw a green glowing object over Nørreskov. It "hung" in the air approx. 10 seconds, after which it "sunk" or descended behind the forest. I looked for a while to see if it came back. It didn't. The object looked flat elliptical. My house is located at 56.15 degrees North and 10.3 degrees East.

A purple flash like airplane. Just bigger more colorful and just a glance. Don't come again? Drove on the E45 motorway. The flash came much higher than towers that stand on the ground, and lower than airplanes fly. Looked a bit like an explosion far away. Duration under one second.

The sky was completely clear when I saw a strange "Cloud" in the sky. It was elliptical and stood vertically, like a rocket. It was far away and not very big. I took pictures of it on my mobile, and when you zoom in, you can see that it is hollow in the middle. After a few minutes it began to stretch upwards. I have never seen anything like that.
I was out walking the dog before going to bed when I saw an object the size and color of a bright bright star coming from the lake. Flew right over me and disappeared towards nv.

I saw something incredibly beautiful. I could hardly believe what I saw... I was afraid to go out on my balcony. Unfortunately I had nothing to record what I saw. A large triangle that glowed red and white alternately, it had several like small light bulbs. All of a sudden 2 more came, very close together, almost on top of each other, and they were all transparent, after that came another and another, in total I think there were 5 or 6 flying in the same area. They were all glowing triangles and flew in different directions except for the first one I saw which went silent. I quickly called my boyfriend, but he didn't believe me... After several minutes of knocking on my neighbor's door, she came out with red eyes as if she was sick, and I asked her if she had seen the strange triangles outside in the sky. She said I'll have a look, but closed the door, so I don't know yet if she saw the glowing triangles. I went back to my balcony and the triangles slowly disappeared, one became completely transparent, the other flew up towards the room and two others flew together towards the water and the others did not see. After a few minutes, several different airplanes flew over Østerbro, maybe a helicopter, because I could hear the sound. I was completely confused and began to doubt what I saw, as I myself thought it was a very very strange experience and because my girlfriend did not believe me. But I know what I saw.

There are actually 2 observations with the same appearance in the same area with a distance of 200. First object moved in one from E to W, and I sense, was accompanied by slight engine noise (perhaps imagination). I didn't think much of it, but thought it must be a sports aviator. The next time, i.e. after 10 min., I became much more alert and observed the object quite clearly as it passed over my head completely noiselessly coming from the NW. It looked like a container/bag with strongly pulsating glows in a yellowish and faint reddish color, which passed over my head for maybe 100 mtrs. height carried by the wind perhaps using a helium balloon.

I was out in my yard to smoke a cigarette. I looked up at the sky and saw a machine of some kind flying across the sky at a pretty high speed. Much faster than normal planes. It was light grey/white and completely silent. It only took a few seconds to fly across the sky. It was not so high up, like a very low-flying plane.
My family and I went for a walk by Fredensborg Castle and took some pictures. When reviewing our images, we saw a strange gray feature in the sky. Pictures can be sent if interested.

Me and my sister were driving a few years ago on a small country road outside the village of Gørding in West Jutland. When we both noticed an object that seemed to be floating in the air over some fields further up on our right. After watching the object for a few hundred meters we stopped the car and both got out to see what it was. What struck us most was that it stood completely still in the air without making the slightest sound. It was relatively large. It's a bit hard to judge the size as we don't know how far away it actually was, but would shoot at about the size of a medium sized airplane. The object lay horizontally in the air, was triangular, black and had white lights in each corner and a reddish light in the middle.
There is not much more to write than your questions. Feel free to call for details.

Driving east on Brandevej, where an object comes at very high speed across the sky from south to north, but my view is blocked by trees after a few seconds. The object glows green and red either in front or behind, but it flies so fast that I can't remember if the red is in front or behind. I stop the car and get out, but can't see, hear or smell anything! The object appeared to be pretty far down, probably about 20-25 degrees above the horizon.

I was out for an evening walk with my dogs, when suddenly something the size of a small orange/glowing beach ball with some kind of wreath on the edge comes. At first I think it's a street lamp, or that I've seen visions, but then it comes like jumping silently over a house and then jumps further across the street and almost like a bouncy ball it jumps over two other houses. I have the choice to run in after someone, as I am alone and of course without a mobile phone. Typical. But I chose to follow it, because it changed direction behind the houses heading upwards towards the sky over Helgenæsvej, and up into the sky to become something flying that flashed red behind. Unfortunately couldn't see what it became, as it was too far away heading towards Præstø/Næstved Centrum right there in between. My brother thinks it's ball lightning I've seen, but it wasn't bad weather, actually frosty, and it wasn't fireworks, I also ruled that out when I saw it, which was otherwise a fascinating sight, and I'll remember it as long as I live and am grateful that I got to see it.

When my sister and I were out walking the dog, we first saw an orange-red fireball moving behind the trees in the forest - I thought I was going crazy, but it was moving across the sky. The "thing" moved relatively quickly - another one came and we ran home to get a camera - suddenly there were three more and we had seen a total of 5 UFOs? of approx. 10 minutes. There was no sound to be heard and the glow from the fireball flickered slightly. There is absolutely no doubt that it was not a plane, a shooting star or fireworks. The apparent size when they were right up above us was like a football.

There were 3 of us looking at the starry night sky, where first I and then my girlfriend spotted the 2 objects flying in a zig-zag pattern one after the other. The distance between them was not constant, but variable. When one side moved, it took 2-3 seconds. before the other moved in the same direction. The distance to the ground was well above flight height and in min. 15-20 km. height. It was not satellites or planes, as the speed was too high, and both fast and slow in tempo. They were both with a faint red-white light, neither square nor oblong but more round or oval and very small due to the distance. The whole thing lasted approx. 2-3 min., before they were out of sight and towards the east above a cloud cover that lay over Copenhagen.

Had been visiting my son when on the way home I see a very beautiful glowing warm (orange/red) object in the sky. Saw immediately that it couldn't be a plane, as the plane's light is bright white and bright red. My phone rang and my son asked if I could see the 6 luminous UFOs in the sky... But at that time I could only see one... Needless to say my son stood on his balcony to wave goodbye to me. I stopped and waited a moment, then came over the roof and just after the first object an equally beautiful luminous UFO. I told him to get his camera, which was out front. However, my son still saw the 6 flying in formation, 1 in front, 4 in the middle and 1 coming as a rear stopper.. It was all over quickly, because they seemed to disintegrate or fly behind some clouds.. No sound or flashing lights..... My son got a picture of one of them... Since I've gone approx. 5 min and I'm about to get home, another beautiful object comes from the south, which, however, flies directly to the north, but disappears behind some clouds... It was quite an intense experience..

I saw from my balcony something I thought at first was a plane because there was plane noise at the same time, but the light was far too strong to be a plane - in that case there was fire in the plane. Upon closer observation, it could be determined that the sound and object were not connected. I saw to the north in the direction of Roskilde Cathedral, a fireball-like object coming from the east and moving west at a speed faster than an airplane. To follow the object, I ran into the living room to see it from my northwest facing window. The object disappeared behind the houses on the other side of the street. Then I went out onto the balcony again, and then another fireball, similar to the first, came across the sky in the same direction. It was as if you could sense a disk rising up behind the light/fire.

An orange/red ball shape, no sound. Moving from north to south and at a speed roughly equivalent to an airplane during landing and at constant altitude in a very straight trajectory. Looked like it was only approx. 1 km up and approx. 5 km away from me (Safe optical illusion). The size was approx. to a single crown held out in outstretched arm. Didn't disappear into the horizon, but disappeared from the sky suddenly after it got far away from me. Could watch it for approx. 4 minutes. I spend a lot of time looking at the night sky and almost every time I see flying satellites high up and know very well that they can shine a lot and disappear suddenly when the sun no longer shines on them, but I have never seen this before, and as I said so it seemed to be close. Many must have seen it, because it shone brightly on the starry night. It was DEFINITELY NOT an airplane. It must surely also be visible from Kastrup airport, as it was approx. in the direction it eventually disappeared. Hoping very much for an explanation.
Half-round sphere with red beam. To the east-northeast perhaps. Took a picture of it with my digital camera, three pictures.

There are 5 of us sitting when my mom sees an orange light coming in obliquely from a northern angle and looks like it's descending. At first I think it is a piece of comet (rock) that burns up in the atmosphere and makes the others believe it. Immediately afterwards, there are 3 completely identical phenomena that I want to shoot at, have been almost vertical over a point a little south-west of Aarhus. The color was orange, like a body with fire, but there was no tail, as expected for e.g. a comet. The 4th "ball" dissolved/split in two, with one part crashing to the ground at exactly 10:26 PM, and then the other half burned out - although it continued somewhat on the same trajectory. There were no sounds at all, and the path in which they flew was not exactly the same, but still roughly the same in direction. We have contacted DMI, who were not aware of any special weather phenomena this evening.

Sees a stretched bright star in a still bright evening sky, but notices that it shines VERY brightly. Tells my boyfriend to come and see the planet hanging outside the window. He says: Hm, strange how bright it shines in a "day" sky. He sits on the sofa and looks at it and then says: but - so it moves a bit fast from a star of being, I think it's a plane. A plane I say - it has had the same direction and altitude for the ten minutes I have seen it. And then I go out and film it to see if it moves. And later I take a few photos after it has moved a distance of approx. 20 minutes. Is it a planet? Doesn't it seem to move like an airplane should?

I woke up last night and lay looking at the stars from my pitched roof window. It didn't take long before I spotted a very clear glowing "thing". At first I was convinced it was the North Star, but when I located the Chariot it dawned on me that this was not a possibility. The size of the "thing stone" was slightly larger than the other stars (about 3-4 times larger than the average stars), I would actually say that it was a bit monstrous compared to the other bright objects in the sky. The shape of the unknown "thingest" was oblong, and from the object two rays shone from the sides - whereas the other stars were more circular, and their light under the star was a circular arc, and not two rays. The color that the "thing stone" had was dark, clear, luminous and curry yellow. The "thing stone" moved in an oval path that took approx. 5-6 min. I observed the "thingesten" at 2 am and stayed awake for approx. an hour, i.e. until 03, but the "stone" was still visible. When I got up at 4.30, the "rock" had disappeared from the sky.
My daughter took a picture of flying swans, when we got home and saw the picture, there was something UFO-like in the picture.

Went out on the balcony to get some fresh air, when I immediately saw a strong light that alternated between white and red. I do that often, as I often see the planes come in for landing at the airport. After approx. 30 seconds the bright white light got weaker but still pulsing/flashing, nothing obnoxious about it either. I've seen hundreds of planes coming in, so I assumed that was the case here as well. Usually when I see this I can also see a movement in the direction of the plane. However, what caught my attention was that this seemed stationary. It hung in the same spot for some time, dimly glowing/pulsating. After two to three minutes it started moving at a very slow pace towards the east and in the same trajectory the whole time. It was thus not a question of a plane that was coming in for landing. I know the routine by now and this was, the more I think about it, quite unusual. It could of course have been a plane, but I doubt it. Just wanted to share this in case there are others who have seen the same thing.

My niece and I drive home on the Holbæk motorway in a westbound direction, between the Gevninge and Kalundborg exit. Suddenly, my niece spots a flying object with a large black trail of smoke behind it. It doesn't look like smoke from an ordinary airplane, as this is much more powerful, and then it is as if it suddenly steers very downwards towards the ground. It also wobbled from side to side as you can see in the pictures. It didn't look like an ordinary plane, more like a plane with a fire on board, or a missile-like object, like when a space rocket goes wrong.

I was sitting on our terrace, and suddenly I saw above the neighbor's roof a white round light the size of a 1 krone - that is, something bigger than an ordinary star, slide quickly across the sky, to disappear behind a tree.

Was out on the terrace on Saturday night smoking with my father-in-law - an architect, a man of few words and an old sailor. He has seen everything and believes in nothing. Just before we go in, my eye is caught by something moving - quite far down, maybe 40 degrees above the horizon. Four-six dots of light in a kind of formation. Looks exactly like a constellation that has "torn loose". The formation races off above us and is gone in seconds, maybe even less than the five seconds. I point and shout "look, look!". Father-in-law looks up and just manages to see them before they disappear above us, behind the roof. Apparent speed only slightly slower than meteors. If they were birds, they must have been very few meters away. About the size of the bar in the Chariot and surprisingly unchanging compared to the large bow I managed to see them. There was absolutely no sound and the light intensity was the same all the time, like stars. No stretch, just dots. Even I thought the strangest thing was the way they slid. It is difficult to describe. The flight did not look like anything organic at all - supernaturally fast, more "sucked" than pushed, not at all a known way of flying. Father-in-law knows all about birds and celestial phenomena, but has never seen anything like this.

We come driving on Hygildvej from Ikast and turn left onto main road 439 (Fasterholtvej) towards Ejstrupholm, but I don't know how many km from where we turn off, but via the GPS numbers it was approx. here I saw it (N 55° 59.166', E 9° 14.762'), it had the same shape as a layer cake, I saw it by the sun being reflected from it, like when the sun hits a mirror, up above the trees. It moved from south to north.

I often sit up at night and stargaze as it's pretty so I know what a shooting star looks like, what satellites look like, what an airplane looks like, night storms, etc. Just for the record. But I was sitting looking at the stars when suddenly out of nowhere this object appeared. There was no light on it, no sound either. It was clear light gray and had an oval shape, with a bulge on one side. It was moving in a straight direction to the east, quite fast. I saw it approx. 3 - 3.5 sec. before it disappeared over the roof. As I said, I have seen many things in the sky in my time, but nothing like this at all. Just forgot that for me it was the size of a 20 kroner, so I find it difficult to estimate the height.

I notice a very small white spot in the sky almost overhead, it is flying in a northwesterly direction, the speed exceeds what I usually see on the scheduled planes that fly over the area, maybe double, and the shape is round and doesn't look like an airplane either, and there are no condensation lines. At first I think it is a soap bubble or feather, but with the constant fast speed of the object and the direct direction to the northwest, it is not likely, however, I have a hard time judging how far away the object is. If it's a soap bubble, it must be close, and I want to get my binoculars, but see that I can't reach it, and immediately afterwards the object disappears. It has been in the sky for approx. 10 seconds, and probably 5 seconds pass when it appears again, but this time the object zigzags like a butterfly, although still with a direction to the northwest, after 5 seconds it then disappears into thin air.

I go out and see a strong light in the sky, similar in strength to a car headlight at night. Very bright light, quite large object, flashing, possibly a smaller section attached below with a smaller light - we are talking about, it is a bright balloon, but it changes height and rises again sharply several times and it is speeding from the south to the east - I call one more person - no one understands what the powerful rather large object can be and not at all because it flies so fast - it all lasts 3-4 minutes, then it is out of sight to the east.
Comes driving in an ambulance on night shift and observes luminous oval in the sky north of Kolind. After approx. 20 sec it accelerates very quickly to the east/north-east and disappears.

Late on Monday evening, when I get home from a trip to the steakhouse, I decide to walk around the garden to enjoy the enormously beautiful night sky. The stars are incredibly bright and I am amazed at how many are visible this evening. After standing and looking at the sky for approx. 3-4 minutes, 3 red/orange lights catch my eye. Due to the light of the stars as "background light", I manage to see that the 3 lights form a triangle. I can sense that there is a dark, solid "body" that forms an isosceles triangle. It is the "tip" that flies forward, meaning that it is the short side of the triangle that is the rear end. The 3 candles sat on the points of the triangle. The speed was neither slow nor fast, but I could follow it with my eyes for 10-15 seconds. However, I was left with the feeling that it was "floating" above the sky, which is the word that best describes it. It was completely silent, I heard nothing that could be described as engine noise. Since I live out in the country, there are no sounds that could "blur" my hearing. I also had the feeling that it was flying relatively low, that is, it was not particularly high up in the atmosphere. I followed it with my eyes until it disappeared to the west. I've honestly never seen anything like it before! I felt like I was witnessing something completely unreal. I even whistled for it? For my brain imagined for a moment that it must be a very strange bird. And it always helps to whistle for strange birds... But must have known that thing in the sky was not quite normal.

My husband and I are on our way to Albertslund by car and drive on the motorway from Amager. Around Avedøre/Brøndby I think I see some light up in the sky. At first I think it's the cars' reflection of the lights, but when I look up I see for a split second a light moving at rocket speed to the north. As I am in doubt about what I have seen, I ask my husband and he tells me that he thought it looked like a saucer with light in it that disappeared extremely quickly to the north.

The object is not at a high altitude. At the same time, an airliner is seen much higher. The light is large - larger than the largest Venus, with a warm yellowish color. It is moving rapidly to the west. No sound and no flashing. We are usually quite sober and as sailors used to watching the sky.

Saturday 22.01.11 at around 21.00 I was out for a walk with my girlfriend. Near our apartment we saw a red light danger across the sky as it came out from behind the roof of a building. At first glance we just thought it was a plane, but suddenly another one came with the same light, speed, direction and height. This continued and we observed about 20 red lights passing silently across the sky. Glowing disappeared as they got far enough away. We are both curious about what it could be, but haven't found anything on the web about the same sighting, so I'm writing here to hear if there is anyone who might. could explain these lights. They were moving too fast and there were too many for them to be planes.

I'm lying in my bed watching television, when my eye, out of the window, suddenly catches a star-like object floating. Since I have already had experiences with UFOs before, I of course kept my focus on it. It was reasonably high above the ground 100+ meters and it moved slowly out over the fields in the direction of the køge center with a few minute pauses where it just hung still. As the second UFO I have seen, the best way to describe it is as a moving pulsating star that changes colour.

I had an experience on Refshaleøen that I would like to share with you. Video has been posted in the FB group on 20-05. A small flying thing comes by as I stand filming with my mobile phone. I'm thinking it can't be a bird or insect since it's winter and tempp. is approximately. 0 degrees and at 21.52. Do you have any other sightings in that area that night?

At is 23.10, and we (my wife and I have guests) are on our way out into our garden, partly to see the full moon, partly to follow our guests out to a hut in our garden, where they will sleep tonight. At 23.11 we stand looking at the full moon, and in addition we see Saturn a little to the west at the same height just to the south, and further to the west Mars stands fine. It is cloudless and very bright because of the moon, and there is almost nothing else to see in the sky, except for something that looks like a star a little east of Saturn. It stands still, so we perceive it as a star that appears approx. half the size of Saturn, but suddenly it moves to the east, but at the same time becomes weaker, and then stops long before it reaches the Moon. Then it becomes clear again and rises at a steady speed towards the NW up above Saturn, until it is perhaps 10 degrees above, where it stops and disappears, that is, the light disappears. Then we saw no more of the object. We are quite speechless by what we have seen. None of us have an explanation for what it was. I am an amateur ornithologist myself, and have been all my life. I am also interested in the starry sky and have been looking at constellations and galaxies for several years. I wear glasses, but my vision is ok, and the people I was with have fine vision. I have also always followed the UFO phenomenon, but without seeing anything.

As it was a lovely starry evening with no moon, I went for a walk in the dark. I saw a star (looked like it) twinkling and saw it move. Thought it was a plane, but it was moving quite fast and was also faintly visible between the flashes. Then at the same time one more, it behaved the same way, flashing, but also faintly visible between the flashes, moving across the sky faster than a (router) plane. Spotted at least 4, maybe 5 simultaneously moving, flashing and shifting objects in various places in the sky, 2 of them at one point moving close past each other. There were several twinkling "stars" that did not move, but all other stars were visible as usual. It wasn't shooting stars, could follow the objects for many minutes. So none of them directly disappeared, but they could be gone if I looked in the opposite direction for another, then looked back - and it was gone. Curious if others have observed the same or if there is a completely natural explanation.

I sat looking to the east-south-east just after 1 p.m. 20 and then a red light. At first I thought it was probably a plane or something. After a few minutes, however, I became curious enough to go out into the field and see what it was. There was a red ball of light hanging over the field approx. 100 meters from me. It shone down on the field with a "pillar" of light. I went inside to get the mobile phone to take a photo, but when I came back out and was about to take a photo, the ball started to spin, then it disappeared where it was - it didn't fly, it was just gone.

There is no sound to be heard, but I see the object, like a jet fighter shape, sometimes turning on its side, like when there are displays. My daughter thought the object looked more like a large bird. The object size was probably around 20-25 centimeters. Too bad we weren't smart enough to take a picture before the object was far out on the horizon. The object flew far in a straight line out towards the water, it looked like it was going to land out there, but immediately afterwards we saw it rise up and far beyond the horizon.

I tested my newly purchased photo tripod by taking some long exposures with my digital camera from my balcony. When I had to check the result, I saw on two of them some objects I could not recognize. There are three objects on them: two groups of lights (three in each, with a 'beam' or 'halo' below) and a single brighter light to the right of them. As I said, I have 2 photos of them, one taken with an exposure time of 20 seconds, and one with 10 seconds. On the Photo in 20 seconds, the lights are strongest. Both photos were taken with my Canon EOS 300d camera and are in RAW format.
There were several of us who by chance saw a beautiful round bright red UFO over the sunset.

2 pcs. white dots. At first thought they were stars, but they were flying insanely fast. One stops completely and sort of waits for the other. The first one flies almost zik zak. They come very close to each other, after which they disappear to the east at an insane speed.

From my balcony, my daughter and I first saw a black ball-shaped flying object, followed by a similar object no. 2. No sound, or anything that could indicate high-flying birds or the like. No wings. The objects apparently flew slowly, without any form of evasion. Constant in direction and speed, from N towards N/W. I would guess that they flew for approx. 200 m height.

Walking the dog. Looking up, as always... In comes something elegantly floating. Be it at very high speed. The object is similarly shaped with 2 straight wings and a core. Fly somewhat diagonally/skewed in relation to the direction it follows. The strange thing is that it all happens so effortlessly, elegantly and yet so quickly. The light from the object cannot be compared to a light bulb, but more from glowing iron or similar - Light with faint orange, from inside the object. It all takes only 2-3 seconds, but is very clear and very different.

I study at VUC Holbæk. During the break I went outside to smoke. There I heard and saw a Nordic airplane. Keep an eye on it. Then all of a sudden I saw a circle with a powerful ball of light flying along under the plane. It went so fast that it took maybe 3-4 seconds before it disappeared.

properties.Colors: hvid med skær af, rød, grøn, blå
properties.content: I am walking towards Stærevej when my attention is caught by a created white light. At first I wonder if I have caught something in my eye, as the light flows out and has color changes at the edge. I look at it and think, it's probably just an airplane that has the landing projector on, but I think that the colors in the edges and the large diameter of the lights don't remind me of an airplane's projector. So I follow it and think, when it has passed me, there must necessarily be a change in the intensity of the light if it is a plane. But there was no change at all, 1 minute after it passed, a "real" plane came flying almost diametrically opposite the object. And I thought, that plane is probably flying low, but it also fits very well with the fact that if it could be seen on a flight operator's radar, he must have told it to fly low. After the real plane had passed, I followed the object with my eyes, which by this time was a tiny dot in the sky, and it most resembled a star that stood all alone, as there were no other stars directly on it. that section of heaven. In the middle of all this, I came across a man who had stopped his car and got out. Thinking that this was a very strange experience, I asked him if he had seen it too. To that he replied yes. He didn't know Danish. He said something about having experienced the exact same thing two years back in a forest. He turned right off Hulgårdsvej, possibly to try to follow the light a little further. And I turned my nose towards home.

I'm standing in the parking lot outside my car and I'm about to lock it. I look up at the sky in a western direction when I spot some light moving in the sky. It flies in an easterly direction towards the place where I stand. Suddenly I think - what on earth is that coming flying there. It comes flying at a height of maybe 200-300 meters and is enormously long, I would say over 100 meters. It's loud. I can't say the speed exactly, but it flies reasonably fast. The whole session takes about 5 seconds, after which it disappears behind the roof of a building. But the view is incredible. I will try to describe it. As I said, it flies at a height of 200-300 meters. It is very long, reportedly over 100 meters and is tall and at the same time a bit slender. It is cigar-shaped, however, with a nice rounding both at the front and at the back. It passes almost directly over the place where I am, however, slightly offset to the north, so that I can see the entire right side of it. Approx. 1/3 from the front on the right side there is a large window and approx. 1/3 from the rear there is a correspondingly large window. Light comes out of these two windows. There are only these two windows on the page. I can also see light shining out symmetrically to the opposite side, i.e. its left side, but I could not see windows there. I wonder that the light I could see from the windows seemed hazy and a bit dull. The color was slightly yellowish. The weather was very clear with a starry sky and moon. The object itself was very clear, but the light from the windows seemed somewhat hazy. There was no light anywhere else on the object to be seen other than the mentioned windows on the right side and symmetrical light on the opposite side. There was also nothing that flashed. There was no sound from the object in the form of engine noise, nor was there any sound of drag or other indications of noise or commotion. The object had no wings. This was what I saw. I could feel a growing sense of insecurity, so I went back into the factory where I worked. The clock on the wall showed 04.07 and the clock runs correctly (matches the radio). Therefore, the exact time for the observation is 04.05-04.06. I jotted down various details on paper, in addition to trying to draw the object as I saw it. Later in the morning (at 10 o'clock) I contact the Ringsted police to find out if they should have received reports of a flying object over eastern Ringsted at the time in question, but they had not. I can't be the only one who has seen this. Hope others have seen something that can confirm it. I myself know 100% that I have seen it. Unfortunately, I have no witnesses, photos or any other documentation for the above. Finally. Why have I chosen to rewrite and email this post? At first I was also against doing it, but curiosity and the hope that others besides me might have also seen something made me do it. I would also like to hear from you (SUFOI) if you have received this email and also from other people who may have on the night in question (18th March 2003 around 4am) seen something about this I have described. And at the very end, I would like to say that this feature is not fantasy, but really something I have seen with my own eyes.

Driving from the Helsinge side, where it is completely dark over the fields. I look out of the right car window. Sees a rather large ellipse shaped "object" in nice green colors with a large clear/luminous ball in the middle --- and like a whoosh it disappeared / "crashed" to the ground. I had to pull to the side and catch my breath. It was an amazing sight.

It was back in the eighties. We were 3 people in a south-facing living room when a 12-13 year old boy suddenly says: "What is that?". Then we looked out of the south-facing window and saw a large red ball moving quietly from west to east. The diameter of the sphere was between 10 and 15 m. Height above ground was slightly more than its diameter. When we could no longer see it from the living room, I ran out of the house and down the road so that I was directly behind its direction. Then I could see that the hemispheres, as on the left circle, moved after each other, did so in a track next to each other. There was no sound from the ball, no beams of light. When it had gradually become quite small, I went back to the house, and approx. ½ - ¾ quarter of an hour later, the boy said: "There it is again". This time the movement was a mirror of the first time.

Last night, out of our kitchen window, I observed an object at "star height" emitting red, white and blue lights in "flashes". Thought it was a plane at first, but it barely moved. It caught my attention, so I stood in the window. Then, for the next hour, I could follow it moving more and more to the south - approx. same line in the horizon. All else being equal, I would have thought it was a satellite (except for the light changes), but sometimes the "object" also moved up and down. A bit like a (slow) bee buzzing around something - i.e. the movement pattern. My husband watched it briefly but went to bed - a little shaken. My in-laws live in the house next to ours and I could see they were still up so I called them. They went to the window and then looked out into the garden. I went over to them and they admitted that it looked very strange. And I have some pretty down-to-earth in-laws. Since it was taking so long, I felt I had to contact someone. The best thing I could think of was to contact the police - not 112, but 114. I actually got to speak to a quite friendly police officer who did not - as you might expect - write me off as a Christmas brat or mentally ill. He said he would then stick his head out the window. Whether he just shook his head afterwards, I don't know. When it was a quarter past twelve I decided to go to bed.
