Last night at two o'clock my one son had to go to the bathroom and I went out to see if "it" was still there. It wasn't, but by then some fog might have started to come. It was gone. By way of background information, I would just like to say that last night the weather was unusually clear and almost no clouds. I should just add to this story in closing that I am quite shaken by this experience which goes against everything I normally hold to. I have never believed in aliens, the supernatural or karma/fate for that matter. There is probably a pretty good explanation for this, but what it could be is beyond my comprehension. I spoke to a close colleague about the incident this morning and he believed there was an org. like yours - and we found this website on the web. Now I have reported what I saw.

On Saturday evening, my girlfriend and I smoke a cigarette on the terrace and look at the starry sky. I had been lucky to see a few shooting stars, so looked for more, but out of nowhere a very bright light suddenly appeared, started as the size of a star that is normally in the sky, but grew very quickly, probably 5 times the size, and turned very bright white, shortly after it was like a light bulb going out, went from very bright, to fainter and gone, it lasted approx. 7-8 seconds. I really don't know what it was, but it wasn't a shooting star or anything like I had experienced before.

My husband and I are driving from Viborg towards Ravnstrup when we see a very bright white light in the sky. At first we think it's an airplane, but it doesn't move. The light is very bright and white - a large luminous shape. There is only the shining light formation in the sky, no tail or the like. Suddenly it's gone (like flipping a switch) and won't come back, even if we keep an eye on the sky the rest of the way home.

I have followed a lot of various programs as well as had a website about so-called "Unknown objects" including unknown military aircraft types, including I have dealt a lot with the popular "Area51" also known as "Dreamland" in the large Groom Lake facility. Here I have heard a lot about research into a new propulsion system for aircraft. I saw on television pictures of an "airplane trail" that they believed was formed by this new propulsion system. I mean what I saw was VERY close to that. I walk home from work and look at the sky, I see a very strange trail of a plane. It starts very thin and then gets thicker and thicker. As it has become as thick as a normal airplane trail, the trail suddenly disappears into a nice gap, after which it reappears. The special thing is now, however, that small "notches" come out of the track, i.e. a straight flight track with small "bumps" from one side. The track continues like this for quite a while, after which it disappears completely. I wondered if it might be a gust of wind or something that had caused this strange formation, but I don't see how that could be possible. I have taken 2 pictures of the phenomenon, one of the place where the track stops and starts again, and 1 where you can see the small boils coming out of the flight track. However, the boils are not nearly as clear as they were when I first saw them, when I was on my way home from work and didn't manage to take the picture until the wind had taken hold of it a bit. What I might be interested in hearing were "log books" from the observation stations located in the area. The track came from the north, so it must have been across Tirstrup airport. Here, for example, you could find out if a plane has had engine problems and has stopped and started the engines in flight, or the like.

Orange flickering light the size of a little fingernail observed to the southeast. Moving slowly at a steady slow speed to the west. Gradually becomes smaller and finally disappears completely approx. 120 degrees above the horizon in a westerly direction.

I must have been around those 14 years. I sit on the windowsill outside the kitchen and look down on the street. I'm in love with a boy who lives in a house opposite. So I sit and see if I can catch a glimpse of him. At one point I look up at the sky a bit and then it appears. It looks like a star that seems to jump from one side to appear a little further on and then back again. It does that sometimes, and then it's gone again. I didn't commit to it at the time, but several years later I hear about UFOs and have thought since then that maybe I should tell about it. I have only told my family and a few really good friends, as for many years I actually thought it was something I had dreamed, sitting there on the windowsill.
Then 3 glowing dots in a row. Horizontal. Came from west to east, with great speed.
No information, just a link to a Facebook address which requires a password. Here should be a video of the observation.

Weather: Lightly cloudy with starry skies in the "holes". The sky is bright (illuminated by street lights), in stark contrast to the black night sky. I'm sitting in a café's backyard talking to an acquaintance while smoking a cigarette. My attention is caught by movement (from the area behind my acquaintance, i.e. in a northerly direction), and I see what I first think is a plane from Billund. The plane (referred to from here on as plane, as I am skeptical and distrustful of these observations) passes under the cloud cover, over my acquaintance and me. My acquaintance sits with his back to the plane, so I am the only one who notices it. At first I think that it is a low-flying plane from Billund, but when it passes very quickly and completely and completely silently, I am very surprised (the plane also has a strong silhouette against the illuminated clouds above it, so I had no doubt , that it was very low-flying). My friend didn't see anything.

Me and my wife were out smoking, when first two luminous "balls" appeared at two different heights above the horizon. After 2 minutes, 2 more appear and disappear in the same place as the others. It was windless and cloudless, and they had a moderate speed.

I saw three bright points that looked like red emergency flares with absolutely constant light. They moved at a steady speed across the sky like airplanes at high altitude. As they moved away to the southwest the light dimmed a little because they were above the slightly transparent clouds. They kept a solid triangle formation the entire time. There was no sound from them. My wife saw them too.

I had gone out into the garden to put a pram in the shelter, as they had promised rain the next day. I looked up at the sky and was quite surprised at how starry it was. I decided to study the sky a bit. We have a good view to the southwest and northeast. It actually looked like a triangle standing on its tip. Then the 2 BRIGHTLY luminous objects began to move vertically into the air. They followed each other with exactly the same distance between them, all the way up, while the light in both grew dimmer and dimmer. It went very slowly. Then they were gone. I was all over the floor and went in to get some paper to draw on and I also looked at the clock. I hope there are others who have seen the objects, because it was an incredibly beautiful sight.

properties.Colors: vil sige grå som noget der oser
properties.content: My inquiry concerns a UFO experience.. however some time ago. It's funny how people think a UFO is almost always round/oval. The experience of a UFO that I saw many years ago is nowhere near similar to anything around. Unfortunately I have no pictures, but fortunately a witness, so I know. that I'm not completely crazy ;). Unfortunately, I have to guess a bit ahead of the year. But would think we are around the late 80's. There I was, a teenage boy (from 1974) and one late summer evening I was cycling on a path on my way home. We are in a town south of Aarhus (8355 Solbjerg). It is not dark yet and the weather is mild and there are no people anywhere. Just me and my bike. The trail I ride isn't crazy long, but that day it seemed extra long. On the right side of the path there are a lot of tall trees of various grand and pine trees, and on the opposite side there is a soccer field and some institutions. The road my home is on is just like parallel to the path on the opposite side of all the trees. Well, I come by bike, and for some reason while I'm riding I look up at the sky. And there, just above me is an elongated moving cloud-like object (I have no idea how far up the object was.. maybe half a kilometer.. maybe more). I can feel myself shuddering and getting a little scared, so of course I cycle faster and see that the cloud seems to be following me along the path. When I reach the end of the path and have to turn right onto the road, the cloud speeds up further ahead of me, and I quickly cycle the 30 meters towards the road I live on. When I turn, the cloud just turns with me. Yes, it is actually true, although it sounds like a good story. And when I turn right again into the road where I live, I finally see another person at the end of the road (Parkvangen). The cloud is then above me, just as it has followed me. I cycle as hard as I can and look up and the cloud just got faster. I actually cycle past my home and down towards bystanders and shout "look up at the sky".. or whatever I have said. The cloud "gasses up" and disappears over the field at the end of the road. The woman, who fortunately managed to see the object, still lives on the opposite side of where my parents live. So every time I see her, I have to check to see if we still have the shared experience together. And she confirms that it is true. That was my story. Don't know why I haven't told about it before. But now it's done and wondering if there are others who might have experienced the same thing. Because it will probably be a bit difficult to explain away my experience with a raindrop on my retina or something else;).

My daughter and I were out looking for shooting stars when we saw some light in the sky moving rapidly to the east. Height maybe like a smaller plane. There was just no sound at all. And no blinking. We followed it with our eyes and in a split second it was gone.

It was cloudy and close to dark, and a few stars could be seen in the sky. I looked out the dormer window from my living room and saw a dot of light in the sky that almost looked like a firework rocket heading for the top to explode. I didn't think much of it at first, as it is now normal at this time of year for people to start trying out their fireworks, and it often happens in that direction for approx. same height (10 degrees above the horizon) and light intensity. I looked anyway because I was waiting for the explosion. However, it did not explode after approx. 5 seconds of observation and, strangely enough, was left hanging for approx. in the same place in the sky. When I looked closer, the object had what looked like flashing traffic lights, so I thought it was an airplane that had come down a long way, but it didn't really move out of place like an airplane does. The object appeared to be about 0.5 km away, based on the brightness of typical air traffic lights. My curiosity was really piqued when I discovered that it danced restlessly and randomly around the place in a way that neither a plane nor a helicopter can do. I could see it moving because I was looking through the branches of our leafless birch tree in the garden. It was still bright enough to distinguish the branches from the sky. I opened the window to see it more clearly and observed the movements for about half a minute. The movements were approx. a finger's width wide, as when you hold your index finger out in an outstretched arm. It was cloudy in the area where the object was located. I ran downstairs and called my mother and I then ran down the driveway to study the object which I estimate was probably between 0.5 and 1 km away and still approx. 10 degrees above the horizon. We both observed the object for a few minutes and saw several of the unusual movements. We both agreed that it was no ordinary aviator. The object flashed in a rhythm of 4 or 5 flashes alternating between red and white lights placed in a diamond shape at each of its 4 corners and an additional light in the center. The flashes were symmetrical and each cycle lasted about 2 seconds. It still looked like a traffic light, but seemed a bit more "advanced" and a bit more powerful. I then ran in for binoculars and in after my father. When I came back out, the object had weakened and was descending behind the trees to the south. Through the binoculars I couldn't really see any more detail than when I first saw it and it was too dark for me to see a shape. I guess it was now between 2 and 5 km away. Unfortunately my father could not see anything and the object was now approx. as faint as a star. My father and mother then went inside again. I then went further up the road to the south-east to get clear of the trees, so that I could have a view of a field between two farms down to approx. 2 degrees above the horizon. The object was now so far away that I could only catch a few glimpses through the binoculars. I looked around regularly to check if there might be more objects in other directions, but there were none. After approx. 3-4 minutes I caught a few glimpses of it approx. 6-8 degrees above the horizon heading towards the clouds, and then it disappeared. Since we live in the countryside, it is difficult to judge whether there was sound, as agricultural machines and cars drive around in the distance, so possibly sound from the object would be difficult to distinguish from other sounds, but I could hear nothing from that direction. A helicopter would have made a lot more noise. If the object had not moved as it did, I would have thought it was a normal airplane or a helicopter. In fact, I later thought it was returning, but this was a regular flyer heading north-north-east, its traffic lights alternating between either side of the wings.

In a westerly direction from Hhorsen's west, low on the horizon I saw 2 yellowish objects just around sunset. You could just guess that they were moving in a northerly direction. The objects were round, but the distance was great, so it was hard to see if they might have looked different. They were the size of a pea from my point of view. I've spent a few days wondering if it was the sun doing some kind of mirroring I don't know about, but the strange thing about it was that they weren't at the same height. I would think that one object was approx. twice as high horizontally as the other, and there was also quite a distance between them vertically. The observation lasts approx. 8-10 minutes, then they disappear behind a cloud cover that was about to move in over the city. After the last one disappears, I think I can sense one more disappearing behind the cloud. The date must be taken with reservations, it may well have been 1-2 days before or after.

One morning surprise on Constitution Day, 5 June 2018, I see something really striking. It was around 07:22 in the morning, when I had just walked out the door from my apartment and then had to go over to my car, which was parked 30-35 meters ahead. I manage to take only 4-5 steps forward, after which I look up into the clear sky, a beautiful almost transparent moon and a white cigar-shaped object flying directly past the Moon and quietly moving forward to the right. I pick up my stupid mobile phone, and it takes me 12 seconds to, first of all, find my phone, unlock it, go into camera, switch to video, and finally start filming it. I have a video recording of it. But since this thing that I would classify as a "UFO" flies behind a lot of trees and tall buildings, I can no longer see it, which is why I could not film it anymore. A short video, and unfortunately filmed with a measly iPhone 4s. It is difficult to see it in the video on a handheld phone, but if you watch the video on the computer and in zoomed mode, you can spot it. My first thought upon discovery was… is that a strange bird flying? No, impossible, not quite up there around the Moon (almost). Is it a drone? (as my girlfriend also suggested).. eh, I thought that was impossible too, i.e. a drone at a height around the Moon, I don't think so. My thoughts afterwards, when I ran the video through with my eyes, were also... that it can't be a drone flying that far away at all. There are no giant drones that can fly so far away that you can see them. If it were an ordinary drone, and if it could fly that far, I doubt you could see it clearly with your eyes. Also the weird shape? It was definitely not a plane, I thought, especially since there was no smoke or anything coming out the other end. Not only that the speed of the object was somewhat faster than an airplane.

Was a slip in the garden and hit a line. Looking up over the road above the neighbour's house in the direction of Skarridsø and sees this red-orange glowing spot. Thinking ok, there are some fireworks in December and looking away. A few seconds later focus again on the object, bearing in mind that I have previously seen the same sight a year or two back a kilometer away from our residence, in a southerly direction. Now I'm absolutely sure, it's neither fireworks nor flares. The object moves quietly further south. The weather is overcast and the air hazy, but the glowing orb stands razor sharp and pulsates a bit like some kind of star beaming, still in a mixture of red and orange. A little minute has passed and the light fades and disappears completely. I think the distance to the object is between two or three hundred meters, maybe more than half a kilometer, which is the distance down to the big lake in Jyderup.

We are driving from Ejstrupholm and have to go through Brande to get home. I'm driving and my 22-year-old adult son is sitting next to me. It's about. 9 km between Ejstrupholm and Brande and forest on both sides. We see a very large luminous white object (looks like a huge star) with 2 more luminous lights in the middle. At first we think it's a star, but it's too far down and it's not moving. My son sees that it flashes 2 times with an orange/golden light and then it is not visible. When we get to the roundabout - we drive back in the hope of seeing it again, but we no longer see it.

Approx. at At 22.50, myself and my friend drove into Svendborg. When we stop at an intersection in the center, I first notice a strong reddish light with a slight white glow in the sky. At this time there are no clouds in that part of the sky and think that at first it might be a very clear planet or star. Turning off at the intersection to pick up a pizza further down the street. When we get back to the intersection, we will stop for red again. K is now approx. 23.14. Looking skyward again, we see that there are now 2 more lights, all styled like the first one we saw. They stand in the sky as a larger slightly lopsided triangle with 2 lights evenly spaced and the 3rd with a greater distance to the 2, but in a way strategic in relation to each other. We drive on a road through the city, which is open with a clear view of the sky. As we watch, the 3 lights change from a triangle to a line across the sky. A very clear but calm shift, and we stick to the side and get out to be sure that we are being cheated by sounds from any. helicopter. Since I myself have an understanding of flying, I could not see anything related to airplanes or helicopters. And the way the formation changed direction was also out of the ordinary of flight. borders. I get 2 very weak pictures taken from the mobile phone and after 25-30 seconds the lights disappear one by one. At the same time, clouds have started to come over the city. During this whole process the lights were in the same air space in the sky and when we saw the other 2 lights they were considerably closer than when we observed the first one and all were below cloud level. The 2 lights have not been covered by buildings or clouds when they appeared.

We drive a taxi (each in a separate car) and had just dropped customers off at Faxe Ladeplads, when we notice in the sky 5-6 white and independent, elongated mists whizzing around the sky, and there is speed. Suddenly, they stop and “stand still” for a moment, then rush on. It goes fast. They move smoothly and at high speed and can change direction lightning fast. They can gather into a large and elongated fog, which suddenly splits into individual fogs, which then rush across the sky at high speed.

The flying objects resemble the lights, small clouds or balls of light. They are round and slightly elongated and blink once in a while. Their flying routine circled around each other a lot, with small quick movements to either the right or the left. Sometimes there are two other times three and they sometimes flash. The weather is very cloudy, so it looks like they are up above the clouds.

Both flew completely parallel and synchronously. They seemed to be triangular, or similar to our planes. Direction west south west. It looked like they had a lot of heat impact in the snout like a little less than when a meteor breaks into the atmosphere.

Over the horizon, an unexplained phenomenon can be seen from a family member's balcony. And then a mysterious, incongruous object, almost triangular, with bright white light, flashing, with yellow, red. And almost flew, up and down, and there were no planes, during this time. The object's origin came from the southwest to the northwest, where the object disappeared.

As indicated, my wife and I observed an unidentified object in a slightly overcast sky, making it difficult to judge speed and altitude. The course was completely correct. No blinking. It didn't seem like a strobe light or landing lights from an airplane. If there are other similar observations, we would like to know.
There were a total of 6 pieces - varying size (perhaps due to distance). The color was reddish. They slowly disappeared like a fading light - one by one. But it was always in the same position.

Tuesday 03. 04.2, at 22.15 I stood on my terrace, which faces north-east. I saw a plane the size of a 737, the whole plane plus the wings looked like it was on fire or, everything was glowing like it was burning but without any flames flickering. I hurriedly called my wife so she could see it. It moved toward us at normal flight altitude slowly, then it turned north and stood still for a short moment, then it moved more north, then it looked more like a round glowing ball, after which it rose vertically and became smaller and smaller . This happened in 3370 Melby. We thought it was an unusual experience, so we would be happy if we could get feedback from you. PS.: There was no sound of any engine.

Over the last 2-3 years I have observed these lights around 8-10 times on my way to work in Copenhagen. Always at approx. same time - around 22.40 to 23.10, when I have not been able to see them anymore. It took place on the section route 155 and route 21, from Svinninge to approx. Taastrup I have stopped a few times, and once looked at them through binoculars, and here, the episode in question, filmed them with my iPhone. The lights themselves look the same from time to time, and are also located in the same place. These are 1-3 strong yellow lights, which alternate to light up, 1, 2 or 3 at a time. It doesn't look like they are moving, not even between each other. The intensity appears to be constant. In the videos it looks like the intensity varies a lot, but it doesn't look like that when you look at them with the naked eye. And not even the one time when I looked through binoculars. The distance is impossible to say, but they are far away, as I have, most times, observed them from around Svinninge/Tuse, to Roskilde/Taastrup. The observations have only taken place in the dark months and when the weather has been clear and not cloudy. I actually wanted to see if I couldn't get a better recording with a better video camera with optical zoom and image stabilization before I contacted you. But unfortunately I haven't observed the lights since May 1, and have now switched to the day shift. So I probably won't see them again unless they also occur early in the morning. I have wondered a lot about what it could be. I am convinced that it is not spaceships, airplanes, hot air balloons, astronomical phenomena, street lamps, fireworks, emergency flares, laser lights, etc., as the characteristics of the lights do not match with some of these. I have loosely figured out the direction via various places, I have observed the lights, and Google Maps, and have got a direction around Frederiksværk. But I am far from certain that it is exactly there. However, I have thought about whether there is something military in that direction, and it could be flares in connection with exercises, for example. It surprises me that the lights are in the same place every time. But in the first of the videos, you can clearly see a flash of light at the ground, and two seconds later a ball of light appears. I have not noticed that before, nor by the observation itself. I first saw that on the video itself. However, it is only seen once. I don't know if it is something you have the time and desire to go into, but my curiosity is piqued, and it could be that it was something you had heard about before.

It was starlit when I went to bed, so I opened the first floor bathroom window to enjoy the view. I noticed a very bright star that glowed a little greenish. At first it stood still for a while, then I thought it moved a little. That couldn't be right, I thought, but then it suddenly moved a little to the left and stood still for a while. I called my wife and told her to come and see something strange. The light moved further to the left and stood still again. Then it moved to the right again in a long gliding motion, stopped and descended beyond the horizon. I thought that was it and did something else for a few minutes. I looked out the window again and saw that now there was a new luminous object, this time glowing red. Meanwhile my wife had come upstairs and we both stood watching the phenomenon. The new object behaved in the same way as the other. Smooth movements to the left and right, and all the time at the same height. Suddenly the light changes to green, and after a while it drops behind the horizon approx. same place as the other object.

I admired the starry sky from my apartment, it was completely starry, and I looked out through the open garden door. I looked at the constellation Cassiopeia and saw a "star" below Cassiopeia. I didn't immediately think about it, but suddenly the star quickly flew a short distance across the starry sky and then stopped very abruptly. This repeated three times and the star flew in different directions and very, very fast. Faster than, for example, a shooting star. The last time I saw it was in the south, but I didn't see it disappear because I was startled by the experience and closed the garden door.

properties.Colors: 3 blændene lys med en udefinerbar baggrund
properties.content: I just got home from work and was unhooking my trailer and just looked up in the air. When I looked to the north I saw 3 bright lights in an indefinable way, first they moved to the right very quickly and then slightly up. There was no sound and it went fast from one point to the next, I think of a helicopter or a drone, but there was no sound, I think, I see. I wanted to film with my phone. But then the 3 lights were gone, they just disappeared very quickly. A bit like someone was looking down from the sky. Light was probably everything between 500 meters and 1 km from me. They didn't light anything. So I don't know why they were there. I don't know if it was only me who saw what I saw.

For several evenings now I have seen a white light that looks like a star, but shines 5 to 10 times brighter than a star above Ballerup, but the strange thing is that it falls diagonally to the right very slowly during the evening, the time is approximately. 22.30 - 01.00 and then disappear.

I am a hobby astronomer and regularly look out the bathroom window to observe the night sky as I smoke a cigarette. The phenomenon was clearly moving too slowly to be an airplane, and no navigation lights like those of an airplane, helicopter, or other aircraft were visible. It was not an emergency flare. Although some flares could be slightly similar in color, the phenomenon moved too fast and too horizontally, and too controlled. The phenomenon had approx. the size of the outermost joint of the thumb when the arm is extended. The distance from the observation point was between two and three kilometers, and the height above the ground lower than the lowest flying passenger planes in the area. If it was an object, it must have been considerably larger than a large airliner. The phenomenon moved slowly, horizontally, stopped for a few seconds, where it stood still, (did not get smaller, i.e. did not give the impression that it was standing still, because it was moving away from the observer), then continued on the same course, stood still again , after which it suddenly became invisible. I sail and am very aware of what flares look like. I am a hobby astronomer and know the difference between Mars, Venus and what I saw. I am a psychologist and have sufficient knowledge of cognitive processes to have misinterpreted planes, emergency flares, Venus, or "Swampgas".

Saw an anomalous shape hovering in the air - hard to judge the distance, but will shoot at 500 - 1000 meters. It was about 1 cm wide at arm's length. The object changed shape: From a kind of deformed square (diamond-like) to a more oval (vertical) egg shape. This transformation happened several times. But so quickly and with great precision, an explanation of a loose pressing or similar swirling around seemed lacking given the way the shape changed. Because when it had this ruder shape, it was very insistent without transformation, and the way it changed shape was not characterized by spinning around itself. It sort of happened too quickly, and once it had assumed the more geometric pane shape, it sort of maintained the geometry without changing shape. I tried to explain to myself that it could be a weather balloon/plastic or something. eq., and that the changing shape could be different shades on the balloon, but the metamorphosis was almost too extreme. And despite the distance, it was initially very clear in terms of shape. There was also a slightly darker "dirty" area in the middle - but rather amorphous. During the observation, it "slipped" farther north/northeast, and became a bright spot. We had to put our heads back a little at the start of the observation, and at the last observation it was approx. 45 degrees above the horizon. The observation was interrupted by my children, so I could not observe its exit. Duration approx. 10 minutes. When my girlfriend managed to see it, she went home to our apartment with our son and then came back - when she came back it had turned into a spot of light further away. The father I was standing next to (our children went to nursery together) also thought it looked very strange and thought the only thing that could explain it was that it must be a piece of pressing/plastic - the way it moved.

In the summer of 2010, at midnight, I see 5 small luminous dots on the horizon, on my way home from work. I call my husband and ask him to see if he sees the same thing, which both he and a guest do. The luminous dots accumulate and become dark. They come towards me and I get out of the car to get a better look at them. As they come upon me, they have taken the shape of (can't describe it better than) a huge oil slick-like object that hovers calmly above me. I jump into the car and follow them over a stretch of 4-5 kilometers before they float over a field... happened at 8990 Fårup. Is this something you have heard of before or possibly know what is???

Sunday at 02:35 I stand outside and look up and enjoy the starry night sky, something I often do when it's clear to see shooting stars, and to my astonishment I see a faint red/orange circular disk pass across the night sky from an approx. 23 degrees NE direction towards SSW direction approx. 224 degrees. the one approx. 5 - 10 degrees crack in the sky. I thought it was a meteor at first, but it never lost its brightness as a meteor would, and a meteor cannot change direction as it travels across the sky. It was also a smidge fuzzy around the edges. index finger. If you can find out how high up it was, you can work out how big it was in circumference. I have written to Flyvertaktisk Komando and they said I should write to you. So I wanted to know if you had registered anything at this time that was not quite normal.
12 orange lights, almost in line at the height of a silent helicopter, came from the north east.

There were 9 red fireballs in the dark sky. No sound. I opened the window and tried to shout down to a cyclist who was coming on a bike, but it didn't work. didn't hear me. I was completely paralyzed. I have never experienced that before. I am a very grounded person and with a natural skepticism.

We had seen the sunset from one of the highest dunes in front of the Spinal Cord Injury Center in Hornbæk. We observed a very strong luminous point that had suddenly appeared far out on the horizon, immediately thought it was a star/planet, but subsequently had to ascertain that it was moving rather quickly to the east (land/us). The light decreased in strength the closer it got, thought it must be a plane, but the speed was much higher than you normally see a plane flying over you for 11 km. height. It was now almost above our heads, it was without light, which surprised us, because it had had the sun on its "back", so it was obviously not the sun that had caused it to shine.!! As it passed over us, it was completely WITHOUT any sound. We saw to our great surprise that it was a sort of cigar-shaped silver-gray body, but what was most strange was that it had 2 large, completely red "funnels" sitting on either side of the FRONT 1/4 of the the body, and they FACED FORWARD IN THE DIRECTION OF FLIGHT!!! (the "funnels" turned so that the large opening turned in the direction of flight, and we have no doubt about the color). Our best bet is definitely a satellite, due to the speed and the lack of sound and then of course the strange shape.
I was about to let the dog in when I saw an object in the sky, incompatible with a plane, it had no lights and the shape was unusual and silent. I have taken a photo

My 9-year-old grandson and I were driving from Slagelse town in the direction of Slots Bjergby/Vemmelev when we discovered a flying object that behaved strangely. It was far from us, but we could see that there were several different lights, not like an airplane. The lights didn't sit the same way either. The object could fly sideways and stay still in the air. When we got to my grandson's home, the object seemed to be standing still in the air, but occasionally it would jump to the side. We picked up my daughter and a pair of binoculars. When we looked through the binoculars, it was clear that a lot of different colors flashed around the object, just as a sharp white light formed a clear outline of the object's shape - almost hexagonal in basic shape with something like a round tip on top - if you can describe it like this. It was fantastic to see the object in the binoculars as it appeared quite clearly in this form. I told my daughter to call my stay-at-home son and tell him so he could go out to see it. I quickly drove home myself, but had to note that the object was gone.

Driving to work, and since I approx. 300 m from my place of residence driving down a hill with forest and meadow on both sides, I see from the right a round, green ball coming quite strongly across the road at a good height and towards the left. Few seconds. after that it disappears without either falling or rising, just poof away. Never seen anything like it, no sound. From my point of view, it was approx. the size of a small football. Hope you can use this for something, am keen to know what it was.

I was sitting watching TV and suddenly I saw a bright light out of the corner of my eye. I looked towards the window and I saw a big ball of light. The size was approx. 10 times the size of a shooting star. I ran to the window immediately to get a better view. The ball of light went slowly to the left (approx. satellite speed) for approx. 3 seconds, then it sped up as it descended and disappeared at the speed of a shooting star. The color of the ball of light was yellow-white. I have never seen anything like it and I was very shocked/surprised. I have always liked to look at stars, satellites and have always sat up for a long time to spot a shooting star. Have seen a lot of them too. However, I have never seen anything like what I did today. Whether it was a spaceship, I don't know. I don't want to say/believe that - but I would call it an unidentified flying object.

My wife and I are sitting on the terrace. She notices a "plane" with its landing lights on, which so often flies over us when CPH runway 22 is used. However, lane 04 was used at the time in question. Soon after, more appear, and this continues for approx. 10-12 min. We estimate that 25-30 objects came. On some of them I thought that together with the strong white light there was also a red beacon light, but it was weaker, so I am unsure about that. At the start of the observation, I estimate that their course was approx. 90g, but they turned off and disappeared at a rate of approx. 120g. The light from them did not dim after changing course, as a landing light would. At first I thought it was a plane that was going to land on runway 12, which was not logical at the time. As it turned out to be such a large cluster of objects close together, landing in the CPH would not be possible at such short intervals. If they had been planes I would estimate their altitude at 4000-6000 ft. and the speed around 200 kt. It should be noted that we could not hear any sound despite the large number. We are surprised that no one else on Zealand has apparently observed the phenomenon, or that it has been able to be ascertained on surveillance radar. We listened to the midnight radio news but there was no mention of it and we haven't heard anything since. Yesterday, 4/6 approx. at At 00.05 and 00.10 I observed two similar ones, albeit more distant in the north-west direction. Coming from the N and turning towards the SSW.

Doubt what I have seen. The observation, in all its simplicity, is that I saw a clear white light (dot of light) that moved at an oblique angle of approx. 30 degrees to the ground. The speed was less than I usually see from a shooting star, the light was constant, and there was no trailing motion.

4 pcs. round orange colored luminous objects that moved two by two slowly in several directions and at one point revolved around each other. Officer on duty at Aviation Tactical Command contacted at 22.15, where I got your phone number, which I called at 22.17, but there was no answer.... On the way from Silkeborg to Lemming at approx. 22.25 Cimbrer Air flew from KBH. towards Karup over the Lemming-Kjellerup area, perhaps they have also observed something. It was frosty and starry...... There might have been a mirage in ice crystals or what..???? It was nothing I had ever experienced before and made an impression on me. I'd like to hear more about what you find out, so I don't have to go and think about that experience for the rest of my life.
Webcam Rømø-Sylt ferry, ferry berth in List harbor looking east towards Hjerpsted/Emmerlev Klev/Højer.

Was out walking the dog when I noticed something bright. At first thought it was a star, but the wobbly movement pattern revealed that this was not the case. Next I thought it was a plane, but the up and down and side to side movement pattern didn't suggest this either. It was also not possible, despite the clear night, to see the red and green flashes that are usually on an airplane. The light pulsated and alternated between yellow and white light, at one point almost standing still and then rising for a short time, then again began to jerk sideways.

I was smoking a goodnight joint on my patio, which faces south-west, when I observed a bright orange light in the sky coming from a south-west direction. It was absolutely unlike anything I've ever seen before. About 30 seconds later another one came from the exact same direction. The first light turned at an angle of 90 degrees to the south-east, then quietly faded and disappeared, and shortly afterwards the second light did the same. Then there were 3 more who behaved in exactly the same way. The first 4 at intervals of 30-40 seconds, the last a few minutes after the others. It was certainly not an airplane, helicopter, shooting star, lantern, meteor, or anything else known. There was no sound and I have no idea of height or distance.

I am an angler, and was on the southern part of the coast at Asnæs after the area called the forest. I carried around an extra pole, which stood upright in my rucksack. I had to check if it was still standing as it should, and here I look vertically up in a southerly direction and at an angle of 85 degrees from me, I see a clear round ball. I have no doubt that this bullet is something I have not seen before. The weather is crystal clear and blue skies. It is held in the air for the approx. 2 min I watch it, only interrupted by the one time I threw out the blinker. To me, it had a reddish streak or streak - maybe from the sun's rays. Otherwise it was completely shiny and shiny. When I throw out again and look up, it's gone. After several attempts, I have tried to distance myself, and here it is still difficult for me to distance myself. But if, at my height of 186 cm and an outstretched arm, I bring my index finger and thumb together so that there is a distance of a small centimeter, then it is very likely the size as I saw it. After half an hour, I narrated the episode to my 3 fishing buddies, who could only be there as oral witnesses.

I was out to see the horses on 16/2-10 at 11:20 p.m. and stood straight and had a nap. I noticed that there were 8 stars in the Chariot, which surprised me quite a bit, there are usually only 7 stars. The extra star was between the 2 stars that form the bottom of the cart. After approx. 8 - 10 minutes, the extra star started to flutter around, but all the time right around the Chariot and not in any fixed pattern, and it happened in small jerks, there were small pauses of approx. 12 sec. between each jerk. After approx. In 11 minutes, it wandered back to the starting point in the carriage bottom of the Chariot. This time it was only there for a short time, approx. 1 - 2 minutes, after which it disappeared at very high speed in a north-westerly direction. It shone like another star, though much clearer and brighter than the North Star. There was nothing with any color changes that you see in airplanes, just a very bright white light. When it disappeared it was almost like seeing a shooting star, here there was only a very small tail.

Sitting watching TV when our eldest son discovers it in the sky. At first we thought it was a plane, but the color it had and the speed, it couldn't possibly be a plane. Large ball that was red/orange that flew at the same speed across the sky.

I came walking on my way home from gymnastics. I look up as there was something that lit up a little dimly. At first I thought it was a meteor, but it was too slow and it flashed. It was too small and too close to be a plane. It was bluish, can't describe the color ultraviolet, but still too bright, and then it flashed with some white flashes and with a white glow behind, as if it was giving momentum. Then it disappeared across the church. I wanted to run after it, but it disappeared right after. Since then, I haven't thought about it until all kinds of programs came out with UFOs and recommended this site if you have seen something. I don't remember much as it was a year ago and I was only 13 and didn't care about UFOs, but now I thought I had to get rid of it.
The UFO moved like an airplane with red lights, at an even level. There was also a bit of an orange color to the light. It might have been a hot air balloon or something similar.
I saw a completely stationary flying object that looked like a large goblet/mercury hovering to the right of the tower of Vfrue Kirke in Aarhus. I stood on my balcony in Gl. Munkegade and so on.

My father was out on my balcony facing the yard to take a breath of fresh air through a cigarette when he calls me out to look at a rather strange light that he doesn't think looks like a normal approach light on one of the many planes from Kastrup airport. It is a very bright light similar to an approach light, but more reddish and vibrant. The light came directly towards us from Kastruplufthavn in a north/east direction and was observed for a few minutes from a 40° to 80° angle, where the brightness was the same. As the light was passing over us, around the 80° angle, the brightness changed and became fainter but more concentrated reddish and a few seconds after, 85-9° angle, went out completely. And suddenly we could see a very dark outline of a classic disc-shaped shadow step forward and calmly glide over us. We followed it for 3-5 seconds before it disappeared over the building and rushed through the apartment, but all lights were turned off to see if it was visible from the other side. Despite road lighting, it was successful. And it could be followed as a dark faintly quivering blob, which after half a minute to a full minute, disappeared completely out of sight along Peblinge Søen. It was completely round and, from our perspective, about the size of 2 crowns, seen from the second floor at a 90° degree angle. It had no obvious lights to see anymore, but it still looked faintly glowing or shimmering. The speed appeared to be constant, estimated at 150-250 km/h, depending on the altitude, which is estimated to be between 1-3 km. up.

Within 15 min. came approx. 20 "flying machines", at a height of approx. 3-400 meters. They came in a very scattered formation that could be seen approx. 8-9 pieces at the same time. There was no sound and all that could be seen was the red light. Passed the moon and disappeared.
Saw 2 white lights very close to danger across the hilm back and forth. Then it was gone and then came again. It is also seen in Karise strangely.

properties.Remarks: se beretningprojektørlys om talt i BT
properties.content: I walked from Amager st. Subway around 22 d. 07-03-17. It was there that I spotted 4 white lights in the sky that didn't seem to be coming anywhere from the ground. The four white, pale, round lights appeared far apart and then raced across the sky with far more speed than an elm. plane and then gathered in a clump of light in the middle and then went off in different directions again after a few seconds. Later they appeared once more and repeated the pattern, much further away from where it happened before, leading me to rule out the possibility that it was a light source on the ground (there were no cones of light either). Then the lights began to "chase" each other across the sky and then disappear. I think for a long time to come up with a logical solution, but still can't see where it would come from. Read another observation from approx. same time which was very similar to mine. Very spry.

I was out for an evening walk and noticed an apparently very slow moving plane out near the horizon. I could see it as two white lights with an occasional red flash in the middle and it made no sound. 5-6 minutes later it was closer and flying over at low altitude and it was now making the same sound as a jet so I continued to assume it was one. There was just one thing... I could now see that there were three white lights and the occasional flashing red light was in the middle. It looked exactly like a classic 'black triangle'... the only exception to the norm of these was that every time the red light flashed, the two rear white lights did the same. I am still convinced that it was a conventional jet aircraft I saw (due to the engine noise and movement), but this sighting deserves mention as it points to misidentified aircraft as a likely explanation for quite a few sightings of "black triangles".

properties.Colors: gråt objekt, der lyste op i solens lys

properties.content: I went out into the garden to take pictures with my new Pentax K01 camera. I wanted to take pictures of the moon. I took 3 pictures and in the evening I suddenly saw that there was something in the last 2 pictures. Haven't seen the UFO with my own eyes, only a photo, which I will email to Ole Henningsen. See also my film on YouTube UFO 309.

At 12:57 AM on 5/5-16 I saw a bright flash of light fly toward the ground at high speed from my south facing garden door. (55°38'22" N 12°16'29" E) Don't know if you are the one to report something like this to.

The night of Monday, a midsummer night. Lay awake, looked out the window at approx. 2.30 time. Observed a mysterious light, stationary, above Roskildevej in Brøndby. I'm surprised that (the plane) didn't blink or move, thought it was probably going away from me or right towards it. Nothing happened. I got out of my bed, opened the balcony door, looked closer and listened. No sound. It is difficult to estimate how far away it is when you do not know how big the object is. I stand and watch it approx. 5 minutes Laying back in my bed and still looking at the mysterious light approx. a few min. Plus, the light disappears at a very high speed for me to see to the east with an increase of approx. 15 gr. It had no trail of fire, but moved from zero to a volsom speed of 1.? SEC. It disappeared behind a high-rise building about the fifteenth floor as seen from my bed. A stretch of approx. 1 m. Falling asleep and actually forget the episode, but Wednesday morning, read the Jyllandsposten before I had to go to work. Saw in a smaller article that in Frederikshavn and Skagen, on the night of Monday, a mysterious light was observed disappearing at great speed in a south-easterly direction. I thought immediately, it was exactly the same thing I saw. Have since thought that there are some really good fix points if there is someone who wants to calculate the speed and not least the direction of its possible target.
Oblong vessel, silver no condensation, flash or sound. From west to east high speed. Checked flight schedules24 no flights nearby. Seemed too big and clear to honor satellite. Clear sunshine.

Had with my wife on Sunday 04/04 2011 at 21.45 saw a very strong orange burning light in the sky. It was so sharp that it formed a cross. I was actually sure it was a meteor I had seen that day, also because it looked like it was speeding up, so I reported it to ildkugle.dk. Monday 05/04 2011 At 21.30 we had a visit from our neighbour, who stood on the terrace and called me, I should hurry up and get out there. Then I saw the exact same light again, just a little dimmer in light and slower than the day before. Couldn't see where it went because it came so low that I couldn't see it for a long time because of the neighboring houses. Then I borrowed an old video camera, but unfortunately it was very cloudy for the next several days. So I waited until 14/04/2011 at 21.00 and stood ready with the camera and then got a profit, but unfortunately it shone much weaker and was much slower, so my wife and I talked about whether it could be a plane we had seen, also because that evening it was heading towards Viborg Airport, but we agreed that what we had seen the first few days was not a plane.
Bright star-like object, but very, very close compared to stars. Very strong light. Stands still for now. At 20.19.

Must approx. 21.10 wash dishes. 5-7 degrees above the horizon in a south-westerly direction, I see 2 luminous balls, as they hang over the Jyske dragoons Regiment's training ground, I think they are "flares", however I have never seen flares in that color (I myself have been in the defense for 2 years ) the balls first fall towards the ground, but then begin to rise towards the sky. I therefore estimate that it must have been 2 helicopters, but I have never seen helicopters with such powerful searchlights. The spheres rise higher in a northerly direction, but approx. 20 degrees above the horizon, the balls fly in different directions. One ball flies in a 248 degree west direction as it drops in height, then disappears behind a building. The second ball continues to rise in a northerly direction, and approx. 40-45 degrees above the horizon, the light goes out, but I can still sense the black ball, which continues to rise in a northerly direction, approx. 55-60, the sphere stands still, after which I lose sight of it in a 278 degree west direction. The time here is approx. 9.30 p.m. I am a rational thinking person and I do not believe in flying saucers and aliens visiting us, but what I experienced on Thursday night I cannot explain. There are quite a few helicopters flying around over Holstebro (medical helicopters, military helicopters), but I have never seen helicopters move like these two UFOs did, and I have never seen a helicopter fly so high into the sky. If you have any other information or know what I saw that night, please write back to me. I also managed to take a picture of the glowing balls with my Ipad, but the picture quality is very poor (of course).

I'm out walking the dogs. When I casually look towards Rudkøbing, I see a strong whitish-yellow light. In a split second it turns red and in a split second it was gone. Many years ago I saw something similar, but many more lights, where I recorded it on a mobile phone. Since the camera was bad, it was only some bright colors on the screen.

My girlfriend and I are watching TV, we zap between TV2 (World Cup summary) and a broadcast on Investigation Discovery. At is here 22.23. I then see a clearly luminous "ball" out of the window, moving from west to east. I see this glowing dot or ball between the blinds, and fly off the couch and pull the blinds apart. I observe the light moving east for approx. 2-3 seconds before I call my girlfriend so she can see it too. We observe it together in the window for approx. 7-8 seconds until a tree blocks the view of the light. We literally both jump over the couch and open our patio door and run out to look. I start my phone camera and film the object for 8 seconds until it disappears over a building. The object disappears due east. While I'm standing there filming, my girlfriend has run along the building where it disappears, and she thinks the object is rapidly increasing in speed and disappearing. The object appeared to have a pulsating distinct white/yellow light. A very strong light I thought. It wasn't really dark outside yet, and the sky was pretty much completely overcast. The object was VERY clear! Possibly because there were no other luminous objects to be seen in the sky such as stars and the moon. That was probably why I discovered the light through the blinds to begin with. I want to shoot the object and fly low. I think this is because the clouds were low. I would suggest that the object has been approx. 500 meters up in the air. The object generated no sound at all... at least nothing we could hear. My girlfriend is absolutely convinced that it was NOT a plane, and she was slightly shaken and elated by the experience. She was very surprised that it made no sound at all when it flew as low as it did. We could not see any form of the object, although it was flying low. It just looked like a shiny ball of some sort. It was certainly not flying slowly, but I dare not guess at the speed at which the object was moving. During the entire observation, the object appeared to maintain the same speed. It is only my girlfriend who saw (or seemed to see) that the object speeded up tremendously until finally disappearing. One thing is certain in my mind, and that is that if the object had kept the same speed the whole time, then the object should be visible when my boyfriend and I come around the parking lot. The time we spent running in and putting on shoes and grabbing a shirt on the dining table next to the patio door did not exceed 17-20 seconds (we timed it with a stopwatch during a subsequent reconstruction). The person we meet out on the road seems very much influenced by his own experience of the object. I don't know exactly how he experienced it, but he was very much affected by it anyway. I have NEVER seen an unidentified flying object before, neither has my boyfriend. But we both think it was unlike anything we had seen before.

It looks like 12-15 stars that stand together but change position. Either they stand together as if within a circle - or together in the shape of a cigar. In between, light radiates from it, alternating between 1 beam and 6-7 beams, which are always directed downwards. Before, it was like a big searchlight that was aimed directly at where we stand.

Come running. So strong, round red light that was orange in the middle. Got out of the car. It was starry and windless, but it moved quickly like a low-flying plane. There was no sound as I sail a lot, I saw no navigation light when it changed direction. Knows emergency rockets. The wife wanted to take a picture on her phone. It was ready, said click, but no picture. Strange.

My boyfriend and I had a long and serious talk at home. We live in an apartment on Amager with a good view of the city. The bed is next to a window, and we had not drawn for it. We lay and talked while just staring out the window. Suddenly a very bright object appeared in the sky.

I'm standing at the 1st floor window when I spot a bright flashing light that I first assumed was an airplane. But something was wrong. The light guide did not fit. The object emitted a very strong white flash followed by a somewhat weaker one. After that again a strong. That's how it went on. There was also a red and a blue-green light - not particularly strong in the direction of flight. The speed of the object was faster than an airliner, but significantly slower than a fighter. Suddenly it changed course and was now flying due north. I estimate its flight height to be approx. 4-5000 m. I opened the window to listen for engine noise, but there was not a sound. Meanwhile, the object disappeared from my field of vision. Due to haze, I could not see any contours. Only the lighting effects mentioned above. If anyone else has seen something similar, I'd love to hear about it.
I was at the model airfield at FL Schmidtsvej with my son today.

Sees something bright up in the sky. Cloudless. Very little wind. Approx. 20 degrees C. Grabs my binoculars and studies it. Certainly not a plane, helicopter, hot air balloon or drone. Maybe 5-7 bright points in the phenomenon. As in a circle with a line down towards the ground below it. Presumably blown with the wind? Must have been a weather balloon made of gold-colored material that reflected the sun's rays?

We see a white figure in the sky. My son calls and says it looks like an airplane on a leash as it is on a fixed route and looks like something that is circling. I look out and see something that looks like a shooting star, but I can tell it's not, since it's the same place, it appears every time. Then I say, it's a guy, but we don't have one that close. I then stand and focus at the same time as I try to find out what it could be. I have no answer.

Unfortunately, I can't remember the exact date of the observation, but it was at the end of December 12. I was eating some food with my friend, then we see a kind of fireball come flying down diagonally over the rooftops. We can see the flying thing for approx. 20 seconds before it disappears again. I have 3 photos taken with my phone that I am sending.

Followed my son and friend to the Halloween party at Vesterbro ungdomsgård. We look up at the sky and see what we think is a satellite. However, it was then that I see a reddish dot of light in the sky close to the "satellite's" orbit. The red spot of light accelerates to the east, and for a moment I think it's a shooting star. But then it changes direction at high speed - almost in a zig-zag, it quickly disappears from view due to the apartment building. It kind of looked like a cigarette glow in the dark, which is the best comparison I can give. My son and his friend didn't see it as they didn't look up for more than a few seconds.

Lay on the couch in our living room. Looked out of our terrace window (we live on the 2nd floor) and saw a star that twinkled strongly. And changed color. Kept looking at it. I lay still. And using the door frame of the patio door, I could see how it moved. Come closer. Fly zig-zag. Became stronger in color. Fly further away. Come closer. Repeatedly. At almost 3 now and it's still there. Woke up my husband and he can see it too. Have called my mother. She lives 4 km from here. And can also see it. It has really been big and close down. At eye size half a cm approx. Maybe a little bigger. If I look at a star, it is in my eye measure one mm. Approx.. if you are in Herning, it is beyond Lind.

Three white lights in a clear triangle that moved very quickly and silently apparently low under the clouds. The movement was a clear elongated trajectory, which is why light thrown up from the ground does not appear sensible. Came from within the land and moved towards the sea.

Through the roof window of my telehandler I happened to see what I first thought was a shooting star, but it was very different and much longer than usual. When I noticed it, it was like there were 3-4 flashes/explosions after just this fireball speeding across the sky. I didn't think it was quite normal, it was against But and lasted far too long for a shooting star and far too powerful to be a satellite? But then what was it? A rocket or?? Hope you can help

Two dots appear in the night sky. My friend suddenly sees them... I also look up and see two bright yellowish rather obvious dots, and I think that it can't possibly be a plane. Wondering a lot what else it could be... It all happened quite quickly, suddenly the dots split and one disappears from sight by flying upwards until it disappeared completely. We follow the other with our eyes. It's coming down the slope of... I thought it could only be a UFO. The object disappears out of sight quickly and silently as the rooftops were in the way...

Of course it was a long time ago, but I remember it very clearly. We were 2 friends aged 14-15, and we were on our way home from riding school. We had recently seen quite a few unexplained lights in the sky. Looked a bit like the light of an aviator, but flew too erratically for it to be an aviator. From the looks of it, it could also just be a star, if it wasn't for the fact that it was moving. Sometimes there were more. And suddenly the light went down again.. From top to bottom.. And it was gone. There was nothing that rose into the air.. It just disappeared. It couldn't be car lights.. Not the way the light went down. It was only maybe a year or a year and a half that we saw those lights. And now it has been passed on.

An object comes flying across the clear night sky, the time is approx. 2:30. It comes from the north/west, at first very fast, like a shooting star, but it is much bigger, bigger than any shooting star, approx. 1/10th of the sun. Then the object's speed begins to decrease. The object is now to the west, but stands completely still. I think about whether it is a plane that has caught fire and when it will crash. Suddenly, the object begins to fly west, but the altitude increases. It continues until I can't see it anymore. When the object was still, it really looked like a huge fire / sun in the sky to the west. It is therefore much larger than anything else I have seen. As the object disappears on the horizon to the west, it is as if the height is increasing and increasing, so not as an airplane would do!!

My wife and I were looking for shooting stars a little before 01:00. We both spotted a hazy luminous object coming "calmly" from an eastern direction and in a straight line to the northwest until it disappeared behind Selskov (due north from where we were). I retrieved a pair of binoculars but only caught a brief glimpse before it disappeared behind the woods. The object was blurry/foggy. When it disappeared the tree branches could be clearly seen in silhouette.

I had had visitors in the evening, ate good food and drank wine, but was definitely not drunk!! When my guest had gone, about midnight, I cleaned up a little, and then stood up on the windowsill, and with my head stuck out of the upper window, looked up at the night sky. It was something I often did back then before going to bed. The night was not completely clear, there was a slight haze in the sky when you looked up. However, I could easily see the brighter star. Suddenly I saw two orange/reddish lights come flying across the sky, in a straight line from approx. east towards approx. west. I looked at them for a split second before it dawned on me that there was something very strange about these lights. Strange because the lights moved in semi-circles, as if they were on opposite ends of a long pole, which was then constantly tilted back and forth from the center, 180 degrees clockwise and then 180 degrees counter-clockwise. This means that the lights were almost directly opposite each other, and their movements described a reasonably large circle. This unison motion alternating clockwise and counterclockwise didn't seem particularly fast in frequency.... maybe twice a second. It was therefore easy to follow the movements with the eye. The lights did not flash and were similar in size to regular pilot lights. It was not possible to see any form within this circular form which the movements of the lights formed, either rod-like or plate-like. So it was not possible to see how the lights were connected, or if they were at all. The center of this invisible axis, which was as it were described by this semi-circular motion, moved in a straight line across the sky. There was no sound. It is very difficult to judge distance when looking up, but considering the weather and the fact that nothing could be seen but the lights, I would guess between 100 meters and 300 meters up. The distance between the lights is also difficult to judge, given that the distance as a whole is a bit unclear. If it was now 300 meters up, then it has been a distance between the lights corresponding to about twice as far as a jumbo jet, I want to shoot. So something reasonably large. The object (or objects) flew right over my street, almost right over my house. I rushed up to the roof (lived at the top) to see if I could see them disappearing towards the horizon, but of course they were gone. I can't say how fast they were. I could see a horizon to the east that was maybe 300 meters away (over the rooftops) and then to where I could no longer see them (as they flew over my house). It went reasonably fast, approx. five seconds from start to finish.

An object, to me an airplane with landing lights on and a red glow around it (could be navigation lights), is coming towards me, but several kilometers out. The height of the object is hard to guess, but I would imagine 5000-10000 feet. I just stood there and wanted to watch as it flew over me, but the object slowed down more and more and then stopped before it passed. After a minute or less it started moving again, but now to the south. Now only the red light was visible, and after perhaps a minute, the object became smaller and smaller and finally disappeared. Have thought about possible causes like satellite or aircraft but just never seen a satellite be so big and clear and change direction. You would also be able to hear a plane, since it was completely silent otherwise. Could be cool with a good explanation.

2 hours ago at 21.00 on 30-7-2017 I look out of my window and see a light in the sky. I would have thought it was a star, but when I was about to look away, I noticed that it was moving to the side. Subsequently, I had to observe more closely, as a star does not normally move to the side without leaving the "picture" as e.g. a shooting star. After a short time it instead moved from the side, as well as up, as well as diagonally, and everything happened in a split second, as if it was looking for something or "someone". It still hangs in the sky here at 00:00 midnight, but somewhere else 30 degrees northeast, and does the same there,

At 4 o'clock I looked up at the starry sky a little west of north. The constellation I saw was different than usual, so I stared at it. 3 stars, slightly fainter than the others, stood out and moved with mad speed to the west - max. 4-5 seconds - and they were gone. There was a great distance between the 3 lights, but they followed each other in a flat triangle, so I got the feeling of a flat object. Curious if others have seen the same.
A silent pale yellow light/object came gliding from the south where it turned to the east. In binoculars, a kind of corona can be seen on the right side of the light. It was the size of a planet.

It's been quite a long time, it was when I was approx. 17 years, but I can't stop thinking about it all the time. It happened in the winter of 1980, when I was living at home with my parents. I was sitting in my room listening to music when two girls I knew came into my room. They were all driving and yelling at each other saying that they had just seen a UFO land in a field right next to my parents house when they were on their way to me. I told them to calm down and tell me quietly. They said they were on their way back to me and saw some lights of many different colors that twisted around each other like a light show in the field near the road they were driving on. They got very scared and they peaked their puck maxi popped to see what kind of strange light it was. Just then, the light stopped shining, and then there was a large white ufo with windows. They could see there were some people behind the windows. It stood for a few seconds. and hummed a little, and then it flew up into the air and turned to the north. It went very fast approx. two seconds, then it was gone. I've always wanted to say that, even though I haven't seen it myself, it sounds real enough.
See video 3 here: After 10 minutes of recording, it was possible to observe 1 object.

Sitting on the terrace with my adult daughter when the object is suddenly in the sky. It flies a little forward and a little back a few times. We get up and think at first that it might be some kind of cone of light, but suddenly it flies over our terrace in a northerly direction. It is completely silent and feels like it is quite far down. It is luminous and the size of a hot air balloon.

A late summer evening approx. 30 years ago we, 3 people, fished at Langesø just outside Ringsted. It was starting to get dark, well called twilight. Suddenly we all see a completely silent object in the air, round or perhaps cigar-shaped. As the crow flies, probably 500 - 1000 m from us. It stands completely still and changes color several times. We are aimless. The object can be observed for perhaps 1-2 minutes, after which it suddenly disappears to the west at a very high speed and completely silently. We have never been able to explain the phenomenon ourselves, and even here 30 years later we still talk about the experience. However, we agree that it was something "not earthly" that we saw. For the record, it must be said that the story is 100% true, but at the same time it is the only UFO experience we have had. But we still wonder. But it is certain that it was NOT about planes/helicopters, kites or hot air balloons etc.

An orange colored object is seen to the east moving from north to south. Angle for the track approx. 60 degrees. The object moves at a uniform speed horizontally across the sky. From the time we see it and for approx. 6 sec. it is seen as a clearly luminous, orange-coloured object, slightly elongated in shape across the direction of movement, a bit like a bird/plane. Size is most easily described by a comparison with a buzzard at a distance of 100 - 150 m. Diminishes gradually as it fades to the south and disappears like a slowly fading (extinguishing) star. There is no sound. Observers agree on a description of a satellite debris/low-responsibility shooting star, but wonder about the completely straight trajectory, why our perception is a very large object seen at a great distance, even though we perceived proximity. 3 minutes later (at 11:28 p.m.) a very large (2 - 3 x Jupiter) white light is seen moving from southwest to northeast for about 7 seconds. - quickly becomes smaller to an ordinary satellite size, which can then be followed for another 15 - 20 seconds, now also with binoculars, which do not change the size. This observation only seems strange because of the very large size at the start (could be an unusually strong reflection from a satellite) - and is taken into account in relation to the above completely different, for us, inexplicable observation.

I went for a walk in the garden to get some fresh air, whereupon I lay down to look at the sky. While I'm lying and looking closely at a star, I see some kind of light turn on next to the star. It then flies past the star as its brightness dims. It flies on until it disappears. Have no data from the sighting other than rushing in to write it down as I am deeply fascinated by space.

I was lying in my bed on the first floor of our house watching a movie with the lights off when I heard what I thought at first was a plane. I quickly became aware that the sound was not normal as I could hear it getting closer and closer (sounded like a weird constant hum). Suddenly there was a bright light outside that lit up the room through my slanted window and I jumped out of bed and tore open the window. A large flat triangle with a white light/lamp under each corner and some smaller flashing red lights hovered at a very leisurely pace almost directly above me for what must have been approx. 100-200 meters high. As it slowly disappeared I climbed onto the roof to catch one last glimpse of it before it disappeared behind the roofs of the other residents' houses. The "plane/ship" was not quite triangular, but more precisely a slightly elongated triangle, three of whose edges had been cut off. The observer's drawing of what was seen.

We were on our way from Sindal to Hjørring, when at the roundabout we can see a huge orange oval-like ball hanging just above the roundabout. At first I thought it was a plane that had been set on fire in some way, then contacted the emergency center, who of course could do nothing until we knew what it was. There was no sound about it at all, and all of a sudden it began to move quietly, and later became smaller and smaller, until at last it disappeared. It looked most like a burning object, but completely without sound. My boyfriend and I watched it from our car, but we noticed a few people who had gotten out of their cars to watch it.

I have previously reported about me and my family's experience at our summer house, which we still have in Udbyhøj Syd, on 03.11.78.. It has become a little unclear to me whether it was 03. or 07.. Yes, even the year 77 or 78, embarrassing, but otherwise I've always been able to remember it. Can ask my sister, but the correct information is in my report from that time. My sister's husband goes outside to empty a trash can. It is starry, completely windless, at is maybe 19?. Then Jan comes in and says: Come out and see, there is something strange in the sky. My sister and I and their two children look up in the sky - yes, there are three, green, red, white, pulsating round balls, three of them, like connected together, one at the top, two at the bottom, like a triangle. And it is an object that looks like this, the other two in the same way. They are quite a way up in the air above - or in the direction of Koglevej and Krammesvej, where we usually go for a walk, and it is probably three hundred meters away, but the objects may well have been further away. It's hard to tell, but they were totally clear up there in the air. Well, but they kind of move up and down, a bit slanted, and in straight lines. A long movement can be described as "a shooting star" in speed?, where the UFO from point a shoots off at lightning speed, where it has stopped abruptly - in such an almost straight line. Eg. close to one of the other UFOs. A little later they move a little to the left. They are in these clear colours, pulsating, just as the colors flow together. They now change in shape, and we see a totally beautiful and bright orange, yes, like an airship in shape, bright as the light of the sun. We take turns looking with the binoculars, but see nothing but what we see from the ground, it's just closer with the binoculars of course. But now there are four? much smaller UFOs away, i.e. transformed into the large luminous object. A short time later, it sets off and moves steadily towards - yes, north-west. It starts on one - as if it immediately had max. velocity. It struck me even then that it moved so immediately. Well, we went for a walk down towards the harbor later that evening. The man who steered the Udbyhøj ferry must also have seen it. It was written in Randers Amtsavis that two sea hunters had seen an orange object, and we knew that it must be the same one we saw, so we thought it was interesting. I am writing about it because others must have seen it and if the same colors and shapes could have been seen elsewhere. I'll probably never get an answer to anything, but it's as true as the amen in church. There were no sounds from the UFOs, I must remember to mention. Think how incomprehensible our life is, and scary too I think, it is not something created by humans, what we saw, it is a hundred...
Three white lights, stationary above the clouds, and shining through. Disappears pulsating, without direction.

We are sitting on the couch and suddenly observe a flying, luminous thing outside our window. We immediately go to the window and see this object very clearly and close to us (500 meters from us and at a height of 45 meters). It moves quite slowly and holds still for a while before moving easily. We open the window and look through binoculars at this object. We're talking about, it's a drone with a light on it, but the light is orange/red and they don't have that. We are considering whether it is a glowing lamp (china lamp), but this can stand completely still and then move again. We look through binoculars and see that it has at least 3 lights in a row, but we can't see what it is. Then it starts moving calmly towards Sweden, and after a few seconds it picks up speed and disappears straight towards Sweden at a very high speed. It is a very clear evening, no clouds and a full moon that gives us a good clear view. We are hyper-aware that we have seen a UFO - and regret that we did not take a photo or a video.

Part 1, Preben's part of the story. Around. At 01:15 on 28 May 2001, my friend Alex and I came driving a large van along Juelsmindevej towards Vejle, a few kilometers from the large transport centre.
