I see a faintly glowing oval object hanging far out on the horizon. I'll wait a bit to mention it to see if Alex notices. Shortly after, Alex sees it, and we then agree to pull over to the side and take a closer look at the phenomenon. Then we turn off the engine and all the lights in the car, after which we open the door and hear a faint hum in the distance - within 8-9 seconds the oval object has come close to us, in fact so close that it fills more than half of the windshield through which we look. We sit completely still in the car and don't know what to say or do when a completely white, powerful light "turns on" on the left side of the object, after which the light is almost raised above it and slanted to the left. The object now stands still in front of us and almost "shines" on us for approx. 25 sec., after which it fades out, leaving a large oval hole between the clouds, where you can look out into space, and a thin glowing green line from the hole and diagonally into space, which stands still for a few seconds, after which it fades out and disappears. Then we sit completely speechless for a quarter of an hour, after which we choose to drive on, - we then pass the transport center and shortly after Alex observes 3 completely quadratic objects on the horizon to the right. He points it out to me, and just as we're both looking at them, they almost close together one by one like a camera lens. Alex then turns his head to the left and discovers a completely quadratic object more near the water tower, - when I look at it too, it closes and disappears in the same way as the other three. After getting really curious, we decide to drive up to the top of a nearby hill and take a closer look at the horizon. When we reach the top and look out to the right, we observe two completely quadratic objects again, we look at them for 5-6 seconds, after which they close together like the other three. We stay as a team on the hill for 10 minutes, observe no more, after which we choose to go home with an experience a little out of the ordinary.
Totally looked like a plane engulfed in flames. Humming sound, speed and altitude indicated aircraft, but then flickering orange color, almost like flames.

Just drove on the motorway at the Tappernøje approach and on my way to my work in Copenhagen. It is a little after 8 o'clock, the weather is fine approx. 20 degrees and with scattered clouds. By chance, on the left of the windshield, quite far away, I spot a shiny object. Immediately I think it looks like an airplane. And think no more and that until I look out of my side window. The object has not moved much, perhaps a little to the north. Now very sure that it is not a plane anyway. Even if I'm driving on the highway, I try to slow down, but it's hard to keep the observation. It is therefore quite difficult to judge the distance (perhaps 3-4 km away) and see further details. Just that the object is shiny and oval/oblong. Something I've never seen before. There is probably a good explanation behind this object, but which one. It might be interesting to hear if others on the motorway this morning have seen anything similar.

We stop on Lindholmvej, where a girl we are to pick up asks if we have seen the shooting stars there. I get out of the car and we all spot a big orange/red light to the south.. It's coming straight at us. But unlike shooting stars, which are seen very small, fast and high in the sky, the light here was large, constant, without a "tail" and with a constant speed. On top of that, it seemed like it was flying at helicopter height, so quite close, but completely silent. We all got a little puffed up because it was such a sour experience.. It wasn't a shooting star.. Neither was anyone flying. The object was round, constantly glowing at high speed. But completely silent. Managed to shoot a short video with it. The witnesses were 3 children and one more adult.

I want to start by saying that I have seen quite a bit in the last six months. In total I have seen 6 unexplainable things. But now I will write to you, because the last thing I saw here last Friday was the wildest of them all. And all my sightings I have seen with one or more witnesses. I have been interested in the sky for a long time and wondered, like a lot of others, if there really was something out there and if it could be that we were alone in the universe. And I've read and watched a lot of documentaries over the past year. And also have a lot of questions for you. But to get back to what I saw last Friday. We sat out all evening. I have a friend who is just as into it as I am. He saw something the day before which was a glowing orb on a rainy day.,The sky was completely overcast and it was pulsating white and yellow/orange. And they have a balcony with a reasonably good view. So he called and told about his sighting the day before we were to go in there. But then the day after we came in in the evening. I have to say that all Friday it was cloudy and rainy. Then at 8 pm it started to clear up, and an hour later it was completely cloudless. So we sat out there looking for UFOs. And suddenly there was a light similar to what my friend had seen the day before. Exactly as he had described. 10 minutes after that another one came in the same place, and right after that two more came. So you could see three at the same time. It was crazy! They were flying low, because there was an airliner which passed the three luminous objects. At least it looked like it, but the direction can be deceiving. They came from behind one of the tall buildings in Odense. As I said, it was inside the city, and we sat by a balcony. But I haven't seen anything like it. They pulsated, and if you looked closely, you could sense that they were spinning around themselves. They were only there for a scant 20 seconds. And it was completely cloudless. They pulsated (brightly and faintly glowed). But when they shone dimly, they were still brighter than the brightest star in the sky. And then suddenly you could see that luminous contracted and disappeared out of the blue. So we were speechless. But this is the first time I am writing to you, and I would very much like to get in touch with you to hear what you have to say about it. Now I will soon buy a good camera so that I can get it on tape and show what I see when I sit and look for UFOs in the evening. I haven't seen anything about the day yet though. I almost have to tell you about another experience I also had. But that was a while ago. So can't remember when. But the time has been approx. 01.00. I live in Svendborg in a terraced house and have a reasonably large sky to look at. But that night I had to go out front with my dog so he could pee before we went to bed. Then I look up and there was a great light which was much brighter and much bigger than a star. It stood completely still. And I ran in and got my girlfriend and her sister. Just as we got out, it set into motion and flew over our house. Not directly across, but like that, so we had to run in through and then out into the garden on the other side. It picked up speed more and more. It pulsated the colors red, yellow, green and blue/purple. So yeah... I'm very interested in what you guys have to say about that.

Observed the object from my yard after loading firewood on the stove in the barn building. Went inside and briefed my wife and daughter on the sighting, which we subsequently observed further from our west-facing garden room as well as outdoors from our west-facing backyard. After approx. five minutes we sat down to eat, but the object was still visible in the direction of approx. SW 50 degrees in the sky. It was a very clear night with a full moon.

We are driving on the motorway near Fredericia when we first see a light in the sky. We think to begin with that it might be a large searchlight that runs across the sky, as the movement is the same way. But we continue to be able to see the light crossing the sky both from side to side and back and forth over the car. At Kolding we switch over to the Esbjerg motorway, and I think that the light will probably continue with the motorway south, but no it turns towards Esbjerg. However, it is as if we have come a little in front of the light, but my daughter, who is almost 12, can still follow it out of the side window. We drive off at Lunderskov and keep on the viaduct over the motorway and see the light zig zag across the motorway. The light continued towards Esbjerg. Was it a police helicopter with a searchlight?

I was on my way home from work that night. I cycled down Vejlevej, and when I got to the lower part of Vejlevej, before it turns into Ringvejen, I saw a bright light in the sky over the city. At first I thought it was the moon, but when there was a bright star-like light at the bottom, I realized it was not the moon. The powerful light looked like a very strong searchlight. I got off the bike and looked at the light. It had a flat oval shape and at the bottom was this bright light. The oval shape was completely illuminated, almost like a giant light bulb. I stood and watched it for a few minutes, also looking around at the rest of the sky to see if I could find the moon. However, it was apparently cloudy, at least I couldn't see any stars or any moon. The big glowing thing was totally silent. I continued cycling along the Ring Road up to the junction at Tøndervej/Skydebanen. As I cycled I looked at the light. When I got off again at this traffic light, I could see that it had gotten smaller. Either it must have moved, or it must have been quite close when I first saw it, because I cycled about ½ km. from between the two places I got off the bike. I then cycled further up Bjælderbæk by the shooting range, from there I could no longer see it. I think there must be others who have also seen something, since there are a lot of people in town on Friday nights.

Searchlights can be seen at up to quite large distances (up to approx. 60 km) and often no cone of light is visible from the ground up into the sky. When the light hits the clouds, a "spot of light" is seen on the underside of the clouds. Usually 1 to 3 spots of light are seen, which rotate and (if there are more) alternately gather and spread - however, you must be aware that there are many types of projector and laser light. The phenomenon's gradual disappearance can be explained by clearing and/or increasing haze and fog.

We are coming by car from Ringsted towards Køge, when we see an orange light in the sky, moving very slowly to the west for approx. 1 min, "stops" in the sky, then goes at a sharp angle to the east, then flies silently at first very slowly to the east. After a small minute acc. the object then pretty quickly and disappears into the sky. Would love to hear from you.

It had become dark, partly cloudy. From my bedroom window I constantly see many planes, as Copenhagen airport in Kastrup is not very far away (by plane). At the same time as two planes pass at different altitudes and in separate directions, I see a faint white light, which is significantly weaker than that which the planes are carrying. There are no flashing lights, like on airplanes. Only this dim white, which at some point I doubt, may be two dim lights. The light moves at roughly the same speed as the planes, but differs drastically in performing maneuvers that I certainly can't imagine any plane being capable of. First a small vertical dive, then direction directly opposite to the original, another vertical dive, and again the original direction, steep ascent, again opposite direction, steep vertical dive, and again opposite direction. After that, the light can no longer be seen. Whether it went out or went behind a cloud, I could not determine, but it did not become visible afterwards.

Standing talking on the phone and looking out the window to the north. Sees an object passing at an incredibly high speed, but in the same trajectory as the aircraft approaching the runway, but very low in the sky. The object is dark purple and appears to be two objects in a row with a very long reddish tail. Within 3-4 seconds it passes from approx. 8 degrees north and disappears around 188 degrees south. Basically in the same trajectory as planes land, but lower in the sky.
Is very sharp in colors, stands almost still and flashes green, red, white. Is it a space station. It does not disappear.

I was standing in my kitchen pouring coffee and looking out the window and suddenly saw 2 orange round objects come flying and was suddenly gone again, but came back in the same place approx. 30 seconds later and disappeared again just as quickly. Can't explain what it is, but there was an airplane higher up than what I saw.

Seems to be the only site I can find regarding UFO activity in Denmark. Live in Amager. Last night we were sitting on the deck behind my house watching the meteor shower. 4 witnesses (3 adults and a 12 year old). We started at 10pm and at around or after 11pm (time not exact, sorry) we witnessed the following: 3 orange orbs or discs directly above my house, stationary but changing formation - as my mother pointed out it almost looked like a dance. They then moved in a triangle formation towards the direction of the city, stopped dead changed formation again and then moved off rapidly. I gauged the altitude to be under 10000 feet but really there was no reference point to back this up. We are however in the flight path for incoming flights to Kastrup. The whole incident lasted about 10 seconds. The sky was clear and visibility was excellent. I've ruled out birds, planes, sky beams etc. It or they were under intelligent control.

I look up at the clear sky and see three lights under the Chariot - see the drawing sent. They glow very brightly. Approx. somewhere between the brightness of Venus and Mars. The bottom two lights faded out and very shortly after the 3rd and top light followed. The lights were completely stationary. There was no sound. My friend saw it too, but only managed to see the last light.

I was 12 years old and with a friend in his parents' summer house during the Easter holidays. On a clear sunny day, Easter Sunday, we walked from Sandvig towards Allinge along Kongestien. My companion happened to spot a dull greyish cigar-shaped object moving silently from west to east at a steady downward 20 - 25 degree angle to the surface of the sea. The forward end of the object in the direction of flight was initially orange, in an area of varying size, until it disappeared, as if the object was overheated, glowing from drag. The size was difficult to determine, the distance to it also difficult to determine. But it seemed as if it was at a distance equivalent to more than half way to the horizon line - and if so it was very large, larger than known aircraft, perhaps several hundred meters or more long. When it was close to the surface of the sea it began a shrill, lurching motion (like a swinging plate on a stick) at varying altitudes, then zig-zag maneuvers with such speed and acceleration that no known craft could imitate . Finally the object disappeared at an insane speed heading towards the horizon and disappeared out of sight still close to the surface of the sea. We knew nothing of the concept of UFOs at the time, but when we told my friend's parents about the sighting the next day, we were made aware of their existence, as acquaintances of the parents were interested in UFOs, and sightings with attempts to photograph them. It was probably a little unusual at the time, and it was only later, when I was 14 - 15 years old, that I became interested in UFOs and read about them - prompted by a classmate. I have since read about UFO sightings - and have become aware that this sighting matches descriptions of so-called mother ships, which should have a size of 1 - 2 km in diameter - and which should be quite rare to see in daylight.

My daughter and I are out walking the dog when we suddenly see a very bright white, almost limb-like, flickering light in the sky. We could quickly see that it was not a plane. It was far too big and bright. We had a feeling it was moving closer without actually seeing it move in the sky. We jump in the car to drive around to a road, closer and parallel to the one we are on, but where there are open fields so we can see better. The trip in the car takes approx. 1 min, and when we arrive, the light is gone. There is nothing to see in the completely clear, light blue evening sky... Very mysterious for a girl with both feet firmly planted in the Jutland soil.

A quiet summer evening on the balcony. Suddenly a large glowing ball appears. It quickly appears behind some rooftops, but then slows down and glides slowly across the sky, where it suddenly takes a turn to the west. I pick up my husband who is coming out. Normally he is very skeptical about such things, but here he immediately exclaims: "What the f... is that". At the same time, another one emerges from the same place, following the same trajectory. We get binoculars and can see that it is almost a flat plate that emits a very strong light all the way around itself. In total, while we stand and watch, 5 balls emerge, all of the same size, color and following exactly the same path. It is completely silent that night, so it was very clear that they did not emit a single sound. I subsequently checked with the local fireworks factory if they had shot anything off, but no, it wasn't them. For us it was a very mysterious sight that cannot be immediately explained.

At approx. At 22.30 I had gone out into my kitchen, where there is an unobstructed view of Vor Frelser Church tower through the large window. Suddenly I first see a strong organge yellow luminous object fairly high above the top of Vor Frelser Church Tower coming into view from the north and moving in something that could resemble a helicopter speed across the sky towards the south - towards Kastrup Airport. Since we are quite used to seeing ordinary airplanes, whose landing lights are flashing, fly by and pass Vor Frelser Kirketårn here in Christianshavn, I think that it must be an airplane. It surprises me, however, that you cannot hear any engine noise as usual. A short moment later, there are suddenly exactly 3 more of the same size and at the same high speed - and considering the angle and height, they must have been quite large. 10 sec. after that comes another flock of perhaps 10 - 15 objects of exactly the same nature gliding across the sky. I grab my mobile phone and call my mother, who lives in Voldboligerne 2 by Christianshavns Vold and has a beautiful view from her apartment over the rampart and the whole of southern Amager. She rushes into the kitchen and immediately sees - exactly the same strong organ luminous objects. At the same time, even more objects have now come into view from my point of view - and they are flying so close together that they cannot possibly be aeroplanes/helicopters. I agree with my mother to call the police and therefore call 114 - and get hold of it after speaking to a switchboard lady in station Amager and then speak to the officer on duty. He sounds amazed to say the least - and begins to explain something about some Chinese paper lamps with lights in them that you have been able to buy in Copenhagen within the last 14 days. Now it just so happens that, in connection with one of my engagements a number of years ago abroad, I actually witnessed a shipment of such Chinese paper lamps with lights in them - and I can safely say that it could not possibly have been talk about here. When Chinese spirit lamps are sent up, they fly up very slowly - just like when you played with paper kites as a child in Kløvermarken - and they usually stand quite still in the sky and not very high - maybe 10 - 50 meters into the air and later go out and fall back down. This was definitely not Chinese spirit lamps - on the contrary. It was both the amount of objects, height above the horizon and not least the speed was completely wrong. There was absolutely no sound. My mother could also see them, as they all passed at intervals over the Voldbolingerne and out towards the airport, where they gradually disappeared away from her visual range. We assume that there must have been many more people in Copenhagen than us who must have seen the sight. Incidentally, I asked the officer to go outside his office and look for himself, after which he said something about wanting to call back - he hasn't done that yet. The total number of objects was probably approx. 50 in total - and they came flying either one after the other, then a short break, then another 3 - 4 pieces and then again a break of maybe 2 - 3 min, after which a whole lot appeared at the same time close to the side each other in rapid speed across the sky. If it was supposed to have been Chinese spirit lamps that moved with such speed - the same as an airplane, then there should almost have been a hurricane outside - or strong wind - and as you know, there was not, but completely calm weather and reasonable clear skies. When the large clump of strongly organge-yellow luminous objects had passed, approx. 5 - 10 min, after which 3 objects came again and then again a break of 2 - 3 min, after which a single one came. The whole thing lasted approx. ½ hour to 45 min. After which no more came. Now it's not like I run around on a daily basis and see UFOs in the sky or see apparitions etc. I can be upset that I didn't take a picture with my mobile phone camera, instead of calling the police. Even though until yesterday I did not believe in UFOs or life from outer space - and it is mostly a concept that exists in American Sci-FI, action and suspense films such as CIG visual effects - in Steven Spielberg films etc., it could be quite interesting to find out what it was - because the fact was that these many objects appeared in the sky above Copenhagen yesterday.

New Year's night/morning, a silent flying UFO came across the sky. The UFO was egg-shaped with 12 powerful lights placed at equal intervals around the UFO. Another person saw the same thing as me and wrote in Ribe Ugeavis about his observation, and the weekly newspaper confirmed that there were no planes or helicopters over Ribe at this time.

Have looked every evening/night after my first observation back in Aug. But was most interested in the many shooting stars that have been here lately. I look straight up and spot something dark/black far up, almost like glimpsing a fish down in the water, it was big and already speeding when I saw it, but right as I see it, took the extremely high speed. From when I saw it straight up until it disappeared in the horizon NW, it took less than 1 sec. It was completely surreal and I still can't get over what I saw. 2 hours later I then find out that it is lightning in that direction. Don't know if there is a connection?

I sat and smoked a cigarette out on my balcony because I'm not allowed to smoke inside. My balcony faces south and the orange static orb came from the west and flew east in a straight line across the sky. It was silent, but when it was right in front of me I could hear a very low crackling humming sound from it. I've never seen one like this before. It took 7 to 9 seconds to fly from the western horizon until it disappeared in the east.

I was out for a walk in the mall, and when I was down by my neighbour's house, I saw a flying object up in the air that came flying overhead. It spun around and had some red lights in the middle. It was 19 meters above me and suddenly it flew away.

I noticed a black "thing" that I thought was a bird at first. However, I became aware that it couldn't be this, as there was no question of wing beats or the like. At the beginning of the observation, the size has been like the hole in a five-crore held in an outstretched arm. It moved slowly from right to left all the time approx. 30 degrees above the horizon. Furthermore, it looked like it could be a balloon (lighter pear-shaped with the thick end upwards). But the shape changed so that at times it was shaped like a banana, and the way the shape changed could suggest a rotation. My wife also saw the object and also the change in shape. After approx. For 1½ minutes it seemed as if the object stopped - but I now think more closely that it was a change of direction because the size decreased until we could no longer see it (the height above the horizon was constant to me). The height and distance of the object was quite difficult to determine - but there is a high thin cloud cover and the object stayed below this.

We have just driven from Svaneke to Østermarie on Bornholm. When we got halfway, four low-flying lights came towards us at even speed and equal distance from each other. They didn't have much speed and it looked very mysterious. Is there an explanation? At was 22.35 so it was probably not 4 gliders.

I stood looking at the night landscape from my bedroom on the 2nd floor when I spotted a reddish electric light out over the Århus bay. orange light. My first thought was that it was a planet, but quickly realized that the object's brightness was significantly stronger than even the brightest planets. Then thought about whether could be a rescue helicopter, which is often seen out over the bay. I retrieved my binoculars, located the object again and adjusted the scope to see if there were any flashing navigation lights to be seen. It wasn't there, which could also rule out that it was the landing light from a scheduled plane heading towards Tirstrup airport. In terms of perspective, it seemed like the lights were 5-10 kilometers away, so it would fit very well that the objects might be near the airport. Shortly after, 2 more lights appeared. The funny thing is that it looked to me like they suddenly turned on 3-4 degrees above the horizon. There are no objects in this direction that they could be hiding behind. It is approx. here that it occurs to me that they are moving quite slowly upwards at the same speed, although not a constant speed. They also hover alternately from side to side, without violent fluctuations in their trajectory. Their movements made me think of motorized paragliders. Eq. After approx. 5-6 minutes of slow ascent, the lights quickly dimmed and disappeared, all approx. at the same height. I could faintly see cloud cover around where they disappeared, so guess they disappeared into this. I've thought about it, and the closest explanation I can come up with myself is probably some kind of paper lantern. However, I do not recall that these move that high into the sky, unless you use a long-lasting form of fuel at the bottom, such as a tealight - however, the brightness of the objects and the immediate distance (which seemed to me to be at least 2-3 km) were much too strong for it to have been the kind of paper lantern that we know from Asia (and now also at home). I certainly don't believe in UFOs, so the explanation about the lanterns is probably still the one I lean towards the most. However, I think it would be quite fun if someone with a little more experience in this kind of phenomenon could give a better offer, as I myself have a little doubt about my conclusion.

I observed 1 light emerge over the ridge of the building across from me. I just thought it was probably an aviator, but approx. 30-40 sec. later one more came forward. I filmed some of it from my iPhone, which I'm also submitting.

I don't really know where to start... I think he is lying to me again, but as I look up at the sky, I clearly see 2 bright objects. I was 14 years old in 1971 and at this time was very interested in airplanes (what 14 year old kid isn't!). I went with my parents one Sunday to visit my grandfather, who had a house on Lucernevej in Rødovre. The approach route to Kastrup airport almost went over my grandfather's house, so it was exciting to stand and observe the different types of aircraft that came over. On that day in September, there was, as usual, traffic in the air. It was a typical autumn day with cloudy weather, and I notice that there is a Fokker Freindship (twin-engine domestic plane with turboprop) on approach with the landing wheels out, it was from SAS by the way. The plane is coming from the direction of Ballerup and is probably about 3-400 meters up, since it is almost in front of me, an extremely fast flying object comes in a curved path up from the clouds and lands about 10 meters behind the tail of the plane at the same speed like the plane. It looked like it was coming at 2000 km/h and stopped at the same speed as the plane in a fraction of a second! The shape of the object was pear-shaped and it flew with the wide end forward, the color was matte black/metal, it had no wings, but closely resembled a bulb painted black, and there was no sound except for the aircraft engines. By comparing with the size of the plane, I would think that it had a size of approximately 8 meters long and 4-5 meters wide. It flew at the same speed as the plane for 25 - 30 seconds, after which it sort of "stopped" and with an incredible speed (I could hardly see it, it was going so fast) disappeared in an arc in the clouds again. I was completely stunned and ran to my mum and dad shouting: I just saw a flying saucer, their response was of course, it's good with you kid, you've shown too much imagination. It was fantastic to see again, because I had seen something similar once before, but I can always tell about that another time. I am 48 years old today, but I will never forget that day in 1971.

On Monday 15/8, at some time between 21.00 and 21.20, my girlfriend and I saw a strange object flying/hovering over Copenhagen SW in an eastern direction, possibly a bit northeast if I judge correctly. We live on the 7th floor at Rektorparken and have a totally south-facing window. From our angle it looked as if the object was hovering from Sydhavn and towards Islands Brygge or Amagerfælled. The object was black, and at first we thought it was a large hobby helicopter drone, but then suddenly we could see that it was rotating slowly on itself in the air, such that any horizontal propellers would have turned vertical at least once in this rotation of the object. It was not pure rotations in a fixed path, but the rotating movement took place at a speed that I would estimate to be approx. 4 seconds per rotation - i.e. not particularly fast and probably much in the style of a cut, black plasic garbage bag being carried by a gentle breeze. The object flew/hovered in a path that could easily be a straight line, and its translational speed could also resemble a plastic bag being carried by a breeze. However, the object appeared more rigid than a plastic bag, in a way that gave me the impression that it was an airborne plate in rotation. At times the object rotated into a position so that it became completely invisible to us, as if the plate shape had its thinnest side oriented towards us, and shortly thereafter the object rotated further into a position so that we could see it again. I might be able to build a toy kite out of black garbage bags and carbon fiber rods with the same flying and hovering properties as the object we saw, but I'm not so sure that this kite would be able to rotate in the same way and still move on a reasonably straight line. I therefore cannot fully see what we have probably seen. Do you have any suggestions? Or have you received other reports about this object?

Very similar to the observation from Humble and Kokkedal, especially with mist and direction to the north. Size 3-4 times larger than the ISS, very white in the center and with movement (seen with binoculars). Here at 23:57 on 19 July I had a very remarkable experience in Frejlev. Saw a glowing green phenomenon with white smoke or light as a tail come flying for a few hundred? meters high across Budumvej while I was driving south by car. The object has appeared on the horizon in the same place for the last several evenings. It lights up and fades in at least three colors. I came driving on the E45 in a northbound direction between Horsens and Skanderborg. I spotted a stationary flashing object up in the air (at a position equivalent to about 11:30 as seen from the driver's seat of a car - if that makes any sense?) I thought the object was far too high up to be a warning flash on a mast or chimney. At the same time, I know that there are no masts or tall chimneys in that area, as I often drive on the stretch. The closer I got to the object, the more I realized that it was something I have not seen in the sky before, mostly because I could tell that the object was completely stationary, and I mean COMPLETELY as seen from the driver's seat of a moving car . I had to stay in the emergency lane. It turned out to be directly opposite the object, which I thus had at 9 for me. More or less immediately, it moved away in a leisurely motion and at a slow pace, I would say, southward in a straight line. It looked like a slow gliding and calm movement. Maybe there were a few short stops along the way, because I could see it for a few minutes out of the rear window. As best I could see there were three or four small flashing red lights that were around an object (I couldn't see any kind of object, just the lights) Between each of the red flashing lights were white ones, too flashing light in a kind of rays. It's hard to say anything about the height, but try the idea of flashing lights at the top of a television mast. Which, however, is far too high up for it to be a "mast" light. I can't say anything about the compass direction, because I don't know the coordinates of the starting point. But I know roughly where I stopped and might be able to find it again.
Not a sound was heard and then it disappeared into a brighter sky.

Saturday 15/12/07 in the evening I went into my bedroom, which faces north. You can see the Rigshospitalet from my bedroom. I often look straight out into the backyard, towards the Rigshospitalet or towards the night sky without turning on the light in my bedroom, as I personally like the dark. Astronomy has always been a great interest and therefore a dark room is natural for me. This evening I saw something that I have never seen in my life. Up towards the night sky at a height of about 40-50 degrees above the horizon, i.e. fairly high in the sky, I saw two objects which in size, appearance and brightness reminded me of Venus, except that both objects were orange. They stood completely still in the night sky without blinking, and there was a distance between the two objects of approximately 5 degrees. This means that one object was approximately 5 degrees higher in the night sky. I continued to observe the objects for approximately 10-13 minutes without any movement whatsoever, until suddenly the uppermost object began to move at a relatively steady pace obliquely upwards at a 50-60 degree incline from its original position, it was in. Over the course of a few minutes (3 minutes?), the top object got smaller and smaller until it was finally the size of a faint star in the night sky. At this time, the second object began to move in the same direction, obliquely upwards with the same inclination of 50-60 degrees, until, also after some minutes, it could no longer be seen in the sky. The whole episode lasted about 20 minutes. At the time of their disappearance, they probably had a height of approximately 60-70 degrees in relation to the horizon. During the episode and afterwards, I searched my brain for what it was that I had actually observed. Since I am interested in astronomy, I have spent almost my entire life looking at the night sky and therefore seen almost every object you can find out there in the dark. It must be said that I have never seen any strange objects in the night sky that could not be explained naturally, until now. You cannot find two natural orange objects in the night sky as bright in brightness as Venus that move suddenly. Therefore it must be something else. I thought of two options, either two helicopters or maybe anti-collision lights from aircraft. Regarding helicopters, the height of my sighting seemed to be well above the height that helicopters travel. I also don't know of any helicopters that stand still in the night sky for 10-13 minutes without flashing, then move diagonally upwards and disappear in about 3 minutes. As for anti-collision lights, that light may be orange, but again, I've been watching planes in the sky all my life and have never seen anything like this phenomenon. I was also aware of whether it might be an optical illusion. Over the Rigshospitalet and the city as a whole, there is always an orange glow in the night sky, which could perhaps induce an optical illusion, but I would immediately reject it as the case here. Firstly, the observation was not over the Rigshospitalet, but further west in relation to the building, and it was so high in the sky that the orange glow of the city does not bother. It was against a background of starry night sky. In conclusion, I would like to say that I do not know exactly what it was that I was looking at, but since for many years (over 20 years) I have observed the night sky and all natural (stars, planets, meteorites, etc.) and unnatural ( airplanes, helicopters, satellites, the space station, etc) objects, I can calmly say that what I saw on 12/15/07 for about 20 minutes is something new that I have never seen before in my life. For those who may think that I am a conspiracy theorist or similar, I can say that I am a doubter by nature and always seek to find a natural explanation for everything I experience in life.

So two balls come flying with a certain distance. They flew slowly and faded out slowly. Not like shooting stars that fly fast and downward. Bullets flew horizontally and disappeared in a horizontal position as well.

I had been out photographing, as I am a self-taught nature photographer, when on my way home with the camera over my shoulders, I see that beyond the Kattegat, a yellowish round light is coming closer towards me. See a glowing white dot. Just like when I look at Venus. The distance to the object seems much closer and lower than the aviators I see every day. It made a quick zig zag movement and was gone. Shooting stars strong white at a distance of 5-10 km in constant strong light come into view to the southwest. After approx. In 2 seconds it disappears due west as seen from my place of residence. Due to trees/vegetation, it is out of sight approx. 15 degrees above the Earth.

I'm sitting in the living room and see some big yellow lights in the sky between the trees. There were four lights. The lights went horizontally. They quickly disappeared into the sky. They became almost innocent with one.

Lay in a sun lounger at midnight and look towards the sky to observe if possible. shooting star. My house covers half of the northernmost sky, so I can't see from 13. We are sitting on the terrace enjoying the evening when this fireball suddenly appears. We quickly agree that it is not a plane. We are close to the airport, and see quite a few planes landing and taking off, but not in that direction at all. The light is also far too red, the shape wrong and the speed far too high. A few minutes later, three more of their kind appear. Same height and speed. The two of them fly very close. There is no sound. These are not rice lamps. We hope to hear from you as we have never seen anything like this.

I suddenly saw a small light that looked like a very bright lamp on an airplane, but there was no sound coming from it and it was moving faster than an airplane, so I thought it was a satellite. It languished in the south and flew west, half way across the sky the light disappeared and it was just a black dot in the sky with no other kind of light on it. Two to three seconds later comes another one. It flies in the direction south to north. It quickly came closer to me and flew over my house but so low that it flew below the clouds. It had a bright red color and a triangular shape, but also without any sound. I am very much wondering what this could be, and if you have an answer or others who have seen the same thing this evening, I would very much like to hear about it possibly by mail.

Just saw what I want to think is a meteor ... From my balcony with my evening coffee in hand, I have Roskildevej right next to where I live on my left, and it leads out towards Glostrup ... Roskilde, etc. .On my iphone's compass which I pointed to North.. the direction of the white glowing falling thing was .. South-West direction.. At first thought shooting star but as it neared .. the end.. I could clearly see fire and tail .. a total of 2 - 3 seconds.. before it disappeared behind the ridge of the neighboring house. I was lucky to have my distance glasses on, which I use when I occasionally look at the stars - so it was razor sharp. A shame I didn't have my mobile at hand so I could film it.. but it didn't last long... but I picked it up for the compass. Now I know it's not a UFO as such.. but it could be very fun to hear if others also saw it. Hence this report.

Standing and looking for shooting stars with my 3 year old daughter. We see 5 lights/stars in a window shape moving across our roof, but they have probably been 8-10 km away. They move 3 jerks across the sky. First jerk they stand still for approx. 2 to 3 sec. Second jerk 1 sec., and 3 it stands still for approx. 5 sec., where they move incredibly fast to the west.

My girlfriend and I were newly in love and cuddling in a bed with a window to it. We had opened the window all the way, and we both lay looking at the starry sky. I remember turning my head towards my girlfriend and was about to kiss her when her face suddenly lit up with a bright blue/white color. (A bit like the color of a blue halogen lamp.) I quickly turned my head towards the window and saw something inexplicable. Two triangle-like angles, slightly offset from each other, came rushing towards the sky and, as it were, dived in a soft arc towards the ground and looked directly into space. It went so fast that I sat up, looked at my girlfriend and asked her what she had seen. She had seen a little more than me. She had seen them sort of fly in waves down towards the ground and out towards space a few times, and suddenly they flew straight out into space. We were both 16 and we never reported it as we kind of just put it away. But every now and then when we look up at a clear sky we hope that we will get a glimpse of it again.

I was lying reading when a yellow light moved into the frame of my skylight. I opened the window to get a better look. There was a very yellow orb surrounded by yellow rays. There was also a smaller dot just outside the halo. The object moved at a steady speed across the sky for approx. 2 minutes before it disappeared over what little clouds there were. There was no wind.

Three objects floating slightly faster than a satellite in a perfectly straight line until disappearance. At first I thought it was a satellite when I saw the first one, but soon after another one came and then the last one. I had just looked up when I had seen a shooting star in the same place on the horizon. Just before they disappeared/extinguished, the rear one pulled up on the side of the others.
Today at approx. 23.40 a ball of light falls towards the west the size of a football, What was it?

We are three people sitting out in my friend's garden in the evening at around midnight. at 23.30-24.00 on Monday 6 August 2018 and suddenly what I can only describe as a large strong horizontal oval light that can be seen over the ridge of the house is switched on. I would estimate the size of the object from where we see it to be the size of a large full moon. From standing completely still in the sky, the object begins to move slowly horizontally, all the while shrinking within a relatively short distance and eventually disappearing. Just then, two white flashes follow in the sky not far from each other close to where the object has just been.

A beam of light that shone directly down, circular and then changed to a square, the light shone directly down from a very high "square" a good distance in the air and was like a strong beam. Was observed from a hill some distance away, so the size etc. cannot be written. Nothing else can be disclosed, just a more solid input to your observation archive. NB. Picture is taken, but it is completely white.

Clear green object, apparent size, approx. tennis ball. Descending from east to west for approx. 40 degree angle. Compass direction almost due north. Could be seen by me for approx. 0.5 sec through window before disappearing behind buildings. Distance? Not to judge!

After seeing you in MorgenTV, I have decided to submit a report, which I have thought about many times, but never got around to doing. On May 5, 1995, the day after the 50th anniversary of Denmark's liberation, (where there had been a "happening" in Kirke Såby the night before, which ended with a huge torchlight procession with about a thousand people with torches). Now all 3 of us saw it, it looked like this "Nilfisk top" again, it was very very low down, and suddenly it almost tilted so that we could see the bottom, but then the shape suddenly became elongated and triangular to look at, and it flew very silently slowly across the edge of our section in a north to south direction. This time, my husband had followed the whole process with binoculars, and he said that it was almost brownish in this triangle-like bottom and so massive to look at that he could not actually describe the material, but the closest description was a "very brown finely plowed soil ", because it almost had a "raked" bottom in longitudinal stripes, but still that very massive material to look at. We have talked many times that we wondered what it was that we had seen, and whether that day there was a test flight of the new low-flying American planes, and that there must be others who had seen it, when it was of 2 laps, and precisely because it went so low, but totally silent and no light to be seen, but of course it was also sunshine from a cloudless sky.

I'm sitting in my living room watching TV and out of the corner of my eye I see a flying orange/red ball. At first I thought it was a shooting star, but on closer inspection I could see that it wasn't. The object flew out into the horizon and became smaller and smaller. The color did not fade. The object was very clear all the way to the horizon.

Me and my brother were just out walking the dog this evening when we saw a lot of alternating lights and flashing things in the sky. Sometimes they flashed and flew around in a swarm. At one point two of them lit up and flew down towards the ground, where they disappeared, and after a while they flew up again. Sometimes they also disappeared completely, and just as suddenly 10 of them appeared again. We stood looking at it for over an hour. After which it got too cold so we went home. It can probably still be seen now, fantastic experience!

I also saw the dancing lights on the night between 8 and 9 April. After looking at it for approx. after a quarter of an hour, I agreed with myself that it was the light of the moon peeking out between the dark clouds. The wind was quite strong and there had been a full moon a few days before.

I had just come home from night work and went out onto my balcony on the 4th floor above Bodenhoff's Plads when I observed an orange light coming floating down Bodenhoff's Plads approx. 30-40 meters up. As it sailed past me I would estimate I was about 10 meters from it. The object was the size of a football, possibly larger if I had been a meter away from it. It shone with a strong red-orange light, which gave it the shape of a so-called morning star or Christmas star, i.e. jagged. It moved silently and dimly up the street, passed me and continued beyond Copenhagen's harbour. The speed was approx. 15 km per hour. When it was around Kongens Nytorv, it quietly changed its course to the west. At the same moment a similar one came from the same south-easterly direction, and it behaved exactly identically to the first in height, speed, brightness, stillness and course. It followed exactly the same trajectory as the first one. Both "UFOs" were very beautiful. They were clearly together. This is not about mistaken observations of meteors. They don't fly so slowly or so far down - in that case Copenhagen would have been in ruins. It wasn't an emergency flare either. They move high up in the sky, then fall. The two UFOs flew horizontally at the same height over Copenhagen, while I could follow them. Bodenhofss Plads is very quiet at night. You can hear a pin drop, and it's 100 per cent. certain that the objects were completely silent. They couldn't have been balloons either, if they had had an engine I would have heard that, and if they were just filled with helium and a burner they wouldn't be able to hold such a steady course but would have been shaken off the wind. They were clearly driven forward by something hitherto unknown. And I'm not Christianshavn's village madman. A fireball or ball lightning cannot move as determined either, i.e. follow a completely determined course, which includes a turn to the left, which was also executed in the same way.

Tuesday 12-06-01 in the evening, when my wife and I had to vent before going to bed at approx. 11.33 p.m., my wife sees a red/red-orange glowing spot far out on the horizon and asks me what it is. I say that it's probably a helicopter or maybe a star, I look at the light in a bit of wonder, and at the same time my wife gets a pair of binoculars, she looks at the light and says that it's behaving strangely, after which I get a pair of glasses. ship's binoculars and, when I catch the object in the binoculars, find that it is a similar reddish object swirling around within an area that we can both fix with the binoculars. It almost looks like a luminous snake that winds around at a fantastically high pace and at times takes the form of a ring. In the binoculars it looks as if it is moving within a small area, but this cannot be the case because it is so far away that it disappears behind the clouds twice before being seen again. Before I picked up the binoculars, I also saw a small 2-4 person plane that passes in our field of vision much closer than projected, but it has disappeared further from its route before I am back with the binoculars. The last thing we see of the object is that it disappears again behind a large cloud, after which we lose eye contact with it. WHAT could it have been?

On 20.07.08 at 00.15 I was sitting on my parents' terrace just outside Herrested, on Funen. My sister's dog (Border collie) was with me outside, it ran up and down the stairs and put a ball at my feet, after which it went down into the garden, lay down and waited for me to throw it out to it again. Which I didn't. So it just lay there and waited. It was quiet and peaceful, just a light breeze. Suddenly it stood up, but its gaze turned to the southwest. It was alert, fully tense, it barked, laid down and then ran into the house. I thought it had been scared of a cat or something in the dark, and went out on the stairs and looked. In the sky approx. 30 degrees above the horizon in a south-westerly direction there was a red glowing orb. My first thought was that it was a big plane. Suddenly, it dropped, very quickly, to approx. 10 degrees above the horizon, after which it quickly rose again to the same height as before. It then moved faster than a plane and slower than a satellite in an easterly direction, over the house, so that from my position it came up in approx. 80 degrees. At that point I ran into the house for a camera. When I came out it was on the other side of the house for a long time. From the other side of the house I saw another red ball in an easterly direction approx. 50 degrees above the horizon. Much further away than the first mentioned. It was gone after approx. 1½ min., in the east. The first one was moving at the same speed as when I was on the other side of the house, in the same direction as number two bullet. To the east. The whole experience with no. one bullet lasted for approx. 15 - 20 min., and the sky was sporadically covered with clouds. My thoughts were many as to what it could be. First a plane that was about to crash, but it went up again. Maybe someone flying a night dragon of some sort. But that was out of the picture when it got closer. A satellite, a space shuttle that was about to land, a large military helicopter... The thoughts were/are many, but whatever it was, it was exciting and I hope you can help me with what it could have been.

I have taken two pictures of a 2-masted schooner on the Baltic Sea. It sailed approx. 1km from the coast off Hesnæs today between 13.08 - 13.10. The pictures were taken from two different places/positions with approx. 100-150 m distance from each other. There is nothing special about it anyway, but there are some spots/dots in the sky in both pictures approx. 45 - 50 degrees above the ship! I can't really figure out what it is! Do you have an offer for it?? As well as the best that I have been able to make! I mean those dots are too big to be birds! I only saw this when I emptied the camera of pictures have in a bid??

I saw an object gliding across the sky, without sound and without light, but clearly an object which was not a bird, which was immediately my first thought. However, the object was not clear, it almost seemed to be easier to see through, approx. 80% visible. To me it almost looked like two vertical "plates", black and white, continuous, but with a slight angle. As I said, there was no light on the object, just as there was no sound either, it slid across the sky just below the cloud cover in a straight line coming from the east, sliding to the west. Steady speed, without changing direction or altitude, although once it seemed to disappear into the clouds. As mentioned, I first thought of a large bird, but it soon dawned on me that it was partly too large, and also not organic in its shape. It was reasonably clear with plenty of moonlight, and sound-wise I could make out the sounds of airplanes from the airport in the distance before and after, and still not a sound as the object slid across the sky above me. I have no idea what it could be, and being the rational person that I am, have gone through all the logical explanations in my head, and still cannot find a rational explanation for the object. Maybe you can help, I hope so.

Hmm. Yes. Now I write about my report anyway. But I'm more upset that people who know something about this UFO thing don't come forward and tell it. Don't ever think anyone found the truth funny no matter what or what the subject is. But if you tell the truth, you have nothing to lie about either!!!!!

I have here tonight at 17.48 observed a very very fast flying object flying from east to west. Although it was dark, the entire object was dimly lit. What made me react was that the object was flying reasonably low, at a very high speed and completely silent. The sky was completely clear at the time of observation.

I stood on the balcony and looked out at the fjord. Then I saw a ball of light drifting to the south. It was close to the other side of the fjord, after about three minutes. It became smaller and disappeared to the east southeast. I am writing to you because I have just seen the UFO obsavation footage online, exactly like the glowing ball I saw.

I was out walking the dog before going to bed when I saw an object the size and color of a bright bright star coming from the lake. Flew right over me and disappeared towards nv. At first it was like there was a warm glowing hole in the clouds, then it turned into some warm yellow lights in 2 or 3 lines just above each other before it disappeared as if it flew away in no time. 30 sec. later the light in the clouds appears again, this time they first stay in a kind of circle with lightning in it (a bit like the ball with purple lightning in it that you can influence with your hands), but in warm yellow light. Then it changes shape to what is best described as a parachute or jellyfish shape still with "lightning" in it. And then it disappears again.

On 18 June 2011 at 22:33 in the evening, I am driving on the Sorø country road and see 5 large flying fireballs, which are dark above, floating up over the horizon. The first two were close to each other and approx. 200 m after, 2 new fireballs came floating. The last one came approx. 300 m from the others. They hovered over the sunroof of my car so I could look right up at them. They were very large and completely silent, and they floated in the same direction towards Ringsted and at the same pace. Approx. 1 month later I saw a ball of fire similar to the one in the afternoon coming up over the horizon at Vridsløsevej in Næstved. It disappeared into a garden at the end of Vridsløsevej. It was even bigger than the others I had seen on June 18th. Have given them a lot of thought afterwards. They made a big impression on me. I got a picture of 2 of them from June 18, but unfortunately it was taken in poor resolution, but you can see them in the picture.

At first I think it's a joke, but still look out the window and see to my surprise that he is actually right. A balloon-like object rolls across the lawn - it's an orange slashing color and the spectacular thing about it is a ring of fire around it. I immediately rush out of the basement door to get this turned off - as I immediately perceive it as pranks. But when I get out on the lawn - 2 seconds later - the object has disappeared, there is no trace of it overhead - So you ask - What the hell did you see???
Fast and slow moving bright, bright object that suddenly rises and slowly disappears to the north. After 20 seconds of "flight", it is completely gone - just as the light is turned off. Mysterious!

About 5 times as big as an airplane. Green light surrounded as a triangle that sometimes turned red. Strange rapid movement back and forth as if it was close, but there was approx. 20 lights which made it look like a triangle and you could see the lights were very small. At times it looked like a circle and it was so weird. When I come back out, it is far away, size has decreased, but it was still moving from left to right, and vice versa. Really crazy phenomenon, and my mother was also 100% sure that it was not a plane, and wondered about the movement.

At 1.30 on Thursday, I was on my way to bed and was just going to have a smoke on the balcony. I saw a white/red thing (white above and red below) moving slowly across the sky, but no flashes as usual. airmen use. I'm used to a lot of air traffic over the Hedehusene, so I know what they must look like. I watched it for a few minutes when it seemed strange that it was standing still in the air. Then it floated south and then stopped again. There it changed to a green color, and of course that surprised me a lot, then it couldn't have been an ordinary plane. It then moved relatively quickly to the right and stopped, then quickly to the left and stayed there for maybe 1 minute. Then it changed color again to white/red and flew to the northwest slightly descending until I couldn't see anymore because of the trees and houses. I waited approx. 10 minutes, but then no more to it. I'll try again tonight, same time, to see if I can see it again.

I saw what I first thought was a star, although it was bigger and sharper and there were no other stars. It first stood relatively still for perhaps half an hour, but then slowly began to move around for another half hour. It didn't move very much, but a little up and down and back and forth, not like any airplane would. Eventually it disappeared behind buildings.

I was out with the dog, suddenly he reacted violently and pulled a lot to get home. When I looked up at the sky, there was a star and next to it a bright light that was almost still. Soon after, the light moves quickly to the southwest, much faster than an airplane could. I walk the last 40 meters home, and when we stand under the roof of the carport and look up, the light has moved north of us. It couldn't have been a plane at that speed and brightness, the dog was completely out of it until we got inside. I run inside to get my phone so I could film it. When I come back out, the light was gone.

I had seen an white Light in the sky, it does abnormal moves around the Night Sky from Römö. Also comes from the white thing yellow lights these lights bild an cicle in the sky and go down to the ground. I see this every day the last week from 22 - 3 o'clock.

I was out for a walk - Thinking of a UFO documentary I had seen yesterday.. Looking up at the sky and thinking "I wonder if we can see any tonight", the first thing my eyes catch is a white little light in the sky!! It was moving slower than a plane.. but seemed to be at about the height I usually see the planes flying here - But there was NO "chem trail".. whatever we call it in Danish?? (No white smoke). I followed the light with my eyes until it suddenly disappeared into nothingness!?.. Is this like satellites doing that? Went home with the idea of writing to you.. When I got home, I looked out the window (about where I saw the UFO).. can hardly believe it myself - the first thing I spot is the SAME white light ! This time it moves faster, again at the same height.. WITHOUT CHEMTRAILS! Took out my phone to take a picture - but it was too far away to see it on the camera... Followed it with my eye until it disappeared into the blue - finally it seemed to fly further away in the same direction as the light became less and less. It was 21:40-21:50 when I saw them. It was/is still bright outside!

Monday 11-07 approx. At 23:30 I observed an unusual light about the size of the moon, standing low in the southern sky - A strong yellowish light, shaped like a downward facing backward flame approx. 1 finger width above the moon. I sat by the back wall in my south-facing living room (about 4 meters from the window) on the 4th floor. There are 3 reasonable windows, as well as a terrace. The flame moved with great speed, west to east. When the flame/light appeared in the 2nd bay window I ran out onto the terrace, with a feeling that it might be a plane with a burning wing tank. From here, a cigar-shaped silhouette could be seen emitting the flame/light. The direction of flight was almost parallel to the block of flats, silent and at a constant height. At a position that could be over Copenhagen, it made a slight left turn and a flat dive, then straightened up and headed in its original direction at the height of the building's roofs (6 floors). Duration of observation, 15 to 20 seconds. A confusing and illogical experience.

I observe a dark heart-shaped UFO with red flashing lights on the back and a bright white light at the end of the "heart" tip. It hovers and turns like every now and then (to the right, down and up again and to the left) during the short 10 minutes I watched it. At first I picked up a pair of binoculars. When I picked up my camera a little later, it had unfortunately run out of power, and when I came out onto the terrace again, the object had suddenly disappeared.

Suddenly strong white light in the shape of a ball. Then the sphere opens up on the left side and very clearly shows something gray that looks like a section of the side of an airplane...just like the front of the wing. Then the ball gathers and disappears without direction and without light.

I stood and tried to see if I could see any stars, when I suddenly saw a luminous ball in front of a cloud in an almost southern direction. I think it was 5-6 degrees above the horizon. A little later I saw another glowing orb almost directly below the first one. I tried to take some pictures of them with my mobile but the camera was not good enough. Then it was as if the top ball was shining towards the right, so it looked like there was fire in it. I tried again to take a picture, but when I looked again they were gone.

3 April 2017, at 20:37, Google Position: 54°45'28.1"N 11°54'39.1"E. Going for a routine evening walk and almost home. I'm heading due east as I'm looking at two low planets as usual. One approx. 10 degrees to the right of my direction of travel (probably Jupiter), and the other almost straight ahead. Both are located at an angle of approx. 10 degrees above the horizon. At It's 8:37 p.m. when, high up on the right, I spot a luminous object, which I at first assume is a third planet. It is located due south and at an angle of approx. 70 degrees above the horizon. After a few seconds I learn that it moves for approx. same direction as myself, i.e. east. The speed of the object corresponds to that of a passenger plane if it flew at an altitude of 10 kilometers. The distance cannot be judged, but just for reference. My own first explanation is that it is a satellite. The reason for this explanation is that it does not have flashing lights and the white light it does have is constant. But two things do not fit well with the theory of a satellite. First, it shone much brighter than the many satellites that I have seen over time. Its brightness was similar to the said planet 10 degrees to my right (as mentioned maybe Jupiter). Second, it must have either followed an unusually low trajectory and/or had an unusually high speed. I then immediately rule out that it was a plane, as there were no flashing lights, and that the constant light of the object seemed far too strong. The brightness of the object can perhaps be explained by the fact that the sun had set relatively shortly before (perhaps 35-40 minutes before). The twilight in the field of observation, combined with perhaps direct sunlight reflecting on the object, could perhaps make it shine extra strongly. It could thus be both. A very bright satellite, or a very bright plane where its flashes were drowned out by the light of the sun. The observation takes place for approx. 1.30 – 2.00 minutes until the object disappears behind some low-hanging clouds/cloud cover. At that time, it is located approx. at the height of the two planes (approx. 10 degrees above the horizon), and at a compass angle of approx. 5-10 degrees to the right of due east.

It was raining heavily, I was on a bicycle. When I reached the traffic lights, I suddenly observed a huge oval brown thing that was completely still for approx. 8-10 m above street level. I was terrified, sure that in a little while I would be sucked into a UFO manned by strange beings. I droned around the corner to backsværdhovedgade at full speed. But suddenly - and fortunately - the object moved away at good speed towards the east. I was so scared, I was the only person outside, everyone else was in cars, but apparently saw nothing as the rain poured down. I choose to tell the story now, as one of my colleagues the other day also observed 3 UFOs from a side street to Stengårds alle - post no. 2800. Scary that so many people observe UFOs just in the UK.

I stood with my roommate out in the kitchen to drink a glass of water. When I look out the window, I see 4 orange lights in a row in formation. Just after the first observation, another 2 similar objects (lights) followed. Then I went to the bathroom to brush my teeth. I then went back to the kitchen to see if there were still any objects in the sky. Now two more objects (lights) were added, making a total of 8 lights (objects) in the sky flying around silently, (I opened the window to see if I could hear them) There was no sound from the objects at all. I observed them for a quarter of an hour until they finally disappeared approx. southeast from where I was with my roommate. I have taken 2 photos of the objects and, together with my partner, am willing to tell you more about my experience, should this be of interest to you.

Entering Ring 3 towards Glostrup from Herlev, stopped the car and took pictures of the beautiful Moon, hence these lights appeared in the sky and on the screen of my phone, as I took pictures of the Moon.

Last night I was standing outside with three friends. Suddenly I saw a red light moving quickly across the sky. The size of the light changed. It did not move in a straight line, but made strange circulations. It disappeared after 5 minutes, when the red light either flew up and out of our sight, or "burned up the red light". This is not the first time we have seen this light. Exactly one week ago (Tuesday) my girlfriend and I saw exactly the same light, exactly the same place, same time and same disappearance. I don't usually believe in UFOs and such superstitious "bullshit", but this seemed strange and unearthly.

I'm standing looking out of my kitchen windows when I spot something that looks like a very large bird and immediately wonder, I've never seen one like that before. Since I have binoculars at hand I can immediately see it as it is, it is NOT a bird or balloon or similar. It is a silver colored black object the size of an alm. refrigerator that rotates strongly on itself. Have it in my powerful binoculars for approx. 25 sec. It was approx. 250 meters outside and approx. 150 meters in height. Never seen anything like it and was deeply shaken. Was close to calling the police, but then I thought of this website.

First, some initial personal information. I am 43 years old (adult), rarely touch alcohol and have never taken drugs. So what I see in Haslev on 25/10 – 05 am. Approx. 00.50 I have to take note myself, as being real, and will claim the same to the outside world. I have also worked as a prison guard at Herstedvester — Denmark's only psychiatric institution. You are not allowed to do that unless your psyche is 100% in order. However, I predict that others will look at this report with a lot of skepticism, which is understandable in and of itself. I work the evening shift, and therefore go to bed relatively late. That night it was starry, and I stood in the yard and looked at the starry sky for a bit, after parking the car in the garage. Suddenly the farm (abandoned farm) is overrun by "something" in a SE direction and at a, I mean hellishly high speed. I can't determine the height, and therefore won't make a concrete guess at either the speed or the size. It is only visible for approx. 2-3 sec. Since the yard is three-legged, and one long one blocks the view in that direction. A description of the "thing stone": Yes, when you watch television or listen to the radio, my obervation is actually rather boring, I have to admit that - but! it was a triangular, single-angled black surface with a number of dull glowing things along the edge - but these, however, clearly located within the surface itself, a 4 or 5 piece. along each edge. Unfortunately, due to the time (dark) and the viewing angle, I can only give a two-dimensional description. In addition, it was silent. Every now and then I want to say that it should have broken through the sound barrier with the resulting noise, but it didn't. There was no hint of engine noise either. Furthermore, it had some strange wiggling movements in a horizontal plane. Hard to describe in writing, but I'll try: It oscillated horizontally around its own vertical central axis, just as some cogwheels inside a clock also oscillate around their own central axis. I manage to see a "tick and a tick", it flicks out and back again. Why? Don't know, you have to tell me, but it is my clear opinion that it was intended. It was not in any way unstable in its trajectory. That's what I saw, but since I'm a trained boiler attendant and process operator it can't be avoided, the technician comes up in one, so I'd like to attach a personal comment to the lights along the edge and to the distinctive movements. It was hardly a light in the usual sense, but probably a more integral part of the craft, probably part of the forward/buoyancy, as they pointed down and were located all the way around. The commute makes me think it must have been unmanned. There are hardly any living creatures that can withstand such movements over a long period of time — aliens or not. The G-force must have been terrible. Do I need to tell you that I went to bed an hour later than usual that night? I have always believed in the possibility of life elsewhere — now I don't believe anymore, I know!

Observation of luminous circular bodies that passed at high speed low over our house, which is located approx. 12 km from Holbæk town. The incident happened between October 1975 and April 1976. It was dark and the time was around 11 pm. The bodies came in group formations in different numbers from two to four from the SW in a NE direction towards Holbæk town. However, it appeared as if individual groups turned "perpendicularly" from their "normal direction". This continued for approx. 5-8 min. At work the next day I told about my experience. My colleague's son had the same experience, but from Slagelse. The observation did not appear in the local newspapers that afternoon, but only several days later, from which it appeared that 2-3000 people had noticed the remarkable "display". According to the newspaper, it was airplanes that were circling and waiting for landing permission from Copenhagen airport because of fog!!!!! Yes, death must have a cause. There had NOT been fog at Copenhagen airport and the observatory in Brorfelde was NOT allowed to comment on the incident.

Looking after newborn grandson and is out in the garden to get some fresh air and wait for him to be fed. Looking at the stars as it was starry that night. Completely unmotivated, I see an object that can be described as a tuning fork - straight edges no round, white and yet not - almost transparent, and while I look maybe 20-30 sec. the object disappears over Roskilde Fjord at high speed without a sound. Strange and moving experience and at first I thought it was a Stealth plane or something like that, but thought they probably don't fly in Denmark. It was very strange and I hope you have an explanation for the phenomenon as I have been thinking about it ever since.

We sit and eat barbecue in the garden (haven't been drinking :-)) and observe one of many planes on the way to Kastrup. (I am a keen plane spotter and can say with the Fligtradar24 app that it was SK1260 from SAS). To my amazement I discover a smaller white round object, about the size of the plane's wing, flying parallel to the plane at maybe 500 meters distance and at what looks like the same height. After 6-9 seconds the object changes direction and flies directly south, so I lose sight of the object after 2-4 seconds due to our large tree in the garden. Unfortunately, it goes by so fast that my wife or parents-in-law don't get to observe it. I rush around to the other side of the tree, but then the object is gone. We have quite a few birds in the area that can fly high up, but the object here was flying straight - and flying at the same speed or faster than the plane. It didn't seem like the object changed speed.

properties.Remarks: Forklaring: Bryllup på Havartigården i Holte!  Balloner med hjerter!se beretning

properties.content: Observed last night, September 27 at 03:45 in the southern sky, a flying object that had a very bright white light with a flashing red signal light. Flew west. Very far out, saw it through a scope with an eyepiece of 5 cm in width! It took 24 minutes for the object to fly "the 5 cm"!

A whole lot of small, bright, shiny objects rushing by in the sky outside my windows. The windows face the yard - not Vesterbrogade. The detached house only reaches the height of the second floor, so there is an unobstructed view of lots of sky. They entered from the left, ie. from the inner city and moved to the right, i.e. against Valby. They flew in a formation that at first looked almost like Chariot (with a few that were outside of this distinct formation), but as they moved past the formation became more blurred. I don't know how many there were, but I'm guessing 10 - 20. At first, the objects looked almost like small clouds with light in them, a few of which were larger and brighter than the others. As they moved past and the sunlight fell on them in a different way, they no longer looked quite so much like clouds with light in them, but became more "shiny" and "metallic". There was otherwise a blue sky with no clouds, and almost no wind. It was all very significant - but also went quite quickly.

The object was observed completely by chance on 2 different evenings when I looked out of my kitchen window to look for luminous night clouds in the bright night sky to the north. The first time was in June 2012. Here the object lay still for approx. 30 seconds, after which it disappeared at a high speed for us humans above a high-lying lighter cloud cover to the north and was gone. I chose to suppress this, because yes, there was probably a natural explanation, and maybe I was just tired and saw.... Approx. On July 1, 2012, I looked again for luminous night clouds, and now something was hanging in the sky again in the same direction and height. This time the object was illuminated in colors similar to a sunset and it sparkled. I have subsequently thought that it must be the sun, which had indeed set on the ground, but which was still "up" at the height of the object. The object was relatively quiet, where a plane from the airport in Tirstrup would pass quickly. I mean it moved a few times in small jerks, like if you put a dot on your window and then move while looking at the dot on the window - so a quick little jerk. Now it had to be documented, so I had to get my camera, but the 10 seconds I was gone was enough for the object to have completely disappeared from the clear sky, and there were no signs of smoke/vapour in the sky, as after a emergency flares or a plane - ugh I would have liked to have seen it disappear at high speed and also had it on film. I am very interested in hearing if others have seen/observed the same object north of Aarhus approx. 35 degrees above the horizon during the mentioned period.

Me and my fiance had to go down to McDonald's, which is a 5 minute walk away. It is a quarter past twelve in the evening, and we spot an orange-colored (almost burning) spot in the sky. We don't know how long it has been there, but we had our eye on it for approx. 5 minutes It disappears after the five minutes we stood looking at it. We get down on the MC and get our food and go out again. When we get out, it's back, and we keep an eye on it all the way home. This time we keep an eye on it for 7 minutes, when it then disappears behind some trees. Noticed that there are several people describing something similar, but has anyone figured out what it is?

This morning at 6:00 I was looking out the window when I suddenly saw a large, white light flying around in the sky. There is a large block some distance from my window and a park behind it, and the light flew down behind the block and up again many times. It was long, like two lights strung together, and sometimes it was only half as big as if one of the lights was gone. It also flashed a few times and went away, but suddenly came back. My sister saw it too, and it was there for at least 8 minutes, when it kept flying down behind the block and up again.
