I go and talk on the phone, look up and see two lights coming towards each other from a distance that will correspond to the width of the Chariot, at a 90 degree angle. At first I think it's satellites that happen to cross each other. The speed is faster than that of an airliner - a little faster than a fighter jet at high altitude. The lights are completely uniform and have an intensity that is slightly weaker than the surrounding stars. Before the lights meet, they straighten (turn each 45 degrees) and continue in a perfect pair run (they lie on a line perpendicular to the direction of movement) with a distance equal to half the distance between two stars in the "handle" of the Chariot. The lights continue in a north-westerly direction and begin to "swing" from and towards each other with an inner position which corresponds to the one mentioned above, and an outer position which is double - i.e. like between two stars in the Chariot's "handle". This continues for approx. 30 sec. after which the rhythm is broken, they reduce the speed in the direction of movement to half, before picking up the speed again after 5 seconds. Then the lights keep an equal distance (corresponding to the outer position). The lights now begin a slow clockwise rotation, still in line. The mid-point of the line which can be drawn between the two lights follows the same speed and direction of movement as the lights turn, so that the south-west light is at the front in the direction of movement as they come so far towards the horizon that they fade and become blurred in the center of the city light.

It is COMPLETELY clean in outline and shines completely white - not like the Moon. It accelerates, but seems completely stable and under control. I notice that the perfect shape invites to contain a sphere in the center or that there HAS been one. I reach the motorway exit at Hadsten and the exit ramp covers the "object" on my right. As I drive under the bridge, a car turns from the direction of Hadsten down the access ramp in the same direction as me. I'm trying to connect the car's headlights with the "light" but it's just not that at all, and I can't see anymore...

In a blue sky at sunset, I am out walking my dog. I observe an elongated metallic shiny object in a westerly direction, which I first assume is an airplane heading due north. The distance was great, but I don't see any wings or tail rudder - it just seems elongated. It moves slower than I would expect from an airplane and emits a pulsating, possibly rotating, white light that seems to get stronger all the time. After observing the object for a good 30 seconds, I pass under some trees and lose sight of the object for no more than 10 seconds. When I have a clear view again, the object has completely disappeared into the blue sky. It is completely inexplicable to me, as the object has not been near a cloud or similar. There was no audible sound, which in itself is not surprising given the great distance.

My friend and I wanted to sleep on the balcony last night, as it was almost completely starry. We had been looking at the stars for approx. half an hour (approximately from a quarter past 12 to a quarter past 12), when a very bright star began to "dance" almost vertically above us. It had not moved until then, but suddenly it began to move in choppy movements, both side to side, up and down and in circular movements - it did not move far from its original position at all, but it looked very strange out. We managed to fall asleep before it stopped, and it lasted at least half an hour.

At approx. 21:25 while eating on the terrace here, my friend observes an American football shaped sun yellow bright object passing from right to left, from west to east at low altitude and with considerable speed. The object passes silently in less than a second. I sit with my back to it and watch the terrace light up strongly..

6/7 luminous objects at sunset on 24 Nov. Three light TV for sunset smaller size, 15/20 degrees? earlier right up (25, 30? degrees), later closer to each other, triangle formation, finally disappearing (without "landing"). Second side, th for sunset: at first I think I could see three, but lost sight of one of them: one very high up (can be seen in the picture), and one more, th for it, lower down. At the end of my observation period, the low seems to flare out on the right side, then they both also disappear very slowly down towards the ground. I stood for about half an hour at a small bridge north of the Swan lake at the Kildegård allotment, lowest part at Harrestrupvej, Skovlunde, became very fascinated: pictures were taken towards the end of the observation, when I remembered if my mobile has a camera: I know the tail of an airplane well at sunset... maybe it was the bright streaks you write about, but very low in the sky: quite a few alms flew. aircraft in the meantime. The objects were "almost" still, except when the three TVs from the sun came closer in formation, so slowly that I could not register it, and just as slowly the other two "landed". Only today have we tried to download the images, and you can only see by manipulating the colors and contrast, otherwise the object disappears in the light. I am sending herewith the two pictures, one a little, and one much enlarged and the original.

I see out of my living room window a bright white light coming out of nowhere. It is moving north at a speed equivalent to an alm. object (e.g. a falling ball), or a shooting star moving across the sky. However, it has no tail and easily changes direction from due north to a slightly north-westerly direction. I can't decide for myself what I saw, but I am convinced that this was not an airplane, helicopter, fireworks, shooting stars, etc. By that I would mean that it was a UFO.

Lay awake in bed, couldn't sleep. I had just read the news on my mobile when, through our semi-transparent roller blinds, I see a strong orange glow, exactly like a fire in the neighboring building. Wakes up my girlfriend next to me and rolls up to see where it's burning, the whole space between the buildings is brightly lit up by the glare from the "fire" and when we look down at the ground very close to the window, the light source disappears very close to our roof (2 storey building), a completely sharp raised shadow. The shadow from the roof shows that it is on its way to the other side of the building, runs around to the other side of the apartment, but now cannot see any light source. We are both very puzzled and also a little scared as we cannot explain what it could be. It all happened silently.

A strong light phenomenon moves across the horizon at low altitude above the ground from west to north-east. The phenomenon is experienced as a strongly luminous and sharply defined sphere that moves in an arc over the horizon in the described direction.

Saturday evening (May 17, 2014) I was standing on the terrace smoking a cigarette when I saw a very bright light in the sky to the south (I live in Egå, north of Aarhus). I stared at the phenomenon without saying a word, and for a moment I was convinced that it was an airliner in flames (although the light was clear, it was more like a fireball in color) headed for my house - size, speed and color of the phenomenon was fit for an airliner, except that absolutely no sound was to be heard anywhere, which puzzled me greatly. It was high up - we are used to seeing planes in the sky, which lose speed and speed because they have to land in tirstrup, but that is certainly not what we are talking about here. It was far too high up compared to the Tirstrup planes, and as mentioned, there was no sound of any kind either. Best as the panic was getting the better of me in relation to the fact that the "passenger plane" in flames/the object was heading towards us, and I had to evacuate the house for my wife and children if necessary, the object turned sharply to the left (as seen from my angle of view), towards mols/ebeltoft, after which it faded and disappeared soon after. And the turn the object took was sharp; it wasn't just a soft curve. And right after the turn it also faded away with tremendous speed. It went from being a violent large fireball in the sky to within 5 - 10 seconds (after the object changed course) to having largely disappeared from the sky. And it didn't come back again. I have no idea about the height of it, but I would guess that it was at least 2 kilometers high. as I said, I stood on the terrace and couldn't say much until it was all over, so I told my friend through the open garden door what I had experienced - he was visiting so we could see the speedway from Finland, but of course he asked me to check the quality of the wine we had consumed. Just after he asked me to pull myself together, another one of the same caliber as the one described first came - I called my friend, who came out on the terrace and fortunately was able to film the whole thing - albeit with his iPhone. But the scenario played out exactly as described above - same object, color, height, course change, fade out, etc. When he had filmed the whole thing, he was just as pumped as I was. And then it happened that number three came flying, which we also got on video - unfortunately again only with the iPhone. I say on the video that it is 23.13 when the last 2 "arrives". I would guess that there have been approx. 4 - 5 minutes between the first to the next and the third. So, all in all, the whole thing is settled within approx. 10 minutes. We/I have searched like crazy to find an explanation for what we experienced on Saturday - and of course without success. I am on the verge of donating my firstborn to whoever can provide a plausible explanation. Not because I believe that there is a plausible explanation - for that it was simply too strange an experience when you take the size of the object, color (fire-coloured), speed, height, etc. into account - and that there were three of them in line, same behavior, change of cow etc. My wife will certainly also oppose the donation of our son. It was simply so crazy that I need an explanation for it - I'm not sure I'll get a good night's rest until it happens. And in general I'm not a big UFO hunter or conspiracy theorist, but here the line to my skepticism has been crossed several times..... The reason why I choose to write in this forum is also that I naturally googled the phenomenon and found that others had the same experience on 17 May 2014. So it sounds easy to come up with a story 3 days later, but hopefully our videos can make up for this - if only so that the other observers of the same date might nod in recognition to the phenomenon based on the videos of the "last two" - we saw three, but really have no idea how many there might have been....

I went out on my girlfriend's balcony, which is on the ground floor of a large block of flats, because there were some neighbors playing loud Turkish music, which I wanted to turn down. I then saw a strange phenomenon, which I first thought was a star, but I have never seen such a large triangular star with light on all three sides. It appeared to be far away and did not move for the half hour I observed it, but there was some red light occasionally for a longer time on the left side (not like an airplane). Also, there were some small white lights swarming around it (might resemble airplane lights), but no sound came from any of the objects. I could judge this when the Turks stopped playing. The triangular object appeared half the size of the moon, but appeared to be far away. I went in to see if there was anything special on the TV and when I came out there was nothing. This may be due to cloud cover.
Picture since it is there. Some say reflex of my iPhone? Took a picture of my curved window sill for another purpose and behind it was gray stuff - which I don't know what it looked like.

The night of 1/8 2016 at approx. 01:28 I stood smoking on the balcony. I had my eyes fixed on the sky to the east, about 60 degrees above the horizon. Suddenly I saw what I assumed was a satellite flying from north to south. As I watched it, without further ado, it changed direction to the west in a 90 degree turn. It flew much faster than a plane, which I conclude on the basis that it must have been high up, perhaps as far as 10-20 km. It was of approx. same brightness as a faint star, and of similar size. As I unfortunately didn't have my glasses on, I quickly slipped in after them, but it was no longer visible when I was out on the balcony again after just 10 seconds. It may have disappeared behind one of the scattered clouds. Since I don't know of any other craft flying that fast, or changing direction that abruptly, I assume it could possibly have been a UFO.
No report.

A luminous ball from the EAST over Copenhagen was moving due west towards Valby (Vestervang), which caught my interest as it was an abnormal flight line (deviating from the normal flight corridor). When the light phenomenon was close to Valby, the UFO turned from EAST 90° STEEP towards NORTH and disappeared in the distance. It was completely SILENT!!! So not a plane, - but maybe a light balloon (launched by humans ???) or something similar. An acquaintance of mine (associated with NASA) believed that it was a NASA phenomenon, ie a surveillance device that we are (without being told) exposed to. I doubt. Incidentally, the UFO moved COMPLETELY SILENTLY at an even speed and movement. I would estimate the size to be slightly smaller than a hot air balloon. I still wonder what it could be! And would like to hear from SUFOI if you have a good explanation.

Standing outside in the garden smoking. Suddenly, out of the corner of my eye, I see three white lights, which come in from the right and stop right above my head. The three lights stand together. They "zapped" to all four corners of the world, each time returning to Zenit. Zapped to the east, and was gone.

I was having a cigarette on my mate's terrace, it was starry and there was a 'star' that caught my attention as it pulsated more than I have seen a star do before. To the naked eye it seemed to change color (quickly changing) and I got another mate to watch. After we agreed it looked strange (while we had all the news with comet ISON in the back of our minds) I had a 3rd mate fetch a pair of binoculars. Through the binoculars the color shifting became much more apparent and I thought it looked like the colors were changing regularly. It could also look like there was a "ring" of changing color around the "star", but this could also be because I couldn't hold the binoculars any longer. We discussed which direction it was coming from and agreed it must be in a southerly direction. It seemed that the "star" was moving slowly in the sky, after 1/2 hour it became cloudy. Got a picture taken with my iPhone camera and just looks like a smudged star. (due to zoom, etc.) I doubt it could be the comet ISON, and since I don't understand this sort of thing, I also doubt it is just a star that can sparkle in the mentioned colors (red /blue/white). All in all, I just became incredibly curious and therefore chose to write to you. Ps about 45 degrees (height above the horizon, I'm in doubt) as well as whether it was due south, I didn't have a compass on me.

At first I thought I saw an airplane where an engine had caught fire, as it fits with the altitude and speed. I first observed an "orange bright fireball" with a constant light/glow. After 30 seconds it was followed by 2 identical flying objects. I again have an idea of what I have seen, and would like feedback on whether others have seen something similar and what it is that I have seen.

I was washing dishes in my kitchen on the 5th floor and had the window open - when I looked up in the sky and saw a white shining star - which I thought at first glance was Venus. But I could see that the iron seemed to be moving a little, so I yelled at my husband to come take a look. We could both ascertain that the star moved down and later moved away from us in a south-southwest direction until it disappeared from view. The whole thing took approx. 2-5 minutes. It was otherwise starry, no clouds and air traffic is still closed.

When I was younger, me and some friends walked home from a place we had been in the evening. On the way home we saw an object with fire and a tail of fire, after a while the fire on the object went out and changed color to something red and yellow and a little green (a lot of different colors). The object flew across the sky at a very very fast speed. Never seen anything move so fast. We all saw the same thing and became very curious. The object continued to drift across the sky. It stopped a few times, at one point over our school/stadium and later over a water tower further out. The object moved very quickly and sometimes changed color. We are all sure that there was fire in the object and it was not just an illusion. We saw what we saw. And we still remember what we saw! I can't remember what day it was or what year. But I can try to hear the others who were with about degrees and direction etc

I step outside to smoke and look at the full moon again when I see what I first assume is an emergency rocket. But the wind is still, and the red ball is moving rather quickly, and at the same time I think I can hear a faint hum. The light changes to yellow and back to red, while continuing in the same direction and height to the west. I run in to get my binoculars (unfortunately my wife and daughter have just gone to bed). With the binoculars you can see the round light continue towards the horizon and occasionally change from red to yellow, still with a faint humming sound. No smoke like an emergency rocket would have given and probably much bigger and higher up.

Having seen satalites before, I was aware that, for one thing, they fly much higher than this object. Another said it was a plane, but planes have beacons on their wings that flash every 3-4 seconds, it didn't observe it, and that it was moving at a high speed and totally silent from the time we observed it until it was right over our heads, and that there were no sounds either after it had passed. The item was approx. max. 1 kilometer up. The object was yellow in the center circle and around this circle were like 40 or more rotating circles of silver color. The object moved at a very high speed, a speed that far exceeded normal aircraft speed. Personally, I have never seen anything like this, but have always wanted to experience something like this, and I am glad that there were many witnesses to this, otherwise they would probably have said that I had sunstroke and had seen visions.

I went out into our little backyard to have a smoke before going to bed when I see what I first think is a shooting star appear behind the neighbor's house (to the west). It continues on a course that I would think is horizontal across the night sky until it disappears behind another house (south-east). The actual object I saw was moving very fast approx. 1/3 of the speed at which you normally see a shooting star. (I've seen shooting stars in the past that lasted 3-4 seconds and am reasonably sure that's not what I saw). The object as I saw it appeared to me to have or be composed of 2 or 3 lights and had what appeared to be a tail behind it.

I report the memory below because I got a tip from my sister that a "site" on Google about a sighting in England in 1993 contained a description that sounded a bit like what I had experienced. Otherwise, I have not approached anyone other than a few friends about it - mostly because the memory is so strangely difficult to retrieve, but also because my observation seems "science fiction-like" and does not describe a UFO in the classic sense either - by that I mean a rotating, round thing with lots of light and very high speed. For some reason it is completely impossible for me to remember exactly when it took place. I'm just certain that it was after 1998 and that it was before 2001. I haven't been able to reconstruct the time since, because my memory of the sighting fades within minutes, then I forget all about it in weeks or months before it hits me again that something strange happened. So the following is my observation: Probably in 2000 - either spring or early summer. It was evening and dark, but relatively warm. I am standing in the middle of the floor in our living room on the 2nd floor and am blinded by a white floodlight the size of a car's headlight coming from the west, where there is a clear view from the living room windows. We (my then 16/17 year old daughter, 11/12 year old son and myself) are very surprised and rush out onto the balcony – which also faces west. Here we see a very large vessel approaching very slowly – and flying very, very low. It's not loud, but has a very deep, unpleasant hum that I almost feel more than I hear it. The vessel is huge and completely dark gray against a black sky. It appears to be only 10-20 meters up and is at least a few hundred square meters, but seems flat. It is triangular, almost shaped like a fighter plane, only much larger. The underside is not smooth, but full of edges and shapes (actually like the underside of spaceships in movies). I don't remember there being any lights (this part of my memory is completely different from my daughter's?!) when it first came over us. It was approx. 10 seconds to pass over our heads, and then had come so far over that we would lose sight of it due to the roof of our block. We wanted to rush through the living room, out into the hallway and into the kitchen (usually about a 5 second run) which faces east to see where it flew to, but.... all I remember is that I reached the hall,—after that I know not what we did, or what we saw. On the whole, I don't remember at all what we did afterwards that night. I had no recollection of this entire experience until at least ½ or a full year later. We go for a walk with my sister and talk about everything, when suddenly - without warning - I remember something about a huge vessel that the children and I had seen. I'm thinking like crazy about what it was I saw. I tell my sister that I suddenly remember seeing something, and I call my children who are running some distance away and ask them if they don't remember some strange craft we saw a long time ago. They both look a little surprised, but after a few seconds, I can see that something is coming to their mind. They think a lot and are a little hesitant, as if it is very difficult for them to hold on to the memory, but after a few more seconds they begin to tell - a little in leaps and bounds and in each other's mouths - about the same experience. But all three of us find it very difficult to recall the experience. And every time we've talked about it, we forget it again within minutes, and don't think about it again until weeks or months later. It is as if the memory "will not be remembered" - as if there is a filter that is almost impossible to penetrate. And none of us still remembers what happened when we wanted to go out to see the vessel on the east side...none of us remembers anything else from that night!

It is completely cloudless. Obliquely up to the right, probably at a high altitude, what I first think is a satellite is observed, however, a little faster. It shines like a big star with the same light quality, i.e. approximately white and flies in a straight line. I know a great deal about airplanes and my instinctive interest was immediately piqued. This was unusual. After approx. After 10 seconds, the light suddenly goes out like a slow-extinguishing light bulb, and only a small luminous horizontal line remains. Which then vanishes before my eyes. The speed was nowhere near a meteorite. The observation is linked to an observation I made in 1978 over Lyngby of two objects with exactly the same quality of light, which in turn performed aerial acrobatics, which at that time, and is not possible today in a human-made machine. The then observation was made at approx. 17 on a winter's day from Lyngby Station Square. Two lights came, like two planes side by side, flying from the right at great speed. They made an approx. 110 degree turn and then flew from left to right as they performed, at high speed, some local very sharp changes of direction in the direction of flight before flying steeply and very quickly upward literally into space. It was because of this very telling observation in 1978 that the luminous white point-shaped object immediately piqued my interest last night.

Approx. At 00.50 I stand on the step by my front door and look in a west-northwest direction. Here I look up at the sky and see until several unidentified silent objects with a reddish florescent glow one after the other come gliding across the sky into Skern city, continuing in an east-southeast direction. Took a whole series of pictures up to 29 pictures with my iphone 4s in zoom mode.
Another one, this time coming from a northwesterly direction. This one with a slightly red tone otherwise like a star. Moved in small jerks and hung for about 3 minutes above Hjørring midtown.

We are 4 girls who have seen an orange, large, oval shaped thing that flew through the sky at 21:30 in Svendborg. It was silent and flew through the sky approx. 3 minutes before it died out. We have documented it on video, and would really like to hear if you know what it is? We have never seen anything like this and are beginning to believe that it is something that cannot be documented with a professional reason. Help help, we are scared and need a reason for what it might be before we can put it away.

Today there was a bicycle race in Vejle on something called Søndermarken. The cycling team usually cycle past in this area where I live. I didn't want to see it, so I contented myself with looking out of my bedroom window and watching the beautiful blue sky, and I could hear that there was full documentation around the bike race. A helicopter came into view and moved in the direction where the bike race was happening. They might be filming the race or watching traffic and things like that. Suddenly I see two lenticular luminous objects moving across the sky, over the parking lot which is outside my bedroom. The objects were silent and shiny, slightly dazzling. They kept pace with each other all the time, sometimes circling each other, but they never parted. They came from the south, i.e. from the direction of around the place where there was a bicycle race. They moved over the forest that I am next door to, in a northerly direction, and down towards the city (I live a little high up and away from the city itself). I'm all excited and call my mom who lives down town and tell her what I've seen. About five minutes later, I see a single sphere, perfectly round and chalk white, moving (floating almost) in the same direction, just a little further away. Almost immediately after, a green military helicopter arrives, which has obviously lost interest in the bike race, and it moves in the direction of the place where I saw the bullet. A few minutes later I see something moving very high up in the clouds, in a northerly direction, and it's a gray and metallic ball, and I assume it must have been big as I see it so clearly and so high up , as it is. My mother calls and tells me that the military helicopter has reached the town where there is no bike race, and I tell her about the other bullets I saw and that the helicopter may be chasing them. Soon after, I see the last bullet, which is close and very clear. It moves quietly across the parking lot, again from the south and again to the north. Silent. It is perfectly round and very white. I am fully up to speed and keep my mother up to date. Nothing more happened then, it was over. I'm not very good with heights and distances and can't provide satisfactory data about those things, but all this happened between about 4 and 5 pm this afternoon. Maybe under half an hour. I didn't keep an eye on the time, I just observed and was completely up to speed. I have a video camera and I have decided to have it ready in case more of these orbs/objects appear. It must be said that I have seen similar objects many times in my life, also in my area, day and night, but have never been prepared and therefore never been able to e.g. to film them or take pictures of them. There must have been others who must have seen some of these balls/objects today, but it can be thought that most of them probably focused on the bike race. There may be few witnesses who dare not report it. I know what I saw today was very unusual, they were neither drones nor balloons, they were intelligently controlled, and the two lenticular objects I first saw behaved intelligently. And when the military helicopter suddenly moves away from the bike race and towards one of the balls, there must have been something unusual going on.

There was a triangle formed by three flashing lights: red, green and blue. There were four of these in total, and together they formed a perfect square over central Copenhagen. At first we thought there was a plane (because it was at the same height), but it wasn't moving at all. After approx. 50 minutes then they all slowly began to move higher up and south. We then found an article on tv2's text tv, which said that in a city in Australia they had seen the same lights (a triangle formed by a red green and blue light), no one knew what it was, and the airport confirmed that it was not some of their planes! I'm not usually one to believe in UFOs at all, but it was a very strange experience and I want to find out what it could be!

Sitting on the balcony belonging to the apartment, when we observe a single bright reddish "star" to the southwest approx. 15 degrees above the roof at the far end of the yard. At first we don't think much about it, apart from the fact that it's the only light you can see in the sky, but when it suddenly changes to bluish light, it's a bit mysterious, but you think drone or other man-made phenomenon. It is only when the object suddenly falls very quickly towards the ground, hovering approx. 10 degrees to the north and disappears to the southwest for approx. 220 degrees until it is under the roof. The speed at which this maneuver was accomplished surpasses anything I've seen from even fast drones and the like. We're talking maybe 2-3 seconds for a fall that looks like many 100 meters (maybe km, it was hard to tell how far it was horizontally) followed by the horizontal movement to the southwest until it was out out of sight. Took some pictures and videos, unfortunately not as it moved away and the quality is not great as it was taken with an older HTC phone at night, but will try to email them anyway. Also made a daylight sketch of the process. Hope you have a qualified guess as to what size the cave was.

I was sitting with a guest in our living room when our guest spotted something in the sky that caught her attention. I looked out and could see a very bright star, low over the horizon. Since it was a relatively bright evening, with a nearly full moon, it was difficult to see other stars, making the bright spot we saw appear to be an anomaly. We observed the spot for maybe 5-7 minutes and it varied in brightness, sometimes flashing, other times slowly pulsating. Our guest experienced it as if there were more than one point, very close to each other. A bright bright spot, with a faint spot just above, and one just below. I didn't have the same experience but thought there was only one point. I experienced it as if the point was far away, at least several kilometers, maybe 10 or more. My first thought was that it might be an aircraft, possibly on its way in for landing at Bornholm Airport, but since it was not moving relative to the ground, I had no theory as to what the point was. When the first 5-7 minutes had passed, something very unusual happened. Another point, somewhat smaller, appeared in the sky, somewhat below and to the right of the first point, and it quickly moved in a straight line up towards the first point and struck it, causing both points to disappear. Just as the smaller dot (resembling a New Year's rocket in a dark sky before it explodes) hit the first dot, the brightness increased somewhat before it all disappeared. There was no visible explosion or the like. After a few minutes there was again a point in the sky, in the same place. It all repeated in the same way with the difference that the dot did not disappear when the smaller dot hit it. After a few more minutes, the spot disappeared after slowly losing its brightness. At that time I called my colleague in the air traffic control tower at Bornholm Airport to ask him if he might have any information about the phenomenon. He had not seen the point, but looked to the east, and then the point was back in the sky again, and he could see it too. The firing ranges east of Bornholm, ES D 138 and ES D 139, were not active, according to the information he had available. He had a plane coming in for landing from the west and we ended our conversation. Shortly thereafter, the dot was hit a third time by the smaller dot that again suddenly became visible in the sky, below and to the right of the first dot, and this time both dots disappeared again on impact. I immediately called my colleague, but unfortunately he had been talking to the arriving plane and had therefore not seen the collision. After some time the first point returned again, in the same place. This time we did not observe any collision, but the point eventually disappeared in the same way as the second time, it slowly lost its brightness and disappeared. This last time our guest observed from the guest room on the first floor and I from the living room. After the fourth time, clouds began to move in from the west, and it was no longer possible to see if there were any more points of light or collisions.

properties.Colors: uklart hvidt lys med rødt skær
properties.content: Came out into the kitchen and saw the light, it had great speed over the city. Ran out onto the balcony on the other side, but when I wanted to film when it appeared, it had disappeared.

We were sitting in the garden with a fire and looking at the stars, when suddenly a red "lantern" appears over the hedge to the SW. The neighbor had just sent lanterns into the air, so at first we thought it was something similar, but it was moving in a completely different direction and much faster. There was no sound at all from the object, and there was absolutely no wind at all. It was VERY difficult to judge the distance to the object (especially due to the lack of noise). We lost sight of it as it disappeared behind our large beech tree.

I saw a luminous object flying in a straight path corresponding to a distance of approx. 8 km in the sky. My first impression was that it looked like a shooting star, but the meeting it flew at seemed to be mild. It was in a stringy line. The object moved across the sky and disappeared just as it appeared, a bit like "it went off". The observation was taken on Thorbeksgade in Odense in the direction of Helenevej.

Suddenly, in clear weather, something very high up that looked like an ordinary star, but it had an elongated shape, as if there were 2 stars joined together. It stood still. When I was almost at the entrance to Lyngby, a small "star" suddenly came out of the big "star", this also stood still. I drove up the exit for Lyngby and had to turn right off Klampenborgvej, so I couldn't follow it anymore, as it was then behind me. 2 minutes later I was home and rushed out into the garden with my husband, but unfortunately there were too many trees so we couldn't see what happened next. There must definitely be others who observed it as it was very clear in the sky.

Not in the air, but on the ground. On my mother's lawn in Stenstrup, Sydfyn, on 2 January 2001 there were seven distinct rings, 30 cm in diameter and 1.5 cm in thickness. It looked like something had been there for days, the grass was pressed down and withered. There was nothing to see on 1 January. The rings were scattered over the lawn, but not in any pattern and only where there was space above - not under the trees. Has there been a hit by mini-vessels, or what could it be? Too bad no one saw how they came to be.

When I see a round bright dot above Kbh., I thought there was a star, then I thought it probably hung low. But it stood still, so I thought nothing more of it. A minute or two later I see it again, it had moved a little up and a little to the north. That surprised me a little. Then I got coffee and when I came back it was moving slowly up and in a zigzag. I looked at it for several minutes, when for a moment it seemed to split into two separate lights. I see planes take off here daily from Kastrup. I have also traveled a lot by plane myself. It was NOT a plane, and it wasn't a helicopter, because I would have been able to hear that. Also, I ended up seeing the unfamiliar light so high up that there is no helicopter up there. I would estimate that it rose 60 degrees or more upwards and 40-50 degrees to the north. I've never seen anything strange without an explanation before, and I'm just having a really hard time finding a logical explanation for this. I wouldn't normally report this kind of thing. But maybe there are others who have seen the same thing, and then you can use it as supporting data.

Was out at my father's company building in Ballerup, and I decide to go for a walk with my dog Anton before driving home. This is something I have done often, as there is a large golf course right next door which is completely quiet in the evening. But unfortunately I don't get all the way down there this evening because I observe two orange red lights out in the sky far out on the horizon in the direction of the golf course. They fly from right to left at a leisurely pace. The upper one is a bit ahead of the lower one, but they fly completely in sync. Distances between them are perhaps a clenched fist. I now stop and look at the lights seriously and notice that there are no sounds and the light is constant. And in the same second that I think that this seems a little mysterious, the upper light goes out, and it never comes back. But the lower one continues at the same calm pace, but suddenly begins to fade its light until it disappears completely. It all only takes one to two minutes, but am 100% sure that I have witnessed something I have never seen before. It should also be said that I grew up right next to Værløse Airport and have seen all kinds of civil and military planes and helicopters since childhood. The constant light and the pace they kept, plus the fact that they flew in sync, arouses my wonder. What is a fist to me must be several kilometers away to them, which is why I am still very amazed that they were able to fly completely in sync. It was as if they were one and the same organism. Also never before seen a plane with that constant orange-red color not to mention it dimmed down like it had a dimmer switch attached. I'm sorry that I didn't make it all the way to the golf course in total darkness, but unfortunately it's not something you choose for yourself.

I was awake and looking at the sky with the stars at 02.10. Suddenly a bright white light appeared very high in the sky. It reminded me of a car light that just came from above. The light disappeared soon after - without any movement across the sky. After a short time another much smaller light appeared. It looked like a perfectly normal satellite, just moving perfectly normally across the sky - from north to south.

Then I could see on the horizon a bright ball with two colors of light. At one end it was red and the other white. It floated over the sky slowly, it was as if it was spinning around its own axis. with a strange flashing frequency.

I had just showered and was about to go to bed. My wife had just fallen asleep. When, as so often before, I just look up at the sky out of the window, I spot a strong light in the night sky to the southwest. At first I think it is a plane, but soon I can see that it is coming closer and is shaped like a huge shining diamond, with the pointed end at the bottom. The object radiated bright yellow streaks of light all around, almost like a sparkler, but the light was not pulsating. It was at 01.03, the street lights had just been switched off, there were no stars or moon to be seen, it was completely windless with a few degrees of frost, the ground covered in snow. There was no sound, everything was completely silent. I managed to take a photo, but due to the darkness, long shutter time on the camera, and the speed of the object, which was faster than a plane, it was almost like a picture of lightning, a shame because it can't be used for anything, can it? It all lasted approx. 5 minutes, luckily I woke my wife up so she could see it too, otherwise she'd think I'd gone crazy. The object, when closest, was slightly larger than a clasped hand in an outstretched arm. I would think it flew between Ruds Vedby and Dianalund, it seemed to disappear beyond Brandstrup/Orebo/Vedde with direction approx. Holbæk. It would be fun to hear if others have seen the phenomenon. I think there is more between heaven and earth than we imagine.

Was at about 02:30 am aware of three objects in the western sky, which were moving at high speed between each other back and forth, and up and down in circles, figures of eight, and random patterns on a large part of the western sky. Thought for the first second that it might be light from show projectors, but quickly ruled it out (Who would turn something like that on on a Monday night anyway?). Have seen this kind of thing time and time again, and it looks completely different. Partly you can see the rays, partly it is limited how large a piece of the sky they cover, partly you see the light as misty blobs of a certain size, and partly the light is reflected against blobs of clouds. It doesn't disappear behind them like these did. It was about independently bright light sources - not reflected light. Airplanes, drones etc. can also be excluded, because it is not possible for something like that to move so quickly over such a large area. Besides, drones probably don't go higher than the clouds either. The observation was made by the undersigned and my son, whom I summoned. We observed it for approx. 45 minutes, however interrupted by the fact that at one point a plane passed in the area. During that time, the objects disappeared, only to return when it had passed. In between, the objects streaked rapidly due east, across the observation site, and were grounded out of our sight for a time, then returned after a moment and again traveled around as described in the western sky. Due to increasing cloud cover, we could at approx. 03:15 do not see them anymore, and therefore do not know if the phenomenon has continued any longer. The phenomenon did not repeat itself last night (8-8). Would love to hear if others have observed it and perhaps have a good explanation for it. I'm a bit skeptical about the little green men thing.
A small round object observed in some photos that primarily involved photography of so-called halo phenomena.

2 objects which fly across the sky independently of each other. They tilt a little at the disappearance. But they come back approx. 1 time per minute. Flashing lights came from one. They don't fly up, but across the sky. Several times it looks like they are chasing each other. Other times away from each other. Then they disappear and then they come back again. The size is hard to describe. But both look like a completely bright tube with enormous speed. Nothing resembling a plane or helicopter. It is completely dark, but they appear reasonably clear at a place that is slightly less dark on the horizon. They are definitely not planets. However, they both stand still for a while and float down the dark sky with enormous speed. I'm seeing it right now as I type. It has been approx. 15 minutes.

Was standing on the garden path and saw a bright light coming, thought it was a plane on. Often see this in the sky where I live. I remember being upset that I didn't have my mobile so I could see which plane it was, I have the app "Flightradar 24". I stood and watched the light, which grew sharper and immediately changed direction, continued straight up until I could hardly see it anymore and disappeared into the sky. There was no sound or flashing of any kind. Thought to myself it was a reverse shooting star.

At 23 I happened to look out of the window. In the far horizon I saw a plane coming, to the wife I said come and see. I have never seen a plane with such a powerful light. She suggested we go out. When we got out it was almost in front of us in the sky followed by more. There were 6 flying things in total. They moved at the same pace as an airplane, but completely silently. When No. 2 was ahead of us, No. 2 and No. 4 began to spin violently around themselves while still moving forward at the same pace. Both machines turned off their lights as they began to spin around, where I could make out a silhouette of the nearest machine. It was almost like holding up a deep plate; around and with something underneath. The light from the machines was very strong, just as the whole machine was in light and with a strength like a star. It sounds very incredible. If I heard it from others, I wouldn't believe it, but that's what I saw. I've never seen anything even remotely similar to this before. I didn't manage to take a photo, as I wasn't prepared for it at all.

I came walking with a friend who lives in Gug, I myself live 300 meters from where he lives, and we went for a walk to his house with a cigarette in hand. Suddenly we spotted a bright star and we both saw it. At first I thought it was a falling star... but suddenly it was moving upwards at an amazingly fast speed. And it disappeared into the horizon. We were both in shock. Can't forget what I saw, hence the late message. Been doing some reading on UFOs after seeing what I have seen. Looking at the sky every single night now.

My cat sat in the window and looked out. I saw that he was not sitting and looking down (at the arch-rival), but at the horizon and I stand next to him in the window. When I looked, there was a luminous ball the size of a 50 øre with strong speed. It stood still in the air for a few seconds and disappeared incredibly quickly. A bit like a giant comet. As the weather was very windy I couldn't get it to fit a white flare or anything that would risk flying out in that weather and not so low in the sky. Since then I have remembered that in the summer of 1997 a local farmer found a crop circle in that direction. There was something about it in the local paper. I normally live in the US and am not a big UFOist, but I saw a feature about SUFOI on the news on TV today and found your website.
A very fast light that flies quickly around the sky. It's not an airplane light, very mysterious light that disappeared suddenly....

My son came home from shooting and said there was some bright light over the field. I went outside and could see for myself a large, round luminous ball hanging in the air. I went back in and out 5-10 minutes later and it was still in the same place. after 20 min I went out again, and it had sort of drifted out into the woods and had lost some of its clarity, just like when something gets further away. And after approx. 45 min, it had disappeared. But it was round clear and bright for a long time, have pictures of it.

This morning at 06.13 my colleague and I saw something very strange in the sky. We drive as night guards in the home care, and when we are on our way to Tårs we experience the following: In front of the car at an angle of approx. 50 - 60 degrees suddenly an object comes into view, appearance similar in size to a handball. I experience a luminous ball in blue/green shades, with a small tail on the right side in luminous white colors, the luminous tail can be ½ to a full meter in length. My colleague, who sits on the right side of the car, experiences an orange glowing ball that is suddenly there and immediately disappears again - she does not think there is a "tail". We pull to the side to look around, it is dark everywhere, there are no lights in any houses over the fields, the sky is almost starry, there is a full moon, with a very thin transparent cloud layer. It's not fireworks, it certainly doesn't look like shooting stars that we so often see in the night watch, but what is it? Hoping someone might be able to give us an answer, that was a very interesting sighting.

From an older gentleman - KB - newly sadly deceased, I have this observation which is somewhat appalling. The observation dates from 1958. KB drives every evening on the same small road to get to a farm. KB has no idea what's wrong, as the car stalls. He now holds a watering hole on the left and open field on the right. A hedge runs from the water hole to the road. It is along this fence that KB now sees a very strong beam of light directed at the car. The light is white and pulsating. He notices that there is no sound to be heard. You have to remember, it's 1958, when at least a helicopter could be heard!! The point is close to Skrydstrup Airport, so an aircraft of some kind could not be unthinkable! The light moves along the fence as if it were a natural obstacle. It makes movements as if it is "searching". It stops in the middle of the road and moves over KB's car. It is now clear that it is a massive object of 25-30 meters in diameter. Not something I think you have in Skrydstrup! It is still completely still, and a few seconds later the object slides away with great speed. - To the south. The object is constantly 10-15 meters above the ground. The car starts again, KB rushes home to the farm and tells it. He was a very down-to-earth man who did not let himself be shaken, and was quite skeptical. But in the time after, he was clearly affected by the incident. He finds it very difficult to find words that can explain his experience, only when he hears the term UFO several days later is he himself convinced!!

Last night, July 21, 2014 at Around 2305 my husband and I experienced a strange phenomenon which you may be able to answer. Before bed we stood outside on our terrace and enjoyed the cool evening breeze. Suddenly two clear beams of light came at a vertical angle from the sky and shone where we were standing, it lasted for 3-4 seconds. We naturally looked up, but there was nothing to see or hear! Could it have been a shooting star or similar. It was a very strange experience.

As I drive to work as usual along the Holbæk motorway in an eastbound direction, on my way to work, I see a flash of light out of the windscreen. I can best describe it as a shooting star or the burning up of a small meteorite. A light with the power of a bright star suddenly appeared, continued like a small shooting star, but without a tail at first. This luminous moving object does not look like it is particularly high up, maybe a few kilometers. It "falls" obliquely downwards in an easterly direction, with a dip of perhaps 30-35 degrees in relation to the horizon. After 1-2 seconds it starts to burn up, like a New Year's rocket with a tail. It retains its size as a powerful star and brightness, which however diminishes as it "burns up" in the sky. After that, it disappears out of sight because it is no longer warm enough to be seen. The whole incident takes between 3-5 seconds and happens while I'm driving on the freeway. FYI the sky is cloudless, maybe only on the lowest part of the horizon and the moon is almost full in the opposite direction (west).

My grandson watched it out the window before school. Asked me what comet it might be. She had filmed it with her phone for approx. 1 min and called a friend who lives a few km away and she could confirm the direction and altitude looked the same.

Report: On the way home, my daughter wanted to take a picture of the beautiful sky. Just as she takes it, a bright "object" flies across the sky very quickly. It went so fast and there was nothing to see afterwards. After all, a plane can be seen as a victim over a long period of time. There were not so many clouds that they could cover the strong light afterwards. But she was lucky enough to have caught it in the picture. I have seen many planes/defense drills/shooting stars and NOTHING at all compares to the one in the picture.

Was standing looking out the window to the south when an object, with a green light flashing at a steady pace, suddenly appeared in the sky far out on the horizon. It moved very quickly far, from side to side, in very fast movements, after which, after a while, it suddenly went directly north, several km from where it was otherwise, after which it disappeared. It all happened very quickly. It seemed to be fairly high in the sky, like when I see an airplane. This one just moved a lot faster than I've seen before. airplanes do.

Come by car with the family. Saw a spherical object hovering at the entrance to the garden. Approx. 20 cm dm. bright yellow transparent for 20 seconds, disappeared into the garden to the east. Both my daughter and I watched it. Thought a lot about it then. Your article in BT on 6 August made me remember it again. Is it something you have heard of before?

Was out driving with a friend when I suddenly see 2 flying objects in a glowing orange color. We stop the car and start observing them. They fly slowly across the sky and eventually disappear by losing their color and being no longer visible. Temporarily we can see that 3 large objects reappear on the horizon. They follow the same route as the other two and disappear again in the same way. These are objects that neither I nor the other passers-by had ever seen before.

Standing with a friend looking up at the sky and then seeing an orange-red thing in the sky moving pretty fast towards us to start with. Then it appears to change direction and move in a horizontal line. Right away, it's as if something either falls off the ball or is shot out of it. It falls slowly in an arc to start with and then descends slowly. It happens 1 time, but the third time it shoots something out it doesn't take long, then the large object falls a little faster than the 3 small ball in an arc and then falls at the same pace as the ball no. 3 and then disappears. Very puzzled as to what it could be. It was moving faster than a plane ... After thinking about it for a bit, I got the idea that maybe it could have been a fighter plane, but after that the object must have collided with the third thing it shot out. I don't want to think it could be a fighter jet that shot out flares. We wondered right with me and my friend.

Me and my two daughters, aged 12 and 18 respectively, were out to catch a glimpse of the International Space Station ISS. On the way back, my youngest daughter observes a star-like object in the sky moving from south to due north, the object was too high up according to my observation to be a plane, and no twinkle from the object is seen. My guess would be that the object was level with the other stars in the night sky, but moving far too slowly to be a shooting star. The object moved at the same pace and in the same straight line during the entire observation from start to finish. My immediate guess would be that it might be a satellite?

My 10-year-old son was at a children's birthday party. The party took place indoors, but at one point he got hot and went outside, where he found a soccer ball, which he played against a wall. At one point the ball fell down the driveway and one of the other children ran down to retrieve it. She called him to come and see something strange: He describes what they saw as a craft that looked like something out of a Star Wars movie. It was green on the underside. A strange sound came from the vessel - he could not describe it - had never heard anything like it. The craft moved back and forth over the site as if searching for something - at one point it rose vertically into the sky and disappeared. Why do I believe the story? There were 2 of them who saw the incident. It was by chance that we came to talk about it - no sensationalism about the story. I asked him more about the blade as to whether it could be a plane or a helicopter or possibly a remote controlled UFO, but that is out of the question. Children's imagination - no, I don't think so here, the situation arose spontaneously and the whole story was played down as if it was nothing special. The children had merely noted what they saw and were not afraid.

Driving on the Hillerød motorway between Birkerød and Allerød towards Hillerød right at the start of the forest in the direction of Skævinge and Frederiksværk in the same direction as the road I see a strong light down over the sky straight down stopping a little way up due to clouds.

I was just going to check if it was starry (which it was) so I could look at the stars. But I saw something that looked like a satellite. It was just below Sirius at a speed of what a normal jet has, so I took my binoculars, which are 7*50, and looked a little closer at it. But I couldn't see anything as the light was too bright (I also tried with my telescope but couldn't catch it). I now noticed that it was starting to change course and speed. I know a fair amount about airplanes and I know it wasn't a landing light from an airplane. My thought that it was a satellite changed when the UFO began to slow down and stop once in a while. It then did that for a while, and then the light began to fade and finally disappear completely. As I am very interested in the subject, I immediately went to your website and wrote a report. I know it wasn't a comet because it flew too slowly for that, and a comet doesn't slow down and then stop for a while either. It can hardly be a laser or other kind of spotlight, because it was a Thursday evening. I have no scientific explanation for it.

I have talked to my parents several times about an experience out of the ordinary. Unfortunately, I have not had the pleasure of experiencing this myself, but since I could never imagine my parents telling lies, I have become extremely curious about this. I have searched for it on Google and found on your website an account of a similar phenomenon, however approx. 8-10 years earlier than my parents' account, which was in the late 70s. It concerns something they saw when they lived in Gråsten. They mention a green glowing object that flew across the sky at high speed (3-4 seconds) from the time they could see it until it was gone again. They explain it as flying from east to west, and the green light being the size of a round bale (so it appeared to them to be quite close - less than 500m). They describe it as being silent and fast. They mention that the next day it was in the newspapers that there had been intense UFO activity in the area - it could also be interesting to get your hands on these ads!? What I found on your website is below: Reports 1/4-30/6 2010 as 6300 Gråsten, but as said being approx. 8-10 years before my parents' experience. Thus, I am now very curious about whether you have other information or reports - or possibly a more detailed explanation of this phenomenon?

Saturday 7 August in the evening at 22.35, we sat with some friends on our terrace in Høje Tåstrup near Copenhagen. Best as we sat and talked about loose and firm, the undersigned noticed something, which I first thought was one of the usual planes on approach to Kastrup Airport. It was a bright light, like the landing lights of an airplane during take-off or approach, moving from northwest to southeast. I am a plane enthusiast, so I always keep a watchful eye when the planes come close above us. But suddenly I noticed another light behind the first object and thought it was strange that two planes on the same approach route were so close to each other. I then told the others at the table that there is something wrong here and everyone now looked up and saw the same thing as me. The objects moved quite slowly, almost like an aircraft on approach, but completely silent. The light grew brighter and brighter, and the objects drew closer to each other. When they were closest to us, one object began to pick up a bit of speed and went higher, while the other continued out on the horizon to the southeast and quickly disappeared. The other could be seen for a while as it quickly disappeared up into the sky. The objects were moving so slowly to begin with that we were able to pick up the camera and took a few photos that are not particularly good. But you can see the balls of light together in one photo. The second shows only one. We are very surprised that it was so local that others have not noticed them. The weather was a bit hazy, but the lights were apparently under the cloud cover. It wasn't ball lightning or shooting stars. Of course, we are not aware of what it was.

I stood on my mother's balcony and looked up in the sky to the south, also there were 6-7 brightly shining large balls flying from west to east. They were much larger than a star. When I first saw them they were flying in a line, but then they moved more unevenly, like more up and down. They flew medium-fast across the sky, they also almost disappeared into the sky.

I live in a house with a first floor, and it was on the first floor that I happened to look for an aviator. When I look out, I can see Herlev Hospital and in that direction I often see planes on approach to Kastrup. But there were three yellow lights and I thought three planes at the same time? Then it was that two of them moved up and down, while the thirtieth had a more straight direction. After the 5 min. was it gone.

I would estimate the size of the object to be about a golf ball. Speed like an airliner. No engine noise. After 5 min. repeated the episode. At first I thought it was a plane engulfed in flames. The witness has worked in aviation for over 40 years and has never seen anything like it, ruling out the possibility that it could be a plane.

A powerful white-blue orb increasing in brightness to almost blinding light flies slowly to the north. When it flies behind a tree it disappears and cannot be seen on the other side. I said it to my wife who saw the grand prix, it was just when Greece gave their points to dk that I stood in the door and saw the glowing ball. It was the size of a tennis ball at a distance of 10 metres. There was also a plane under it, it flew quietly approx. at half the speed of the ball, I could normally follow that after the tree. The plane had nothing to do with the ball, but the pilots could have seen the light, which appeared to be slightly behind the ball at first.

One evening when I was driving from Horsens north to Hovedgård with my father, we saw a light in the sky which was easy to see as it was dark. At first we thought it was a plane or a helicopter, but we decided to stop at a rest area to have a closer look. When we got out, we could see an almost triangular object 100-200 meters above us, which was illuminated along the sides. There was a faint noise - almost humming like from a vacuum cleaner. We agreed that there was no way this could be either a plane or a helicopter. The object remained suspended in the air for a few minutes, after which it slowly moved south.

At 23.45 I see a single luminous object coming from NW, thought it was a satellite, until a few minutes later I see two coming from the same direction, one of which crosses and comes a little on top of the other. Later I see a coming rising from n, which also suddenly disappears. A few minutes later, another one comes from nø and sends towards nw. At 7 when I wake up I see a single flying from nv which disappears quickly. A few seconds later, I suddenly see a cluster of 6-8 pieces, which disappear just as quickly as the first one. Shortly after they appear again, this time they come from all directions, but mostly from nv. Calling a friend who is a neighbor where I live and asking her to look out the window. She sees the same thing as me. Now they fly into each other, while approx. 2 from nø towards nw, but they continue the direction towards nw in steady motion. One or two look like they're flapping their wings like birds, but no matter which way they turn, I can see them all the time. Some come from n and seem to come from higher up than the others. At this point it looks like there are around 15-20 pieces. I usually see birds coming flying from about s, but when they get to where they are shining, I can no longer see them. At approx. At 7.30 they are completely gone. Saw on page 23 that it could be reminiscent of a bird phenomenon, but what surprises me is that I see it at 11.45 p.m., where a few disappear quickly, and again at 7-7.30. And that it was only on some that I could see wings and not others..... Degrees and direction are a guess, as I don't quite have a handle on it.

On 27.07.08 at At 01:50 I saw out of the corner of my eye that two stars were standing one above the other some distance below the right part of Pegasus, and my attention was momentarily taken away from Jupiter and its moons. I have a rough picture in my head of the starry sky and quickly agreed with myself that there should not be two bright stars nearly level with Vega in this location. I also ruled out planets, and as I pondered this and considered taking a photo, the two lights disappeared simultaneously for 15 seconds with erratic light variation, as if clouds were drifting in ahead, but there were no clouds in the sky. At this point it dawned on me with considerable hair-raising that these were neither stars nor satellites nor comets, but two UFOs. The lights were exactly vertically above each other at a distance corresponding to well over half the distance from Altair to Altair's nearest flanking star. The observation lasted approx. 2 minutes and the lights didn't move. It took over an hour to get the little hairs to lay down again, but maybe there is a down-to-earth explanation? Subsequently, I have come to the conclusion that the lights have been on for approx. in the position R 23h50m D 9 degrees 21 minutes corresponding to the star 80 Peg.

Drove from Slagelse in a westerly direction on Valbygårdsvej/Stillingevej in the evening. Light from a flying object caught our attention as it passed across our direction of travel. The unusual thing was that the object appeared to be completely triangular with 3 x 3 steady shining very bright white lights which clearly defined the "tips". Held to the side and stood out of the carriage. The object passed "over my head" relatively slowly and completely silently, although it appeared to be very large. Never seen or experienced anything like it before or since, and have been very reluctant to tell anyone else about the phenomenon - until I surfed past your site and read about the "Belgian phenomena" - although the lights here are different. Have evaluated all possible and impossible theories about what kind of aircraft it could be. The incident happened a few months before the start of the Gulf War (where the F-117 was introduced) and I remember wondering if it might have been such a model on "test flight" from a German base - but as I said the object was very large in the field of vision, flew slowly and at the same time was totally silent - and led the mentioned 9 permanently glowing "navigation" lights - so I personally have no doubt that it could not have been.

We were in a shelter looking for shooting stars, but saw a bright object moving in a straight line, just a little slower and much more powerful than a shooting star. It appeared to be at plane height, but the speed was faster than a plane. And the light stronger. After approx. 2 sec. it brightened even more and appeared three times larger, after which it regained strength as before. It continued its trajectory approx. another second and the light disappeared, but the object was still sensed, just without light. Couldn't be seen soon after.

Quote from my diary, written later that evening: "Sitting in the garden, I saw something strange in the sky - 4 'balls' moving from east to west completely parallel, no idea what it was." There was no more space in my little calendar diary, but with more space I could have written that my mother and I and the dog were sitting in the garden on a warm September evening. It was clear weather, and due to dense vegetation, our garden is shielded from street lights. The dog was sleeping, but suddenly he became restless, barked and seemed scared, got up and ran inside and hid under the table. My mom followed to find out what was wrong with the dog - and that's when I saw the 4 bullets. They glowed with a bluish fluorescent light, in the same way as embers in a fire that has been burning for a long time and is about to burn out - the fire in red colors, and these balls in blue. I cried out, but when my mother came back out, it was over. Have thought about it many times since - orbs, the strange light and the dog's behavior... Thought about it again when a few of your people were on TV recently.

During a short hour, we saw 10-12 objects at different distances.. It started when stars and planets appeared, when it was getting dark, we discovered a bright dot flying high up, too high up to it was a plane, and by the way no "tail", sound or blink.... Then thought it was a satellite - Meeeen, when it then changed direction - quite clearly, and soon after once more, had to it must be a spaceship high up.... While we are looking at it, one of the others who is watching says, oh, one more... And from due west to east comes one, very clear - bigger and clearer than the clear stars and planets, which are otherwise very large and clear - and again, NO sound, flashes or tail - it is, quite large, quite close compared to the first one and flies 3-4 times faster across the sky than airplanes normally do otherwise it does, and not at all as fast as a shooting star, which also comes and disappears quite quickly and briefly, this one we could follow in its "calm", but fast pace. It was fast and clear.... After that, in the course of 45 minutes, we saw 8-10 more, which were further out at different distances, and which also changed course one or more times.

When the object is observed, I first think it is a shooting star and tell my son to look, but a split second later I change my mind because the light is not white and the body is large, but dimly lit and with a red/ orange area in the middle. Therefore, I think it is a satellite, but the body moves very quickly of a satellite, so I wonder. When the body then a second later makes an unnaturally sharp turn at the violent speed that the body had, I have to give up. I often see shooting stars, airplanes and satellites. Had the body just flown in the same straight path, I would still have wondered what it was, but would not have written to you. But this body was either very large, or flew at a low altitude completely silently, so it was not powered by an internal combustion engine, at least not as we know it. It was a circular body, with a not very bright outline and with an orange-red center, which was approx. 1/4 of the diameter, and it wasn't particularly lit either. A shooting star or a satellite shines much more powerfully and clearly. The body did not blink, the lights were constant and dim. The movement of the body in the sky was unnatural. The speed was very high, approx. 45° in 3-4 sec. but the height was difficult to determine, so the speed cannot be immediately calculated. The body filled much more of the sky than an airplane, maybe like an airliner at an altitude of 2-3 km, but it was not an airplane. The shape was circular. The body makes a left turn about its direction of motion and crosses its own previous direction of flight at an angle of approx. 90° and disappears. I've seen cones of light make similar rapid movements in the sky before, and that would be my only natural explanation. But this was not a light cone, the body was actually very dimly lit and there was no light cone or light trail from the movement. The movement was so fast and the turn was made at a speed that cannot be made by an airplane, it is out of the question.

My name is X. I am 14 years old and from Koldingen. My best friend's name is Y. She lives on a farm in Z, with many fields around. We are often together, but the last time we were together, something quite unusual happened. We also often spend the night together, and in the summer we are used to lying out on the trampoline and sleeping. We have done that to both her and me. Then we cover the trampoline with blankets, blankets and pillows, and lie down looking at the stars and talking together until we fall asleep. It's summer vacation, and today is Monday 28 June 2010, and the last time we spent the night together was Saturday to Sunday 26-27. We had planned to sleep on the trampoline and we had taken her one dog out. The oldest of the dogs is a small faithful Danish-Swedish farm dog. And the youngest, a playful Labrador, was not allowed to go out. It was a full moon that night. When we were lying out on the trampoline, we talked about how it couldn't be right that our planet, Earth, was the only planet with life out of all the planets in the universe. Suddenly we both look to the right, where an object that is not an airplane is flying. It is round and square at the same time. It's sort of a square with very round edges, but still round on the sides. It looks a bit like a deep plate, with a flat plate on top. It has a green fluorescent tube all the way around the side, and some red fluorescent tubes at the bottom of the sides. It hums a strange sound, and lights up a lot. We quickly whip up a feeling that it's a UFO, because it couldn't possibly be an airplane, since it was flying too far down, and didn't have the same shape as an airplane, or anything we'd seen before for that matter. It must have been around 1 in the morning at that time. We were both pretty sure it was a UFO, and therefore wanted to take a picture of it with a mobile phone. But when we tried it and looked at the picture, we couldn't see the UFO in the picture. It flew away over/past the yard. We lie and talk about it, and behaves unusually, locking its gaze in the direction of the Moon, where the UFO came from. About 15-20 minutes later, Y suddenly says: "went out into the field"! AND I look out there. Out in the field I see two smaller objects, flying at a height of about 4 meters above the field, and they were quite a bit smaller than the first one. They are slightly more elongated and round, and do not have the same round square edges. They were more round and elongated, and they didn't have the same green light around the edge. Instead, they had three glowing red circles that glowed off each other. That is that they shone in turn. First the first one, and when it stopped blinking after one time, the next one took over, which blinked once, and finally it was the last one that blinked once. The light lasted for approximately 1 second at a time. Of the last two small UFOs, one was approximately 200 meters from us, and the other approximately 400-500 meters from us. They flew considerably lower than the first one. The first probably flew about 10-15 meters above the ground. They all came from the direction of the moon. The last two flew, they began to fly lower and lower towards the field and we were afraid that they would land, but when they were about 1.5-2 meters above the field, they did not fly up obliquely, but directly up in the air about 4 meters, and then straight again, and disappeared behind the yard. We were really scared because we were convinced that it didn't look like anything we'd seen before, or anything man-made. When it had disappeared over the yard, there must have been 3 bangs in a way. They cannot be described as bangs, but more like horses galloping over the cobblestones. We then ran inside because we felt unsafe. It was around 1.30 in the night at that time. When we ran in, the dogs got quite nervous and bleated and barked. We woke up her mother, who got up and looked out the door, where one of the dogs ran out. It ran to the opening into the courtyard, from which came a bright light. It was difficult to get it back in, but we succeeded in the end. Carried the little dog in her arms, and it was very afraid. We ended up having to sleep inside.

My girlfriend is out on our terrace and she comes in and wakes me up. She tells that there is something I have to see. We go out and she points up in the air. There we can see a very powerful yellow/orange object flying slowly and steadily from southwest to northeast over Næstved town. Further out on the horizon we can see two more objects of the same color and speed coming towards us. As the objects pass us, I can make out a very irregular flash behind the strong light. There is no sound at all. It is difficult to assume how high they have flown. It seems at first glance that they are the same height judging by their sizes. In addition, they fly under the cloud layer that is valid at the time. The speed is estimated to be the same as in a single-engine propeller machine. Unfortunately, we do not have the best view in the direction in which they disappear, as our terrace is covered.

Best as we sat and watched "Wild with dance", I sat back on my sofa, and suddenly I observed through a window on the other side of the living room a bright reddish light in the sky behind the trees. I went out on the terrace to observe the phenomenon and then saw that it was followed by 2 similar objects of the same brightness. If one can talk about extent or shape, it must be roughly said to be more horizontally oval than circular. It is difficult to describe when it emits such a powerful light. I called to my wife of 48 years and daughter of 11 years, and together we stood and observed the 3 brightly shining phenomena that came in from the Baltic Sea due east, and straight ahead they all made a 70 degree turn in the same curve to the south. After that they continued until they disappeared behind trees or the horizon if you will. The speed is difficult to estimate, but the height is assumed to be 500 meters max. Speed 3-4 times that of a regular private plane. I myself have flown OY-RPU, a 4-seater Piper Cherokee, so I think the assessment of altitude and speed is very safe. There was no sound or any kind of audible movement. Where we live is "dead quiet", as it is a summer house area (Marielyst centre) with very few permanent residents. All 3 objects had the same curve and brightness, and the direction was not affected by gravity, which is why they must have had their own power for determining speed and direction. The velocity appears constant and linear from the east. Unfortunately I didn't get to take pictures, but expect to be able to read about it in the local paper tomorrow, as several people must have seen the same sighting.

Sitting on the balcony, enjoying the silence and the clear weather, when from the southwest comes a very bright luminous, for me to see around object The object is silent, flies in a straight horizontal line to the North/North/East, the distance is difficult to judge, I probably between 1-5 km.
