The observation takes approx. 3 sec, I follow the object, suddenly it turns off and an electrical/metallic sound occurs.

Standing at the quay, Enghave Brygge Kbh. And tells a colleague about Orion. Looking with my binoculars navy 9x63 field 6.2" at the nebula under Orion's belt, where suddenly 2 light yellow "stars/satellites" appear in front - very far away. They fly close together, but cross in the flight I see. I only see them for a few seconds. But I have no doubts. It could be air traffic to Kastrup, or satellite. They flew very fast, and I made it clear to my colleague that it was a UFO.

I saw three fast flying objects on 01.11.22 at 19:37. They streaked across the sky at a low altitude (a few hundred meters directly above me), with a faintly luminous outline (a bit like a window shape) without making a sound. The objects had a considerable size, and were probably approximately 20-40 meters diagonally. I watched them cross the arc of the sky from horizon to horizon above me. I only looked up when a passenger plane came flying from south-east to north-west, and by the way it was a beautiful and very starry evening. The objects crossed the path of the airliner from southeast to northwest (the plane was coming from south to north). I was standing in the garden by my gate, which I had just closed, but the surveillance camera only recorded my reaction in the seconds after the objects passed (which is a bit unusual, since the camera often starts as soon as it sees movement). It was fun! Not creepy or scary, just weird. Wildly strange. That something big can move so fast, fly so low and be silent is incomprehensible. In addition, one of the three objects drastically changed formation in an almost zig-zag turn in front of the other two, just as they passed over me. My very first thought was fighter jets as they came fast, low and in formation. But there was absolutely NO sound when they had passed... That was the strangest thing about the experience. I have worked approx. 3.5 years as an engineer in the air force (2016-2019, transport and inspection aircraft), but never heard of or seen anything like it. I immediately looked at Flightradar24, but only saw the airliner on the radar display. It was only in the area around Frederikssund. Do you have other reports from the same short period of time?

Just had to vent, as I look down towards the water approx. 700 meters from where I live. Here I see a strong red light hovering over the field, I think approx. about 1,500 meters up. It comes from the north and goes south. Grabs my phone but when I go to record it's gone. Kind of spins around. Expect more bright white lights today around 5pm. Could also see a ship over by Ærø, maybe they have seen something.

I made a report to you on 6 February 21. My current report is about the exact same thing! At the time of writing I see the same flying object in the pitch black and cloudless sky. The scenario is completely identical to my observation on February 6: At first glance, the object looks like the Star of Bethlehem, as we know it from movies and stories. Big, clear and sparkling. The difference between the Star of Bethlehem and the object I see is that the object moves slowly and in a straight and horizontal line from west to north/northeast. Sometimes the object stops and stands still, after which it moves a little up and down, and flies back a little. I can't judge how far away the object is - or how fast it's flying? However, I can report that the object has moved a full arm's length in 1 hour. The object has a very clear and strong white color which occasionally changes (flashes) to cobalt blue. Unfortunately, I do not have the right equipment to record my observations (my I-phone cannot focus so sharply. I have tried, both with video and pictures. If you have the opportunity and if you are interested in seeing it repeatedly phenomenon, please contact me by email. The object is clearly visible every late evening from 11:30 p.m. to 2:30 a.m. in the same orbit and on the same course. I am quite aware that airplanes and satellites can sometimes be observed far, far up in the night sky , but neither planes nor the satellites move up and down, or back and forth. So I am convinced that it is something completely different (but what??) Finally, it should be mentioned that the observations were made by 2 - sometimes 3 people. So I'm not crazy.

Saturday evening, 9 grC. Mild, dry weather no stars. At 21.39 (Immediately before the final X-factor voting). I'm sitting in my living room watching TV when out of the living room window I see what I assume is a parachute flare or flare. Just tonight our curtains are not drawn for what they usually are. The light comes from a westerly direction and appears to be rising from behind a small group of trees, approx. 250 meters from our house. I wonder, however, that the light seems to narrow our house, and not rise vertically. The object appears to be nearly round, bright orange in the center, without any precise demarcation of the edges. The edges were placidly flickering like a flame. I get up and open the patio door in the living room to listen, but hear nothing. The family, my wife and 2 daughters, come to see the object as well. They don't hear anything either. I ask them to get a camera, which they don't understand. However, my youngest daughter takes a picture with her phone from the west side of our house, towards the church, north. At that point the object is north of us, and I estimate that it is no more than 50 - 70 meters up, although very uncertain, just as the size is difficult to judge. From when we observe it until it reaches the northern point, where it passes the longitude of our house, it takes a little over 1 minute. Since I can no longer see it from our west-facing terrace, I go out on the east side of our house and see that the object continues to the east. I think that my parents, who live in Ulkebøl (approx. 7 km as the crow flies), must lie on the line that the object follows. I call and ask them to go out to see if they can observe the object, but they see nothing. Approx. 4 minutes after the object appeared, it disappeared out of the field of vision, following the described line. The movement was very constant, and not accelerating, and completely silent. The likeness of a very slowly horizontally moving flare, which however did not change height.
3 people see it, my brother, my mother and myself.

On my walk at approx. 20.40 I saw a bright light in the SW - I couldn't follow it due to trees and buildings - later I saw it disappear in the NE. At 21:00 I then saw it again coming from the SW and moving towards the NE, where it disappeared. It was still bright and the light from the object was very clear in the sky. This time I could follow it all the way. It moved at a constant speed like a slow-moving airplane. It was a bright white light - reminiscent of a searchlight, and it was sharp from all sides. It was completely silent. I would estimate the height to be 1-2 km, but it is difficult to judge as I could not estimate the size of the object.

Observation at 19.40 DST. Whether the lights are double triangles, as can be seen on film, I have subsequently become unsure, as I can see that the triangles are only visible when the camera can't figure out how to focus. But I have not been able to reproduce this effect. I have no idea what it was we saw. There was no sound about it, so if they were planes, they must have been very high up. If it was a plane, then the light might be reflections from the sun, since it is not that long after sunset. And the sun might well be shining on planes that were a few kilometers up. However, the size of the lights was so large that I somewhat doubt this. The video camera is a Panasonic NV-GC280, which has a 3.0-30 mm Leica optic. (This corresponds to an SLR with 42-430mm optics). I would very much like to clarify what it was we saw.

Lying on the sofa and through the window to the south high above our roof, 4 blue lights came on in a row, which were very powerful, but not blinding and disappeared over the house in a split second. Never seen that kind of light. Went out to the front door to the north and it was gone. No sound, engine noise or the like from airplanes or helicopters, completely silent.
Standing and watching the sky, a plane came. Suddenly an orange light came at high speed without a single sound. Soon 3 more came at the same distance still without a sound. Don't know what we saw.

Standing out in our garden and looking vertically up. Sees a planet, looks down again and thinks, whoa, there are no planets at 90 degrees in the night sky. Looking up again and the light is gone. My thoughts fall on the Chinese rocket, supernova, gamma ray burst, drone or satellite. I have goosebumps. But there is, as always, a natural explanation.

I stood outside on my roof terrace and looked up at the starry sky. Then I saw what looked like a jet fighter formation. One in front and then several spread out in a V-formation. It was yellow light and no sound, and it flew across the sky 2-3 times faster than a jet fighter formation would/could do. It was a beautiful sight and I have no idea what I saw.

Two bright lights moved quickly, approx. 30 seconds, from SSV towards E, where they were lost sight of. More powerful than ISS and Venus, but not like the strongest Iridium flares. The color was more orange than a normal. satellite - much like sodium lamps. The (angular) velocity also seemed higher than ISS, but I have no idea of the absolute height or distance.

I'm out for a smoke, and always look up for satellites and possibly shooting star. Spots first something that looks like a nice shooting star, but as it passes across the sky, there are 3 luminous objects moving at different speeds in a 3-edged formation. Never seen anything like it......... Shut up......
Our camera picked up two luminous objects, which in my eyes are inexplicable. I am sending the video surveillance footage to the webmaster here, which I see is referenced.
Discovered it when I got home and put the picture on my PC.

Out of my roof window and under a starry sky, a zig-zag rapidly moving semi-luminous object is suddenly seen moving across the night sky from east to west after two past meteors and a satellite have just passed in the ten minutes before. Observed initially at 90 degrees and possibly only 1 km over land. The speed seems to change in displacements and the direction is continuously changed in small degrees several times, until either the distance itself or the given deviation from the sun's light diminishes its marking on the night sky, and then in a 20-25gr. above the horizon clearly changes course during an angular angled maneuver and moves north several/many kilometers west of Horsens. In any case, the object could not be compared to ordinary celestial phenomena and also seems to have several smaller light sources (as it now appeared at the uncertain distance/height). Seen something similar twice before in my life but never reported. Thinking it's important we remember to write them down so we don't go and brush them off like it didn't happen.

I'm lying in my bed and can't calm down because of the heat. The time is 00:16. All of a sudden, out of the upper window (slatted windows) I spot the "object", which has a slow gliding movement across the sky. I (Michael) jump out of bed and tumble into a metal suitcase, it makes noise, so my girlfriend wakes up. Together we observe through the window (which I open) the following: a very clear, yet dim light, pointing down, but not like a beam of light, the light moves west above, and (as Lotte formulated it) at one point strikes a small sparkly! I see it as a tiny thin line going from the bottom edge of the light with a small lump at the front end, this can be seen approx. 1/2 sec., the object is now somewhat far to our left. Immediately after, the light starts to dim and light up a bit two or three times, after which I can no longer see it, but I should be able to, as the object still couldn't be that far away. After discussing the experience and turning and turning it in my head, I am 100% sure that the light we have seen has been at the bottom of something!, meaning downwards. We believe that the distance approx. fits with the object having flown over Randers Fjord. A little after 00:32 a plane came in a north-easterly direction (presumably a passenger plane), its height we guess is approx. twice the speed of the object and approx. twice that of the object. I've seen the raw amount of shooting stars, planes and satellites before, this was definitely not it. Finally, I would just like to say that here, where we live, there is not a sound to be heard in the evening/night, nor was there in connection with the observation.

I saw what I first thought was a satellite. I then spotted 3 other "satellites" flying at the same speed in a semi-circle, one of them looked like an airplane, you see far away from "white light, red flashes". When it reached over in the northeast direction, it stays in the same place in the sky. When I look again 10 minutes later it is still in the same place.

Driving east on Brandevej, where an object comes at very high speed across the sky from south to north, but my view is blocked by trees after a few seconds. The object glows green and red either in front or behind, but it flies so fast that I can't remember if the red is in front or behind. I stop the car and get out, but can't see, hear or smell anything! The object appeared to be pretty far down, probably about 20-25 degrees above the horizon.

My husband and I were on our way home by car from a lovely Christmas Eve with children and grandchildren, when we saw a flying "thingest" just around the hospital in Ringstedgade. It was rather large and almost elliptical in shape, with a very strong golden light, which in the middle was a sea of light and at the end something that flashed. The sky was overcast, it couldn't possibly be a plane. It flew very slowly and low. For information, the hospital is on 14 floors, and it was not much above this height that it flew. Suddenly, after a very short time, it was gone. The time was approx. 23.40 when we saw the flying thing.

I saw 5 white lights shaped like a boomerang out my bedroom window, the front one flashing and completely silent (usually when planes or helicopters come over the house I can hear them clearly). Saw it/it in a northwesterly direction and disappeared over the house. Went into the living room to see if I could see it coming across the house but there was nothing, waited for 2-3 minutes.

Very fast moving continuous light at flight level. At about. 75 degrees on the horizon, it lit up strongly for 2 seconds, then flared down again and disappeared shortly after (5 seconds later). No engine noise from the light and it was a quiet evening so should have been heard. 2 minutes later, a plane came from the west, towards the east. A distinct motor noise was heard. Light moved at 3-4 times the speed of commercial aircraft and in a straight line. Too low and bright to be a satellite and far too slow to be a shooting star.

There are three of us who drive towards Aalborg early in the morning. We drive along the road from Lillevorde towards Klarup just before Rumdrup and just before the road to the left towards Gistrup. We see further ahead (approx. 1 km) a very large strong bluish/turquoise-like light for 2 seconds. It goes out, but after approx. 4 sec. is there again for 2 sec, it seems like it is right at the surface of the ground. It looks like a half sun or half moon, and because the light is so strong, it shines a lot in the dark. We ask each other what it could be, but we don't know. We drive but do not see the light again nor anything it could have come from. There wasn't a house with lights in it or anything else that could explain this. The stretch is out in the country and it is very slippery as there is ice on the road so we drive carefully. We soon turn left onto a country road towards Gistrup, where we let another car turn first, as he comes from the road we are going to turn onto.

The night between Tuesday and Wednesday I sat and watched x-files (Strengt Fortroligt) on TV2 in my summer house on Sydfalster. Suddenly I felt that there was someone outside on the terrace. So I went out to see what it was and if there was anything at all. When I got out I looked around as I thought there was someone walking around out there. As a reflex, I looked up at the sky. There were a lot of white dots circling the round as the object moved back and forth between my summer house and the neighbor's. The dots formed some rings, and I think the inner one had 4 rings, then 8 and finally 16. And since it was moving at 70-90 degrees, it must be right above my head, and it looked like the object was very low in the air. But you couldn't hear anything, it was completely silent. At first I couldn't believe my eyes, I went straight in for 30 seconds and when I came out it was still there. So I ran in and woke up my mother as she could be used as a witness. When I dragged her out, she saw it too and was very surprised by it. I happened to have my digital camera with me, so I ran out and took some pictures, but they didn't seem to materialize. But I haven't deleted them. After a while I got tired of looking at it so I went to bed and so did my mom so we don't really know how long it's been there but 30 minutes minimum.

I was awakened by a bluish strong light coming in from my bedroom window. It fell on my bed and pillow. At first I thought it was the full moon or similar, but at the same time it was far too strong. When I look out and up at the sky (I have "skysight"), I see against the dark sky something that appears to be round and with blue and red lights in 2 rows placed on top of each other. It hovered right in front of my house, but higher, and it quickly disappeared again behind the next ridge. After a second or two "it" came back and hovered over the roof of the "Family School" right here next to my building for a 3 - 8 seconds. It had blue and red big lights on the sides. A row of red and a row of blue. As it flew away there was a very quiet deep hum!! But not mechanically. WHAT WAS IT?? Today I spoke to a DRONE specialist over the phone, as many of my friends have suggested it could be a Drone. He said it MIGHT have been a drone. However, he doesn't know about the red and blue lights that I described AND he said that Drones are generally noisy!! The one I saw was practically silent. So he thought it was either a "cumstom made" Drone or a real UFO. Furthermore, he said, it was forbidden to fly inside the city like that without special permission, and he could not recognize the location or the colors of the lights I saw at all. He also said that Drones in general make a LOT of noise..... this one just made a low humming VUISHHH right before it disappeared again. Strange experience.

At approx. 22.25 we see a large flying object flying around. At first it looks like a star, and then we think it's a satellite. But it moves far too slowly and was very close to the ground. Next it flies around so we could see it from the other side of the house. After the approx. 10 minutes it is indistinct and then it is gone. There was no sound and no color change, it was just incredibly bright and looked bigger in the sky than an ordinary star.

Sees plane/bird-like object flying in and out of a cloud, the size of twice an F16....it makes sharp maneuvers and without sound and jet trails....the wing shape is a bit like an eagle, but it is too big and fast until it could be an eagle and the speed is also too high....after this aerial acrobatics, the objects suddenly start moving in a southwesterly direction just below the clouds at high speed....slightly faster than an F16 plane.... the object appears brownish and without reflections from the sun.

Lying in my bed where I have a view of the water. I was about to roll down the curtain when I saw a light flying horizontally across the sky. The light alternately disappeared and shone a strong white color. I called my girlfriend and she just managed to see it flash a few times before it stopped flashing and we couldn't follow it anymore. It stopped in the middle of the sky, and there was nothing to block the view. I sat and looked for a few minutes, but it did not appear again. I had the window down and couldn't hear any engine noises.

At 10 pm I was on my way in through the front door when I look over my shoulder. Over the neighbor's house in a northerly direction, I see a large UFO hovering over the neighbor's house. Moves from side to side and suddenly disappears in a northerly direction. Sounds a bit like a morse code. The thing was completely red and had blue glowing dots, and was completely round. Much bigger than the house.

Flying object observed by red flashes. Fast four-five blinks at a time, about a second apart. At times the flash would disappear for minutes, only to reappear elsewhere in the night sky. The object flew in arcs, but the direction and shape of the arcs varied. The object also appeared to have varying speeds. As it turned out (completely without reasonable distance judgement) the object flew quite fast at times. It was definitely neither a plane nor a helicopter, and my best guess is that it was a drone. I tried to film, but the resolution of my phone could not capture the flash.

I was out walking with a dog I look after once in a while. Just as I look up, my eyes catch 5 flying objects. They are not bigger than the stars and fly in the same direction, of which two of them are almost dancing/playing (they fly crosswise).. after 5 sec they are gone at the same time.. I stood with my mouth open and said "wow, wow, wow“... amazing :)

Driving south along the water, on the northern edge of Køge city, we suddenly saw an object fall, at a relatively high speed and disappear below the horizon. It fell in a straight line, heading south, a good distance away from us. From when we first observed it and until it had disappeared below the horizontal line, about five or seven seconds passed. The object itself was dark, and not identifiable, but it had a greenish light, almost like a lantern on a ship (it shone very brightly, not like the meteors, in the pictures we have tried to compare what we saw with) in what can be called the front end, and behind it was a yellowish-orange-greenish "flame" light (like from a jet engine). This latter appeared when we saw the object, disappeared briefly, appeared again, then disappeared completely before the object disappeared. Our first impression was that it was a passenger plane coming down. And it really still is, since we can't find an explanation for what else it could be. We are writing, as it were, to ask if something similar has been observed, by radars, satellites or the like. equipment. Possibly. military, perhaps? Or if maybe a plane HAS crashed?!? Although there has been nothing about it in the news until now.

The light phenomenon was seen 10 - 20 times from 0 to 30 degrees above the horizon. A relatively large part of the sky was illuminated. The light was sometimes strobe-like. The light fluttered randomly across the sky, like when children play with a stick lantern and light it up in the air. But the luminance was perhaps 100,000 times stronger here. My thought was: Could it come from a very powerful projector (laser light?). Because it's hardly the Northern Lights when it comes from the south, right? It should be noted that it was dark and cloudy.

Immediately light as aircraft on approach, but slowly and completely silently. Disappeared to the north, quite low, as stated approx. 45 degrees above horizons. We thought satellite, but the orbit much closer to the earth compared to the ones we occasionally see.

Three round/oval lights move relatively quickly in an arc, maybe a total of 10 degrees. The three lights "hang together"/follow each other in the same constellation. At first thought it was the lights from a plane turning into "smudged" lights due to clouds, but the speed is too high (I think) and the cloud cover is not even/dense enough for the three round lights to be able to "keep the same shape". The "leaky" cloud cover also excludes light from the ground.

My wife and I sat on the terrace and talked. Suddenly she asks what is behind me. Here I see 4 objects floating in the clear blue sky. The sun is behind me, so there is clear visibility. 3 of the objects are uninteresting, they are about 600 meters above me and it is clear, they are some kind of white plastic bags floating with the wind (from the east). They move erratically and randomly. The last object was immediately more interesting. It was significantly further up and was moving slowly but surely to the east, i.e. opposite the "bags". The shape was difficult to judge, but I observe it is in rotation on its own axis, based on the reflection it made at regular intervals. We observe the objects for 5 minutes, during which I think of finding my binoculars. I'm gone for a minute max and come back and can no longer see the last object. Looking with binoculars around where it was, I pick up a small dark object speeding towards the west... I don't think it was the same object though, and it probably looked more like a bird... but a very busy bird. Looking through the binoculars I could clearly see that the white bags were plastic of some form. They still hover over Randers at a height of approx. 500 meters.

I'm sitting at home in my mother's house smoking in the garage, at Is 01:00 at night. Suddenly 40 degrees northeast in the sky, I see a half round black circle with a tip on the top, behind which there are two lights, both of which glow a red yellowish color, I can't see the bottom of it, but the top appears as a half circle with a point on top. I have never seen anything like it, it was too big to be a plane, nor was there the sound of a plane, but if you saw a plane from behind with the tail rudder and then without wings. It looked like the one where there was a light on either side of the tail rudder. But as big as it was, it couldn't have been a plane, because if it had been that close, it would have made a lot of noise.

I looked up and saw the object almost directly above our heads heading east. It was silver, shaped like a ship's propeller, and moved roughly with the wind. We have an agreement to film immediately, we see something suspicious and I took out my mobile. Unfortunately, before I had fumbled for the mobile phone, the object was already so far away and high up that it could hardly be seen with the naked eye, and I only caught a brief glimpse on the video. If you look closely, however, you can see the object glinting silvery. What was special about the object was its shape and its movement. I would almost liken the movement to if you rotate an oblong piece of narrow paper and drop it. Then it will also rotate around the longitudinal direction as it falls towards the ground. We have discussed whether it was a special type of helium balloon. However, it would then be a very fast-moving balloon, as in the course of 40 seconds it moved from above our heads, to away in the horizon at a height approximately 3 times the starting height. But again. Nothing can be rejected.
A faintly luminous object appeared to the east and flew across the sky to the west. It wasn't an airplane because there was no sound. Disappeared after approx. 5 minutes in the clouds.

On my way to work at 06.13. Cycles on the cycle path between Vojens and Haderslev, more specifically between the villages of Styding and Hammelev. It is very dark, yet starry. Suddenly, a bright light comes from behind - I think it's a truck on the road, driving with its floodlights on. However, there is not a sound, and there is no truck either. Then see an orange-red ball coming slightly obliquely from behind my right side (southwest) fly straight above me and then disappear over the bushes/trees standing on my left side (northeast). There is no sound - no bright lights - no tail, just the ball. The sight lasts max. 3 sec, because when I get clear of the bushes (about 15 sec later), there is nothing to see. One min. later comes an oncoming cyclist who stops me and asks if I saw the very bright light in the sky - must answer that I only got the bright light from behind and that I saw a red-orange ball fly over. He hasn't seen the bullet. We agree that it must be a UFO and that it wasn't even that high up - I want to immediately shoot at 400 meters up and the size difficult to judge - but as it flies over? Outstretched arm - the size of a 2 crown. The moon was larger and the stars much smaller. It was not something from the air station - I and the oncoming cyclist agree on that.
Experienced a strange light in the sky. It moved in different directions in the sky, was very clear in a warm, almost glowing, color. Suddenly it disappeared. Have pictures.

Have seen the same incident two days apart. Three objects that lie on a horizontal line with roughly the same distance from each other. At first thought they were stars, but discovered they were moving. They are at the height of scheduled aircraft or higher. There is a flight corridor from north-east to south-west, and there were several scheduled flights in the same period, but how long does it take the scheduled flights approx. 5 minutes from when they come into view to when they are gone, then it took the objects 30-45 minutes to cover the same distance. They can't be helicopters as they were very high in the sky and they didn't make a sound. They disappeared into the horizon when they became so small that you could no longer follow them. There were not the normal flashing lights that are on airplanes, but more changing from white to blue.

Me and a buddy are taken to the woods on a hilltop that's out here where we live to look at a meteor shower. I choose to share this observation, as on 11/10-2020 I also saw something inexplicable in the sky. I have also made an observation sheet on this incident. In connection with looking at the Starlink train, I looked up directly above me and saw three white lights forming a triangular shape slowly rotating counter-clockwise. The three lights followed the rotation accordingly. It was silent and filled about half of what the Pleiades see. Floated slowly to the east and disappeared.

Myself and a friend have just observed 7-8 very fast moving green spots in the sky above Copenhagen. They moved in higher air layers than the clouds, and in comparison with airplanes that had to land in Copenhagen, at a much higher speed. The first four followed in a column, and the last followed one by one at 5-10 second intervals. We observed it around 00:20 and it lasted for about 1-2 minutes - i.e. their passage of the night sky.

The object was black, without visible wings and as wide at both ends. It moved very slowly towards/over Roskilde, lower than a usual aircraft. We were driving in a car and could have watched it forever, if we had time. The picture looks rather bad and is not as representative.

Standing out on my terrace and looking up at the sky. At first think it's a star, but it comes at very high speed, no sound, no flashing/electricity. rear smoke screen like on an airplane. See it out on the horizon, coming from Fåborg and over Kværndrup and continuing east. The whole thing only takes approx. 1-2 min. Since I often watch planes in the evening, I know approximately how long it takes them to fly over here, hence my wonder at this phenomenon, which I have never seen before. It was probably the speed that surprised me the most, because it went very fast. Don't know if it's something, but won't fail to pass it on. Maybe you can give me an explanation.

properties.Colors: hvid koldt lys, men mindre blålig halo
properties.content: I get up that morning to see the plants lined up and have a nice view of them. But then my eye catches the white light moving from the direction of 190 degrees, with an estimated heading of 70 degrees (compass). The light is approx. 5 times larger than Venus and has bright cold white light with a bluish halo. I assume it first for a cargo plane that is waiting to land in Billund or Karup. It looks like airplanes with landing lights on too early. But then after approx. 15 seconds, accelerate it to an estimated 5 times faster than before in approx. Two seconds. Now it has my attention. After approx. 5 seconds it makes a tight 180 degree turn and immediately after the turn down to the same speed. The light is still the same intense white light. What puzzles me besides the abrupt speed changes. It now flies approx. heading 220 degrees for approx. 15 seconds, where it again makes a sharp 170 degrees. After the turn, it is quiet for approx. 20 seconds and now it moves up to me 45 degrees, estimated direction 150 degrees heading. Suddenly it accelerates upwards, becomes smaller and smaller until it disappears as a tiny dot. It changes shape at no time. It didn't change color or intensity. It was totally silent. How high up it was, or how far away it was, is impossible to estimate. Have been wondering for a long time what it was?? Do you have a reasonable explanation for that? If it had been passenger/cargo aircraft with landing lights on, I wouldn't have been able to see them when dt turned 180 degrees, then I would have been able to see navigation lights, nothing, just the spherical cold white light with the blue halo. The halo, I estimate, is height reflections in ice crystals in the air. If it had been so high up that it was light from the Sun, but there was 45 min. to sunrise, then the light would not have been as bright, and the light would probably have been more reddish. At this time of day, there are city sounds again. I strained to hear if there was any engine noise, nothing, totally silent.

I had the most bizarre experience last Thursday. It was a clear evening and the stars were clear, so I sat and watched the beautiful view from the kitchen window, sitting on the kitchen table with the window open. I had been sitting there for approx. 5 min., when my eyes caught a strange sight. I saw a black "plane" glide by quietly. It was black/coke gray and had a cloud or fog/smoke around it, like a cover, but still transparent, so you could see through the fog, but you couldn't pick up the structure of the "plane" on the surface. It was almost a triangle and a square put together, it also had 6 black circles under it. (I only saw it from below). There was no light in it and it was completely silent. It was very close and yet quite a way up, I'm a lousy judge of distances, but I stayed on the 4th floor in Sionsgade in the window facing Sions Church (which is the top floor in this rise). In the same yard behind there is a 14-storey high-rise building, it was approx. at that height. I am very interested to hear from others who have seen something similar or witnessed this experience themselves as I cannot find any other similar accounts. I've checked everything, drones, spy planes, UFOs, etc... nothing like that is described anywhere.

We are two friends who love stargazing through my telescope, and one day when we got it up, the Moon wasn't there anyway - we had planned to look closer. So we sat down on two chairs where the backs could be laid back. We first saw one or two shooting stars. My friend asked if we should go in and get some chips and soda - we did. I pointed and after a while he spotted it. The yellow lights had no tail behind them, thus "shooting stars" are excluded. We have seen satellites in the night sky before, and they were far from the satellites we were looking at now. We both asked each other if it could be a UFO. One flew out of the triangle formation and behind the other two so that they were now flying in a straight line. A few seconds later, the rear one flew the opposite way and continued away - it ended up being a small dot that then disappeared. We wanted to try to take pictures of it, but unfortunately you couldn't see it in the pictures - we only had phone cameras.

Observes a bright white light coming from the west and expects engine sound afterwards, as Tirstrup airport is relatively close, but the sound does not come, and there are no red/green/white flashes, as you normally see on planes. The object is not a satellite as it flies too slowly and is not part of the night sky, but closer to the earth than the sky. It glides silently to the east and clear observation is approx. 5 sec. Continues behind tree crown and can be seen behind branches.
Luminous object observed in the sky. It flashed blue, green, red, white. The object moved up, down and sideways. But otherwise it was just as quiet. It was with 100% guarantee NOT an airplane.

I was driving from Søllested towards Nakskov on route 291, and saw, immediately after I had come off the roundabout, a strong orange light to the west. The light initially appeared to be stationary, but as I moved, I sensed that the light source must be further away and higher up than a floodlight or similar. At one point I pulled over to the side and got out of the car to make sure there were no reflections in the car window. At the end of the observation, the light had become weaker and came a little closer to the horizon, it seemed as if the light had moved away from me in a straight line. I could not see any marker lights and there are no regular flight paths at the observation site.

I would like to tell you about an observation that took place way back in January 1975. A very close family member saw the following in the sky in the evening, at approx. 10 p.m. She had previously called you (we kept your magazine) and was told that there was "a lot of activity in the sky". the second, the shape was rounded at the bottom, and on top was like a dome, divided into panes/windows. They were high up. There was exhaust coming from the objects. They kind of came "out of the blue". They flew quickly over a distance and the family member described that it looked like "the sky opened" and the two objects flew in and were engulfed. The family member (obviously) never forgot this incredible sight. I can't imagine there is a natural explanation for this. It must have been 2 UFOs. I hope my account will be included in the sighting chart. At the same time, I also want to mention that the family member and I, also in the 1970s, saw another thing, a large red light that moved jerkily, without a sound and flew from right to left i.e. horizontally I would very much like to ask for an explanation. I think it will be very difficult to find a natural explanation for the 2 objects and also the big red light (NOT a plane or helicopter and not a star or planet at all). It is a fact that lots of people have seen UFOs over time. Items where you just have to say that there is no other explanation.

I go out with garbage, and look up at the sky. It is slightly cloudy, but you can see quite a few stars. I spot a tiny dot moving at a steady pace from south to north. At first I think it's an airplane when I kind of spot it when it flashes. But notice that it does not flash more than once. Now I'm thinking maybe it's a satellite that has reflected sunlight. After a while it flashes up again quite strongly. I notice that the blink is not fast, but a "soft" blink that lasts a second or two. I think it seems a bit strange, so I call my wife, who comes out. I can't see the object now, but she can, and a moment later it lights up in the same way again. After a while I can no longer see the object as the sky seems a bit hazy.

The observation was made last night - the night between July 3 and 4 - at 1.30 in postcode 2690. The observation was made by 2 people, and concerns 8 or 9 objects moving from east to west in a straight line south of the observation point. They moved in two groups of 4 and seemed to be in some sort of grouping. The observation is made within one minute. From each object came a strong reddish light which was constant. My best guess is helicopters, but there was no sound. They were too close together to be planes. Given the movement, it didn't seem like it could be anything that wasn't motorized.

We look west out of our window, which faces the allotment gardens. Says that the clouds to the west (Jutland-England/Ireland) are very heavy and look incredibly beautiful. To the southwest of us we observe a large dark object of enormous size appearing in the clouds (Long thin clouds), however it disappears into the clouds again and reappears a little further to the south in the clouds again, here it moves vertically down in a identical cloud that lies a little further down. Here we observe the further "side" sticking out a few times before it disappears in the cloud due south. In between all this we see that the big cloud we were looking at to start with has something that looks like the fog from an airplane (can't see what's pulling it) sent straight up it and has turned sharply to the south-southwest (to our left). From these "fogs", three more rise up. It is so far the largest object we have ever observed in the sky.

We have sat out all evening, and end the day by looking at stars, shooting stars and satellites. We live in a small town on Lolland. Head south from us there is at least 10 km. to the nearest town (also small). We sit in dark surroundings to better enjoy the evening sky. Suddenly, 2 large white luminous objects appear (approx. 5-6 times larger than Mars, which we can see to the west). The 2 objects are vertically above each other. The halo around the 2 objects makes them almost 10 times larger. The 2 objects have a distance from each other of approx. 10 cm. (from our side of course :-)) The objects are clearly the brightest in the sky. Both objects become fainter in the halo and again after 10 seconds both objects just as suddenly disappear from the sky again. The experience left us wondering, and we still talk about it today.

Probably no more than 5-10 degrees from the vertical and no more than 5-10 degrees to the east. A star's brightness increased by perhaps 3-5 times. I dare not say whether there were colors involved. It happened 3 maybe 4 times and each time lasted no more than 3 seconds with maybe 5-10 seconds between the flashes. The sky was completely cloudless and the other stars behaved normally. It was obviously not a UFO, but I am curious as to what else it could be.

New Year's Eve, sober, drove the car home with the family. Standing outside looking at stars when a red flying light slowly approaches directly towards me at low altitude. (Parachute rocket I think). It flies right over me and I can see a circle of 7 or 8 round razor sharp and constantly shining lights. It flies straight, straight and low, I hear a hum from it/it, and it quietly disappears out there, to the south.?? I scout for it until it can no longer be seen. Very strange and deeply thought provoking. Has anyone else seen this and is there a reasonable explanation for this flying unidentified object(s)?

Me and 2 friends were watching a movie, when one of them suddenly spots some yellow sparkling dots in the clear sky. We watch as a few more appear behind some buildings. We talk briefly about what it could be, and the first thought was helicopters, but approx. 3 minutes of observations later, there are approx. 20 luminous dots in the sky. Since there is no noise from engines or the like, and the dots seem to rise quietly, we agree that they must be such "paper balloons" with tealights, which i.a. is used in China and Thailand.

My girlfriend and I were in our backyard smoking when she spotted two EXTREMELY bright stars. They moved and kept the same distance between them all the time. They lit up at least 5 times more than the brightest star I have ever seen. I ran in and shouted at my mother that there were UFOs - that's right! - and she was out in 20 seconds and saw it too. They were only insanely clear for approx. 15-20 seconds, after which they faded into motion. It's probably the most mindblowing thing we've ever seen! :IN

My boyfriend, our mutual friend and I saw here last night approx. 04.50-05.05 two flying blue star-like objects that flew in patterns not seen from aircraft or the like and at extremely high speed considering how far away they were. All three of us saw this!

Sitting at home in the yard and enjoying the warm evening. Holes have started to appear in the cloud cover so that you can see the stars. I see here in a northeasterly direction what looks like a star, but it moves in a wild zigzag pattern. It was right next to another star, so it was quite obvious that it was moving. I wanted to point out the spot to my wife, who was sitting next to me, but there it was lost in the cloud cover. Meanwhile, she catches sight of it for approx. north-northwest, where it stands almost still while it becomes sharper and sharper so that in the end it looks like a very powerful searchlight without us being illuminated at any time. After this, the light fades, as if moving outwards, where it finally disappears.

I came by car from Ganløse towards Farum. I had just come out where the forest ends on the left, and the valley with the Mølleåen appears. Here is a fine view of the horizon line in an eastern direction, where the sky was cloudless. The sun was not yet visible, but the sky was reddish on the horizon. I saw three very conspicuous lights approx. 15-20 degrees above the horizon. The distance was impossible to judge. The lights were almost glowing and a bit angular. They looked more like a huge piece of quadratic silver paper with odd curled edges that the sun shone on. In an outstretched arm measured between thumb and forefinger, each light measured just about 4-5mm. Comparing the lights to a large star, they were several times larger. The lights appeared in a triangle formation - one to the left, and one approx. a hand's breadth and a finger's breadth further down - from there two finger's breadths to the right and two finger's breadths up the last light. The lightnings moved with small quick movements, but within their own size, ie measured with an outstretched arm, within 4 - 5 mm. Suddenly the middle light moved with a somewhat uncertain course up towards the right light at a speed so that it would reach it in 5-8 seconds, but my observation ended before the lights reached each other as I now drove down into the valley where the vegetation overshadowed the events. On my way through Farum and out along Hareskovvejen, I tried to catch sight of the lights again, but without success. Approx. 10 minutes later I reached the Helsingør motorway, where I drove in a northerly direction. When I got onto the Helsingmotorvejen in a northbound direction, I again had a good view in an eastern direction, but unfortunately the lights had disappeared. These lights were so dominant that I have no doubt that others must have observed them.

Started by seeing something bright shining floating out on the horizon and followed it flying from left to right. The light became partly sharper and weaker, and it stayed to the right for a few minutes, after which it again pulled to the left and stopped and became sharper again, but then it dived under the trees laid out and disappeared. It looked like two bright orbs that followed.

I have, among other things, took these two photos at the Copenhagen light festival 23/2-21 Both photos were taken on a tripod, where the exposure is 5 seconds. On one, I see three green dots in the right corner. Since they are taken on a tripod with a 5 second exposure, I can ascertain that the objects are standing still in the air. The second picture that was taken 30 seconds before, there is nothing to see.

My boyfriend stopped the car and was as shocked as I was. It looked almost like the Chariot, but just lacked one wheel at the back. I fumbled with my phone, which unfortunately wouldn't cooperate. Meanwhile, my girlfriend saw 3 of them flying to the left over some trees, and then they disappeared.. The last 3 were still there, where it seemed like the 3 flew up into the sky and disappeared. Then it was all gone.

I was sitting in our car. We had just had lunch at my grandmother's. And had to deliver my faster. Suddenly up in the sky I saw a strange object which was a mixture between round and cigar-shaped. It was about one and a half km up. But I zoomed in on it with my mobile. I didn't get to take a picture with my cell phone because my mom drove off, so it disappeared. I didn't see it disappear, but I'm pretty sure I saw it, but only I saw it.

One of the typical reports about the fireball on 27 January is from project manager Filip Steenholdt, Vesterborg in Lolland, who says: "My son was sitting in the right rear seat of the car and looked out of the side window towards the sky. "Look, there's a shooting star," he said. The rest of us in the car looked out of the windows and also spotted it. I've never before experienced that you see a shooting star and be able to pass it on to others so that they can too. managed to see it. The time was 17:53. Duration 2-3 seconds. The size was not a thin line like a normal shooting star but rather like a roman candle fired from the neighbor - though in the wrong direction - slanting downwards. There were no houses in that direction . The direction was slanted up from the right down to the left. I think it was almost vertical, but the rest of the family think it was a little more horizontal. I estimate that the 'impact' was in the direction south of the southern tip of Langeland." The fireball on 27 January was seen in all parts of the country. It moved in a southern direction and ended up somewhere over N-Germany. It is therefore excluded that something from this meteorite may have fallen on Danish territory.

2 white/yellow reddish round light objects, they came into view from the bottom of the horizon in a southern direction (Kolding/Vamdrup). They flew at the same speed with 0.5-1 km intervals right after each other. After they had been visible for a few minutes, they turned east at approx. 90 degrees, where they quickly disappeared in the cloud cover. Approx. 1-2 min after both had disappeared to the east, 2 identical objects appeared from the same place in a southerly direction, they repeated the maneuver of the 2 previous objects. And these 2 also disappeared in the same way. No sound could be heard from them, and they were probably 5-10 km, but difficult to judge. Just before they came into view for the first time, a white flashing object came. Presumably a scheduled flight on its way to Billund.

properties.Colors: grøn, lilla, gul, hvid og blå
properties.content: We observed something that at first glance looked like an airplane, then we saw that it was completely still in the air. At first it held the height, but slowly began to fall slowly. Approx. 2 degrees per minute. As it approached 20 degrees, it began to shoot out something that resembled stars, and suddenly disappeared. Its light was green, purple, yellow, white and blue, and immediately flashed asymmetrically.

Large (Ø-20 cm) white round light is seen horizontally across the sky to the east to southeast for 5-6 sec. with relatively "slow" speed, but faster than an airplane. Suddenly the light "switches on" and then abruptly switches off again. Distance 1,000 m or slightly more. Definitely not like a typical shooting star.

Light constantly flying at low altitude and low speed west to east to west. To the east the light is red, to the west it changes to green. There is also a white light that flashes, which is only visible for a short time. No noise and the observation has now lasted for at least 20 minutes. It's definitely not a plane or a helicopter. Possibly a drone? But it apparently flies in the middle of the airport's arrival corridor. Filmed with a mobile phone. Don't know if it can be seen.

It was when I was on my way home from my friend in Roskilde. I walk by the police station, listening to music in my earphones and happen to look up at the starry sky, as is my habit. Looking up into the sky to my right, my gaze falls on four round dull-white discs that, in formation, slide in a straight line along the direction of my walk. What I noticed was that they were almost undulating or fluttering, kind of like the way a flatfish might swim, very fast, probably in sync... I followed them for maybe max. two seconds before they disappeared behind some houses and trees. The first thing I thought was, it must be a searchlight of some kind, the kind you can look at the cone of light and see how the light ripples under the base of the clouds if they are low... There were just no clouds... So I thought maybe it was because I had just crossed a road and got some headlights reflected in my eyes.. But their/its movement didn't match the "headlight reflection" that you can see, like after a flash. They moved straight ahead, and "waved" as I said, very fast... Then I thought if it could be the landing light from an airplane, as there are quite a few airplanes that fly over Roskilde... But I don't remember any plane at the time, there were no recognizable flashes, and I have to admit I have never, ever seen such a "light" before... It wasn't really shining, it was more like dull ghostly shadows fluttering rapidly across heaven.. It was about 9:00 p.m. when I left my friend's place at about 8:45 p.m. ...

Looked at the evening sky and saw what I thought was the ISS, heading south to north, but it faded and came after approx. 3 sec. back. However, I have seen this before. What makes it strange is that the approx. in compass direction 275 degrees, turned 180 degrees, took a return course approx. 2 sec. for (270 degrees) then off disappear vertically down.

I go out into the garden to get some fresh air and look at the starry sky. All of a sudden, a clear, black triangular object with three clear lights on each of the three edges flies across the night sky at high speed. It wasn't a plane, it was going much too fast for that, and was too close. There was no sound at all. It wasn't a shooting star. It had a form. In the three or four seconds I observed, the shape of the object could be discerned. As if it had a "texture" in the dark area. Has anyone else seen it? What on earth could it have been? My wife thinks I'm crazy 🙁

It was all a long time ago, but a friend and I had to go over to his place to get something, and since he didn't live more than 800 meters away, we decided to go over there, it was 10 - 11 pm, and I lived in Ydervangen at the time, and he knew a route that went from Ydervangen. We had to cross Hobrovej and over to the road where the scouts and Falck were and along a path that filled the parallel with the old barracks. On that path there was a large field on one side, and on the other you could see the barracks and the apartments we were going to further on. It was a cold evening and there was not a cloud in the sky. And since it was incredibly dark, we could see "thousands" of stars. When we have walked a short distance, I want to light a cigarette and therefore stop, as I cannot light the smoke because of the wind. When I had taken the first puff, I lean my head back to blow the smoke away, I see a "star" coming at a very high speed. This "star" comes from the south and is very similar to a star, although it was somewhat stronger. I point to show my friend this "star" and he spots it. While we stand and look at this object for a bit, I spot 2 other lights at the same speed and just as powerful as the first one we spotted. The 3 objects came from each corner, just as they had come from each corner in a triangular object. No. 1 comes from the south at high speed, object no. 2 comes from the northwest, and no. 3 comes from the northeast. These objects fly almost towards each other, and a good 20 to 30 seconds pass. Just before they meet, they stop and hover above us a good 1 - 2 km up in the air, and it takes approx. 3 - 4 seconds and the objects fly together or in formation in a southerly direction. I am a man who must have the facts in his hands and would very much like to know what we saw, because we know it. I can tell the difference between satellites, planes, balloons and other objects in the sky, but not this.

I'm sitting in the car on the way home and I'm looking at the stars when I see a movement in the sky. It looks like it's falling, but it says for 2 seconds, lights up brightly, and quickly disappears back into the sky.

My friend, my brother and I decided to watch a movie, but due to the never-ending pestilence of bugs, my brother suggested we take a short break until we got rid of the bugs. My friend and I now saw our cut to go out in the backyard and smoke a cigarette. It is for lack of better words that I call it a backyard. It is a tile area of x5 metres, where we e.g. has our rabbit cage. It's half past three in the morning when my brother comes out and makes small talk while he waits for us to finish so we can continue the movie. Now we suddenly hear a kind of hum/hum/machine sound approaching from our right. We quickly look at each other to confirm the situation, and we quickly conclude that there is indeed this hum/hum/machine sound approaching relatively quickly. It can be clearly heard that the object is not very far from us - between 3-15 meters away from us, and although it is quite difficult to judge, we all have the opinion that the object was moving 5-15 meters above the ground. The object's speed is also difficult to assess, as distance also has an influence on our perception of the current speed, but it has not been much more or less than 20 km/h. All three of us listen and look like crazy, but even though we can hear that the object is in front of us now, we can't see anything. The object continues to the west, where it disappears approx. 10 seconds after we first heard it. It should be mentioned that at no time did we see the object or catch a glimpse of it. We are three very rational boys who all study physics, chemistry and mathematics, but this experience we simply cannot find any reasonable explanation for why I am writing this post. We could observe/hear the object over a distance of approx. 50 metres, and if the object had not hovered/flew, it would have been impossible to cover that route, as it would have been stopped by fences and houses etc. The sound is hard to describe. It was a strange machine noise, a sort of electronic hum. The sound varied constantly in power/volume/decibel. Under NO circumstances can it be an insect/airplane/helicopter. The sound was very faint, although the intensity of the sound varied rhythmically. Had we been 10 meters further away, we might not have been able to hear the object. We're pretty sure it's a small object. The route taken by the object is characterized by tall trees and houses. The object has thus managed to evade and fly past these trees and houses, so it might be thought that the object must have been controlled by intelligence. Finally, it should be mentioned that Espergærde is a provincial town in North Zealand. I myself live on the outskirts of Espergærde, and the object had a direction towards a forest area with fields and marshes. It is also noteworthy that the object passes us at 2.30 - the time when it is the darkest - despite the bright summer nights, we were not able to see the object, we could only hear it. We have considered whether it could be some kind of drone? None of us leans towards any explanation, or has an idea in advance of what it could be. The incident is close to inexplicable, which is why we don't expect you to be able to give us an answer to what it was we experienced, but one can always hope.

We had guests and sat and looked at the appearance of the star and for any satellites. Looking to the northeast and seeing a plane that has its landing lights on, but it's bright orange and there's no flashing or sound. After approx. observation in 45 seconds, a stub falls vertically towards the ground, also luminous, and I take my binoculars, which we had been looking at the moon with, a 7X35 not very powerful. Focuses sharply on the gizmo. Couldn't make out anything other than a strong orange spot that was still moving across the sky. Suddenly, 3 more slightly smaller orange spots appear from the same point in the sky that the first one came from. They move at the same speed and with a smaller distance between them. The last one also drops somewhat vertically towards the ground. It looked like a helicopter formation that had to land. The first big spot just turns towards the city and suddenly disappears. A little later, the other three turn in the same place across the city and disappear. Could there have been some fallout in the atmosphere or what was it that came across the sky? It was special but beautiful. They were twice as high up as Mars normally stands.

It is probably ten years ago, but I have often wondered about the experience, so here is the observation: My father picks us up from the house one evening in the month of March, as he wants witnesses to his observation. There are three of us (my mother, a young girl and I) who reach out and see it. An object flies slowly across the sky. It is not that high up in the sky, but it is difficult to judge the distance down to the ground. It emits a very bright light, has no sound, and the light is much bigger than satellites, airplanes, etc. There is nothing flashing. The shape of the light is not spherical, but flatter round, like a flattened sun. It flies slowly without changing direction. At first I think it might be a comet, but it is bigger and very close to the earth. Beneath the object, a cone light is suddenly switched on, just as a flashlight can shine out in a cone shape. The light stops abruptly a short distance below the object. We stand and look up at it, and it flies towards us and the house. My parents live out in the country and it is dark around us. The light is very bright and the object is flying right above us and we are standing in a mighty bright light that blinds us. My mother runs into the house scared, she says afterwards that she was afraid of radiation?? I stay standing and hold the other girl's hand as she is very scared. The bright light suddenly goes out and all that remains are three smaller lights in a triangle. I can't see the shape of the object. Now it flies away infinitely fast, but still no sound is heard. My mother runs upstairs to follow the object's path away, but it is out of sight. We are left amazed. We have often wondered what was flying above us. We were pretty upset about our experience afterwards. Do you have an explanation? Are there other observations that resemble it?

On the way to work in Gråsten, approx. halfway between Broager and Egernsund, we (myself + 2 Americans) see a luminous rectangle in the sky. It is completely rectangular with sharp corners and stands out sharply against the sky. It is completely dark and very cloudy, only the lower part of the horizon is cloudless. There is no moon to be seen, and nothing nearby to explain this strange luminous rectangular field. All three of us have seen it and observed it for some time before one asks what it might be. We can't find any explanation, and suddenly it's like it's disintegrating. It almost shrinks to nothing. As if it is evaporating from the outside in. It takes maybe 10 - 15 seconds, then it's gone. We talk about it when we get to work, but no one seems to have seen the same thing as us. In the following days, we pay close attention to the surroundings and the position of the moon around the place where we observed the phenomenon, in order to find a logical explanation if possible, but we have not been able to find one. Is there anyone else who has seen the same thing as us??!!

I went for a walk with children. The weather was fine (windless evening). All of a sudden I felt a strange but pleasant pressure of warm air all over my body. I thought hmmm... strange and looked up at the trees to see if maybe it had started to blow a little, but the leaves on all the trees were musty still. While we slowly moved on, I still felt the heat and the air pressure, then I look up at the trees again and see just behind them a strange object - machine (at a height of approx. 20 m max) in the form of two thick cigars joined by two equally long beams between. The cigars were very bright like highly polished silver and the bars were dark gray. This machine was completely silent and came very slowly directly above us and has been standing still for approx. 2 minutes I started whispering to the children ("Hanna, Thomas look, look at it!!, it looks like a UFO"). The machine began to move towards the south at the same altitude without a sound, and still I felt a blast of pleasant warmth over me. After approx. 1 min, the machine very quickly changed direction to the west and crashed into the sky at lightning speed and disappeared instantly. I was shocked but not scared, on the contrary I was happy and started thinking about the machine and explained to the children "what is ufo", I thought if it was a plane or a jet plane, then why didn't their sound come after or below and they fly not at this height, and they don't light the seed and mm... many thoughts. It took approx. 5-8 min, and we went on, but then the feeling of hot blowing pressure came again, and then I look up at the trees again, no movement, think it's strange!! Looking up at the sky in all directions, and then the same thing happens again, the same object comes at the same height without a single sound, two glowing cigars connected by two non-luminous beams, hanging over us silently for approx. 1-2 min and flew in the same direction as the first object, and just as fast and without sound. Right after each time, the pleasant blowing pressure of the heat over me disappeared, and now I was so sure that I saw a UFO, so I ran home with the children and quickly told everything about what I had seen and felt. My husband's two sons ran out with me again (about 5 minutes passed), because maybe the UFO came again. We all stood together for at least half an hour, glaring at the sky above the trees, hoping the object would come again, but it didn't. To this day, I have told many times about my experience. And to this day very often (in the evening when it is dark) I look to the sky and hope that this object will come again and appear to me for a longer time with its pleasant warmth above me. No one can tell me I haven't seen this!! I only wish that people would trust others more if they experience or see something strange. I still hope that some other people in the world see such an object as I have seen, so that my experience will be confirmed. This year I have found a strange stone on Møns Klint, which looks like a meteorite (but it is not magnetic, like the one from Mars or the moon), so I hope it is a real meteorite.

A warm yellow ball floated quietly and slowly to the north, and came closer, tried to take a photo with a cell phone, which flashed, at the same time the ball changed direction to the east. As it flew to the east, it slowly disappeared like a fire burning out. Could be one of those hot air balloons? Just strange that it could change direction from north to east.

Tobias, 9 years old, sits on the toilet and looks out the window. The object comes flying very quickly, stops abruptly, hangs in the air approx. 3 seconds and disappears with the speed of lightning. Its shape is oval. Underneath it, it looks like it has little orange and green lights. He is very upset afterwards and comes flying in and shouts in utter fright what it is that he has seen, and he can tell over and over in detail what he saw here, and can recount the direction in which it flew and how long it hung in the air etc. I believe he has seen a UFO.

I am on my way home from a friend's house when I see a car that has stopped further ahead. I wonder and look up at the sky. Here I spot an object floating towards the city. At this time I am standing at Papirgården on Århusvejen in Grenå. What I could see of the object as it comes from the northwest is 2 red lights next to each other, which I assume was the front one with green, round lights around in a saucer shape with flashing blue light at the back. Video recorded!!

A friend and I sit by the harbor and look at the city and a bit around. Suddenly we both spot something that at first looks like a reddish, long-lasting shooting star, but since it continues for quite a long time towards the horizon, it must almost be out of the question. A few minutes later we observe 3 star-like objects, also with a reddish glow, in a clear 150 degree formation for approx. 10 seconds that come flying over us and also disappear into the horizon.

I was sitting on the floor of my kitchen on Tuesday, April 18, 2023 at about between 20-21, and suddenly I see through my window a large green dot in the sky, which appeared at my eaves, moving quickly and disappearing over my neighbor's roof. It was a bigger dot, perhaps like you have been able to see Venus lately. It was moving at a speed so I wouldn't think it's a helicopter or plane, and there was no sound either. It might have been a fast-flying drone, but the size of the light/dot in the sky, I don't think I can get a drone to vote either. There's probably a logical explanation, but since I don't have a good plausible explanation myself for something I've never observed before, I'll report it here, just in case it has relevance.

I was out taking pictures of the stars. When I looked out of the corner of my eye, this white with greenish-blue tinge came flying diagonally across me and disappeared away after 2½-3sec. It could remind me of a fireball, which I've read about now. But not sure, so will post it here anyway. Had set my camera to take a picture for 30 sec., typically enough it flew right past on the wrong side...... flew over Vordingborg from south to north-northwest.

I'm not sure if what we saw was a UFO.......but it was mysterious anyway....especially after talking to several people today who also saw it. My boyfriend and I arrive driving a little after 19 up Feggesundvej towards Dråby Vig. When we are a little outside Alsted, we suddenly see more than half of the sky in a NNW direction light up strongly in a neo-green/white glow, with what appears to be a round "centre" from which the light emanates. We can only see the sea part of the "centre", as we are outside Alsted and the hilltop that separates Alsted City from Dråby Vig. My girlfriend and I immediately started talking about the fact that there was probably another firework warehouse going off... and we quickly agreed that it was coming in the direction of Flade or Thisted. When we got over the hill, however, we could see from a distance that Flade by looked as it used to in the dark... We then quickly agreed to drive to Sø Bugt, from where there is a clear view across to Thisted. On the way, I called my parents in Thy. They hadn't seen or heard anything, but they had just lost the TV2 signal... Immediately I thought that maybe it was the Thisted mast that had fallen over in the strong wind (20-25 m per second). I ended the phone call. Soon we were at Sø Bugt... and I could immediately see that it was not the mast that had fallen... when I saw the characteristic red flashes on the horizon. But where was Thisted...... it was completely dark over there. Some time passed (x number of minutes, max. 3-4 minutes I think), then suddenly the light came on... first in the northern part of the city... then in the center of the city... and immediately after that everything was as it used to with regard to the lighting over from Thisted. But what the hell had happened? When we got home and were going to watch the handball WC, I could see that there had been a power cut as my computer was switched off. The next day I rushed online to see if there was anything on Thisted Dagblad's website or on DR's website under region midt og west. There was nothing! And it still doesn't at the moment. (Sunday evening at 11.40 p.m.). When my girlfriend came home from work on Sunday afternoon, she could tell that the water had been yellow in the morning when she had to make coffee. Sunday evening I was at some friends to look at a computer. When we sit over coffee afterwards, one of them asks if we know what happened over in Thisted last night? She had spoken to several people today (Sunday) who had seen the same light... and knew that the light had disappeared over in Thisted. They had all had short-term power outages and many suddenly had no more water!?? Our friends also had a brief power outage...... but no water issues... as far as they know. All those she spoke to also live at Mors. We talked about what it could be. The other of our friends perhaps thought that it could be the high-voltage masts in Thy that could have predicted the flash of light and the power failure, if the wires had been knocked together in the wind... if the power had gone... the power probably also goes to those pumps, there is water pumping around from the water works, as he said... but the rest of us didn't think it should be able to give so much light, and the huge flash of light we saw. We started talking about little green Martians.... that is, whether it was a short-term visit we had from a UFO........ who had foreseen the whole thing....... In any case, we CAN'T understand that there is NOTHING whatsoever about the episode in the media!!! As I said, I don't know what it was we saw...... but I needed to get it out in print anyway..... so it doesn't just go into oblivion. It is hereby done!

In the sky in the inner city (Copenhagen) at approximately 22.30 d.9. April there were several orange lights in the sky. They formed a formation and then a new formation. Slowly they faded away. I think there were seven or eight pieces.

On the night of Thursday 17/9-2020 I saw to the south 3 searchlight-like lights in the sky. The color was white and there was an equal distance between them. At first thought it came from the house next door, but could see that the angle was not right - they were too high up. They stood perfectly still, and there was no sound associated with it. Checked to see if there were any tall cranes or similar behind the house, but there weren't. Don't know how long there was light. Only discovered it when I turned off the light in the living room. After that it lasted maybe 10-15 minutes.

I was sitting at home in my living room that night, where I have windows to the north, and suddenly out of the corner of my eye I saw a relatively large ball of light, which was whitish-yellow and which flickered a little bit. It moved rather quickly across the sky. Thought it looked strange, so I quickly took my mobile phone and filmed it, and this resulted in an 18 second clip in UHD quality, before it was so far above me in a south-easterly direction that I couldn't really could film it more, but also because I had a bad grip on my mobile and was about to drop it out of my window, after which I naturally stopped recording. I rushed into my bedroom, which has windows facing S-SE, to see if I could spot it there, but unfortunately I had no luck. Could possibly have been due to low lying clouds as it was partly cloudy that night. There was also no sound from the object, and that the object flew about twice as fast as a regular airliner. I also checked flightradar24.com shortly after the incident, and there were no planes in a large radius of Næstved at the time in question, and absolutely no planes flying/had flown from NW to SE. I have tried to find historical data from flightradar24.com or similar sites to support my claim, but unfortunately I have not been successful. As I said, I have a video of the object that I have uploaded on youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5qDi5k4lhn4 If SUFOI has doubts about the authenticity of the date of the video clip, since I first uploaded it and wrote to you now (been very busy), I can also send it to you in original format, with all the video details encoded in the information in the clip. If so, contact me by email or phone.

An object of relatively high speed, shining bright white, comparable to the light of the nearest stars, flew across the sky without a sound, not particularly high up, but with an irregular course, not in a straight line......

Just went to bed but heard a few noises outside and wanted to check by looking out my front door which faces east. At the same time saw an object with a very bright light come flying in over the center of Frederikshavn. Right above my house. The light consisted of 3 to 4 or more powerful lights in a row in the direction of flight. I could not see the shape of the object, but only the position of the light on this row. The light was yellow to orange. There was no sound at all. I would assume the altitude to be somewhat lower than domestic aircraft, rather a little higher than a sports aircraft flies in. The speed was calm and steady, but difficult to judge as I could not see the size of the object and the naked height. Looked like it was a bit quiet to the west but was hard to tell. There were no flashing lights as usual. aircraft, only the very strong downward-scoring yellow light.

While driving on the Holbæk motorway one evening, I became aware of some very flickering lights in the sky. With fast zig-zag movements, they stood out from the airplane, helicopter, drone categories. Sometimes the lights went out and came back on somewhere else. It was approaching the highway from the northeast, and in order to observe it more closely, I turned into a rest area. But in the time before I got hold of the mobile phone, put it on video recording and got out of the seat belt and opened the car door - it had reached right over me at full speed - and disappeared a second later behind some vegetation. I have divided the second recording that was on the video into single images. It looked like it was big, about 8-10 meters, and probably approx. 30 - 40 meters up. The lights on it rotated and pulsed.

Luminous, slightly yellowish point, observed in the sky in a north-north-east direction from Klintevej, 8240 Risskov. Steady, not pulsating or flashing. Observed slowly rising vertically, for 15-20 seconds. With safety in motion, as it was seen in relation to nearby roofs. When I fumbled with my phone to take a picture (about 5-10 seconds) and looked up, the dot was gone and didn't come back. The sky was crystal clear, no clouds. No buildings in the direction to "shadow".

My wildlife camera takes a still photo when movement is detected and then 10 seconds of video. Image STC_0197 on wildlife camera contains a spot of light. The following video shows nothing. The still images before and after also do not contain the light spot. I'm not on Facebook, so I want to know where else I can send pictures/video to you. I am sending the actual image STC_0197 to the Webmaster. The date and time are not correct on the recordings, but are approx. 7 hours

1st observation: We were by car from Assens to Voldbro. We are approx. 250 meters from the village, which we approach along Egerupvej, when not far above the horizon (so probably far ahead) we see some (about 3-5, didn't focus on counting) fairly flat ellipses, all of which are yellow/white. It's still bright. So that was the observation.
