We drive into the farmyard at Bangsgården in Voldbro, where the company Interacoutics is based, and where I work as a newly trained person, to pick up an amplifier and a speaker (plays in a band). Soon after, we are on the road again towards Andebølle, where I and a few others rent a house, where we live and practice music. On the way to Andebølle we have our 2nd observation: 2nd observation: It is now dark. We drive on Assensvej towards Vissenbjerg. Approx. 2 km. from Bred, my father says: "There they are again". He sits in the passenger seat and watches them from the right side window. Soon after, I see them through the windscreen, where they are heading towards Bred. They are now seen for approx. 45 degrees above the horizon and are oval - as opposed to elliptical. The color is now orange. Still in the form of rings. This time I count them to 5. They look like the Olympic rings, except for the color. They do not overlap each other, like the Olympic rings, but are separated from each other by approx. 1 times the diameter of the individual rings. Each ring has the same diameter as the moon. Their speed is approx. twice ours (from the time my father saw them until shortly before Bred, I picked up the speed to catch up with them, and we then drove about 100 km/h). We drive in a Morris Mascot, where you turn the light on/off manually with a button. I blink 3 times: turn off light, turn on, turn off, turn on, turn off and turn on. But no response. When we drive into Bred - approx. 100 meters from the track crossing, we lose sight of them as they disappear behind a larger hill ahead. We don't see them anymore. PS: In the days around this weekend, there was a NATO exercise in e.g. Denmark with the participation of forces from several NATO countries, so maybe we have seen some of their stuff. However, we have never seen anything like it before or since.

We stood and watched the fireworks over Brøndby Strand in an eastern direction. Suddenly a broad luminous cloud-like formation appeared in the dark night sky approx. 20 degrees above the horizon and distance approx. 4-5 km, like when the moon shines through a hole in the clouds without being visible. Out of the top from this luminous formation, 6 orange-yellow bright objects came into view one by one. They floated slowly descending towards the north, after which they disappeared after approx. 5 minutes The luminous formation turned dark again.

We sat in the garden on Saturday evening at approx. 22.30, where we see three luminous objects. The height is difficult to judge, approx. 300 m above ground, approx. circumference 10-15 m round, it looked like there was fire or bright light at the bottom, and something dark on top! They came flying without a sound at different speeds. It lasts approx. 5 minutes Our 7 year old daughter was standing on the other side of our house watching them. She came running through the house to us crying and was scared of them!!!! We saw the same, but only two objects in week 26 I think it was, They came at high speed from the south right after each other, stopped suddenly just before they were over us and then flew parallel to the west. I'm not one to believe in UFOs, but I really have no explanation for what we saw?????

I was standing in the garden looking at the stars when I saw what I immediately interpreted as a shooting star due to the speed of the phenomenon across the sky. Upon closer inspection I could see the outline of 2 triangular luminous objects flying across the sky in close formation slightly offset from each other, somewhat reminiscent of the fan in a goose migration, but they were flying far, far too fast for that were birds and were also distinctly triangular in shape. I heard no sounds that I could associate with the sighting. As a hunter, I am used to seeing birds in flight in low light conditions, but this sighting is so different from all my previous experiences with birds in flight.

I am on my way home from my workplace in Hjørring. On the country road between Vrå and Serritslev, I suddenly see a very strong white light to the west. I looked at the clock in the car, at was 05.11. I was very startled and got goosebumps. I also got a little scared as I couldn't explain such a powerful flash of light. If it had been an explosion, the car would probably have been blown off the road, but there was no bang.

Since I have encountered some of these inexplicable things in life, I think you should have the story, and like to tell back if others have seen similar things. things at the same time. It starts when my mom is pregnant with me, here my mom and dad say they were chased by a green light 3 times... my dad froze and was scared. It happened in Langeskov near Urup in 1967. One evening, the light followed them to my grandparents' home, and my grandmother said that she also saw the green light, which was an elongated cone of light, or like a large fluorescent tube, rotating above them . In 1974, when I was 7 years old, I went for a walk with another girl, who was then in a foster family, to swim in a stream that lies behind Hindemae in Skellerup. When we are on our way back along the field, we see the big gray round thing hanging in the air diagonally above us. It is put together with several plates at the bottom, with round rivets... there are 3 legs under it. Around its belly, there are black windows divided into fields, and I can see that there is light behind it. I feel like they are looking at us and we are looking at them. On top of it, there are several antennas placed somewhat randomly. We talk about how strange it is that it doesn't have wings, because we don't know anything about UFOs at this point. I run home and tell my dad, keep an eye on it, but it's getting away. My father and I go up to the terrace to see the rest of it, but don't make it. Since I am 12 years old, I am looking after children in Ellinge. Here I go out with the girls, we go for a walk in the field and then see a lot of white balls coming up from the ground, in the direction of where Hindemae is. The orbs come up vertically from the ground, stop high in the sky, the orbs stand still as if waiting for each other, then they pick up speed and now all fly horizontally. I ask one of the girls if they have a camera, she runs in for it and of course when she comes out they are gone. The last experience I had was when I was 17 years old and I was on a moped over to a girlfriend's place in Rolfsted, here a blue ball follows me out in the field, it flies horizontally, then a forest comes and it disappears behind the forest.

I was out walking my dog yesterday and saw a strange object in the sky. Almost thought it was a meteor about to crash. It looked like it was getting closer, but the further we got down the field, the further away it seemed to be. Have pictures on my phone, and really can't see what the object is, I couldn't with the naked eye either. But I could see an energy or heat ray. Please write if you want to see pictures or if you think there are others I can contact.

It then became clear that it was close. But then something happened that I will never forget. It split into 3, 1 large and 2 small. The little ones flew to the top of the forest and disappeared into the forest, and the big one flew up and sped wildly. Could follow until it was no longer visible. But the reason I'm writing is that I saw a bright ball yesterday in the same place, but there were so many clouds that I couldn't see it anymore.

It looked like someone fired a flare from the atmosphere and straight down to earth. Come in different explosions, in 3 different colors. Red, green and white, and looked like it ended 20 degrees above the ground, from my vantage point. Never seen anything like this before.

I walk my dog at 10 p.m. 10 minutes later I look up. as it has just become clear and there are many shooting stars. At the same moment I see something. that looks like a satellite at first, but moves 3-4 times as fast as the ISS. I think so briefly. that it's a VERY long shooting star, but it's too slow. It is point-shaped, possibly with a faint streak of condensation, but it may be the aperture of the eye that gives it. The color is orange-red to whitish, the light intensity does not change while it disappears into the horizon, as with satellites. From the time I spot it exactly vertically above me, until it disappears into the horizon, approx. 20 sec. Approx. 30 sec. after it disappeared, my older brother who was also out watching shooting stars, he had seen it since it appeared on the horizon, calls and confirms that it flew SIGNIFICANTLY faster than any satellites we have seen. 40 sec. from horizon to horizon would require an enormous speed even for the ISS, since it actually passes over the Zenith. Have since used "Orbitron" to search for satellites, but no luck. In general, I think it would be impossible for the sun to illuminate a satellite passing at such a low altitude, and since it had a constant brightness, I don't think it was a satellite.

I'm standing smoking an evening cigarette in the patio door when I see a light - like the ISS space station, and think it's here - but the light dips and turns as it descends. Approx. 30-45 seconds later, the light shoots up and flies away, falling slightly towards the rise, which is an easterly direction. I have previously observed the Air Force practicing against the Stigsnæs plant. But this observation stirred something. When I saw it fall and turn, it was like the movie was being played backwards. You know, a fighter jet takes off with afterburners and you can follow the light. But here the light came towards me as it fell and turned. And approx. 30 seconds later, I saw a light shoot up over the roof at an angle of approx. 25 degrees to the east, where it sort of leveled off and disappeared. As I said, I have previously seen the Air Force train, but there they have also run the same exercise over and over again. This observation was there only once.

I was changing the rear light on the car when I suddenly saw, A ROUND disk shaped ufo with white light in square shapes very bright, red light that pulsed all around the ship, blue/green flashes at different speeds. I quickly called my girlfriend who also saw the whole thing but she got scared and ran inside hehe.. Very convinced it's not a plane as we often see planes in the area. This was something completely different and much closer to a plane. When she had gone in, it glided on quietly across the sky and suddenly it disappeared.. Very cool experience!

To begin with, I thought it was a plane, as it glowed about as much as if you see the lights of a plane from the front. However, it became clear that it was not a plane, as it did not appear to be moving to begin with. I looked closer as it looked like it was blinking and could see it was moving. The way it moved was most reminiscent of a remote-controlled helicopter, "hanging still" in the air, but still moving. However, it cannot be a remote-controlled helicopter, as it disappeared into the clouds when it became cloudy. It twinkled and shone much brighter than the brightest stars in the sky when it was most clear.
Bright white light, same speed as airplane, but no engine noise or flashing lights. Soared high. Fly north/east in a straight line.

I looked up at the sky around 22, when there was something my eye caught, like when you can feel that a person is looking at you, even if they are doing it from the side, and you can't really see that they are looking at you. It was an instant sensation I had of looking up into the air, for something was moving up there. I was bored. Just got off bus 5A at Sundbyvester Plads and had to find Gyldenrisvej to go up to someone I was staying with. I live on Bornholm, but have lived on Amager for 14 years before that. I was on a weekend to visit friends in Amager. I looked up and noticed that the street light was a bright orange color. These are the ones at Sofiegade and Gyldenrisvej on Amagerbrogade. I thought it was a nice color. Not as white as the other street lights. There were no people. Yes, a man came while I was looking up, but I didn't ask him if he saw anything up there - because then he would think I was crazy. I looked at the street lamp and it was a bit hazy in the air and windy and cold. Fairly clear weather with some low clouds. Then I saw a big yellow spot next to the street lamp. The lantern was elongated square. (What's it called? a rectangle - a long narrow rectangle) and slightly oval. The spot was circular and very yellow. And then it moved. I thought - it's me and my eyes. I am getting old - spots are coming before my eyes. I don't see this. It is optical illusion. It's my eyes playing tricks on me, like when you look up at the sun for too long and then look down. Then you see stains everywhere. I looked down at the ground. Rub my eyes. Then up again. It was still there. It flew in a straight line from west to east just above the lamppost - quite high up, but not as high as an airplane, and then it flew across Amagerbrogade - quietly and actually a bit slowly - but completely aimed towards the east. Was it a weather balloon? Was it a satellite? It was silent. At first I was scared of them, but then I felt completely safe watching it. Was it a UFO. Some object? But maybe it was a satellite. Then it was just really far down towards the ground. Or was it the kind of one-diameter party balloon that someone sends up with fire in it? No, because then it would have flown hither and thither with the wind. It did not fly according to the wind. It was controlled by some technique. It was quite large. A circular dark yellow ball or spot about the size of a saucer when viewed from this distance. So it was probably about the size of the bottom of a helicopter. There were no wings or anything. Only a round ball with a color almost similar to the street light on Amagerbrogade. It lasted approx. 5 min., then it disappeared into a cloud on its way to Sweden. I have never seen anything like this before and regardless of whether it was a satellite or a UFO, it was beautiful and it was a fantastic experience.
It's the brightest light in the sky I've seen, and I can tell the difference between a shooting star and what this will end up with.

We are sitting in the pool and spot a white light to the right of the Moon, which has risen. We haven't seen the light move across the sky, it's just there with one. Distance, speed and strength immediately seem like landing lights on an airplane, but there is no green/red color or flashing. In addition, the speed is not constant, but "oscillating". The object moves in an s-shaped path northward for eight to twelve seconds, after which it slows down and disappears. The movement was clear in relation to the Moon nearby, and a flagpole next door. Not a super exciting sighting, but we agreed it couldn't be a plane, balloon or planet/star.

I saw 2 stars, but one had direction west from east. There was a visible star to the northeast and a UFO was between it and the Moon. I could see it coming closer, I could also see it moving towards the Moon and getting less and less light, and then with a flash it disappeared up to the Moon.

Friday 1.9.23 at 21.55. Clear weather = no clouds. Standing exceptionally in my darkened guest room to see the clear sky. To the west I spot irregular red and white flashing lights moving east. They don't blink like usual. fly 1 time per second alternating red/white, but irregular, without fixed rhythm. It seemed as if it was seen through light cloud cover, so everything flickered - but there WERE no clouds! Could only see the lights, no vessel. It moved jerkily and erratically in a straight path from west to east, faster than ordinary aircraft, but alternately gliding/jerking over a small distance. Followed it until I lost sight of it to the east. I have no idea about height/degrees above the horizon. It was high up where scheduled planes would normally be.

Was on my way out for a walk with my dog when there is something that shines brightly behind me and reflects light in my glasses. Turns head to the northwest and sees a huge orange-red orb that first moves quickly, slows down, and then takes a good jerk to the east. It changes direction and then moves slightly to the south (towards me). I call my better half and ask her and her parents to find binoculars. While I'm talking to her, object appears to be moving down towards the ground (never been high above, in my estimation) and suddenly takes a decent jerk back up and then moves further east (would consider object on this time must be above Skibsbylejren). My mother-in-law gets the binoculars pointed exactly in the direction of the object as it disappears from view, possibly hidden by cloud cover. Don't know what it was, but it was big and it moved at a very high speed at times. Can write off the moon as it hung to the east/southeast and had a completely different colour. Will reject an airplane as I have never seen an airplane that can change speed and direction in the same way nor have I ever seen an airplane that glowed so brightly in this color.

I was sitting in my office when by chance I could suddenly observe a light in the sky some distance above the horizon outside my window. I then got up without looking away and went out onto a small balcony I have. There I stood and observed this phenomenon. The strange thing was that the light was completely still, and after a while it started to disappear, after which it started to light up in another place a relative distance away, it continued for a while as I stood wondering what it could be for something though!

I just heard on the radio that some inexplicable phenomena had been observed over Skanderborg in April. I observed exactly the same over the northern part of Silkeborg on Easter Sunday 8 April 2012. I was supposed to have an evening cigarette on the terrace at approx. 22 and in the clear sky 2 very strange things danced around each other, apart and together they flew away towards the city. I have seen searchlights in the sky before and I absolutely do NOT think these were searchlights, considering one took a very long jump away from the other and back again and flew away together. I told far and wide about it and was very surprised when I just now heard about the same consideration about Skanderborg, also in the month of April.

On the night between 30 and 31/7 I sat by the bonfire in the garden to enjoy the silence. It was very dark and as far as I remember there was no moon. Around. 23.30 I lit a small fire, which is important in this context, as the fire could have an influence on my observation. I didn't have a watch on, but I estimate that approx. 1 hour when I suddenly hear a strange hissing/hissing/pulsing sound passing over me at very high speed. I couldn't look directly up into the sky because of some trees and had to walk a few steps forward to see what was making this strange sound. Unfortunately, I could not see anything, but only heard the sound disappear for a few seconds behind the silhouette of my house. I also noted that there were no sounds of cars on a nearby main road. The sound was very intense and almost electronically pulsating, which is why I'm sure it wasn't a large bird where you could hear the whirring of the wings, nor was it the characteristic steady sound of an airplane. When the sound came from upstairs, it couldn't possibly be either. wet pieces of wood in the fire that sizzled in the flames. As mentioned the speed was very high so I only caught it for a second or two before it was right over me and followed it for 3-4 seconds as it disappeared into the darkness behind my house. Furthermore, I took it to mean that the sound was relatively close to the ground, as my house has a flat roof, which makes it possible to see further than if it were a house with alms. pitched tile roof. As I could not see anything, I cannot specify the course, but my immediate assessment is that the sound came from the south-east and continued in a north-west direction beyond Roskilde fjord. I have never heard or observed anything like this before and have therefore scoured the Internet to find a place where I could report my experience, and perhaps get an answer as to whether there were others who had heard or seen something in the same period of time, just before or later?

My boyfriend came in and told me to come outside and see something he's never seen before in his life. And. Yes There was a huge perfect round ring of light above the cloud cover. It was approx. at 23.30 Last night. So I tried to film it, which I couldn't even though there was no light around at all, but I got something else, I have no idea what it was... It comes back and forth.. so no it can't be a shooting star.

On my way home from work, I walk through a large, green area surrounded by 2-storey blocks of flats. In fact, it is a large lawn with benches, handball goals and a playground that lies behind a horseshoe formation of social housing. On the way through this green area you have a clear view of most of the big, black evening sky. And when there are no clouds, you can clearly see most of the countless stars in the evening and night sky, if you are not standing in a certain place, so that one of the few trees in the area is in the way of your field of vision. On the way through this green area, I suddenly catch sight of a small, round object in the huge evening sky, which comes rushing across the sky from an eastern direction. The object is very, very high up in the atmosphere. It is difficult to describe how big or small it really is. In the evening sky, the round object occupies approximately 15-20 times as much as one of the respective stars in the sky, seen/assessed from my field of vision, mind you. The object can almost be described as round, as it looks most like a star. That is that the object in the sky looks like a luminous dot, just like a star, but only 15-20 times larger, and therefore yellowish/luminous in colour. The only thing that is remarkable is that the object almost comes rushing across the evening sky from an eastern direction. There is no sound to be heard from the object. Its speed is enormous, as it flies much faster than the usual airplanes often seen in the evening sky. You can typically stand and follow an airplane for several minutes in the sky. Its speed is snail-like as you follow the airplane across most of the evening sky. But this object came rushing across the sky from an easterly direction, then zig-zagged in very fast motions and completely disappeared in a north-westerly direction. (I walked with my back turned to Orion, which is in the southwest direction). The object flew almost in rapid zig-zag movements, changing from a northerly to a westerly direction 3-4 times in total, before disappearing completely from view. It almost disappeared into nothingness. As if it has completely flown out of the visible celestial sphere with its enormous speed in just 4-5 seconds. The object and the incident itself are therefore very sparingly described, as the mentioned object's presence in the evening sky only lasted around 4-5 seconds. I wonder a lot about the object. Mainly because of its fast zig-zag movements, as shooting stars most often come descending from top to bottom. Incidentally, a shooting star can only be seen in max. 1-2 seconds. My experience is that you barely manage to see a shooting star before it has already disappeared again. The particle burns itself up in no time. But this object was no shooting star. It was an object that almost consciously controlled itself. A luminous object in the evening sky, which came rushing from an eastern direction, then flew 3-4 times in zig-zag movements far, far up in the atmosphere, and finally completely disappeared into nothingness. I highly doubt it was a meteor or satellite.

My cousin and I came driving near Helenelyst, and suddenly we saw a white light, like a big flash, that lit up the whole sky for about 3 seconds. Then the light in the lampposts disappeared for a brief second and came back on. It sounds strange, but none of us know what it is. But have registered that the light disappeared for a short second at my mother in Brabrand and my friend in Galten.
I was on a canal cruise with my husband and son. We were on our way into Nyhavn again when our eyes were caught by some flashes of light in the sky.

Luminous ball of fire clearly falling towards the ground. I sensed the ball of light as round and the fall as easy to see and follow. It was only extinguished relatively shortly before impact. It was felt as if the impact took place southeast of Skæggær on the eastern side of Viborgvej.

The weather was lovely on Saturday. My friend and I were lying in my yard sunbathing, we were lying looking up at a completely blue sky. There were quite a few seagulls flying high up, but there was also a small object moving very slowly to the south. We talked about maybe it was a balloon from Tivoli, as it flashed a little (the reflection of the sun) and moved with the direction of the wind. We observed this thing for approx. 15-20 minutes. Suddenly it flew with great speed in the complete opposite direction and was gone in a few minutes. Later we saw two balloons and they did not behave the same way at all. Since half of Kbh's population has been lying with their noses in the air in the good weather on Saturday (18/5-02), perhaps there are some who have seen the same phenomenon from the same angle?

I was watching TV and a little before midnight, I saw a flash that could remind me of the grain ripening (lightning over the sea) and didn't think about it. At first I thought it might be a satellite, because I have seen that before, but then I could see that it was far too big for that, and the speed was also too fast. There was no sound and suddenly the light turned a faint orange and without further ado changed direction 90° and disappeared into nothingness.

Sitting at home watching TV with my mom, at some point something catches my eye and I go and look out the window. I see an orange/yellow orb hovering in the air next to the building opposite. When I spotted it, it seemed to retreat behind the building and look back and forth a few times. I call my mother and she sees the same thing as me. After a while it seemed to "slide" up and down the side of the building (though without touching it) and suddenly it disappeared faster than I could catch it.. I have to admit that I never found out what this phenomenon was, but I'm sure it wasn't a lamp that gave that kind of light, because it floated smoothly back and forth..

During a children's birthday party with subsequent barbecue fun, I observed an incoming "meteor/shooting star", however its tail was very short, almost stopping. The strange thing about the observation, however, was that the "meteor" continued to shine as a very powerful "star", floating in a westward direction, at a speed of approx. 1-2 sec. per cm. evening sky. I then take my laser and shine in a circle around the object, and receive a response back via a quick POWERFUL flash, and the "UFO" continues in the same direction to the west, albeit with less strong light. I mark again with the laser and get the same response fast STRONG flash, then the "star/light" disappears/goes out and can't be seen anymore!

Looked out the kitchen window and suddenly I saw a big round white light (The moon in smaller format. Stayed in the air for at least 7 minutes. Suddenly it was gone. Have seen several very yellow balls of light in the same place, on November 29, 2012.

Runs the trip from Silkeborg to Horsens every day via Brædstrup. For a long straight distance, I see a strong light hanging in the sky directly in the middle of the road, somewhat further up than it could possibly be a street light somewhere on the horizon. It doesn't move, and after driving and keeping an eye on it, I pull in and take a few pictures with my cell phone. Suddenly the light moves to my right and disappears. When I pass Brædstrup, I see the light again briefly, when I come to a place with a good view of the sky. After that I don't see it again. I wonder what it was?

Could it be the ISS? This beautiful evening, my wife and I are sitting on the balcony, we naturally also look at the evening sky, birds flying and the like. I have not seen this observation before. The time is 21.04, the field of view is from south to north-northwest. In this field of vision, I spot an object that my wife also notices. The phenomenon glides across the sky, from a southerly direction to the north-northwest, slightly slower than an airplane, the height is approx. 10 o'clock on the clock face. The craft appears dark in the sky, which is illuminated by the setting sun. Seen for approx. 3 minutes Observed through binoculars, it almost looked like a lying banana with a sail. Attempts to capture it on video failed.

They then fly in a southerly direction and probably turn "ass" towards me in a westerly course and disappear. You then see that more people come up above the house horizon approx. west-north-west across the houses at Amerikaj. Coming up here and being clear is to me a sign that they are either flying low or taking off in close proximity. There wasn't much that made it UFO-like in flight style or appearance: just lines of light from planes. But the direction these planes came from in a combined group of approx. 8 in something that looked like close moving on a random Saturday night, I think seemed special. It could easily be a plane, but then you know for sure.

We sat on the ground by a garage door and talked. We looked up and observed an object, approx. 10-15 meters above our heads. It "stood" quietly over our heads for approx. 1½ - 2 minutes. After this, it moved slowly to the south-east and again slowed down further after approx. 25-30 meters, this took approx. 4 minutes, after which it "flew"/"floated" away at a very high speed and disappeared. The object was completely silent from its appearance until its disappearance.

We had been out with our horses at 18.28, when we 18.31 saw something most strange in the sky. It was round, flashing - not like an aviator, but it was round and there were 5 lights that weren't flashing. They were light (off-white), otherwise approx. 2 red - 2 blue, 3 green and 1 yellow - it was hard to see as it was dark and high in the sky. When one was almost gone - i.e. that it flew on towards the north-east - there came one that looked just - very slightly - bigger (of course a little bigger :). They flew in the same direction, and we will never forget this. We stopped - we have seen a program about UFOs, they said that you should stop and manage to remember as much as possible - we also tried this.

I just stumbled across this site. Basically thought it was closed, had seen something on TV about it. I've thought about reporting the incident countless times, so now it's happening to the best of my ability. 2 classmates and I were standing at the end of my parents' barn talking one summer evening. Suddenly we saw 2 oval, luminous objects sailing across the sky, slightly offset from each other. It was going pretty fast, faster than low-flying aircraft, and it was unlike anything we'd seen before. We saw all three of them and we were speechless. I haven't really talked to anyone about it, apart from the immediate family, because no one believes in such a thing. The year is around 1960. What I wrote in the form is what I believe is correct. I heard that someone had been seen over Esbjerg that same day, but at the time I didn't know where to go with my knowledge. This is as I remember it. It is etched in my memory because what we saw was so unusual and fantastic. I am glad to be told so that I do not pass away without passing on the observation.

I have now experienced something flying 2 times. It's about something black that moves quickly past my house. It's great, but this only happens at night. All I can see is a black silhouette with 2 bright stripes. It floats by silently.

properties.Colors: rød, guld, grønlig, hvid og blå
properties.content: At approx. 22.55 I go out into the backyard. Quickly sees a "light" in the sky that I have never seen before. It changes color so quickly that it almost flickers. I call my girlfriend out and she looks the same as I do. We stand together and look for approx. 10-15 min. After that, I call a friend who, like me, has an interest in space. After some persuasion, he also goes out into his garden and looks. He sees the same thing as my boyfriend and I. He also confirms that there should be no planets in that area. After that I grab hold of my father. Both him and my mother go out and see the same as the rest of us. I look, initially, at the incident intensely for approx. 30 minutes Here it does not move at all. When I come out again approx. 30 minutes later. Has it moved significantly, but otherwise behaves in the same way. This time I look for about 5-10 min. Comes out one last time approx. 30 minutes later again. Here it has moved even more significantly both vertically and horizontally. I have taken quite a few pictures and film clips, but unfortunately all with the iPhone xs, as I have no equipment for anything else. On both film and photos, the changing colors are clear. I hope to hear from you. As it was quite a special experience and I am very curious as to what it may have been.

I was standing with my friend waiting for her father there at 18.45 on 11/10-10. Suddenly we see 3-4 luminous and round objects coming at a speed from east to west, faster than airplanes, and almost have a fire-like streak (very short) behind them. Neither my father nor my friend's father believed us. My mom saw it too but wasn't convinced until we saw a video here today from East El Pasto where there were others who had seen something similar. It lasted approx. 30 min., after which it disappeared.

A white blinding light that came from a single point, almost a prolonged flash effect. It illuminated the area we see from the window, garden and field. We were awake because the dog had just entered through the cat flap.

4 reddish specks came from the west in the sky and towards the north and disappeared. They were followed side by side 2 and 2 with a larger gap. I found myself on Østergade in Hadsten and looked to the northwest

Have occasionally observed some strange objects in the air over the fields near our house. What I have seen are large round ball-like objects hanging low in the sky and flashing or glowing in red, yellow and orange colors, but it spins rapidly and goes up and down in the sky alternately. I actually just put these observations away and forgot all about them until this evening I again observed the same phenomenon over the field. Right now it's actually still there, but just further away than it was last time. Trying to take a picture. I would like to know what it is? Am actually quite skeptical about UFOs, meeen still thinks this phenomenon is quite strange by now. Here where we live, there are also rumors that our neighbor (a now deceased old lady) has repeatedly said that she has been abducted by what she then called aliens, etc., etc. We have laughed at that story several times. times, but I have to admit, I think it's starting to seem a bit mysterious.

I was standing on the balcony smoking a cigarette when I spotted a constant red light in the sky, slightly larger than the brightest stars. The first 5 min. not moving at all. Then it changed to a green light and flew at high speed in an S shape down towards the ground. It circled behind a factory where it flew up over the roof of the factory, stood still for 30 seconds and then flew down behind the factory again. It then changes back to red and flies in a southerly direction, far down and close to the ground.

We go out into the garden to smoke a "goodnight smoke" around 10.30pm. Since "P" knows about the Perseids later this month, we stand looking at the sky. We live in the countryside with no light from the city or street lights, and therefore have a perfect view. "P" spots an object that moves "jerky" and has many changes of direction.. It flies high in the sky and is relatively far away. The speed at which it flies varies. It flashes in shades of red and blue. It disappears after a few minutes in a northerly direction. "P" has not finished smoking and therefore stays in the garden when another object comes into view. This time a little closer. Same movement pattern, change of direction and blue/red colors. "P" gets to call "S" and we both stand and watch it for 15-20 minutes, after which we go inside and go to bed. It was guaranteed to be neither a plane, a satellite, nor a meteor, as "P" has studied the night sky many times and knows the sight of satellites, shooting stars, etc.

I spotted a large "star" which turned out to be moving very slowly in an easterly direction. A ball of light came loose and sped five or six degrees to the east to be extinguished. A shooting star, I thought, but in a strange direction. This repeated 3 times (so a total of 4) while I was standing there. No sound.

I was standing outside smoking when I saw a white flat thing come flying and it quickly disappeared again, but kept coming for the next approx. two hours and all the time in the same place, kept quiet and looked away....

What has made me wonder a lot about and report the following is that the object, which otherwise with a little good will could have been a drone, helicopter or something else, disappeared "into thin air" in a way that none of the flying things I know of are capable of. I was a passenger (in the front seat) in a car, driving in a westerly direction on the Silkeborg motorway (route 15) just after 17 (to the best of my knowledge it was 17.05-17.07). We were approx. 500 m. before exit 23, i.e. just before the Boar. The sky was completely cloudless and there was full sun. Here I became aware of a "thing" in the sky directly in front of us, ie. due west or slightly more north, 30-35 degrees above the horizon. The most remarkable thing about the object was that it was incredibly glossy/shiny. I would immediately describe the color as chrome/silver, but the surface reflected the sun's rays so much that the object was almost bathed in light, which means that I cannot be sure of the color (it may have been a very light light blue), as well as the shape was also difficult to see due to the strong reflected light. However, I got the impression that the form was "complex", i.e. it was not smooth, "closed" or symmetrical, but appeared to have "things" protruding from the center, especially in the part of the object facing the earth. Since I couldn't estimate how far away the object was, I also can't estimate its size (if it was the size of a helicopter, it might have been 300m away, but it could also have been bigger and further away or smaller and closer). I looked at the object for 2-3 seconds, then I looked away for a split second, triggered by something in the traffic or something the driver of the car said, and when I turned my gaze back to the place in the sky where the object had actually been less than a second before, it was gone! As I said, the sky was completely blue without a cloud, and at the place in question there is a completely clear view of the sky (there is a tall mast in Klank just south of highway 195, but it has nothing to do with the observation, as the object was significant further south in relation to it). No drone, helicopter, plane, bird, balloon or anything else that I know of can fly away so quickly or, as seems to be the case, suddenly become invisible. I therefore cannot explain what it was that I saw (the driver of the car was concentrating on driving and did not see the object) and I would really like an explanation.

I was standing out in the garden having a cigarette when a strong flash caught my attention out of the corner of my eye. There was a series of flashes at intervals, as seen from an aviator, however the interval varied slightly. Blinking also moved like a flier from right (north east) over to left, also at varying speed. At first I just thought it was an airplane, but it moved illogically and was impossible to follow with the eyes, as it was as if it was jumping around. It disappeared out of sight behind a house and soon after, another one came from the same side, exactly as before, while the last one reappeared shortly after. I saw what I believe were 3 objects at the same time in different locations. I think there could be practice at the air base at Nørresundby, it must be in that direction, but the illogical speed and interval make me write here, as it seems unbelievably mysterious and I would like to hear a possible explanation. Sometimes it could actually look like anti-aircraft guns like you see in movies. It's a little hard to explain. After half an hour or so I went in, don't know how long after or before, it has been going on. One thing is for sure, there was something moving across the sky, it flashed really violently every now and then, the speed was fast from the right, but the speed decreased further to the left. It varied in both height and speed, there were several objects with the same pattern, and some only appearing as flashes now and then, almost stationary. It was a bit cloudy and some flashes could be seen reflecting in the clouds located between the flashes and my location. Hope there is an explanation.

Was standing outside talking to a friend on the phone, looking up at the sky in a south-facing direction and seeing a V-shaped greyish (with dark/black markings) object without light, hovering at a reasonably high speed. From the time I see it until it disappears in the sky, approx. 2 sec. It must be said that it disappears into thin air, since there was still a clear view of the rooftops. Very fun experience!!

When I have entered the forest a little, I look back that something is coming. I see a large double-decker auto transporter like you see on the autobahn. I wonder how it got there, but went on into the woods and thought no more of it. As I am on my way out of the forest a little over half an hour later, I can from a distance, approx. 200-300 m, see that the big car is still there, and that on top of that, a few meters above the other smaller lights, it had turned on a powerful light that lit up the parking lot without me being able to see the car itself. While I go and try to see what it is, I mostly think about police work, or some road light maintenance. However, the bushy light is lower than the street lights and partly stronger and whiter than the street lights. I look to see if there is anyone (police) standing by my car, (which is on the opposite side of the parking space at Skovvej). When I come out of the forest on a path 50-80 meters from the car park. I don't know how many seconds I look, but I notice that there is no one by my car and now that I have come out to the road, I want to see what it is that is holding the parking lot. There is now no light at the parking lot and the parking lot is empty. A huge car transporter etc. would under no circumstances be able to get away so quickly and without a sound. In addition to the large light that illuminated the area, there were several smaller rectangular white lights, these placed partly horizontally (mostly) and some that were slanted (about 45 degrees). It was the placement of these smaller lights that made me think of a double-decker car transporter. It was only afterwards that I thought that such side lights would not be white.

Sitting on the balcony on the 13th floor in Lyngby and looking at the stars. Three red "balls" come from the south at a distance from each other and disappear out of my field of vision at approx. 3-5 seconds. The sky was clear and they flew incredibly fast. Can see many kilometers ahead from the 13th floor, but they were gone in no time. Just can't forget it. Airplane star satellites etc. Can't it possibly be... hmmmmmm weird

Approx. 23:05 I go to sleep as I look out the window and up at the sky. There I see something that looks like a twinkling star. But it is quite large and seems very close to what a star usually is. It is still quite bright, and there are no other stars visible in the sky, which is completely cloudless. For 2 min I look and generally think it's a star. But then I think it moves a little to the right, and I make a fixed point with my finger, and after 10-15 sec. it moves straight up. But slowly. After a few seconds. I move my finger, as it is clear that it is moving. After 20 sec. approx. is it out of my field of vision, which is the window. I no longer cling to it and sleep. It twinkled yellow/orange.
Randomly looks up in the sky and sees a bright ball flying fast forward, after a few minutes another one comes.

We drive by car from Sorø to Slagelse by road. Between Sorø and Slagelse, it is as if there is a cloud formation hanging to the left over the car's windscreen - it looks like a jellyfish. It hangs in the same place all the way to Slagelse and spins around itself. At Slagelse we turn off onto the motorway, where we can see that it is to the right of the car as we come down onto the motorway. I see this first and ask my co-passenger, a 14-year-old, if she can see the cloud to the left of the car. She can see the same thing, and her explanation is that she could see something spinning around herself - like an Aquarius. We were quite insecure - thought it was totally sour, so we didn't take any pictures as we didn't dare!

At approx. 22:25, on 04-04-2017 I see two strongly luminous spots moving slowly in a southerly direction over a cloudless sky. I look towards the east, and the spots can be seen approx. 45 degrees up in the sky with a constant distance of approx., which corresponds to 4 cm when I measure with two fingers in an outstretched arm. All the time with the same distance - right after each other. Luminous first approx. 20 sec. as powerful as the strongest "star" in the sky (Jupiter). After this, both spots lose brightness at the same time and become very weak and difficult to see, but they continue the path - right on the heels of each other in exactly the same path. In total, I observe the two bright spots for 1:30 to 2 min. - they eventually become so faint that I can no longer see them. I would estimate that they move approx. 20 degrees across the sky during this time - so very slowly. It was a very clear night sky - without visible clouds, and a few seconds later I observe an elongated shooting star in almost the same orbit, but in the opposite direction - without it disappearing behind clouds.

Just heard that the Norwegian Armed Forces have released older information about UFO sightings. Of course, I was curious to see if my own would be included. It is, but rather lacking compared to what I and my then 8-year-old daughter saw on the way home from a friend's house. We come walking across the lawn, enjoying the lovely evening and suddenly look up. Is something huge standing, hanging or flying in the sky? My daughter gets very scared, grabs my hand, and wants to run home, which we do. Unlocks the door, runs to the west-facing window, and we see that it is still "hanging" there. We stand and observe the large object for about 5 minutes, after which I call Værløse Airport in a sort of helplessness, because they must be able to register something on a radar screen, I thought! The fact that I got that thought must be because my father worked precisely with radars at the Air Station. The object my daughter and I saw was round, cylindrical and almost curved on the "underside". On the side or around were what I would call windows, and from these windows streamed a strong, almost white light. It was very, very spacious, and my daughter and I talked about it being at least as big as a jumbo jet, except for the shape. At the top sat a thing that resembled the fruit of a maple tree, but just huge. I missed my camera - it came with my husband when I got divorced - so I tried to borrow it from my neighbor, but unfortunately she wasn't home. I ran back to my apartment, not wanting to miss the weirdest, most amazing sight I've ever seen! Overall, I would guess that I spoke to a man from the Airport for approx. 10 minutes We had the pleasure of observing the heavenly body, which today I will call an airship, for about 25 minutes, after which it disappeared very strongly and with a "loud, thin" sound towards the north-west. Of course, I can talk to my daughter about the incident, and it has also happened that I have told about it to a select few, but I cannot rid myself of a feeling of frustration at having seen something that not very many can nod in recognition. That is why I was happy to find that the Norwegian Armed Forces have released a number of reports, but saddened that so many of the details that I described to the man on the phone have not been included at all. So we, my daughter and I saw: Clearly and clearly in detail, a very, very large round, cylindrical, almost round at the bottom, object, with luminous "window parts", and with a maple fruit-like, screw-like object at the top. Back then in 1984, we talked about if there could be people in it, it could hold a few hundred, but it is very difficult to judge the size ratio of a large thing in the air that you have never seen before. I remember that my daughter was scared during the experience, and didn't much care to talk about it for a long time afterwards. I myself still feel weird about this experience, which of course I know is completely true, but I wish I could talk about it without having to fear that people will think it's all just vivid imagination.

I was standing in the parking lot at Skamlingsbanken. A strong yellow/orange light was spotted in the direction of the Lillebæltsbroerne. But not as far away as the bridges. In the beginning, the light is not so high in the sky. Only a few degrees. Then it moves to the east/southeast quietly and slowly becomes weaker. I couldn't hear anything, although I suspect the light is only between 5-8 km away. There was almost no wind and clear skies.

A pyramid-shaped object appeared in such a way that the stars disappeared where it was. It blocked the light of the stars and then its shape could be seen. A fairly large cloud disappeared behind it and reappeared on the other side, giving an excellent picture of its shape. We had forgotten all about the experience until we saw an ad on You Tube and realized what we had seen. I hope you can use my information for something. From our bedroom we have a clear view of the spire on Godthåb's Church tower, and the object flew behind the tower and emerged again. It flew very slowly, but it was too dark to see if it was rotating or something else. My wife observed two stars disappearing and reappearing and the cloud that appeared out of nowhere. I was the one who alerted her that something was up. None of us wanted to believe what we had seen straight away either when we read in the newspaper about the visit to Moscow, but when we saw the pictures on "You Tube" we recognized the outline of what we had seen. Unfortunately, we have not written down the exact date.

We sat in our yacht and enjoyed the first warm summer evening of the year. At 22:55 I saw two "bright stars" appear above the treetops on the Funen side. The two "bright stars" came into view right in the middle of the faint red evening glow that was still in the sky. We now saw that the one "bright star" was moving towards us, and I was sure that it was an airplane where the "strobe light" had turned into a fixed light. Approx. 90 seconds later, another "bright star" appeared on the horizon, right next to the "bright star", which was still completely still in the sky. After another 90 seconds, another "bright star" appeared in exactly the same place where the others had come. I hastened to get my binoculars, as the first "bright star" was now approaching on a course directly above our heads, and I could now see with the naked eye that these were no ordinary airplanes (I have a pilot's license myself). With my binoculars I could see pretty much nothing but a large orange/brown light that appeared to have a clear core and it looked like the light was reflecting in a parabola. The "bright star" passed directly above us at greater speed than a sports pilot can achieve. When the "bright star" had passed us, and I was still following it in the binoculars, it was as if something shaded the orange/brown light and the object was now completely darkened (about 45 sec after it had passed directly above our heads). As I was now not "dazzled" by the light, I could now clearly see the outline of the object and easily follow it for a further 45 seconds. I'm sure the objects were not fitted with wings as I know them. Exactly the same procedure happened a total of 10 times, in an unbroken streak (fantastic experience). Despite it being a quiet evening, there was no sound at all from the objects. The 10 overflights lasted approx. 15-20 min., and while we were looking at the scenery, 2 airplanes crossed the course of the objects, but at a higher altitude. However, not louder than we could clearly hear the engines from the planes. We sat and discussed our experience and looked at the last "bright star" for approx. 40 minutes, during which it stood motionless in the sky. At exactly 23:55 the last "bright star" started to move, but it took a north/north north east course and thus did not come over us. This object did not go "dark" like the others when we saw it disappear. Exactly at 24:00 the object disappeared below the horizon. I tried to contact air traffic control in Kastrup, but was referred to the local police, who I contacted and told about our incident. I am sure we saw what I have described and I would be very grateful if you would contact me if there is an explanation for the phenomenon.

A little more than an hour ago (10 to 20 minutes after midnight) I saw a rectangular and bright colored spectra moving in the sky. The spectra were bright orange, bounded below by a green or blue stripe and above by a yellow or light stripe. It moved silently and in the same way as an airplane on the horizon, but it was too big and too angular to be an airplane. When the specter disappeared behind a roof, I ran out into the street to see more. Here I met two young men, one of whom had also observed the spectrum, albeit in a green hue. The other said his dogs had been howling around the same time the friend had seen the spectre.

Comes driving in a car and sees a white glowing star/ball floating from right to left. It doesn't blink, it flies too fast to be a drone and it also lights up very brightly. The object flies past us and suddenly it splits in two for just a few seconds before turning back into a single ball. We're both like "WTF?!" And follow it with our eyes until it's out of sight. We drive around a LOT at night and are used to seeing a little bit of everything in the sky, but none of us have seen it there before.

Standing on the balcony and looking out over the city. Sees a plane (I assume) coming from the east and flying west. It lights up normally. white light but can't see it flashing either since it has passed. When the plane has passed, 3 white/yellow lights come on, which rotate around one after the other quite quickly. They follow the plane for approx. 3 sec., still spinning around as they play, and turn off or disappear. I don't manage to get my camera as it went very fast. The plane was approx. 8-10 min about the overflight from east to west, and the 3 lights approx. 30 sec... for the same distance...

I saw some very bright light and it looked like it was spinning a bit as the cones of light changed from being elongated to short. They came from the south and were not as high up as a plane. They flew north and flew higher and higher, but I could still see the light from them. Eventually they were gone. There was no sound from them at all and thought maybe it was a drone but I'm thinking maybe drones fly that high.

My colleague and I followed a flying object from a black dot on the horizon that got bigger and bigger. It floated completely silently and was far down. It was pitch black with no light or sound. It was a bit elongated and maybe looked like a person flying with their arms close to their body. It was like nothing we had ever seen before. It flew very far down over our heads and not a sound came from it. We followed it until it was gone on the horizon. It was hovering or flying at a slow and steady speed and we were honestly a bit depressed for the rest of the evening. Do you have any idea what it could be.

Looking through the window a "big New Year's rocket" with a shining whitish tail, moving "the wrong way" - from above and diagonally downwards. Think it might be a small "meteor stone"? The light can be a reflection of low sun against an otherwise dawn blue sky. I would assume the "impact" could be in an area near Thorø Huse.

I was out for a walk with my mom and her dog when I see a bright white light in the sky that quickly disappears (3-4 seconds), the light did not move but "burned out". I ask my mom if she saw it too, which she did. We talked about how there were a lot of clouds in the sky, but that it was strange that the light didn't come back, as you usually see with planes that disappear behind a cloud. Could be interesting if others saw it too.

Around. At 00:30 we three people sat on the terrace and talked. Suddenly one of us looks up at the sky in a southern direction, where we discover these two bright spots that looked like stars. At first we thought it was two satellites flying parallel to each other, but suddenly they both stopped completely - and started to fly a little uncontrollably: as if they were chasing each other or similar. And poof, they were gone. We were three people who observed it, where some are quite skeptical about UFOs, but none of us could explain it.

I was out walking my little poodle at 23.10. There are fields and cattle, I stand and listen to the birds, and turn to the right, look up, and what I see, I think at first is a helicopter, but no propellers, and no machine sound, but a kind of windy sound , which came from the bottom of it. It glowed red and white, so I thought it belonged to Odense Hospital, but no, it flew right over me. I quickly sent a message to my daughter who was inside on her computer. I was probably startled, but it was no worse. I was wearing a headlamp but took it off and shined it on the object, strange.. it sort of stopped in midair and turned down towards me as if it was observing me for a few seconds. I couldn't manage to set my camera on my mobile but recorded the sound of "it". I stopped lighting it. It turned around and flew towards Lillebælt, that way out of there. Haven't seen anything since. Got curious.

I saw an incredibly large and bright spot in the western sky high in the sky. Then it was white. I've NEVER seen a star shine so bright + this one was moving, plus it was bigger than any star I've seen. As it got lower on the horizon, it began to flash red, and eventually it was an almost constant red. - At that time, however, it was so far away that it can be difficult to assess it exactly. It disappeared relatively quickly behind the horizon. I am not the only one who can come up with the same explanation when I told my parents. They saw the same thing. However, I took my binoculars outside, but I was only able to focus on the object with the scope and thus never got the close-up I had hoped for. I saw the object a little after 23, and it disappeared completely only at 00.10 - this is approx. times, and it could therefore have been a little earlier or a little later.

We stand and look to the south and see two satellites flying 2 cm apart in exactly the same line directly to the north. They first appear above our heads and disappear already after 4 seconds a little further above our heads. Similar to two completely ordinary satellites in light and strength and speed, but a rather strange sight, that they chase each other's ass and disappear very shortly after. They were only visible for approx. 15 cm in the sky, where normal satellites are seen for a longer distance in the sky (80-140 cm in the sky) before disappearing. You know these two satellites that fly so far down and chase each other very close together at exactly the same speed and line? Or was it something unknown?

I started at Ærø Højskole on 17 August 2009. Our principal Henrik Hartvig had a principle that we students were not allowed to drink alcohol the first week we were at school, so it has been the second week we were there, so maybe the last weekend in August. We were 6 people who decided one evening to go out on the town in Ærøskøbing. We walked down Smedegade to reach Vestergade, where there was a small tavern called Arbo. When we were walking down Smedegade, someone suddenly shouted, "hey, try to look up at the sky", and when we looked up, we saw a flying object that flew incredibly close to us, so close that we could see the bottom of the object, it was perfectly flat and had an oval shape, in the middle there was a strong red light as if it shone constantly, it did not pulsate, like on a passenger plane for example. At first it flew fairly slowly, but then suddenly the red light disappeared and the object took off more into the sky flew away at tremendously fast speed, but there was no engine noise at all.

Have experienced the same light, at approx. same time, here it looked like more than a light, and it came from Frederiksberg and flew north (observation was from my balcony facing Jagtvej with a view of Mayor Jensen Allé). Was out getting some fresh air and saw the light, which was bright red at first (like an airplane landing light). When it got close it looked like three red lights. So the first thing was that it was a small plane or a helicopter, the Rigshospitalet is not far away, and I can see a helicopter next day both night and day. But back to this light, then it started behaving differently, there was no sound, and the flashing lights that are on an airplane or a helicopter were missing, which in addition started to slow down and keep still in the air ( like a helicopter), then start to rise and the red lights went out one by one (the possibility that they went up into a cloud cover is high. It was slightly cloudy that night). The funny thing was that a day or two earlier I experienced the exact same thing at about the same time, so the possibility that it is either a helicopter or maybe a drone being tested is high. Have fun with UFO, have always had a great interest in this subject, as all my family members have experienced things that lie under the UFO concept. It took off when I had to read the New Testament for my confirmation and discovered that this is actually the best UFO book ever written (after that the conversation with the priest was so much fun). But since I was simultaneously dealing with film, photography and lighting on a semi-professional level and then on a professional level, I could start sorting through the films, video and photos that are there and find a logical explanation, and that has given me the knowledge that probably 99% of UFO sightings can be explained logically. And today with cell phone cameras, it is true that more UFO videos and photos are taken, but the quality, especially at night, is of such poor quality that it can't actually be used for anything, plus today there are more funny man-made things flying around the air. There is speech and military and civilian drones (where you experiment with swarm, both within military and civilian drones). It is certain that drone flying is developing into the aerial version of crop circles, that is, that you do not want to come forward, as what you have done is often illegal (have used a drone within a built-up area and in a far too high altitude), and the people who do it often get a cheap laugh when the so-called UFOs come on TV and more. Also, the Chinese hot air balloon has become very widespread in the West. So yes, I am interested in UFOs, but do not believe in UFOs, after several years of studying this, the only thing that can convince me that UFOs really exist is if I have a third degree close contact, and i am able to prove it with prof video and photo otherwise not. But I am amazed at how many people throw money at authors and lecturers, who are often nice people with a high education, whose only purpose is to make a lot of money by throwing pure gas at people who really believe in it. Maybe you should write an article about drones and about drone swarm flight, as they are seen both night and day.
6 pieces. objects flew past each other and spread out and disappeared. They have been seen 4 times so far here.

I was out looking for the "Lyrids" meteor shower. I lie on a bench and regret not driving further away to avoid light pollution. But as I lay there I see 5-6 VERY dimly lit objects flying across the sky at very high speed. Maybe 10-15 times faster than satellites (and birds), and in a straight line formation. Maybe it could be that visual disturbance where you see dots, but never have I experienced them having such a consistent speed and straight formation (and I hadn't looked at lamps of any kind for over an hour). I have previously doubted whether I have seen anything unidentified, but logically dismissed it as birds or planes. But this experience is truly inexplicable to me.

My husband, daughter and I saw something strange (at least we think so). We were on our way from Brøndby to Copenhagen Ø via the Helsingør Motorway. At approx. 21.10 close to Herlev we saw a flying thing in the sky. It was quite large, with a LOT of light in front, it actually lit up some of the sky and clouds. It had white light on the two "side wings" and red light at the back. It was more wide than long. None of the lights blinked, everything shone with uniform power. It was sort of shaped like an airplane, only it wasn't as long as one at all. It was VERY wide on the other hand. It wasn't flying anywhere - and it was especially that and then the VERY bright light that caught our interest. It didn't disappear while we were looking at it, and we could probably follow it approx. 3-4 minutes. At first we thought it was a helicopter, but it was far too big for that. I have asked Flyvertaktisk Kommando, but no official explanation can be given for this.

When I wanted to walk my dog on the evening of 18/02 2008 at 20:40, a strange white light that hung almost directly above me caught my eyes. At first I took it to be an unusually bright star, but soon realized that the object was moving. My sense of logic told me that my eyes were playing tricks on me, that I was most likely just imagining that there was movement, and that maybe it was actually me that was moving and not the object, since I know how easily you can be fooled by stars and the like. Furthermore, it can be difficult to determine whether something is moving or not when you don't really have a fixed point. However, I could tell that the object was moving when I had to turn to keep sight of it. Again my brain kicked in and told me it must be a plane. But even this thought I had to give up when the object suddenly accelerated very quickly, heading north. The story could well end here, but the truth is that it only begins here. Before I continue my story, there are just a few things I need to get straight. I live in a place where we often see planes, both propellers, fighters, helicopters and very often scheduled planes, heading towards Billund airport, and we have never had difficulty identifying planes and other air traffic for what they were. This evening, however, something happened that neither I nor my wife had ever seen or experienced before. As described earlier, the luminous object disappeared in a northerly direction at a speed I have never seen an aircraft move at before. Naturally I was surprised, but at the time did not attach any particular importance to the observation. This changed, however, when at the same time I saw several similar objects coming from the southeast and rapidly approaching. At this point I decided to call my wife who was inside the house. Pretty soon after she was out by my side and together we now watched about 20 to 25 very bright and white lights cross the sky about directly above us. They kept a mutual distance and speed to each other, without at any time changing formation. It should just be added that they were not in close formation, but had several hundred, or maybe even a thousand meters between them, (depending on how high up you would judge the objects to be. Our assessment was that they were very high up!). Still, it wasn't hard to see that they kept the same speed and formation. We followed the luminous objects from their appearance in the southeast until they disappeared out of our sight to the north. Just for the record, I will try to describe the weather this evening, which I would describe as slightly cloudy and with a bit of wind. I am fully aware that stars that sometimes disappear behind a cloud could easily be mistaken for a moving object. I must clearly state here that this could not be the case in any way. (Although I was initially tempted to use this explanation myself, for lack of a better one.) But the movements of these objects were so pronounced that we had to turn approx. 180 degrees around our own axis, in order to follow the flight of these objects across the sky. I would also like to point out that after these "luminous objects" disappeared beyond our field of vision, we could ascertain that no stars could be seen in the sky. What I was trying to illustrate by this, of course, is that it would be natural to assume that if we had mistakenly taken stars to be luminous objects in motion, then there would necessarily also be other stars in the sky, which there are not was, and they were unlikely to disappear completely. Furthermore, one could clearly see the movement of the objects in relation to the moon, which was clear in the sky this evening. Before I completely end my rather long story, there are just a few more facts that I must include. First, these objects, as I call them, were completely clear and white. They neither blinked nor changed their appearance in any other way. Normal airplanes, which, as previously mentioned, we often see, both during the day, evening and night, are always equipped with flashing lights (red and green, starboard and port lights). This was not the case this evening. Also, normally when we see an aircraft approaching Billund, these are almost always using the same approach corridor, or whatever we should call it. These objects were nowhere near what we would consider an approach to Billund. Thirdly. When we see aircraft on approach, or aircraft in general, the observation is almost always followed by distinct engine noise. Either at the same time or shortly after the sighting of an aircraft. This evening there were absolutely no engine noises to be heard of any kind. Neither before, during nor after the observation. Everything happened completely and utterly silently. One final piece of information I haven't gotten into yet is that the sighting lasted for about 10-15 minutes, from the time I noticed the first object until we lost sight of the last one. My wife participated in the observation from the time I called her out. This was approx. halfway, i.e. after 5-7 minutes.

Looking at this very black sky and seeing what look like triangles and noticing that they are standing still. After looking for several minutes, I see that there is no movement, so I take some pictures. You have to enlarge the photo.

Goes out on my balcony, looks up at the stars, suddenly sees a white light coming across the sky, and due to its greater height, it must be something moving at high speed.. The light flies over towards Roskilde, and disappears with a snap of the fingers..! Subsequently, another light comes from the same direction, and moves in the same direction, but a much stronger light.. I confirmed that there was NO flashing or similar. These are 2 observations shortly after each other! My conclusion is that it was far too fast to be a plane.. Far too long to be a shooting star.

On the way to work, drive from the center of Silkeborg via Århusvej towards the gml. Resenbro crossing. In the sky hangs something that resembles a powerful star in brightness, but 2-3 times larger. The light slowly fades out, the object becomes more metallic/gray in appearance and slowly merges with the blue background in the sky. From my perspective field of vision, it is 2-3 mm big after the light has completely gone out. The sky was December clear with few clouds in the sky. The object was very clear. It appeared that the object was located well behind the few clouds in the sky. The object did not move - but it was visible for too short a time for me to identify whether it was moving slowly or whether it was a (very) strong reflection from e.g. a satellite.
Ball of light with varying speed, rapidly changing direction (minor degrees) coming from a southerly direction, becoming less and less visible and disappearing near the star Vega.
Recorded 2 luminous balls on video - they came one after the other with approx. 30 sec distance.

I was standing in my front yard just past midnight when I saw this orange spot of light moving quickly and silently across the sky. I've never seen anything like this before, so it surprised me a bit. The speed was very similar to a fighter plane, but there were no flashes and it was completely silent.

It started with a small oblong bright dot in the sky, it flew almost diagonally across the sky at a speed that did not resemble that of an airplane, and it did not have the white streaks hanging behind it. It was definitely not a bird as it was clearly flying above some clouds and there was NO movement on the object. There I and 6-7 other people stood watching the object when it disappeared again in a cloud. 2 minutes later the object reappeared like a bolt from a clear sky and began some, for an aircraft, insane turns and was far more maneuverable than other aircraft I have seen. Then it disappeared again into the now clear sky.

Thursday 16-7-2015 at 21:07 I stood out in the garden and looked at the beautiful evening sky. The clouds were really high and the air was clear. I wanted to make a small approx. 1 min film on my new phone Microsoft 640. I made the film and stood approx. 10 minutes afterwards and looked up at the beautiful sky and I didn't notice any UFOs in the sky. The next day I watched the film and saw that there was something wrong with the recording, there were 4 small lines in the film. Opened the VLC player, pressed several times the - key so that the movie played slowly, select full screen 1920, with approx. 1 second at a time. Then the four small lines became a UFO. After that I looked through the whole film and found one more UFO that was close to me, and on the film you can see 7 maybe 10 other UFOs in the distance like little dots flying up and down from the clouds. These UFOs fly at a tremendous speed and are therefore difficult to see with the naked eye. With all those UFOs, I'm thinking that we might just have had a nice visit from the outside.

Noticed stationary object when we were looking at swallows. At first thought it was a bird. But it stood still. It looked like it was welding a bit from side to side. We talked about it being a drone. But I fly a drone pro myself. So I think I can be ruled out. Both height and shape as well as movement did not seem right. Nor the size of the background of the distance. It hung there and swayed then moved a little to the west. I had taken pictures there with the iPhone. And thought "to get the camera". 30 seconds. And then it was gone. Photo taken. When zooming in on the photo, the shape can be seen. No flight. Drone. Bird. Planet. Maybe a UFO.?
Observed 2 green lights flashing. After ½-1 minute the lights moved to the southwest and disappeared.

My wife and I were on our way from Skjern towards Tarm, when on our left we see 3 luminous balls, which alternately flash out and come back again. It's a bit interesting, I think and find a parking lot where we observe the phenomenon. It looks like smoke is coming from the balls and at the same time it looks like lightning is coming from the ground. The orbs don't seem to change height at all and after some time they disappeared as quickly as they had come.

Is just a slip out in the garden, which faces south. It has been raining and it is completely dark when I see a white/red light coming from the south. At first I think it's a helicopter, but there's no sound at all and no flashing lights. It flies at about the same height as a helicopter, maybe a little higher. However, the speed is slightly faster. Then thought it might be a small plane, but again no engine noise or flashing lights. I follow it a bit in its progress, when I discover another one on the same route. After a very short time, 3 completely identical ones appear, which also disappear in the same way. This is how approx. 10 pcs. up to a total of 1-2-3 pcs. at a time, completely silent with a stationary light and the same route. Of course, no more came when I finally got enough presence that I decided to get my binoculars. However, I had my mobile in my pocket, but those pictures only show small bright dots in the sky, nothing where you could possibly could see what it was. There is probably a natural explanation for the phenomenon, but what puzzled me was the lack of sound and that the lights did not flash like they do on airplanes and helicopters.
There are two observations. At the time of observation, the moon was due south 180 degrees and with a height of approx. 45-50 degrees.

Saw out of the window over the fields 2 lights, alternately flying forward just as one was behind and overtook the other. It turned on and off. Was white and red. There are fields and then water. As far as I could see, it was over the water. There are no boats there, but it also went too fast. What was it. Has been quite light lately.

Friday late evening, probably around 23:00-23:30, my boyfriend and I lie in bed and look at the stars. We are caught by two stars. At least they look a bit like (haha) stars, they are just as "indistinct" and shine in exactly the same way - i.e. not strong and artificial and no flash. The only difference is that they move. Fast - not satellite speed. They are to start with completely parallel to each other and move at exactly the same speed. After covering a certain distance they come closer to each other and suddenly it is as if they are playing with each other, close to each other, further apart, around each other. They disappear from our view behind some trees after about ten minutes.

I was with my friend on the way from Frederikshavn to Jerup, where I live: Just before Strandby we saw a red flashing light over the forest. It looked like it was going to land, but then it flipped over and we spotted the port and starboard red lights. We stopped the car and turned off the engine. We could hardly hear any noise from the vessel. It came whizzing at high speed towards the car and flew over Strandby harbor and turned around again. We then started the car and drove 500 metres.
