Then it came back again, made a quick glance, flew out over the sea again, continued north and disappeared. As the craft made the loop, we could see a lot of white lights below it. It also had some sort of wings which were also filled with light. We agreed that it was a UFO, as small planes can't go down that far.

Three objects above the address Fredericia further above Strib/Fyn. More elongated than round. They were between the clouds, but the speed seemed too great to be birds. It was just after sunset, 15 min. The light was very constant until they seemed to disappear over Funen. The rear rotated or moved more. The front two kept the formation.

Comes driving from Birkerød towards Blovstrød and approx. 500 meters before you can turn left towards the Høvelte barracks, there was suddenly a strong green beam of light that flickers around the road just like a laser beam. First in the opposite lane and then straight across our lane. I continue towards Blovstrød, but can see the green beam in the rearview mirror, and it continues to flutter around. It comes down vertically, and there are no planes in the air to be seen, and it cannot be from something high up, where possibly. you could make something fun out of it. I watched it for at least 30 seconds. in the rearview mirror, and the boys sat and looked out the back. They couldn't see any planes or anything either, but the green beam of light seemed to be searching for something.

A flashing white light, like that of a helicopter, came gliding across the sky, silently, at high speed. the vessel itself was hidden in low-hanging clouds, so that I could see only the light. Maybe there was a faint hint of the outline, but not sure. When it appeared I thought it was a helicopter until I saw it move in jerks. Never seen an aircraft move like that. Unfortunately it was only visible for 3-4 seconds.

Wednesday 18 February at 11.00 I see a large plane with four engines and the resulting white streaks in the sky, it is cloudless weather, and I can see the tail fin is red on the jumbo, possibly an SAS plane on its way to Billund? The plane has direction from south to north. In a westerly direction below the plane, I then see a smaller flying oblong object, however, this has no white streaks behind it, the object has a direction from south-west to north-east and moves relatively slowly, for approx. 45 degree elevation. My own unauthorized explanation is that it could possibly be the International Space Station ISS that I have observed - but is this possible on a bright February morning???

There were a lot of us watching for Sputnik. Suddenly two luminous discs came to a stop in the sky. They hung and dove up and down. Suddenly a long cylindrical tube with conical blunt ends came from the west. The discs disappeared into the middle of the tube and were gone. Was mentioned in the Vejle County Gazette. Was also seen in Norway.

In a thinly clouded sky, a large diffuse object appears below Capella. Movement h towards v and obliquely down towards the horizon in a straight or slightly downward curved path. Acts as bright light that illuminates the clouds from behind. For brief moments, obj is seen between clouds as a vertical compound arc-shaped streak of light, with the arc at the front. disappears low, but fades beyond the horizon. Orbit speed as a satellite. Diameter measured as little finger in outstretched arm, like the full moon. Also seen in 10x40 prism binoculars. To the naked eye, the diffuse area looks like a waning crescent moon on the horizon. Seen by three independent groups with a total of 7 people. There are drawings from several observers. Note in the desert at Anholt after the DarkSky arrangement. There was a German naval vessel, the frigate Al Aziz, in that direction according to the MarineTraffic app, en route Kiel-Wilhelmshafen.
Observing something in the sky hovering over lampposts. I rush to take 3 pictures with my mobile phone.

We clearly see a bright red light on the horizon. My first thought was that it was a plane flying in our direction and that the backlight looked a little too red. My girlfriend's first thought was that it was a flare, so we waited for it to start descending and light up the sky. But instead the light continued at an angle of approx. 80-85 degrees up towards the sky. The light grew smaller and smaller until it was the size of one of the average stars in the night sky, then it moved exactly like a satellite, constantly speeding across the sky without changing direction. The red light grew larger and larger in circumference, but at the same time more blurred. In the last millisecond before it suddenly and disappeared.

Was out with the dog and admired the starry sky. Spots a "star" moving, initially in a straight line at high speed and appearing at high altitude. Suddenly it moves in jerks and after a few minutes, it seems to shake and disappear abruptly. Thought maybe it was a shooting star, but not when seen lasts this long and behaves like that.

I was standing in my garden. Suddenly the object came into view. There was no tail or smoke. At first I thought it was an airplane with its landing lights on, but as it got closer it was a large fireball with a diameter equal to 1/4 that of the moon. I took three photos with my iphone 4 and a short video sequence.

2 appeared over the southern horizon while I was out in the yard collecting forgotten drying clothes. One behind the other slightly offset, like a kind of formation. The wings or the whole fuselage were slightly diffused at the edge. They were shaped like a boomerang with the point at the front. Estimated height: maybe 3000 meters.

At At 2.00 in the morning there was a thin cloud cover, where stars were seen here and there. I watched a pillar of light sweep automatically back and forth across the sky covering an angle of approx. 30 degrees. Approx. in the middle of the angle, the column of light hit an object every time it passed. The object lit up brightly every time the pillar of light hit it. The object, which was motionless, looked almost like a very large, upright lens when viewed from the side. The column of light, which turned out to originate from an automatic searchlight at "Skovridergaarden", Charlottenlund, did not linger on the object, and moved quite regularly. Over the next 15-20 minutes the phenomenon became weaker and weaker, finally disappearing.

Let it be said at once. It's been quite a few years since my sister and I saw the mysterious object, but it stuck so well that I still think about it now and then. We were walking in the street, in an ordinary residential area of the small provincial town, when we spotted a triangle-shaped object, which came flying silently and quickly across the sky on a sunny afternoon in June or July. The remarkable thing was that the object was difficult to judge from a distance. Whether it was 50 meters or 2 kilometers away is still unknown. But one thing is certain: the object was completely out of sight after 1 minute - without a sound - and without the characteristic white "tails" that a plane can sometimes drag across the sky. Finally, it should be noted that it was as if everything became strangely still when the object was visible. - Whether it was pure imagination, or whether the object really managed to put an end to the chirping of birds and the whistling of the wind, is not known. But the experience that I still think about took place - sure enough!

A large red-orange light, dull, not brilliant, but "alive" with rays out in all directions, calm movement across the sky, almost the same speed as when you can make out a satellite. Then it slowly disappeared directly away from me, becoming a dot that disappeared. It was 1.5 cm. seen through the fingers of an outstretched arm (I'm 1.75cm tall). Right after the sighting, there were many high-flying planes from different directions, but the planes were only 1/10 the size of the ball of light. I actually heard a buzzing hissing sound but not sure if it was from the glowing orb or from the many airplanes/routers

Date 6/11-2013 I came walking with my dog on my way home. It was dark. As I reached outside my garden gate, I saw a bright orange, glowing ball-like object moving towards me at a low altitude at a steady speed. Suddenly it slowed down and disappeared behind the roof of my house. I went around the garden to see where it had gone and found the object hanging perfectly still above my head. Below, two elongated luminous triangles protruded. There was no sound to be heard. I ran in to get my son so he could see the phenomenon. Meanwhile, it had risen high in the sky and was now moving in a straight line in a northerly direction and suddenly disappeared.

A friend & I often go for walks at night, precisely so that you might be lucky enough to observe something unusual in the night sky. I have binoculars (10-30x60 zoom) with me. Suddenly, in a westerly direction, I spot some white light, which was the landing light from a plane, coming calmly flying WITHOUT engine noise. I use my binoculars, but can see nothing but the white light, which continues to be equally sharp even after it has passed me in an easterly direction, & at least the landing lights of an airplane do not. There was also nothing else to see, such as red/green flashing lights, which you often see on planes. The "UFO" is no higher up than the domestic planes that come (from the east) over Kolding city at night to land in Billund. It would be nice to find out what the object was.

On a walk outside, the three of us were looking up at an unusually starry sky and noticed a "moving star" (without flashing lights and the same size as a "normal" star). At first glance it was just a satellite judging from the light and the movement, but it suddenly changed direction several times in quick succession in a serpentine pattern, after which it disappeared in a direct easterly direction in a straight movement (the light disappeared with the movement, hence the high degree indication above the horizon). The reason for this inquiry is that it was not possible to calculate what it was, as both balloons, fireworks and falling parts from space could not have made such a movement with such a sudden change of direction. Nor helicopters/airplanes, as they must have simply been too heavy for such manoeuvres.

I have been approx. 12 or 13 years. My parents and I were out walking our dogs before going to bed. It's been a number of years, so I can't remember the exact time, unfortunately. But it was a pretty special experience. It was completely starry, and very dark. I remember it was quite cold and there was quite a bit of snow. Suddenly we see in the sky, almost directly above our heads, a bright spot that moved with great speed. The spot glowed almost white. My father started talking about a "sputnik" - meaning a satellite, or maybe it was a shooting star. But the spot was just a good deal larger than a sputnik typically sees, and it was moving too slowly to be a shooting star anyway. We stopped because it was a little weird. Suddenly the spot stopped - completely! We were about to lose both our noses and our mouths! It hung there for a while, then changed direction 90 degrees! It then continued at the same speed as before it stopped. It disappeared behind the horizon to the north. We discussed what it could be. There was no engine noise - and it was a very quiet evening. I have since thought about what it could be....but can't find any answers. I have since graduated as an engineer, but nothing I have learned here has been able to explain our observation. The only explanation must be a UFO.....not necessarily from "Mars", but in the sense of the word - an unidentified object.
Dark object observed in binoculars. Quiet, almost stationary to very fast speed in 1 sec. Approx. over Herlev/Gladsaxe.

On the way from Aalestrup to Aalborg. Driving on the main road A13 to the north, and where the A13 cuts through the small forest, Skatskov, I randomly observe a series of lights above the trees. At first I think it's a plane which is very, very far down, but the lights are still and there are no red flashlights. Suddenly the lights move quite slowly across the trees and over the car heading west. There were maybe 6 or 8 lights, placed in a straight line going north - south, and a pulsating orange light further to the left. The location and distance between the row of lights and then the pulsating orange light is just like a triangle. A car was driving behind me, so I couldn't just brake..., but got myself together to roll down the window to hear any noise. sounds. There was no sound, only the screeching of the car's tires, and when I looked to the left, to the west, to see where it disappeared to, there was no light at all, although there were a few trees to obscure the view. I have no idea how big it was, but I would think it was max. 100 meters above the road. I have to say that the lights were not strong, but almost dull yellow.

On Saturday the 22nd, my mother and I experienced something that cannot be explained. At approx. 21.50 three objects appeared in the sky followed by more. We went outside, but it was quiet. They were red changed to blue, as if they were standing still just above the nursing home in Storvorde (almost next door). This lasted for approx. 7 to 10 min. More came one by one. We saw at least 10. We regret so much that we didn't get it recorded, but probably because of the shock and harrowing experience. We can't be the only ones who have seen this ????

Looked like a constellation in slow motion, three-dimensional, disappeared to the northwest. Consisted of approx. 10 luminous units. followed exactly as if they formed the outline of something. At first came directly towards us while we were driving, after which we quickly pulled to the side and got out of the car to get a better look. After that it started to turn to the side or the front, it is not known, and it was as if it was a huge flying thing that changed direction in front of us.

I was waiting for my train when I turned and saw three lights in the sky some distance above the city. They were in a straight line and maybe there was a red or green dot in the middle. It was dark, so I couldn't see anything but the lights. All of a sudden the lights rose very quickly into the air. Then my train arrived and I had to get on. I asked one of my fellow passengers if she had also seen the lights in the sky, but she said it was a plane. Later that day I told my mother about it and she said that it couldn't possibly be a plane that had gone up into the air as quickly as I told it had happened. Also, there was no sound either, which there would have been if it was a plane or a helicopter. When the train moved on approx. five minutes later, the lights were gone.

I was on my way home from my grandmother's, when I had eaten and was almost home, I see a light falling from the sky. At first I thought it was some kind of meteor, which it might be, but just to be sure, I called my grandmother and calmly asked if it was okay for there to be a shooting star that night, and sure enough, it was there, but when my grandmother was about to say something, I became completely silent and speechless, and I almost shouted that "NOW FANTASTIC LIGHTING BALLS ARE FLYING OVER MY HEAD AND IN A TRIANGLE FORMATION". I see that for almost a little over 2 minutes. Then they fly away from me silently... I don't know what I saw that night, but one thing was certain, it was neither a plane nor any light.

Was just out in the garden when I look up, there is a white flying object that glows green and red in the binoculars. Hovering slowly and no sound. After approx. 3 minutes it disappears. It is clear and moonlight. Height is approx. at 10 km altitude very low down. What can it be, satellites are never that far down.

There was nothing to see, but to a large extent something to hear: I was in the entrance hall of my house when I heard a sound like air being pushed through a pipe. I went out into the utility room where there was an air vent. That was where the sound was coming from. Then I noticed that there was indeed a violent draft coming down into the utility room. I went out the door and tried to see where the sound and air flow was coming from, but there was nothing to be seen. Not wanting to be picked up in a spaceship, I went back inside. Then the air flow was significantly reduced. I now opened the door again. The noise now moved in a slow arc away and stopped above a group of old chestnut trees where the noise became stationary. There was absolutely nothing to see. Suddenly I heard the sound make a turn in a northerly direction and it was completely quiet again.

This evening I saw a very powerful luminous object suddenly appear in the night sky, It lit up very brightly. It moved quietly to the east. Soon after, the light grew fainter and fainter until it disappeared. Approx. a minute later it appeared and stood still in the sky for approx. 10 seconds and then disappeared completely. As it is in the direction of billund, I thought it might be a plane with the landing lights on, so I checked my app flightradar on the phone and there was no plane close to billund.

I was on my way to Aabenraa by bus from Sønderborg and had to cross the new bridge. It was at approx. 8.05. As I was about to drive over the bridge, I saw an object next to the bridge. It was completely still in the air, so I drove straight past. I think I was approx. 5-10 m from it, so I saw it really clearly. It looked like a large bicycle helmet with two lights next to each other. It was approx. 60 cm. It was gray with a blue wide stripe down the middle. I drove slowly past it and looked at it really hard. There were cars behind me, so I didn't manage to get a photo of it, unfortunately. There was also another bus and cars in front of me, so they must have seen something too. It was a little below me, so I could see that it had a dark blue broad stripe.. Don't know how long it was there, because it was there after I drove past it. So I didn't see it disappearing…

Was out walking my dog. I look up in the air and see this floating object. It flies relatively fast. Luckily I managed to film it. I have 2 videos of it. Contact me by e-mail if you want to receive the 2 videos.

Driving down Adelers Alle from Fårevejle Kirkeby towards Gislinge, when far out on the road I see something that looks like a star that blinks slowly, but it is not that high up, as it floats under the clouds. I am approx. 5 km away when I see. The one it seems to float from side to side across the road. As I get closer, it falls a good distance to the ground. When I get really close, it hangs over the field approx. 20-25 meters above the ground. Now it no longer flashes, but constantly shines down towards the ground without really lighting up anything. It is approx. 150-200 cm x approx. 100 cm x approx. 40 cm. I drive past, turn the car around, drive back, but there it is gone. It hung in the air over the field off Fjordvej. If what I saw was man-made, I would very much like to be in touch with whoever made the flying thing, as I have worked in the model hobby myself and have never seen any flying model hang in the air like that. There was another car that drove in at Fjordvej to look at the same thing I saw.

I've always dreamed of LYING DOWN and looking at the stars, and yesterday I finally got myself together to make it happen. It came up from behind, where I was lying, as a fast dimly glowing orange thing, headed downwards, where it slowed down and approx. 3 meters above the ground, where it slowly disappeared into the night, (never knew before that what others have seen has also been orange, it was only now right here before I got that information, (by reading about it, in this forum), i.e., I wasn't colored by other people's experience/opinion about what I saw, by the way it seemed a bit creepy, lying there alone in the dark, according to my experience), but it wasn't particularly loud/right far away from me, and there was no doubt at all that it was an isolated thing I saw, i.e. no cone of light, I was on a terrace at the height of the 1st floor - I would really like to know if there was others who saw the same thing I saw last night.

They fly straight out in formation, and then they change direction, what is equivalent to 90 degrees without a curve, just like perpendicular, and disappear, after which a luminous object is "thrown", yes a completely white luminous one, which looks like a shooting star, but it keeps falling. My friend perceives and sees this and wonders too. The 3 objects had a color like fire, but what they "threw" off was as white as I don't know what, and then it had a tail that was falling. I've seen 3 fire objects fly around that direction before, but never seen anything fly that fast and change direction like that. We are not alone.

I have never believed in UFOs until about 2 years ago I randomly came across something with a base on the moon, I thought it was very interesting. And since our world leaders haven't said anything to us that it's ours, it was a natural thing to also see a little about UFOs and aliens... And it was even more exciting, so I watched a part of all those movies , which is online, and then shelved it again, until sometime in November 2005, when I came back to it and watched "The Disclosure Project". How can they refrain from telling such things...? If all those people aren't lying...?! Well, I'm watching a lot on the Internet and I'm sitting in my room at 5:00 a.m. on 1/12 2005 and I'm watching these UFO things on the Internet... And all of a sudden out of out of the blue, I get up and lift my patients and see over a block of flats outside my windows a powerful white pulsating light... A bit like small explosions, or those "led lights" you can buy in a fireworks shop, then it, if I think so, is since there was no sound, at least not through the windows. As I've always had an interest in fireworks, I'd just stay and see if anything else happened... if only I knew better... The white light changes to a light like a car with its high beam on so it's slanting down towards the road and something I can't see lifts up and turns green at the bottom... And here it says I mean... I've never seen such gunpowder... But the now green at the bottom and black or not present flying thing, starts just as slowly and goes to the left, or west, with the green light on, and goes then over for approx. north west where it just shuts off and the show is over... total anticlimax that there is a ufo right in front of you... will shoot it to be max 500m away and then there won't even be a grand finale, but just lights out... I've just had to think about it a bit myself, and haven't really talked to anyone about it, only my dad, and his reaction was just "screw you" like... but there it was, for the feeling in the body I have not experienced before... a little scared and curious at the same time, fantastic! Hope you can use it for some peace out!

It takes between 1 minute and a minute and a half in total. At the same time, there were clear stars and up to 3 ordinary planes in the sky. Absolutely fantastic. Have seen something before, but never so clearly. So there are two of us who saw it, my husband and I.
2 stationary powerful lights.

The phenomenon was observed at 18.45 but could easily have started earlier. The phenomenon was more or less in the same place for the 50 minutes but slowly sank downwards, just like following the direction of the moon downwards. Disappeared behind the surrounding houses, so it might still be there! Could this be the comet they've been talking about that could be seen around New Years? But it should probably have a turquoise glow and I don't think this one had that.

I was making dinner when my boyfriend suddenly called me outside. We saw 6 or 7 dark orange objects in the sky. They came gliding right after each other completely silently. The objects came from the same place in the south and suddenly disappeared again in exactly the same place every 6 -7 in the north. Just before they disappeared again, they changed color to reddish. It was a fantastic experience and we hope we have seen a UFO in reality.

We see 3-4 lights in the sky, it seems they are above the clouds. We wonder if it is some projector light from somewhere. But it moves in the sky. The lights travel in circles, alternately clear and faint, and move further away as we watch them. We try to follow it and can follow it to Gislev, but where it still seems to move away. I then drive back home, but my son-in-law and daughter and a friend continue.

properties.Remarks: Forklaring: Bryllup på Havartigården i Holte!  Balloner med hjerter!se beretning

properties.content: Now my wife and I have experienced 3 sightings within 1 month in almost the same place. Sightings similar to the one filmed 12/2-12 at Malling. Around 18-19/1-12 I drive to our house at 7pm and see a large circular light source orange/yellow coming flying towards my direction of travel. I would guess the light source is approx. 100-150 meters above the ground. At first I think it is a plane, but there is no sound and no other light on it. When I first see it, it is approx. 500 meters from our house. I drive to the house and get out of the car to observe it. It is about 150 meters from our house and 100-150 meters above the ground. There is no sound at all and it moves quietly and smoothly in a smooth motion. When it is approx. 50-80 meters past our house, it stands still for a few seconds and then starts to move out over the water, and then it is as if it accelerates violently for approx. 10 seconds it disappears into nothingness and finally disappears completely. The entire observation lasted approx. 2 minutes For this sighting, I was the only one who saw it - the next one was seen by both me and my wife. This took place on the same day as in Malling - namely on 12/2-12 at around 10 p.m. My wife and I are sitting on the sofa watching TV when Janne (my wife) spots a light approx. 50 meters above the ground around the neighbour's house. We rush to the window, and then I spot the same light source that I saw around the 18th-19th. January. A glowing circle/ball in orange/yellow. We only observe it for approx. 8-10 seconds before it disappears. So on Tuesday 14/2-12 my wife observes it again. This happens in the evening around 22.25 when she comes home from a visit to her mother. She sees it again when she comes driving towards our house. Again it is above our neighbor's house hovering from west to east. She rushes in and calls to me, but when we come out together it is gone. I am very interested to hear if anyone else has observed anything similar during this period. The reason I am writing is, among other things, the video on your website and have just read about a person in Hjørrin,g who experienced something similar in January.

We were 3 people and we saw what we thought was an airplane. It was a bright light, but there was no sound. However, it ended with the object stopping and standing still for several hours. We wondered and also thought that it could be a star, but it was strange that it had moved across the sky and now just stood still. Every once in a while we saw a red light, but it wasn't that obvious and it didn't flash all the time like an airplane. The object shone too brightly to be an airplane and there was no sound.
Drove north and saw a very large "star" - apparently stationary. As I got closer, 2 lights appeared next to each other (close). They were brightly lit when I drove "under them".

I went for a walk in the evening. When I got to the bus stop just west of Galpestykket, in addition to some planes, I saw what at first looked like a very bright twinkling star, but appeared to be moving slightly, so I assumed it was a slow-flying plane. I suddenly noticed that if I focused my gaze on the object, which was still moving extremely slowly with an almost zig-zagging changing direction, for a particularly long time, it seemed that everything else I could see began to go dark . That's why I also made sure to look at other things in between. At times I could also see what looked like a purple ring around the object. I kept waiting for it to get closer so I could see what it was, but due to its constantly changing speed, which was always very slow, at some point I got tired and went home to report this observation to SUFOI.

I left home at 6:35 as usual. On the way to work. I drive the same route as always. All of a sudden I can see something from the car window. An elongated object that is quietly moving west. It got smaller and smaller and finally it disappeared into the horizon.

Two bright red ""dots"" moved quickly (much faster than airplanes) across the sky. (They weren't that big so either they were far away and moving fast or they were relatively close (so of course they would have physically moved slower even though it looked fast). I got Flightradar 24 started to check whether it was airplanes or the like, but it was not something Flightradar registered).

My observation matches well with the report at the same time from Viborg. I discovered the glowing/burning object approx. 30 degrees above the horizon to the SSW. It flew across the sky - faster than an airplane. but slower than a shooting star - to the north and probably fell approx. 10 degrees before. it disappeared behind trees and buildings to the NNW. It probably took approx. 7 seconds. It had clear smoke behind it and small burning pieces fell off along the way. I would guess it was space debris?

I am writing for my father who told me this: My father was going to bed on Thursday at the mentioned time. The bedroom faces the road (to the west), and my mother slept in the same place. Suddenly, the bedroom was illuminated by a very strong yellowish light, reminiscent of a searchlight. My father rolled up the curtain and looked out. Just above the genbo's roof (point west) he observed a ball of light. He could not say anything about the distance, but stated that it was the size of a tennis ball. It stood perfectly still for a few seconds, after which it disappeared very quickly to the west in a straight path.
Watching from the window a "UFO" very quickly pass high up (1 sec.). Goes out to observe and sees one more pass at same height, same speed, same time, but east-west.

Saw a white light not very high in the morning twilight. Flying at a very high speed without sound. Since the object has flown approx. 2-3 seconds it changes to 3 close together lights and then suddenly it was gone. It all happened when I was on my way back after picking up the newspaper from the mailbox. The object was not an airplane.

Just below the moon's corona I saw a light moving very quickly in an easterly direction, then 4 more lights appeared that seemed to follow the first light. Each individual light was only visible for approx. 10 sec, after which the next thing appeared in the sky. I have no doubt that they all had the same direction and that they flew right after each other.

A couple of my friends and I had gone up to jump on the trampolines at the hotel, and after a few hours we just laid down on them. At I guess it was about 11:00 - 12:00 p.m. when this happened, which we can't quite explain. It went pretty fast. It was very bright, almost like a ball of fire, but still not something we initially talked about. We thought that it was probably just a shooting star, but after my roommate and I have talked about it as much as last Friday, we have become a little doubtful. It's also been a while, but at the time it didn't mean much to me. Since I have now begun to take an interest in non-earthly matters, I would like to know if there was something to the sinking or if it was just a shooting star.

I come driving on the country road between Skærbæk and Toftlund, approx. 4 km before Toftlund. I look out of the car window, where I have the Moon on the right and the daylight, which is making its way, on the left. Suddenly I see a very bright, white shape, which flashes up briefly with a repetition, approx. 1 second after which it is completely dark again. The time was 02:40. The object had a very special shape. And of course I have my own explanation. I have also, a few minutes later, drawn a drawing of the sky. I would naturally like to share it with you. I am left with the feeling that many know "It was something you had not seen before". I can hardly believe it was an aircraft of earthly origin. When you see the shape and the completely white light, I think about whether it is, for example, the back end of an object that is getting ready to leave us. Now, if it had been a Jetfighter, from the nearby air base in Skrydstrup, it would probably be more of an orange to bluish light, as combustion takes place. But could it be thought that the object uses light as propulsion. ? I've been thinking about that a lot since that night.

Luminous yellowish ball crossed the sky at a height like an airplane 10-12 km but at a higher speed than an airplane. Planes out of the question, maybe a satellite where the altitude has fooled me. Airport very straight. The color like a burning match. If right up to me is 90 degrees, I see the object approx. 45-50 gr.

In the period from 01:09 and 6-7 minutes onwards, we were 3 people who were out to get some air and cool off a little from the party we attended. It was overcast and the moon disappeared in time and time. Sometimes it was completely clear, other times it was covered in thick fog, so that you could only see the light behind, and other times again it was completely gone (i.e. also the light) because of the fog. Suddenly, 2 luminous objects arrive at a relatively low altitude, but at a speed that is somewhat higher than when you see an ordinary airliner. They came from an eastern direction and flew in a south-southeast direction. While we were looking at the 2 objects, another 1 came into view and followed the other 2. The first 2 were offset from each other in terms of height, and the 3rd was level with the lower one. We watched them for approx. 3-4 minutes and talked about how they were very atypical objects. We also discussed where Kastrup was in relation to where we had seen they came from. Our wonder was now that there were 3 machines that apparently took off at the same time and so at that time of the night. When they were gone we dismissed it as a little prank. 1-2 minutes later, 2 others arrive and shortly after 2 others again. Now there were 4 on the horizon all offset from each other and at the same speed as the 3 earlier. There were no sudden movements up or down. It was at a fixed (relatively high) speed. Again, the discussion turned to what we actually stood and watched. The sky was still very cloudy. One of us suggested that maybe it could be the exhaust from F16 planes because it was very yellowish and because the speed was so high. But there was no noise from planes or anything else. There was also no question that the objects were flying in formation in any way. But the heights were different and the speeds the same. Except for one of them, the 3rd, which flew so fast that it reached the 1st before they disappeared again. Just when we thought we had seen the last of it, another 3 came staggered. So not on the "heels" of each other, but at different heights and at the same speed. Also the same speed as the previous ones. These 3 objects disappeared in the same way as the previous ones. Of course, we were now somewhat more keen to see more in order to get closer to an explanation of what we saw. But despite the 15-20 minute wait, no further incidents occurred. Not so strange, after all, we all think we must have seen something from "outer space", but really it is probably just a UFO sighting. We are therefore very interested in hearing about what it was that we saw and whether others have had similar experiences that night. We do not believe that so many planes have arrived or taken off from Kastrup within that short time and at that time of day. We also do not believe that 10 F16s should be training at that time of day. There must be a more rational explanation for what we saw. We have also not been able to find anything in the various newspapers and internet media that mentioned what we had seen.

We, wife, my two small children and I) drove home from a family Christmas lunch, Saturday 28.12.96 approx. at 7 p.m. We drove beer mugs towards our home in Viby. We drove along Ølsemaglevej towards Højelse. When we get to the small mill, we turn left and then right towards Højelse. Here we see the light in the sky for the first time (9 spots of light which form a square and there are two of them which revolve around themselves and each other). At first we don't say anything to each other, but just drive. We come up to Højelse Church, turn right, and drive past Højelse School, turn left down Baunebjergvej. Here I ask my wife, she also sees what I see, to which she replies yes. We get down to Ejbyvej and drive to the left (now we can no longer see the two lights). We turn right off Assendrupvej and drive a short distance, approx. 400 meters and there they are again. we stop the car and turn it off, roll down the windows to listen, but can't hear anything, we keep quiet for maybe a minute, and then we drive again (the bright spots are about 200 meters in front of us, and a little to the left . All the time we observe them in the sky above us, there are clouds to the left, but clear stars to the right. We drive west along Assendrupvej again all the while looking at these lights. Then we come to Ladagervej, where we turn to the right, and gone are those lights. Then we turn left onto Gammel Skolevej, drive 100 metres, and then they are there again. Right onto Hestehavevej (they are still there), then right onto Åbakkevej (then they are away again), park the car in the driveway. Get out of the car to look for them, and there to the west about 200 meters out in the field a little to the left, there they hang for the next hour. We come in with the children, let the dogs walk , have to light the wood stove, so I bring firewood over to the shed and see that they are still there.

My location: On Gl. Church path approx. 150 m from Vårhøj. Location of the lights: in a western direction. Enough more km. away. Apparently up in the dark clouds. The movement of the lights: Primarily circular arcs within a square of approx. 5 x 5 cm. At arm's length. Like a group of seagulls circling or laser lights that light up the clouds and move in circles. Number of lights: Approx. 5. At least 3. The nature of the lights: Weak, somewhat diffuse, similar white lights that turned on and off or flew in and out of the clouds. They glowed approx. 2 second duration. Size of the lights: Each of them like a small spot. Sounds: None.

I'm out walking my dog when I see 2 glowing objects hovering in the sky. There is no sound from them and they float with the same speed and the same direction. It looks like they are far away and floating at high speed. After approx. 30 sec. the light gets weaker, and they both disappear at the same time in a cloudless sky. I have taken a picture and a small video with the iphone 4.

At approx. 22.30 we observe a strong light in the sky approximately from a south-westerly direction. At first we think it's a plane with lights on. The light was shaped like a large triangle with a reddish glow. It's fast approaching. The speed slows down until it seems like the light stands still in the sky. We look away for a moment. When we look at the sky again, the light is gone, but there is a black spot. It grows and we become aware that it is an object falling towards the earth. It looks like a very large piece of fabric or pressing, which we initially thought was a parachute spring. We lose contact with the falling object as it comes under the tree and take height.

Observation 1, at 19.40 A luminous ball moves slowly towards us from the south south-east. The light seems bigger and more powerful than on an airplane. There were no flashing lights to be seen. As the object is in front of us, it turns to the east and slowly disappears into the darkness. We hear no sound from the object, despite the windless weather. The object lights up roughly the same amount during the entire process (approx. 5 min.)

On a nighttime beach walk, I met two peers. We fell into conversation, and suddenly one of the strangers exclaims - Look there, and points to the sky. Two bright stars appear, shine brightly for a while and then fade. From where we stood, there appeared to be two centimeters between the objects. Soon after, there was no sign of them.

White object, as it is clear, it is illuminated/reflected by the sunlight. The object stood completely still in the sky, looking like an elongated or distorted triangle. Unfortunately a front came in (clouds) and it disappeared behind the clouds. My wife noticed that it was unusually bright in the sky. So didn't get to photograph it.

I was laying down to watch a movie when I saw a bright orange light over some buildings that you can see from my couch through the glass door to my balcony. I could see what looked like the "tail lights" of an airplane and a fourth light to the right of the 3. All of a sudden the "airplane" starts spinning in circles!!! Either it was a huge airplane that was just about to fall from the sky, or it was also way too close (as the lights were a little far apart). But how could such a large machine turn so fast? And why couldn't I hear them when I went out on the balcony? Then came the 5th and then the 6th light. No. 2 and 3 kept turning and then No. 1 disappeared behind a cloud. Then No. 2 did the same, and afterwards No. 3 and No. 4. Then No. 5 disappeared, while No. 6 remained there, without moving. After 15-20 seconds the last light disappeared behind the same cloud. I tried to take video with my old cell phone, but all you can see is the light from a window in that building "under" the lights. It was strange and mysterious!!!

Photograph of "Planet Uranus" (unsure of planet name). When magnifying on PCs, the celestial body appeared, stars and the object was not seen with the naked eye, but appeared to be moving. Photo series is sent. I am a bit anxious to hear back if there is a natural explanation.

This happened in the summer of '95, on a Friday, early in the evening. At the time I lived down by the harbor in Vejle (Fjordmarken). Me and a friend should have gone to Grøn Koncert, but we decided to stay at home. So we were not influenced by alcohol. I had a terrace that I went out on. It was still bright. I spotted a round object that came hovering over a few blocks close to where I lived. Now it's been a few years, but I remember that the object was not very high up, it was clearly visible. It floated in a special way, a bit in a zigzag. Sometimes it would hold still but still move, and then it would float again. I called my friend and we looked at it. It looked like a silver ball, but at times it looked like it was black at the bottom. Maybe it revolved around itself? It was metallic, sometimes the sun seemed to reflect in it. It was silent. It sounds strange, but we both sensed that whatever it was, it was aware of our observation. There is a huge chimney on the road where I lived and the object came to an abrupt stop right above it. Like it was curious and didn't know what a chimney was. It looked rather strange. Then the most astonishing thing happened, that which made us both sure that it must be something unknown, not of earthly origin. It disappeared upwards, abruptly upwards, incredibly fast. You hardly manage to blink your eyes, and you thought it all felt so unreal. We were both shaken for the rest of that day and I felt a little anxious about sleeping alone at home. A few days later we heard on the radio that there had been other sightings in Vejle and the surrounding area on the same day. Not necessarily of the same UFO. Sometimes we have a bit of fun with it. There was a Green Concert that day. Maybe ET wanted to go down and listen to some music.
At intervals two luminous objects appeared in the sky. They were speeding around at high speed, very high speed. They circled around and disappeared. Came back after some time and did the same thing.

What is it that I have photographed. I'm sitting and editing pictures from yesterday's birding trip. I'm going to delete a sick picture of a flock of piping ducks taking off. Suddenly I become aware of what I think is something bad on the sensor, a spot on the left in the upper third of the photo. I don't see any other spots on the rest of my photos. It is only when I enlarge a section that I can see that it is a flying object. At the right end of the vessel something metallic/engine/nozzles can be seen. I noticed no sound other than ducks taking off. The picture was taken at Skalleværket (Dyndet) Roskilde Fjord on Wednesday 19-10-2022 at 10:44:26. The direction of view is east towards Jyllinge Nord. Nikon Z7 47 million pix, 1/3200sec, f:5.5 500mm (Nikkor 200mm-500mm).

Saw a light coming in from the western direction. Sharp and with an even speed, but significantly slower than a satellite. After approx. 30 sec. it was as if a series of lights were lit, forming a circle. This continued for 30 sec. There was no rotation or change in speed. Ran to our bedroom window where my wife and son stayed. At the time of writing, I cannot say whether they could see anything because of background light. The object had now again lit the entire circle and in addition, 4 new lights had been lit/appeared, which could appear trapezoidal. My wife thought I should relax, but I was really up for calling. Couldn't get my mobile camera to work but it was absolutely amazing. The object disappeared at the same speed as it entered the field of vision with a direction to the east. It's partly cloudy with 0 wind, so I can't immediately understand if it's a balloon. Nor with the light formation it assumed.

White glowing object whose light could be seen clearly through the cloud cover and which moved at several hundred kilometers per hour in a descending arc towards the earth. Immediate guess at fall site in the vicinity of Hårup/Mejlby. However, it is difficult to judge the distance to the object.

Around Thursday, July 23, 2020, or the night of Friday, I saw a phenomenon in the sky from my garden. It was about 02:00 or 02:30 I saw in the sky what I first thought was a satellite coming from north to south. Suddenly at high speed, it made a 180 degree turn to the right and continued north at a higher speed. From lighting up like a regular satellite, it changed color to a brownish to dark red, probably due to the increased speed away from me. The object continued until I could not see it because it disappeared behind the trees. 20 to 30 seconds later I observed a flash of white light above me. It might look like lights from an airplane, but there were no red and green lights, and there was no sound. There were four flashes of light in a straight line from south to north in the same direction and high speed as the first object. The following check on the flightradar2 app shows that there were no planes.

It's been a few years since I saw it, I still don't quite know what it was. I'm having a hard time getting myself to believe it was a UFO, but don't know what else to describe it as. I didn't tell you about it until now because I didn't know about this site and because it's easy to sound like a fool. Date/month are not exact as I did not note the date then and today do not remember exactly. It was 2007. I was jogging and playing basketball in my parents' yard when a low-flying glider flew over our lot. I looked up and was following the glider when I spotted a small round black object significantly higher up that followed a straight path to begin with, to turn over my neighbor's roof and out of my field of vision eventually.

At approx. 22.30 we were in the car on our way home from Århus, where we had been for grinding at Jysk Stenklub's workshop at St. Annagades School. It was a dark evening with quite a few stars and fairly clear weather. Along the way I noticed a light which I at first assumed to be a plane; but it moved in a strange way, until I realized that it did not move; but that it only looked that way because the road turned and changed direction. At the last rest area by the open road before Hovedgård, I made my "driver" drive in and keep still, so that it was possible to look at the phenomenon, which then appeared as a "triangular" star that flashed blue above the forest before main yard The drive up to our house is quite steep, and the car's headlights shined very brightly towards the forest, which was leafless at that time of year. The light pointed like an arrow up into the sky above the forest that lies just behind the garden. My "driver" turned off the lights and locked the doors while I stood looking at the sky to the south when something strange happened. From the eastern direction came an orange colored "ball", which moved quite slowly and absolutely silently across the sky and disappeared in a western direction over the forest. It didn't go very high, but was visible for maybe 5-6 seconds. My "driver" didn't get to see it, as he was standing with his head in the car. I wanted to go out on a piece of open country road to see if the "strange star" was still in the sky as it had been when we drove home; but there was nothing to see, so we just had to turn around and go back home. As we began to walk back, and for my part still with my eyes fixed on the sky, I suddenly saw the orange colored "ball" coming across the sky as calmly and silently as before, but this time in the opposite direction of what had been the case up behind the house. I pointed it out to my companion and I think he saw it too.

First came a strong light at a nice height (it's starry so the view is pretty nice). The light came from the south and at first looked like a plane/helicopter, but was too brightly lit for it to be navigation/landing lights. The speed was reminiscent of an airliner, but it began to reduce speed sharply. 30 sec. Then another "object" came from the same direction and in exactly the same trajectory. My boyfriend was standing next to me and we joked about it a bit at first. The first light turned 90 degrees to the west and flew on at "normal" speed. The second light now stood almost still almost above us, but then continued slowly to the west in the same course as the first. The other light began to glow more and more dimly and was finally gone. It seemed to rise vertically at high speed. The first light continued to the west. There was no audible engine noise. Ok I've never believed in little green men, UFOs etc, but right now I'm having a bit of a hard time ruling out weather balloons, helicopters etc. Finding logical explanations!! I would like to add that I have a background where I worked for a period at Kastrup airport, as an air traffic controller trainee, and therefore I have no natural explanation for what I have just observed, and therefore I have to post it immediately.
I saw some flashing lights in the sky and no planes are coming in my area.

Standing and enjoying the cloudless sky and looking for shooting stars, when over Horsens in the direction of Hatting a strong light came up over the horizon. The light was just twice as strong as the ISS. The color was orange or like fire, but in a fixed slightly elongated, defined area. The light flew very fast and in a straight path, will shoot the speed to 4 times as fast as ISS. It came up over the horizon in the west-northwest, and continued in a straight line overhead and disappeared in the east-southeast. It flew right through Orion before disappearing behind the rooftops. The light had constant brightness throughout the observation. I'm used to being outside when it's dark looking at the night sky, have a pair of binoculars that I use once in a while. However, I have never seen anything of this type before, from one horizon to the other it took a maximum of 20 to 30 seconds. I don't think it was a satellite as they are usually not illuminated from rise to fall, the speed was also way too high. It also did not appear that the object was illuminated, but rather appeared to be glowing itself. The only thing I could think of that it could be was if it was the shuttle being launched, but it's not flying right now. But I could see that they have fired a rocket from NASA today at 3 pm Danish time. Don't know if it could be this one. Immediately after the observation, I called my little brother, who happened to be out walking the dog, he had also seen the light, but couldn't explain what it could be either. Due to the very beautiful sky and the much press coverage of the many shooting stars, I hope that there are others who saw the same thing as me.

I think I want to report on 2 observations that I had during my childhood in Viborg. The first is as follows: I was on my way home from swimming on a Tuesday evening when a whistling/whistling sound caught my eye. It was reasonably clear, only a few clouds. Over my head in a northerly direction, I spotted something I hadn't seen before. Something moved across the sky. Eight glowing dots that together formed an H. They were moving at a slow speed, so I thought it must be a plane. But within a few seconds, they almost came together and changed direction and speed. They disappeared at high speed to the east. I'm not sure how far away they were, but half a minute later a commercial airliner came and it seemed like it was closer than the object. There was a man waiting for the bus and I asked him if he had seen it too and he had. The second sighting is very clear in my memory because we were eight friends/cousins who saw this object on a fishing trip at Søndersø in Viborg. The eel fishing was not going so well, so we sat and talked when one of my cousins drew attention to something approaching from the NE. A low-flying dark object approached. In terms of size, it seemed like a large plane that was on its way to land, but there is no landing pad nearby. As it passed over our heads we could see light below the bottom and the object looked triangle shaped. There was no sound from the object and the speed was relatively low. When it had passed we sat and talked about what we had seen and one of the comrades was sure we had seen one of those STEALTH planes that the Americans have but there is no one who can tell about these planes has flown in Danish airspace and so low.

My girlfriend and I see a light that moved across the night sky. At first we thought this was an airplane, but the object didn't blink and didn't make any sound. Then we briefly considered that this might be a satellite. But this seemed wrong as the object appeared triangular and closer to the ground. At the same time, we could see that the object had 3 lights close together in a triangular shape. The object did not move in a completely straight line, but turned slightly towards the east. I grabbed my cell phone to film the object, but a video would be too dark, so I took some photos. However, one cannot guess the shape, but only a strong light.

Came driving from work in Vordingborg heading towards Næstved, early in the afternoon on Friday 4 June 2010. It was beautiful sunshine and I enjoyed the trip as usual. Suddenly became aware of an object, which I first interpreted as an airplane, because of the color, quite high up in the sky, very far away. So typical airplane distance. Then it occurred to me, after noticing that it was moving somewhat slowly for an airplane, that it was not leaving the usual trail of condensation behind it. I looked for other airplanes, and in the distance I could make out another one to my left, which had the prettiest stripes on it. But this one had nothing. And another "funny" thing: the sun did not reflect in the hull at any time, as is otherwise known from airplanes. Usually there is a solar flare at some point, but this was just a non-reflective gray object that I sensed as saucer-shaped with a "superstructure" on top. It could very well be an airplane seen slightly obliquely, with the wing at the back as the "superstructure". But again: strange speed, no condensation streaks and no reflections at all. Almost like the surface of a gray desktop computer. I observed the object as well as I could while driving on the highway, and only lost sight of it when it disappeared behind some massive clouds that lay to my right, that is, to the north-east. I observed the object for approx. 2-4 minutes.

One late evening I was together but my parents and my little brother. We stayed on the 4th floor and could see over part of the city. As the evening wore on, my father noticed something in the sky. It was a light none of us had seen before. It was a light that looked like a sparkler. We took out a video camera and got it on film. However, I myself have tried to find out what it was that I/we had seen that night, but have not been able to find anything. It is now a little over 2 years ago. It was only on this one evening, but you couldn't avoid seeing it. We haven't seen it since.

I was out to smoke. As I looked over the rooftops of the cluster of townhouses I live in. To the south, just above the rooftops (2-story building), I saw an orange circle floating calmly across the rooftops. It was from the start approx. 5 cm in circumference. It "flew" towards the north for approx. a minute and then changed direction and flew "away from me". Over the next minute, the object became smaller and smaller until it disappeared behind the cloud cover. I heard the sound of a plane, but it sounded like it was coming from a different direction. I didn't see any flashing lights, couldn't see any features on the object - just this orange glowing color.

This evening I sat in my garden and looked at the stars. All of a sudden I spot two stars that I think are moving. But that can't fit. Looking around at the sky, and then looks back. Yes, they have 100% moved in the sky. But their distance is basically the same. It also seems as if they are "shooting" at each other. But I don't know if it is my view that teases on that point. But that is very far out. I can only see the two "stars" when all the light is off around me. I don't know if it is a UFO or what it is, but I am 100% sure that the two stars have moved in the sky and that all other stars "stood still". I can still see them after 30 min, so I know it's not just two shooting stars either.

Was just parked by the fjord at Kølstrup/at Kerteminde and immediately saw a luminous phenomenon moving between the clouds. It moved slowly from east to west, then moved very quickly in an easterly direction and quickly changed direction to the west and rose upwards and disappeared. Waited a bit and then two luminous objects appeared, also moving very quickly in different directions, and they disappeared after approx. 30 seconds.

On Saturday evening 18-08-01 we (my wife, our three children and a friend of our daughter) went to a street party at Frydendalsvej 2, Hostrup. At approx. 01.00 we decided to go home. We had to pull our bikes as we had no lights on. Our two boys and a friend had already gone home approx. at 23.00. When we got outside, we admired the beautiful starry sky. After walking 100 m, my wife saw something turning behind a sheltered fence (east of the road). At first she thinks it was the Northern Lights, which it wasn't. The phenomenon was small approx. 1 m. in diameter white "cloud spots", light, in two circles, approx. 12-15 in the outer circle and approx. 8-10 in the inner circle. The circles revolved around themselves. It approached us at a low altitude, just above our heads it stopped while turning first anti-clockwise, then suddenly changed direction and turned clockwise. All 4 of us stopped to look at this. The phenomenon was about 15-20 meters above the ground. It was flat, there was nothing between these "clouds of light" or above, and you could hear nothing. We continued walking. The phenomenon began to fly east again, and for a moment it poured approx. 45 degrees. After we had walked now approx. 200 m, we saw it coming back towards us, we were now out on Sønderskovvej. It followed us from the east for 500 m and was above us again just after Hostrup, again it came from the east and stopped just above our heads. We looked at each other and tried not to scare the girls. We continued walking. The phenomenon flew east again across the river valley, we could see it all the time. After walking another 200m it returned over our heads. We stopped, looked at it. Decided to hurry. It disappeared again to the east, and we started cycling - when we turned right onto Varde Landevej. When we had cycled 300 m, we turned right down our "little road". The phenomenon now returned and again stopped just above our heads. (It had now become cloudy). We now cycled the last 400 m home while it flew to the southeast. At home in our courtyard it came back again. All the time it revolved around itself. Our older son and a friend now also came out. We all looked up at the phenomenon. Kent now went in to call the information and got the phone no. at Flemming Poulsen, Odense. He got the description of the phenomenon. We tried to take pictures (there was nothing on them when they were developed). Sometimes it flew across the field to the east (while we could see it all the time) to return again. My wife went down to the neighbour's, approx. 80 m, the phenomenon followed, and was right over her head. When she later asked the children where it had been in relation to them, they answered on their left hand when looking east. It all stopped at 01.50, when it suddenly disappeared. We have drawn the entire route on a map. It must be stated that on Saturday night there was a town party in Starup/Tofterup 6 km away - to the east. Whether it could have been light from there, we can't get it to connect at all, there was no question of laser light at all, and if it had been light from a mirror ball, how can it be so concentrated over such a long distance and for approx. . 20 meters high with not quite flat terrain and large trees/forest, and how can these "clouds of light" follow us all the way home and then remain largely above our property for approx. 20 minutes.

Last night I observed a luminous object, approx. 20 degrees above the northern sky. The object glowed white/yellowish and pulsated from weak to more intense, and back again, at intervals of a few seconds. At first I thought it must be a plane, but the object changed direction several times in a pattern not typical of a normal plane. At the same time, it seemed that the entire object was shining, and thus did not just have a flashing light fitted, due to the distance, this is however somewhat uncertain. Through the traffic noise I thought I could faintly hear the noise of a jet engine, and got the feeling that it might be one of the air force's fighters, although I am also very uncertain about this. After a few minutes the object disappeared in a northerly direction. I don't realize what it was I saw. But perhaps you can compare my observation with similar reports from the Copenhagen area, at the time in question.
It was a quiet morning when I took a walk down towards the city. When I got to Emilievej 56, I saw a flying metallic object in a westerly direction.

I saw about 8-12 lights "dancing" in the sky, they flew up between the clouds, back and forth. In quite a few cases they stood still and started flying again. At first I thought they were drones, but they flew high into the clouds. There was also a couple that suddenly came down from the clouds. I have recorded it on video and pictures if it is. The direction was towards Valby in the direction of Sct. Jacob's church tower on Østerbro. The height was from the church tower to the sky.

On Saturday night I went out in front of our house at 1am and looked for shooting stars. Didn't know which direction to look for them, so I looked a bit in all directions. It was then in this connection that I looked in a southerly direction and spotted this object. It flew at a leisurely pace across the sky before finally disappearing from sight. No sound came from the object. It was spherical and surrounded by some kind of atmosphere. The atmosphere sort of came and went a bit like when you look at a fire and look into the flames. It was in this connection that I could sometimes see that it was a silvery orb within this atmosphere. There were also fliers in the area at this time and they in no way resembled the object or behaved in the same way. I've never seen anything like it before.

2 luminous balls (not as luminous as e.g. the North Star) came flying/hovering at a much higher speed than satellites have. Also, they didn't flash like an airplane would, but had a constant light. They were bigger than an ordinary. star and seem more circular in their shape, they had no tail behind them. They flew parallel, then flew towards each other and then flew apart again. The pattern they flew in may appear as 2 opposite parentheses, ie )(. They disappeared as quickly as they appeared.

I observe a strong light being lit/illuminated towards the south/west. I expect to see an aviator, but no one comes (the light is just above the cloud cover), but it doesn't move, then a very bright light comes on, which descends diagonally to the ground at the other end. It confuses me somewhat, as it is not normal for a pilot approaching Kastrup. Both lights last for approx. 1 min. Suddenly the light pointing towards Kastrup goes out. The second light remains, and it disappears in a south-westerly direction. I can't manage to follow it as it is directly above my head and silent. I estimate the cone of light towards the ground to be between 2 - to 10 m.

properties.Colors: kulsort, som et hul i himlen
properties.content: Hexagonal object, 20-40m high, 15-30m wide. Rotates slowly on the y-axis and floats south at accelerating speed. Silent, beautiful and completely without markings or surface marks. Disappears into the clouds far away on the horizon.

Was out walking my dog and daughter when we observed a white light in the sky. Having a little trouble understanding what just happened there? It was a long tail and a round ball, which moved very strongly in different directions. Can see there are observers in our area who have seen the same thing. Does anyone know what it is? Ølsted on 29.12.2012 at 18.30.

I was going outside to smoke a cigarette and suddenly witnessed a scenario. First came 2 gliding across the sky, then came 2 more. Then I called the rest of the party-goers out so they could see the same thing I witnessed. After that came 3, and then 2 and then 3, later 3 and 3 and 2, we counted 20 in all. We all agreed that it must be unidentified "UFOs" objects that came in a steady stream across the night sky. There came approx. 20 pieces in total in gliding movements across the night sky. Some of us would report it to SOK, i.a. the civil engineer who was there, but couldn't find a phone number in the confusion that we could call and, incidentally, where we could report the sighting. But ever since then I have been reading magazines and watching TV news to see if there were others besides us in the company who had observed the strange night show, but I have now read all the news and have not found a single remark about this strange sight. The objects flew just as quietly across the night sky. I tried to take pictures of the sight but nothing came up on my camera as I must have had a flash on which someone told me was probably a mistake and in the dark without my glasses I was unable to set my camera correctly. The party was held in Farum, Brudedalen no. 13, on Saturday 21 June, but it was past midnight, i.e. Sunday early at 2.10 the observations were made. I was neither drunk nor crazy, I had agreed with my husband that I was the one driving that day and had therefore not been drinking. There were civil engineers and engineers among the company, who, like me, agreed that it was a completely unusual sight. I have tried to write for TV news, but I have not seen anything described on the subject, and I do not understand, because the observations lasted for over 20 minutes. It surprises me that there is no one else but us who has seen the scene, I am thinking of radar from Copenhagen Airport, which is not far from the observation point. The reason I'm only reporting this to you today is because we were going to a 90th birthday party in Skive in North Jutland on Sunday morning and didn't get home until today, Tuesday at 5:00 p.m. I would like to know if anyone else has seen anything.

I was out walking my little poodle at 23.10. There are fields and cattle, I stand and listen to the birds, and turn to the right, look up, and what I see, I think at first is a helicopter, but no propellers, and no machine sound, but a kind of windy sound , which came from the bottom of it. It glowed red and white, so I thought it belonged to Odense Hospital, but no, it flew right over me. I quickly sent a message to my daughter who was inside on her computer. I was probably startled, but it was no worse. I was wearing a headlamp but took it off and shined it on the object, strange.. it sort of stopped in midair and turned down towards me as if it was observing me for a few seconds. I couldn't manage to set my camera on my mobile but recorded the sound of "it". I stopped lighting it. It turned around and flew towards Lillebælt, that way out of there. Haven't seen anything since. Got curious.

Fishing in Aarhus harbor when a fighter plane flies low over the harbor Looking up in the air and sees a white object, 3 small balls together. Suddenly looks like a soap bubble around the ball, shrinks and winds, while a small sports plane flies around, 3 times around the harbor and the building. 2 minutes later a helicopter flies to the east. I suspect the pilots have seen the same thing as me :)

2 sickle-shaped, upright objects with fire at the bottom, fly at approx. 50-100 m distance from each other from south to north. The fire disappears quietly, but the objects fly on at the same speed. It's definitely not the Chinese flying lights. They flew too fast and were at the same height all the time. Objects were completely silent. The same was seen on 30 July 2011 at 22:34 approx. There it was an object that flew from north to south as seen from Bryggervej, 3200 Helsinge. On 18 June 2011 at 22:33 in the evening, I am driving on the Sorø country road and see 5 large flying fireballs, which are dark above, floating up over the horizon. The first two were close to each other and approx. 200 m after, 2 new fireballs came floating. The last one came approx. 300 m from the others. They hovered over the sunroof of my car so I could look right up at them. They were very large and completely silent, and they floated in the same direction towards Ringsted and at the same pace. Approx. 1 month later I saw a ball of fire similar to the one in the afternoon coming up over the horizon at Vridsløsevej in Næstved. It disappeared into a garden at the end of Vridsløsevej. It was even bigger than the others I had seen on June 18th. Have given them a lot of thought afterwards. They made a big impression on me. I got a picture of 2 of them from June 18, but unfortunately it was taken in poor resolution, but you can see them in the picture.

A bright flashing object moved very slowly across the sky, but also moved in some very quick jerks both laterally and vertically. It looked very unnatural, and my son and I recorded the phenomenon on video approx. 1 hour, but you can only see a bright spot on the screen, as it is quite far away. It is also difficult to see on the video the jerks it moved in. When we at 4 were very tired and had to get up the next morning, we chose to go to bed, therefore we do not know when it disappeared.

We were sitting twenty people, children, young people and adults, when one person observed a ball of light coming in from the SW in a horizontal path. After a short moment, the orb rose vertically into the clouds and disappeared. Soon after, two more fireballs came from the same direction, they also disappeared into the clouds. Shortly before 22.00 the fourth bullet followed exactly the same route. Some adults subsequently claimed that they observed a dark dot disappear in a close direction. Maybe a bag/parachute from an emergency rocket. No noise or tail of fire was observed after the balls, which were the size of a traffic light.

Yes, sigh, I had hoped to find out that by chance there were about half a million other Danes who had seen what I saw then, especially because I can't even remember the year for sure. But as I said, it was in the summer that I had a summer holiday, and it wasn't before '80 and not after '83. It was late and I was standing on my balcony when I saw something out of the corner of my eye. I was immediately convinced that it was no "natural" phenomenon, but I looked very intently anyway, hoping to find something familiar about the thing. How big it was I don't know because I don't know how far away it was when I saw it. But it was elongated, looked like an airplane without wings and about a third shorter than a normal charter plane, like a short cigar. It was completely white, without any kind of writing, numbers or symbols, but with a lot of "pipes" all over it. There were, as I recall, no lights flashing, but it seemed lit from the outside, so white was it. It moved very calmly and completely, completely silently (it was a very quiet night so I would have been able to hear it) from east-southeast to south and slightly to the southwest. And I glowed. I ran through the entire registry; could it be an aviator? No, no wings, no flashes and no noise. A helicopter? No. A hot air balloon? No. An American Air Shuttle? I thought about that for a bit, but firstly, there was nothing on the machine, no text, no flag, and secondly, you would probably have heard about it in the TV newspaper if such a thing came past Denmark. Then I made the big mistake of calling my mother, who was sitting out in the kitchen, but instead of just getting her out there so she could be my witness, I shouted: Mom, I'm looking at a UFO. .. and then I was ordered to bed in a hurry, and it was many o'clock, and I saw visions, and it was also too crazy and... I turned around for just a few seconds, and when I turned around again, the thing away, piss away. If it had continued at the speed it had had until then, it should have been only a little further west, but it was gone, and I was so sorry not to have seen how it disappeared. And it took approx. 15 years before I told anyone about it, - most people look at me like I was the closed one, but I know now it wasn't a dream. Has anyone but me seen it?

Followed what I thought was a common satellite for 25-30 sec, quiet speed, straight line across the night sky, and high above the rooftops. Suddenly the object accelerates at an outrageous speed and now continues due west for approx. 4 seconds before it disappears from my field of vision. Didn't change shape or color, always spherical and a little faintly luminous at the end.

At 21 last night, I stand out on my balcony to smoke my cigarette. Above me, the sky is completely dark and starry, while the sky to the south is illuminated due to the city's street lighting. To my great surprise, I see in the sky above me 4 disc-shaped objects. The 3 fly in a triangle, while the fourth flies a bit by himself. They have come from the north and are moving south. They would be invisible if it weren't for the faint red/orange light that outlined them and formed a pattern at the bottom of them. I called my husband a little panicked, who came running out and saw the same thing as me. My husband is a military man and has never believed in UFOs/aliens or anything like that. But, like me, he's a total nerd. Unfortunately, we could only see them for approx. 30 sec. As the lighting of the sky caused street lights to the south, making them invisible/impossible to see. They flew high. Higher than sports planes, but lower than the high-flying passenger planes. They were silent and appeared large. Despite being disc-shaped, you could still see that there was height on them - they were not completely flat.

My mate notices 2 orange lights moving across the sky and asks me if they could be planes/helicopters, which I decline as the lights are not flashing and they are completely silent. We go out into the garden, and there are 6-7 more lights coming from the same direction. They move reasonably fast in a long line, although not all equally fast, and it is immediately just below the cloud height, which I estimate to be max. 1000 meters. At the same time, we notice that the clouds move from south to north. so the lights do not move in the direction of the wind. The entire session lasts max. 60 seconds, and we both notice that it happens completely silently. The lights are orange, almost like from hot air balloons, but the speed and direction make it impossible for it to have anything to do with hot air balloons.

Got home and when I got out of my car I took a quick look at the night sky. Here I spotted the object traveling in a straight line from west to east. I thought it seemed a little strange, because it was completely silent, and the light seemed too bright to be a high-flying plane. I also observed no flashing lights like airplanes usually have.

Circular lights, from 2 objects circling around. Sudden turns in the opposite direction. Without sound. Moving towards each other so we thought they would fly into each other but just floated past each other. Hovered criss-crossing each other, both at slow speed and very high speed. Agreed that it was not quite a normal flight. Gets a bit uncomfortable at some point due to something inexplicable........

The lady is standing on the terrace smoking and calls to me when I am standing in the living room. I go out to her and she points in a southerly direction where there is a black object hanging (a bit like a spaceship - wide at the bottom and tapering at the top) with orange flashing lights at the bottom of the object that pulse around in circles . She says that it came flying quickly from the west, in connection with the burning of some fireworks in the local area - which made her attention directed to the sky. The lady initially thought it was an emergency flare - as I am a sailor and we live close to the fjord - I had to observe carefully in case of an alarm. The emergency flare is bright red and lights up for approximately 30 seconds. with smoke development, so it wasn't. The black object rocked a little, but was reasonably still in the air for about 1½ minutes. The object then slowly disappears to the south - and almost evaporates into the sky. The distance/height is difficult to assess, as the size of the object is undefinable, and the clouds hang low/close at dusk. But estimated the object appears to be 0.5 to 1 kilometer up.

The sky is overcast, it's not quite bright yet. I'm driving my car in a northerly direction when I spot what I first think is a star. I think it is unusually large and oval in shape. I would estimate it to be more than twice the size of the largest star you can usually see in the sky, which is the North Star. It is also oval in shape. I think it almost looks like an eye.
