It looks like it's above the clouds, which is strange. It lights up for approx. 10 seconds, and is completely motionless, after which it narrows, like when you close your eye, and disappears. It doesn't show up again.
At first there were two lights....changed to three.

Standing and brushing teeth in the window, with a view over a green area at Munkholmvej in Holbæk. As always, I scrutinize the stars and see, at a relatively low angle above the horizon between some buildings in a NNW direction, a small slightly flashing orange/white light, the same size as a star - so it must have been far away or something small. But the reason I would call it a UFO is that this object is flying a very curved direction, zig zagging and flying again a little straight, a little to the northwest, but still low horizontally. I shout to my girlfriend to come see a UFO and we stand together watching the funny way this "little star" flies until the light gets too dim and a lamppost closer to me makes it more difficult to see more. It is reported immediately as others may have seen the same thing or thought it seemed like an inexplicable occurrence!

1-2 luminous objects flew at great speed and without sound across the sky. They "shaken" a little, as if they were not flying exactly next to each other, but almost turbulently. But still in a direct line due south to due north according to the compass on the iPhone. It was 10.15pm when they were observed. They flew between the constellations Cassiopeia and Charlemagne.

My wife and I stood looking at the fantastic big red moon that had just risen over the horizon. We both saw 2 "stars" that shone unusually brightly. I found my phone and opened stellarium, but when we looked up the lights were gone. I saw nothing on stellarium that could be stars. They glowed constantly and flickered a little. We both saw those lights/stars for approx. 10 sec.

I stood on the balcony to smoke the last cigarette of the evening. I stood looking up at the sky, as I now do when the weather is starry. I see a boomerang-like object fly over my head for approx. 300 meters high. At first I thought it was a larger species of bird heading towards the Brabrand lake, but I will assess that the speed was far too high for it to be a bird, and the wingspan of the object was more reminiscent of a small private plane. It had better not be a plane as there was no sound or any visible signal glances which I suppose you have to fly especially at night at such a low altitude. I also mean to observe two pointed cylindrical shapes under each wing. The object flew in a completely straight direction towards Gl. Brabrand and disappears into the darkness. The object had no visible lights and could only be seen by moonlight.

On the link, our location is on the road, as we see something falling diagonally from right to left over the trees and houses a little way ahead. It is burning to look at, falling obliquely and somewhat slowly, with a white tail about as long as the object itself. It is possibly over the houses we could see further ahead, as Børkopvej ended at a T-junction. It's not something we've seen before. It was like what you imagine a meteor strike would look like, only smaller. In terms of size, it was too big and "single" to be fireworks. I immediately thought it looked strange and mysterious. My best idea would be a drone that caught fire in flight.

We saw a reddish/orange light emerge over the rooftops in a southwesterly direction and continue across the sky to the northeast. The speed is hard to determine, but it went pretty fast. There was no sound from it. After it passed so that we could see the "back end", the light gradually got dimmer and dimmer, but you could still see a dark shadow. We have quite a bit of helicopter traffic over the area, but we hear them. The tourists send up quite a few rice balloons, but I just think the speed was way too high, since there was no significant wind at ground level, but now I also know what the airspeed was at that height. I was wondering if it could be the International Space Station, could that be the solution??

Just got off the A-train from Copenhagen (arrival 21.25) and walked down Højstrupparken towards the beach. Went and enjoyed that it was starry and spotted the Carlsvogn. I stopped and looked at the constellation and shortly after 3 faintly shining orange "dots" moved quickly across the sky in the direction of Carlsvognen. The 3 dots flew in the same direction, but they zig-zagged in sharp jerks independently of each other. There was no sound to be heard and I could see ordinary planes in the sky characterized by their red and white flashes and slow movement across the sky. The distance could not be judged as it went very quickly. When I stopped to look at the stars, a man in a tracksuit ran by, but he was gone before I saw the 3 orange dots. I got to thinking if it was secret planes patrolling the skies now in connection with the American terrorist attack?

Have you received reports of UFO sightings in North Zealand on Saturday and last night. Have observed a luminous ball in the colors red, blue, green, orange and white circulating. It did not move and was present for over an hour. It was approx. 5 - km up ... It was not a plane, helicopter or satellite. Been in aviation for 10 years, so used to seeing pilots.

I came out into the kitchen and saw that the garden was fully lit. After that, the object came gliding quietly from SE to NE, after which the light in the garden faded in the same direction as the object disappeared. The object was not stationary at any time. The distance to the object is estimated to be at least 1 km and the height above the ground cannot be immediately estimated. The size of the object was about 15-20 cm long in the field of view and about 10 cm high. The shape was oval. The object had many green points/lights, about 0.5 cm in size, all around, located higher up than the middle. At the top was a bright red light, about 2-3 cm in diameter. No light was radiating down from the object.

At approx. 22.50 9 flying objects could be seen over Bogense - they came from a southern direction towards the north. First, 4 orange bright (constantly) luminous objects could be seen flying in formation, like "panes on a deck of cards" - these could be followed for approx. 1 minute, after which they seemed to rise very quickly, and the lights faded, and disappeared very quickly. Immediately after this, a new object came from the same direction and on the same course - again clear, constantly luminous, bright and strong yellow. Disappeared in the same direction as the other 4. Quite shortly after 2 objects from the same direction and on the same course as the others - again clear constant luminous clear & strong yellow. Disappeared in the same direction as the others. And again very shortly after the last 2 objects from the same direction and on the same course as the others - again constantly bright clear & strong yellow. Disappeared in the same direction as the others. It all had a total duration of approx. 5 minutes. There was no sound to be heard - and that evening it was completely windless in Bogense. It cannot have been a question of airplanes, balloons or satellites.

My sister and I went for a walk to see if we could see any shooting stars as it was fairly cloudless. Suddenly another satellite came from approx. northeast towards the first. As they are about to pass each other (I assume they are not the same height) #2 starts zigzagging, ahead of the other, which, not zigzagging. Lasted approx. 60 sec. I just couldn't get my camera out of my pocket!
Reminiscent of a satellite that stands and flashes, but flashes very clearly in green, red, white and stands still. Been looking at it for almost 2 hours and looks od to stay in the same position.

I would like to know if there are no others who have seen the phenomenon my wife and I saw on Saturday, August 7 at 10.30 p.m. We sat on our cozy terrace and enjoyed a glass of wine. My wife had just lit a few candles when she noticed that there weren't very many stars in the sky. As I was about to comment on this, we discovered a large circular orb heading our way. It glowed VERY bright orange and a little yellow. It came closer and closer and we were deeply concerned with this phenomenon. Suddenly it stood still for a few minutes, then jerked to the right of us - to the left of the phenomenon. After three to four jerks it stood still again and then VERY quickly "flew away" and it disappeared into the horizon. We have of course investigated whether this could be a plane. It is out of the question, because then it would have been on fire and would fall down. It couldn't be the aurora either - because it's not just a ball, and it doesn't shine that brightly either. My wife and I are convinced that this was a real UFO, but there must be more people who have seen this phenomenon.

First I saw a big bright light. When I looked, it was a constant light of several colors - blue-green, orange-yellow, red-purple, like a chain of lights where the lights change. There was a vertical line through it that glowed blue. In a large circle around there were two white lights flashing (airplanes?). After a long time, a whitish mist with balls of light came from the bottom. Then there were 4-5 less bright lights that flew around, or suddenly stood completely still.

One evening my wife and I had been out moving irrigation systems in the bog. When we finished that and stood looking at the horizon, we heard a whisper over the neighbor's field just over a ditch from north to south. We looked for the sound and saw a glowing orb coming closer. We were startled. There were some 1 meter pipes, we had decided to crawl into them, even though there were 50 cm. water in. When it was 100 m from us it retreated the same way it had come, and we breathed a sigh of relief. We heard some aerial phenomena today and got the address for you.

My wife notices some very bright dots in the night sky, so we go out on the terrace and see approx. 7 objects, clearly constantly glowing in yellow-orange colors, which move at an extraordinarily high speed (faster than ordinary airplanes). They come from the south-southwest, not in any formation, but very scattered, dripwise and well over several kilometres, and after they have passed the New Little Belt Bridge they head east (towards Copenhagen). And they are not scheduled planes that we know of, as they sometimes come from the same direction, but partly the scheduled planes take the direction of Billund Airport and partly the light from these objects is extremely large, clear and bright yellow-orange - yes, it actually looks like UFOs as we have seen from the TV. We can see that this looks strange and I rush for my digital camera, I take a picture, but unfortunately I can't turn off the flash, so there is nothing to see in pictures (immediately anyway), I take a more, this time without flash and zoomed in on one of the objects (and this is okay). I wanted to take more pictures with the whole night sky on to show a number of the unexplained and strange objects... BUT before I can click the lights disappear... you'd think "they" saw the flash from my first image and command blackout for the entire fleet. I expected to get an explanation in the press the next day... but it didn't happen - I wanted to state my observation... but where and to whom? I mentioned the incident to an acquaintance and he suggested that I consulted ufo.dk - hence this report! You would immediately think that there are many, at least in our area - Fredericia/Middelfart/Strib, who have seen this?

I was out with newspapers and was up at the top by the other way. There I saw a light in the sky. It rose slowly above a cloud. When I looked for it on the next road, the light was gone. At first I thought it was a plane, but it didn't rise in the same way. Maybe it was a satellite, but it shouldn't be that bright. I don't know what I saw and I'm still in doubt.

We are 4 people who one evening in early August sit on our balcony and chat. The weather is calm and it is completely starry. One of the company has never seen satellites travel across the starry sky, and she is captivated by sitting with her head back and spotting satellites. Occasionally we also observe shooting stars, including a large shooting star that explodes with a flash of light in the middle of the Chariot, a fascinating sight. Suddenly our "observer" lets out a hoof! what is it?. We all look up and spot a V-shaped object which is traveling across the sky at great speed, the object moves in a straight line across the sky in a west-southwest direction, but approx. 25 degrees above the horizon it suddenly changes direction to the south, then disappears. The V-shaped object glows with a diffuse warm yellowish color. The V shape was broken in the middle where there was no light.
The object hangs approx. above Odense, is luminous with rays around it, as if it is circling a little.

properties.Colors: som en metalcigar med røg i

properties.content: Was actually on my way to bed and had just brushed my teeth when I decided to go out on the terrace and get a few mouthfuls of air - which I often do, if it's cloudless, I face the sky to admire the starry sky... As I consider going back inside, I see from my left a luminous object coming floating at high speed across my garden heading straight for the church tower... Its route was very significant to me, as one from my garden can see the top of the old water tower to the northwest and the top of the church tower in the opposite direction... The object appeared just above the water tower and followed in a straight line towards the church tower, however it disappeared in a "fading" way before reaching the church tower . I perceived it immediately and was able to follow it all the way without any problems... I managed to think a lot of things.. And the first thing that crossed my mind was that it was a shooting star that I remember seeing so many of on countless summer camps and canoe trips.! But I quickly realized that it couldn't be - otherwise it would have to be the first square shooting star I've ever seen. Only when it was directly above the garden did I notice its actual shape – if I have to describe it briefly, it looked like a long airplane wing, but there was no airplane body to be seen in the middle of it. I managed to notice the way it was lit - there were no flashing lights or lamps as you often see on regular aircraft - it seemed more like it was lit from within - or the way a statue or building might be illuminated from upwardly shining floodlights. Against the night sky it looked a bit yellowish - and from the way it came into view, it seems that even before the water tower it had been illuminated for a while... And it was only when it had reached the opposite side that it kind of dimmed the light to disappear into a kind of pocket in the sky – just above the church tower. The route had no bends or curves, it flew in a horizontal and straight direction. My first reaction was to stand for a moment and look in the direction it had disappeared in and I really tried to work out what it was I had just seen - not many moments after it had crossed my garden - then my boyfriend arrived out at the door; he had just taken out his lenses, as he was also on his way to bed. I told him what I had seen and he got a little "squammified" as I did - but he didn't come out on the terrace to look in the same direction as me as he can't see very well without lenses and so gave it up in advance. I explained to him the appearance of it and just had to recover a bit and sat down in my office chair in front of the computer - as I had to turn it off anyway. I estimated the time it crossed my yard to be at 01.45 – 01.46, and that the actual observation of it lasted about 4-5 seconds – so it had a fairly high and sliding speed. One o'clock was noted on a note and I decided to sleep on it before I started looking for somewhere to report it to.

I was sitting watching television, when suddenly at approx. 10:30 p.m., there was a bright light in my living room window, right next to where I sit, I turn my head towards the window to see what is happening in the window, which is illuminated by a flickering bright light, and in the glare I can see a profile face of a person, the whole thing stood for approx. 1 min. or less. When I get to work the next morning and go for coffee, one of my colleagues is sitting and telling me about a strange incident she had last night at 10.30pm, when she was on her way home through Sejs near Silkeborg, when suddenly she sees a luminous ball of fire above a treetop, which is there for approx. 1 min.

When I saw a broadcast about UFOs on 26 9, I thought of an episode in 1971. We were 4 people sitting on a terrace in Hareskovby. There we saw 3 large round lights just above us, circling around. A few minutes later, 3 jets arrived, then quickly disappeared to the east.

Was out fishing with my family on a very beautiful and quiet evening when I suddenly see a very clear stable light moving slowly and completely silently, not very high in the sky. It does not twinkle and is not a satellite or a shooting star ...(sees a little later a satellite that I have seen so often before, but it certainly does not look like the other one we saw)... Everyone stands in wonder and observes the light, which begins to descend almost vertically downwards, and suddenly the object begins to "lose" its light, then turn slightly orange-red and then disappear completely. I regret now that no one took a picture or filmed :(

Standing at my workplace at Aarhus University in Emdrup close to Emdrup Station. I stand on a roof terrace and look over towards the station, where further out I can see a light and think it's not a star, and think it might be a plane, but it's standing still in the air. Suddenly the light becomes creative and it pulses with a bluish light 2-3 times. Then it moves calmly across the sky towards Bispebjerg Hospital, where it stops and pulsates sometimes with sharp, bluish light again. Then it stops pulsing with the light and flies back again to where it basically came from and stands still again. That's how it looked. Then it starts pulsing loose again with the bright bluish light and flies on and out of my sight. It must be said that not a sound came from it.

This observation has bothered me for many years. I have thought a lot about what it was I saw. I was on my way to evening school. The year was 1986 or 1987, but I'm almost certain it was 1986. It was autumn anyway. I cycled down Fuglebakken and turned onto Tarupvej. I could see from a distance that the light curve was just changing to red. I slowed down and looked up at one light curve to see if it turned green. Right above this strange thing was hanging and I got so scared that I ran into the curb and almost fell off my bike. I looked up again, but the thing was gone. There had been no sounds at all. Everything was quiet. But I have been able to see the object with my inner gaze ever since. It's like it got stuck. It looked like a triangle, but with curved sides. These sides curved inwards. In each corner sat what looked like large round glasses. I don't remember if there were lights in them, but they were plain to see. The object hung quite far down, I would shoot it to have hung approx. 1-2 meters above the light curve. The object did not seem terribly large, I mean there approx. was 2-3 metres, between the 3 "corners". There was a light pole quite close by, and I remember the object as being dark or silvery.

I observed what at first looked like an ordinary shooting star from my terrace. It went from north to south and almost across my entire horizon before it disappeared - so much longer than a normal shooting star usually lasts. But, the strange thing was that when it reached the "zenith" it turned sharply to the west and then continued south again. It didn't last more than a good second, and I've thought of explanations like the ridge of the roof interfering with my line of sight - but that doesn't really hold up, because I see lots of shooting stars where I live, and no one has acted like that, neither before nor since. I don't really believe in aliens, but I think you must be used to finding "natural" in strange phenomena, so I hope you've heard of this before and have a natural explanation close at hand :-)

Today 15/3 at approximately 14:45-15:10, during that time anyway. Is my mother out in her garden in the Boholte/Hastrup area in Køge. She looks in a southern direction towards Herfølge and sees an object, approximately the size of a car. It has a white underside, is elongated/egg-shaped and has 2 wing-like protrusions on each side, though smaller than normal airplane wings. It flies very very fast towards the north without a single sound, and it leaves no contrails in the sky. We've seen planes here all day and they've all had contrails. She follows the object with her eyes, and when it has reached a distance towards the north, it suddenly slows down and begins to circle around. As she describes it, it must have been over the north/western part of the Boholte area in Køge, as it begins to circle in a ring. After circling around in a circle a few times, it disappears madly quickly, again without sound or condensation, in a westerly direction, approximately towards Lellinge/Åshøj. The closest object must have been to my mother, I can roughly calculate, like a little 180-200 meters away, as she describes that it circled over a small forest we have between us and Boholte. She describes it as being at the same height as the planes that we have flying over us, which have to land in Kastrup. We live under the approach route to Kastrup and therefore see and hear many, many different types of aircraft every day. So it's been that far down, so she should clearly have heard the sound of engines, especially the furious engines that various drones are equipped with. The object cannot have been some form of balloon as it moved incredibly fast, stopped and circled, then disappeared very very quickly. Furthermore, it is blowing from the north today here in Køge and it moved from the south towards the north/west. What my mother particularly notices is the total lack of sound, as well as the fact that it could stall and then accelerate very quickly.

It was a Sunday (or bank holiday) morning, in the month of January (I think) in 1978/79. I was 16 years old and in the 10th grade - I remember it because I told my physics teacher afterwards. I was standing in the kitchen of my childhood home on Kierulffsvej in Slagelse. From the window you could see over a field (Soldatermarken was called it, and there was a barracks which is closed down now). Over to a road further away (Rosenkildevej). It was bright and quiet. All of a sudden - as if out of thin air - there was a flying saucer some distance above the field (probably 10 m above and 150 m from me) - very clearly, as I have later seen them pictured; round and with "windows". It was there for maybe 5 seconds. and just as suddenly was gone. Subsequently, a blue star appeared in the same place, which was also there approx. 5 sec. and then just as suddenly disappeared.

We arrive driving on Ibjergvej in the evening, and it is still relatively light. There are no oncoming drivers or drivers nearby. Up from the sky comes a ball of light the size of a fist approx. It travels directly vertically towards the ground, and a few meters above the ground it disappears. It has been approx. 50 meters ahead of us and it was 100% not a shooting star.

We saw 2 round balls approx. 300 meters away. I took my binoculars and saw a glowing orb that was metallic and had like grids around it. Lightning came out of it. One ball went down, and later it came up again and together they both disappeared. I would think the balls were the size of a table tennis ball in an outstretched hand.

On the evening of 18 August 2005, in the square above Frederiksberg metro station, the outdoor concert had just been held: "music from the underground"... In addition to the stage people, who now left and packed up, there were quite a few, mutually independent groupings, remained hanging in the square. Everyone looked up...and then looked - AN EXTRA TIME (!!), because none of us had seen anything like it before... ; an orange "object"; moved over our heads; Both distance and size are difficult to judge when you do NOT know information on just one of the parts (and when you have NO IDEA WHAT it is you are looking at), but when the object was closest above our heads, it resembled (in APPARENT size) about an emergency rocket (several of those present talked about that... (which everyone knew at the same time was completely and utterly out of the question... of course!!)). It was orange with a distinct "ball-like shape". MYSELF perceived it as being a bit "woolly" (blurry) at the edge...but with a clear shape. The object did not blink in any way and had no other colors of light... other than this orange "solid, saturated" light... There was absolutely no sound! It flew in a straight line from approx. east - south - east, and towards approx. west - north - west. As it moved away to the west, it became more apparent that it WAS very far up in the sky...it was getting smaller and smaller, and although the speed was reminiscent of something that might be compared to a regular airplane's, it took several minutes before it started to go out of sight... (before that finally happened, however, it disappeared rather suddenly... and came back a bit... and then disappeared completely!! - mysterious!!). By the way...it was windless and completely clear and cloudless!! We were a LOT of independents (about 30 - 50, aged about 18 - 50!) who saw this mysterious object, and MY take was - CLEARLY - everyone gaping and looking in amazement and talking about HOW strange it was ...and people asked each other what time it was "this definitely needs to be reported"... "it's too weird"... "a real UFO"...etc...!! It looked absolutely nothing like anything we are used to being able to observe in the sky... we had not seen anything like it before...!!!! ....It WAS real... and we were many witnesses...!!

I know my observation is short but I still humble myself to write because! I saw something I've never seen before. I've read your front page about coming comets, so it could very well be, but no! a shooting star, I've seen a lot of them. Since I was 10-12 years old, I have had an interest in UFOs and the beyond, but have put it into oblivion or behind me, but even though I have been wearing glasses for a year now, I know that what I saw was oyster/oval shaped and had a small tail behind it and moved relatively slowly across the sky. Yes, I'm writing that it didn't last more than about 5 seconds, but there was enough time to realize that it was something I hadn't seen before, and by the time I eased up and got up to the windows, it away. Hope I haven't wasted your time.

Was standing out in the garden when two gray objects - looked like gray plates - came from the north and flew south. Was probably approx. 500 meters up (my best guess) and they flew next to each other with 100-200 meters between them. When they were past my garden, but still within my field of vision, they flew towards each other, switching positions as to who was flying farthest east and who was flying farthest west. They flew at a fairly high speed and there was absolutely no sound from them. Just 5 minutes later, two planes came into view. One came from the northwest and one from the east, they flew higher up and you could hear them clearly. Planes occasionally fly over my property, but often higher up. I don't know if it was just a coincidence that they should come now, but it was funny. I don't think it could have been drones, as they flew reasonably fast and there was no mouse, but whatever it could have been, well...

After we launched our rockets on New Year's Eve and stood watching other people's rockets, we saw a bright yellow oblong glowing object. It was observed from an open field out in the countryside approx. 10 km from Ringkøbing. The object moved from the west with varying speed (periodically stationary) towards the east. Appearance approx. 70 degrees above the horizon. The object was considerably more powerful than the North Star that it passed by.

Saw the same thing as the person from Brabrand on the 11th or 12th - but......first the object flew from west to north - then there was an explosion and after that it became small again and flew south. AND IT WASN'T BALLOONS OR SHOOTING STARS !!!!!!

I was sitting in an apartment with a friend of mine when I heard a bang, a bit like something broke through the sound barrier, I looked out the window and saw 3 relatively large red lights fly by. i rushed to look out the window but i couldn't see anything at that time.
There were 3 yellow lights that came on with a good distance like the wooden dots that are here. . .

Sat and had a cup of tea. Saw a white/silver oblong object in the sky. It flew pretty fast and I only got one picture of it and then it was gone. I don't have Facebook but will try to post it if I can figure it out. I took the picture on my Samsung duo mobile phone.

I live high up, and have a view as far as the eye can see towards Roskilde.. I often look out at the water, but this time something quite unusual popped up over the Roskilde area.. It came out of nowhere, probably flew what corresponds to 200 meters, and now comes the reason why I am writing this report.. I stand looking right at it, and it continues quietly and calmly pace, and with a snap it became invisible.. I wondered a lot, and tried to find it with binoculars, it was just gone.. Because the direction and height it flew in, it is impossible that it could fly out of sight behind the horizon, or behind forests/city or other things.. I would describe the object as oblong and gray metallic, and considering the distance it was very large.. See often scheduled flights in the same area, and they are not even half the size..!

In the evening before I go to bed, I often stand in the balcony door and look at the stars. This Monday night it was a little hazy, but starry. I bent my neck back and looked almost vertically up at the starry sky, where I suddenly spotted a large "shooting star". However, the object was too large to be a normal shooting star, the light was woolly-yellowish, and did not trail any tail. Also, it was moving slower than a shooting star, but still fast. The object first moved down towards the western horizon, but the course suddenly "broke" towards the west-southwest horizon, after which it disappeared behind some clouds/haze on the horizon. I must honestly confess that I dismissed it a bit because I had seen a similar object in August. So I thought maybe my eyes were teasing me a little too much here at the end.

I looked at the stars before bed. The sky was starry. Suddenly two very fast lights came across the sky, from the east due west. They both seemed a bit blurry in their appearance, and it was hard to tell how high up they were. They might look a bit like floodlights on a cloudy sky, but this night was 100% starry. The two lights were also much smaller than a floodlight normally is in the sky. It took the two candles approx. 5 seconds to go from due east, across the sky to due west.

properties.Colors: grøn skiftende til rød og tilbage
properties.content: The first part of the observation at 20:00, where a green ball is observed coming from the south, changing to red and back again 2x, from which to disappear as a red object behind the houses in front I am still on target for; but the second part, where first 1 red, then 2 red non-moving orbs are observed several times over 2 hours, is now identified as being 2 red lights on top of cranes located southwest from the observation site. They are located on the quay area at Kalundborg harbour. I think it is just as important to report back if the object is identified as to report the first sighting, in order to be left with the "honest"

To the north-northeast, a luminous object was seen falling directly towards the ground. It was unlike any shooting star, rather space debris. It fell straight down, appeared red-hot on the underside with a bright tail behind it, before extinguishing/disappearing from sight approx. 105 degrees above ground. Was in the middle of the road between Klovborg west towards Nørre Snede as a passenger in a small passenger car. Far off to the right is an object in the sky moving down through the atmosphere at such a speed that it is red hot on the underside. Judging from its trajectory, it was no further away than perhaps as little as 20-50 km, judging by its relative motion across the starry sky as we moved at a good 80 km per hour. The driver of the car could not see the object, which was 95 degrees to the right of the direction of travel, when it was observed and approx. 100 degrees five seconds later. North Northeast.

I was out for a walk... coming right out of my door and can sense that I should be looking in the direction of Hvidovre Havn. A bright red light comes on, which I look at for a few minutes, after which it disappears again. I was looking up at the sky to see if something was passing by, when I saw an object 100 meters up or something in that direction rotating rapidly... It flew out towards Køge Bugt... The object was square, dark gray ... And it spun around very quickly... I thought at first it could be a Japanese lamp, but it behaved strangely. Sorry, unfortunately I have a bad camera in my phone...

I went out with garbage at 10.30pm and looked up at the stars and saw this orange ball of flame which pretty quickly flew by and quickly disappeared in an easterly direction as it became more red orange (here my wife comes out and sees it ) and smaller and smaller and finally disappeared of sight, it did not change direction at any time. All day I have had this feeling of looking in this direction where me and my wife saw the UFO.

We sat 4 people and looked at the stars. Suddenly we observed 2 lights high up in the sky which appeared to be moving in the same direction and about 5 degrees apart (between 30 and 40 degrees up). After 30 seconds they turned slightly to the east and disappeared. It seemed like the lights were fading.

I sat watching movies and looked out the window by "accident". I noticed 2 orange "comet-like" things moving closer and closer. Also looked a bit like it had a fire tail. Grabbed my wife immediately and took her out into the garden, where we looked at it for approx. 15-20 sec. Then I ran in and got my digital video camera and managed to film a bit. Don't know how much and how good the footage was. After approx. 1 minute both "comets" were gone. They both had the same course and came from the same direction and also disappeared in the same direction.

A blurry light circling in big rings, at a constant speed and moving like that too... At first thought it might be youths playing with lasers, but the light also came close and there were no people below , as well as it probably can't be done at such an even speed over such a large area... Just looked again... It's still here..

We had driven my mother home, and had reached the landfill road intersection and stopped at a red light. When I spotted a bright dot coming from the Sjællandsbroen side of the Sjællandsbroen flying in the same direction as the road, but a little above the town and towards Amager. I told the wife it couldn't be a plane as it had no flashing lights so if it was a UFO she should get the video camera out She was reluctant and tired but it only lasted that moment as she couldn't really see either some flash. Our oldest looked out of the sunroof and decided it wasn't a real airplane. It was flying slower now and was out over the harbor, maybe over downtown. Just after the bridge flap on the bridge itself I drove in and out we jumped, our three children stayed in the car but looked out. I tried to film it but only got a tiny dot, a brief moment, which could be anything. A couple of fishermen down by the water saw it too and hoped I could see it better. It was approximately 20 degrees to the right of us, perhaps above Amager. It kind of backed up and back a few times, like a car that couldn't turn in a narrow place, before it slowly flew over Copenhagen and disappeared in the clouds about 15 degrees to the left of the bridge. The size was a little bigger than an airplane that has landing lights on, but it was the same light, even though it was flying in different directions, there was maybe a slight pulsation, the light was slightly orange.

2 red-orange spots on size with a 2-crown parallel in the sky, one spot stopped and stood still for approx. 1 1/2 minutes while the second spot continued and became fainter. During the entire observation there was no sound and there was nothing to see in the binoculars, the spots just got a little bigger.

I went to my south facing window to draw the curtains and immediately spotted a pair of orange glowing objects floating silently (I immediately opened the window) across the sky from southwest to northeast. I live on the fourth floor and have a great view of the sky on both sides of my house! It reminded me at first of the paper balloons with a small light in them that are sent up in the East on certain occasions. However, I found out that it wasn't! There was a total of approx. 20 pieces, unfortunately I didn't count them. I was far too busy pacing back and forth in my apartment to watch them appear in the southwest and disappear in the northeast in a light cloud cover there. Pretty quickly I remembered that I had a pair of bird binoculars lying around of pretty good quality. I found it and pointed it at one of the objects and was thus able to observe that the objects consisted of a circle that moved as if on edge, and in this circle there were a lot of glowing points that almost looked like light bulbs that were lit, however, the light was much stronger! At approx. 00:29 it was over, no more came!! A very unique experience and it looked very beautiful! I wonder what it was?

I am sitting with my mother in front of the Culture House on Iceland's brygge, and at is 12.50. We get a cup of coffee and sit and look at the seagulls in the sky. Suddenly I spot (again) a group of bright spots in the sky. Unfortunately, I don't wear glasses, but my mother does and counts the spots up to 15 pieces. Is there anything here that repeats itself? PS I can easily see the objects, but with my mother's glasses on, they were sharp in the sky until they disappeared. We sit and follow the objects, which are moving at a good speed towards us from the Nordhavnen and towards Islands Brygge in a straight line with the harbour, - and see that at a very high altitude they disappear further and further away from where they eventually disappear from sight. The objects are far away and very high up. My mother describes it as at flying height, and I mean it too, and possibly higher? They are luminous, and a bit light blue in colour. I notice which way the clouds are moving in relation to the objects, and it is not the same way!! I have told my mother about the last time I saw similar objects in the sky, so it was really nice to be able to share the experience with another person. After the objects disappeared upwards (notice they were coming towards us and therefore should become more and more visible) and disappeared, of course we sat and looked further to see if more came. It did! At 13.07 2 objects of approx. same place far far away. They followed the same path and disappeared approx. where the large group disappeared. Now we got a little excited, to say the least, and my mother joked that now more would probably come, after approx. 20 minutes. Believe it or not, but in exactly the same place at 13.21 2 more appeared. They followed the same pattern, and you could really sense that they were bright and almost neon blue.. Now we are out in balloon considerations again, I know, but come on!! 15 objects as last, and not! same way as the wind blew, as well as that they kept a good speed, and disappeared out of, even though they were coming towards us, - and therefore should become more visible, if you otherwise know a little about perspective and size ratio... I don't know, but balloons , birds etc. it just can't be!! What are the chances that someone once again sends up 15 balloons, which by the way are insanely high up and flying against the wind, and apparently disappear out of, is random?? In any case, I think regardless of the outcome, it is my duty to report what I/we saw, and at the same time I am really happy that others besides me have shared the experience.. Unfortunately I didn't have a camera with me, and I don't know either Has it made a difference? Since, like last time, they will only appear as spots/balls.. As a small side note, my mother called right after she had returned home to herself, on Tagensvej. Just looking out in the same direction before she puts the key in the door, she sees God help me 3 more. It is at 15.53.. She says, as she also mentioned to me earlier, that they were triangular!! (I did not write that in the report). I couldn't see it myself at Iceland's wharf.. But she was also wearing glasses..

I stand in the garden, cloudless blue sky, as an ornithologist I always look up into the sky. Suddenly between the trees to the east I see a luminous object in a constant speed to the west. I have never seen before in the 40 years I have been observing birds. 100% sure not a plane. Lower route than flight altitude and at a "strange" fast forward constant speed.

We were out for an evening walk along Arresø, suddenly we see 3 pink, half-sized round like balls hanging in the air approx. 200 to 250 meters above the forest on the opposite side of the lake in a southern direction, (we stood on the Ramløse side of the lake, looking south) - 1 above and 2 below, like in a triangle, with equal distance between these "balls". We estimate these to have been about 3 diameters/each of these... The distance was the same between these all the time, and suddenly all 3 slowly shut off at the same time and they were gone... We thought that maybe could be very large balloons?... but they wouldn't be able to be extinguished 100% at the same time, we think... I wonder if others have seen the same thing!!!

One summer evening in Skovshoved Harbour, I see an object coming towards the ground at high speed. Since we can see the approach to Kastrup, I think it could be toilet waste thrown from a plane, as there were some stories about this in that period. But as it gets closer, I see that it is a diamond-shaped, steel-gray object that rotates completely silently on its own axis. When it reaches a certain height (50-100 m, and probably the same from the port), it stops falling, and begins to move back and forth between north and south directions, still rotating on its own axis. This is also observed by some anglers, but these speak Polish/Russian, so we don't get to communicate in any other way than pointing to the object. A couple of planes come in for landing at Kastrup, and then the object starts to vibrate in addition, as if it is "disturbed" by the planes, after which the shaking stops when the planes come a little distance. The object lingers longer and it begins to darken. I go to a phone booth (this was long before the cell phone, after all) to, in my excitement about this, ask with the information if there is a place for reporting UFOs, (I think there was then), but only get the number for the UFO- jeans - comical but unfortunate. When I go back, the object is still there. Being the relatively reasonable teenager that I was, I had to go home at the appointed time, knowing that an excuse that I saw a UFO would not be enough of an explanation for coming home late. I cycle home, somewhat affected by the experience. I cannot give more detailed data than - compass direction etc. than what I have described. It was like nothing I've seen before or since.

We were at a 30th birthday/garden party in Ishøj sommerby last night, where we saw some strange lights that we had a little difficulty in identifying. They moved fairly quickly one at a time across the sky with a certain distance between them.. There were probably about 10-14 lights (white lights) one after the other without counting them well enough. At first we thought it was helicopters but couldn't hear a sound even though it was a calm and clear evening. They disappeared like a candle-wick smoldering away.. The company came up with several possible bids, but has not been able to confirm whether it has also been one of these.. i.a. that it should be weather balloons, but why so many, and why with lights on.. someone thought that there were also short flashes of green/red light flashes.. but it wasn't planes, they don't come that close on eachother. We also didn't think it could be gliders, not that many at all and then at night.. as far as I know gliders also fly more in bird flight paths, and not quite as precisely straight lines as these objects. Unfortunately, I am not that well known in Ishøj, so I can give a direction, but they came in a tail after another, one white light per "object", and they came in approx. 2 - to me - straight lines.. and with a roughly equal interval between them. Didn't seem like a practice flight either. Hope possibly through this to have the veil lifted as to what it was that we saw last night. Several people in the company had a military background, and they did not have any qualified guesses about the phenomenon. Can't remember the exact time, but think it was in approx. Half an hour between 22:30 and 23..

A sound of deep frequency - not a helicopter (my husband who also observed has a lot of experience with helicopters in his job as a geologist) - catches our attention and first my husband looks up and sees the object, calls me and I'm out in the courtyard while running (5 sec). We then see strongly flashing, slow-flying object with characteristic "light formation" moving at an uneven pace over our house, where the object stops and hangs in the air. It is difficult to judge distance, but the object is perceived as large and brings to mind both pinball machines and Star Wars. We view the object from our illuminated courtyard. My husband photographs the object with his iPhone, and when the phone comes out, the object flies away in a south-southeast direction across the forest. As we will see the image afterwards, it is completely white and without a trace of the object. For the sake of comparison, we took one more picture this evening in the same direction, and the picture shows the dark sky and part of our house.

Was on my way home from Albertslund station along the track, when a golden colored bright object appeared on the horizon. What jumped out at me was that there was no sound, and there was no tail either. (Like something burning) but a very bright golden light gliding across the sky. The funny thing is if it's raining and it's cloudy, then it would be something burning, it would slowly go out, and if it was an airplane, there would be some kind of engine noise or some flashing light , as the clouds hang fairly low when it rains. Now comes the strangest part. Five minutes after the first sighting, a similar one appears in the same straight line as the first, but it is followed by a third in the same straight path as the previous two. When I discovered number 2, I called my wife and asked if she could go outside and look up at the sky and tell me what she saw. (Just so I wasn't imagining things), but she saw the same as me, although not the first, but the last 2. We tried to take some pictures, but they didn't turn out that well, but you can tell.

We drive on the motorway at Silkeborg - towards Aarhus - and approx. 2 km after the 110 km/h speed limit ends, we both see a shooting star straight ahead over the road on the horizon. It starts at the top and descends almost vertically, although approx. 5-10 degrees to the east.

Like quite a few others, we also saw a flying triangle. It flashed in all the colors of the rainbow alternating with approximately 0.2 sec. gap. Not very large object flying very close to us. One pole vault and I could have reached it. No earthly idea what it was, but the object came down to us out of nowhere. Hovered over us for about 15 seconds and slowly took off again with a sudden explosive change in speed. Size: best compares it to a large fireworks fountain. Material: transparent and yet not as the colors made it difficult to see through and the changing colors teased one's eye. Recordings have unfortunately not been taken. when we went into shock.

2 bright orange objects observed (however with like atmospheric flicker and not at the same time) with approx. 3 minutes gap. Moved from SW to SSW where movement ceased and the objects separately during approx. 30 sec. slowly diminished and finally disappeared completely. No specific sound, but traffic noise close by. Used to seeing airplanes and helicopters in the area, but this was definitely not normal "airplane" behavior! At the same time as the observation, there were planes in the sky with normal plane-light flashes without the atmospheric flicker. The objects were moving at normal airspeed during the observation, but appeared to be outside the Earth's atmosphere, just as stars do - glowing with atmospheric flicker.

My daughter and I come walking on our way home after. I picked her up from work. Suddenly the sky lights up enormously to the east, it lasts a few seconds. We stop and wonder if it was thunder, but no sound comes and the light disappears. We continue to walk home. After an approx. 3 minutes, the strangest rumble comes in the same direction as where the light was. The boulder itself probably lasts approx. 45-60 seconds. And we're talking about it being pretty weird. And that we have never seen anything like it.

Noticed a luminous object in the sky which was flashing continuously. Where all colors were present! Moved west at very slow speed! Can you help me? What have I seen? An hour later it was still present in the sky!

My husband and I park in front of the house at 21.24, and gets out of the car. When I look up at the starry, cloudless sky, I first think I see a shooting star, but in the same second realize that there are several "stars", all speeding away at a furious speed in a straight course and unchanged V- form across our house. In the V-shape there is a "star" at the tip and 3-4 "stars" on each side of the V-shape. Behind the V-shape follows a single "star" which moves at the same furious speed as the "stars" in front, but in a safe slalom-like course. There was no sound, and in a few seconds the lights "went out" - not all at once - but as if the lights were being gradually, rapidly dimmed, starting with the front ones and towards the back ones, as if they were flying in behind a cloud - but it was cloudless around them, so you could see the surrounding, stationary stars. I was so surprised by the sighting that I exclaimed "What is that?", causing my husband to see the whole thing as well. While we were still speechless back on the road, we called the family we had just visited and told them what we had seen. We stood looking up at the sky to see if there were any more bright "stars", while the family asked if it could have been birds - but unless birds have started flying with turbo engines and white headlights as bright as stars, we could immediately rule out that it was birds we had just seen! But what it was, we'll probably never find out... ?

Around 22.00 the time of approx. 12 years ago, I was driving home from my son and daughter-in-law, who then lived in Agtrup near Kolding. I am driving with my two dogs towards Kolding, it was dusk, not quite dark yet, the weather was completely cloudless, over the horizon lay a faint pink daylight, it was too bright for a star to be seen so clearly. As I get clear of a row of trees, I see to my left a bright, I think, star, - unusually bright white light, but not enough with what it was moving, - almost dancing, just above the treetops. I have become curious about it and allow myself to be tempted to drive up a country road, where I had a better view. To my astonishment, it lowered itself even as I drove up to get a better look - it was right on the edge no matter how high I got up. Here I lasted about five minutes. It just danced, and moved from side to side, quite a lot, actually got smaller. I felt it recede, so I doubted whether it was a star, it had now become a little more dim in the evening light. I got a bit nervous/scared, turned the car around and drove towards Kolding. Here I experienced being followed, slowly as quietly it followed me. It was my intention to get out of the car and try to stop others who were driving in order to confirm my observations. However, I had become so nervous that I continued my drive, slowly, and kept following it on my left. I followed it up over the high-rises, and in the middle of the houses came a bright streak of light, not what you would perceive as a light from a helicopter, it was like the light came from the ground and slowly hit a point on the observed light/phenomenon, which now stood completely quiet in the middle of the high-rise buildings. I got all the way to Kolding, where I had to turn right, so that I got the phenomenon behind me. Here I decided to drive to a place where I could see over most of Kolding to the south. When I reached my decision point, there was nothing, nothing at all, the sky was devoid of anything resembling it. I should note that I had my car window rolled down for a brief moment while I was driving on Skamlingsvejen and where I stopped for a very small moment. There was no noise! - no noise at all! I was scared, I was curious, but I was actually shaking all over. The dogs were calm! A long time later I was on an errand with Egon Petersen, who I knew was interested in UFOs. He had a business in Kolding. Talked to him about what I had seen. I didn't dare tell anyone else. Egon said it was a daily occurrence for him, it was something that happened all the time. Just writing about my experience makes me feel the excitement. Somehow the event has done something to me, a deep impression and to this day I am sad, I was so scared, it was so close to me and I don't understand there is no one else who have observed it. It could be a star, which I also thought at first, but this one was moving, so it was easy to dismiss it. Basically, it has been good to be allowed to tell my experience. I have often had my doubts, but it runs like a movie on my retina when I think about it, I think I myself have observed something that was different.

Was looking through my old cloud videos and found this strange object that passes in front of me the second after I start a recording on my JVC HD Camcorder GZ-HM200 (*.mts). Filmed out of my terrace door with a compass heading west. I think the object came from the north-west and flew south-east about The special thing about this one is that it looks like it emits condensation/fog as it flies. At the top of the object you can see mist of some kind being emitted. And it's like there's a ring of mist around the object too, most evident at the bottom. I did not notice the object when I was filming, unfortunately only 7 years later I discovered this. Have shared the article on your Facebook page under the title "UFO fly-by on surveillance footage from Denmark"...

At 20.00 we arrived at our home in Køge. After driving the car into the garage, we see a number of glowing orange/yellow "balls" flying/drifting from east to west. We couldn't hear any sound. They flew in groups one after the other. In one case, one light faded. The luminous objects came in 2 groups while we observed them - and talked to 2 people jokingly that it was strange enough and that we were probably being invaded. I contacted the police on 114 to see if they knew anything, which they didn't. The person concerned asked if it could not be laser light, and in any case it was not. I tried to take two pictures with my mobile phone, but they were not clear because of the light from the house. I am happy to send the beetles by SMS if there is interest.

One summer morning, the weather was really good, I stood out on our east-facing terrace and looked in the north/east direction, the sky was completely clear and there was no wind at all. Suddenly I see something slowly flying from west to east. It is a relatively small object which corresponds very well to the description given in the article, it most resembled a flying refrigerator lying down, and it actually had some things sticking out at both ends. At first I think it's a balloon, but since there's no wind, it's moving too fast and far, far too steady to be anything like a balloon. It flew almost as if it were on rails, which a balloon doesn't do. Could it be a remote-controlled plane of some kind? No! Because there was no sound at all from it, and the hum that a remote-controlled engine makes can be heard far away. I think it was moving at 30-40 kilometers an hour and it flew right over some blocks of flats which are about 60 meters from our house so it was quite close to where I was standing and therefore I am quite sure what i saw matches my description. It has been up to a height equivalent to 10-20 meters above the roof ridge of the blocks, and the blocks are 4-storey standard blocks from the 60s. I follow the object and see that it is flying in the direction of the center of Køge, and here it is that I think that if it has continued on that course, approximately north/east, then it will end up in Copenhagen at some point. I have never forgotten what I saw, but I have also never seen the object again, however I do know that there have been people over in the blocks of flats that it flew over who have experienced a strong light beamed into their windows late in the evening, and those reports are about 10-12 years back in time, and I remember that there was a lot of talk about that/that light in the neighborhood that summer. About 10-12 years ago, I also saw some lights over Køge bay, for which I also have no explanation. I stand one evening at 9-10pm outside our front door, which faces south. It is completely starry, and it has also been during the summer period. I look at the stars and see one of them start to move slowly to the north/east, it could easily be a satellite, I think, but a few seconds later, another star starts to follow the first, and then my serious attention. And believe it or not, a few seconds after the first 2 start moving, they were completely still to start with, then first a 3 and then a 4 start moving after the first in the same direction, and there are now 4 stars flying in a straight line one after the other to the north/east. It should be said that our house is right under an approach route to the airport, so I see a lot of different planes every day and night all year round, but these 4 objects simply could not have been planes or helicopters and certainly not those Chinese hot air bags, it has become so popular to send up. I have not seen anything like it since then, and therefore I remember it as clearly as if it were yesterday.

I observe a luminous transparent milky white object coming flying from the east over my head - it is difficult to estimate the height and speed, but perhaps it is 500 to 1000 meters up and apparently flying fast in a straight path. I follow it with my eyes, it disappears over the sky 30 degrees above the horizon to the northeast.

I was out with my dog and looked up at the sky when I stood still. I looked up to look at the planets currently showing. As I have my nose to the south, and look approx. 80 degrees up in the sky, I see that there is a white light that passes for about 1-1.5 seconds. At 2 second intervals the same white light comes passing again. Exactly the same place for the same amount of time, same direction. Then 2 seconds pass, and another one comes, exactly in the same place. And it happens a total of 4 times from what I saw. I can't say if more came before I spotted it. It appeared to be something flying into the atmosphere or like 4 missiles being fired. Shooting stars do not come 4 times in the same place at equal intervals. Neither do meteorites. It did not flash like airplanes nor did it have the same color light as the above. Nor were they satellites, as they do not fly in such a column. I'm pretty sure it was something from outer space that came in or something that went out there. I've never seen anything like it.

Just arrived home from work and sitting on my terrace with my girlfriend. Looking up at a blue cloudless sky to enjoy the good weather. Discovering a bright spot in the sky, at first I would have thought it was a plane, but not this time. (the speed catches my eye). The object comes from the southeast and moves at a speed of approx. 6 - 7 times faster than a passenger plane can perform. I assume the height to be 10 - 20 km, probably higher. No sound or condensation streaks and moves from one part of the horizon to the other in approx. 10-15 seconds. Impressive. I find it hard to believe that it is a plane, but a natural explanation could perhaps be a smaller asteroid that has passed quite close to the earth and has been so illuminated that you could see it even in broad daylight.

In search of the Perseids, a white/yellowish ball of light, surrounded by a similar haze, appeared northeast of my residence. Approx. 15 degrees to the left of Cassiopeia, and midway between the horizon and the Cassiopeia constellation. It then moved in a NW direction at a leisurely speed and without any noticeable noise, then disappeared behind some trees further away from the observation point. During the observation I opened two apps, plane finder and radarbox, to see if it could be some registered flying object or a larger registered drone, but nothing to be found. All the glory lasted about a minute.

Randomly sees a yellow-orange light moving across the sky. It's star clear, think it's MIR at first, but it's too big (measured between 2 fingers in outstretched arm, it's as big as 5-6mm) and it moves faster too. Followed it with my eyes in an open window until it disappeared. There was no sound or smoke. Stood for a while looking for it and then went back inside. Immediately after I sat down, another one came, maybe a little bigger, but otherwise the same movement pattern and still no sound or smoke trail.
Looking at the two red stars in the sky, suddenly a bright object rises vertically along one star, disappears after a few seconds, appears between the two red stars, then disappears completely.

We saw a triangular object that was spinning around itself over and over. It looked like it was darker on one side and brighter on the other. However, the light may also have been the sun, which reflected on the object. It started heading west, then stopped and circled directly above us for about 20 seconds. Subsequently, it turned around and headed east at a higher speed than before. At the same time, it dived somewhat towards the ground. Size and distance from the ground was difficult to judge. Part of it was filmed with the iPhone 4.0.

properties.Remarks: se beretningprojektørlys om talt i BT
properties.content: Driving on the motorway, towards Folehaven. A few hundred meters before the Hvidovre exit, two round spots of light are seen chasing each other, up in the clouds. Duration one to two seconds. It may well be thought that it was across Damhussøen as told previously. I have seen a bright spot before, actually many times, in the same place, but there the spot was very clear and sometimes I could see the beam from below. These two spots were almost half the size and almost looked like the light was inside the cloud. Saw them briefly again just before Folehaven. A bit mysterious.
I went out for a smoke, but happened to see two like see the "MM" with weak green light for only 3 seconds. on the east. Very fast and away.

Was milking cows in the afternoon when suddenly a very bright light comes on, all the while it started to be very windy, I went out of the milking parlor and to see what it was, and there it was, an oblong round thing which shone over the nearby field, but it was moving away. Tried desperately to get a picture but couldn't as my mobile was very slow.

At the time of observation, I lived on a protected farm in Sorø. I often stood and smoked a cigarette by the 400 m long driveway. From this place, at night I had gotten used to seeing the bright lights of passing cars when they came over the hill by Susåen heading from Næstved to Susåen. The property has an unobstructed view down to Susåen to the south, and to Næstvedvej over the neighboring farm's fields to the west, and the forest that borders the property to the east. At the time, the neighbor had a spruce plantation on the north side. Apart from the lights of the cars and the lighting of the house, there was no lighting from either the road or the nearby towns. I also don't remember the moon being visible that night, but am suddenly blinded by a very strong white light, which I first assume to be from the high beams of a car coming up the driveway. I clearly remember my wonder at who could think of visiting us unannounced so late in the day. The light very quickly became more powerful than anything I had seen early on! Only when I noticed that the light source was rising up instead of following the long driveway did it dawn on me that something special was going on. From a height of 0 degrees, the light source rose to approx. 45 degrees... Then the light went out as suddenly as it appeared. A few seconds passed before my eyes could make out anything in the darkness. What I now saw was a strange diffuse lighting, in the same place where the strong light went out. In this diffuse illumination, I saw an oval object bathed in a dim, pale green light. The light was NOT coming from the oval object in the air, it seemed more like it was coming from the surrounding air! I shouted and told my boyfriend, who was inside the living room, to hurry out. Perhaps a minute had passed since the light "turned on". My gaze did not leave the oval, floating and silent object. I could even decipher several different rectangular zones on the oval surface which was a large part of my field of vision.

properties.Colors: rød og lyserød med røde lyn
properties.content: I pulled my curtain and opened the window approx. at 03.10. When I looked up I saw a red/pink neon glowing object shaped like two deep saucers with the deep side facing each other. All around the vessel there was red lightning that looked like it was standing still. The air around the craft was also red and pink, and if I took a pencil and held it horizontally at outstretched arm and measured the craft, it would be approx. 10 cm wide from my point of view. For comparison, an airplane would be 4 millimeters long using the same measurement method. The object was completely still, and the lightning bolts projecting from it appeared to be cut out of cardboard. They neither changed nor changed form. Therefore, I actually thought it was a figure made with laser light to trick people into thinking they were seeing a UFO. But below the craft it was completely dark, and there was no light from the ground. This is how it stood for approx. 15 sec. It must have been between 3 and 8 km high, because my impression was that it was far away and high up, although it was quite clear in outline. Then it flew suddenly and 100 times as fast as a plane to the southeast for approx. 10 seconds before it disappeared behind the roof of the buildings on the other side of Ingerslev Boulevard in Aarhus C. As it flew, there were still these static red lightning around it. I have never seen anything like that.

Looked out the window when I saw a very bright white light, around. It was there for a while. When a large truck came driving, it disappeared. There were no stars in the sky as it was cloudy. What was it, has before obsv. Eq.

Approx. 10 or more balls of light/flying objects flew across the sky with the same heading, same speed and at approx. 1 minute interval. There was no sound or flash of light from the objects and they flew across the sky until they disappeared from our view. They appeared from the same point on the horizon and flew in exactly the same direction at an altitude too low for an airplane. They continued to appear for several hours, albeit with longer breaks between each session. Several people on the street lined up and looked at the phenomenon and wondered.

Monday 19 March 2010 at approx. 05.20 - Clear morning sky, bright object, direction southeast, height above horizon (like seeing an airliner), speed probably 4-5 times that of an airliner in the sky, I observe it from my 1st floor balcony facing south. It flies with a fixed trajectory to look at.

Standing shaking my duvet and looking up at the sky. There are 5 to 7 orange lights in the sky, 3 of them in a line, as one shows that stands at 10 minutes over, the other lights are scattered a little randomly to the left of the 3. There was no sound, but it can also due to the distance. I quickly went inside to wake my mother, who reached out and saw 2 lights disappearing 120 degrees S.E. A shocking experience. What is it???

Just saw what I want to think is a meteor ... From my balcony with my evening coffee in hand, I have Roskildevej right next to where I live on my left, and it leads out towards Glostrup ... Roskilde, etc. .On my iphone's compass which I pointed to North.. the direction of the white glowing falling thing was .. South-West direction.. At first thought shooting star but as it neared .. the end.. I could clearly see fire and tail .. a total of 2 - 3 seconds.. before it disappeared behind the ridge of the neighboring house. I was lucky to have my distance glasses on, which I use when I occasionally look at the stars - so it was razor sharp. A shame I didn't have my mobile at hand so I could film it.. but it didn't last long... but I picked it up for the compass. Now I know it's not a UFO as such.. but it could be very fun to hear if others also saw it. Hence this report.

From the roof window I look out towards Copenhagen, 3 orange/red luminous objects, which move from south to north in a dark sky. With 7x50 binoculars, it is possible to see that the lights do not come from an emergency rocket, as there is a clear corpus. It is difficult to determine the distance, which can be several km. One object appears in an arc above the long house, Carls Ro in Rødovre, and disappears down behind it. It only takes 5-6 seconds. I live less than 500 meters from the house, which has 6 floors and my roof is much lower. The second object rises in the sky from south to north higher up and is completely free of the nave. The light from the object dies out quickly. The third object is clearly closer to me and also comes from the north. It continues higher in the sky, and is now apparently moving east. The light from the object is very strong in the binoculars, like looking into a burning oven. The light then becomes dimmer and after 10 sec. the object has disappeared. It should be noted that the objects emitted a characteristic orange/red light, which was identical to the observation I and a witness saw over Kamstrupvej on Saturday 14 July at 22.38.

My husband and I experienced the following one night in June: Around At 3 in the morning I woke up to my dog barking and wanting to go out - he never usually does - so I shuffled out to the garden door and let him out. I stood in the doorway, waiting for him, when my gaze is caught by a cone-shaped blue light, (almost like a flashlight), which turns on and off every second. It was located by a fir tree, and came from below and up. At first I thought it was something I had dreamed, but when I had seen it 4-5 times, I went into the living room and looked out the windows to see if I had gone crazy - but no, it continued! ! I'll be honest, I thought I'd lost my mind, so I went in and got dressed and went over to the tree - and the light stayed on. The closer I got, the stronger the light. When I had reached almost the edge of the lawn, I agreed with myself that I must have just confirmed that it was not me who was seeing, so I went inside and called my husband. He went out the garden door with us, and we also faced the tree - and sure enough, he also saw the light. We stood and looked at it for a while - and agreed that it was probably a flashlight and some children who were on a night run !! (How stupid can you be, there were no sounds - only lights). We agreed that we could check around the tree in the grass in the morning, as it would have come down... We went to bed and slept the rest of the night. And our dog didn't react to anything - not even when he was let out. He just stood and looked at the light. The next day my husband went down to check - and there was absolutely no sign of anyone - nothing had been stepped on!! So I'm just thinking - what the heck was that?? Has anyone experienced something similar?? I catch myself looking for the light to this day - and if it comes again, I'll go all the way there!! Would be grateful if there was a logical explanation for my experiences.

It was a constant glowing light that was very far away in a NE direction when we saw it. It was moving extremely fast. Too fast to be an airplane, but too slow and closer than a shooting star. When we had looked at it for approx. 5-6 sec. the light went out abruptly and the UFO went pitch black, but continued at the same speed. After a further approx. 5 sec. it disappeared behind some clouds, so I can't tell the degree from the horizon. I assume that this has a completely ordinary explanation, and do not think that it is something extraterrestrial. The only reason I am bringing it up to you is because I have no explanation for what it was. I cannot explain what it was for the following reasons:

I started looking the night it was announced that there would be a ton of shooting stars in the sky. Can't remember the exact day, but it must be possible to check. It was in Aug. month 2008. I could see several from my balcony, which faces west towards a rather dark yard in the evening. The following days I looked again to see stars and there was a nice full moon several days in a row and some stars I could see quite clearly. One stood east/west and the other north/west not as high in the sky as other stars, and to my great surprise, they began to move almost in figures of eight. Then a little to the north and then return to the starting point later, it looked like one made circles, then a little to the north, then a little up to return to the starting point again. After 15 min. I went back in. An hour later out again. They were still there. Stood still and suddenly there is a little movement to the north, to return again. I observed this for 4 days in a row, each time they were in the same position. The one time I could clearly see a plane out of kbh. airport, a larger plane flew below one, and then it stood still for a moment. One day it was cloudy and these were the only stars I could see. Subsequently there has been nothing for 3 days. So on Sunday 31/08/2008 I went out to look again, and there they were again in the same position. The one that's east/west was very clear that Sunday, white, and when I look at it, it's moving very quickly to the east and actually disappears right away. The other, which is more north-west, on the other hand, it moves very north and back and very high to return again. This took place for 10 min. Then I went back inside. An hour later it was still much more to the north, but still moving back and forth and up and down to the exit lane. At first I thought it was my eyes playing tricks on me, but that Sunday I realized that they were actually moving to return to the starting point east/west. The view from my balcony is in the direction of Avedøreholme - Kalveboderne, and northwest is Brøndby - Glostrup. One day I took my bike and cycled down to the mountain at Åmarken St. at Kalveboderne not far from Hvidovre Harbor at 23 in the evening and stood there on the top looking out over the city lights. It was a full moon, and I could not see them in the positions mentioned before. Could, on the other hand, clearly see kbh. airport and those flying from there. Could even see a helicopter over Bellacenter and that way. I'm sure it was one of those because of the lights flashing red, white and it was stationary. After 20 min. I was about to go down when I see a white star-like thing flying by the gas tower in Valby. It stood still and slowly moved slightly to one side so that it was hidden behind the tower. So forward a bit again. It was low down behind the tower again, then never to be seen again.

I stood in the doorway a little before midnight and spotted a yellow-orange light quite high in the sky. It looked like an inverted cross (had no binoculars). The light seemed to stand still, and it did not blink - and pretty quickly the clouds passed. Because of the vertical strip of light, I thought it might be a balloon with lights in it.

I stand outside and smoke before I go to sleep. I always look at stars when I can, and last night I did too. And saw what I thought was a star, but suddenly it moved across the sky. There was no sound. And then it was as if it turned/turned in my direction, because the light became sharp in my eyes. Then I thought it was a meteor. But then it turned again and moved silently across the sky slowly. It was completely white and shining bright like a star, and then it had like a little tail behind it. I have never seen anything like it and have to share it.

My girlfriend observed a golden fireball that flew very quickly over Viborg. The observation lasted a few seconds. The fireball was round in front and had a tail. I looked under the guide to recognizing UFOs. It was probably, as mentioned under point 1, a fireball or space debris, but I am sending this description anyway, as it may be that others have seen it and are writing in. Would like to hear more if you clear up the mystery :)

I lay in my bed and looked out the window. Here I usually lie and look at the planes in the evening sky. But yesterday was quite different. I look out, spot a bright dot that blinks, like it was a plane. I keep looking at it, but it just won't go away, it hangs completely still in the air. I wonder a little, but then think that it might be because the plane has to stay in the air, since there is no space on the runway yet. But after 1 hour it's still in the air, exactly the same place. I then think to myself if it could be a star. But the dot blinks as if it were an airplane, and besides, I couldn't really see any other stars. After about 1.5 hours, when it was still there, I fell asleep. when I wake up again, at 2 o'clock in the morning, it was gone.

I'm standing smoking a cigarette in front of my house when I turn around and observe what I first think is a stationary flare. I notice after a few seconds that the red light is sitting on the underside of what I would call a relatively small and completely black object.
