A few seconds after I observe the object in a stationary state, it begins to move due east towards Tissø. Height and speed are continuous. The object is under cloud cover, the sky was still quite bright and there was almost no wind. The object is also silent. Since it has been moving for 3-4 minutes, I can no longer see the red light, but can still follow the black object until it disappears into the horizon. I got a knock on the window and alerted my girlfriend. We are quite familiar with emergency flares, drones with lights, weather balloons, Chinese lanterns etc., but none of us have ever seen anything like this. I recorded 20-25 seconds of video of the object when the red light was still visible, but on the video you cannot see the black part of the object.

Was standing on the terrace, which faces south, looking up at the stars when a boomerang shaped object came from the NNW and disappeared towards the SE and could be seen for 1 sec. followed by 3 more in wing formation 3-4 sec. following in the same direction. 2-3 minutes later another one came from north to south. All 5 objects had the same size, color, brightness which was very faint but distinct and speed. The speed was the same as that of a shooting star. The brightness was like the most distant stars. The size was approx. 1 cm., where a star is just a dot. Height is estimated to be a few kilometers. Maybe the same height as a shooting star is seen at. I don't believe in a natural phenomenon. For that, it was far too coordinated. Paper candles are also not possible. I don't believe in light reflection either. And above all, I find it hard to believe it's man-made at that speed. I have seen several times the manned space station and other satellites, which are the same size as stars and move somewhat more slowly despite their 30,000 km/h. If they were comets or space debris, they would be so close that they would break the atmosphere and burn up, lighting up the entire night sky. Like the comet that fell here on the island a few years ago. I find it very difficult to believe that intelligence from outer space is capable of visiting us. But this experience was quite hair-raising. I hope you can use my information, and that you can give an explanation for this somewhat distinctive experience.

I was sitting on the terrace and suddenly a strange thing appeared. At first I thought it was a plane, but it stood quite still for a few seconds, then it moved a little to the left, stood, still again and then was gone. It was large and very round.

At 7:28 p.m., Horsens city center at the Vitus Bering park, which is between Horsens railway station and the pedestrian street, a bright orange object appears in the sky. The sky is cloudless and there are also no other atmospheric disturbances in the form of precipitation, fog, etc.

My daughter calls me from the terrace as she is out to blow out a candle and at the same time spots something in the sky, she doesn't know what it is. I go out there and we both look at the object which looks like a big triangle of shooting stars, small white lights/spots that follow in a triangle shape with the point at the front. The movement was in a straight line from north east to south west.
Filmed last night Saturday September 5th. It looked like something oval shaped on top of approx. 1 m high and 500m away.. Floated by completely silently... We were out driving...

Luminous object much larger than star, came at high speed from one side across the highway and later from the other side. At first I doubted whether it was reflexes. It wasn't. When I have now landed in Kerteminde and go out, I observe the same phenomenon. There is high speed. The light is visible as long as the object is behind the cloud. Unfortunately, I cannot take a photo. Tried with video, but it's just black.

At first we thought it was a big black parachute or a weather balloon and it was about 1000m away. It flew silently up into the wind, and suddenly there were two of them. They flew approximately 500 m apart, and suddenly they rose quite quickly until we could no longer see them. Unfortunately, I wasn't that fast with my mobile phone, but I managed to film them in the end when they were far away.

First observation on Vesterholmvej in Herning. Just after passing Gullestrupvej I became aware of a red light to the north over Gullestrup. First thought was that it was the light on a mast. But as there are no masts of that size in that direction, I stopped on a side road. Here the luminous object could be clearly seen. It was glowing bright red and moving at a moderate speed to the east. Tried to take a photo of it without success. The object disappeared in the cloud cover in a NE direction. The sight height above ground is estimated at 10-12 degrees. Was out of the car to observe. There was no sound to be heard. The distance has probably been too great. The direction of the observation matches the approach to FSN Karup. However, having lived in the area for many years, I have never seen aircraft display that color on approach. The light was bright red. Not pulsating. The color tone turned slightly orange as the object disappeared into the cloud cover. At the time of observation, there was an even cloud cover in the area. No visible celestial bodies to be seen.

I was walking along Bolandsvej in a westerly direction when I observed a large, luminous, stationary object in the sky. At first thought it was the moon, but then saw the moon about 45 degrees south. The object appeared approx. half the size of the moon. The shape was the most startling and like no celestial phenomenon: Almost like a drop shape on the head, where respectively the pointed end and the round end are flat. However, the warm white color did not fill the entire shape, but was most pronounced at the outer edge of the phenomenon and then faded inwards to disappear (ie become completely black). This dark center in the object formed a vertical lens, however, with "soft" ends rather than sharp ones. After observing the object for about a minute, I rushed in after my boyfriend. When he was supposed to see "my vision" about a minute later, it was unfortunately gone! So I didn't get to see where it went :-(

I'm standing out on my balcony one evening. And suddenly I see 3-4 red balls of light floating across the sky. They float in a uniform manner at exactly the same distance from each other in an oblique/diagonal line across the sky. Just as quickly they came into view, just as quickly they disappeared across the city to the west. I didn't manage to take pictures, nor have I found a logical explanation. I can best explain what I saw as some small round luminous red "balls" flying across the sky at the same speed and formation.

Driving in a car on Tingvejen in a northerly direction towards Grindsted. The weather is very clear, and I keep an eye on the big, beautiful full moon in the west (standing low) and at the same time orientate myself in relation to the traffic. The temperature is 0 degrees. At one point I look straight ahead through the windshield and see two white spots - no other light. Automatically thinks it must be a plane (Billund airport). Looking around - at the moon and then out the windshield and the two lights stay in the same position, which I see several times looking ahead. When I look forward for the fifth or sixth time, suddenly they are no longer there, and there is nothing to be seen in the sky where they had been. I of course looked to see if it had been a plane, if it/they had changed direction, but there was absolutely nothing to see. Nor do two planes usually fly so close to each other. I have subsequently researched how airplanes look with their lights and have come to the conclusion that airplanes don't look like that at first. The distance between the two white objects can best be described as that there could have been room for two objects between the lights. I really hope someone has a more scientific explanation for the two lights. The size of them will probably correspond to one eighth of the size of the Moon, each light.

I was out for my evening walk. as I usually do and look up into the sky to study my own knowledge/others' knowledge! Reach. Everyone knows how planes move across the sky with their (red/green flashes) and a dim white light. With good eyes and training this can be seen! As lucky as I was a few degrees below the plane flying across the night sky, something came out of nothing that I didn't even perceive. There was this white flashing light in front of me! It moved across the horizon from Æbelø to Jutland with it. It flashed a very harsh WHITE light that made my heart beat wildly fast in shock! And what is it. I took out my cell phone to film it. (But really stand and need a place where I can get my film changed a bit since it's very dark! I'm 120% sure if we somehow get nightvision on that video! Then I'll have a clear shot of a ufo moving across the sky.! Unless you guys can tell me otherwise!? Studied the night sky for 22 years. Seen things people won't believe or look for.

Walked the dog and saw a taller than wider orange phenomenon hovering at about the speed of an airplane over the heads of me and the dog. It didn't seem like the objects were high up, maybe a km, but hard to tell. The weather was completely starry, not a cloud in the sky. Up close, it almost looked like a large hot air balloon completely surrounded by a very orange light. In the center of the phenomenon, what seemed to be the hint of a steel skeleton was seen, in any case, as thin vertical and horizontal black lines. As I said, moved quietly to the southwest, without changing direction or altitude.

I happened to be looking at the starry sky and spotted a star moving across the sky. I followed it intensely with my eyes all the time and did not let it out of sight during the obervation. It first moved from east to northeast, and I saw that at some point it became blurry (probably because the distance increased). Although I could only guess at it now, I kept my eyes on its trajectory, and suddenly I saw it fly at an incredibly high speed back to where it came from more or less, ie. from northeast to east (southeast). So it flew at a steady speed from the east (southeast) towards the northeast, and suddenly it flew back at an INCREDIBLY high speed and had, what I would estimate, a 20 cm long tail behind it. It cannot have been a shooting star, because I never lost sight of the "UFO" (the moving star). If I hadn't seen it fly slowly first, I would probably have thought it was just a shooting star. At the same time, my older brother saw another bright object in the sky in the same position in the sky (almost) that I saw. He claims that this changed direction. However, it is only my observation that I can comment on here in detail. In fact, after this I saw another "star" moving from northeast to southeast. My father also saw this and he said it was a satellite, but then it suddenly came back, just like the one I had seen before, this one kept a steady speed the whole time, and my father explained it as being a high-flying plane. But it was silent, looked mistakenly like a star, and came DIRECTLY back. Nothing about it having to turn an arc to turn the 180 degrees. The observations are from between 22:35 and 22:48. The first, and to me most inexplicable, I saw approx. 22.38.

I'm on my way home from work on my bike. Inside the park I see what I think is a stray plaktic bag maybe 20 meters high coming into my field of vision from the left. On closer inspection, I see that it is a round disc with a white base. It actually flies under the treetops in the direction of Jagtvej. It flies on over the rooftops on the other side of Jagtvej. I would think that the diameter of the object was between 3-5 meters. It was a time when, for a few days, there had been flight exercises with F-16s that had made noise over KBH.

I see an object coming flying as indicated and at roughly the same height the planes come in over Herlev when they approach for landing in Kastrup. I can't determine the length of the object, but it has a plump snout and is completely closed with a couple of rings around the body at the back. It flies and sounds like an alm. jet plane, but there is no smoke or exhaust flames coming from it, and then the very strange thing; it has no wings! A strange experience.

I was out walking with my brother and girlfriend on Saturday 12 Oct. My brother points up to the sky and sees something big orange red hurtling down towards the ground. It was low in the sky. We quickly agree that it is strange and run out towards the field at Frederiksværkvej 19, cycle path, to be able to see better, as there are trees in the way. The fireball, or whatever it is, is hurtling down, but along the way it changes direction and hurtles up, down and up again, and down again. It's as if the "fire" is getting stronger and weaker. From the driveway we see gizmos from the side, but on the field, we see the back of that thing. From going up and down, it continues across the field, relatively low from the ground, towards Skærød. We follow it as long as we can. It becomes more indistinct and becomes almost white at the end, and turns off, or is too far away. Never seen anything so wild...

I, together with my good mate and big brother, have observed two objects in the sky south from Skanderborg in recent days, which suddenly appear and which glow in different colors, mostly red - white and green, it could look like there was fire in the object. We have been sitting in our cars on old Aarhusvej near Gjesing on a hilltop and watched the 2 objects in the sky for 5-7 minutes. This has now happened three days in a row, where we have seen the two objects in the same place suddenly appear in the sky with a reasonably created light. One object shines more brightly than the other, and today we saw the two objects standing still in the sky for 2-3 minutes, after which they flew at a rapid speed to the southwest. In the direction of Vejle. I am convinced that these are not stars or planes, since yesterday 31-07 we saw exactly the same thing just at a different time (22.23 to 22.40). The 3 of us who observed this took pictures of what we just saw.

Large very bright white luminous object, globular with short tail, observed sweeping from west to south direction. Significantly larger than the many shooting stars I have ever experienced. Is there an explanation - or have others observed the phenomenon?

Object is approaching at high speed in the indicated direction from west to east under the clouds. Same direction as wind. Warm, flickering orange light with special yellow core in the middle. When flying over a property, speed is reduced, and it seems as if the object is standing still after flying over. The light is just as clear from behind as it is from the front (a ball?) Then the light suddenly disappears and the object can no longer be seen. The idea goes to balloon (but not with constant flickering lights)! Helicopter was also an option, but there was no sound and the light was too hot (orange/flickering).

I simply have to share my experience today with you. I was in Tivoli with 3 others yesterday, Saturday 20/10. It's Halloween night in Tivoli, and at was approx. 19.10. We were standing right by the Chinese tower, I think it's called. For some reason I look up right where I'm standing and see three very faint lights and it's closer than you think as we could clearly see below the object which forms a triangle. I quickly say that to the others without taking my eyes off the object. It suddenly moves and exits the triangular formation, and the three lights line up and quietly fly away. We soon lost sight of them as there was a large tree in the way where we stood and could not follow them, but they flew towards the main track. It must be said that they were not very high up, and the second was that their light was very faint, like a clear sensation, like something hiding in the air, and no sound. Immediately difficult to say, as there is a lot of noise in Tivoli, and no it was not a drone (flying with a drone myself), and it was rather not something from Tivoli, and it was definitely not a plane. Before they were completely out of our sight, I took a picture without, I figured something would come into the picture, but it did, although very shaken, but you can see there are 3 lights in a row.

I'm on my way from my home over to Aldi, walking. It is dark, the sky is starry. To my left is a white light. It flashes. Behind it a little red. They are moving, same way.. I've seen that before, it's a plane. 5-10 minutes later, I turn up the path to Aldio and randomly look up. What I initially think, for half a second, is three stars. A faint one to the left, one to the right, a little further down and a distinctive white one.. The white floats down and at the same time turns somewhat off, towards a faint northerly direction, while it becomes weaker, in both brightness and diameter. It takes 2-3 seconds, then it's gone. 35 degree angle. It might have been the plane, but I doubt it. The light was stronger and there was only one. A shooting star ? they are gone much faster.

I know it is quite late to report such an observation, but I had no idea that such an organization existed until I saw you in DR2's Tema last night, 9/1-10. It has been almost 4 months since I saw this strange phenomenon in the sky. I was at work (evening work) and had a break where I talked to a friend on the phone outside. The sky was pretty clear with stars, and when it is, I spend a lot of time looking at it. I have faith that we are not alone at all, and want to see something strange and inexplicable in the sky every day... and it happened on Wednesday, September 16, 2009! It was a kind of ball of light the size of a large star, which came at extremely high speed across the sky, in a zigzag curve, with a slight reduction in speed when it was at the top of the sky, and then extreme acceleration to the south, zigzag end. It might resemble a shooting star, but I have never seen a shooting star that went from approx. 40 degrees from the horizon from the north, to about 30 degrees to the south - and WITHOUT a burning tail that a shooting star would otherwise give off. At the same time, its trajectory in the sky was not quite normal. It wound like a wave across the sky, had a small stop-up, and then continued at tremendous speed. To give a rough picture of how it happened, I will explain it like this: (the figures are fictitious, just to give an idea of the situation).

I stood on the terrace at night and looked at the sky. 4 red fireballs came gliding slowly and silently across the sky and disappeared behind heavy clouds. Then another 4 came. Called my wife who saw the last 4. Took binoculars and observed they looked like fire. Very red fireballs. Saw the same sight (only 4 though) two days earlier but didn't mention this. However, I wondered a lot.

There are two of us who look at the stars in the evening between Friday and Saturday. Suddenly something glides over us, a boomerang-shaped object. It seems big, but we can't judge the height. If it had been airplane wings, I would expect the plane to be close to landing. It appeared as if the object was dimly lit, as by a luminous night cloud. It was as if it was slightly transparent, or as if we were seeing it through a thin cloud. There were like oval "slats" close to each other, they were bluish. The object maintained constant speed, direction, height and shape. I expected to lose sight of it behind a tall tree, but it disappeared before. When it disappeared, it seemed like it just became invisible. I couldn't see clouds in that direction either, it was very starry that night. There was no sound at all. If we can get an explanation of what it could be, we will be happy, because it was just too strange to experience. I mean being able to rule out drone, cloud, plane, and flock of birds.

On the bus on the way home from work, I spotted a black object that flew immediately at the height of, or slightly below, the clouds. The object was black and was 2-3 kilometers away, it must have flown directly over Mørkøv in the direction of Holbæk. Both the bus driver and I saw it. The object appeared to be the size of an airliner or larger, but immediately flew lower. There were no obvious wings, and it flew faster than any airship I've seen before. Unfortunately I didn't manage to take a picture of it.

Once in the mid-seventies, I was probably about 12 years old at the time, I experienced something very strange that I will never forget. We had summer holidays from school and it was probably around 10-11pm in the evening. We were a lot of children playing and playing round ball down on the lawn by the block we lived in. Many of our parents were sitting out on the balconies enjoying the evening coffee (I think it was a Friday or Saturday). Far up, like little stars, we can see many, many small red balls flying in and out between each other. We cannot hear a sound. It seems like there are several hundred. We all line up and watch and wonder at this phenomenon. Everyone talks about how it can't be a plane when we can't hear anything, and so many can't fly between each other either. When we have been standing for a while, maybe half an hour, we suddenly hear a whisper to our right. Approx. 200 meters to the right of us there is another 4-storey block. Above this block now comes a huge red ball flying.....the ball seems as tall as the block, i.e. as tall as a high-rise building. It flies as if on its own axis at the same time. that it drives forward at very fast speed. and the only sound we can hear is this hissing. Suddenly it disappears up and out into the sky. In the meantime, it is thinning out in the small red "balls" up in the sky. They are still as small as stars and we cannot hear a sound. Suddenly I see 2 of them coming flying from different directions towards each other. They stop when they reach each other. One ball floats some distance above the other. Suddenly they "melt" together into a ball and fly on. This lasted between 1 and 2 hours before it was all over. We couldn't see where the balls disappeared, it kind of just thinned out in them. If anyone else has observed this incident, or has heard of others who have seen it, I would very much like to hear more. Does SUFOI possibly have received inquiries about this phenomenon once in the mid-seventies, I am also VERY interested in hearing more about this.

There MUST be some inside Roskilde who have seen it, because in my opinion it should be above Roskilde Fjord - north of Roskilde Harbour. We observed the object together over the phone from 21:45 to 22:00 when it suddenly disappeared after we had looked at the Moon and talked about the bright light of Venus. It may well have been there before 21:40 when my brother-in-law called. Last time my brother-in-law saw the same phenomenon (March 4, 2004) the light just "faded out".

Cycling home from Brugsen in Årslev along Overvejen. Seeing a flash-like turquoise light flash on-off: A brief flash followed by no light. Time between flashes approx. 1/10 second. Can only see the light, not how - if at all - it was attached to an object. Incidentally, it moved so quickly (in jerks) that it was difficult to perceive any object in the waning daylight. The light followed me on one side of the road for a few meters, before very soon opportunities to be on the other side of the road where I last saw it. I didn't stop, was a little nervous about the situation. Speculated on laser pens. Haven't seen what their light might look like, but this somehow seemed like it didn't come from such a source.

We were out walking the dogs, and I had a flashlight with me, which almost didn't have much battery, but there was a little. We went north and suddenly from the east approx. 20 meters into the field and approx. 10 meters above us, there was a very bright white light, not blinding, the planes went straight up above us and over the treetops and continued towards the (west) water. The nearest floated slowly and then a little faster, then disappeared behind the trees. I couldn't see it anymore because of the trees that were there and such dense scrub. And then I was about to die of fright. Have respect for the unknown. At the same time, my light went out completely. So we turned around. When we got back, my light suddenly worked again and with double power on, don't know if batteries can do that once in a while. But it seemed as if the object had almost stood still right next to us with the lights off and suddenly, when we come, it turns on, almost like a car. What did we see? There was no sound and it just came out of the blue. I usually always see what comes from above, but this one was just like a car that suddenly turned on its lights to continue at a speed of about 10 to 30 km, after that I couldn't see anymore because of trees etc. .. Had an experience this year, on that edge. Just another light.

While standing on the balcony (I live on the 14th floor), I observe something to the west. It was two bright orange lights that "turned on and off". My guess is that they were somewhere above Verløse at an altitude of 2-300 meters. After the two orange lights (2*venus size) alternated on and off, a series (3 to 5), smaller red balls of light were seen rapidly flying in both directions from the orange objects across the night sky and parallel to the horizon above a distance of approx. 8-1200 meters before they disappeared. I had observed this previously, in two rounds in total, with approx. 5 minutes in between before I got the camera going. My guess? two hot air balloons that turn on and off the burner and play with fireworks (although I've never seen roman candles, only with red balls, and that glow for so long, or balloons that flew after 10 pm). A passenger and I had just got out of the car at our home address. She asks if I can also see the strange orange light moving across the sky from west to east. I can. As I fumble with my mobile to film, it turns into two lights. The big one and a smaller one. They change direction, the small one flies a little away from the big light, and back to it again. They become one light again, and fly-disappear towards the south. I walk our dogs every evening and take great pleasure in studying the sky during the air walks. I often see satellites flying across the night sky, and there is also the air traffic. But I've never seen anything like it tonight.

On the way home from shopping, we see 2 constant red/yellow lights in the sky, no flashing like on a normal plane in the evening, (we often have helicopters and small planes above us, as the airport is relatively close), and after we parked in the driveway , we go out and look at them. No sound, but constant speed from our left to right. Then we see two more come into view flying in exactly the same path and finally a single more following the others a good distance behind. We follow them for 5-10 minutes, until eventually they all fly into a cloud to the northeast, and wait, but they don't come out the other side. We have never experienced anything like this before and they were flying opposite to the usual planes we see coming from the North Sea towards the airport. If you have an explanation or have received other reports on the same, we would love to hear back.

I was out playing alone on the terrace of my parents' summer house when I suddenly spotted a strange unknown object flying low in the sky. It was like it was standing still for a few minutes. There was no sound and no wind either. There was stillness in the air for approx. 15 minutes. I don't know what it was, but it wasn't like anything I'd seen before. Neither a hot air balloon nor anything else. And suddenly it was gone... It was cigar-shaped and gray in silver color.

Was driving my son to school in Jelling, suddenly two lights appeared in the sky far up (about 500 meters ahead, close to Jelling), they were completely still, asked my son to look and we agreed that it looked like light from two searchlights, but there was nothing else to see... no planes, boxes, strings, poles/rods or anything the lights could come from. Reached for my phone to take a picture but when I looked up again they were gone and couldn't see anything no matter which direction I looked... The sky was blue with a few small clouds. They stood still for 20-25 seconds. and unfortunately did not see where or how they disappeared.

Sitting looking at the milky way as it was very clear. I have my camera ready for the satellites, just filmed one satellite and I'm looking for more. As I look straight up above the house, I can see something dark orange in the corner of my eye, at first I thought it was birds, but then when I see the speed they were on and maneuvering, I could see that they were not birds . There were two of the kind of dark metallic and I think the orange color is from the city lights? They were incredibly beautiful when they catch the light. They flew in a braid side by side at very high speed towards the north and about 70-100 m up. Have pretty much observed the starry sky all the days I could since my first report of the boomerang UFO. I regret that I didn't film them when I had the camera in my hand, because it was almost indescribably beautiful.

Lives on the west coast of Bornholm, approx. 8½ meters above sea level. Has a view to the west and can often see the south coast of Sweden (also lighthouse that glows green). My experience this night started with a bright (sharp) white light illuminating the room where I had just gone to bed. Stayed there as I was in doubt about what I saw. - During approx. For 20-30 seconds, the white light illuminated the room 2-5 times, almost as if someone outside shone in through the window with a sharp searchlight. So bright a light that I wondered if my curtain was still drawn. I got up, went to the window and could now see that the white light "was" over the Baltic Sea, approx. 20-40 km west of Hasle (Bornholm) and approx. 5-15 km south / south-east of Ystad, Sweden. The position was just below the horizon line (or rather where I am at the horizon line - at the time of the observation it was dark over the sea). The white light flashed a few times, so that parts of the Baltic Sea were illuminated, and at one point the light was, as it were, "collected" in a large sphere, which was slightly larger than the full moon. The light was very bright for approx. 10-15 seconds, I decided to find the video camera. But unfortunately the light disappeared when the camera was ready, - the light disappeared behind the horizon. Smaller rays of light, however, continued to shine forth from behind the horizon line. After a total of approx. 10 min there was no more of the white light or small rays. I would like to add that I have seen the Northern Lights in Greenland, - but this white light did not resemble the Northern Lights, perhaps with the exception of the smallest closing rays. Furthermore, it was due west, and ended west / north-west. So today my daughter and I agreed that I must have seen my first UFO.

UFO seen at 3 on 25 March 2020 first. Bright light - then it disappeared (it was starry weather), then it reappeared with white light - it changed colors with red and green light then disappeared in white light as we fired SOS towards the object.

I'm standing in the garden, a light comes flying over me. Doubt at first it's a plane but it looks like it's much higher up plus it's a constant bright white light. Suddenly it accelerates to the east and stops for a minute or 2, after which it again slows down towards the lake, where there is another light. I notice, it almost looks like they fly together and then a few times around each other, and with one in a vertical line, one flies down and the other up and disappears....

I was sitting with my family in the morning on the terrace, when suddenly we heard a sound from the sky, which sounded like an engine "chocking". We thought it was a plane at first, as we had looked at planes earlier. But I looked up and saw a gray-black, triangular, flying object, and rushed out onto the grass to get a closer look at it until it flew away over the house and trees. It flew in the same direction and speed the whole time, never changing course.

Now my wife and I have experienced 3 sightings within 1 month in almost the same place. Sightings similar to the one filmed 12/2-12 at Malling. Around 18-19/1-12 I drive to our house at 7pm and see a large circular light source orange/yellow coming flying towards my direction of travel. I would guess the light source is approx. 100-150 meters above the ground. At first I think it is a plane, but there is no sound and no other light on it. When I first see it, it is approx. 500 meters from our house. I drive to the house and get out of the car to observe it. It is about 150 meters from our house and 100-150 meters above the ground. There is no sound at all and it moves quietly and smoothly in a smooth motion. When it is approx. 50-80 meters past our house, it stands still for a few seconds and then starts to move out over the water, and then it is as if it accelerates violently for approx. 10 seconds it disappears into nothingness and finally disappears completely. The entire observation lasted approx. 2 minutes For this sighting, I was the only one who saw it - the next one was seen by both me and my wife. This took place on the same day as in Malling - namely on 12/2-12 at around 10 p.m. My wife and I are sitting on the sofa watching TV when Janne (my wife) spots a light approx. 50 meters above the ground around the neighbour's house. We rush to the window, and then I spot the same light source that I saw around the 18th-19th. January. A glowing circle/ball in orange/yellow. We only observe it for approx. 8-10 seconds before it disappears. So on Tuesday 14/2-12 my wife observes it again. This happens in the evening around 22.25 when she comes home from a visit to her mother. She sees it again when she comes driving towards our house. Again it is above our neighbor's house hovering from west to east. She rushes in and calls to me, but when we come out together it is gone. I am very interested to hear if anyone else has observed anything similar during this period. The reason I am writing is, among other things, the video on your website and have just read about a person in Hjørrin,g who experienced something similar in January.

I stood talking on my phone and looked out the window and saw 3 round orange lights on a strip floating silently after each other at short intervals. 2 more lights/balls came. Never seen anything so strange before. I see airplanes fly by every day, and it wasn't airplanes that I saw. Don't know what it was, but never seen anything float in that silent way before.

D. 17-08-2013 me and my friend are sitting on my balcony at 10 pm. Suddenly I see a round fire thing very clearly in the sky that was cloudy and not a single star in sight. At first I think it's one of those Chinese lanterns that you can send up. But we quickly agree that it is not, as it is quite large and has a lot of speed. I live close to Billund airport, and there are many airplanes a day here, as the route is around the area. They fly very low and make a lot of noise. So we actually thought it was an airplane that was on fire. But it wasn't on its way to land, and it wasn't exactly taking off, as it was way too high up and wasn't going down or up, then it just held the height. It was completely silent, we couldn't hear a single sound. We have also not heard of a plane crash. Not many seconds passed. before it was gone and unfortunately we were so amazed by what we saw that we didn't get to take a picture. I've googled everything I can think of that it could be. We mostly think it looked like a comet because it was fiery red! But didn't it have a "tail" behind it?

Sees a light floating in the sky. It is constantly orange, but appears dimmer at times. I call my wife, who also comes out, and we agree that it is probably a "planet". We then notice an ordinary plane coming flying with its flashing lights heading east, i.e. towards the orange light. The orange light then begins its flight in a northerly direction. We observe it for approx. 3 minutes after it starts flying, after that we can no longer see it. There was no sound at all.

My wife and I are sitting in the living room talking when, out of the window, we suddenly spot a luminous ball in the sky, moving west at high speed. It drags a small tail of light behind it. The size of the ball of light is relatively large. It appears very suddenly and disappears again just as suddenly. What kind of phenomenon was that? The time indication is approximate.

We were sitting inside the living room when I saw the light from an airplane (I thought). We went out into the garden, because the light was unusually bright. The light came from the north, moved quite quickly to the south, suddenly it seemed to stand still, but that was because it changed direction to the east, then disappeared behind the clouds, all the while getting smaller. My friend, who was with me, observed the phenomenon through binoculars and said it was round and orange like the sun, and there were spiky flames coming out of the object, also like a sun, or like it was burning.

I was sitting on our terrace, and suddenly I saw above the neighbor's roof a white round light the size of a 1 krone - that is, something bigger than an ordinary star, slide quickly across the sky, to disappear behind a tree.

On Saturday evening, I am walking across the bridge in Silkeborg, when a piece of black airplane of a strange kind comes flying. It was silent, had the size of a helicopter normally. It had no wings or any shapes of any kind that I have seen before. Light came out of it, but not in a window, more that the lights were in a circle. It looked like a helicopter until I could see it from behind and then it was a piece of black material, a lump that glows. It flew over the central Silkeborg almost like an observer. It was fast and slow at the same time. When I took my mobile out to film, it had flown by.

I saw a flying fireball, but too slow to be a shooting star, too fast to be an airplane. It flew approx. 3-4 times faster than an airplane. My first thought was a crashed satellite or rocket. Was observed in Greve in a north/northeast direction.
4 continuous luminous round balls in a zig-zag movement over the roofs of Østerbro.

I was standing with my friend on a green or bunker just behind the clubhouse at Rungsted golf course. We were 13 years old and waiting for my mother, who was attending evening classes at the school next door. While we stood talking, we looked towards the SE and watched the air traffic around Copenhagen. The weather was clear, and due to the slight rise in the terrain there was a good view. One of these points of light moved out from the city towards the SW; i followed it as it seemed a bit different from the other planes. As the light gradually grew in size, we marveled at the fact that there was only one, steady light, where usually there would be multiple and flashing lights to be seen. It otherwise had the size, speed and height of a normal plane. When the light was approx. SW, we noticed another, identical light coming from the NW at the same height, like a mirror image; it appeared that the "planes" were on a collision course. But just as they looked set to collide just to the west of us - they almost seemed to touch each other when they were closest - they both reversed and flew back exactly as before, but on the opposite course - again like a mirror image . They did not turn immediately, but almost; it probably took a second at most before they had the same speed again. Our only guess was helicopters, but we both found it hard to believe that helicopters were capable of turning so quickly or would make such a risky maneuver, although of course they might be slightly offset to us in the longitudinal plane. In any case, drones did not exist then.

We sat 6 people on 2 benches and looked up at the tower of Saint Petri Church in Copenhagen. We sat right next to the tower and talked about the cone of light from a disco, which in circular motions lit up some light clouds just behind the tower, We joked that it was probably Batman's. Suddenly we saw a spot of light (like a medium-sized star) travel across the sky and stop – it was only when it stopped that we all really saw it because it seemed so unnatural for something to stop in the sky. The spot of light was still for a second or two, then it made a few strange zig zag movements. Then the devil touched it and it disappeared in a flash. The whole thing only lasted approx. 10 seconds. All 5 of us agreed that it wasn't from the cone of light, not a satellite (because it moves slowly and only in one direction), not a plane or a helicopter (since they can't stop, turn and accelerate that fast) nor our imaginations – we all saw it. For the next half hour you alternately looked up at the sky, but the phenomenon did not repeat itself – and that rules out that it could have come from the cone of light from the discotheque nearby. Saturday night at 01:07 the night sky was bright, and there were some quite light clouds through which you could see the stars - but there were no clouds in the whole sky. The reason the last person didn't see it is because the person wasn't wearing glasses.

I am making this report on behalf of my father who had an exciting experience with a UFO about a month ago. He does not remember the exact date, but since he was lucky enough to take a short video of the phenomenon with his iPhone, the time is ihf. registered. The film is still in his phone and it is possible that the date will appear if the film is transferred to a computer. Apparently you can't see the date unless the movie is transferred first. It could be interesting to find out what the film actually shows, and that is the background for this inquiry. My father claims that under no circumstances can it be a plane or a helicopter, and he goes on to say that there was no sound during the entire sequence of events. He has also described to me a yellowish-orange ball that floated rapidly in a SE-NW direction, about a quarter of the size of the Moon when the object was closest. He has not been able to provide details about the object's distance or height. The experience lasted 1-2 minutes, he guesses, but unfortunately he only managed to film the object for 14 seconds while it was moving away, as he had to go inside to retrieve his iPhone shortly before. We are very excited about whether SUFOI can contribute with an explanation of what it is that my father has seen?

15.04.2007, 21.31 (summer time) I was in Augustenborg looking at the starry sky. In the western part of the sky I saw a constantly bright object moving in an easterly direction at about the same speed as the airliners that frequently fly over this location. I noticed the object because the direction was different from the NE-SW direction that is apparently preferred by the airliners. The glowing object also attracted my attention, because the white light was about the same strength as the domestic scheduled planes use in the future when they approach for landing at Sønderborg Airport from completely different directions, at a lower speed and at a low altitude. This object had no direction from or to Sønderborg Airport, and most importantly: the strong, constant light shone equally brightly as I observed the object from the front, side and rear during the passage, which followed a straight course south of my location me. And I couldn't see the blinkers or starboard/port lights that planes otherwise use - there was only this white light that obviously shone equally brightly in all directions during the passage. I often observe the sky from this location - day, evening and night, and I am familiar with many different objects in the sky that I can identify as celestial bodies and aircraft. But this object differed in several ways from what I am used to seeing. Therefore, I am now reporting my observation.

Sitting in my caravan and hearing a very loud noise in the sky. Many commercial planes fly over here, but this sound was different and louder. A mix between a loud turbine and a dark hollow rumble. Then turned off the radio and looked out. There was a blanket of clouds over the sky going from west to east. On the horizon was blue sky. Out at the end of the cloud cover (approx. above Frørup or Storebælt) was a circular cloud formation. And out of it flew a luminous object with a luminous tail. It looked like a small comet. It flew at very high speed across the blue sky to the south. I had been up early to take pictures of horses in the morning sun, so luckily my camera was lying on the seat opposite me. I reach for it in a flash, and as I'm about to aim the camera, the object either disappears at the speed of light or just vanishes into thin air. I do a lot of UFO research on my own, so I tried to rule out various possibilities and rationalize. But both the appearance and the speed, the sound and the cloud formation gave me reason to believe it was a UFO I saw. It was all confirmed by the fact that last night and this morning large military helicopters flew around here in the residential area and out around my observation. They flew no more than 80 m above the rooftops. The weather is bad today, but thinking of going out for a drive and seeing if there is any unusual activity in the area today.

Hi, I read with interest everything you write and especially other people's accounts of experiences! I also have a story that I thought you should have. I am convinced it was not an emergency rocket as it will descend continuously and follow the wind.

Coming by bike from Beder up Oddervej towards Århus after football practice - It's really dark here on this trail system in the evening. Suddenly up around Søsterhøjsenderen a neon green object appears in the sky, with a whitish tail - It disappears at very high speed in the direction of Moesgaard Strand and to the east. Seeing it for the first time in the sky, it's hard to say where it appeared from, but there was really speed when the object disappeared - It was definitely not a shooting star, because it changed direction twice in the approx. 10 seconds, I observed it.

It seemed as if a light came from higher up than the stars you can see, the light came closer and became the biggest star in the sky. The star moved around in a very small circumference, after which it disappeared and became an almost invisible dot after approx. 5 minutes

I'm lying on the couch watching darts from Dubai when I look out the window and notice a big bright light (star) moving across the sky. I go out on the terrace and see a white glowing ball moving from west to east for approx. 50 degrees above the horizon to the south, it flies at a fast pace, there is no noise or engine noise nor marker lights. I immediately Google the ISS to confirm that it is the one, but the strength and height and time do not match it, that it should be a plane or helocopter isn't it, we often see medical and rescue helicopters over the fjord and planes for Aalborg and Karup use Mors as landmarks. I saw it disappear to the east, and I estimate it was on the other side of Skive.

I was sitting with my friend and saw a large light object coming from the water and onto land, after which the object went out. The object was 10 times the size of a star and flew at the height of an airplane, but was many, many times larger than an airplane. It moved at a speed of approx. twice as fast as an airplane. I took binoculars and could see a toadstool-like figure. Before the object went out completely, it had 2 times where the light went out partially. We wondered about the object and will therefore hope that others at Marielyst, Falster, have also seen the object, as it was very clear and mysterious.

I was standing by the road and saw something dark flying over some trees. It flew down behind the trees and disappeared at an angle. There was a gap between some of the trees, and if it were to be a bird or something, it would DEFINITELY appear in that gap. But this just didn't. The object was oval, not like two plates put together, but more egg-shaped without looking like an egg. The sun was shining brightly when I saw this object. I am very sure it was some kind of UFO
During evening walks with the dog, I go and look up at the sky with stars and bright Jupiter. Suddenly this "layer cake" appears with a wreath of white candles (6 to 8 pcs.) around it. No sound.

Heading towards my apartment from my car. For some reason I stop and look up at the sky. There are quite a few stars, but between them, a thing that lights up like a star flies quickly across the sky. Thinks that maybe it's just a shooting star, but it kept going and suddenly it stops immediately. Don't slow down it just stops. And it wasn't a plane, which also blinks and flies a lot slower. When I saw a plane a few minutes later..

I walk my dog up an old railway track that has been made into a nature trail. We're the only ones up there. We are going west. I look at the stars. I see something that looks like a very nice star and I think stop it's shining. It becomes more and more clear. I just look straight out and up. All of a sudden it splits in two, as if they were flying separate ways around the Earth. And they are gone.

I was awakened by an enormous loud noise. Thought it was a helicopter, but I don't think it was. It was approx. 40 meters long with bright light below, no floodlights at the front. There was a light at the back as it stood almost still, and there was only a slight breeze as it flew on. It came back again approx. 4 minutes later and then disappeared completely.

The incident took place on Saturday 24 September 2011, when I was with a friend, where we were going up to visit my friend, who lives in the same housing complex. Obejket flew so far that I don't know if it stood still. The strangest thing was that it seemed to be studying the whole city. The incident happened incredibly for 2-5 minutes, unfortunately I didn't manage to get a picture of it, but my friend did.

I was almost home when I saw on the horizon a large green ball of light followed by a green "tail" which was almost twice the width of the ball of light. Saw it in a southerly direction, but it disappeared more vertically down than horizontally. I know nothing about space, but have seen shooting stars several times and this one was MUCH bigger than what I usually see...

My wife and I were out walking the dog. We stand on top of a hill and enjoy the sunset. I turn around and discover a glowing orb. It is apparently stationary, at first glance it looked like a star, but it was too big and it seemed relatively close. It takes approx. 10 minutes, where I look at it and wonder what it could be. My wife saw it too, but she was busy with the dog. Now it was time to go home, thought the wife, so I turn around and walk towards my wife. I just had to look one last time before we left. but it was gone 20 sec. after.

For many years I wanted to write to you with the following observation. I wrote down the details then, and have kept the paper ever since, so remembering the story hasn't been a problem. Slept under the open sky on Humlebæk Strand, right next to Louisana, with my girlfriend at the time. I woke up very early from the cold and decided to go for a walk up to the harbor pier at Humlebæk Harbor and watch the sunrise from there. From here there was a view across the strait to Sweden, where Helsingborg lies a little to the north. I sensed that it would be a while before the sun rose, but was determined to enjoy the dawn. I had no watch with me. The weather was good, the sea calm. There was a light breeze and the sky was cloudless, both above and to the east. A little further north of Helsingborg there were some very high, thin hazy clouds. When I looked over towards the harbor area at Helsingborg, I saw that there were two tiny cumulus clouds, greyish in colour, hovering just above each harbor building... silo-like buildings. It immediately struck me as strange that in an otherwise almost cloudless sky, there should be such two small clouds. So I looked at them in the early morning light, and as I looked I could see that they were moving quietly... first towards each other, then away from each other, then in the same direction, as if they were moving independently of whatever wind there may be. It was plain to see as they could be seen in relation to the buildings. However, they stayed above the buildings the whole time. Furthermore, they changed their appearance, from elongated to circular, as if they had turned, and now showed the end profile. And in this circular shape they seemed to be surrounded by a faint green light. Slowly the "clouds" became elongated again, as if they had turned again. Of course I wondered what they could be if they weren't clouds. I thought it might be about balloons that were attached to some buoy that might be in the water somewhere out in the strait. But I couldn't connect that with the perspective, which indicated nothing more than that these "clouds" were where they seemed to be. I also thought it might be something to do with warm air, just above the roofs of the silos, forming clouds when it met the cold morning air. But how could they move from side to side? I watched them for about ten minutes, during which they continued to move as described. Then I briefly looked up towards the north, to see if the sun was about to appear (after all, the sun rises high on the horizon at that time of year), which was not the case. When I then looked back to where the "clouds" had been, they were gone. I had looked away for half a second. There is a small footnote. A little later in the morning, after the sun had risen and some of the locals had started coming down to the beach to take their morning dip under the lovely summer blue sky, I was lucky enough to see a meteor burn off. It was like watching a match being lit against the sky... there was a long flame and then a clear cloud of smoke, pretty much right over my head, maybe 50 meters up. It was beautiful. There is an additional footnote, and it is an observation that I made late in the evening of the same day. But I will write about that in a separate report.

At the time, I was on my way home from Glumsø after dropping my aunt and uncle off at the station, where they were going by train. I had both my children in the back seat. They were 2 and 3½ years old at the time. On the country road on the way home to Engelstofte, where we lived at the time, I saw a rather dim light over the road, it got closer as we drove in the same direction. I thought at dusk that it was a hot air balloon and told the elder to roll down the window to look. I stalled the public van and rolled down the window to see for myself. The youngest had fallen asleep. It just hung in the air, relatively close to the ground. When I look in the rearview mirror it's gone.

On an evening walk with our dogs, we suddenly discovered 4 luminous objects in the sky. The first 3 were located in an equilateral triangle, and the 4th came a little after the first 3. They flew at a steady pace in the direction of Middelfart. After some time the rear one receded and disappeared completely. Then the other three entered a line and then slowly disappeared one at a time. What did we see????.

This is exactly how it was experienced: as if someone had drawn a line of light in the sky, or as if there had been a hole in the sky and light was shining in. Of course, it was not an ordinary line, from an airplane. This one was very different, in that it was yellowish, relatively strongly luminous and very thick. As I looked more closely at it, it seemed to me to look very much like a comet, with a ball at the bottom, followed by a tail. However, the tail was wide, as opposed to a stereotypical comet tail that tapers at the end. At first it appeared that the object was standing still, but gradually it became clear to me that it was moving. During the ten minutes I watched it (I dropped the observation when my bus arrived), it moved completely vertically from high in the sky to low over the rooftops. The time should be quite accurate when I looked at the clock on my mobile phone. However, my clock is three minutes too fast compared to teletext's time. A light in the sky may not sound that alarming, but I cannot stress enough that the phenomenon appeared very surreal and out of place. As the above quote shows, so was the impression it made on the children who saw it. It was unlike any human aircraft or celestial phenomenon I have ever seen (not that I spend much time looking at the sky).

We were driving on the motorway towards Skødstrup when we saw 3 lights. At first I thought it was hot air balloons. But it couldn't fit, when I looked further up, there were even more, it looked like they were hanging on a string down towards the ground. The light was like a flame from a hot air balloon. They hung down from north to south. They were close to the highway. Wish I had turned around + a camera.

I lie in my bed and look up at the stars and yes just lie and look. Suddenly I see something black bigger than a plane... It has been very high up, so really high up... At first I look a second time and don't quite understand what it is I see, but follow it and can see this black shadowy things fly across the sky and can see it shadows the stars it flies under, or whatever they say. Sorry if I phrased myself so badly, but I've never seen anything like it. I KNOW I saw it and have no doubt at all. It was almost impossible to see, but I don't know, I'm a bit in shock right now. I'm not posting this for your forum or anything, but I have no idea who will believe me if I tell anyone this, but it was NOT a plane because there was no light just a big black shadow ( the shape like the fuselage of an airplane only bigger) move pretty quickly across the sky... I apologize again for my poor phrasing and my possibly confusing way of writing, but I can't really believe and understand what it is I just have seen! Always skeptical of the stories you hear and it's not like the sightings described on your site no lights or flashes just a dark shadow/spot moving north and well then it was gone again after the short time i followed it across the sky...
Reddish phenomenon which is visible from late evening and during the night. Lightly pulsating as if on fire.

I stood out on my balcony and had a pipe of tobacco while looking at the stars. Suddenly there were three bright dots rushing across the sky, two of them flew together and the last one a bit on its own, it joined the other two before they disappeared into the horizon. I have seen many shooting stars and this was definitely not one of these, the dots of light were clear but gave off a slightly fuzzy light and they did not trail behind them. They moved very quickly and were gone after approx. five seconds. Well... the hairs on the back of my neck haven't really settled down yet, because it's not every day you see something like this, but I actually felt like I was in the middle of the movie "Close Encounter of the 3rd Degree", and the objects actually moved a little likewise, rapid but distinct course changes.

I followed what I believe was a satellite - from west to east. Just before it passed the moon, there was something that looked like a small crooked/curved shooting star close to the satellite - it lasted approx. 1-2 seconds, then it disappeared and there was nothing more to see - the satellite disappeared on the horizon in the east. Have often seen shooting stars, but never anything like this, and I don't think it was a plane/helicopter. Could be my eyes playing tricks on me - but I followed it and focused on it, so I don't think so either. Hope others have followed the satellite and seen the same thing.
Observed bird-like object in sky showing extreme abnormality.

My sister, brother-in-law and I were having Easter lunch when I spotted a luminous object in the sky around midnight. I picked up my camera and started filming and filmed a total of over 18 min on 2 films. First briefly handheld and then after approx. 17½ min. On a stand. Several strange things happened while it is on a tripod and filming ... We see, among other things, a shooting star, and my dog starts behaving strangely, and the neighbor's horses make noise, and my camera starts filming mysteriously at some point .. So there are many things that make me think I have filmed something special ufo halloy...
We wanted to look at comets on Thursday night and suddenly I see a green web, which looked like some kind of luminous green web (rionet-like) flew by, or into the neighbor's tree, and was gone again.

I woke up last night to an incredibly loud sound, that sound, like a machine that tramples the earth, just louder. I thought maybe someone had stolen such a huge machine and was driving around right down the front, so I got up to have a look before I wanted to call the police, because it was very loud! When I looked out the window there was a large triangular flying thing with white lights across its belly. I'm not sure how many, but maybe 6-7 pieces from tail to tip and red lights from wing to wing.. When I was standing and trying to get my phone to work, the plane turned then the tip came slowly towards me. I got so scared that I jumped back into bed and lay there waiting and listening. Then the sound disappeared just like that, then it was gone. I didn't dare look out of the window and didn't dare sleep until it got light. I'm still very afraid of it coming back. I really need to hear if anyone else has seen or heard the same thing. As I said, I'm still very scared and would very much like to hear what it was and if it was really a UFO or what to calm down..
Large plane-like object. Very slowly and gliding across Sejerø Bay.

Cylindrical shape with 2 wings. Part below soaring, metallic-colored with shadow gray wings that sit at the top and bottom of the cylinder. So opposite to plane. It has a 'belt' around the center which is dark grey/black. The cylinder is very clear, it is metallic bright, not chrome plated. It moves silently a little to the right and also to the left - approx. 20 meters each time. Then it takes a trip away from me, approx. 50 meters to return. Here it "dances" a little back and forth with approx. 5 meters away. There is no light or sound... Nothing. It actually looks like an airplane when viewed from above. However, there is no rear end. The most amazing sight my son and I have seen. There were virtually no clouds and it was almost over our heads. Approx. 50 meters from above our head. I would assume the cylinder was 6-7 meters long with a "ribbon" around it. The wings went approx. 2 meters up from the cylinder, and 2 meters down below. The most amazing thing was when it flew away from us, it was like it just "disappeared" in front of us!!! Silently again...

Was walking out in my garden and looked up when I saw a dark shadow coming towards me. I called to my daughter who was just reaching out as it passed. It wasn't very big. It was triangular, black with 5 white lights below that followed its shape. No sound came from it. It quickly hovered over us and was gone as quickly as it came.

Last year, the cows came out on the access road to the new Frederiksund motorway, when I suddenly got this sight of the night sky. I haven't really thought more about it, but took 2 photos which I have sent to Ole Henningsen. Hope you can use this.

4 of us stood on a balcony (to smoke) and looked in a western direction. The weather is drizzling light rain with cloud cover. Unfortunately, I do not know of exact observations, but the cloud cover was quite low. The weather was dark, but the lights of the city could be seen on the low clouds. I see an object sliding from the right through the air. The distance to the object is difficult to judge, perhaps 500-750 meters. It is completely round, and has a diameter in the sky of approx. 4-5 millimeters. It glides at a constant speed (about 250 km/h, estimated) and the entire object glows with a constant orange-yellow light. I immediately alert the other three to the object. We talk about what it is - one thinks it is a satellite, but it is several times larger than the satellites you usually see. Furthermore, we will later talk about the object flying under cloud cover, and thus it is not a satellite. The object is at no time in contact with the clouds, and is clearly visible until it disappears behind rooftops. At first glance, it would be reasonable to write the object off as being a large balloon of some sort, but it was very brightly luminous. It's hard to say what it could be.

We were 5 people who observed something inexplicable in the sky. Tried to take pictures with the mobiles in the dark, but just turned into little dots. There came approx. 20 (not counted) silent objects flying slowly to the south, they were within the atmosphere, actually not that high up. - We do not know about your degree system, so we cannot specify that. They flew over Bagsværd Sø, came from the Furesø area (north) and flew slowly south. We were at the end of Søvej, Bagsværd. At first we thought it must be someone who had sent up a lot of balloons, but they flew much faster. They formed formations and stood still in between and flew on to eventually get smaller and disappear (to the south). The objects were bright orange-red - partly round. Can draw the shape, but your report can't... A bit like a jellyfish shape - flat on the sides, but round in the middle. They were very luminous, floating, floating, calm, all facing the same direction. They did not change direction at any time, other than the front ones formed - in a fluid movement a kind of formation that could look like a constellation. We called 118 twice to get the phone number for SUFOI, but they gave the wrong number both times. So the embedding only takes 45 minutes. later. Can you tell us if you know of a natural explanation, perhaps from other people's observations, we would very, very much like an explanation, please send an e-mail or call the contact information provided.

properties.Colors: Sort med 3 blinkende hvide lys i venstreside og 3 røde lys i højre side
properties.content: My husband and I are driving from Allerød along the king road when we see something hanging in the air and alternately flashing 3 white lights on the left side and 3 red lights on the highest side, while it remains still in the air. As we get closer, it begins to fly towards Allerød over Høvelte. Suddenly a flying one comes and hovers in the air above McDonald's. We drive into the tank opposite to see what is hanging in the air. After approx. 1 min. it starts flying in the same direction as the first one. They were approx. 200 - 300 meters up in the air.

Sitting and drinking coffee with my friends, who live on the 4th floor and have a good view over the horizon to the north, when I see to the right of the Holy Cross Church sprouting 4 strong red lights in formation flying at a good speed to the south. Then there will be 3 more with approx. 1 km distance between each other flew the same way and then disappear to the south.

On Saturday 18-9-2016 we went on a family trip to Zoo Copenhagen, and we saw the little new baby giraffe. We took 4 selfie photos approx. next to the camels seen in an east direction with Frederiksberg castle in the background and with the Zoo tower on the right in the selfie pictures. In the first picture, a purple square "UFO" can be seen. A little behind you can see a small "ufo" more, but hard to see from the poor selfie image quality. Is there exhaust gas? to the west of "ufo". In selfie picture 2 is exhaust gas? almost obliterated, but can be seen. In the last pictures, there is quite a bit to the left of the "ufo". In all 4 pictures, the "ufo" hangs at the same height, slightly above the height of the Frederiksberg castle flag. "Ufo" has approx. same size as the flag at the Castle. The 4 photos were taken during approx. 10 sec. We did not hear any "UFO" sounds. But there was a really good atmosphere from the many happy people who were in the Zoo and saw all the animals. Don't know if there were some of them who also noticed the "ufo".

My daughter and I were on our way home from a confirmation preparation in Dyrup Church at 9 pm. When we walked on the path home, (located in an open field), we had a beautiful view of the total clear starry sky. We could see 360 degrees around with a clear view of the sky. We went and looked at stars and airplanes, which we talked about a bit. There were lots of flashing lights, red and white. They were airplanes, we were aware of that. But then an object appeared almost sailing across the sky. It looked very strange, a bit like an airplane flying high. Maybe it was just turning in its orbit, but I've never seen an airplane this close before at this point. There was a red flashing light at the top, and a good distance below was a white one, and in between, there was also something flashing. Then there was a white light running across what I assume was the "belly" of the object. If it was an airplane turning, then it could be a red light on one wing tip and a light in the middle and a white light on the other wing tip and then a white light running across the "belly" itself. It just seemed like there was no tail on. Here I am thinking of an airplane. It took a long time before it was out of sight. We stood still and looked for it, then walked a little and stopped and looked again, it was still in sight. Very slowly it disappeared to the west. There were no sounds to be heard. From the time we saw it until it was out of sight, it was still flying "high".

Went out on the terrace when Matador was just starting to get some fresh air when I observed a bright orange light in the sky. The object came approx. from VNV in the direction of Copenhagen. As the flight routes go directly over Birkerød, I immediately thought that there was a fire in a scheduled plane on its way to the airport, but when a few seconds later another object appeared in the same direction, I concluded that it was possibly some balloons with this light, as there was no sound that the planes emit. As the objects moved at great speed and furthermore (approx. above Farum) made a turn of approx. 90 degrees and with great speed disappeared into the horizon in the SSW direction, it must have been another kind of flying object. - Today I investigated more closely what it could be, and my conclusion, based on pictures and reports from the internet, must be the same as what others have experienced under the term UFO. Since I can't find any other reports, which makes me wonder, I'm posting mine for your convenience.

There were 7 missile-like things flying over a school, I stood looking out the window and when I saw them I thought there must be deafening huge noises with all the machines, nothing came. Only after a while I thought that airplanes make noise and that this actually had nothing to do with airplanes, there were no windows, it looked like missiles. I've asked everyone in the area if they've noticed anything, but no one I've spoken to has seen anything. I talk to a friend and say that I think I'm a little crazy in the head and tell about my experience, where he says that one of his friends has seen 3 orange-red things in the same town at evening time. 2 of them suddenly disappear but come back and he has tried to record it on his mobile, however I don't know if anything came out of the recording.

When I was about to drive home from my parents, I stood and looked up at the night sky, but couldn't see anything. When I went around to the other side of the house, I looked a bit again, while I waited for my mother the car drove off. Here I saw a very bright white light in a westerly direction, which dimmed just as quietly, and after 10-20 seconds it was completely "extinguished" and did not come on again.

Drove on the extension of the Hillerød motorway in the direction of kbh. Around Allerød, I see a flying "disc" at an altitude of 800-1000 meters about 5 km ahead in an easterly direction, (to the left of the southern driving direction) with a direction to the north-east. I first assume it's an airplane and the shape is an optical illusion due to the angle, but since the object continues at "airplane speed" (the speed doesn't seem particularly high or low compared to an airplane), the shape remains the same. Sharp at the edges, with a smooth transition to a thicker hull in the middle. The object has no blinkers or lights, which is why I rule it out as a plane, and the object disappears behind a cloud formation.

I walked the dog in the garden approx. at 21.55 and walked around the garden a bit. Then I went around to the other side of the house. It is located so that you look towards Svendborg, but it is 7 km. to Svendborg. I look up at the sky and see some mysterious fast oblong faint white lights in the sky. The first thing I see looks like a powerful shooting star behind some haze, but plus there are 4-5 pieces coming from different directions, all happening within 50 to 100m in the sky. But I can see stars and planes at the same time as the observation. I call my wife who is inside the house and tell her to look in the sky to see if she can see the same thing as me and she could but she only sees one of the lights for approx. 5 seconds, and then it's all over and we don't see the lights anymore.

Observed a triangle shaped red light with no bottom with a strong red light at the tip (top of triangle). Stood still for approx. 5-10 min. At times there were several red powerful lights, swapping places.

I currently live with my parents in Brabrand, as I am working on my graduation project at the School of Architecture in Aarhus. I had an important deadline this morning, so I've been up all night at the computer. At about. 01-01.30 time I clearly see 4 red balls moving quickly across the sky. I sit and observe them for a while when out of the blue two of them disappear! I ran out to film them, but immediately you can't see them on film. I stood for almost 1 minute on the terrace and watched the last two disappear over Lake Brabrandsøen and into the horizon. At first glance I thought they were flares, but they moved horizontally and very quickly in formation until two of them disappeared. It was a steady red light that didn't blink. They didn't fly very high and didn't make a sound - I'm curious if you guys got any other calls since they were visible for almost 2 minutes?
Then last night, what could possibly be described as an asteroid burned up in the atmosphere.

Saturday late evening, I saw something very strange, maybe a UFO?. I saw three lights (they were round, like they came from a lamp on the ground), it came from above. But before that, I saw a bright light across the grass, at first I thought it was from a car, but soon after I saw these three lights at the same time. Wondering about this. I talked a little later with an acquaintance about this. Then it happened again, but this time it was a bright light that lit up the room, and a little later there were three little looks (these could be from a car). but the others came up from above. Wondering if it was a UFO visiting. This experience happened on Vantorevej in Nysted by the paddock where horses walk.

I have an experience I would like to share. Last night I was on a drive with my autistic son, I was out to find some plants for the garden. I shop at private shops that have stalls along the road, and I shopped at a shop a bit out of the way. My car sat idle while I found what I wanted and put it in the car. It was really nice to shop, even though it was raining and the sky was completely gray covered with clouds as far as you could see, - it still smells like spring. When I finished, I sat in the car, which was idling - and drove. I drive maybe 15-20 metres, then the car stalls, the windscreen wipers and radio stop, and the car is totally dead. Something I would hate to be stranded in No Where with my autistic son on a Sunday night. I try to revive the car but it is dead.. I turn on the ignition and try to start the radio to calm my son. It doesn't work, I try the wipers - doesn't work. Maybe - eight, five minutes in all - the car is dead and it's getting dark. Suddenly the wipers and radio start again - there is a light on the car and it starts as if nothing had happened. Confused but happy, I turn the car around and drive down the road, at the crossroads I casually look at the sky, which is gray all over - no clarification anywhere. There I see a pink splash in the grey, to the south - at an angle of between 70 and 90 degrees. I take my phone and get it ready to film, but I have to move the car away from the intersection where I stopped.. I drive a few 100 m and want to take a photo - but the pink stain is gone, and everything was gray in gray again.

I am an amateur astronomer and saw the first object coming from the SW and it had a color like the flame of a fire. It billowed in a way that could have been heat haze. I expected to hear a sound, because it came rushing towards me. The object passed in front of me at a height of 70-80 degrees and immediately after disappeared behind ridges for approx. 45 degree elevation in NE direction. At At 19.05 another one came at the same speed, but more "fixed" in form. There was surprisingly no sound. I got a picture of number two.

I don't believe in a rice paper lamp - then it would have to be lit with a full-grown oak tree to light so much - and the high speed is also not connected with the fact that it is completely windless outside? My husband also got a glimpse of it when it was closest, and confirms that the ones in the video in the link are similar to the one we saw - both in terms of size, light/clarity, color and movement, "ours" though with a little higher speed, but not much higher.
Tags: ufo Title: yellow light

I'm out with my dog, and since it's very starry, I go and look up at the stars. I can then see that a plane is coming from the south. I have no doubt that it is a plane as it flashes white light. Looks like it's approaching a group of stars, and as the plane is on the outer edge of the stars, there's a quick flash from the other side of the control group. It only lasted for 1-2 sec. Then it was gone again. It looks like it's at the same altitude as the plane, which I estimate to be flying at 10,000m.
Round ball of light which disappears to the north at a very high speed. No streaks of condensation, no sound. Am a plane freak - but have never seen that speed.

This evening I spotted approx. 7 balls of light float in the direction from Sweden towards Amager. More lights popped up continuously, but then it became cloudy. At first they seemed to be followed across the sky, but some lights "ran away" from the others. They made no sound. They were fairly far out on the horizon and the lights seemed small, so my guess is that they were a few km above the surface of the earth without being able to say it more precisely. The lights were steady - not flashing - and were white/slightly yellowish.
