They did not seem to be constant in their movements, as they could move a little "confused" around the sky, and against the direction of the clouds. I have recorded a video that I would like to send you where you can see them. It was recorded on a camera phone, so the quality is accordingly.

We were watching the fireworks when Søren pointed out that he had seen something. I directed my gaze there and saw a white spot, and after about 10 minutes of observation, it halved its light emission and flew in a small circle, followed by a kind of cross (a circle and a cross of about 2 cm diameter in front of the naked eye) . We decided this needed more investigation and so picked up binoculars. Since Søren uses glasses, it was me who initially used the binoculars. He engaged my observations later. When looking at the spot through binoculars, it had grown to twice its size (which should rule out a star, and this was not due to increased radiance). It was very strange, so we decided to go in because we might be shaking our hands. Approximately 4 minutes pass from the time we entered until we resume the observations. By this time it had almost halved its radiance by 75%, (we concluded it was not due to the clouds as it was perfectly starry.) During its faint radiance it resumed its movements. We continued to observe it for about 50 minutes during which it did its fade and movement number. Several times, when it completely dimmed its radiance, through the binoculars you could quite clearly see 3 lights below it and a round underside. The velocity was estimated to be approximately three times the velocity of the stationary stars. It couldn't be space debris as this wouldn't be moving back and forth, this shouldn't be a satellite either as this shouldn't be moving either. We can only conclude that it is an object which is trying to masquerade as a star, but still cannot do so. The observation was made in a completely sober state, by Ole O. and Søren RF, as well as Ole's parents and a few guests. (the guests were not sober though) With a little good will, the object bears some resemblance to the objects that were observed in the Netherlands (the triangular ones with three lights, can't remember when it was) However, this one is just a bit further away. It is now 01:40 and we continue our observations.

In connection with the fireball on 02.04.05, I saw it from our living room window, which faces east, I go out into the garden and stand outside for any to look for smoke trails from the fireball, and listen for any sound. Since I have been out in the garden for approx. 8-9 min., 5 bright dots appear in the sky directly above my head. They come in a south-west direction and fly north-east, the 4 in a straight line with the same mutual distance, the 5 in the same direction, approx. between no. 2 and 3 and on the left side of the row with the 4. The break-in distance between 1 - 4 was the same and no. 5 approx. at double distance out to the left. I have seen many satellites and planes, we live on the approach route to Billund. They came as 5 satellites at a fairly high speed and disappeared as satellites usually do, they got fainter and fainter. There was no sound. I stood out there for approx. 10 more minutes. Since I wear glasses I looked up and saw them and thought what the heck is that. I look away and look up again and they were still there, also no visible flashes like from airplanes. If my eyes are not deceiving me, they immediately looked to be very high up, birds do not usually fly with such a precise distance between themselves. The color was faint white/yellow like sunlight on satellites.

An object moved rapidly and at constant speed across the sky in a straight line and suddenly disappeared without changing direction. It emitted a constant, white light and gave one observer the impression of a triangular shape, while the other perceived it as oval. We heard no sound. One of us noted the time immediately. Independently of each other, we got the impression that our observations did not agree with phenomena we have previously observed - even though we frequently see planes, helicopters and celestial bodies in the same area.

Gliding object seen with the eye the size of a small sun or moon, delicate yellow with a little haze around. Observed on a farm with no lampposts only full moon to the south. Glide along the horizon and first glided from East to West, but suddenly changed direction and went down behind the forest to the North.

I got the drivers out of a small town (Kr. Sonnerup), where I first see a reddish object in the sky NW direction approx. 30 degrees above the horizon, which I thought was an emergency rocket from a boat in distress on the ice fjord. In addition, two reddish objects appeared. They form a 1/4 of a circle. At this point I turn north on highway 53 which goes to Fredriksund and can see them start to take a different course, but am disturbed by a small forest (beach forest) first. when I have come 2/3 of the way through the forest, I can see that they have changed direction and are now above another forest (ryes forest) N-E direction approx. 25/30 degrees above the horizon. I am now completely free of the forest and can see that now there are only two left, and they are on their way out across the Isefjord again. They now begin to turn on and off alternately and at the same time move vertically and move north. I then follow them all the way to Ejby, where my son is with some friends, where I pick him up. When he comes out to the car I show him them. And we drive out where we can have a clear view. We follow them as long as they are in heaven. They then disappear in a northerly direction. I will use my son's expression for this experience: SOUR!!!!!!
We tried to record it, but my friend pressed the wrong button on his digital camera, so we didn't get anything. There was a completely clear sky and no clouds.

There was something about the fact that there was a night when there would be many shooting stars, and a friend and I would lie out on a garage roof to watch it. Suddenly up among the stars there was a light (which looked like the other stars) which moved. The funny thing here is not that it just moved, it also moved among the stars! What I have pondered most, when I have thought back, was/is that this light must have had an absolutely extreme speed - when the movement was so clear and so far out there among the stars... I just wanted to write, when I just saw the broadcast on DR2 and thought of it.

Around 8:15 p.m., my girlfriend and I saw a strange light in the sky. An orange colored object, located to the southwest, moved to the west, first thought was: A flare, but since I'm a sailor, I think I know how a flare behaves in the sky, and this was definitely not a flare, since it was moving horizontally. I have recorded it on video camera, and would like to hear from people who have seen the same thing as me. The object started out as very orange, and slightly larger than a normal. star, whereupon it flared up, and even changed color to green, for short periods, and later to a clear color, and with a the object stopped and held its position to the southwest, whereupon it slowly faded away, yet flared up again a a few times until it slowly disappeared. I have asked on tv2.dk about the same thing, and some believe that it could be Venus, I don't think that fits, since the object was moving far too fast to be Venus.

Was looking at shooting stars... Then a boomerang like. pale white object is spotted just above us. I am the first to observe, because it must be my friend's friend... It flies a kind of reconnaissance route.. At very low speed, and makes a u-turn at the end and is suddenly gone.. 3rd person does not manage to observe it. Have googled it and found a couple of pictures which show exactly the same object that has been observed in different places in the world.. Others who have seen something similar. at the same point in time?

Drove my son home by car. Spotted a cone of light approx. 500 m away from my car approx. up to a little over 1000 m high. Could only see the light. Also saw 2 bright spots on 28/3-12 above my home at Eskebækparken, approx. somewhere between 2-3 km. above the E45 motorway at Skanderborg.

At 23.55 I go out my door to smoke a cigarette and look at the evening sky. Looking north and seeing a very distinct red star. Had to rub my eyes. The object came closer and, in my estimation, at that time was around Sengeløse village. I went out into the backyard and at approx. 90 seconds the object had dropped horizontally from 60 to 20 degrees from my point of observation. It slowed down and hovered over a neighboring house approx. 15 meters away. I could hear a sound from the object which I identified as a low hum. I flashed my lighter to signal and it came approx. 5 meters closer. Then it stopped and the sound disappeared. From approx. 20 meters high, the object stood still above me for approx. 60 seconds and then disappeared back to the north. When the vessel had come some distance, it began to flash white and blue lights. Reminiscent a lot of ordinary signal lights from airplanes. It then disappeared above the tree line, but I could see the lights through the woods. I estimate the object to be approx. 120x80. The sound of the craft died away as it stood still. It is probably drone activity, but I find the lack of sound suspicious. Hence this observation.

We were standing outside my house at 00.15, when my girlfriend suddenly sees 2 yellow/orange balls in the sky. They move quietly to the east - same direction, same speed - one following the other. We see them disappear - stand for a while and talk, and then bullet No. 3 arrives. It has the same direction and speed. All three are completely silent.

My girlfriend draws my attention to an airplane-like object that moves somewhat faster and more clinically across the sky than normal aircraft in the area. This object also has neither green nor red flashes on it. It just looks like a star moving quickly across the sky. After moving from east to west for about 15 seconds, the object suddenly begins to fade in strength, but not as if it was moving south, but as if it was moving directly away from us. It went from being as prominent in the night sky as a normally bright star, to being completely gone in 15 seconds. At no point did it gain or lose speed. Likewise, the light was absolutely constant until the graduation began.

We were four people who saw, first a ball of light closely followed by another ball. A total of six balls came. They flew low and fast. Suddenly they ascended in a great arc and disappeared. The last and 6th bullet flew a little lower and more erratically, but it took the same course and disappeared. It all happened completely silently and faster than an airplane. It probably took a few minutes in total. They came from east to west - right along the coastline. The balls were yellow.

I was out in my garden with three friends when we suddenly see an oval, silver-white, almost rocket-shaped object in the sky. Since we live in a small town, we can see the thing for a relatively long time. We saw a similar thing about ten minutes before, but thought nothing more of it. They flew at medium speed across the sky. They both fly from northeast to west.

I was lying in my bed and looked out the window, but the curtain was drawn almost all the way down. All of a sudden I see a very bright white light and a quiet hum that suddenly turns into a smaller hiss and it was gone. It wasn't a car, because I could see the light, it floated over the house and I could see. My dog usually barks when a car comes on the road, he didn't. I'm 100% sure it wasn't a car. Has anyone seen or heard anything.

On 11/08-2012 I am sitting outside in Skanderborg, during the Skanderborg festival, together with a friend and talking, when I look up at the sky and observe 3 luminous objects, similar to stars. (However, there were no stars in the sky this evening). These 3 luminous objects were positioned as a triangle in the sky. While I sit and look up, they start to move around in a strange circular way, where shortly after they gather again in less than 1 second. My friend looks up, and I point and explain, after which they disappear, like the lamps being turned off. It should be said that I hadn't been drinking this evening, as I work during the festival and had to be on duty at 00.00. The reason I'm writing to you is, of course, that I'm wondering, and especially because it wasn't long ago that I had seen "paranormal investigators - hoax or fact" on TV3, where they showed footage and pictures of 3 luminous objects in the sky, also positioned as a triangle, exactly the same as those I saw. However, these observations had been discovered in the United States. I'm hoping to find an answer from you, or possibly that you might have some pictures lying around of something similar? Unfortunately, I didn't manage to take a photo of these 3 glowing objects myself, as I was so shocked that I couldn't concentrate on anything other than looking at them, which I regret now. It's not the first time I see inexplicable things in the sky, it must be said, the last time I saw something it was more clear, a flying object in the sky, shaped like a saucer, where the center was dark and the outside was bright, it happened on Oddervej between Malling and Odder last year, and I have 2 witnesses to this.

Came driving along Langgade, sees light and a cone of light down towards the ground. I think it's a helicopter, pulls into my driveway, then runs up to the road to look, but then it's gone. No light or noise, so it can't be a helicopter. Goes and thinks about it for a bit, and suddenly it hits me, it's a UFO after all.....!!

Wednesday morning. I drive towards Kværkeby and see a spherical object to the north. It hangs in the sky. I drop the boy off at kindergarten and tell him about my story. A padagog comes along and takes a look. We observe for 3 min. It doesn't move. It is clear. I drive towards Roskilde and drive over Hvalsø/Lejre. I almost get under the object

The night between Thursday and Friday is completely quiet, as it really can be in the countryside. I am alone in the room in the NW gable and my wife in the room in the SW. It is warm and has the window open. I wake up to a deafening noise, and I look out of the window (you're curious, after all!), and only see an object coming in from the NE, but immediately only see the lights red and white in fixed patterns and then the noise! I'm pretty sure it's a helicopter. I guess it is on the other side of the "City Hill", approx. 200-30 0m from me. I hear my wife get up and go to the bathroom and I wonder if I should say something to her! She will usually reply that: You can read about that in the newspaper tomorrow, so I'll leave it at that. I am convinced that there is someone who is sick and needs to go to the hospital quickly. The helicopter lands, the rotors stop and eventually the engine stops too. It's quiet again, but I can clearly hear people talking! I sat and watched the whole thing (even though I could see nothing) and was sure I could get the report later from him who lives in No. 3. He otherwise never lets the chance pass when there is an opportunity. Great was my astonishment when he had heard nothing. He was much closer, but gets up early (04.50). I don't know if that might have had a meaning. Him and the resident in 8A have examined the grass fields for marks, but have found nothing. They can of course have landed on the paved road! No one, apart from me, has observed anything close to my good friend in No. 1. He has heard a lot of noise though. The end of it all is that the helicopter only starts the engine again at approx. 03.50 - then I hear the rotors start, it takes off and flies to the NW, and disappears. I can once again clearly see its light in steady rhythm. We are used to being "overflown" every now and then. our location, but not that anyone is landing! I assume that there is a natural explanation, i.a. is there a new helicopter landing pad out on Stevns, probably in connection with the offshore wind turbine project. Have always shown that I would report if I could not find an explanation. You are 100% sure of the time of observation.

Driving in a car from west to east in the countryside outside the city. There was a large gap in the cloud cover and an object was crossing at very high speed. Will shoot at 2-3 times faster than fighters. Relatively low altitude, just above cloud cover (or very large and slightly higher). Much larger and slower than shooting stars, very bright and large object. Approx. twice the size of low-flying fighters. Powerfully luminous in green/uv/blue shade. Mostly greenish.

Driving in a car and suddenly see a large plane with 4 vertical propellers like a drone. It flies very low above the trees. Much larger than a normal helicopter. I wonder what type of plane it is, as I can't find pictures anywhere on the web that look similar. Maybe you can help?

7 lights floated on the horizon in a random pattern. Watching them hang around for approx. 15 sec., after which they disappear. Approx. 1 minute later they come again. See them again in approx. 15 sec., after which they disappear as if someone turned off the light. Stands and waits for 20 minutes where nothing happens.

On Saturday evening I recorded some unusual orange-red orb-like phenomenon gliding across the sky - without sound. It caught my curiosity and so I stood and looked in the direction of discovery, it was rapidly approaching, a similar object appeared, followed the same trajectory. I followed it to the other side of the house, found my Iphone 5S, photographed with it. There came 3 maybe 4 of the same kind. They followed the same trajectory. I haven't seen anything unusual in the night sky since! Keep thinking about what it was!

My younger sister and I were lying in my room and needed to go to rest. We lay talking about what the day had in store, and I lie looking out of my window, which is opposite my bed. Suddenly I see a "Star" about 3 times larger than Venus (the evening star) coming flying from the west. It doesn't blink, it doesn't make any sound. It moves quietly across the night sky, and in between it made some strange zigzag movements. It continued to the east behind the trees so we ran outside to keep looking at the object. It slowly disappeared into the horizon with its strange zigzag movements. But before it disappeared, as we stood outside looking at the object, we saw a light near it. A kind of "star", which once flashed incredibly strongly and almost lit up the surroundings for less than a second. It all happened very quickly, but one thing we are sure of is that it was at least a rare experience and that it was definitely not an airplane.

Description of pictures and video films. I aim towards the UFO, in the pictures it looks like I hit it. It was a shame I didn't have the opportunity to focus. But it was good that the format stood for Nikon's highest format NEF. The time/date stamping on these 3 files matches and there have been no edits in these files. At the beginning of the film there are two UFOs, further on in the film you see a UFO moving at a high speed and making a dive. Note that there is no sound from the UFO, the clicking sounds you can hear are when zooming in/out.

I came riding a moped on my way home from work in Assens. Then I see a large orange glowing UFO rising above some treetops. I stop the moped because I can see that if I continue I will get right under it,,which I didn't want to. So I stay between 50-100m away and observe the phenomenon. It flies quite slowly across the road without a sound, and with nothing to see but the orange light. The object was quite large, filling both the road and over the treetops. When it had flown away, I restarted the moped and drove forward to watch it as it flew on. But there was nothing to see, it was gone. I know this is an old observation, but it still bothers me a lot. As fate would have it, we bought the very property, here before Christmas, over whose lands it disappeared, so now I am looking very intensely for more, especially since I know there have been several sightings in the area.

My mother alerted me to two large red glowing balls in the sky... They floated slowly and far out past our dining room windows.... We then went out on the balcony and looked at them... They then hung quietly a little time before they disappeared behind some trees, where we could no longer see them, and they never came back again.

I detected the object by the brownish light, and then we watched it come flying slowly and without sound just below the thin clouds which were in the sky last night. The light disappeared after we had looked at the "thing" for a minute and then we could see no more light, only a large circular brownish/rusty red thing! It disappeared quietly into the horizon in a straight line to the north-northwest.
Three glowing orbs come flying across the sky. Looks confusingly like rockets. It takes place completely silently. Observed through a window in one's own home.

At 23:30 we went to the garden to smoke when we saw 3 bright lights flying at great speed from the northeast direction to the southwest. As the first light is about to disappear, 3 more come. There will be at least 10 lights in total. There was no sound, no flashing, and they flew far too fast to be balloons. The observation lasted at least 6 min.

On an evening walk I suddenly see 6-7 brightly lit objects moving slowly across the sky. I am standing on a relatively dark road and see them clearly in a clear sky. They are completely red. They do not blink and move at exactly the same pace across the sky. The four front objects form a square. After the front four, there are only a few more objects. But more will follow. In total, I would think that 15 identical, bright red objects pass in a long line with relatively large gaps. They came in approx. from the south-west, and I would think that they were above Bagsværd/Buddinge. They almost described a circle, as if they were flying around Copenhagen. I guess they were a few kilometers up. Out here in Virum/Sorgenfri, we are used to seeing planes on approach to Copenhagen airport. These objects have nothing in common with the usual air traffic, nor was there any indication that they were going to land. Since it is a fairly quiet evening, I am very sure that there was no sound from the objects. I can only imagine that others must have seen the same sight. And there is probably a reasonable explanation for that. But since I've never seen anything like it, I'm curious and would like to tell you about it too. Interesting what it was!

I can see on your website that a person has observed 2 objects that flew over the sky near Næstved on 2 October approx. At 21. I can confirm having seen the same thing. It was 2 white objects which from 20.45 and for more than 1 hour flew at very high speed horizontally across the sky, almost as if they were chasing each other, sometimes there was only one object. They appeared every 1-2 minutes and disappeared, then returned. I live approx. 5 km north of Næstved, and it was in a western direction that they could be seen. It wasn't planets, planes, helicopters or the like, there was absolutely no noise to be heard. The first light I saw I thought was a comet flying in a north-south direction west of where I was, but soon after the object flew the opposite way. The weather was relatively clear with scattered clouds. I have no reasonable explanation for what it was I saw.

My wife and I were getting into the car when I noticed a bright light in the sky in the direction of Gentofte. It moved rather slowly across a patch of cloudless sky until it was about due east of us, where it seemed to disappear into the clouds. The light seemed larger than an airplane searchlight, but not blinding, and appeared a steady red-yellow/orange without pulsating. Since there was nothing else to compare in the sky (no stars were visible) and I do not know the height of the cloud cover, it is difficult to give an exact size. At first glance, it didn't seem like there was a solid object behind the light. The weather was cloudy, but visibility was otherwise good. We judge the gap in cloud cover to go from northern Gentofte/Jægersborg to a bit south of Hellerup.

The time was approx. 20.30, still light outside, and we had just been up by my horse on Potterhusvej. We were on our way home and took the regular route via Gammel Tinglevvej, which is just outside Ensted Kirke. We walked next to each other and observed the lovely nature in the area. Suddenly something catches our eye in the sky. Two "white" objects float lightly but quickly in the blue sky. I explained to my mother that it looked like the same strange objects that I had seen earlier in the same area on June 26, 2016, which I had also videotaped and shown her. The objects were white, they flew in "flocks". There was no noise at all! They had no "smoke tail" behind them, as a normal motor plane would have. They were up at jet height, so they couldn't possibly be gliders. It looked neither like a motor plane nor a glider. It looked like they had short round wings. It also looked like there were windows in them, but this is not certain. We walked further down the road and came across one of my father's friends who was out mowing grass at the time. The strange flying objects were still in the sky at this time. We asked him if he knew what it was. He looked carefully and could not answer our questions. One of the objects suddenly lit up. It was as clear and bright as a star in the night sky, even though it was bright in the sky. All three of us saw it and couldn't answer what it was we had just witnessed. The two objects suddenly disappeared. We continued home without being able to catch sight of them again. When we got home and looked out the windows, we could suddenly see them again. It was as if they had been following us. After this experience, we have noticed that our phones, nets and other electrical items have been buzzing/breaking and that our German Shepherd is breaking the windows even though there is nothing. Whether it's a strange coincidence or not, I don't know. But we go out one evening at the same time and place with a telescope and a really good camera, and then we hope to be able to capture better pictures and videos of "Them".

At At 09.35 a plane came over our house, sport plane, and I looked up. Above the sport plane was a large silver plate about the size of a small Fiat. It followed the pilot and pulled out along one wing and then the opposite, and then it left the pilot approx. 270 degrees with a speed like a cannonball, and after 5 seconds it was out on the horizon.

We are on our way home from my cousin's when we see an orange light very close to the ground. After a short time it is at the height of a tower with an airplane lamp (which warns airplanes to fly into it). After that, a short time passes before it continues to rise. The object rises very quickly and flies directly to the south, i.e. right for us. As the object is well on its way to the right, it stops and starts flying north, i.e. left from us. While the object is changing direction, it gains a lot of speed and flies away from the scene very quickly, shortly after it flew to the north/left. As it began to gain speed, it flew very quickly into the horizon and disappeared from view. We have talked about the possibility that it could be a Japanese lamp, but when the object picked up speed very quickly and disappeared shortly after into the horizon, we became doubtful. Do you have an explanation for this or is it a UFO? We would very much like an answer, as it interests us a lot.

They then fly in a southerly direction and probably turn "ass" towards me in a westerly course and disappear. You then see that more people come up above the house horizon approx. west-north-west across the houses at Amerikaj. Coming up here and being clear is to me a sign that they are either flying low or taking off in close proximity. There wasn't much that made it UFO-like in flight style or appearance: just lines of light from planes. But the direction these planes came from in a combined group of approx. 8 in something that looked like close moving on a random Saturday night, I think seemed special. It could easily be a plane, but then you know for sure.

Approx. at 19.45 I drove down to the Sheel tank in Galten. On the way back, I saw out of my window on the right a red light approx. 80 meters above the top of the forest far beyond several fields where there is a forest. I pulled into a parking space on the road and stood looking at the light. I saw several drivers drive by slowly, but they did not stop. I thought it was probably just a flare that someone had shot into the air because it just hung there completely still. But on second thought, it was too big to be an emergency flare. After I watched it for a few minutes, it started to move. First slowly to the right and then move to the first seen position and then slowly to the left. Then I got a little scared and started thinking about getting back into the car, but then it slowly descended into the forest, after which I hurried to get into the car to get home and tell 3 of my friends who were waiting me, but they did not believe my observation at all.
Several luminous dots around 6-7 pieces which moved synchronously in a kind of zigzag pattern in an upward direction and then disappeared. The light was not bright, but a little dim.

I woke up at 4:45 and looked out my bedroom window. I see a great bright star, I will call it. It stands still and does not move at all at any point, but again I wonder about the size and amount of light in the object. I have a feeling it's not a ufo-like thing, but maybe the earth is close to some planets or some other star nova hall eye I think. I take 3 pictures with my mobile. I zoom in on one picture with my mobile phone, and when I look at the picture afterwards, where you can enlarge it, I am quite surprised at how beautiful this phenomenon itself is, so I hope I can send in my pictures so you can judge for yourself them...
Powerful yellow ball came from the east with great speed and disappeared on the horizon in the west within 10 minutes at most. later. What could it have been?

Seven spots of light, shape, size and light like stars, but moving very quickly across the sky. Far faster than jet aircraft at medium to high altitude. In addition to the speed, the strange thing about the "star formation" was that all or several of the light spots changed places among themselves during the observation. Have often observed planes in the night sky, but they blink. These spots glowed continuously. Have also often seen a satellite, but it is only a spot of light at a much slower pace. So to us it was a UFO. I looked at the clock and saw that it was half past one. It's been a few days now. My wife and I believe it was half past one, the alternative is 28.06 at 11.30 p.m.

I am standing in the garden and suddenly 4 white powerful lights come rushing across the sky at a very high speed. In the first phase, there are 4 powerful lights in a square formation, but after approx. 5 seconds, the 4 lights are separated, to three times the distance, after which they begin to rotate around an axis at exactly the same distance from each other. The whole thing takes approx. 25 sec., after which it disappears from view. It was a very mysterious experience that gives food for thought.

Come driving along the road from the Skanderborg motorway exit west towards Ry. Approx. 500 meters before Dover Church I observe two oval lights in front of me approx. 45 degrees up in the sky. My first thought was that it must be light reflections from oncoming cars. But there was not immediately any fog or cloud mass on which such a light would be able to reflect. Suddenly they start asynchronously "dancing" with each other or playing some kind of "tick game" with each other. When I'm outside Dover Church, I think for fun that it's probably some of the dead playing a little. They continue and it seems that they are not that far away from me. I check if it should be reflections on my windshield, but it is not. Measured on my windshield, they are approx. 4 cm. on the long joint and 2 cm. on the short. They are not sharply demarcated, but look like when you make an oblique incidence of light from the side on fog, or on a cloud. It just doesn't seem like they are quite high up, maybe 100 - 200 meters. They continue to "follow me", where they occasionally disappear to the side, sometimes separately, sometimes together and quickly reenter in front of me until I reach the first roundabout in Ry. When I get home, I tell my wife about my experience, and it's no wonder that she looks at me a little "askew". After a few days we read about the phenomenon in the local newspaper and I decide to write to you. My explanation is that there may be reflections on some invisible water drops that hang low, but where should the "projectors" be ??? My son-in-law, who comes from Wales, says that exactly the same observations have been made several times there. (Swansea, Gower area).

In the middle of August, I stand in the evening and smoke a cigarette out of my window, and suddenly out of my left eye I can see that up in the sky some white balls of light come flying. They were somewhat further down than the stars and had a distinct clear white light. They first flew straight ahead, then made a 90 degree turn and then straight again. It all lasted about 6-9 seconds and there were between 8-12 white balls of light. The following evening I look up at the sky a lot, and to my great surprise I see a small explosion of white light. Again, it is further down than the stars. It is difficult to describe, but the light was coherent and for a millisecond the explosion becomes almost oblong, after which it flattens out into something round and disappears. The size of the explosion was about the size of a hazelnut. I absolutely have expectations that you will investigate it further with my sparse information, I just have to say it. I find it difficult to say the exact day, but I think it happened around 10 - 12 September, but whether it was Monday and Tuesday or Tuesday and Wednesday, I simply don't remember, and I'm still a bit unsure if, it was the following week.

I was on my way home in my car, north along Frederikssundsvej. When I reached the last roundabout on the way out of Ølstykke, approx. at 22, I saw a small flyer as they usually look, red/green markings, bright white light in the middle, and a strobolight somewhere behind. Nothing unusual there, apart from flying for approx. 200 meters high. It appeared in the north and flew south-southeast. When it was roughly directly off my left side, it abruptly changed direction and flew the exact opposite direction (north-northwest), with no banks and speed changes. When it was over Frederikssundsvej, approx. 100 meters in front of me, 100 meters up, it adjusted to my speed of 85 km/h. There it followed me for 1.6 km. without deviating from his position in relation to my car. During the 1.6 km. blinded it down to the white light in the middle and I could see that it had three closely spaced rectangular floodlights. When "we" got out of the last bit of forest at the 1.6 km from the roundabout, it slowed down abruptly as the center light went out and its marker light/strobe turned orange. Then slid a little to the left and stopped completely, inside a grassy area. In the meantime, I threw the car into the parking lot just before Svestrupvej, hurriedly turned off the engine and got out to have a look. Then it just hung above the ground, for approx. 50 meters high and 150 meters from me. It was completely quiet and there was also no wind/cars. Here I could see that its bottom surface was an equilateral triangle of approx. 5-6 meters per page. The three marker lights, which used to be red/green/strobe, now all glowed constantly orange in each corner of the triangle. It hung completely stationary, as if it had been mounted to a concrete anchor in the ground. After I had looked at it for 20 sec. then it slid south parallel to the road, still no sound, and while accelerating up to the speed of a normal small plane, the orange lights faded to red/green/strobe again and the center light came on. Still very low flying, but increased to approx. 2-300 meters before it turned off, in the direction of Roskilde, approx. down at the roundabout where the observation began. As I followed it the last distance, could see one more, flying a kilometer ahead of it, same direction, height and speed. And to my right, flying from north to south, one more... I just had to sit and recover from the incident before driving home. It was quite overwhelming and strange, but also extremely exciting as I am a technician and interested in flying. This object did not fit anywhere in my otherwise broad knowledge of technology and aircraft. It was a very great experience, and I have taken great care to describe it as precisely and in detail as I could.

My two children and I come driving home last night. In front of us - towards the harbor we suddenly see a series of powerful red lights in the sky. They sit as if on a strip that bends slightly to the right of us. My first thought is that they are lights on a tall crane or a wire or similar. But then think that it is impossible for a crane to stand that high in the harbour. Then we suddenly see that the lights slowly move further up. We stop the car and get out to hear and see better. There is no sound to be heard. One by one, the lights fade higher up and disappear. We start the car and drive on, but then see a single remaining light. We stop the car again and get out and observe that this light also slowly and silently fades further up and disappears. Once home, I look up my FB page to see if anyone has a natural explanation. A few mention possible drones? A friend who lives in the same area says that he has also seen the phenomenon when he was out walking his dog. Is there a good explanation?

We were 3 people who went for a walk in the heath in Skagen at 11pm on this cloudless July evening. We observed what we believed to be the planet Venus, shining brightly from its position, low above the horizon in a southern direction. After approx. 10 minutes we looked again in the direction of Venus and now saw a strong orange light, which shone with almost the same intensity as Venus - and was in a position approx. 10 degrees to the right of Venus and approx. 5 degrees lower on the horizon. We discussed whether it could be Mars that had come into view, because it gradually got darker and the stars became clearer. After approx. 5 minutes we observed that the orange light became smaller, glowed fainter and disappeared in the same position it was in - as if it flew away from us. After another 10 minutes we looked up at the sky again and now saw 2 orange lights which shone with the same intensity as Venus. They were in a position to the left of Venus and very close to the planet. The 2 lights began to circulate around each other for approx. 10 seconds, after which the No. 2 light split into another 2 lights and where it almost looked like it "lost" one half/light. After this, No. 2 light disappeared, as if it just turned off. No. 1 light slowly faded away as if flying away and getting smaller. The duration of this "light dance" and disappearance lasted approx. 30 seconds. We were very surprised by the sightings, as we have often seen emergency rockets on these edges, which do not resemble at all, and which behave completely differently from this phenomenon. And we are very curious to know if others in the area have also observed the phenomenon.

Was standing looking at the night sky and spotted the Chariot and then looked a little south and to the left of the Chariot, when suddenly there was a big white flash of light, and then it was completely dark where the star had been.

Thursday evening at approx. 20.15 my girlfriend and I sat on two deckchairs out in the garden, while our three children jumped on the trampoline. We sat and looked up at the many beautiful cloud formations, when we suddenly spotted two bright dots to the southeast. They look like stars and don't move, but the sun hasn't set yet and we can't really get it to fit. It looks more like something metallic that reflects the sun's rays. When I try to find my phone and want to take a picture, a lot of clouds come in ahead, and we wait for fifteen minutes for them to disappear.

I'm standing looking out onto the road from my terrace in a westerly direction when I turn my head slightly to the right and spot a gray robot vacuum cleaner like object hovering silently over the roof opposite and I've never seen anything like it turn around and trying to get in touch with my husband, who is sitting inside, but he doesn't want to come out. I can't say anything because I'm pretty shaken. I turn around and see it still there, but then disappears behind trees.

Observed a bright white light for 2 sec. in a west-southwest direction approx. 35-40 degrees above the horizon at 23.45 Danish summer time (B ?) This happened again at 0015. The flash of light was several times stronger than a star in the sky. I was actually only out to smoke and look for Saturn.

Saw a fireball moving pretty fast south. Called my husband, who managed to see it from the 1st floor of the house on the other side of the house, where it disappeared to the south behind some trees. Interesting - never seen that before.

A bright blue "ball" coming from the southeast, which suddenly turns into 4 smaller balls, of which 3 flew towards N - W and E. The 4th flew towards the earth. The incident took place over Funen, presumably southeast of Middelfart.

Triangular object, two bright white lights and one flashing red in what appears to be the front. The light was not like on airplanes (I see them all the time at the airport), but more sharp, like a strong diode light. Soared at a height between 800-1000 meters just below cloud cover. Was approx. over Frederiksberg > KBH NV > Ydre Østerbro > Hellerup. At the same time heard fighter planes above the cloud cover. The object disappeared in approx. 1 second while watching it through binoculars.

Watching TV but sensing some light in the sky moving like an airplane across the sky but MUCH slower, same height all the time. For the next half hour I watch it - it then stops completely, but remains as a very bright spot in the sky, not flashing at any point. What could it be?

I put my car in the carport and walked towards my front door. I couldn't help but see a few very bright white glowing points moving across the sky. They were much clearer and much more luminous than any stars nearby. They moved completely parallel, but one well ahead of the other. The front one then faded out as if coming across a thin veil of clouds, but the sky was perfectly sparkling clear. The second light did the same approx. 2 seconds after, still in a parallel orbit. There was no sound and they were clearly further apart than is usual for aircraft. Besides, they weren't switched off at the same time either.

Was out in my backyard playing with my camera and zoom I had bought for it. It is a phone camera of the brand Huawei. Almost new and then bought a zoom lens for it. Taking pictures of today's full moon. To the left of this one I notice a very bright star and think that was strange. Haven't noticed a star in that direction before and not that clear at all. Trying to zoom in and not getting exactly what I expect. Here I see a white object of some kind. Two deep plates placed together. That was the way. I check my lens for dirt and reflections. It is not. Nothing to see just below or just above. Not to the side either. BLot this point with the star. Turns away a bit and takes pictures in a different direction and comes back to the point. It's still there and I get the same thing with my zoom. It tilts a little to the other side while I'm looking at it, and then it just shuts off. Away. No star or anything on that spot and it hasn't been back since. Been out to see if there should be a star I can see in that direction. There is nothing.

2 days before, me and my mate were on our way home together at the same time when we see a ball of light coming in from the west. We immediately say it's a shooting star or a comet and wait for it to go out, but instead it slowly flies over us and starts turning southeast over our apartment and disappears. We wondered a little about that, but the next day it was forgotten. But last night when I was out in the parking lot and happened to look up, there it was again. So I rush up to my mate and tell him, and we knock on the neighbor's door to borrow his binoculars. Now there are 3 of us and we watch it fly over us through binoculars. There were no flashing lights or any noise at all. Just a big bright white light. And it seemed both times as if it flew in small notches.

On the night between Saturday and Sunday, i.e. between 9 and 10 May, I am on my way home from a party, and am NOT drunk or under the influence of euphoric drugs. I am cycling along Ågade in Frederikssund, in a direction from west to east, when I see that a white-green light appears in the sky. As it becomes sharper, I stop and observe the phenomenon. As it passes me, the center of the light fills approximately, as if you were holding a tennis ball up in front of you in an outstretched arm. The light emitted by the "ball" is very bright and illuminates everything nearby in the split second when it passes me. I can hear a crackling and almost crisp sound as it passes me and can see a condensation-like tail behind the bullet. However, the tail does not remain visible immediately afterwards. Since it flies parallel to the water and horizontally, I can rule out various types of fireworks, emergency rockets, etc. Since I grew up as a neighbor to the American air base in Sdr. Strømfjord, I can also rule out any kind of human-manned vessel, due to lack of beacons, too low a height, and sound. In terms of. its height as it passes me I can't give an educated guess but will shoot at between 30 and 50 meters (and maybe descending). The reason I can go into detail about the observation is that immediately after the incident I noted all the info.

One July evening in 1975, I was home alone as my wife and son had gone to Sweden, I was vacuuming when I observed a bright light outside. I turned off the vacuum cleaner and opened a window to see what it was. Slightly obliquely above the house, I then saw a strong, downward-pointing light with a circular shape. It was moving in an easterly direction, but no sound was heard from the object. It must have been later than 9pm as it was almost dark and I was able to observe this light even though I had the light on in the living room. I judge the object to be at a height of 300-500 m above the ground. What compass direction it came from I did not see, only that it disappeared in an easterly direction. So no contours due to the dark evening sky, just the circular shape of the downward light.

We were on our way home from work, it was approx. 00.30 summer time, so relatively bright. We pass a field on the right just before the town of Flade. In the middle of the field hovers something that looks most like a cloud for approx. 8-10m height. The subject is approx. 20-25m above the center and approx. 5m from bottom to top. It mostly looked like 2 deep plates placed on top of each other, but in appearance it resembled a cloud. No sound or light from the object, it just hung there. I wanted us to stop, but she wouldn't. I think she was a bit scared by this phenomenon, especially because it was neither foggy nor cloudy that summer night at approx. 00.30. So to her it struck me as a bit of a hoot that anyone could believe such nonsense, but she still wouldn't hold back and study this further.

I was cycling west on my way to work, in a strong headwind - it was approx. a quarter to 6 and have my head full of the day's challenges on a Monday morning, and there is never anything or any kind of activity this early in the morning! But when I saw a ball of orange light descend from the cloud cover - I think it's probably a helicopter about to land in Beldringe (a small airport NW of Odense) I just cycle out there while I observe further - on the object for just as it was coming down towards the earth – it swings in a half arc up towards the cloud cover ig, but still has difficulty seeing what it must be. It does not move in the sky. When I get to work in Roskilde, I can still see the object. The last time I check is 09:45. It is gone.
Sat on a bench by Søndersø in Viborg. Spotted it right above me high up at high speed.

My boyfriend, niece and I go to a birthday party outside to smoke. We look at stars and keep an eye out for any aurora borealis that could potentially be seen in the night sky. However, we do not see the northern lights, but suddenly we can see a luminous object that looks like stars, which for about 2 min. flying to the right. First at high speed, then the speed slows down. Subsequently, "it" stands still for a few minutes and then flies to the left at low speed.. Then it stops and flies upwards, after which it decreases in visibility.. We discuss whether it could be a satellite, or perhaps a military aircraft?

By chance, I spot 2 faint stars in the NW direction. Suddenly, the left one of these seems to drop a bit, to come to a stand still and then drop in jerks again. Fortunately, I had the position of the 2 stars in relation to each other, and was thus able to register the movement. The whole experience lasted maybe 30 seconds. Subsequently, I became aware that the incident took place below and slightly to the left of the Chariot. Possibly the right of the 2 stars was the lower left star of the Chariot (subject to caveats). A moment later, while I was pondering over the episode, a very powerful shooting star came from the ENE towards the WSW covering half the firmament. Hope the above experience is of interest, I myself am very surprised by what I observed.

We were at our campsite located at the Fjordkroen by Præstø Fjord. In the evening I had gone out to walk the dogs on a field road that connects Bækkeskov Stræde with Sjoltevej. On the open stretch of fields on both sides of the dirt road, I observed a streak of light in the clouds moving at great speed from the forest across the fields to the northwest. It was not a cone of light, but a strip of light - which then moved around in different directions. It looked as if the light came from above. Very strange.

Have observed an object in Grenaa and subsequently seen it at our home address. The next day I put myself in the garden to see if it should come back. At 23.27 it comes into view due west and flies silently across the sky due east. The color is bright white and can be described as a searchlight on an aviator, but does not change due to the direction of flight. There is no sound. Don't blink anyone.

The ball slowly moved obliquely downwards and disappeared completely in the sky after approx. 5 seconds. The light was clear and on the top half of the sphere there was a shadow that curved upwards in the middle of the shadow. The ball was the size of a one-crown coin in an outstretched arm. We had both initially thought it was a shooting star, but had ruled it out as it was simply too visible for too long and too big. We had also each thought about whether it was a New Year's rocket or a plane. We also excluded this as we did not think this was consistent with our observations. It was only when we got home that we talked about the phenomenon and the possibility that we have seen a UFO-like object.

We are 4 adults sitting outside in the garden and enjoying a cup of coffee in the summer heat in the silence of the night. Suddenly I see a constant orange light the size of the hole in a five flying without sound and at an estimated height of 1.5 km. The ball of light flies without a sound from east to west. I ask the others to see the ball of light in the sky, and we manage to see it for 10-15 seconds before the trees block the view. We all have a good sense of reality. One has a good knowledge of aircraft and new technology, but neither of us comes up with an educated guess as to what it could be that we had seen. Only that the light purposefully flew at a relatively low altitude over Slagelse. It was partially starry and the stars had an almost white light compared to this glowing orange ball of light. We think other night owls might have seen the same thing…

We drove along the forest road, from Holbæk towards Kalundborg approx. 10 km from Holbæk, when my partner and I, at the same time, observe a very green luminous ball with a tail of sparks! The object appears very large from our angle. After approx. 7 to 10 sec. subject splits into two parts, then accelerates and becomes indistinct, or just shuts off? I, the undersigned, have seen a lot in the sky, throughout my life, both meteorites and various other funny things, but never anything like this?? My partner and I have absolutely the same idea of what we have seen, even if neither of us can explain what it was!!!

My girlfriend and I are walking down Søndersø in Viborg after we have visited a friend in town. We walk on a path along the lake, and we talk and have fun. I look up and quite by chance spot a plane (I think). Because at first it really looks like a plane. A glowing thing of some kind, but not flashing, just glowing white and flying across the sky. At first I just think it's a plane, but when I look closer, it doesn't look like a plane at all, but a round circle of some kind. I notice it's not a plane because I think it's changing speed. I notice that it's round, but it's notched all the way around like several sort of triangles sticking out, but it's still round. It was only tiny thanks, so it's a little hard to explain. To put it as I perceived it; it is round with triangles all around. It's flying as I said, and when it dawns on me that it's not a plane because it's not flashing, but just constantly glowing white and flying across the sky, I think my next thought; That it's a shooting star. But a shooting star does not fly so slowly. It almost changes speed, a little up in speed and a little down again, but nothing that remarkable. My boyfriend thinks it's a bird, but it's completely dark and there's no light in the sky. The next thing the object does is slow down and speed up again (can't quite remember). What I definitely remember is that it speeds up (I think). What I can definitely remember is that suddenly it says ping, and then it's gone. It simply disappeared. If it is finally a bird, it can't just suddenly disappear and there was no light in the sky. It gives me such chills. It was very fascinating, but after I watched it, I just want to go home. When we turn around the path in a bend to come up towards Randersvej, which goes through both Søndersø and Nørresø, I look out over the lake again and see an object exactly like it. This time it changes trajectory so that it either flies straight ahead or to the side. But it flies in very FAST and STRAIGHT lines. It does not turn, but change trajectory like this; quickly across the sky, then it flies quickly to the side, but still in a soft way. When it has flown a bit, then all of a sudden; ping, it's gone. There were no clouds and it was very clear. The strangest thing about it all was that it seemed like it was way up in the sky. Closest up to the stars, but still it seemed like it was right above us... So far down. The first one didn't fly over the water, but the second one did. I'm sure it wasn't a bird, as a bird hovers and turns in a different way (as a bird does). This one turned like this; ping to the right, ping to the left, etc. And a bird cannot light up the sky, and if it finally does, the light on it cannot suddenly go out in the same place as it shone a little earlier. It looked very mysterious and I am very objective in my description. Hope that doesn't sound corny. I have never experienced anything like this before and would like an explanation. I've seen satellites before, but this wasn't a satellite. The first object flew from west to east and then disappeared on its way to the east. The other flew from south to north and then flew in all possible direct lines.

We were on our way out from Aalborg towards Hadsund. We observed a total of 7 pieces. strange bright things in the air, 4 pcs. to the southwest and 5 pcs. moss southeast. As we turn the roundabout we pull over to the side of the road and jump out of the car to see if we could film them, but they flew at a fast speed. The 4 pcs. disappeared suddenly, while the 3 pcs. flew away, very strange. We don't normally believe in something like that, but we were completely blown away. We were driving 2 people in two cars and we all saw it.

I was talking on the phone as I looked out over the city from my window. Suddenly a red light appears, and I tell my girlfriend on the phone that now someone has fired an emergency rocket. I take it for an emergency flare because of its bright red light. A moment later, however, the light changes color to bright white - and now begins to switch between the two colors at irregular intervals. I tell my girlfriend that I don't think it's an emergency rocket, but something else, and I observe for the next few minutes the movements of the UFO. The dot of light - because I didn't see it like anything else, it was too far away and it was almost twilight - moves a little around, back and forth, but mostly to the right. Suddenly it turns off - only to turn on again less than 20 seconds later, a little further to the left than it disappeared. The height was pretty much constant, but the movement in the horizontal plane seemed very random. Finally, the light went out, almost like an old-fashioned TV being turned off - it got smaller and smaller, and disappeared. I tried to contact SUFUI on the phone but there was no answer. (I thought it was a hotline...? But I guess there isn't as much status in UFO hunting as there was when I was a boy... I was an avid UFO hunter myself...) Immediately I would think that what I saw could be a plasma phenomenon of some kind. As I said, the movement in the horizontal plane seemed too random to be a vessel controlled by a thinking being. I am a big fan of Eugen Semitjov's book "Unfathomable UFOs", and I agree with his thoughts regarding plasma phenomena.

I look out the kitchen window and see something different come flying over the treetops. Then walks out onto the stairs and watches it get closer. Calling my mother, who also comes out and sees it. It comes so close that we can see that it looks like 2 deep plates put together with windows in between. It has come flying silently and slowly in a straight line towards us, stands still very close to us, where we can also see that colored light comes out from under it, and then changes direction and disappears away again in a flash and silently .

A very indefinable object, white-transparent box-like, never seen reached, I can compare it to, hovered over the neighbor's roof, flashed, then slowly rotated 90 degrees vertically, spun around itself in a very controlled movement but at the same time it seemed light and floating as it (seemed like slowly) floated away but it was gone in seconds. Very strange sight. It seemed as if it was constantly changing shape, or it was some kind of reflection that disturbed the eye.

I was sitting at night smoking a cigarette, when suddenly two large airplane-like things streaked through the air a little further on at the end of the building (one flight from me). I was able to draw it the next day and the boyfriend, who unfortunately wasn't there when it happened, said it looked like fighter jets (have googled pictures and that's what the shape was like, but there was fire all around and everywhere on them). The thing that caught me the most, besides the fact that they looked like they were on fire, was how fast they were going and that they were flying right over and past the top of our building. They followed each other very closely and precisely with maybe a meter distance between them. And then it went as fast as the sound of a quick hiss, but there was no sound at all. It looked really beautiful, just had the feeling of having been lucky to see something so special, which unfortunately I haven't seen since.

We sat 3 people and enjoyed ourselves. The guests were about to break up when one of them spotted a luminous object in the southern night sky. Another filmed it with his iPhone (film clips have been sent to you in a separate email). The undersigned assumed it must be a drone, but it moved in a way where, as a complete skeptic, I still had doubts. At one point the object flies sharply to the east. We run through the apartment onto a corridor on the opposite side, where we spot it again. Here it is almost silent in the sky. Suddenly it disappears, but comes back briefly, after which it is gone at a very high speed.
I showed it looked like a cigar at first, then got closer, I thought it was round. It was gray white. No sound came from it.

While airing the dog I see what looks like a big shooting star. It glows in colors as if metal is burning - there are hills in the direction of observation, the fireball disappears behind the hills - it is estimated that it is a meteor or debris from a satellite that is on its way down - it could be assumed that there has been something left that may have hit Jutland south of Solbjerg - distance cannot be judged - I hope to hear about observations from other positions. It was so big that others must have observed it.

After the morning broadcast on TV-2 today, January 20, about UFOs, and where I could then see where I should write, I would like to tell you that on New Year's Eve 2008 I saw five luminous objects, approx. 20 min. past twelve to half past one, (the fireworks had died down). First an orange glowing dot came flying and it turned sharply to the southwest just above the neighbor's roof and outside my windows, then another came and I could then see a row of 5 in total coming at the same height one after the other with approx. 2-3 minutes apart, everyone turned sharply to the southwest, and from my point it looked like it was beyond Djursland. I could follow them until they were little dots. They seemed to be holding both altitude and course. I told others about what I had seen, but I didn't know where to go with it. But then it happens that I am invited to my neighbor's house, who lives on the 3rd floor of the same building with almost the same view, this New Year's Eve 2009. We then stand in her window and look at all the fireworks, and it gradually dies down approx. . 20 min past 12, and then I say for fun, so now the UFOs may well come, and they did, but this time there were only 2, same light-color size and at the same height, but unfortunately her window turns a little more slanted to mine so I couldn't see where they went. But this time I got a picture of the last of them, and also my neighbor as a witness, I can't see where to put the picture here, but can send it if I get an address.

It started when I got hungry and needed something to eat when I was on my way home from work. I went to Istegade to eat as they do good food etc. Just parked my car, go inside to order food as I choose to go outside to wait. It is a hot summer day. Then I just look up at the sky just for fun, when I immediately spot a strange strong white light coming towards the ground at insanely high speed. It's getting bigger, and I thought maybe it could be a shooting star very high up. Approx. 4-5 kilometers up, but no it flew in a zigzag and then up and down side to side. Very strange. Never seen anything like it, which then disappeared in a flash. Couldn't understand at all what it was I saw. I'm sure it was a UFO, because it's not the first time I've experienced it. but 3 times in my life. Similarly, it is very difficult to explain it in writing.

We were standing for a while talking when a cyclist comes driving and shouts, look out, it's going damn... fast. Up in the sky there was a bright white spherical light which quickly disappeared behind houses and trees. We were standing in a fog, so we couldn't see where it went down, or how big it was. was when we had nothing to compare it to.

We thought we saw a plane on approach. The speed and height matched it. As it got closer we could see that it was orange/red and there weren't the flashing lights that are on an airplane. It flew right over our heads, but there was no sound, so we agreed that at least it wasn't a plane. It was flying very fast and there was no wind, so we also agreed that it couldn't be a weather balloon. Before I got my mobile phone out so I could take a picture, it was already very far away, but I still managed to get a picture of a small "dot". When you enlarge the image, you see a straight orange line, which may be due to the speed, as I immediately perceived it as being round. We looked at it for a maximum of 1 minute, and can therefore assess that it has had quite good speed.

I recorded video of an object that actually flew over my street area!! approx. At 23.09. I am 100% sure that it was not a plane, helicopter or drone etc. This object flew in the direction of approx. From skt. Klemens towards Ravenbjerg in a straight line.

Sunday 26 July 2015 around 22.55 I see something strange. I am standing in my kitchen on the second floor - the light is off - the window is open - and I can hear the usual traffic noise from Hovedvejen/Roskildevej. Suddenly, out of nowhere, I see a strange light coming from the south – down around Brøndby Stadium – in a northerly direction. It looks somewhat like "gaslight" in that it flickers between blue and green. It moves horizontally across the sky – it neither loses nor gains altitude – and then it is completely silent. As it passes my window I can see it has an oval shape. You have to make an effort to spot it, it is surrounded by some white dots. It is probably 50-100 meters above the ridge of the neighboring property - which is also a 2-storey dwelling. It seems to follow a route up along Vestvolden/Motorring 3. After passing my window, but before it seems to reach Jyllingevej, the light disappears abruptly - and it becomes invisible. The episode lasts 5-10 seconds. Then I look out of the window to the south and immediately spot a plane taking off from Kastrup and heading south. The wing lights of an airliner are clearly visible over a distance of more than 15 km. The "gas light" I had just witnessed was subdued - it did not sting the eyes in any way. Could the white spots I saw encircling the oval object be some kind of heat shield? It is difficult to say anything about the size – it could be anything from 6-12 meters long and 2-3 meters high.

At first glance it looked like a very large star with changing shades of color. It moved in a defined pattern (could be observed all the time through a window) with very variable speed and especially in very fast jerks, which is completely unthinkable for any human-made flying object. Also not conceivable for a natural phenomenon. It was far away, and when we went to bed it had not yet disappeared. Around. 5 the same night I observed 2 new "Stars" not so close in a westerly direction, with the same moving pattern.

My wife and I were having dinner when she suddenly saw a relatively bright orange/red light in the direction of 155 degrees. At first I thought it might be a plane, but we got up and went outside to the garden. The weather was cloudy and the ball of light flew relatively low. It was no flyer, no red or green lights, and when it had passed us there was no white tail light. There was no engine noise and the fireball was completely silent. When the balls of light had passed us, it turned as if in a northerly direction and disappeared on the horizon approx. 30 degrees above us. Eventually we couldn't see the ball of light anymore because of the neighbor's roof. The entire observation lasted at least 3 minutes.

properties.Remarks:
se beretning
Den internationale Rumstation ISS
properties.content: A great bright star, which was almost stationary, but suddenly moved silently and silently to the southwest. I called to my father, who saw it move across the sky and disappear into the mist. It certainly moved towards Kbhn. Airport, but without saying a sound and with bright lights facing backwards. It wasn't landing lights. The light was the size of a small pea in an outstretched arm.

For approx. 30 years ago I had a strange experience. I was then a child of 8-10 years, I think. It was the end of summer, when the harvest had been done and towards evening. Unfortunately, I don't remember many details after so many years, but I will try to tell what I remember. At the time, I lived outside Tommerup. Precisely Tommerupvej 224, where I grew up. One evening, when I had been out playing, I had walked down our gravel road towards our neighbor who was approx. 100 m to the southwest, - I think. I don't quite remember how it all came together, but I think I was downstairs looking for my older sister, and as I reach a little way down towards the neighboring house, she comes running up the road. She seems scared and frightened. I don't remember what she says or if I see anything at this point, but I myself run back to our garage, which is under the house. On the left side of the garage, a staircase leads up to the house itself. Walking up the stairs, I turn to see what was really wrong and why we ran up to our house, or at least that's what I remember now. Down in front of the garage of our neighboring house approx. 3 m out in the cornfield (which has been harvested at this time) I see a metallic gray object that looks very much like what you would call a classic UFO today. Around the vessel are some beings. I don't remember how many, but think 2-4. The creatures, as far as I can tell, are not particularly large and grey. I run around the corner of the house, but look forward again. Here, however, I feel that one creature becomes aware of me, and I get scared and run into the house to my parents and tell them that there is something strange down in the field in front of the neighbor's garage. They look out of the window, but can't see the big picture, as there are plants and it's getting dark. The next day I ask the neighbor's boy if he has seen anything strange as we go down to the road to catch our school taxi. He says that he and his family sat and watched it from their living room window, which was approx. 15 m from where the object had landed. They had been told by their parents that these were devils and they were not allowed to look. It should be added that the family were Jehovah's Witnesses. When I came home from school, I noticed a large round spot in the field that had been burned where the object had been. It was approx. 3-4 meters in diameter, I think. I remember this ring was there long after the incident. As I said, it was many years ago and I don't remember the details. Strangely enough, I have been interested in UFOs for many years and read many books about UFOs, but only recently it seems that this incident has come to the surface again. I mentioned it to my sister, who could confirm that she had experienced the incident as well, but didn't really believe it herself and therefore dismissed it. I don't know how much you can use that somewhat imprecise and old observation, but I just recently felt the urge to come forward with it, so that's it. I know that to many it probably sounds like pure fantasy, but there really is so much that goes on until you find out what it is or recognize what it is. Many people have a strange belief that we are the only intelligent beings in the universe, which I personally find completely utopian. When you have experienced such an incident yourself, it only confirms that we are absolutely not alone in the universe and probably not very intelligent either, compared to the beings who are able to travel here. Many times things simply require that you open your horizons to see what is right at our feet, but often unfortunately we have to see it with our own eyes, and even then it can be difficult to believe what you see, and sometimes even harder to deal with.

Was out looking before bed and saw a very large luminous arrow-shaped object. Approx. 25 - 30 times longer than e.g. a passenger plane. The "arrow" was completely symmetrical and very clear with no "fogs" or anything that could look like cloud formations. On the "arrow shaft" approx. one twentieth from the tip it was twice as "thick", and this again ended approx. three-quarters of the way down, where the light also faded. The "thick" part was, seen in my Bresser 8 x 40 CB Grossfeld (143m / 1000m) Binoculars as "divided" into a kind of windows (bars) approx. 50 pcs. I did not observe apparition, it was approx. to the north when I came out. It had a slope towards VSV when it disappeared behind some vegetation. There was light (white/blue) throughout the "arrow", i.e. also at the tip itself. Only at the back did the light fade slowly. No sound from the object could be heard as it was quite windy.

I went for a walk with the dog in the evening and enjoyed the starry evening sky. Saw something coming from a more southerly direction than the usual evening flyers. It also came slower so I thought it might be a helicopter. But the weather was calm - no obvious reason for a rescue operation. Then I listened - no - absolutely no - sound. Then I turned around running back and in (with a slow dog in tow as it definitely didn't think we had walked enough) called to my husband to come out and have a look. We ran to the neat door, and it flew just as quietly over the sitka firs. My husband is visually impaired, but with normal night vision. I told him to run in and get the binoculars. It took some time (since I had thrown it somewhere it shouldn't be), but when he brought it (a Cobra - Optisan 8x24 field 6.0) that flying thing was still hanging there between the treetops (without my wanting to set an angle on it). I could now clearly see three white lights in a line. In addition, there was a red light that seemed to swing around.

When my wife and I were out and on our way home from my father-in-law's, we stopped and looked up at the sky. East of the North Star, where we looked towards another bright star. Just below the shining star, came a powerful white light. It wasn't a shooting star. It is certain that it could not be. This object we both had seen can only be an unidentified object (ufo). At 21.07 there were no planes in the sky to be seen over Fredericia and to Billund airport.
A pentagram is visible for 20 minutes over Papirøen and calls the Copenhagen police.

At 0020 I see a strong luminous "ball". es as the size of the North Star. The direction is increasing from west to east. Seen towards a due south direction. The speed is increasing at the same time that it disappears as less and less in an upward direction. Disappears then completely. I have recorded the incident as a video on an alm. smartphone. but haven't had the movement confirmed by having a fixed reference point, unfortunately. As it rises to the east, my view is that the speed increases tremendously.

I was out to see Andromeda when I looked up there was a star, planet, Venus strength even more at max. At first I thought it was Venus, but it was wrong, and when I had looked at it for approx. 5-6 sec., it quickly started to decrease and disappeared completely. I quickly got my camera and took a series of pictures (Nikon d5300 with Tokina 11-16mm f 2.8. with tripod and made pictures with different settings. Best result 4 seconds iso 800. But could not see anything in the pictures near the area. It was close to Andromeda.

We sat on the balcony and talked to our mothers. Suddenly we all saw a very strong red-orange color in the sky. A little to the left and below the lower left corner of the Chariot. We thought it must be a planet under special lighting conditions. I went in to investigate what planet it might be. I couldn't figure that out. When I came out on the balcony again it had disappeared. It disappeared by slowly becoming weaker and weaker. While we were talking about what it might have been, - an airplane with the sun as a shadow, or something else - it came out again. It now appeared more northerly and much larger. A bit shocking one must say, because it was now absolutely certain that it was not a planet or an airplane. It moved quietly to the same point a little to the left of the Chariot's lower left corner, where it stayed for a few minutes and then again became fainter and fainter like the first time it disappeared.

Saturday night at 0015 I saw a strange light west of exit 36, Borup. There were about 12 lights of various heights moving towards the north. It was probably over Ringsted. I guess they were Asian paper lanterns ???? Can see that this has been seen many times before and also above Ringsted.

1. Object (spherical shape) flies faster than an airplane above the clouds from north to east. We can see that it occasionally disappears behind the clouds, only to reappear and disappear to the east. After approx. 1-2 min, another object similar to the 1st appears, and the same thing happens. We also see a 3rd similar to the first. All at the same speed. All 4 of us are talking about the 1st maybe being a satellite, but since there were 3 at short intervals, they can't be satellites, nor can they be planes.

I was out fishing at Arnå (approx. 35 km from the German border). I looked down into the water when I caught a glimpse of something in the air. Looking up, I observed 3 bright objects. I thought there was a plane that explored in several pieces. They rotated a bit in on themselves, grew more intense and turned off. The light phenomenon lasted approx. 4 seconds. After that, the only thing left in the sky was smoke which was a zig zag spiral shape which could be seen for a long time, at least 10 min.

Stood in the garden on the night of Wednesday 16/4-2014 around 01:00, and spotted something that looked like a comet with a distinctly long tail. It was in an easterly direction, and slowly disappeared in a south-easterly direction. There were no sounds to be heard, but the object also seemed like it was very far away (like out in space). Have previously (in the early 90s) observed a comet, but it moved relatively quickly, so if it was a comet, it must have been very close to the earth. The observation lasted approx. 2-3 minutes. Went in for camera, but the object was almost gone when I came back out, so unfortunately didn't get any pictures. Has anyone else seen the same thing?

Then a bright white light, like in January. Stands still and lights up brightly and then goes back down in brightness. It is moving very slowly to the right, to the south, appears to be approx. at an altitude of 3 km. Seen from my window. It then disappears after fifteen minutes. What was it. No stars in the sky or moon. Very reminiscent of a star.

At sunset, we were enjoying the beautiful sky on a car trip, and suddenly we discovered three luminous objects in the air, which were apparently in a formation.
