These three objects were to the left of the sunset. When we stopped at the side of the road, we saw two more objects of the same kind (though less conspicuous) to the right of the sunset. You could not sense that the objects were moving, but after 10 minutes you could clearly see that they were moving away from the original formation. We drove on after 10 minutes and didn't get to see the objects disappear, but it's certainly possible that they were there for a considerable amount of time before we spotted them as well as after we drove. The images I have attached are of relatively good quality and show a reddish blur of small black bodies -- this could at first glance look like some kind of rocket like those used to launch satellites. I saw to my surprise that an observation from Skovlunde, at roughly the same time, describes the same thing.

Woke up to a strange sound, not a plane or helicopter, but a strange loud engine noise. It came and went, and at At 4.40 I saw to the right of the block of flats opposite our house a round object with flashing red lights, it disappeared behind the building and flew to the north-east, where I could see it again to the left of the house, disappearing to the east. Our neighbor had also wondered about the strange sound, but did not get up. At 4.44, I heard the sound for the last time.

It was slightly smaller than the moon and was as bright as the sun - so dazzling! It went behind a cloud and you could see it through the cloud! It flew very fast! I saw it out my window! It seemed round throughout, but was round at the top and sort of had a notch in both sides - from there it went diagonally inwards and was so round at the bottom! It had a very short tail!

The two luminous dots moved parallel in a south-southwest direction without changing their mutual distance. The imaginary line between them was approx. 45 degrees in relation to their common direction of movement. I observed the two luminous dots as elongated and smudged, while my daughter claims they were pure dots. Their color was almost like the color of the high-pressure sodium lamps used for street lighting. My first thought was that it was a question of the light reflections that one can observe in damp weather from car lights when their light is reflected in electrical overhead lines. However, it was not humid weather, there were no cars, the color was wrong and the height of the sky was too high to be reflections in overhead lines. My next thought was that it could be birds illuminated from below, for example from the stadium lighting from Dalum Stadion, which (as far as I know) is located in the direction of observation. However, this would mean that the birds would have to move at considerable speeds, estimated at several thousand km/h. In my opinion, it cannot have been a question of planes, as they should have been audible with the given trajectory and speed. I have some experience with satellite observations. It was also not about satellites, as both the speed and the size of the light phenomenon were wrong. What, in my opinion, would fit best in terms of trajectory and speed would be a meteor, but in that case it would have to have been blown into two pieces. I myself have never observed anything other than short-lived shooting stars, and thus not a large meteor that crosses the entire sky. Even so, I don't think that the yellowish color matches my expectation for the color of such a thing.

I was about 10-11 years old. The boy next door (a year older), my sister (3 years younger) and I threw frisbees after dark on a quiet residential street in Holbæk. It wasn't a real Frisbee, but a plastic plate. We ended up throwing it into the merchant's yard and therefore stopped the game as we couldn't get into the yard and pick it up. It was quiet and starry. We stood out on the road (in the middle of the road) and talked. My sister and I stood next to each other facing the neighbor boy. There were approx. 1 - 1.5 meters between us. My sister and I stood with our backs to the west and the neighbor boy's back turned to the east. After we had been standing there for a few minutes, it came. It was disc-shaped and was approx. 20 cm in diameter. The shape was like 2 plates that are joined so that the bottom points upwards on one and downwards on the other. It had no cow eyes or flashing lights. The most peculiar thing about its appearance was that it resembled a hologram: it looked as if it consisted only of light (green) and not solid matter - though not one like a glint of light, the shape of which cannot be seen, as when looking directly on a strong light source. On the contrary, it had a clearly defined form. I could see right through it but couldn't see into it (sic!). It came from a northerly direction at a height that was just below my eye level at the time. I saw it when it was a few meters from us. It flew straight towards us at a pace similar to slow walking. Its movement was smooth and it didn't zig-zag or jump or anything like that. It continued and flew right between us. I (and the other two) were less than a meter from it and could have touched it if I dared. It continued between us and on in the same direction, pace and height. It flew approx. 5 meters further, after which it rose upwards approx. 45 degrees, accelerated and disappeared in 1-2 seconds. It didn't fly into a cloud when it was cloudless, nor did it go behind anything else. When it had disappeared, the neighbor boy asked if we had seen it too. We nodded and ran to my mother and told her. I knew even then that you could forget important things, so I carefully reviewed the experience to make sure I could remember the details. I never spoke to the boy next door about it again, and I lost contact with him when we moved shortly after. My sister only remembers seeing something strange but can't remember any details.

properties.Colors: blålig med lille, grønt og sølv

properties.content: Clear white light, which flickered in the air (not fixed like a twinkling star), stood for a long time in the sky approx. 2-3 min and then disappeared to the west, still with the white light that could be seen from Ebeltoft.

I stand smoking my cigarette and look up at the sky. I see 3 bright objects flying fast across the sky. The 3 objects fly in a formation in a row and when they reach the sky one flies closer to the other and they disappear quietly so that I can no longer see them.
Three triangular planes. Disappeared suddenly. Soundless. Diffuse contours. Not faster than helicopters. Fly below cloud height.

We were driving towards Copenhagen when I noticed some bright light in the sky. It occurred to us that it was probably a plane waiting for landing permission, but we became curious when it stood completely still in the air, and it was as if it was coming closer to us. It was clear to see 4 white lights, and two blue lights and a red light that went from one white light to the other. Three - four different red lights. We concluded that it must be helicopters, but the light was coming from underneath, and was going straight from side to side and not moving around, as if there had been a red light on a helicopter. Suddenly it began to move very strongly and flew off to the right, where we discovered another strange phenomenon. They flew very fast beside us, but were far away. At one point we could see that it looked square, almost like a rhombus. Suddenly one sped up and flew away from us, and just disappeared... Then we discovered that there was one more and it was quite close. We could almost see a cone of light from it, and it was completely still. All three were exactly the same with the blue, white and red lights. Diamond-shaped and quite large, although they were probably far from us. We couldn't hear any sound even if we rolled down the window and slowed down. But we were also on the highway. They took turns standing still in the sky and speeding up a lot. They were in the sky quite early on the motorway, and the last two only disappeared around Copenhagen, where the road started to be lit. I don't believe in UFOs, but this is very mysterious. We hope that there are others who have seen it too, and that we can get a logical explanation for the phenomenon. I can't answer which direction they had, but they flew on our right side from Næstved towards Kbh. The one that disappeared flew away in the same direction.

I could see three lights flying in formation, at a fast pace, lower than airplanes fly. Before they disappeared because of the block of flats, it was as if it "flip-over" to the left (to the south). One to two minutes later it came again. This time I could see four lights, again the same faint brightness, and now I could follow them for a relatively long time, as this time they flew along the block instead of across. If I had only seen them the first time, I would have dismissed it as rice paper lanterns, but I saw them fly first one way and then the other, and the second time was a long straight stretch. So what was that...? and has anyone else observed this?

Stood and watched the cloudless starry sky. Suddenly, a white spot - looked like a faint star - moved across the sky at high speed (speed like a shooting star, but without a tail). Suddenly changed direction almost 90 degrees and disappeared in a few seconds.

I stood on the bridge at Brede Sø and looked at the starry sky on my way home from DTU. A luminous ball came floating from the north (Virum) at 30-50 km/h and continued south towards Copenhagen. It looked like a round, frosted glass ball with a 30 W light bulb in the middle (white-yellow). Since I couldn't judge the distance, I also couldn't judge the size exactly, but it must have been between 40 cm and 150 cm in diameter. It could also be described as similar to a rice lamp. It was less than 150 meters away, because I could see the trees 150 m in the background, and more than 40 meters (came into view behind some houses) The bullet flew for approx. 10-20 meters high (the terrain varies a lot in this area). It was completely silent. When it was almost out of my line of sight, it seemed to rapidly accelerate upwards until I could no longer see it. I have very good eyesight and am absolutely certain that it was not some kind of known flying object. I was not under the influence of drugs.

We were sitting in the living room when I spotted something strangely bright in the sky. My daughter and I rushed outside to take a closer look. There was no engine noise to be heard, and we observed the object for approx. 5 min., where it disappeared across the sky at a leisurely pace. It was brightly lit the whole time. We took 1 photo and recorded a video on a mobile phone. Unfortunately, there is not much to see on the video. The image shows a golden light which, when zoomed, acquires an orange-red "tail".

I lie in my jacuzzi spa on my terrace in the garden, and look up at a clear sky and observe quite a few satellites, which fly quietly over past the stars, over a period of maybe an hour, when I just stare up at the stars. Then I notice what I think at first looks like a series of stars moving into the line of my eye...looking over at them I see that there are maybe 10-12 new "stars" moving quietly and calm over my house. The "stars" did not shine brightly, but were fainter, like the faint stars in the sky that you can only look for after you have stared up at the night sky for some time and your eyes have adjusted to looking in the dark. The 10-12 "stars" were moving slowly, in a fixed "formation" that looked like a chevron, with the tip of that chevron being the direction it was moving in... It was as if the "stars" were flickering, like they flew in and out of fog. I look at it with my mouth open for approx. 8 seconds, when I thought, I have to try to get it on camera - after I picked up my phone (it was next to my jacuzzi), only I didn't see the "stars" again ?? I would also like to mention that there were no unusual noises...

My girlfriend and I sit on the Øresund coast at Kokkedal and look out over the water, towards Sweden. We looked for shooting stars as the Perseid meteor shower was due to peak this evening. Suddenly a yellow-orange spot of light appears in the east (over Sweden). It is moving west, towards a point north of us. At some point it changes direction, to the north. There is haze around it and it is moving towards the horizon. At the same time, it is getting bigger (because it was closer to us?) and more and more orange-red in colour. Finally it disappeared out of sight, just above the horizon to the north. After a number of seconds I started filming it and I have an approx. 3 min long video of the phenomenon/UFO. Since the Perseids peaked last night, REALLY many people must have seen this, and there are probably also more who have it on video.

As a young 15-year-old, I picked strawberries during my summer vacation. Together with some friends I lived in a tent on Funen. One afternoon we wanted a trip to "town" and do some shopping. On the way there we spotted something up in the sky. It was summer, high sun and clear weather. It looked like 2 plates put together. It was grayish- actually colorless. We were a group that all saw the same thing. It zig-zagged away from us. After looking at it for a bit, we ran home as fast as we could to get a camera, but unfortunately we didn't get to photograph it. It was a great experience, I will never forget it, but there are not many people who believe in me apart from my son. Now I would like to know if anyone else has experienced the same thing?

True to habit, I like to smoke 1 cigarette in the evening out in my driveway. Live out in the country, so when it's cloudless, the starry sky is very clear. Usually look up at the stars when I'm not staring down at my smartphone. A few weeks back I noticed a change in the constellation when I look up. I see something that looks like a star at first glance, but it blinks, so my mind is drawn to an airplane, but it is standing still in the air. In addition, it changes size, if you look closely, you can see that it shrinks and then becomes large again, and it repeats this in an almost "hysterical" way. It can easily find a way to move, but only seen it do so slowly. It hasn't been there every night and only see it when it's starry, but it's there NOW as I write here, and it's the 4th time in 2 weeks. Usually the same place in the sky, southeast direction, where it appears like over the neighbor's farm! It is difficult to tell the height, but it is clearly lower than the stars. I usually look at it for 2-10 minutes before I go back into the heat. Have shown it to my wife and a few family members and we are all amazed. Have also filmed it several times with my iPhone X, so have video of it even though the camera struggles with auto focus and the darkness. What and who should be contacted to get an answer? I thought it was very fascinating, and it could be wildly exciting to observe the phenomenon through some proper optics, so if you have something like that at your disposal and you want to, you are welcome here at the address. I can only say when it's there, it doesn't seem like it's going away any time soon and would like to know what/who it/they are.

Saw a strong white round light coming from the NW quickly across the sky in a straight curved direction to the SE. Lower than the starry sky. Was wondering if it was a satellite but does it move that fast?

I went to Rolling Stone's concert with my boyfriend in Idrætsparken in Copenhagen. We sat and waited for the band in the back stand, at the top right, with a view of Øster Alle. When I saw the object, the same one I had seen five years earlier in Blåvandshuk. A green ball with an orange tail, moving parallel to the horizon at high speed! Unfortunately, the boyfriend did not see the object. The object disappeared from view in a few seconds. I have wanted to submit my observations for years, but unfortunately have not been able to do so until now.

My boyfriend was about to let the cat in through the patio door when he noticed a strange blinking object high up, and further ahead. When he has to let the cat out again approx. half an hour later, the object is still hanging there. We have now observed it for half an hour through binoculars, and the shape of the object is triangular. Occasionally it splits in two. And when we saw a plane, the object moved quickly, and found its place again, at is now 21.56 and it is still there.

On 26.05.2016 approx. at 20.05 I rode the bus (line 3a) on Jernaldervej towards Ringvejen. Not so high above the street I could see a large square charcoal gray object flying over the street. It came from the north and was heading south (towards Viby Torv). There were people on the two rows on the right. It should have seen the really big object.

My son called me and pointed up to the sky. We looked out of our window on the 1st floor of our house. We saw an almond-shaped object flying silently and low at high speed across the sky. The colour White. I thought it must be a small plane at first, but the speed and gliding speed at which it flew meant that it could not be. I can't explain what it was. Maybe you can help us?

My husband and I are sitting in the living room on Sunday 28 April 2013 at approx. 22, we are in Svendborg Vest. Suddenly I see through the window "something" coming in the air from the south - I run out onto the terrace and shout to my husband to come and look too - over our house - how high up, I don't know - we see a very shiny orange /yellow, slightly angular thing? pass - no sound, and it has a direction to the north, where it disappears. We see it for approx. 5 min., and I am very inquisitive about what it is that we have seen. My husband does not believe in UFOs, but I will tell him against that.

In the south there is 1 reddish/orange glowing object. Then there are 2 more, i.e. 3 on a line, then the first turns approx. 120 degrees to the southeast, so that the 3 are in a triangle. They disappear in a southeasterly direction. The light was strange (not from aircraft that have red/green lights on wings, anti-collision light or stroboscope light), like a glowing red/orange. It was absolutely clear that these objects were controlled (controllable), no sound, no glowing tail.

The complainant immediately calls Billund Airport, where no one answered the phone. I then called Beldringe, where I spoke to the watchman in the tower, but he had no plausible explanation for our observations.

I just stumbled across this site. Basically thought it was closed, had seen something on TV about it. Brightly shining object comes into view to the north, where it rises rapidly from the horizon and moves in a southerly direction. Subsequently, the identical object appears at the same place above the horizon and follows the same direction. Next, the 3rd object appears in the same place on the horizon and follows the same course as the first two. The mutual distance between the objects appears to be the same. No sound. Great sight.

Was visiting family in Klarup and sat on the terrace and looked up. As the rescue helicopter flies we look up and spot an object that is silent and rotating in the air - it had straight surfaces that reflect in the sun - it seems to be moving at the same speed - constantly and we lose it a place above Aalborg. There were three of us who saw it.

We were out for an evening walk at approx. 10 p.m. It was dark when we started walking, but could see grey/bluish clouds in the night sky and a few stars. At the beginning of the walk, Cissel sees a shooting star, and soon after we both saw a lightning/strong flash of light by a single whitish cloud in the sky. We both noticed that it was not like ordinary lightning as it was very broad, short in length and was not followed by a thunderclap. The phenomenon occurred in the northeast. We continued our walk for 10 min. more before we returned home as it started to rain. We chose to seek shelter from the rain under a tree overlooking a field (northwest) with a small patch of nearby trees about 100 meters from where we stand (approx. 10 meter tall trees.) In the distance a larger forest max. one km away. Cissel then sees a whitish round light that does not look like a star, the light aligns with the tops of the nearby trees. We reckon that the light was closest to the distant forest, or further away. At first we both think it's an airplane. But then we observe that no flashing lights occur. The light first moves straight up, then slightly to the left, and we both start to joke a bit that it doesn't quite know which direction it wants to move in. I jokingly exclaim that it's a UFO. It continues to move in alternating directions at short intervals. Right, left, slightly down and up. When it is at its highest point, which is about 30-35 degrees from our point of view and is still moving slowly upwards, it disappears like turning off a switch and does not return, even if we stand and look for a while time. There were no clouds in the sky where the light was and nothing to cover its light. On our walk home we saw several airplanes flying to the east, and the light in no way resembled these airplanes, nor stars, which were now more visible in the sky. When we went out to the observation site in daylight, we saw that there was a house by the nearby trees, and there were electricity pylons with wires connected between them, which sloped over the field. The electrical wires were in the field of vision where we spotted the light phenomenon. We reacted quite calmly and jokingly at first, but after 10-20 sec. we both got the feeling that this was not quite normal. When the light disappeared with one, we were both very surprised. The light was slightly larger than a star, round and whitish, yellow/orange and with a faint red glow. The colors blended more into each other than being defined.

It looked like four stars. Luminous entities, appearing first two, then the others, fairly gathered as a flock and flew away together - fast, too far away to be from the same object, moving too independently to be the same. no light cones.

Standing and looking north for an airplane - out of the corner of my eye to the left (to the west), I see a light coming - I think it's the start of a shooting star. When I look more closely at it, I see that it is round and dark and at the same time luminous. It changed neither color nor shape and flew in a straight line, at the same speed to the east and disappeared.

For many years I have thought back to the night when I saw this, which I have not been able to explain in any way. By writing this, I hope to get some sort of clarification on whether others may have experienced something similar. One evening I was on my way home from work (on foot because my bike was flat). I saw in the sky three very bright stars that I did not remember seeing before, in exactly this pattern, like an isosceles triangle. I'm no star expert though, so I didn't think much more of it. However, it puzzled me (and really unsettled me) that an equally bright star moved from the lower right star to the lower left star, up to the upper star, and then started over; down to the lower right star, etc. This went on for several minutes as I tried to figure out what could possibly be moving that fast. Since these lights looked exactly like bright stars, they must (in my mind) be moving at thousands of kilometers per hour to get around so fast and make such sharp "turns". Finally, the star moved quickly away in an uneven path and with a speed that varied greatly and suddenly, before disappearing completely.

On the way home along the Sindallund path, I tell my wife that it is a strange blue/blue-green color "Venus" has tonight. We both look at "Venus", which remains in the same position and retains its color for 4-5 minutes. Suddenly it turns red and moves at quite a high speed to the southwest and disappears. A few minutes later, the object appears in the same color and in the same position as the first time we saw it. We were now home and I rushed up and out onto our balcony to see if I could see anything in my telescope, but then the object was gone.
Sitting on a daily basis in an office in a basement, where we have a camera installed for security reasons. This camera is a night vision camera that records as soon as it detects sound/motion.

I came driving from Struer towards Thisted at 5 o'clock in the morning. It was cloudy and there were no stars to be seen. I had probably driven approx. 20 minutes (it must have been near Hurup), when I spotted 2 blue-white lights far out in front of the car (several km. away). They moved around the sky, almost dancing, independently of each other, but all the time with approximately the same distance between them. They moved at varying speeds. I watched them during my drive for approx. a quarter of an hour, after which they disappeared to the east at high speed. The lights looked like stars at first glance, but they shone somewhat brighter. I have thought about whether it might have been laser light, but I think that seems unlikely as it was at 5 in the morning, besides, the way they disappeared didn't look like laser light.

There are often quite a few helicopters in Esbjerg in the evening. Last night it was almost starry, which is a rare sight in Esbjerg. A circular light appeared in the night sky, like an airplane/helicopter. Right after this there was again a circular light as if there was a new helicopter/plane close behind this and another one behind this spot. Then there were 3 spots of light, powerful as airplane lights. Then they disappeared with one and changed direction and went down (still 3 spots) then they changed direction and went up and then they disappeared with one. It didn't look like a laser show. The phenomenon was easy to see, as there is a good dark night sky outside Esbjerg when there are no clouds.

Three yellowish/orange powerful lights in an equilateral triangle, with the point downwards, with a large distance between them. Observation is also done with binoculars, as this was brought after the theater trip (Grønnegårdsteateret). With binoculars it is difficult to focus because of the distance. The lights moved in the same direction (to the north) for approx. 8 min., after which the top left light disappeared first, then the bottom and finally the top right. Then a fourth appears, in unison, moving in the same direction as the three that just disappeared. But this light accelerates unnaturally strongly as it disappeared.

I live in such a way that I have a view of the Limfjord and the whole of Aalborg. I sense that it is far out on the other side of Aalborg. What I observe is my first thought that it is a star, but wonder that it is just above the horizon. Then think of a plane, but it is not, because it moves with a very violent speed. It moves in a straight line over the city. As it is right next to me, it rises from 20 degrees to approx. 50-60 degrees, and it happens so fast that a pilot will not survive the G press, it makes some movements on the way up, stands still for a few seconds, moves down in the same way and continues its straight line and disappears.

I must regret that I did not note down the day and exact time, but the sighting took place 2-3 weeks ago and has puzzled me ever since. It was afternoon and sunny weather and I had laid down on my back on our buried sea trampoline to dry off after a dip in our garden basin/pool, so I was lying looking straight up into the blue sky. It was a clear day with a few clouds on the horizon, but the area I looked up into was completely cloudless and there was only a very light wind (at least at the ground where I was). A flock of birds had just flown by (they were not flying in formation) and shortly after they had passed I spotted a circular object in shades of gray flying high in the sky at a very high speed in the south-east or east-south -Eastern direction (by the way, in almost the same direction as the birds had flown shortly before, although they were at a much lower altitude). The object's flight path went almost directly over where I was lying, although a little further to the northeast as it was closest, so not quite 90 degrees above the horizon where I was lying, but close. So I saw the object almost directly from below, and from that angle it looked like a perfectly round "plate". The colors were in shades of grey, and even though it was a perfectly clear day I would describe it as a bit hazy or surrounded by a faint haze, so it was dull and not reflective. It can be difficult to judge altitude and speed from the ground, but I would compare altitude and speed across the sky to that of a high-speed airliner, if not a bit faster. The direction of flight was constant except for two sudden, small, sideways "jerks", so the movement pattern definitely deviated from that of an airplane. The only natural explanation I can come up with would have to be a gray weather balloon which was in a particularly windy and slightly turbulent air layer high up. The reason I'm reporting here, however, is that I don't really think it looked like a weather balloon, and I'm particularly having trouble getting the speed it flew at to be consistent with a balloon. I had it in sight for 20-30 seconds max, so shorter than I could have reached to get a camera before it was gone in an east-south-east direction. For the record, I had not consumed alcohol (which, by the way, I only do rarely and in extremely controlled quantities), and I had neither sunstroke nor the sun in my eyes.

That night, my then-girlfriend Louise and I went up to the city to buy cigarettes. We hadn't gone more than 200 meters when we spotted the object in the sky. I can't remember which one of us saw it first but we couldn't hear any kind of mechanical sound, like an airplane, helicopter ect. There were 3 very orange lights in the sky, like the rattle of an orange. My first impression was that it was some new Chinese "firework" that consists of a form of cardboard/paper that is about 40 cm in width and length and a meter in height. You light a light inside and it can float up to 100 meters into the air. I had seen such "fireworks" New Year 2009/10. But after just a few seconds, I could see that the speed of the object, the synchronization between the lights and the lightest constant sharpness (stability) made it impossible to be what I first thought, as the fireworks light is easily affected by wind and floats much slower. The object flew on over one of the residential buildings on kastanievej towards Sdr. Boulevard in a N/NW direction. We were going the same way and had barely 150-200 meters up to Sdr.Boulevard, so we went up there at a very fast pace to be able to follow the UFO, and we lost sight of it for 10-15 seconds when it flew over the residential building on Chestnut road. When we got up to Sdr. Boulevard we are facing Ansgar facility (a park), and I had expected a good view to be able to observe the vessel some more, but it was gone. As it was autumn and the leaves on the trees had started to fall, I was a bit surprised that it was now out of sight and remained so for the rest of our trip. The time, place and direction of the vessel is very correct as Louise sent a message to a mutual friend immediately after we had seen the object. That text message is dated 10 Oct. 2010 at 03:38, and I have lived here for 12 years so know the place and directions to the 4 corners of the world as well as you know the value of 100 kroner.

Looking at 23.20 3-4 flashes of light, the size of which is 2-3 times larger than the star Arcturus, but roughly the same brightness. The flashes are seen in a point which I would describe as a right-angled triangle to the south with the star Arcturus and the largest star in the Northern Crown as the fixed points. Duration total 1-2 sec. At 23.29 1 glimpse is seen, a little lower in the sky and a little further to the south than that point at 23.20. This flash is short-lived, but of the same size and brightness.

My 2 sons and I come by car driving down the hill between Måløv Byvej and Ballerup Byvej on a Saturday evening, when we suddenly spot 8 very large, round blue objects, which are spaced equally apart. We began to slow down and focus only on the objects that were completely inexplicable. Other cars almost stopped completely, and one pulled over to the side of the road on Ballerup Byvej. On the road, there are 2 gas stations next to each other, and we chose to drive into one to stop. I mean we pulled up to a Shell tank and there were 3 other cars where the passengers got out and pointed to the sky. A taxi driver stood outside with a mobile phone and called. The 8 huge blue balls of light stood completely still in the air. It felt like they were looking at us and at the same time were completely silent. My children and I were completely stunned and could not say anything. My youngest son, who was 6 years old at the time, was hanging out of the window and pointing up. All I said was for him to stay in the car. My whole body was shaking, it was the most scarry thing I have ever experienced. We were very close to the bullets at that time. The 8 balls of light were distributed in such a way that 4 of them went from the ground and slanted upwards, while the other 4 went on slanting vertically upwards towards the sky very high up. I think we stood and watched for a few minutes when suddenly all 8 of them started driving into each other at a very high speed. So fast that you couldn't follow them. And then one by one they disappeared like ping.. ping without any noise at all. All 3 of us were totally out of it, it was very surreal and unfortunately in our wonder and anxiety about it we didn't really get to talk to some of the other witnesses. However, the taxi driver said what it was and I answered a UFO. But it was as if no one dared to admit, they were convinced that it was a UFO... or rather 8 UFOs in the same place. What we saw was both very beautiful, but also shocking. The experience is still with us, and sometimes we still talk about the inexplicable balls of light. Tried telling others about the incident but like people make fun of it. So have tried to repress it, but now I finally get to tell and write it.. and it's a bit of a relief. Hope you can use it for something :-)

Sunday 27 March at approx. 23.50 I went out on our south-facing terrace to get some fresh air and look at the beautiful starry sky. I spot a plane - I think at first, because it flashes red - but when I had been looking at it for approx. 5 minutes the object had not moved. I now go in and get binoculars (a regular bird binocular) and see that there are 2 more objects flashing in the same way in red, green and yellow colors in the southwest/western sky. When I went out here at At 0.30 the objects were still in the sky and they are still there. They don't seem to have moved but are still flashing very clearly in multiple colors. Can someone explain what this could be. Is it the moon's (almost full moon) rays that give the colors or what could it be.

I was sitting on my terrace and saw a flying thing across the night sky. I don't know what it was, but it was an amazing sight. It flew across the sky at slow speed. It was neither a salellit nor a plane. I have never seen anything like that. Hope someone might be interested in this information.

properties.Colors: den største let rødlig, den mindre gullighvid
properties.content: As so often when I get home from work, I sit in my good chair to relax with minimal light in the living room. At the moment it is starry in the evening and I enjoy looking at the stars and moon to the west. Has a wide view over open areas and lots of sky to the southwest, west and north to the Helsingør motorway. Yesterday I saw something that I first thought was a small and large star. The little one was approx. at 11 compared to the big one. They stood still at first, but then they moved - I think - within a short time - maybe less than 1/2 hour right down to the horizon to the west, and disappeared. I was a bit puzzled - it didn't look like an airplane and there were no flashing/red lights. When I went home from work in Herlev today, I heard a small group of people talking about the lights, they were locals who had observed the same lights, but couldn't see them for so long as they lived down in the city. But obviously there has been something. In these times, one could of course think that these are military exercises from the Danish defence. But don't all planes including helicopters usually have flashing lights/red lights? These 2 luminous round things looked like a big and a small star....but the earth doesn't spin that fast...or what? Has anyone else seen anything? Will be happy for a feedback. 😊

Went to walk the dog in the garden. Noticed a very bright "star" in the southern sky. The star was in the same place for the first 15 minutes I saw it. Suddenly it became weaker in the light, approx. half strength and it began to move eastward. After moving in a straight line to the east, approx. 20 degrees, the light disappeared completely. This movement took approx. 10 sec.

My Great-grandfather told me on New Year's Eve that he and his friend were out for a walk in Ålsgårde on Saturday 17 July 1982, and when they had reached the station, my great-grandfather saw a very bright and red light up in the air. My great grandfather told his friend that it couldn't be a plane, but they couldn't figure out what it was. My great grandfather saw a man walking with a camera in his hand and my great grandfather told the man to hurry up and take a picture. Just as the man had switched on his camera, the red light faded to purple. My great-grandfather does not know anything about the man with the camera today, but only knows that on the night when the light was there, the man was approx. 20-30 years. I asked my great grandfather if we could tell his friend about it, but unfortunately his friend died in 2005 of lung cancer. My great-grandfather is 98 years old today.
Changed from 2 lights to 4 lights with yellow wings, stood still so it approx. 15 minutes
A luminous (in orange red and luminous glow) figure passed silently in the sky with no sound at all.

We saw the light and are now convinced that we are not alone in this universe and that they are closer than we know. This orange/yellow burning glow of a round ball of light. Flew quietly over the sky, danced for a few minutes in the sky.

A total of 5 objects in almost the same trajectory from south to northeast. First 1 in normal satellite size and speed, but with yellowish color, which disappeared 60 degrees above the horizon. Then number 2 approx. 60 degrees above the horizon from the south with a golden color and significantly larger and stronger light than the clearest planets. Number 3 is a small dot (normal satellite size) which appears to continue obliquely from number 2. At the same time, numbers 4 and 5 appear, equally bright as number 2, in the same orbit from the south, perhaps 30 and 40 degrees above the horizon . My wife and I watch the big 3 at the same time until the first one disappears approx. 90 degrees up, while the last 2 disappear a little later at a height of 70-80 degrees above the southern horizon. Both the orbit and speed make it most likely that this was a larger satellite that had been torn into several pieces at an earlier time during the first encounter with the atmosphere, and then burned up slowly while maintaining the original orbit.

At approx. 16.30 on 23/04/2009 my son calls. He is standing out in his garden looking at a strange phenomenon through his binoculars. I quickly grab my own binoculars and rush outside. With a cell phone in one hand and binoculars in the other, I get instructions from my son on where to find the phenomenon. I can't see it with the naked eye and search with binoculars. The sky is blue and almost cloudless. After a few misunderstandings about east and west, I get a milky white object in the binoculars. Approx. at 8 and at 5 at a short distance from the milky white object, there are two slightly smaller objects with a metallic shine. The small objects do not stand still, but seem "nervous". The small object, standing approx. at 8, makes a sudden movement towards the large object and back again. Almost like a jump. Back and forth in less than a second. A few seconds later, the two small objects disappear so quickly that I have no precise sense of direction. Maybe to the northwest. The large object remains standing. It is high in the sky to the north, about 70-80 degrees up. The sun is low to the left (west, southwest), and it fits with the object being illuminated by the sun. After observing the object for approx. 5 minutes without any movement or activity, we call it off, as it is a bit difficult with only one hand to hold the binoculars for that long. We agree that we will be called later. After a few more minutes, the object begins to move slowly to the south, i.e. even higher in the sky. I lay down on the lawn with the binoculars to keep it more stable. The movement is slow, and after a short pause it begins to move slightly to the south-southwest (toward the sun). Then the object turns sharply to the northwest (a turn of approx. 110-120 degrees). The speed is still slow, but it does not turn in an arc, but in a "break" without changing the speed. Suddenly the object is gone. I don't see the direction, it's just gone. After searching the area of the sky where it disappeared for approx. 5 min., I give up finding it again. Our son calls again. He has also lost sight of the object. If I were to judge the size of the object, I would compare it to when I see an airliner flying across the sky at a high altitude. I had approx. the same tremors in the binoculars due to the distance, so the sensation was that the object was the size of an airliner. I will also say that the object was quite clear in binoculars and there were no fins or anything protruding from the object. It was completely smooth. Once I knew exactly where it was in the sky, I could also see it with the naked eye. I sensed at first that it was a spherical object, but as I observed the object, it initially changed shape slightly. as if it occasionally became more elliptical in shape. I therefore began to sense that I was seeing a domed underside of an object that was not spherical. The observation took place in Horsens South and for me lasted approx. 15 minutes It gave an unusually strange sensation to see such an object in daylight. I am used to seeing many strange light phenomena at night, as I have two reflecting telescopes, one large and one small portable. I have also often seen many different planes at different heights and distances with my binoculars. It sure wasn't a plane, a balloon, a helicopter, or anything else I've seen before. The two small objects I caught a glimpse of were also highly unusual. Especially their very sudden movements and completely different way of shining. As if they themselves shone or were completely shiny and made of metal, whereas the large object was milky white and illuminated by the sun.

I am often up at night because of pain and I often stand in our kitchen on the 3rd floor and look out at the sky. From our kitchen there is a good view and there is not very much light pollution. I stand and lean my head against the window while I look up at the Carlsvogn. Suddenly there is a mass of white lights rushing across the sky, over my head and over the house. It all happens incredibly fast and I rush to the window facing the other way, but there is nothing to see. My first thought when I saw the white lights was that it was strange that there were lights on those birds. I think there were about 10-12 white lights in a triangle 🔽 with the wide side first. There was no sound and it went faster than the planes we usually see.

I clearly remember playing in the living room on Glentevej in Odense. I looked out the open French balcony door on the first floor, beyond Odense N and Rising school. Up there I saw an elongated brownish/grayish/silvery cigar-shaped thing slowly sliding across the sky. As so often in those years, at first I thought it was the usual airship. The distance to the object was very far away and I could not directly identify it as an airship. I followed it for a few minutes and also saw a jet or other aircraft pulling contrails in the same direction, and this aircraft was significantly faster than the "cigar". But it was only when something strange happened that I thought it must be something else, namely what I then called a rocket. The object simply changed direction and suddenly stood upright before shooting upwards. This is when I called my mother, I was only 6 or 5 years old at the time, and showed her what it was and explained the matter to her. A relatively short time after the object began an ascent, it disappeared and we could not see it thereafter. As I recall, the object left a trail of smoke, which was the immediate reason I saw this as a rocket. I have subsequently, as I have grown older, searched for others who have seen the object, and believe I have found a similar description from the same area, however I cannot remember exactly where I found this, but believe it was on the internet for a some years ago. I very much doubt that this was not a UFO in and of itself, I was far too young at the time to have seen and heard about the phenomenon, and there has been no other explanation for the sighting until now. I had been watching television at the time and had followed the moon landing and the Apollo program on television. I'm not entirely sure of the year and direction, but I know exactly where and in which direction I looked, so I can find the exact data via map if it's interesting. A little old, but still an interesting and still, for me, inexplicable incident.

I just followed my girlfriend out the door this morning when she wanted to go home. I live in a place where all outdoor lights are turned off at midnight, so there is no light pollution. I open the door, my boyfriend walks out, and my eye catches something in the sky. Looking up and saying look honey, where my girlfriend at the same moment exclaims, what the hell is that?! We see a missile like object coming from the north direction, flying in a south direction at a speed we have never experienced before. There is no sound at all. We just see this missile, with a tail of fire behind it, which in the sky is about 7-8 cm. long with fire behind him. We both say what the hell was that? We talked for a bit and agreed that it might be a fireball or something. We have both seen shooting stars and this cannot be compared at all. If others have seen the same object, we would very much like to know. We saw it over Sakskøbing and think it could have been seen elsewhere too, as the weather is clear and starry. It came from almost due north and flew almost due south. The object had a trail of fire behind it and no sound. It was very high up in the sky, but approx. 7-8 cm. long, including the tail of fire.

I had to go out to feed my horses, so I just took the dog with me so he could pee. The horses are in our stable here at home. When I go around there it is dark, so therefore I know that there was nothing when I entered the barn. I leave the door open while I arrange their feed, 10 buckets to be mixed and the scale teases. I go straight in to exchange weights and when I come back I see out of the corner of my eye that there is some light over the neighbor's road right by our horse paddock. My first thought was that it was probably the neighbor who was sitting and talking on the phone in the car, he thought he had come while I was inside to change the scales. While I arrange fodder and the horses are fed, I look out in between and think that it is strange that he is standing there and the car is switched off. I look a little further and see that it is not his car as the outline is much larger, so my next thought is that it must be the tractor. Can hear my dog running around and beeping. I call her as I think she has seen the neighbor and she is not going to run over there. She comes into the barn and is all crazy and I send her out again when I'm done. Then looks again and can see that one light is somewhat larger than the other, and it is the red one, and can see that it is not a tractor, but something larger. I turn off the light as I'm a bit curious about what the neighbor is doing and think I can see it better with the light off. When I go out, I see my dog sitting completely frozen, and he is looking over there. She usually barks and runs around, so weird behavior. I look over there again and now it's up in the air. I get to thinking what the hell is that, there is no sound at all. I rummage through all my pockets for my phone as I want to film it. Unfortunately discovers that I have put on my boyfriend's jacket, so no phone. I get a little scared as I can't see or describe what it is I see and it doesn't make any sense in my head. It flies away quietly and I can only see the red light. It rises quietly and flies diagonally over towards the motorway in a southerly direction.

Looking out my window and seeing this very red circle and it's not Venus or Mars because the circle was too big for that and it moved from side to side and the light got dimmer and brighter and it disappeared very quickly in East.

When I arrived at my workplace and walked towards our entrance and looked up into the sky, I saw a bright green fairly large dot of light 400m up, out over the sea. Next to the dot there were 2-3 green dots, which shone very faintly... It wasn't fireworks or an airplane etc.. When I looked extra hard it moved to the north, and with a split second was gone again. I wonder what it was. Unfortunately, I was the only one who saw this strange object.. My hope is that there are others besides me who have had a similar experience...

I was at Smukfest at 10'øren with some friends, where two of our friends notice some different light in the sky. We see two distinct points of light, larger than the stars in the sky, which are synchronously moving in a north/west direction. In the sky they did not move more than a few centimeters apart. Along the way, they circulate from each other and back again before disappearing in a hurry. It was hard to judge the speed, but it was somewhat faster than a scheduled airliner. It was difficult to tell the height as we were standing almost directly under the observation. But it was far higher up than what the light from the stage show emitted. A group behind us also noticed the incident.

On the 12th of August in the evening, we sat out in the garden and watched for shooting stars, which were supposed to come in a north-easterly direction, but they all came from other places. Suddenly I saw a distinctive round orange bright light in the sky in the northwest for approx. 30 degrees height, which zigzagged up and down at slow speed. Called my wife who thought it was probably an emergency flare, but I said no to that as I am a former sailor. Then it disappeared.

Three kinds of balloon-like objects that flew/hovered in formation!! The formation looked like a perfect right triangle. Each object appears to "rotate" on its own axis. Distance to the flying object is estimated to be around 100 metres. The size of the objects is estimated to be around the size of an ordinary "party balloon". The second witness estimated the size to be different from a balloon. Although balloons have been written about, the objects do not seem to have their precise character. This is judged from the fact that they were floating in a perfectly right-angled formation. In addition, the formation moved with a significantly higher speed and directional focus than ordinary balloons. The distance between the objects is estimated to be between 10 and 20 meters, and of course there was nothing visible that "connected" or fixed the objects to each other. In addition, the formation seemed to rotate slightly throughout the observation. However, as mentioned before, the distance between the objects seems to remain constant, which is why this observation is being reported. No sound associated with the object was observed. However, it must be added that the intersection where the UFO was seen is a busy place, which may have drowned out the object's possible sound emission.

On Monday 25 July I saw something similar to UFOs you see in magazines etc. This happened in Munkebo, Denmark approx. at 10.30 p.m. I was walking the dog in the evening and suddenly saw something that I first thought was a helicopter just above a step by the road I was walking on. There were bright lights in front and on both sides, but I didn't hear a sound, it was completely silent. Then the lights went out and I saw that there was no rotor above, or anything below the body. It hung in the air for quite a while, and then it moved towards the center of Munkebo without a sound before it disappeared behind some trees. The color looked to me to be dark grey, and it could be approx. 5 meters wide in diameter.

Cycle to work along Strandvejen every morning. This morning I see an object high above the water, at Espergærde beach. It is completely cloudless and full sun. I observe the object for a few minutes and laugh a little to myself that it looks like a UFO. Starts cycling again and can see that the sun is reflected by the object. It catches my attention as it is clearly a metal. I take out my phone to take a picture and poof it's gone. The object was completely still in the air and I believe it was about 300m up in the air. It was round/oval in shape, actually very classic UFO looking.

I went to soccer practice with my son, and as always I have my camera with me, I take a lot of photos. I took quite a few pictures and when I was about to file and edit them I noticed something strange, in one picture there was what I thought was a ball flying through the air but when I looked closer it was behind some tall bushes and it had a red ring around it. At first I thought the red ring might be some kind of error in the image, but it is not due to any error that I can identify. It seems mysterious to me, I can't see what it could be.

I'm sitting on my couch when I randomly spot a luminous object in the sky. It moves slowly and I've never seen anything like it before. It disappeared into thin air as I watched, and it certainly didn't look like an airplane or a star. I never believed in UFOs before, but as soon as I saw it, I had no doubt that it could only be something like that. Can pinpoint exactly where in the sky it was, just don't understand compass direction....
When my husband and I are out for an evening walk, we see a bright light that can be seen at a little above roof height and quickly disappears in the sky. It didn't last more than a few seconds.

A strong light pulse of approx. 1 sec followed by a small flash after a few seconds, the sequence repeated 6-7 times with approx. 10 sec. gap before it disappeared to the east. Either a plane with abnormal light guidance or a satellite that rotated 1 time per 10 sec. - the brightness and the orbit could match the satellites I sometimes see.

It surprised me that a "star" was in front of the cloud in the blue night sky. The small white dot of light looked like an ordinary star, standing completely still in the sky. Suddenly the dot began to move vertically down and then turned sharply to the right and continued for a distance, after which the dot again turned sharply vertically down until the dot disappeared from view behind a tree. It went quite fast and the light got stronger as it started to move. There was no sound and the speed was fast compared to a plane at this distance. The movement was vertical/horizontal zig-zag. Would like to hear if others have observed the same thing, who can give an explanation of what it was we saw.

Three UFOs in a triangle formation, one in front and two behind, flew over my balcony, directly above my head, parallel to my residential property at 1.03 at night, heading towards ØzS. They flew in a straight line and held the formation for approx. 5 seconds, after which the formation disintegrated and they sort of clumped together a bit, turned a bit south and suddenly disappeared.

Walking on the way home from an evening of dinner and fun with friends. I walked alone on Voldvej to the west, towards Engstrupgårdsvej in Hvidovre. I look to the sky because I think there are an unusually large number of bright stars that are grouped together too closely to be stars. 10-20 strong reddish points of light, each looked like Jupiter or Mars at their brightest and appeared somewhat larger, perhaps twice as large. The height of the lower ones was just above the rooftops in front, probably 10 degrees or thereabouts, the highest ones maybe 30 degrees up. The distance was hard to judge, probably quite far away. No sound or movement. After a few minutes of observation, they disappeared one by one. At first I thought it was fireworks, a rocket, many flares or similar, but all the points remained completely stationary and the brightness did not vary at all, nor did the sounds of explosions. distribution in the pattern, only with significantly more and much stronger and larger reddish points of light.. They disappeared as mentioned above, one by one without a sound or variation in color, just "turned off"...

I was on my way home by car. It is cloudy and has rained quite a bit and no stars are visible. As I get to the top of the hill on which the city sits, I see what I think is an aviator. I stop and roll down the window, because it flies low and much slower than the planes. It also does not light up green and red, but only orange. There is no sound. It just floats by silently. I recorded it on video, but the quality is not good at night. Think it must have been a meteor or similar, but still think it was moving too slowly for that.

On 27/2/21 I drove north on the Helsingør motorway. Approx. near Hørsholm, I saw a very large ball of light coming at great speed across the sky from the NW. It was definitely not a plane or a shooting star. Pretty quickly I saw that it was heading straight for me - and the highway, and I sat and tried to figure out how to avoid it. Fortunately, it was not necessary, because it stopped directly above the motorway, slightly in front of me, so that I could now see it from the side - to the north. The light was turned off and there were only 2 very small lights, the rest was dark. I passed under it and couldn't spot it in the rear view mirror as I also had to keep an eye on where I was driving.

Have been enjoying the rising and almost full moon on a bench for a while and get on the bike and cycle home north on the path along the coast north of Egå Marina. Looking up at the Moon to the right as I cycle in the dark, but another phenomenon in motion catches my eye. An apparently round and completely silent orange light I detect to the north at an angle higher than 45 degrees moving directly towards the Moon, which is exactly in the east. The size, color and speed of the object is such that it arouses my interest even more, but I cycle in almost total darkness and have to concentrate a bit on seeing the path and choose to pass a short piece of forest of approx. 100 meters and then stop and follow the light after the piece of wood, expecting to see it "under" the Moon after the piece of wood, but now it's just gone!!! The following is a little hard to judge, but I would think that the orange light is the same dull color as a street lamp might be and quite a bit larger than the largest visible planets and quite a bit smaller than the Moon. Best guess for size and speed I can describe like this: 30 times bigger than a light from an airplane and 50 times smaller than the Moon and with a constant orange light. I have to describe the speed as much faster than a charter plane and much slower than a shooting star - and completely silent... What annoys me the most now is that I don't just stop and follow the light until it disappears or immediately find the mobile phone forth and films - just as I am quick to do when it e.g. is a squirrel in my hazel tree, stealing my hazelnuts and burying them in the lawn. It's just like I deny these experiences in heaven as something that didn't happen and I think I go into a state of shock/paralysis, but afterwards I'm - like now - disappointed and annoyed with my own reaction or lack of together.... Am I alone in this experience? Otherwise, just write your observation of the same and, please, what happened to the orange light when passing the Moon, which it had the exact direction towards, when I absolutely had to cycle through the 10 second piece of forest... Did it burn out or did it land on the moon or what? Hope others can contribute - thanks!
We were driving home by car and saw what looked like a very powerful shooting star disappearing very low over the horizon. Could it have been a meteor?

My sister-in-law opens the patio door as we have just come home from some jazz music. The time is approx. 22.38 and she says that something strange is flying in the sky just above. I look out into the open and see a strange object approx. 250 meters up approach the house. It flies directly west/east. The house is located exactly west/east. It is now twilight. The object is the same size as the cabin of a 2-person helicopter. It is elliptical, almost in the shape of a baseball and black-grey-metallic in color and without destinations. In front, a bright orange/red light flashes with a regular frequency, like the blinker on a car. It moves parallel to Kamstrupvej on the garden side of the houses with odd numbers. The speed is approx. 40-45 km. in class. Quickly, the object above my plot is right above and passes out towards Tårnvej and Copenhagen. There is absolutely no sound associated with the item. Just after it has passed, the red/orange light is no longer visible. The object is still visible, but already 10-15 sec. after the passage, difficult to see in the twilight. The wind speed was 0-2 meters per second and it was cloudy. Additional comments: I have never seen that type of light anywhere before and never in connection with anything technical. It is a light that you clearly remember. The object flew without slings in the roller and did not rotate. It followed like a stretched line. It looked like it was just passing the area and there was a clear destination ahead

Just came cycling from driver's license theory (cycling along with ass to the north) on a mostly cloudless cool evening, and happened to look up at the sky and saw what I thought was a glider at first as there was no steam/smoke trail behind it , but then I noticed that it had a slightly special shape. It was shaped a bit like a large m, except that it was of course closed at the bottom (looked to the left). I then chose to cycle on, and then had to go around a left-hand bend, and then stopped again (looked left again), then I saw it from behind, and there it was just a small white dot in the sky and almost looked like a star . Then no more than 10-15 seconds passed and then it was gone. I've always been skeptical of anything like that, but today I had my doubts.

I came in by train from Vesløs and got off in Vust. My motorcycle was parked at the Station building. As I pulled the motorcycle out to the road, suddenly a cigar-like object came directly above me. It was a very bright light - oval windows on both sides of the object. There was a hissing sound from the object which hung right above me for about 3-5 minutes. I tried to start the motorcycle but there was no ignition at all. Suddenly the light went out again and the hissing sound disappeared - towards the north (towards Fjerritslev, when I was standing at the Station building in Vust). As soon as the light and sound went away, the motorcycle started immediately when I stepped on the starter. The motorcycle was an NSU 125 cubic. Which I bought when I turned 18 and had just got my driver's license. At that time I was working for a farm owner in Thorup Holme. I have tried to explain to my family what I saw and was exposed to, but most shrug their shoulders and cannot understand the episode. Shortly after the experience, I drove the tractor past the Station building, and I have never had any doubts about my experience. For approx. 4 months ago I drove with my friend and her parents past the Station building and everything was still, as I experienced on the night of 31/12/1964 - I had at that time visited my girlfriend in Vesløs, and we had not drunk anything, so I was 100% sober.

Last night 21/5-20 at At 22.15 a very clear "big star" was observed. I live on Ore beach approx. 2 km. west of Vordingborg. The observation started at about 10.10 p.m., when the object appeared in the night sky to the west (i.e. in the direction from Southern Langelandsbælt and the Småland Sea and moving in a rather easterly direction. The object was clearly visible for about 10/12 min., and a speed that was somewhat faster is assumed than an airplane. The height could be similar to that of a passenger plane, but there was 100% NO ENGINE NOISE (WIND QUIET) AND NO RED/GREEN NAVIGATION LIGHTS AND NO WHITE FLASHING LIGHTS. The object was equally clear from the front/sides and the back. It was PERFECT DEFINITELY not an airplane. But what could it be??? Several people have observed the object in the last few evenings at the same time/same route etc.

Here at 01:35 on Sunday night I saw something that seems a little strange. Hope you can answer what it might be. I'm looking at a satellite, I think. It flies to the southwest, then suddenly changes direction to the southeast. I was on that flightrader24 to see if it could be a plane and there was no one around. My question is. A satellite it flies in the same orbit it does not. What else could it be.

Vestergade is a steep hill that runs from Struer's torv to Holstebrovej. At the top of the street, Skolegade turns right. My friend and I were riding our mopeds up Vestergade from Torvet, when we spotted a large cigar-shaped object hanging over the street where Skolegade turns to the right. As we approached we could see that the object was circular and appeared to be flat. It hung motionless maybe 50 meters up and it was completely silent. It was like looking up at a flat lamp that glowed white-yellow. But the strange thing was that there was no visible light from it on the street. There were no details, just a flat white-yellow round disc, which we estimated to be at least 25 meters in diameter, but could easily have been twice that. When we got all the way up under the object, it began - still silently - to move slowly across Skolegade, and we naturally followed. But then it moved diagonally across the school towards Bjerggade, which runs parallel to Vestergade. Bjerggade has the same curved shape as Vestergade and also begins at Torvet and ends at Holstebrovej. But Bjergade has a slope on the right-hand side (when coming from Torvet) that goes down to Struer bay. When we almost reach Bjerggade, the object suddenly moves away with a speed that in a flash moves it beyond the summer house town of Bremdal, approx. one kilometer as the crow flies on the other side of Struer Bay. There it hangs again quietly for some time, after which it simply disappears. When we were talking the next day with a friend who lived on the corner at Bjergade, he told us that the night before he had seen something strange over the rooftops from the house's yard. Hence the additional witness in brackets. As I am now 70 years old, I think it is best to share my observation with you before it is lost. I was born in 1948 in the small village of Everdrup, halfway between Næstved and Præstø. When I was in the 4th grade, I entered a private school in Næstved, which is why I had to cycle to a small village Bøgesø and from there take the train to Næstved. On the road from Bøgesø to Everdrup there is a long, small settlement Flintemose and some forest, and after the 2 locations there is a free stretch with a long, steep hill, which everyone, adults and children, pulled their bikes up. The road is called Flintemosevej. A summer day in August or September 1959, on the way home from school, approx. at 14.45 plus/minus ½ hour, I thus pulled my bike up that hill. It was a lovely summer day without a cloud in the sky. When I had reached 2/3 up the hill, I looked back and saw some of my mates who had just arrived at the foot of the hill and were getting off their bikes. Approx. 15 sec. later I absentmindedly looked up at the sky to the north and suddenly saw a giant pipe in the sky. It was completely shiny and completely smooth without any openings etc. protrusion to see. The ends were blunt, and it seems to me that the ends were a little narrower than the middle. There were no sounds to be heard from it, and there was no smoke or electricity. fire out of the object. I looked at the object for 2-3-4 seconds, then turned my head to see if my companions had seen it too, but apparently they hadn't, so I quickly turned my head back and looked up at the sky again - but now the object was gone! I looked all over the sky, but there was no sign of it in the completely cloudless sky. And there were no other things to see either. It is obviously difficult to judge the size of the object as there was nothing in the sky to compare it to, but from how clear and sharp I saw it I would guess it was 3-400m away and as big as 2 jumbo jets. But the size is of course uncertain. However, I perceived it as very large and as a good distance away. Did it fly while I was watching it? I have often thought about that afterwards - but I don't actually know. IF it flew, it came approx. from the east in the longitudinal direction of the object. It had a slightly inclined position in the sky. The sighting probably happened many years ago, but I think I remember it as if it had happened a month ago. I can thus also remember who I follow. told about it, their names and what they answered me. I'm not aware of anyone else seeing it.

Three strange phenomena in the sky. One above us. A larger one in a southern direction and a smaller one in a south/eastern direction. They stand still in the sky for a period of 20 minutes and occasionally move rapidly back and forth. We have tried to photograph with a mobile phone without success. They are still there.
I'm watching TV when I look out the window and see 5 objects in the sky. They are all orange/gold colored. They move quietly across the sky at the same speed. They disappear after 2-3 min.

It was boomerang shaped and there was no light on it. It was moving slowly but only saw it briefly as I didn't have a clear view of the sky. But I'm pretty sure what I saw! Hope there are others who have looked up and seen the same thing last night, as many shooting stars have been predicted??

At approx. 2 on the night of Saturday 21/7 I observe a red-yellow-green flickering light approx. 3 km. from my place of residence in Fraugde with a direction over Odense in a westerly direction. I would estimate the height to be approx. 500 m. The object emits an irregular flashing colored light, like the colors in a prism. At first I thought it must be a helicopter, but the small ones move quickly. which the object did. could not be derived from such. I observe the object for 30 minutes, during which my wife also sees the object "flipping" back and forth in the night sky with changing positions. After that I take my car to drive over towards the object. When I get to a high point close to my estimated position for the object, I climb out to find the light again. Unfortunately I can no longer see anything and want to drive again. Suddenly a white light appears in the sky very close to me (my estimate is about 500 m.) and in the area where I observed the colored light. The white light has the character of a "giant flashlight", where the cone of light is turned from the north and down on me, but not so that the ground was illuminated. I figured now it HAS to be a plane, but as the light is facing me, it is significantly stronger than light from any plane. The light "points" at me for a moment, then turns up and away to the south. Unfortunately, there is no activity at this location at 02.30, so there are no further witnesses to the sighting.
It looked like a star very high up. Moved very quickly. Faster than an airliner, there were no flashing lights. Flew in a straight path from which it zigzagged back and forth. And no sound.
I just saw a black ufo - it was flying fast - but I just managed to see a bit of it. It was quite beautiful!

My friend and I sit out on the balcony late at night and smoke. I sit towards the west as the only one and enjoy a cloudless starry sky. During a conversation I suddenly see 2 white lights moving next to each other from left to right. Almost synchronously... They are approx. 40 degrees in the direction of the west, with approx. 2 finger widths apart, and moves calmly across the sky with a speed reminiscent of normal airplanes. At first I think it's 2 planes, but they're almost too bright and there's no sound at all. Suddenly one changes direction downwards and perhaps to the south, while at the same time it starts to light up VERY strongly! From being something that resembles a large moving star in the sky, it fades to a size that corresponds to a protruding 1 crown! It almost blinds me and still no sound. Its "inflated" size lasts for a little over a second, after which it changes back to its original size. We didn't have time for a camera, the whole thing took approx. 20 seconds. There were no flashing lights, just 2 steady white lights that flashed up and down again in connection with their "dive". The light was perfectly white. No shade of red, yellow or anything. Probably the most beautiful white light I have ever seen. We still find it very very mysterious and amazing to say the least. We are neither pilots nor scientists, but we simply cannot associate the 2 lights with anything we know of or can explain.

Three triangles enter the courtyard from the SSW and disappear to the NE. They flew silently slightly offset (half V-shape) with the same mutual distance and the same constant speed (jet fighter speed). They were edged with blue light and a red light in the middle. Not quite to tell the height above the horizon at the time of disappearance as they faded into thin air.

I stand in the dark and look out of the window to the south, across the road towards Jyllandsringen, where I see two bright lights in the sky. At first I think they are light cones from a car, but they don't stay parallel. So I think it's cones of light from strong flashlights, but the light "dances around" and can't possibly come from flashlights. It looks as if the light is coming from above and not from below the ground. One light revolves around the other, and quickly they both disappear to the south/west. The entire session may last no more than two minutes. I listen to see if I can hear any noise from engines, but there is none.

On the way from Hjørring out of Aalborgvejen, we see several greenish flying boomerang-like coming from south to west in front of us. When we got home, we went out into the garden and also saw one from the same direction.

I've always dreamed of LYING DOWN and looking at the stars, and yesterday I finally got myself together to make it happen. It came up from behind, where I was lying, as a fast dimly glowing orange thing, headed downwards, where it slowed down and approx. 3 meters above the ground, where it slowly disappeared into the night, (never knew before that what others have seen has also been orange, it was only now right here before I got that information, (by reading about it, in this forum), that is, I wasn't colored by other people's experience/opinion about what I saw, by the way I thought it was a bit creepy, lying there alone in the dark, according to my experience), but it wasn't particularly loud/right far away from me, and there was no doubt at all that it was an isolated thing I saw, i.e. no cone of light, I was on a terrace at the height of the 1st floor - I would really like to know if there was others who saw the same thing I saw last night.

I have just seen that the same shining star has come again. The first moves like close and then back, and it is also further now to the south-west, meanwhile there is a new one, which stands diagonally from the first and further to the south-east and has a bright light. Stands still, but moves in between. What is it?

We are three adults standing in the garden smoking while looking at the stars. I say: "See a shooting star". But the object begins to move very quickly in a kind of zig-zag pattern, after which it disappears to the east at a very high speed. All three of us saw it and we agreed that it was no normal object that could move like that.

On 10 November last year (2013), I took 4 pictures of the beautiful sunset from the 4th floor on Gammel Kongevej xxx looking in the direction of the Zoo with my iPhone 5. The pictures were taken in the period from 16:09:17 to 17:09:42. On 4 July 2014, the family sees pictures on the television screen from the iPhone, and here we suddenly discover on the somewhat larger screen a small dot that seems to come flying towards the photographer from the horizon and continues up above the house. When I took the pictures, there was nothing to see in the sky, nor was there any engine noise or anything abnormal. (I have never seen an airplane fly over our house from this direction before). I would be happy if you would look at the pictures, because I think it looks strange at first.

I work as an external craftsman at Haldor Topsøe in Frederikssund on weekdays and arrive at 05.30. At 07.40 I walk north on the factory grounds towards what we call the central workshop when I see a shining white thing to the north-west. It moves to the northeast and then moves back to the northwest at a seemingly steady pace. I wonder and continue along the central workshop, where it is not visible to me as I pass the workshop. When I get past the workshop and out to Linderupvej, I take out my iPhone 12max and film it as it moves back towards the northeast. I will then try to film something with a foreground to be able to judge the size, distance, etc. and put the phone down and want to start over, but when I pick up the phone again it's gone. When I look at the film and take still pictures of it, it shows an elongated cylindrical object with one end rounded and the other end apparently flat. I have no idea of size at all, but in the picture you can see a shadow on the lower half of the thing, so immediately it must have been lower than the sun was out in the east at 07.45 to be able to make the shadow? I think it hung over the fjord.
9 balls of light fly above us, with no sound or other indications that it was a plane or anything else. It was sound light and they fly reasonably fast.

Looking up at the night sky as usual while the dog sniffs. Spotting a reddish light moving straight towards me. Thinking it must be a plane but wondering that the light is reddish and at the same time as it moves towards me I expect the light to change color as it passes me. Notices that the dog's attention is also directed towards the stone, and that at one point it seems to be a little scared.
