Contrary to expectation, the light does not change when passing directly above us, not even as I only see it in the direction of disappearance. Only then do I become aware that there is no engine sound or any other sound for that matter. The dog's hearing is significantly better, and it must have heard something that attracted its attention. I don't think I affected it, the string was completely slack at the moment of sniffing and approx. 5 out.

Sitting in my garden when I see two glowing circles rotating around each other. They fly in a straight line at high speed. Possibly a drone, but the speed and height and the way the two circles were moving didn't seem like a drone.

It was evening. Was out walking with a friend at my secondary school. When he goes in, I stay out for a while. Suddenly I see something. I can't believe my eyes, I see something in the sky that is gray with red dots on it. It hangs almost directly above my head and sounds a bit like a helicopter or a drone, I think it was 3-4 meters wide, and you could almost sense a hum coming from it. I just froze and all of a sudden something weird green came out of it and then it was just gone before. I could manage to blink my eyes.

Last night, at approx. 03.30, I looked out the window and saw that an object stood still in the night sky. There were white and red lights from the object (they did not blink but were constant). In approx. For 6-7 seconds the object maintained its position before it accelerated into space with violent (non-terrestrial) speed. It flew straight up into the air and then disappeared. As a former soldier, I am familiar with various aircraft and types of aircraft, but I have never seen an acceleration like this.

I'm on my way to bed and have to roll down the curtains in the bedroom. Because the sky is starry, I stand and watch the view for a while. I suddenly see an object which is almost plummeting down, albeit slightly to the southeast. It almost looks like something falling to the ground or being dropped and not floating. Fairly large object or maybe not too far away. Can see black/dark outline and on the side to the west the object glows orange ultra briefly, stops, and again glows orange and stops and then disappears behind the rooftops. As I said, it looks like something crashing to the ground. It wasn't a shooting star, satellite or iss. It also had no "tail" behind it. As I said, it went very fast, but looked mysterious.

properties.Remarks: se beretningprojektørlys om talt i BT
properties.content: After an early evening nap.. I woke up after midnight and lacked both milk and tobacco.. so off to the tank, which is just down Roskildevej, where Brandholms Alle starts. My gaze catches 2 pcs. white round .. hmm.. what could look like the field a flashlight makes, in the sky over maybe Danmussøen or even further over kbh. .. hard to assess.. but these 2 light surfaces.. were like chasing each other.. could be exciting and interesting if others observed this.

Many of us stood waiting for a firework display to begin, and we stood looking up at the sky. The weather was clear, and I suddenly spotted 3 orange-red lights flying across the sky at high speed. It is difficult to judge how high they were up, but I would shoot at approx. 10-20 km. In shape they seemed triangular and they followed as if they were in formation next to each other. We followed them for approx. 5-10 seconds, after which the northernmost, in a very sharp turn, turned to the northwest. In a very short time, all three of them disappeared. It looked like they were flying out into the atmosphere at very high speed. There must definitely be more among the approx. 1000 spectators who have seen the same thing, and I can say with certainty that it was not a plane, the speed was too high for that and the change of direction that one made was far too sharp.

At 20, my girlfriend and I saw 6 lights in a V-shaped formation flying silently over our heads. Starry evening, you could see the "disc" blocking light from the stars behind. The craft flew silently and at a constant speed and direction to the west, with no flak or indication of light cones from below or above. Bid on size maybe 2m wide, 20m up.

What I saw that February morning has been playing in my mind ever since. I'm not a guy who believes in EVERYTHING between heaven and earth. I have an open mind and I am not so arrogant to think that we should be the only ones in the entire universe. I sat that morning and enjoyed the light that was growing. I can see the sea and the Hirsholms from my living room window. The sea was almost black and the lower horizon was bright yellow. Above the low yellow horizon was a belt of medium dark clouds, and above that a third belt which was even darker. There was light above. I saw something moving on the horizon. There is a flagpole, so on the fly I thought it was an early flag, or one that hadn't been taken down the day before. But then it hit me. There was absolutely no wind that could make a flag stand completely rectangular. So I go to the window and take a closer look. A rectangle slightly larger than a large flag moved slowly up and down between the light belts I have described. Then slanted up over to the east a few times and then went back to the starting point. Then it went straight up above the 3rd belt and moved in an eastward direction, where it stopped half hidden behind a low-hanging white cloud. It stayed there for a moment, then slowly disappeared. All movements were very slow and it was like watching a large piece of plastic. Sorry I'm not good enough with my PC so I could send a picture seen from my window. But I swear! WHAT I saw WAS something. I do not know what. Maybe a hologram, but in any case not an expression of my imagination. I will always wonder about THAT. I hope that it is a useful input in your work, and I would really like to hear if you have heard of similar incidents.

Saturday 7 July 2012 at 23.07.41 I see from my window, which faces west, a luminous object coming towards me. At first I think it's a plane on fire, but then it gets closer and changes color to orange-red. I manage to get my camera and take a picture of it. It disappears behind some tall buildings and I can no longer see it. It disappears to the south. It follows the firmament. I would say it is round and about the size of a 1/4 full moon as it is directly above me. My camera is a regular little one called Caplio R6 with 7.1x optical wide zoom. I will also send an email with the picture. What have I seen?

Had to walk the dog. Became aware of a light greenish/bluish moving cloud. At first thought it was the Northern Lights, but realized that the cloud was making an exact clockwise circular motion. 6-8 sec. took a turn. Observed the phenomenon for approx. a minute. Run to the wife so she can see it. (She didn't make it). I ran out again. The phenomenon circled 4-6 laps, suddenly stopped due west, and like turning off a light, it just disappeared. I thought it was laser light from a projector until I read Metro-express today 11/15/2010.

I drive my car from Silkeborg to my home in Sejs, and as I turn the corner from Julsøvej onto Borgdalsvej, I see a large glowing "fireball" hanging over the treetops. When I look up at it, it quickly disappears into the sky at a 90 degree angle and disappears. It lasts no more than 4-5 seconds, but I have no idea what it was, only that it was neither the Moon nor a shooting star. I will shoot it to be a few meters in diameter and it moved away again in a flash. It was cloudless and warm that day, so ball lightning also seems unlikely. When I get home 30 sec. later, there is nothing to see in the sky and I rush in and tell my husband. It is inexplicable what it could have been.

Time midnight. My husband and I are on our way home and have just turned onto Bellisvej in Tåsinge. I see 3 red lights at very fast speed disappearing upwards to the southwest. It lasts about 3-5 seconds. There is no sound.

My wife and I went for an evening walk between Venslev and Ferslev. We saw four round but diffuse spots of light that moved several times from a southern direction to an eastern direction and back again. It was partly cloudy. We could see no sign that it was a light source on earth that was thrown into the sky. Disappeared several times and came back. Tried to film with the phone but every time the phone restarted so it didn't work. My wife tried to film with her phone but could not capture it with the phone. Would love to hear if others observed the same.

I saw the beautiful evening sky last night - and just wanted to take a photo with my IPhone from the terrace. We live in a private cooperative housing with 20 semi-detached houses. The roof ridge is approx. 5.5 meters, and I stood approx. 10-12 meters from the neighboring house - and didn't want to include the neighbour's roof in the photo, which is why I "aimed" over their roof - and I don't know how to calculate degrees above the horizon, but would think it is approx. 45 degrees. I didn't notice anything at all when I took the photo - but when I looked at the photo I noticed a black spot. I thought it was probably some dirt on the lens, but couldn't see anything and therefore took a photo inside the living room - and there wasn't a black spot on that photo. Thought "well the bad lens" is obviously gone. So this morning I came to look at the photo again - and suddenly thought that something called "effects" had appeared on my IPhone, among other things. something called a loop - where fractions of seconds before and after the actual photo are included. AND then suddenly I could see that the spot came flying at a very high speed - CAN I POSSIBLY SEND MY PHOTO / LOOP ??

My boyfriend is looking out on the balcony and sees a teardrop-shaped thing flying from east to west. The flying thing shone brightly White on its entire surface, she called to me, and I managed to see it myself for a few seconds. Flying at normal speed disappeared behind the clouds.

Now my wife and I have experienced 3 sightings within 1 month in almost the same place. Sightings similar to the one filmed 12/2-12 at Malling. Around 18-19/1-12 I drive to our house at 7pm and see a large circular light source orange/yellow coming flying towards my direction of travel. I would guess the light source is approx. 100-150 meters above the ground. At first I think it is a plane, but there is no sound and no other light on it. When I first see it, it is approx. 500 meters from our house. I drive to the house and get out of the car to observe it. It is about 150 meters from our house and 100-150 meters above the ground. There is no sound at all and it moves quietly and smoothly in a smooth motion. When it is approx. 50-80 meters past our house, it stands still for a few seconds and then starts to move out over the water, and then it is as if it accelerates violently for approx. 10 seconds it disappears into nothingness and finally disappears completely. The entire observation lasted approx. 2 minutes For this sighting, I was the only one who saw it - the next one was seen by both me and my wife. This took place on the same day as in Malling - namely on 12/2-12 at around 10 p.m. My wife and I are sitting on the sofa watching TV when Janne (my wife) spots a light approx. 50 meters above the ground around the neighbour's house. We rush to the window, and then I spot the same light source that I saw around the 18th-19th. January. A glowing circle/ball in orange/yellow. We only observe it for approx. 8-10 seconds before it disappears. So on Tuesday 14/2-12 my wife observes it again. This happens in the evening around 22.25 when she comes home from a visit to her mother. She sees it again when she comes driving towards our house. Again it is above our neighbor's house hovering from west to east. She rushes in and calls to me, but when we come out together it is gone. I am very interested to hear if anyone else has observed anything similar during this period. The reason I am writing is, among other things, the video on your website and have just read about a person in Hjørrin,g who experienced something similar in January.
3 photos of 2 rows of luminous spots which move individually during the observation period of 6 seconds.

On 28.5.17 at 23.00 I stood out in my parking lot and took a cigarette and smoked. I often keep an eye on the sky in case something mysterious happens. Lucky as I was, I spot two powerful white lights which swing slowly up and down. I keep an eye on them, but soon after, when I had to look down to put out my cigarette, and then look up, they were gone. Since that day, I'm wildly shocked. I haven't seen them since...

I don't know what I just saw, but here is my description. Driving with my son (who sits in the back seat) from Frederikssund towards Ølstykke and just before you can turn left onto Store Rørbækvej/Udlejrevej, I see a flying object approx. above Svestrup, possibly further away. The color of the object is very light/chalky white. I wonder what it is as it moves differently than a flyer. I tell my son, but before he can look at the object, it disappears. It doesn't fly away. One moment it's there and the next it's just gone. On our route further I looked to see if it reappeared, but it didn't.
Saw from my living room window a large glowing orange-red triangle-shaped object moving very quickly and silently across the sky. Never seen anything like it before.

My 16-year-old daughter, who is witness no. 2, had been out looking at satellites. She comes in and tells about what she has seen, and then we go out together and look at the clear night sky. After approx. 10 minutes sweeps 4-5 weak white-orange lights across the sky in a slanted L formation..
An orange object had a long tail behind it. It started by hovering a bit in place, then flew very slowly and rose a little.

In my summer house at the address in Vester Husby, Holstebro, I have set up a game camera. At 06.37.02, on 01.02.2023, it recorded the picture, which I will later send to you via another email. The mysterious thing about the photo is that two cones of light can be seen, which amazes me. It is NOT the moon or other man-made light sources, as my cottage is very secluded. To me, the light cones form an angle of approx. 30 degrees above the ground.

I stand on our stepping stones facing our garden and look up at an almost cloudless evening sky. I first observe a slow moving object flying at a speed of approx. like an aviator. It flies from south to north. At first I think it is a satellite, although it flies significantly slower than satellites normally do. But after 3-5 seconds the object starts to increase in brightness. In approx. 2 seconds, the brightness rises from the brightness of one of the stars drawing the Great Bear to the brightness of Venus in the morning!! I now think I'm seeing a bolide, (powerful shooting star) which I've seen before, but this one is just flying way too slow!?, also it doesn't end up exploding or ending abruptly in a flash of light like bolides often do does, instead the brightness decreases quickly after 1-2 seconds and continues with a weaker brightness than when I spotted it, then it flies on for approx. 5 seconds and disappears. During the entire observation, the object maintains the same speed and speed and extends over approx. 5 degrees in the sky (equivalent to a clenched fist). I have often observed the night sky (amateur astronomer) and am familiar with most natural or human light phenomena, from bolides to twinkling Russian satellites, etc., but I have never experienced anything that behaved like what I saw last night. I am therefore also happy that I found this page on the internet relatively quickly, and I hope that you will be able to give me an answer to my observation.

We also saw the "so-called balloons" at 22-23. 1 came first. We saw it disappear over the roof, and ran to the other end of the apartment, where there is a balcony, and we could follow it again. And out of thin air there were suddenly 3 more that hadn't been there before. They zigzagged across the sky, suddenly turned white-grey and flew on in formation towards Brøndby Strandpark. We hurriedly got dressed and went down to the beach and observed them. They were out on the open sea, flying back and forth and diving into the sea. Every time they came up from the water they lit up completely. White. We got a good recording on the mobile phone of approx. a minute of this and it looks quite outlandish and inexplicable to say the least.

Over Hvalsø west/north west has been observed every evening this week 14 at approx. 21.30, approx. 25 degrees the horizon. A strong light appears, which diminishes over the next approx. 4-5 hours. It may be slowly moving north (we can see it in relation to our flagpole. Sometimes it disappears completely and then returns. It just doesn't look like any light we know.

My wife and I were in Dragør on 8/6. We were sitting in the garden when I happened to look up. I could see two small bright spots snaking around each other. When the sun hit them you could see that they were silver. You could see they were very high up. They flew around each other a few times, then they flew in separate directions.

I was sitting in my apartment on the 1st floor in the living room on our couch talking to my girlfriend and a guest when I suddenly saw something in the sky through the window. A small light in the sky could be seen. I had to squint to be sure of what I saw. At first I thought it was a plane, but it didn't flash the light like it would have done, and it was also now flying too slowly to be a shooting star. The light started out white, but then it turned blue, then turquoise green, then green, then yellow and back to turquoise green. It flew from north to south very quietly, but suddenly it stopped in the middle of the sky. It hung there for about five seconds and then flew at a very high speed to the west until I could no longer see it because of the buildings. It has to be said that it was cloudy that night, so you couldn't see the stars at all.

I had driven my sister to Køge in the evening and on the way home on Ejbyvej between Vemmedrup and Ejby, I see 3 orange lights to my right. Right after that, 4 orange lights come that fly in a rhombus shape and finally there is a single orange light. They fly slower than an airplane and there is no noise. I drive up to Vittenbjergbakken to have a closer look, but already there, the 4 that flew in a rhombus shape have almost "disappeared". It almost seems as if they are spinning, so the light dims and eventually disappears completely. I did, however, film the last bit with my phone, although it is difficult to see anything. My suspicion goes to those Chinese hot air balloons, but not anyway, as they flew very symmetrically.

New Years eve. We sat 5 people on the veranda and smoked a cigarette. Suddenly, one of us notices something that looks like a flare. But it moves in a straight line. One of us suggests it's a satellite. But I have both seen many satellites and shooting stars, and they have all been white. This one glowed orange/red and was bigger and clearer. And since it was cloudy at the same time, one of us ran in for a camera, but it was too late.
Saw out of the living room window a sharp ball that resembled fire or lying. It was bigger than anything I've seen before, it almost fiddled a bit and then disappeared without fading out or anything.

properties.Remarks:
se beretning
Den internationale Rumstation ISS
properties.content: It must be said that the day and time are not exactly precise, as I have no sense of time at Roskilde Festival. But I do know that what I saw is 100% correct. I don't do drugs or smoke weird tobacco that gives me hallucinations, so I was on a high when I saw this UFO sighting. What happens is that I'm sitting talking when I see this round ball in the sky, it's the same color as a star, but much bigger, almost 5 times bigger (visually). When I spot it and sit and look at it, it moves quickly across the sky, all of a sudden it stops, and becomes a triangular shape, after which it becomes more indistinct, and then disappears.

2 orange lights that moved from south to north for approx. 500 meters altitude. Approx. 50 meters apart. Looked like kinetic lights, but moved very fast (about 50 - 100 km/hour). First saw one through the window and thought it was a helicopter so I went outside to look but there was no sound from it. Then the second one. They flew parallel at the same speed.

On my way by car down into Silkeborg town centre, I observed a cluster of very bright objects in a long row - approx. 20-30 points that moved independently of each other. A single one moved in between the others. They moved in an easterly direction. When I was approx. 1 km from the point where I saw them, they had disappeared. Some in the middle were very brightly lit in a yellow color, and those in the sides were faintly lit.

properties.Colors: hvid, med hvidt lys i kanten, og rød!/grøn blinkende lys under bunden
properties.content: I had gone to bed and hear an increasing noise. The noise continues to increase to an unnatural level (comparable to the time I observed a hercules flight exercise). I stand up and look out the window, opening it so I can hear the increasing noise. Shortly after, an object comes flying. Towards me, across my house and on into my forest, where I lose sight of it. It is a large object, not at all comparable to drones and the like. Maybe 10 meters wide, maybe a little less. Below the bottom, red and green lights flashed. It was fairly flat in shape, and completely round, with light around the edge. In the light I could see that the object - or the edge - was rotating rapidly. I couldn't see how it could fly. It was over quickly, but the noise was heard for a long time.

I was working late on an article for the next morning when the lights in the apartment started flickering and there was quite a lot of static electricity in the apartment that could be both felt and smelled. I went to a large skylight and saw that a bright orb of light, berstone colored, yellow probably had passed over the house. The ball of light was for approx. 200 meters high and quite large. It moved south until it was about 1.5 km from the house and became stationary under the cloud cover for a few minutes. After a few minutes it began to move just as quietly in a westerly direction. The static electricity decreased after the ball of light was approx. 500 meters from the property and then slowed down. I am a hobby astronomer and quite well informed about cognitive processes. I cannot immediately give an explanation for the phenomenon.

It was Monday 6 - 08 - 2007 at approx. 14.50. It was a warm day with a cloudless sky. I was on my way home from town, had been out shopping. Driving from Holsted town, and just after the roundabout meets a large tractor with wagon. Sees that it is my neighbour's helper in the tractor, and greets as I overtake. Continue approx. 150 meters, and then sees a helicopter in the sky, it flies from west to east. But then I see something slanting below, a little further to the east, and it's moving west, but much slower. At first I think it might be a glider at that speed. I look more while driving the car and can't spot any wings. It is just a (beam) round at the ends and white and completely defined. Then I realize that it must be a UFO. I now have to turn into where I live, so I do, but stay just inside the road and rush out of the car to stand and observe. The helicopter has flown somewhat further east, but it (white bar) is only slowly heading west. At the same time, the neighbor's helper comes driving and wants to go in where I am with the car, and I have to drive away so he can get there. I point up to the sky twice and hope he has also seen the UFO then. I get into the car and hurry to drive home. Approx. 50 meters. Then I run around the garden, all I can. Out into the field, where I can see from west to east, but it was too late, there was no sign of anything in the sky. Then I run over to the neighbor to see if I can find the helper. I found him and asked him if he had seen it. But he had seen nothing. Although I had pointed up to the sky twice. However, he had seen that. It was a shame he hadn't seen it. But I'm glad to have experienced it, and if it hadn't been for the helicopter, I probably wouldn't have seen it either.

Had a wild experience when I drive from Holbæk and out along Roskildevej, which merges with the Holbæk motorway, because just after the merge I spot a phenomenon up in the clear blue sky: Shaped like a pill (the ones here that are cylinder shaped with curved ends) I saw this object hanging in the air for 3-5 seconds, then all of a sudden it was gone! It was completely white—perhaps a little light gray, but had no shadows or other disturbances affecting it so distinctly as I saw it. It was so clearly sharp and breathtaking to look at. It was 5-7mm in size from the distance I saw it. I had no doubt at the moment that this was something very special!

Was standing looking at the sky when I saw 2 red dots very close together coming from north to south. At first I thought it was a plane, very high up (but "it" was missing the flashing light that everyone else has). It flew approx. 3-4 times faster than airplanes normally do. Then I thought: "It must be a satellite", but then it started to turn (to the west) very sharply (and airplanes don't). Then it flew in a slalom in the shape of a capital "S". and disappeared to the west...

I came walking along St.St. Blichersvej close to the junction with Klokkervej. Suddenly, a Flame Yellow "ball" appears from the west. The object maintains a constant speed across the sky to the east. There is absolutely NO sound associated with the object. The light intensity is strongest from the front. There is no economic pattern to be seen. The light intensity is constant, but very similar to a "yellow flame" from a fire. First thought was. A jet plane. BUT it can't fit with the fluxuring light intensity FROM THE FRONT !! There were no "windows" to be seen or anything else that might suggest that it might be a plane. It was cloudy. The "base" probably hangs around 2-400 meters above the clouds. Clearly, the object moved its UNDER the base. Observes the object as it disappears in an easterly direction. Oddly enough, almost the same path that planes will travel from Århus towards Tirstrup Airport, but still not quite. But I want to emphasize that there was absolutely NO sound (jet sound, propeller sound, rumble, hiss or anything else) to notice. Speed on object. Hard to judge, but around 3-400 km/h I would think. The object disappeared as quickly as it had appeared. Like but putting out a fire.

I'm out for a walk with the cat on a leash, it's starry weather. The two dull white lights come flying from the south and stop above me in our driveway. There is no sound, but the lights rotate synchronously above me at a height of 20 m and with approx. 8-10 m between lights. The cat reacts violently to this and wants to go back inside. I go back to the north side of the house and let the cat in, I get the camera and flashlight. When I come out again, the lights are up above the house. I go back to the driveway and the lights follow. After this I go down to the neighboring property by a 200 m long country road. The object is included. Along the way I try to run a bit, but after a short moment the object catches up with me again. After that I go back again and it comes with it. As I continue around the backyard, the object still follows. I go inside to see if it can be seen from inside the house, but it's gone when I get inside. I go out again but it's gone.

I became aware of a light in a field where there should be no light. There are no farms and no machines running. Have noticed the light several evenings. On 17.11 I go closer and the light moves. I had a camera with me and took pictures of the phenomenon. The light flies to me and stays perfectly still above my head before moving just as quietly to the north.

Approx. 12-15 luminous objects in a kind of formation at the same speed high in the sky from north-west to south-east, some distance after 4 objects at the same speed, one of these suddenly accelerated to speed. A projectile came at the same speed and direction in a slightly more easterly course, but it looked a little lower.

Then a luminous "cloud" which circled round and round. Looked like there was a laser beam down towards the ground once in a while. It lasted for over an hour. Suddenly a very bright "star" appeared in the sky. It slowly headed west.

6 to 8 yellowish dots appear above the northern horizon with an interval of about ½ min. Apparently they rose higher and higher until they disappeared in a position of about 90 degrees above the southern horizon. It was NOT a plane, partly because the red and green "wing lights" were missing, partly because they were too high in the air compared to normal planes (we are used to air traffic from Kastrup). And we are 3 people who agreed that this was not about rockets, (since they can NOT reach that high).
I come driving from Strandvejen in Nivå and discover a strange light. It looks like it's a puff of smoke glowing just below the clouds. It moves across the sky and then disappears like smoke.

Standing in the front garden at approx. 22.30, looking west. A white light appears in the sky. Estimates it to be 150-200 m. away, and approx. height corresponding number of m. up in the air. Not thinking about it to begin with. There are 2 of us standing, going outside to smoke, talking together. It lights up a large area, several nearby rooftops are illuminated and "investigated". As more lights/lamps come on, I become aware that it is something unusual. I immediately start filming with my phone. There is no sound on the phenomenon. The lights alternately become weaker and stronger, they form formations, both curved, pointed and straight. There are up to 20 lights at once, at any one time. I do not associate it with planes, helicopters, drones or Chinese lamps. At once all the lights disappear.
